label: Abnormality of body height
definition: Deviation from the norm of height with respect to that which is expected according to age and gender norms.

label: Multicystic kidney dysplasia
definition: Multicystic dysplasia of the kidney is characterized by multiple cysts of varying size in the kidney and the absence of a normal pelvicaliceal system. The condition is associated with ureteral or ureteropelvic atresia, and the affected kidney is nonfunctional.

label: Renal cyst
definition: A fluid filled sac in the kidney.

label: Mode of inheritance
definition: The pattern in which a particular genetic trait or disorder is passed from one generation to the next.

label: Autosomal dominant inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in heterozygotes. In the context of medical genetics, an autosomal dominant disorder is caused when a single copy of the mutant allele is present. Males and females are affected equally, and can both transmit the disorder with a risk of 50% for each child of inheriting the mutant allele.

label: Mendelian inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance of diseases whose pathophysiology can be traced back to deleterious variants in a single gene. The inheritance patterns of these single-gene (monogenic) diseases are often referred to as Mendelian in honor of Gregor Mendel.

label: Autosomal recessive inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on one of the autosomes (i.e., the human chromosomes 1-22) in which a trait manifests in individuals with two pathogenic alleles, either homozygotes (two copies of the same mutant allele) or compound heterozygotes (whereby each copy of a gene has a distinct mutant allele).

label: Abnormal morphology of female internal genitalia
definition: An abnormality of the female internal genitalia.

label: Abnormal internal genitalia
definition: An anomaly of the adnexa, uterus, and vagina (in female) or seminal tract and prostate (in male).

label: Abnormality of the female genitalia
definition: Abnormality of the female genital system.

label: Functional abnormality of the bladder
definition: Dysfunction of the urinary bladder.

label: Abnormality of the bladder
definition: An abnormality of the urinary bladder.

label: Recurrent urinary tract infections
definition: Repeated infections of the urinary tract.

label: Recurrent infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to infections.

label: Abnormality of the urinary system physiology
Neurogenic bladder
definition: A type of bladder dysfunction caused by neurologic damage. Neurogenic bladder can be flaccid or spastic. Common manifestatios of neurogenic bladder are overflow incontinence, frequency, urgency, urge incontinence, and retention.

label: Urinary urgency
definition: Urge incontinence is the strong, sudden need to urinate.

label: Hypoplasia of the uterus
definition: Underdevelopment of the uterus.

label: Aplasia/hypoplasia of the uterus
definition: Absence or developmental hypoplasia of the uterus.

label: Abnormality of the lower urinary tract
definition: An abnormality of the lower urinary tract.

label: Bladder diverticulum
definition: Diverticulum (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urinary bladder.

label: Abnormal bladder morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the bladder.

label: Urinary retention
definition: Inability to completely empty the urinary bladder during the process of urination.

label: Nocturia
definition: Abnormally increased production of urine during the night leading to an unusually frequent need to urinate.

label: Urinary hesitancy
definition: Difficulty in beginning the process of urination.

label: Urinary incontinence
definition: Loss of the ability to control the urinary bladder leading to involuntary urination.

label: Impaired continence
definition: Partial or total incontinence of bowel or bladder.

label: Megacystis
definition: Dilatation of the bladder postnatally.

label: Dilatation of the bladder
definition: The presence of a dilated urinary bladder.

label: Abnormal male internal genitalia morphology
definition: An abnormality of the male internal genitalia.

label: Abnormality of the male genitalia
definition: Abnormality of the male genital system.

label: Inguinal hernia
definition: Protrusion of the contents of the abdominal cavity through the inguinal canal.

label: Hernia of the abdominal wall
definition: The presence of a hernia in the abdominal wall.

label: Prostatitis
definition: The presence of inflammation of the prostate.

label: Abnormal prostate morphology
definition: An abnormality of the prostate.

label: Increased inflammatory response
definition: A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.

label: Functional abnormality of male internal genitalia
Abnormal male reproductive system physiology
definition: An abnormal functionality of the male genital system.

label: Male hypogonadism
definition: Decreased functionality of the male gonad, i.e., of the testis, with reduced spermatogenesis or testosterone synthesis.

label: Hypogonadism
definition: A decreased functionality of the gonad.

label: Azoospermia
definition: Absence of any measurable level of sperm,whereby spermatozoa cannot be observed even after centrifugation of the semen pellet.

label: Abnormal spermatogenesis
definition: Incomplete maturation or aberrant formation of the male gametes.

label: Cryptorchidism
definition: Testis in inguinal canal. That is, absence of one or both testes from the scrotum owing to failure of the testis or testes to descend through the inguinal canal to the scrotum.

label: Abnormal testis morphology
definition: An anomaly of the testicle (the male gonad).

label: Testicular atrophy
definition: Wasting (atrophy) of the testicle (the male gonad) manifested by a decrease in size and potentially by a loss of fertility.

label: Testicular gonadoblastoma
definition: The presence of a gonadoblastoma of the testis.

label: Gonadoblastoma
definition: The presence of a gonadoblastoma, a neoplasm of a gonad that consists of aggregates of germ cells and sex cord elements.

label: Testicular neoplasm
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the testis.

label: Epididymitis
definition: The presence of inflammation of the epididymis.

label: Abnormal epididymis morphology
definition: An abnormality of the epididymis.

label: Abnormal male external genitalia morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of male external genitalia.

label: Abnormal external genitalia morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the external genitalia.

label: Ambiguous genitalia, male
definition: Ambiguous genitalia in an individual with XY genetic gender.

label: Ambiguous genitalia
definition: A genital phenotype that is not clearly assignable to a single gender. Ambiguous genitalia can be evaluated using the Prader scale: Prader 0: Normal female external genitalia. Prader 1: Female external genitalia with clitoromegaly. Prader 2: Clitoromegaly with partial labial fusion forming a funnel-shaped urogenital sinus. Prader 3: Increased phallic enlargement. Complete labioscrotal fusion forming a urogenital sinus with a single opening. Prader 4: Complete scrotal fusion with urogenital opening at the base or on the shaft of the phallus. Prader 5: Normal male external genitalia. The diagnosis of ambiguous genitalia is made for Prader 1-4.

label: Hydrocele testis
definition: Accumulation of clear fluid in the between the layers of membrane (tunica vaginalis) surrounding the testis.

label: Abnormal penis morphology
definition: Abnormality of the male external sex organ.

label: Male pseudohermaphroditism
definition: Hermaphroditism refers to a discrepancy between the morphology of the gonads and that of the external genitalia. In male pseudohermaphroditism, the genotype is male (XY) and the external genitalia are imcompletely virilized, ambiguous, or complete female. If gonads are present, they are testes.

label: Epispadias
definition: Epispadias is a urogenital malformation characterized by the failure of the urethral tube to tubularize on the dorsal aspect. Unlike in hypospadias, where the meatus is on the ventral aspect, children with epispadias have a wide-open urethral plate on the dorsum. It is commonly seen as a component in the spectrum of bladder exstrophy-epispadias-complex. Isolated epispadias constitutes less than 10 percent of the total cases of epispadias.

label: Displacement of the urethral meatus
definition: A displacement of the external urethral orifice from its normal position (in males normally placed at the tip of glans penis, in females normally placed about 2.5 cm behind the glans clitoridis and immediately in front of that of the vagina).

label: Long penis
definition: Penile length more than 2 SD above the mean for age.

label: Chordee
definition: Ventral, lateral, or ventrolateral bowing of the shaft and glans penis of more than 30 degrees.

label: Absent external genitalia
definition: Lack of external genitalia in a male or female individual.

label: Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
definition: Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism is characterized by reduced function of the gonads (testes in males or ovaries in females) and results from the absence of the gonadal stimulating pituitary hormones: follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH).

label: Abnormal scrotum morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the scrotum, i.e., the sac that contains the testes, epididymis, and the lower part of the spermatic cord.

label: Small scrotum
definition: Apparently small scrotum for age.

label: Hypoplastic male external genitalia
definition: Underdevelopment of part or all of the male external reproductive organs (which include the penis, the scrotum and the urethra).

label: Hypospadias
definition: Abnormal position of urethral meatus on the ventral penile shaft (underside) characterized by displacement of the urethral meatus from the tip of the glans penis to the ventral surface of the penis, scrotum, or perineum.

label: Bifid scrotum
definition: Midline indentation or cleft of the scrotum.

label: Shawl scrotum
definition: Superior margin of the scrotum superior to the base of the penis.

label: External genital hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of part or all of the external reproductive organs.

label: Perineal hypospadias
definition: Hypospadias with location of the urethral meatus in the perineal region.

label: Urethral atresia, male
definition: Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra in males.

label: Urethral atresia
definition: Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra.

label: Macroorchidism
definition: The presence of abnormally large testes.

label: Abnormality of the testis size
definition: An anomaly of the size of the testicle (the male gonad).

label: Micropenis
definition: Abnormally small penis. At birth, the normal penis is about 3 cm (stretched length from pubic tubercle to tip of penis) with micropenis less than 2.0-2.5 cm.

label: Abnormal female external genitalia morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the female external genitalia.

label: Abnormal clitoris morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the clitoris.

label: Abnormal labia morphology
definition: An anomaly of the labia, the externally visible portions of the vulva.

label: Hypoplastic labia majora
definition: Undergrowth of the outer labia.

label: Abnormal labia majora morphology
definition: An anomaly of the outer labia.

label: Clitoral hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the clitoris.

label: Hypoplastic female external genitalia
definition: Underdevelopment of part or all of the female external reproductive organs (which include the mons pubis, labia majora, labia minora, Bartholin glands, and clitoris).

label: Ambiguous genitalia, female
definition: Ambiguous genitalia in an individual with XX genetic gender.

label: Fused labia minora
definition: Fusion of the labia minora as a result of labial adhesions resulting in vaginal obstruction.

label: Abnormal labia minora morphology
definition: An anomaly of the labia minora, the folds of skin between the outer labia.

label: Urethral atresia, female
definition: Congenital anomaly characterized by closure or failure to develop an opening in the urethra in females.

label: Abnormality of the urethra
definition: An abnormality of the urethra, i.e., of the tube which connects the urinary bladder to the outside of the body.

label: Abnormality of the ureter
definition: An abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder.

label: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract
definition: An abnormality of the upper urinary tract.

label: Ureterocele
definition: A ureterocele is a congenital saccular dilatation of the distal segment of the ureter.

label: Abnormal ureter morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder.

label: Ureteral stenosis
definition: The presence of a stenotic, i.e., constricted ureter.

label: Ureteral obstruction
definition: Obstruction of the flow of urine through the ureter.

label: Hydroureter
definition: The distention of the ureter with urine.

label: Ureteral duplication
definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by the presence of two, instead of one, ureter connecting a kidney to the bladder.

label: Ureteropelvic junction obstruction
definition: Blockage of urine flow from the renal pelvis to the proximal ureter.

label: Renal duplication
definition: A congenital anomaly of the urinary tract, in which the kidney is duplicated and is drained via two separate renal pelves and ureters.

label: Abdominal organ duplication
definition: A congenital malformation characterized by the development of an additional organ or organ-like structure, i.e., an extra copy of the organ normally located in the abdomen.

label: Abnormal renal morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the kidney.

label: Vesicoureteral reflux
definition: Abnormal (retrograde) movement of urine from the bladder into ureters or kidneys related to inadequacy of the valvular mechanism at the ureterovesicular junction or other causes.

label: Abnormal ureter physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the ureter. The ureter is the duct by which urine passes from the kidney to the bladder.

label: Abnormality of the kidney
definition: An abnormality of the kidney.

label: Abnormality of the genital system
definition: An abnormality of the genital system.

label: Abnormality of the genitourinary system
definition: The presence of any abnormality of the genitourinary system.

label: Abnormality of the urinary system
definition: An abnormality of the urinary system.

label: Abnormality of reproductive system physiology
definition: An abnormal functionality of the genital system.

label: Duplicated collecting system
definition: A duplication of the collecting system of the kidney, defined as a kidney with two (instead of, normally, one) pyelocaliceal systems. The pyelocaliceal system is comprised of the renal pelvis and calices. The duplicated renal collecting system can be associated with a single ureter or with double ureters. In the latter case, the two ureters empty separately into the bladder or fuse to form a single ureteral orifice.

label: Abnormal renal collecting system morphology
definition: An abnormality of the renal collecting system.

label: Renal insufficiency
definition: A reduction in the level of performance of the kidneys in areas of function comprising the concentration of urine, removal of wastes, the maintenance of electrolyte balance, homeostasis of blood pressure, and calcium metabolism.

label: Abnormal renal physiology
definition: An abnormal functionality of the kidney.

label: Horseshoe kidney
definition: A connection of the right and left kidney by an isthmus of functioning renal parenchyma or fibrous tissue that crosses the midline.

label: Abnormal localization of kidney
definition: An abnormal site of the kidney.

label: Ectopic kidney
definition: A developmental defect in which a kidney is located in an abnormal anatomic position.

label: Renal hypoplasia
definition: Hypoplasia of the kidney.

label: Renal hypoplasia/aplasia
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the kidney.

label: Nephronophthisis
definition: Presence of cysts at the corticomedullary junction of the kidney in combination with tubulointerstitial fibrosis.

label: Abnormal renal medulla morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the medulla of the kidney.

label: Abnormal renal tubule morphology
definition: An abnormality of the renal tubules.

label: Abnormal nephron morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the nephron.

label: Renal tubular atrophy
definition: The presence of renal tubules with thick redundant basement membranes, or a reduction of greater than 50% in tubular diameter compared to surrounding non-atrophic tubules.

label: Abnormal renal tubular epithelial morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the renal tubular epithelial cells (RTEC), a layer of cells in the outer layer of the renal tubule. These cells play a role in the absorption of substances such as glucose and amino from the primary urine.

label: Proteinuria
definition: Increased levels of protein in the urine.

label: Abnormal urine protein level
definition: Any deviation of the concentration of one or more proteins in the urine.

label: Abnormal renal glomerulus morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the glomerulus.

label: Abnormal renal corpuscle morphology
definition: Any anomalous structure of the renal corpuscle, which is the initial component of the nephron that filters blood. The renal corpuscle consists of a knot of capillaries (glomerulus) that is surrounded by a double-walled capsule (Bowman capsule) that opens into a renal tubule.

label: Glomerular sclerosis
definition: Accumulation of scar tissue within the glomerulus.

label: Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis
definition: Segmental accumulation of scar tissue in individual (but not all) glomeruli.

label: Tall stature
definition: A height above that which is expected according to age and gender norms.

label: Glomerulonephritis
definition: Inflammation of the renal glomeruli.

label: Nephritis
definition: The presence of inflammation affecting the kidney.

label: Nephrotic syndrome
definition: Nephrotic syndrome is a collection of findings resulting from glomerular dysfunction with an increase in glomerular capillary wall permeability associated with pronounced proteinuria. Nephrotic syndrome refers to the constellation of clinical findings that result from severe renal loss of protein, with Proteinuria and hypoalbuminemia, edema, and hyperlipidemia.

label: Polyuria
definition: An increased rate of urine production.

label: Abnormal urine output
definition: An abnormal amount of urine production.

label: Renal agenesis
definition: Agenesis, that is, failure of the kidney to develop during embryogenesis and development.

label: Enlarged kidney
definition: An abnormal increase in the size of the kidney.

label: Renal corticomedullary cysts
definition: The presence of multiple cysts at the border between the renal cortex and medulla.

label: Abnormal renal cortex morphology
definition: An abnormality of the cortex of the kidney.

label: Renal dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the kidney.

label: Renal juxtaglomerular cell hypertrophy/hyperplasia
definition: Increased number and size of the juxtaglomerular cells.

label: Nephropathy
definition: A nonspecific term referring to disease or damage of the kidneys.

label: Polycystic kidney dysplasia
definition: The presence of multiple cysts in both kidneys.

label: Proximal tubulopathy
definition: Dysfunction of the proximal tubule, which is the portion of the duct system of the nephron of the kidney which leads from Bowman's capsule to the loop of Henle.

label: Renal tubular dysfunction
definition: Abnormal function of the renal tubule. The basic functional unit of the kidney, the nephron, consists of a renal corpuscle attached to a renal tubule, with roughly 0.8 to 1.5 nephrons per adult kidney. The functions of the renal tubule include reabsorption of water, electrolytes, glucose, and amino acids and secretion of substances such as uric acid.

label: Renal phosphate wasting
definition: High urine phosphate in the presence of hypophosphatemia.

label: Abnormal urine phosphate concentration
definition: An abnormal phosphate concentration in the urine.

label: Phenotypic abnormality
definition: A phenotypic abnormality.

label: Nephrocalcinosis
definition: Nephrocalcinosis is the deposition of calcium salts in renal parenchyma.

label: Unilateral renal agenesis
definition: A unilateral form of agenesis of the kidney.

label: Pelvic kidney
definition: A developmental defect in which a kidney is located in an abnormal anatomic position within the pelvis.

label: Hydronephrosis
definition: Severe distention of the kidney with dilation of the renal pelvis and calices.

label: Dilatation of the renal pelvis
definition: The presence of dilatation of the renal pelvis.

label: Renal salt wasting
definition: A high concentration of one or more electrolytes in the urine in the presence of low serum concentrations of the electrolyte(s).

label: Abnormal urinary electrolyte concentration
definition: An abnormality in the concentration of electrolytes in the urine.

label: Renal potassium wasting
definition: High urine potassium in the presence of hypokalemia.

label: Abnormal urine potassium concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine.

label: Abnormality of the uterus
definition: An abnormality of the uterus.

label: Uterine leiomyoma
definition: The presence of a leiomyoma of the uterus.

label: Uterine neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the uterus.

label: Menorrhagia
definition: Prolonged and excessive menses at regular intervals in excess of 80 mL or lasting longer than 7 days.

label: Abnormality of the menstrual cycle
definition: An abnormality of the ovulation cycle.

label: Abnormal bleeding
definition: An abnormal susceptibility to bleeding, often referred to as a bleeding diathesis. A bleeding diathesis may be related to vascular, platelet and coagulation defects.

label: Gonadal dysgenesis
definition: Gonadal dysgenesis is the name given to any of a multitude of conditions that can cause impaired development of the gonads, i.e., the testes or ovaries, or to the related phenotypic features. The term is to be avoided if possible for new annotations, and more specific terms should be chosen.

label: Female hypogonadism
definition: Decreased functionality of the female gonads, i.e., of the ovary.

label: Abnormal ovarian physiology
definition: Any anomaly of ovarian function.

label: Bifid uterus
definition: The presence of a bifid uterus.

label: Abnormal uterus morphology
definition: Any anomaly of the structure of the uterus

label: Abnormality of the ovary
definition: An abnormality of the ovary.

label: Ovarian cyst
definition: The presence of one or more cysts of the ovary.

label: Uterine prolapse
definition: The presence of prolapse of the uterus.

label: Amenorrhea
definition: Absence of menses for an interval of time equivalent to a total of more than (or equal to) 3 previous cycles or 6 months.

label: Abnormal vagina morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the vagina.

label: Rectovaginal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula between the vagina and the rectum.

label: Vaginal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula of the vagina.

label: Rectal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula affecting the rectum.

label: Septate vagina
definition: The presence of a vaginal septum, thereby creating a vaginal duplication. The septum is longitudinal in the majority of cases.

label: Vaginal atresia
definition: Congenital occlusion of the vagina or adhesion of the walls of the vagina causing occlusion.

label: Genital tract atresia
definition: Congenital occlusion of a tube in the genital tract.

label: Ovarian gonadoblastoma
definition: The presence of a gonadoblastoma of the ovary.

label: Ovarian neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ovary.

label: Aplasia of the uterus
definition: A congenital defect characterized by absence of the uterus. Aplasia refers to the failure of an organ to develop during embryonic growth and development due to the absence of primordial tissue.

label: Abnormality of head or neck
definition: An abnormality of head and neck.

label: Abnormality of the mouth
definition: An abnormality of the mouth.

label: Abnormality of the face
definition: An abnormality of the face.

label: Wide mouth
definition: Distance between the oral commissures more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased width of the oral aperture (subjective).

label: Oral ulcer
definition: Erosion of the mucous mebrane of the mouth with local excavation of the surface, resulting from the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue.

label: Erosion of oral mucosa
definition: Loss of the superficial layer of the oral mucosa usually resulting in a shallow or crusted lesion.

label: Abnormality of the tongue
definition: Any abnormality of the tongue.

label: Macroglossia
definition: Increased length and width of the tongue.

label: Skeletal muscle hypertrophy
definition: Abnormal increase in muscle size and mass not due to training.

label: Abnormal tongue morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the tongue.

label: Abnormal lip morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lip.

label: Abnormal oral cavity morphology
definition: Abnormality of the oral cavity, i.e., the opening or hollow part of the mouth.

label: Narrow mouth
definition: Distance between the commissures of the mouth more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the oral aperture (subjective).

label: Median cleft upper lip
definition: A type of cleft lip presenting as a midline (median) gap in the upper lip.

label: Cleft upper lip
definition: A gap or groove in the upper lip. This is a congenital defect resulting from nonfusion of tissues of the lip during embryonal development.

label: Glossoptosis
definition: Posterior displacement of the tongue into the pharynx, i.e., a tongue that is mislocalised posteriorly.

label: Abnormal oral morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the mouth, which is also known as the oral cavity.

label: Abnormality of the dentition
definition: Any abnormality of the teeth.

label: Severe periodontitis
definition: A severe form of periodontitis.

label: Periodontitis
definition: Inflammation of the periodontium.

label: Abnormality of the gingiva
definition: Any abnormality of the gingiva (also known as gums).

label: Abnormal oral mucosa morphology
definition: Abnormality of the oral mucosa.

label: Gingival fibromatosis
definition: The presence of fibrosis of the gingiva.

label: Fibroma
definition: Benign tumors that are composed of fibrous or connective tissue. They can grow in all organs, arising from mesenchyme tissue. The term fibroblastic" or "fibromatous" is used to describe tumors of the fibrous connective tissue. When the term fibroma is used without modifier
column6: with the term fibrosarcoma reserved for malignant tumors."

label: Microglossia
definition: Decreased length and width of the tongue.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tongue
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the tongue.

label: Abnormal uvula morphology
definition: Abnormality of the uvula, the conic projection from the posterior edge of the middle of the soft palate.

label: Abnormal soft palate morphology
definition: An abnormality of the soft palate.

label: Abnormal palate morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the palate, i.e., of roof of the mouth.

label: Cleft palate
definition: Cleft palate is a developmental defect of the palate resulting from a failure of fusion of the palatine processes and manifesting as a separation of the roof of the mouth (soft and hard palate).

label: Orofacial cleft
definition: The presence of a cleft (gap, opening, or groove) in the oral cavity, including cleft of the upper lip and/or cleft of the palate. Cleft of the upper lip is visible as a groove or fissure in the lip, most frequently due to a congenital failure of the maxillary and median nasal processes to fuse. Cleft palate is characterized by a grooved depression or fissure in the roof of the mouth, most often resulting from a congenital failure of the palate to fuse properly. Clefts of the lip and palate can occur individually or together. It is preferable to code each defect separately.

label: Submucous cleft hard palate
definition: Hard-palate submucous clefts are characterized by bony defects in the midline of the bony palate that are covered by the mucous membrane of the roof of the mouth. It may be possible to detect a submucous cleft hard palate upon palpation as a notch in the bony palate.

label: Submucous cleft palate
definition: A cleft of the muscular portion of the palate that is covered by mucous membrane.

label: Abnormal upper lip morphology
definition: An abnormality of the upper lip.

label: Abnormal lower lip morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lower lip.

label: Thick lower lip vermilion
definition: Increased thickness of the lower lip, leading to a prominent appearance of the lower lip. The height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the midline is more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the frontal view (subjective).

label: Thick vermilion border
definition: Increased width of the skin of vermilion border region of upper lip.

label: Lobulated tongue
definition: Multiple indentations and/or elevations on the edge and/or surface of the tongue producing an irregular surface contour.

label: Abnormal tongue physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the tongue.

label: Tongue muscle weakness
definition: Reduced strength of the tongue musculature, resulting in difficulties moving the tongue and possible accompanied by dysarthria or dysphagia.

label: Cleft soft palate
definition: Cleft of the soft palate (also known as the velum, or muscular palate) as a result of a developmental defect occurring between the 7th and 12th week of pregnancy. Cleft soft palate can cause functional abnormalities of the Eustachian tube with resulting middle ear anomalies and hearing difficulties, as well as speech problems associated with hypernasal speech due to velopharyngeal insufficiency.

label: Abnormal alveolar ridge morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the alveolar ridges (on the upper or lower jaws). The alveolar ridges contain the sockets (alveoli) of the teeth.

label: Short upper lip
definition: Decreased width of the upper lip.

label: Narrow palate
definition: Width of the palate more than 2 SD below the mean (objective) or apparently decreased palatal width (subjective).

label: Abnormal oral frenulum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lingual frenulum, that is of the small fold of mucous membrane that attaches the tongue to the floor of the mouth, or the presence of accessory frenula in the oral cavity.

label: Accessory oral frenulum
definition: Extra fold of tissue extending from the alveolar ridge to the inner surface of the upper or lower lip.

label: Bifid uvula
definition: Uvula separated into two parts most easily seen at the tip.

label: Open mouth
definition: A facial appearance characterized by a permanently or nearly permanently opened mouth.

label: Abnormality of mouth shape
definition: An abnormality of the outline, configuration, or contour of the mouth.

label: Lower lip pit
definition: Depression located on the vermilion of the lower lip, usually paramedian.

label: Paramedian lip pit
definition: Depression located paramedially on the vermilion of a lip.

label: Abnormal parotid gland morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the parotid glands, which are the salivary glands that are located in the subcutaneous tissues of the face overlying the mandibular ramus and anterior and inferior to the external ear.

label: Abnormal salivary gland morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the salivary glands, the exocrine glands that produce saliva.

label: Short lingual frenulum
definition: The presence of an abnormally short lingual frenulum.

label: Pierre-Robin sequence
definition: Pierre Robin malformation is a sequence of developmental malformations characterized by micrognathia (mandibular hypoplasia), glossoptosis and cleft palate.

label: Craniofacial cleft
definition: Congenital abnormality with cleft (gap or opening) in the craniofacial bones. Craniofacial cleft includes facial cleft, orofacial clef, and cleft of the jaw.

label: Cleft lip
definition: A gap in the lip or lips.

label: Pursed lips
definition: An abnormality of the appearance of the face caused by constant contraction of the lips leading to a puckered or pursed appearance.

label: Glossitis
definition: Inflammation of the tongue.

label: Triangular mouth
definition: The presence of a triangular form of the mouth.

label: Trismus
definition: Limitation in the ability to open the mouth.

label: Abnormal mandible morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the mandible, the bone of the lower jaw.

label: Gingival overgrowth
definition: Hyperplasia of the gingiva (that is, a thickening of the soft tissue overlying the alveolar ridge. The degree of thickening ranges from involvement of the interdental papillae alone to gingival overgrowth covering the entire tooth crown.

label: Lip telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the lips.

label: Oral cavity telangiectasia
definition: Presence of telangiectases in the oral cavity.

label: Thick upper lip vermilion
definition: Height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the midline more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the frontal view (subjective).

label: Abnormality of upper lip vermillion
definition: An abnormality of the vermilion border, the sharp demarcation between the lip (red colored) and the adjacent normal skin.

label: Xerostomia
definition: Dryness of the mouth due to salivary gland dysfunction.

label: High palate
definition: Height of the palate more than 2 SD above the mean (objective) or palatal height at the level of the first permanent molar more than twice the height of the teeth (subjective).

label: Thin upper lip vermilion
definition: Height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the midline more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the upper lip in the frontal view (subjective).

label: Thin vermilion border
definition: Height of the vermilion of the medial part of the lip more than 2 SD below the mean, or apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the lip in the frontal view. The vermilion is the red part of the lips (and confusingly, the vermilion itself is also often referred to as being equivalent the lips).

label: Velopharyngeal insufficiency
definition: Inability of velopharyngeal sphincter to sufficiently separate the nasal cavity from the oral cavity during speech.

label: Furrowed tongue
definition: Accentuation of the grooves on the dorsal surface of the tongue.

label: Gingival hyperkeratosis
definition: Hyperkeratosis of the gingiva.

label: Hyperkeratosis
definition: Hyperkeratosis is thickening of the epidermis involving the outer layer of the skin, the stratum corneum, which is composed of large, polyhedral, plate-like envelopes filled with keratin which are the dead cells that have migrated up from the stratum granulosum.

label: Abnormal nervous system physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the nervous system.

label: Hypogeusia
definition: A decreased ability to perceive flavor.

label: Gingival bleeding
definition: Hemorrhage affecting the gingiva.

label: Tongue telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the tongue.

label: Mucosal telangiectasiae
definition: Telangiectasia of the mucosa, the mucous membranes which are involved in absorption and secretion that line cavities that are exposed to the external environment and internal organs.

label: Gingivitis
definition: Inflammation of the gingiva.

label: Everted lower lip vermilion
definition: An abnormal configuration of the lower lip such that it is turned outward i.e., everted, with the Inner aspect of the lower lip vermilion (normally opposing the teeth) being visible in a frontal view.

label: Eclabion
definition: A turning outward of the lip or lips, that is, eversion of the lips.

label: Abnormality of the head
definition: An abnormality of the head.

label: Abnormal cranial suture/fontanelle morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the fontanelles (the regions covered by a thick membrane that normally ossify in the first two years of life) or the cranial sutures (the fibrous joints in which the articulating bones or cartilages of the skull are connected by sutural ligaments).

label: Abnormal skull morphology
definition: An abnormality of the skull, the bony framework of the head which is comprised of the neurocranium (with eight cranial bones) and the viscerocranium (facial skeleton) that comprises fourteen facial bones with the mandible as its largest bone.

label: Abnormal anterior fontanelle morphology
definition: An abnormality of the anterior fontanelle, i.e., the cranial fontanelle that is located at the intersection of the coronal and sagittal sutures.

label: Abnormal fontanelle morphology
definition: An abnormality of the fontanelle.

label: Small anterior fontanelle
definition: Abnormally decreased size of the anterior fontanelle with respect to age-dependent norms.

label: Hydrocephalus
definition: Hydrocephalus is an active distension of the ventricular system of the brain resulting from inadequate passage of CSF from its point of production within the cerebral ventricles to its point of absorption into the systemic circulation.

label: Abnormal cerebral ventricle morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the cerebral ventricles.

label: Abnormal cerebrospinal fluid morphology
definition: An abnormality of the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Large fontanelles
definition: In newborns, the two frontal bones, two parietal bones, and one occipital bone are joined by fibrous sutures, which form a small posterior fontanelle, and a larger, diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle. These regions allow for the skull to pass the birth canal and for later growth. The fontanelles gradually ossify, whereby the posterior fontanelle usually closes by eight weeks and the anterior fontanelle by the 9th to 16th month of age. Large fontanelles are diagnosed if the fontanelles are larger than age-dependent norms.

label: Abnormality of skull size
definition: Any abnormality of the size of the skull.

label: Parietal bossing
definition: Parietal bossing is a marked prominence in the parietal region.

label: Abnormal parietal bone morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the parietal bone of the skull.

label: Trigonocephaly
definition: Wedge-shaped, or triangular head, with the apex of the triangle at the midline of the forehead and the base of the triangle at the occiput.

label: Abnormal calvaria morphology
definition: Abnormality of the morphology (structure) of the calvaria (skullcap), that is, of that part of the skull that is made up of the superior portions of the frontal bone, occipital bone, and parietal bones and covers the cranial cavity that contains the brain.

label: Brachyturricephaly
definition: Abnormal vertical height of the skull and a shortening of its anterior-posterior length, frequently combined with malformations of the occipital region.

label: Brachycephaly
definition: An abnormality of skull shape characterized by a decreased anterior-posterior diameter. That is, a cephalic index greater than 81%. Alternatively, an apparently shortened anteroposterior dimension (length) of the head compared to width.

label: Turricephaly
definition: Tall head relative to width and length.

label: Abnormal paranasal sinus morphology
definition: Abnormality of the paranasal (cranial) sinuses, which are air-filled spaces that are located within the bones of the skull and face and communicate with the nasal cavity. They comprise the maxillary sinuses, the frontal sinuses, the ethmoid sinuses, and the sphenoid sinuses.

label: Abnormality of the upper respiratory tract
definition: An abnormality of the upper respiratory tract.

label: Abnormal facial skeleton morphology
definition: An abnormality of one or more of the set of bones that make up the facial skeleton.

label: Sinusitis
definition: Inflammation of the paranasal sinuses owing to a viral, bacterial, or fungal infection, allergy, or an autoimmune reaction.

label: Dense calvaria
definition: An abnormal increase of density of the bones making up the calvaria.

label: Increased skull ossification
definition: An increase in the magnitude or amount of ossification of the skull.

label: Microcephaly
definition: Head circumference below 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender.

label: Decreased head circumference
definition: An abnormally reduced head circumference in a growing child. Head circumference is measured with a nonelastic tape and comprises the distance from above the eyebrows and ears and around the back of the head. The measured HC is then plotted on an appropriate growth chart. Microcephaly is defined as a head circumference (HC) that is great than two standard deviations below the mean of age- and gender-matched population based samples. Severe microcephaly is defined with an HC that is three standard deviations below the mean.

label: Progressive microcephaly
definition: Progressive microcephaly is diagnosed when the head circumference falls progressively behind age- and gender-dependent norms.

label: Secondary microcephaly
definition: Head circumference which falls below 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender because of insufficient head growth after birth.

label: Acute sinusitis
definition: An acute form of sinusitis.

label: Macrocephaly
definition: Occipitofrontal (head) circumference greater than 97th centile compared to appropriate, age matched, sex-matched normal standards. Alternatively, a apparently increased size of the cranium.

label: Increased head circumference
definition: An abnormally increased head circumference in a growing child. Head circumference is measured with a nonelastic tape and comprises the distance from above the eyebrows and ears and around the back of the head. The measured HC is then plotted on an appropriate growth chart.

label: Wide anterior fontanel
definition: Enlargement of the anterior fontanelle with respect to age-dependent norms.

label: Oxycephaly
definition: Oxycephaly (from Greek oxus, sharp, and kephalos, head) refers to a conical or pointed shape of the skull.

label: Abnormal mastoid morphology
definition: An abnormality of the mastoid process, which is the conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone.

label: Cranial asymmetry
definition: Asymmetry of the bones of the skull.

label: Dolichocephaly
definition: An abnormality of skull shape characterized by a increased anterior-posterior diameter, i.e., an increased antero-posterior dimension of the skull. Cephalic index less than 76%. Alternatively, an apparently increased antero-posterior length of the head compared to width. Often due to premature closure of the sagittal suture.

label: Prominent occiput
definition: Increased convexity of the occiput (posterior part of the skull).

label: Abnormal shape of the occiput
definition: An abnormal shape of occiput.

label: Delayed cranial suture closure
definition: Infants normally have two fontanels at birth, the diamond-shaped anterior fontanelle at the junction of the coronal and sagittal sutures, and the posterior fontanelle at the intersection of the occipital and parietal bones. The posterior fontanelle usually closes by the 8th week of life, and the anterior fontanel closes by the 18th month of life on average. This term applies if there is delay of closure of the fontanelles beyond the normal age.

label: Abnormality of cranial sutures
definition: Any anomaly of a cranial suture, that is one of the six membrane-covered openings in the incompletely ossified skull of the fetus or newborn infant.

label: Malar flattening
definition: Underdevelopment of the malar prominence of the jugal bone (zygomatic bone in mammals), appreciated in profile, frontal view, and/or by palpation.

label: Abnormal zygomatic bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the zygomatic bone.

label: Disturbance of facial expression
definition: An abnormality of the gestures or movements executed with the facial muscles with which emotions such as fear, joy, sadness, surprise, and disgust can be expressed.

label: Small face
definition: A face that is short and narrow.

label: Abnormal facial shape
definition: An abnormal morphology (form) of the face or its components.

label: Narrow face
definition: Bizygomatic (upper face) and bigonial (lower face) width are both more than 2 standard deviations below the mean (objective); or, an apparent reduction in the width of the upper and lower face (subjective).

label: Long face
definition: Facial height (length) is more than 2 standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, an apparent increase in the height (length) of the face (subjective).

label: Abnormal jaw morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the jaw, the bony structure of the mouth that consists of the mandible and the maxilla.

label: Retrognathia
definition: An abnormality in which the mandible is mislocalised posteriorly.

label: Coarse facial features
definition: Absence of fine and sharp appearance of brows, nose, lips, mouth, and chin, usually because of rounded and heavy features or thickened skin with or without thickening of subcutaneous and bony tissues.

label: Edema
definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body.

label: Broad face
definition: Bizygomatic (upper face) and bigonial (lower face) width greater than 2 standard deviations above the mean (objective); or an apparent increase in the width of the face (subjective).

label: Epicanthus
definition: A fold of skin starting above the medial aspect of the upper eyelid and arching downward to cover, pass in front of and lateral to the medial canthus.

label: Abnormal eyelid morphology
definition: An abnormality of the eyelids.

label: Increased facial adipose tissue
definition: An increased amount of subcutaneous fat tissue in the face.

label: Abnormality of the philtrum
definition: An abnormality of the philtrum.

label: Broad philtrum
definition: Distance between the philtral ridges, measured just above the vermilion border, more than 2 standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased distance between the ridges of the philtrum.

label: Abnormal forehead morphology
definition: An anomaly of the forehead.

label: Abnormal adipose tissue morphology
definition: An abnormality of adipose tissue, which is loose connective tissue composed of adipocytes.

label: Loss of facial adipose tissue
definition: Loss of normal subcutaneous fat tissue in the face.

label: Adipose tissue loss
definition: A loss of adipose tissue.

label: Full cheeks
definition: Increased prominence or roundness of soft tissues between zygomata and mandible.

label: Abnormal cheek morphology
definition: An abnormality of the cheek- one of two bilateral soft tissue facial structures in the region of the face inferior to the eyes and between the nose and the ear. Buccal" means relating to the cheek. The cheek is part of the midface"

label: Low anterior hairline
definition: Distance between the hairline (trichion) and the glabella (the most prominent point on the frontal bone above the root of the nose), in the midline, more than two SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the hairline and the glabella.

label: Abnormality of the frontal hairline
definition: An anomaly in the placement or shape of the hairline (trichion) on the forehead, that is, the border between skin on the forehead that has head hair and that does not.

label: Doll-like facies
definition: A characteristic facial appearance with a round facial form, full cheeks, a short nose, and a relatively small chin.

label: Facial hypotonia
definition: Reduced muscle tone of a muscle that is innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Abnormality of facial musculature
definition: An anomaly of a muscle that is innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Hypotonia
definition: Hypotonia is an abnormally low muscle tone (the amount of tension or resistance to movement in a muscle). Even when relaxed, muscles have a continuous and passive partial contraction which provides some resistance to passive stretching. Hypotonia thus manifests as diminished resistance to passive stretching. Hypotonia is not the same as muscle weakness, although the two conditions can co-exist.

label: Mask-like facies
definition: A lack of facial expression often with staring eyes and a slightly open mouth.

label: Decreased facial expression
definition: A reduced degree of voluntary and involuntary facial movements involved in responded to others or expressing emotions.

label: Oval face
definition: A face with a rounded and slightly elongated outline.

label: Abnormal skeletal muscle morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

label: Mandibular prognathia
definition: Abnormal prominence of the chin related to increased length of the mandible.

label: Abnormality of the chin
definition: An abnormality of the chin, i.e., of the inferior portion of the face lying inferior to the lower lip and including the central prominence of the lower jaw.

label: Pointed chin
definition: A marked tapering of the lower face to the chin.

label: Microretrognathia
definition: A form of developmental hypoplasia of the mandible in which the mandible is mislocalised posteriorly.

label: Micrognathia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the mandible.

label: Abnormal midface morphology
definition: An anomaly of the midface, which is a region and not an anatomical term. It extends, superiorly, from the inferior orbital margin to, inferiorly, the level of nasal base. It is formed by the maxilla (upper jaw) and zygoma and cheeks and malar region. Traditionally, the nose and premaxilla are not included in the midface.

label: Round face
definition: The facial appearance is more circular than usual as viewed from the front.

label: Hypertelorism
definition: Interpupillary distance more than 2 SD above the mean (alternatively, the appearance of an increased interpupillary distance or widely spaced eyes).

label: Abnormality of globe location
definition: An abnormality in the placement of the ocular globe (eyeball).

label: Facial myokymia
definition: Facial myokymia is a fine fibrillary activity of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Myokymia
definition: Myokymia consists of involuntary, fine, continuous, undulating contractions that spread across the affected striated muscle.

label: Smooth philtrum
definition: Flat skin surface, with no ridge formation in the central region of the upper lip between the nasal base and upper vermilion border.

label: Square face
definition: Facial contours, as viewed from the front, show a broad upper face/cranium and lower face/mandible, creating a square appearance.

label: Short philtrum
definition: Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border.

label: Facial asymmetry
definition: An abnormal difference between the left and right sides of the face.

label: Triangular face
definition: Facial contour, as viewed from the front, triangular in shape, with breadth at the temples and tapering to a narrow chin.

label: Abnormal maxilla morphology
definition: An abnormality of the Maxilla (upper jaw bone).

label: Hypoplasia of the maxilla
definition: Abnormally small dimension of the Maxilla. Usually creating a malocclusion or malalignment between the upper and lower teeth or resulting in a deficient amount of projection of the base of the nose and lower midface region.

label: Facial hemangioma
definition: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, occurring in the face.

label: Hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma is a benign tumor characterized by blood-filled spaces lined by benign endothelial cells. A hemangioma characterized by large endothelial spaces (caverns) is called a cavernous hemangioma (in contrast to a hemangioma with small endothelial spaces, which is called capillary hemangioma).

label: Short chin
definition: Decreased vertical distance from the vermilion border of the lower lip to the inferior-most point of the chin.

label: Prominent supraorbital ridges
definition: Greater than average forward and/or lateral protrusion of the supraorbital portion of the frontal bones.

label: Abnormality of the supraorbital ridges
definition: An anomaly of the supraorbital portion of the frontal bones.

label: Broad forehead
definition: Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently increased distance between the two sides of the forehead.

label: Hypomimic face
definition: A reduced degree of motion of the muscles beneath the skin of the face, often associated with reduced facial crease formation.

label: Pugilistic facies
definition: Coarse facial features reminiscent of those of a boxer.

label: Sloping forehead
definition: Inclination of the anterior surface of the forehead from the vertical more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or apparently excessive posterior sloping of the forehead in a lateral view.

label: Narrow forehead
definition: Width of the forehead or distance between the frontotemporales is more than two standard deviations below the mean (objective); or apparently narrow intertemporal region (subjective).

label: Long philtrum
definition: Distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border more than 2 SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between nasal base and midline upper lip vermilion border.

label: Whistling appearance
definition: An abnormality of facial morphology characterized by a small mouth opening and constant contraction of the lips as if the patient were whistling.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the mandible
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the mandible.

label: High forehead
definition: An abnormally increased height of the forehead.

label: Widow's peak
definition: Frontal hairline with bilateral arcs to a low point in the midline of the forehead.

label: High anterior hairline
definition: Distance between the hairline (trichion) and the glabella (the most prominent point on the frontal bone above the root of the nose), in the midline, more than two SD above the mean. Alternatively, an apparently increased distance between the hairline and the glabella.

label: Small forehead
definition: The presence of a forehead that is abnormally small.

label: Abnormality of the outer ear
definition: An abnormality of the external ear.

label: Abnormal ear morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the ear.

label: Abnormal location of ears
definition: Abnormal location of the ear.

label: Abnormal pinna morphology
definition: An abnormality of the pinna, which is also referred to as the auricle or external ear.

label: Posteriorly rotated ears
definition: A type of abnormal location of the ears in which the position of the ears is characterized by posterior rotation (the superior part of the ears is rotated towards the back of the head, and the inferior part of the ears towards the front).

label: Abnormality of the inner ear
definition: An abnormality of the inner ear.

label: Tinnitus
definition: Tinnitus is an auditory perception that can be described as the experience of sound, in the ear or in the head, in the absence of external acoustic stimulation.

label: Hearing abnormality
definition: An abnormality of the sensory perception of sound.

label: Otosclerosis
definition: In otosclerosis, a callus of bone accumulates on the stapes creating a partial fixation. This limits the movement of the stapes bone, which results in hearing loss.

label: Abnormal stapes morphology
definition: An abnormality of the stapes, a stirrup-shaped ossicle in the middle ear.

label: Abnormal earlobe morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lobule of pinna.

label: Abnormal ear physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the ear.

label: Hearing impairment
definition: A decreased magnitude of the sensory perception of sound.

label: Abnormality of the nose
definition: An abnormality of the nose.

label: Low-set ears
definition: Upper insertion of the ear to the scalp below an imaginary horizontal line drawn between the inner canthi of the eye and extending posteriorly to the ear.

label: Abnormality of the middle ear
definition: An abnormality of the middle ear.

label: Acute otitis media
definition: Acute otitis media is a short and generally painful infection of the middle ear.

label: Otitis media
definition: Inflammation or infection of the middle ear.

label: Abnormal auditory canal morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the external acoustic tube (also known as the auditory canal).

label: Abnormal cochlea morphology
definition: An abnormality of the cochlea.

label: Abnormal inner ear morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the internal part of the ear.

label: Incomplete partition of the cochlea type II
definition: With incomplete partition II, the cochlea consists of 1.5 turns; the apical and middle cochlea turns are undifferentiated and form a cystic apex. The vestibule is normal while the vestibular aqueduct is always enlarged. Developmental arrest occurs at the seventh week of gestation.

label: Incomplete partition of the cochlea
definition: Incomplete formation of the cochlear partition. The scala vestibuli and scala tympani separated by the cochlear partition, except in the apical turn where the two scalae are in continuity via the helicotrema.

label: Cupped ear
definition: Laterally protruding ear that lacks antihelical folding (including absence of inferior and superior crura).

label: Stapes ankylosis
definition: Stapes ankylosis refers to congenital or acquired fixation of the stapes (the stirrup-shaped small bone or ossicle in the middle ear), which is associated with conductive hearing resulting from impairment of the sound-conduction mechanism (the external auditory canal, tympanic membrane, and/or middle-ear ossicles).

label: Preauricular skin tag
definition: A rudimentary tag of skin often containing ear tissue including a core of cartilage and located just anterior to the auricle (outer part of the ear).

label: Skin tags
definition: Cutaneous skin tags also known as acrochorda or fibroepithelial polyps are small benign tumors that may either form secondarily over time primarily in areas where the skin forms creases, such as the neck, armpit or groin or may also be present at birth, in which case they usually occur in the periauricular region.

label: Small earlobe
definition: Reduced volume of the earlobe.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the earlobes
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the ear lobes.

label: Absent earlobe
definition: Absence of fleshy non-cartilaginous tissue inferior to the tragus and incisura.

label: Abnormal middle ear morphology
definition: An abnormality of the morphology or structure of the middle ear.

label: Chronic otitis media
definition: Chronic otitis media refers to fluid, swelling, or infection of the middle ear that does not heal and may cause permanent damage to the ear.

label: Thickened helices
definition: Increased thickness of the helix of the ear.

label: Abnormal helix morphology
definition: An abnormality of the helix. The helix is the outer rim of the ear that extends from the insertion of the ear on the scalp (root) to the termination of the cartilage at the earlobe.

label: Lop ear
definition: Anterior and inferior folding of the upper portion of the ear that obliterates triangular fossa and scapha.

label: Prominent antihelix
definition: The presence of an abnormally prominent antihelix.

label: Abnormal antihelix morphology
definition: An abnormality of the antihelix.

label: Overfolded helix
definition: A condition in which the helix is folded over to a greater degree than normal. That is, excessive curling of the helix edge, whereby the free edge is parallel to the plane of the ear.

label: Abnormally folded helix
definition: Any structural anomaly of the border of the helix, which usually forms a rolled rim but is highly variable in shape.

label: Prelingual sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A form of sensorineural deafness with either congenital onset or infantile onset, i.e., before the acquisition of speech.

label: Childhood onset sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: Sensorineural hearing impairment with childhood onset.

label: Macrotia
definition: Median longitudinal ear length greater than two standard deviations above the mean and median ear width greater than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, apparent increase in length and width of the pinna (subjective).

label: Stenosis of the external auditory canal
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the external auditory canal.

label: Recurrent otitis media
definition: Increased susceptibility to otitis media, as manifested by recurrent episodes of otitis media.

label: Conductive hearing impairment
definition: An abnormality of vibrational conductance of sound to the inner ear leading to impairment of sensory perception of sound.

label: Functional abnormality of the middle ear
definition: An abnormality of the function of the middle ear.

label: Sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A type of hearing impairment in one or both ears related to an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve.

label: Functional abnormality of the inner ear
definition: An abnormality of the function of the inner ear.

label: Progressive sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A progressive form of sensorineural hearing impairment.

label: Progressive hearing impairment
definition: A progressive form of hearing impairment.

label: Mixed hearing impairment
definition: A type of hearing loss resulting from a combination of conductive hearing impairment and sensorineural hearing impairment.

label: Protruding ear
definition: Angle formed by the plane of the ear and the mastoid bone greater than the 97th centile for age (objective); or, outer edge of the helix more than 2 cm from the mastoid at the point of maximum distance (objective).

label: Atresia of the external auditory canal
definition: Absence or failure to form of the external auditory canal.

label: Bulbous nose
definition: Increased volume and globular shape of the anteroinferior aspect of the nose.

label: Abnormal nasal tip morphology
definition: An abnormality of the nasal tip.

label: Abnormal choanae morphology
definition: Abnormality of the choanae (the posterior nasal apertures).

label: Narrow nasal ridge
definition: Decreased width of the nasal ridge.

label: Abnormal nasal dorsum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the nasal dorsum, also known as the nasal ridge.

label: Abnormal nasal septum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the nasal septum.

label: Short nasal septum
definition: Reduced superior to inferior length of the nasal septum.

label: Epistaxis
definition: Epistaxis, or nosebleed, refers to a hemorrhage localized in the nose.

label: Abnormal nasal bridge morphology
definition: Abnormality of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose. It lies between the glabella and the inferior boundary of the nasal bone, and extends laterally to the inner canthi.

label: Prominent nasal bridge
definition: Anterior positioning of the nasal root in comparison to the usual positioning for age.

label: Abnormal morphology of the nasal alae
definition: An abnormality of the Ala of nose.

label: Abnormal external nose morphology
definition: An abnormality of the external nose.

label: Underdeveloped nasal alae
definition: Thinned, deficient, or excessively arched ala nasi.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the nose
definition: Underdevelopment or absence of the nose or parts thereof.

label: Wide nasal bridge
definition: Increased breadth of the nasal bridge (and with it, the nasal root).

label: Nasal mucosa telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectasia of the nasal mucosa.

label: Depressed nasal tip
definition: Decreased distance from the nasal tip to the nasal base.

label: Convex nasal ridge
definition: Nasal ridge curving anteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip. The nose appears often also prominent, and the columella low.

label: Wide nose
definition: Interalar distance more than two standard deviations above the mean for age, i.e., an apparently increased width of the nasal base and alae.

label: Narrow nasal bridge
definition: Decreased width of the bony bridge of the nose.

label: Prominent nose
definition: Distance between subnasale and pronasale more than two standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased anterior protrusion of the nasal tip.

label: Choanal stenosis
definition: Abnormal narrowing of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture).

label: Choanal atresia
definition: Absence or abnormal closure of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture). Most embryologists believe that posterior choanal atresia results from a failure of rupture between the 35th and 38th day of fetal life of the partition which separates the bucconasal or buccopharyngeal membranes. The resultant choanal atresia may be unilateral or bilateral, bony or membranous, complete or incomplete. In over 90 per cent of cases the obstruction is bony, while in the remainder it is membranous. The bony type of atresia is commonly located 1-2 mm. anterior to the posterior edge of the hard palate, and the osseous septum varies in thickness from 1 to 10 mm. In the membranous form of choanal atresia the obstruction usually occurs further posteriorly. In approximately one third of cases the atresia is bilateral.

label: Broad nasal tip
definition: Increase in width of the nasal tip.

label: Bifid nasal tip
definition: A splitting of the nasal tip. Visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal tip.

label: Depressed nasal ridge
definition: Lack of prominence of the nose resulting from a posteriorly-placed nasal ridge.

label: Anosmia
definition: An inability to perceive odors. This is a general term describing inability to smell arising in any part of the process of smelling from absorption of odorants into the nasal mucous overlying the olfactory epithelium, diffusion to the cilia, binding to olfactory receptor sites, generation of action potentials in olfactory neurons, and perception of a smell.

label: Abnormality of the sense of smell
definition: An anomaly in the ability to perceive and distinguish scents (odors).

label: Narrow nose
definition: Interalar distance more than 2 SD below the mean for age, or alternatively, an apparently decreased width of the nasal base and alae.

label: Anteverted nares
definition: Anteriorly-facing nostrils viewed with the head in the Frankfurt horizontal and the eyes of the observer level with the eyes of the subject. This gives the appearance of an upturned nose (upturned nasal tip).

label: Abnormal nostril morphology
definition: Abnormality of the nostril.

label: Abnormality of the neck
definition: An abnormality of the neck.

label: Webbed neck
definition: Pterygium colli is a congenital skin fold that runs along the sides of the neck down to the shoulders. It involves an ectopic fibrotic facial band superficial to the trapezius muscle. Excess hair-bearing skin is also present and extends down the cervical region well beyond the normal hairline.

label: Abnormal neck morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the neck region.

label: Neck muscle weakness
definition: Decreased strength of the neck musculature.

label: Muscle weakness
definition: Reduced strength of muscles.

label: Increased adipose tissue around the neck
definition: An increased amount of subcutaneous fat tissue around the neck.

label: Increased adipose tissue
definition: An increase in adipose tissue mass by hyperplastic growth (increase in the number of adipocytes) or by hypertrophic growth (increase in the size of adipocytes occurring primarily by lipid accumulation within the cell).

label: Short neck
definition: Diminished length of the neck.

label: Abnormality of the cervical spine
definition: Any abnormality of the cervical vertebral column.

label: Gastrointestinal angiodysplasia
definition: Dysplasia affecting the vasculature of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Long neck
definition: Increased inferior-superior length of the neck.

label: Torticollis
definition: Involuntary contractions of the neck musculature resulting in an abnormal posture of or abnormal movements of the head.

label: Abnormal morphology of the musculature of the neck
definition: An abnormality of the neck musculature.

label: Abnormal central motor function
definition: An anomaly of the control or production of movement in the central nervous system.

label: Craniofacial dystonia
definition: A form of focal dystonia affecting the face and especially the jaw that is induced by the act of speaking. It is an involuntary contraction of the masticatory muscles, resulting in dysarthria or dysphagia.

label: Thickened nuchal skin fold
definition: A thickening of the skin thickness in the posterior aspect of the fetal neck. A nuchal fold (NF) measurement is obtained in a transverse section of the fetal head at the level of the cavum septum pellucidum and thalami, angled posteriorly to include the cerebellum. The measurement is taken from the outer edge of the occiput bone to the outer skin limit directly in the midline. An NF measurement greater than 5 mm at 14 to 17+6 weeks of gestation, or 6 mm at 18 to 28 weeks has been associated with a markedly increased risk for Down syndrome.

label: Fetal ultrasound soft marker
definition: An finding upon obstetric ultrasound examination performed at around 16 to 20 weeks of gestation that is abnormal but not clearly identifiable as a fetal anatomic malformation or growth restriction. Such findings are known as soft markers since they are associated with increased risk for fetal aneuploidy or other disorders.

label: Fetal neck anomaly
definition: A structural anomaly in the fetal neck region. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Broad neck
definition: Increased side-to-side width of the neck.

label: Cystic hygroma
definition: A cystic lymphatic lesion of the neck.

label: Abnormality of the eye
definition: Any abnormality of the eye, including location, spacing, and intraocular abnormalities.

label: Abnormal retinal morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the retina.

label: Abnormal fundus morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the fundus of the eye.

label: Retinal coloboma
definition: A notch or cleft of the retina.

label: Coloboma
definition: A developmental defect characterized by a cleft of some portion of the eye or ocular adnexa.

label: Abnormal cornea morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the cornea, which is the transparent tissue at the front of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber.

label: Abnormal anterior eye segment morphology
definition: An abnormality of the anterior segment of the eyeball (which comprises the structures in front of the vitreous humor: the cornea, iris, ciliary body, and lens).

label: Microcornea
definition: A congenital abnormality of the cornea in which the cornea and the anterior segment of the eye are smaller than normal. The horizontal diameter of the cornea does not reach 10 mm even in adulthood.

label: Abnormality of corneal size
definition: Any abnormality of the size or morphology of the cornea.

label: Astigmatism
definition: A type of refraction error associated with abnormal curvatures on the anterior and/or posterior surface of the cornea.

label: Abnormality of refraction
definition: An abnormality in the process of focusing of light by the eye in order to produce a sharp image on the retina.

label: Abnormality of the curvature of the cornea
Hyperopic astigmatism
definition: A form of astigmatism in which one meridian is hyperopic while the one at a right angle to it has no refractive error.

label: Megalocornea
definition: An enlargement of the cornea with normal clarity and function. Megalocornea is diagnosed with a horizontal corneal diameter of 12 mm or more at birth or 13 mm or more after two years of age.

label: Strabismus
definition: A misalignment of the eyes so that the visual axes deviate from bifoveal fixation. The classification of strabismus may be based on a number of features including the relative position of the eyes, whether the deviation is latent or manifest, intermittent or constant, concomitant or otherwise and according to the age of onset and the relevance of any associated refractive error.

label: Abnormal conjugate eye movement
definition: Any deviation from the normal motor coordination of the eyes that allows for bilateral fixation on a single object.

label: Retinopathy
definition: Any noninflammatory disease of the retina. This nonspecific term is retained here because of its wide use in the literature, but if possible new annotations should indicate the precise type of retinal abnormality.

label: Deeply set eye
definition: An eye that is more deeply recessed into the plane of the face than is typical.

label: Keratitis
definition: Inflammation of the cornea.

label: Abnormal corneal epithelium morphology
definition: Abnormality of the corneal epithelium, that is of the epithelial tissue that covers the front of the cornea.

label: Inflammatory abnormality of the eye
definition: Inflammation of the eye, parts of the eye or the periorbital region.

label: Abnormal ocular adnexa morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

label: Abnormal foveal morphology
definition: An abnormality of the fovea centralis, the central area of the macula that mediates central, high resolution vision and contains the largest concentration of cone cells in the retina.

label: Abnormal macular morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the macula lutea, which is an oval-shaped highly pigmented yellow spot near the center of the retina.

label: Downslanted palpebral fissures
definition: The palpebral fissure inclination is more than two standard deviations below the mean.

label: Recurrent corneal erosions
definition: The presence of recurrent corneal epithelial erosions. Although most corneal epithelial defects heal quickly, some may show recurrent ulcerations.

label: Corneal erosion
definition: An erosion or abrasion of the cornea's outermost layer of epithelial cells.

label: Abnormality of eye movement
definition: An abnormality in voluntary or involuntary eye movements or their control.

label: Abnormal eye physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the eye.

label: Globe retraction and deviation on abduction
Abnormality of ocular abduction
definition: An abnormality involving the movement of the eye outwards.

label: Blepharitis
definition: Inflammation of the eyelids.

label: Abnormal eyelash morphology
definition: An abnormality of the eyelashes.

label: Abnormal hair morphology
definition: An abnormality of the hair.

label: Glaucoma
definition: Glaucoma refers loss of retinal ganglion cells in a characteristic pattern of optic neuropathy usually associated with increased intraocular pressure.

label: Abnormal conjunctiva morphology
definition: An abnormality of the conjunctiva.

label: Tortuosity of conjunctival vessels
definition: The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the conjunctival blood vessels.

label: Abnormal morphology of the conjunctival vasculature
definition: Any abnormality of the blood vessels of the conjunctiva.

label: Abnormality of vision
definition: Abnormality of eyesight (visual perception).

label: Visual impairment
definition: Visual impairment (or vision impairment) is vision loss (of a person) to such a degree as to qualify as an additional support need through a significant limitation of visual capability resulting from either disease, trauma, or congenital or degenerative conditions that cannot be corrected by conventional means, such as refractive correction, medication, or surgery.

label: Telecanthus
definition: Distance between the inner canthi more than two standard deviations above the mean (objective); or, apparently increased distance between the inner canthi.

label: Ptosis
definition: The upper eyelid margin is positioned 3 mm or more lower than usual and covers the superior portion of the iris (objective); or, the upper lid margin obscures at least part of the pupil (subjective).

label: Conjunctivitis
definition: Inflammation of the conjunctiva.

label: Red eye
definition: A reddish appearance over the white part (sclera) of the eye ranging from a few enlarged blood vessels appearing as wiggly lines over the sclera to a bright red color completely covering to sclera.

label: Rod-cone dystrophy
definition: An inherited retinal disease subtype in which the rod photoreceptors appear to be more severely affected than the cone photoreceptors. Typical presentation is with nyctalopia (due to rod dysfunction) followed by loss of mid-peripheral field of vision, which gradually extends and leaves many patients with a small central island of vision due to the preservation of macular cones.

label: Retinal dystrophy
definition: Retinal dystrophy is an abnormality of the retina associated with a hereditary process. Retinal dystrophies are defined by their predominantly monogenic inheritance and they are frequently associated with loss or dysfunction of photoreceptor cells as a primary or secondary event.

label: Vertical supranuclear gaze palsy
