definition: A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a vertical direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal.

label: Supranuclear gaze palsy
definition: A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a particular direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal.

label: Abnormal electroretinogram
definition: Any abnormality of the electrical responses of various cell types in the retina as measured by electroretinography.

label: Slow saccadic eye movements
definition: An abnormally slow velocity of the saccadic eye movements.

label: Abnormal saccadic eye movements
definition: An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impairment of fast (saccadic) eye movements.

label: Abnormal lens morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lens.

label: Cataract
definition: A cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the crystalline lens of the eye or in its capsule.

label: Developmental cataract
definition: A cataract that occurs congenitally as the result of a developmental defect, in contrast to the majority of cataracts that occur in adulthood as the result of degenerative changes of the lens.

label: Ocular anterior segment dysgenesis
definition: Abnormal development (dysgenesis) of the anterior segment of the eye globe. These structures are mainly of mesenchymal origin.

label: Proptosis
definition: An eye that is protruding anterior to the plane of the face to a greater extent than is typical.

label: Alacrima
definition: Absence of tear secretion.

label: Decreased lacrimation
definition: Abnormally decreased lacrimation, that is, reduced tear production.

label: Subcapsular cataract
definition: A cataract that affects the region of the lens directly beneath the capsule of the lens.

label: Conjunctival telangiectasia
definition: The presence of small (ca. 0.5-1.0 mm) dilated blood vessels near the surface of the mucous membranes of the conjunctiva.

label: Abnormality iris morphology
definition: An abnormality of the iris, which is the pigmented muscular tissue between the cornea and the lens, that is perforated by an opening called the pupil.

label: Abnormal uvea morphology
definition: An abnormality of the uvea, the vascular layer of the eyeball.

label: Aniridia
definition: Abnormality of the iris characterized by, typically bilateral, complete or partial iris hypoplasia. The phenotype ranges from mild defects of anterior iris stroma only to almost complete absence of the iris.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the iris
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the iris.

label: Long eyelashes
definition: Mid upper eyelash length >10 mm or increased length of the eyelashes (subjective).

label: Anophthalmia
definition: Absence of the globe or eyeball.

label: Abnormality of globe size
definition: An abnormality in the size of the ocular globe (eyeball).

label: Progressive visual loss
definition: A reduction of previously attained ability to see.

label: Visual loss
definition: Loss of visual acuity (implying that vision was better at a certain time point in life). Otherwise the term reduced visual acuity should be used (or a subclass of that).

label: Opacification of the corneal stroma
definition: Reduced transparency of the stroma of cornea.

label: Abnormal chorioretinal morphology
definition: An abnormality of the choroid and retina.

label: Abnormal choroid morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the choroid.

label: Chorioretinal atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the choroid and retinal layers of the fundus.

label: Abnormal eyebrow morphology
definition: An abnormality of the eyebrow.

label: Epicanthus inversus
definition: A fold of skin starting at or just below the medial aspect of the lower lid and arching upward to cover, extend in front of and lateral to the medial canthus.

label: Pseudopapilledema
definition: Apparent optic disc swelling in the absence of increased intracranial pressure.

label: Abnormal optic disc morphology
definition: A morphological abnormality of the optic disc, i.e., of the portion of the optic nerve clinically visible on fundoscopic examination.

label: Hypermetropia
definition: An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects in the distance clearly, while objects nearby appear blurry.

label: Retinal detachment
definition: Separation of the inner layers of the retina (neural retina) from the pigment epithelium.

label: Impaired ocular adduction
definition: Reduced ability to move the eye in the direction of the nose.

label: Optic disc pallor
definition: A pale yellow discoloration of the optic disc (the area of the optic nerve head in the retina). The optic disc normally has a pinkish hue with a central yellowish depression.

label: External ophthalmoplegia
definition: Paralysis of the external ocular muscles.

label: Ophthalmoplegia
definition: Paralysis of one or more extraocular muscles that are responsible for eye movements.

label: Myopia
definition: An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects nearby clearly, while objects in the distance appear blurry.

label: Retinal degeneration
definition: A nonspecific term denoting degeneration of the retinal pigment epithelium and/or retinal photoreceptor cells.

label: Undetectable electroretinogram
definition: Lack of any response to stimulation upon electroretinography.

label: Color vision defect
definition: An anomaly in the ability to discriminate between or recognize colors.

label: Tritanomaly
definition: Difficulty distinguishing between yellow and blue, possible related to dysfunction of the S photopigment.

label: Anomalous trichromacy
definition: Individuals with anomalous trichromacy possess three types of cones, but one of the three types of cones has an abnormal spectral sensitivity compared to normal cones.

label: Abnormal eye morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the globe of the eye, or bulbus oculi.

label: Uveitis
definition: Inflammation of one or all portions of the uveal tract.

label: Leukocoria
definition: An abnormal white reflection from the pupil rather than the usual black reflection.

label: Abnormal pupil morphology
definition: An abnormality of the pupil.

label: Buphthalmos
definition: Diffusely large eye (with megalocornea) associated with glaucoma.

label: Developmental glaucoma
definition: Glaucoma which forms during the early years of a child's life is called developmental or congenital glaucoma.

label: Abnormally large globe
definition: Diffusely large eye (with megalocornea) without glaucoma.

label: Rieger anomaly
definition: A congenital malformation of the anterior segment characterized by iridicorneal malformation, glaucoma, iris stroma hypoplasia, posterior embryotoxon, and corneal opacities.

label: Hypoplasia of the iris
definition: Congenital underdevelopment of the iris.

label: Corneal opacity
definition: A reduction of corneal clarity.

label: Scarring
definition: A scar refers to a lesion in which wound, burn, or sore has not healed completely and fibrous connective tissue has developed.

label: Absent eyelashes
definition: Lack of eyelashes.

label: Absent facial hair
definition: Absence of facial hair.

label: Keratoconus
definition: A cone-shaped deformity of the cornea characterized by the presence of corneal distortion secondary to thinning of the apex.

label: Decreased corneal thickness
definition: A decreased anteroposterior thickness of the cornea.

label: Increased corneal curvature
definition: An increase in the degree of curvature of the cornea compared to normal.

label: Lacrimal duct atresia
definition: A developmental disorder of the lacrimal drainage system that most often affects the lacrimal ostium and resulting in non-opening of the nasolacrimal duct. It usually results from a non-canalization of the nasolacrimal duct.

label: Abnormal lacrimal duct morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lacrimal duct, a duct that drain tears from the conjunctiva, via the lacrimal puncta, into the lacrimal sac.

label: Esotropia
definition: A form of strabismus with one or both eyes turned inward ('crossed') to a relatively severe degree, usually defined as 10 diopters or more.

label: Esodeviation
definition: A manifest or latent ocular deviation in which one or both eyes tends to deviate nasally.

label: Heterotropia
definition: Manifest deviation of the visual axes not controlled by fusion.

label: Chorioretinal coloboma
definition: Absence of a region of the retina, retinal pigment epithelium, and choroid.

label: Microphthalmia
definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by abnormal smallness of one or both eyes.

label: Hypometric saccades
definition: Saccadic undershoot, i.e., a saccadic eye movement that has less than the magnitude that would be required to gain fixation of the object.

label: Retinal hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage occurring within the retina.

label: Hemorrhage of the eye
definition: Bleeding from vessels of the various tissues of the eye.

label: Fundus hemorrhage
definition: Bleeding within the fundus of the eye.

label: Thick eyebrow
definition: Increased density/number and/or increased diameter of eyebrow hairs.

label: Scotoma
definition: A regional and pathological increase of the light detection threshold in any region of the visual field surrounded by a field of normal or relatively well-preserved vision.

label: Centrocecal scotoma
definition: A scotoma (area of diminished vision within the visual field) located between the central point of fixation and the blind spot with a roughly horizontal oval shape.

label: Exotropia
definition: A form of strabismus with one or both eyes deviated outward.

label: Exodeviation
definition: A manifest or latent ocular deviation in which one or both eyes tends to deviate temporally.

label: Nasolacrimal duct obstruction
definition: Blockage of the lacrimal duct.

label: Pigmentary retinopathy
definition: An abnormality of the retina characterized by pigment deposition. It is typically associated with migration and proliferation of macrophages or retinal pigment epithelial cells into the retina; melanin from these cells causes the pigmentary changes. Pigmentary retinopathy is a common final pathway of many retinal conditions and is often associated with visual loss.

label: Blepharophimosis
definition: A fixed reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids with short palpebral fissures.

label: Abnormal size of the palpebral fissures
definition: An abnormal size of the palpebral fissures for example unusually long or short palpebral fissures.

label: Upslanted palpebral fissure
definition: The palpebral fissure inclination is more than two standard deviations above the mean for age (objective); or, the inclination of the palpebral fissure is greater than typical for age.

label: Band keratopathy
definition: An abnormality of the cornea characterized by the deposition of calcium in a band across the central cornea, leading to decreased vision, foreign body sensation, and ocular irritation.

label: Central opacification of the cornea
definition: Reduced transparency of the central portion of the corneal stroma.

label: Shallow orbits
definition: Reduced depth of the orbits associated with prominent-appearing ocular globes.

label: Abnormal morphology of bony orbit of skull
definition: An abnormality of an orbit of skull.

label: Abnormal optic nerve morphology
definition: Abnormality of the optic nerve.

label: Optic disc coloboma
definition: A cleft of the optic nerve that extends inferiorly.

label: Progressive external ophthalmoplegia
definition: Initial bilateral ptosis followed by limitation of eye movements in all directions and slowing of saccades.

label: Abnormal sclera morphology
definition: An abnormality of the sclera.

label: Blue sclerae
definition: An abnormal bluish coloration of the sclera.

label: Abnormal anterior chamber morphology
definition: Abnormality of the anterior chamber, which is the space in the eye that is behind the cornea and in front of the iris.

label: Shallow anterior chamber
definition: Reduced depth of the anterior chamber, i.e., the anteroposterior distance between the cornea and the iris is decreased.

label: Ophthalmoparesis
definition: Ophthalmoplegia is a paralysis or weakness of one or more of the muscles that control eye movement.

label: Abnormality of the ear
definition: An abnormality of the ear.

label: Abnormality of the hairline
definition: The hairline refers to the outline of hair of the head. An abnormality of the hairline can refer to an unusually low or high border between areas of the scalp with and without hair or to abnormal projections of scalp hair.

label: Abnormality of the pharynx
definition: An anomaly of the pharynx, i.e., of the tubular structure extending from the base of the skull superiorly to the esophageal inlet inferiorly.

label: Hypotelorism
definition: Interpupillary distance less than 2 SD below the mean (alternatively, the appearance of an decreased interpupillary distance or closely spaced eyes).

label: Central scotoma
definition: An area of depressed vision located at the point of fixation and that interferes with central vision.

label: Abnormality of the periorbital region
definition: An abnormality of the region situated around the orbit of the eye.

label: Premature skin wrinkling
definition: The presence of an increased degree of wrinkling (irregular folds and indentations) of the skin as compared with age-related norms.

label: Macular degeneration
definition: A nonspecific term denoting degeneration of the retinal pigment epithelium and/or retinal photoreceptor cells of the macula lutea.

label: Optic nerve hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the optic nerve.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the central nervous system
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of tissue in the central nervous system.

label: Iris coloboma
definition: A coloboma of the iris.

label: Photophobia
definition: Excessive sensitivity to light with the sensation of discomfort or pain in the eyes due to exposure to bright light.

label: Sensory hypersensitivity
definition: A decreased tolerance to sensory stimuli that triggers emotional and/or physical distress.

label: Abnormal nasolacrimal system morphology
definition: An abnormality of the nasolacrimal drainage system, which serves as a conduit for tear flow from the external eye to the nasal cavity.

label: Miosis
definition: Abnormal (non-physiological) constriction of the pupil.

label: Abnormal pupillary function
definition: A functional abnormality of the pupil.

label: Abnormality of ocular smooth pursuit
definition: An abnormality of eye movement characterized by impaired smooth-pursuit eye movements.

label: Blindness
definition: Blindness is the condition of lacking visual perception defined as a profound reduction in visual perception. On the 6m visual acuity scale, blindness is defined as less than 3/60. On the 20ft visual acuity scale, blindness is defined as less than 20/400. On the decimal visual acuity scale, blindness is defined as less than 0.05. Blindness is typically characterized by a visual field of no greater than 10 degrees in radius around central fixation.

label: Impaired convergence
definition: Reduced ability to turn the eyes inward in order to focus on a nearby object.

label: Dacryocystitis
definition: Inflammation of the nasolacrimal sac.

label: Entropion
definition: An abnormal inversion (turning inward) of the eyelid (usually the lower) towards the globe. Entropion is usually acquired as a result of involutional or cicatricial processes but may occasionally be congenital.

label: Blurred vision
definition: Lack of sharpness of vision resulting in the inability to see fine detail.

label: Supranuclear ophthalmoplegia
definition: A vertical gaze palsy with inability to direct the gaze of the eyes downwards.

label: Eyelid coloboma
definition: A short discontinuity of the margin of the lower or upper eyelid.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the eyelid
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the eyelid.

label: Posterior embryotoxon
definition: A posterior embryotoxon is the presence of a prominent and anteriorly displaced line of Schwalbe.

label: Abnormal line of Schwalbe morphology
definition: An abnormality of the line of Schwalbe.

label: Periorbital fullness
definition: Increase in periorbital soft tissue.

label: Abnormal retinal vascular morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of retinal vasculature.

label: Abnormal systemic arterial morphology
definition: An abnormality of the systemic arterial tree, which consists of the aorta and other systemic arteries.

label: Abnormal head blood vessel morphology
definition: An abnormality of a blood vessel of the head, including branches of the arterial and venous systems of the head.

label: Retinal arterial tortuosity
definition: The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the retinal artery.

label: Arterial tortuosity
definition: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of arteries.

label: Retinal vascular tortuosity
definition: The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the retinal blood vessels.

label: Lacrimation abnormality
definition: Abnormality of tear production.

label: Impaired ocular abduction
definition: An impaired ability of the eye to move in the outward direction (towards the side of the head).

label: Blue irides
definition: A markedly blue coloration of the iris.

label: Abnormal iris pigmentation
definition: Abnormal pigmentation of the iris.

label: Upper eyelid coloboma
definition: A short discontinuity of the margin of the upper eyelid.

label: Long palpebral fissure
definition: Distance between medial and lateral canthi is more than two standard deviations above the mean for age (objective); or, apparently increased length of the palpebral fissures.

label: Nystagmus
definition: Rhythmic, involuntary oscillations of one or both eyes related to abnormality in fixation, conjugate gaze, or vestibular mechanisms.

label: Abnormal involuntary eye movements
definition: Anomalous movements of the eyes that occur without the subject wanting them to happen.

label: Gaze-evoked nystagmus
definition: Nystagmus made apparent by looking to the right or to the left.

label: Dysmetric saccades
definition: The controller signal for saccadic eye movements has two components: the pulse that moves the eye rapidly from one point to the next, and the step that holds the eye in the new position. When both the pulse and the step are not the correct size, a dysmetric refixation eye movement results.

label: Red-green dyschromatopsia
definition: Difficulty with discriminating red and green hues.

label: Dyschromatopsia
definition: A form of colorblindness in which only two of the three fundamental colors can be distinguished due to a lack of one of the retinal cone pigments.

label: Blepharospasm
definition: A focal dystonia that affects the muscles of the eyelids and brow, associated with involuntary recurrent spasm of both eyelids.

label: Abnormal eyelid physiology
definition: Any functional abnormality of the eyelid.

label: Amblyopia
definition: Reduced visual acuity that is uncorrectable by lenses in the absence of detectable anatomic defects in the eye or visual pathways.

label: Sclerocornea
definition: A congenital anomaly in which a part or the whole of the cornea acquires the characteristics of sclera, resulting in clouding of the cornea.

label: Optic atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the optic nerve. Optic atrophy results from the death of the retinal ganglion cell axons that comprise the optic nerve and manifesting as a pale optic nerve on fundoscopy.

label: Abnormality of visual evoked potentials
definition: An anomaly of visually evoked potentials (VEP), which are electrical potentials, initiated by brief visual stimuli, which are recorded from the scalp overlying the visual cortex.

label: Abnormal brain-evoked potentials
definition: Any anomaly of brain-evoked potentials, defined as potentials generated by exteroceptive stimuli reflect synchronized activity by neuronal and axonal groups in the central nervous system (CNS) resulting from the arrival of nerve impulses after stimulation of a peripheral nerve or its receptors. Depending on the type of stimulus, evoked potentials are categorized as visual (VEP), auditory (AEP), or somatosensory (SSEP). Motor evoked potentials (MEP) occur when the brain's motor area is stimulated. They result from the activation of a sufficient number of motor units.

label: Abnormal amplitude of pattern reversal visual evoked potentials
Abnormality of pattern reversal visual evoked potentials
Diplopia
definition: Diplopia is a condition in which a single object is perceived as two images, it is also known as double vision.

label: Abnormality of binocular vision
definition: An abnormality of binocular vision, that is of the ability to synthesize the visual inputs from both eyes to a single image with perception of depth.

label: Lower eyelid coloboma
definition: A short discontinuity of the margin of the lower eyelid.

label: Sparse eyelashes
definition: Decreased density/number of eyelashes.

label: Sparse hair
definition: Reduced density of hairs.

label: Decreased light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram amplitude
definition: Decreased amplitude of eletrical response upon electroretinography.

label: Abnormal light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram
definition: An abnormality of the combined rod-and-cone response on electroretinogram.

label: Ectropion
definition: An outward turning (eversion) or rotation of the eyelid margin.

label: Oculomotor apraxia
definition: Ocular motor apraxia is a deficiency in voluntary, horizontal, lateral, fast eye movements (saccades) with retention of slow pursuit movements. The inability to follow objects visually is often compensated by head movements. There may be decreased smooth pursuit, and cancelation of the vestibulo-ocular reflex.

label: Apraxia
definition: A defect in the understanding of complex motor commands and in the execution of certain learned movements, i.e., deficits in the cognitive components of learned movements.

label: Peters anomaly
definition: A form of anterior segment dysgenesis in which abnormal cleavage of the anterior chamber occurs. Peters anomaly is characterized by central, paracentral, or complete corneal opacity.

label: Lipemia retinalis
definition: A creamy appearance of the retinal blood vessels that occurs when the concentration of lipids in the blood are extremely increased, with pale pink to milky white retinal vessels and altered pale reflexes from choroidal vasculature.

label: Nyctalopia
definition: Inability to see well at night or in poor light.

label: Synophrys
definition: Meeting of the medial eyebrows in the midline.

label: Facial hypertrichosis
definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the facial region.

label: Horizontal nystagmus
definition: Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements.

label: Phthisis bulbi
definition: Atrophy of the eyeball with blindness and decreased intraocular pressure due to end-stage intraocular disease.

label: Hypodontia
definition: The absence of five or less teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop.

label: Tooth agenesis
definition: The absence of one or more teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop

label: Carious teeth
definition: Caries is a multifactorial bacterial infection affecting the structure of the tooth. This term has been used to describe the presence of more than expected dental caries.

label: Abnormality of dental structure
definition: An abnormality of the structure or composition of the teeth.

label: Anodontia
definition: The absence of all teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop.

label: Macrodontia of permanent maxillary central incisor
definition: Increased size of the maxillary central secondary incisor tooth.

label: Incisor macrodontia
definition: Increased size of the incisor tooth.

label: Abnormality of the incisor
definition: An abnormality of the Incisor tooth.

label: Oligodontia
definition: The absence of six or more teeth from the normal series by a failure to develop.

label: Dental crowding
definition: Changes in alignment of teeth in the dental arch

label: Tooth malposition
definition: Abnormal alignment, positioning, or spacing of the teeth, i.e., misaligned teeth.

label: Taurodontia
definition: Increased volume of dental pulp of permanent molar characterized by a crown body-root ratio equal or larger than 1:1 or an elongated pulp chambers and apical displacement of the bifurcation or trifurcation of the roots.

label: Abnormal dental pulp morphology
definition: An abnormality of the dental pulp.

label: Abnormal dental root morphology
definition: An abnormality of the dental root.

label: Abnormal permanent molar morphology
definition: An abnormality of morphology of permanent molar.

label: Delayed eruption of primary teeth
definition: Delayed tooth eruption affecting the primary dentition.

label: Delayed eruption of teeth
definition: Delayed tooth eruption, which can be defined as tooth eruption more than 2 SD beyond the mean eruption age.

label: Abnormality of primary teeth
definition: Any abnormality of the primary tooth.

label: Abnormal dental enamel morphology
definition: An abnormality of the dental enamel.

label: Abnormal odontoid tissue morphology
definition: An abnormality of an odontoid tissue.

label: Grayish enamel
definition: A gray discoloration of the dental enamel.

label: Abnormality of dental color
definition: A developmental defect of tooth color.

label: Abnormality of dental eruption
definition: An abnormality of tooth eruption.

label: Hypoplasia of teeth
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of teeth.

label: Widely spaced teeth
definition: Increased spaces (diastemata) between most of the teeth in the same dental arch.

label: Dental malocclusion
definition: Dental malocclusion refers to an abnormality of the occlusion, or alignment, of the teeth and the way the upper and lower teeth fit together, resulting in overcrowding of teeth or in abnormal bite patterns.

label: Agenesis of maxillary lateral incisor
definition: Agenesis of one or more maxillary lateral incisor, comprising the maxillary lateral primary incisor and maxillary lateral secondary incisor.

label: Microdontia
definition: Decreased size of the teeth, which can be defined as a mesiodistal tooth diameter (width) more than 2 SD below mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased maximum width of tooth.

label: Abnormal dental morphology
definition: An abnormality of the morphology of the tooth.

label: Odontodysplasia
definition: The diagnosis odontodysplasia requires clinical and radiological exams, in which unusually large pulp chambers and large pulp room chambers with thin enamel and dentin are visible. It may affect either a single tooth or several teeth. The term regional odontodysplasia is used if several teeth are affected. It affects the deciduous and permanent dentitions in the maxilla, the mandible or both, although the maxilla is more frequently involved. A type of dental dysplasia occurring in dentinogenesis imperfecta in which the pulp chambers are enlarged and there is a reduced amount of coronal dentin.

label: Dentinogenesis imperfecta
definition: Developmental dysplasia of dentin.

label: Natal tooth
definition: A tooth present at birth or erupting within the first month of life.

label: Advanced eruption of teeth
definition: Premature tooth eruption, which can be defined as tooth eruption more than 2 SD earlier than the mean eruption age.

label: Delayed eruption of permanent teeth
definition: Delayed tooth eruption affecting the secondary dentition.

label: Conical tooth
definition: An abnormal conical form of the teeth, that is, a tooth whose sides converge or taper together incisally.

label: Diastema
definition: Increased space between two adjacent teeth in the same dental arch.

label: Periapical bone loss
definition: Radiolucency (reflecting a reduction in the bony substance) around the apex (the tip of the dental root).

label: Abnormal dentin morphology
definition: Any abnormality of dentin.

label: Amelogenesis imperfecta
definition: A developmental dysplasia of the dental enamel.

label: Eruption failure
definition: A tooth which does not erupt within the teeth eruption timeline and after the loss of eruption potential.

label: Abnormality of the nervous system
definition: An abnormality of the nervous system.

label: Atypical behavior
definition: Atypical behavior is an abnormality in a person's actions that can be controlled or modulated by the will of the individual. While abnormal behaviors can be difficult to control, they are distinct from other abnormal actions that cannot be affected by the individual's will.

label: Abnormality of mental function
definition: Cognitive, psychiatric, or memory anomaly.

label: Psychosis
definition: A condition characterized by changes in personality and thought patterns, often accompanied by hallucinations and delusional beliefs, is known as psychosis.

label: Abnormal psychotic pattern
definition: Any abnormal pattern of psychotic experiences, where an individual has significant disturbances in their thoughts, perceptions, emotions, and behavior, resulting in a loss of touch with reality.

label: Hyperorality
definition: Hyperorality is a condition characterized by an excessive preoccupation with oral sensations and behaviors, such as chewing, sucking, biting, swallowing, and excessive mouthing of objects.

label: Tactile sensory seeking
definition: Pursuit of a specific texture that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency.

label: Restlessness
definition: A state of unease is characterized by diffuse motor activity or motion, which is subject to limited control, nonproductive, or disorganized behavior.

label: Abnormally increased volition
definition: An excessive increase in motivated and goal directed as well as non-goal directed behaviors that are usually accompanied by elevated energy and interest that allows individuals to get started, be energized to perform a sustained and directed action. The increase is often disruptive and typically results in unfavorable consequences.

label: Emotional lability
definition: Unstable emotional experiences and frequent mood changes; emotions that are easily aroused, intense, and/or disproportionate to events and circumstances.

label: Impairment in personality functioning
definition: A maladaptive personality trait characterized by moderate or greater impairment in personality (self /interpersonal) functioning.

label: Abnormal emotional state
definition: Emotions are complex psychological states that involve three distinct components: a subjective experience, a physiological response, and a behavioral or expressive response. In an abnormal emotional state, an affected individual shows altered intensity, frequency, or duration of emotional experiences.

label: Agitation
definition: A state of excessive motor activity that is associated with mental distress or a feeling of substantial unease or inner tension. Distinguished from restlessness by the increased level of emotional distress and negative intensity of the experience. Agitation has a significant level of physical activity that is typically threatening to the self or others.

label: Depression
definition: Frequently experiencing feelings of being down, miserable, and/or hopeless; struggling to recover from these moods; having a pessimistic outlook on the future; feeling a pervasive sense of shame; having a low self-worth; experiencing thoughts of suicide and engaging in suicidal behavior.

label: Abnormal diminished volition
definition: A reduction in willful and motivated goal-directed behavior that is considered the determinant of behavior and adaptation that allows individuals to get started, be energized to perform a sustained and directed action.

label: Autism
definition: Autism is a neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by impaired social interaction and communication, and by restricted and repetitive behavior. Autism begins in childhood. It is marked by the presence of markedly abnormal or impaired development in social interaction and communication and a markedly restricted repertoire of activity and interest. Manifestations of the disorder vary greatly depending on the developmental level and chronological age of the individual (DSM-IV).

label: Autistic behavior
definition: Persistent deficits in social interaction and communication and interaction as well as a markedly restricted repertoire of activity and interest as well as repetitive patterns of behavior.

label: Aggressive behavior
definition: Behavior or an act aimed at harming a person, animal, or physical property (e.g., acts of physical violence; shouting, swearing, and using harsh language; slashing someone's tires).

label: Disinhibition
definition: Reduced ability to control, or a failure to resist a temptation, urge, or impulse. Examples include disregard for social conventions, general impulsivity, and poor risk assessment.

label: Inappropriate behavior
definition: An explicit or perceived action, demonstration, conduct, or language (verbal and written) that is contrary to generally accepted norms, rules, procedures, or unacceptable within the context in which it is carried out. Inappropriate behaviors could take place in a sexual or social context and could be aggressive, violent, impulsive, intimidating, or threatening in nature.

label: Social disinhibition
definition: A tendency to violate social norms because of a failure to resist temptations or urges in social settings.

label: Abnormal play
definition: An abnormality in a child's ability play.

label: Compulsive behaviors
definition: Behavior that consists of repetitive acts, characterized by the feeling that one has to" perform them
column5: while being aware that these acts are not in line with one's overall goal."

label: Recurrent maladaptive behavior
definition: A repeating behavior that is either immediately unproductive or has negative long-term consequences. This includes harmful coping mechanisms such as addictive behavior and failure to control impulses and compulsions.

label: Restrictive behavior
definition: Behavior characterized by an abnormal limitation to a few interests and activities.

label: Restricted or repetitive behaviors or interests
definition: A broad range of compulsive behaviors are repeated, including simple motor stereotypies and tics, as well as more complex repetitive movements or compulsions.

label: Psychotic episodes
definition: Periods of time during which an individual experiences significant disturbances in their thoughts, perceptions, emotions, and behavior, resulting in a loss of touch with reality. These episodes are hallmark features of psychotic disorders such as schizophrenia, schizoaffective disorder, and certain forms of bipolar disorder.

label: Dementia
definition: A loss of global cognitive ability of sufficient amount to interfere with normal social or occupational function. Dementia represents a loss of previously present cognitive abilities, generally in adults, and can affect memory, thinking, language, judgment, and behavior.

label: Mental deterioration
definition: Loss of previously present mental abilities, generally in adults.

label: Impaired ability to form peer relationships
definition: Difficulty to establish relations with others in a comparable social group (peers) that may be manifested in pehnomena such as not being able to initiative a conversation, understand social cues, or to discuss shared interests. This feature is associated with poor integration within a community or group.

label: Reduced social responsiveness
definition: A reduced ability to participate in the back-and-forth flow of social interaction appropriate to culture and developmental level, which is normally characterized by an influence of the behavior of one person on the behavior of another person. This results in difficulty interacting with others through emotional, physical, or verbal communication.

label: Diagnostic behavioral phenotype
definition: The Human Phenotype Ontology provides terms to describe specific phenotypic abnormalities rather than disease diagnoses. Nevertheless, it is common for descriptions such as 'Autism' to be used to describe individuals affected with Mendelian forms of neurodevelopmental disease and many other conditions. If possible, we recommend annotation using specific terms in other branchs of the Atypical behavior subontology, but if this is not possible, then terms from this branch may be used.

label: Inflexible adherence to routines
definition: A need to strictly adhere to repetitive routines or patterns of behavior which are created by the environment. One becomes upset or distressed when their routines are disrupted or altered.

label: Motor stereotypy
definition: Use of the same abnormal action in response to certain triggers or at random. They may be used as a way to regulate one's internal state but must otherwise have no apparent functional purpose.

label: Short attention span
definition: Reduced attention span characterized by distractibility and impulsivity.

label: Reduced attention regulation
definition: An abnormality in one's ability to control their attention towards a specific subject or task can include difficulties in changing or maintaining attention.

label: Irritability
definition: A proneness to anger, i.e., a tendency to become easily bothered or annoyed.

label: Hallucinations
definition: Perceptions in a conscious and awake state that, in the absence of external stimuli, have qualities of real perception. These perceptions are vivid, substantial, and located in external objective space.

label: Abnormal experience of reality
definition: Subjective phenomena or perceptions that deviate from what is considered correct or are outside the range of normal human experiences.

label: Anxiety
definition: Intense feelings of nervousness, tension, or panic often arise in response to interpersonal stresses. There is worry about the negative effects of past unpleasant experiences and future negative possibilities. Individuals may feel fearful, apprehensive, or threatened by uncertainty, and they may also have fears of falling apart or losing control.

label: Maladaptive fear-related cognitions
definition: Threat-based cognitive biases result in a skewed perception, experience, or processing of internal or external stimuli.

label: Episodic paroxysmal anxiety
definition: Recurrent attacks of severe anxiety, which occur without restriction to any particular situation or set of circumstances, are therefore unpredictable.

label: Apathy
definition: Apathy is a quantitative reduction of interest, motivation and the initiation and persistence of goal-directed behavior, where often the accompanying emotions, thoughts, and social interactions are also diminished. The individual is typically non-reactive to provocations, positive or negative, and appears to not care. Distinguished from lethargy which involves lack of physical or mental energy.

label: Self-mutilation
definition: Deliberate harm to one's body resulting in tissue damage, without a conscious intent to die.

label: Self-injurious behavior
definition: Self-aggression.

label: Frontal release signs
definition: Primitive reflexes traditionally held to be a sign of disorders that affect the frontal lobes.

label: Abnormality of movement
definition: An abnormality of movement with a neurological basis characterized by changes in coordination and speed of voluntary movements.

label: Low frustration tolerance
definition: The feeling of frustration can be defined as an emotional reaction that occurs when a desired goal is not achieved. Frustration intolerance is defined as an age-inappropriate response to frustration, characterized by crying or temper tantrums in children, or aggressive or other undesirable behaviors.

label: Abnormal volitional state
definition: An abnormality of internal states of motivation or drive that compromise, or interfere with, the ability of the person to attend to basic personal, social, or vocational activities.

label: Delusion
definition: A delusion is a fixed false belief held despite evidence to the contrary. The term delusion broadly encompasses all false judgments that possess the following external characteristics to a significant, albeit unspecified, extent: (1) they are held with an exceptional level of conviction, accompanied by an unparalleled subjective certainty; (2) there is an inability to consider alternative experiences or compelling counter-arguments; (3) the content of the belief is impossible.

label: Disorder of thought content
definition: Thought content disorders are characterized by abnormal beliefs and convictions (that are to be assessed given the culture and personal background of the affected individual).

label: Abnormal judgment
definition: Beliefs that deviate from what is considered rational or within the range of normal human judgment and belief formation.

label: Inappropriate laughter
definition: Laughing that may be excessive and/or inappropriate in context (e.g., laughing at a funeral while others are crying).

label: Delayed speech and language development
definition: A degree of language development that is significantly below the norm for a child of a specified age.

label: Abnormal speech pattern
definition: An abnormality in the sound (volume) or cadence (rate) of speech.

label: Language impairment
definition: Language impairment is a deficit in comprehension or production of language that includes reduced vocabulary, limited sentence structure, or impairments in written or spoken communication. Language abilities are substantially and quantifiably below age expectations.

label: Neurodevelopmental delay
definition: Neurodevelopmental delay (NDD) refers to delays in the maturation of the brain and central nervous system; infants and young children with NDD may experience delays in the development of one or more skills including gross motor abilities, fine-motor coordination, language abilities and ability to solve increasingly complex problems.

label: Personality changes
definition: An abnormal shift in patterns of thinking, acting, or feeling.

label: Hyperactivity
definition: Hyperactivity is a condition characterized by constant and unusually high levels of activity, even in situations where it is deemed inappropriate.

label: Agoraphobia
definition: A type of anxiety disorder characterized by the avoidance of public places, especially where crowds gather.

label: Phobia
definition: Extreme, irrational, and persistent fears of certain objects, situations, activities, or persons can impede functioning in day-to-day life.

label: Lack of insight
definition: Lack of insight (Anosognosia) is a neurological condition in which an individual is unaware of his or her own neurological deficit or psychiatric condition. Anosognosia can be associated with mental illness, dementia, and structural brain lesions and can affect an individual's conscious awareness of deficits involving judgment, emotions, memory, executive function, language skills, and motor ability.

label: Abnormal nonverbal communicative behavior
definition: Abnormalities in eye contact, communicative facial expressions, gesture use, or the use of others' bodies to communicate convey shared meanings within a culture that replace or supplement verbal communication.

label: Abnormal communication
definition: Presence of any form of communication (e.g., verbal or non-verbal) that does not align with cultural expectations or developmental level.

label: Abnormal peripheral nervous system morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the peripheral nervous system, which is composed of the nerves that lead to or branch off from the central nervous system. This includes the cranial nerves (olfactory and optic nerves are technically part of the central nervous system).

label: Abnormal nervous system morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the nervous system.

label: Decreased nerve conduction velocity
definition: A reduction in the speed at which electrical signals propagate along the axon of a neuron.

label: Sensory neuropathy
definition: Peripheral neuropathy affecting the sensory nerves.

label: Peripheral neuropathy
definition: Peripheral neuropathy is a general term for any disorder of the peripheral nervous system. The main clinical features used to classify peripheral neuropathy are distribution, type (mainly demyelinating versus mainly axonal), duration, and course.

label: Peripheral axonal degeneration
definition: Progressive deterioration of peripheral axons.

label: Abnormal thorax morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the thorax (the region of the body formed by the sternum, the thoracic vertebrae and the ribs).

label: Abnormal axial skeleton morphology
definition: An abnormality of the axial skeleton, which comprises the skull, the vertebral column, the ribs and the sternum.

label: Abnormal sternum morphology
definition: An anomaly of the sternum, also known as the breastbone.

label: Pectus excavatum
definition: A defect of the chest wall characterized by a depression of the sternum, giving the chest (pectus") a caved-in ("excavatum") appearance."

label: Pectus carinatum
definition: A deformity of the chest caused by overgrowth of the ribs and characterized by protrusion of the sternum.

label: Abnormality of the breast
definition: An abnormality of the breast.

label: Gynecomastia
definition: Abnormal development of large mammary glands in males resulting in breast enlargement.

label: Abnormal breast morphology
definition: Any anomaly of the structure of the breast.

label: Abnormal rib morphology
definition: An anomaly of the rib.

label: Abnormal rib cage morphology
definition: A morphological anomaly of the rib cage.

label: Short ribs
definition: Reduced rib length.

label: Narrow chest
definition: Reduced width of the chest from side to side, associated with a reduced distance from the sternal notch to the tip of the shoulder.

label: Abnormality of the diaphragm
definition: Any abnormality of the diaphragm, the sheet of skeletal muscle that separates the thoracic cavity from the abdominal cavity.

label: Congenital diaphragmatic hernia
definition: The presence of a hernia of the diaphragm present at birth.

label: Abnormal thymus morphology
definition: Abnormality of the thymus, an organ located in the upper anterior portion of the chest cavity just behind the sternum and whose main function is to provide an environment for T lymphocyte maturation.

label: Abnormality of the endocrine system
definition: An abnormality of the endocrine system.

label: Abnormality of the lymphatic system
definition: An anomaly of the lymphatic system, a network of lymphatic vessels that carry a clear fluid called lymph unidirectionally towards either the right lymphatic duct or the thoracic duct, which in turn drain into the right and left subclavian veins respectively.

label: Hypoplasia of the thymus
definition: Underdevelopment of the thymus.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the thymus
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the thymus.

label: Abnormal scapula morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the scapula, also known as the shoulder blade.

label: Nephrolithiasis
definition: The presence of calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

label: Hematuria
definition: The presence of blood in the urine. Hematuria may be gross hematuria (visible to the naked eye) or microscopic hematuria (detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine).

label: Abnormal urine cytology
definition: An anomalous finding in the examination of the urine for cells.

label: Uric acid nephrolithiasis
definition: The presence of uric acid-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

label: Membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis
definition: A type of glomerulonephritis characterized by diffuse mesangial cell proliferation and the thickening of capillary walls due to subendothelial extension of the mesangium. The term membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis is often employed to denote a general pattern of glomerular injury seen in a variety of disease processes that share a common pathogenetic mechanism, rather than to describe a single disease entity

label: IgA deposition in the glomerulus
definition: The presence of immunoglobulin A deposits in the glomerulus.

label: Glomerular deposits
definition: An abnormal accumulation of protein in the glomerulus.

label: Urethral obstruction
definition: Obstruction of the flow of urine through the urethra.

label: Oligozoospermia
definition: Reduced count of spermatozoa in the semen, defined as a sperm count below 20 million per milliliter semen.

label: Renal steatosis
definition: Abnormal fat accumulation in the kidneys.

label: Impotence
definition: Inability to develop or maintain an erection of the penis.

label: Erectile dysfunction
definition: A multidimensional but common male sexual dysfunction that involves an alteration in any of the components of the erectile response, including organic, relational and psychological.

label: Renal cortical cysts
definition: Cysts of the cortex of the kidney.

label: Xanthine nephrolithiasis
definition: The presence of xanthine-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

label: Enuresis
definition: Lack of the ability to control the urinary bladder leading to involuntary urination at an age where control of the bladder should already be possible.

label: Penoscrotal hypospadias
definition: A severe form of hypospadias in which the urethral opening is located at the junction of the penis and scrotum.

label: Urinary tract atresia
definition: Congenital absence of the normal opening of a structure of the urinary tract.

label: Abnormal reproductive system morphology
definition: A structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the genital system.

label: Bicornuate uterus
definition: The presence of a bicornuate uterus.

label: Hypergonadotropic hypogonadism
definition: Reduced function of the gonads (testes in males or ovaries in females) associated with excess pituitary gonadotropin secretion and resulting in delayed sexual development and growth delay.

label: Abnormality of Krebs cycle metabolism
definition: An abnormality of the tricarboxylic acid cycle.

label: Abnormal circulating enzyme concentration or activity
definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Reduced eye contact
definition: A reduced frequency or duration of eye contact.

label: Abnormal eye contact
definition: Any abnormality of eye contact behavior. We define eye contact as a form of nonverbal communication between two individuals who are facing each other in which an individual directs the eyes towards the eyes or face of the other individual. Eye contact occurs frequently and voluntarily during face-to-face verbal communication. The duration and frequency of eye contact that is interpreted to be appropriate may follow social and situational norms.

label: Diabetes mellitus
definition: A group of abnormalities characterized by hyperglycemia and glucose intolerance.

label: Glucose intolerance
definition: Glucose intolerance (GI) can be defined as dysglycemia that comprises both prediabetes and diabetes. It includes the conditions of impaired fasting glucose (IFG) and impaired glucose tolerance (IGT) and diabetes mellitus (DM).

label: Abnormality of the thyroid gland
definition: An abnormality of the thyroid gland.

label: Hypothyroidism
definition: Deficiency of thyroid hormone.

label: Abnormality of thyroid physiology
definition: An abnormal functionality of the thyroid gland.

label: Hypertension
definition: The presence of chronic increased pressure in the systemic arterial system.

label: Increased blood pressure
definition: Abnormal increase in blood pressure. An individual measurement of increased blood pressure does not necessarily imply hypertension. In practical terms, multiple measurements are recommended to diagnose the presence of hypertension.

label: Delayed puberty
definition: Passing the age when puberty normally occurs with no physical or hormonal signs of the onset of puberty.

label: Growth delay
definition: A deficiency or slowing down of growth pre- and postnatally.

label: Decreased response to growth hormone stimulation test
definition: Insufficient responses to growth hormone (GH) provocation tests. GH deficiency is defined as a serum peak GH concentration less than 10 ng/mL on provocation with a combination of at least two separate stimulation tests.

label: Anterior hypopituitarism
definition: A condition of reduced function of the anterior pituitary gland characterized by decreased secretion of one or more of the pituitary hormones growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, prolactin, luteinizing hormone, and follicle-stimulating hormone.

label: Abnormal response to endocrine stimulation test
definition: An anomalous response to a test that is designed to probe the function of the endocrine system.

label: Hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia
definition: An increased concentration of insulin combined with a decreased concentration of glucose in the blood.

label: Hyperinsulinemia
definition: An increased concentration of insulin in the blood.

label: Precocious puberty
definition: The onset of secondary sexual characteristics before a normal age. Although it is difficult to define normal age ranges because of the marked variation with which puberty begins in normal children, precocious puberty can be defined as the onset of puberty before the age of 8 years in girls or 9 years in boys.

label: Early onset of sexual maturation
definition: An early onset of puberty, in this case early does not refer to precocious.

label: Abnormality of the parathyroid gland
definition: An abnormality of the parathyroid gland.

label: Hypoparathyroidism
definition: A condition caused by a deficiency of parathyroid hormone characterized by hypocalcemia and hyperphosphatemia.

label: Abnormality of the parathyroid physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the parathyroid gland.

label: Insulin-resistant diabetes mellitus
definition: A type of diabetes mellitus related not to lack of insulin but rather to lack of response to insulin on the part of the target tissues of insulin such as muscle, fat, and liver cells. This type of diabetes is typically associated with increases both in blood glucose concentrations as well as in fasting and postprandial serum insulin levels.

label: Insulin resistance
definition: Increased resistance towards insulin, that is, diminished effectiveness of insulin in reducing blood glucose levels.

label: Primary hypothyroidism
definition: A type of hypothyroidism that results from a defect in the thyroid gland.

label: Abnormality of the adrenal glands
definition: Abnormality of the adrenal glands, i.e., of the endocrine glands located at the top of the kindneys.

label: Adrenal hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the adrenal glands.

label: Abnormal adrenal morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the adrenal glands.

label: Hyperthyroidism
definition: An abnormality of thyroid physiology characterized by excessive secretion of the thyroid hormones thyroxine (i.e., T4) and/or 3,3',5-triiodo-L-thyronine zwitterion (i.e., triiodothyronine or T3).

label: Increased circulating gonadotropin level
definition: Overproduction of gonadotropins (FSH, LH) by the anterior pituitary gland.

label: Hyperpituitarism
definition: Hypersecretion of one or more pituitary hormones. This can occur in conditions in which deficiency in the target organ leads to decreased hormonal feedback, or as a primary condition most usually in connection with a pituitary adenoma.

label: Abnormal circulating gonadotropin concentration
definition: An anomaly of the circulating level of a gonadotropin, that is, of a protein hormone secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary of vertebrates. The primary gonadotropins are luteinizing hormone (LH) and follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

label: Pituitary dwarfism
definition: A type of reduced stature with normal proportions related to dysfunction of the pituitary gland related to either an isolated defect in the secretion of growth hormone or to panhypopituitarism, i.e., a deficit of all the anterior pituitary hormones.

label: Short stature
definition: A height below that which is expected according to age and gender norms. Although there is no universally accepted definition of short stature, many refer to short stature" as height more than 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender (or below the 3rd percentile for age and gender dependent norms)."

label: Adrenogenital syndrome
definition: Adrenogenital syndrome is also known as congenital adrenal hyperplasia, which results from disorders of steroid hormone production in the adrenal glands leading to a deficiency of cortisol. The pituitary gland reacts by increased secretion of corticotropin, which in turn causes the adrenal glands to overproduce certain intermediary hormones which have testosterone-like effects.

label: Hyperactive renin-angiotensin system
definition: An abnormally increased activity of the renin-angiotensin system, causing hypertension by a combination of volume excess and vasoconstrictor mechanisms.

label: Abnormality of renin-angiotensin system
definition: An abnormality of the renin-angiotensin system.

label: Abnormal glucose homeostasis
definition: Abnormality of glucose homeostasis.

label: Abnormal circulating insulin concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of insulin in the body.

label: Hyperparathyroidism
definition: Excessive production of parathyroid hormone (PTH) by the parathyroid glands.

label: Elevated circulating growth hormone concentration
definition: Acromegaly is a condition resulting from overproduction of growth hormone by the pituitary gland in persons with closed epiphyses, and consists chiefly in the enlargement of the distal parts of the body. The circumference of the skull increases, the nose becomes broad, the tongue becomes enlarged, the facial features become coarsened, the mandible grows excessively, and the teeth become separated. The fingers and toes grow chiefly in thickness.

label: Abnormal growth hormone level
definition: Any deviation from the normal level of growth hormone (GH) in the blood circulation. GH or somatotropin is a peptide hormone that stimulates growth, cell reproduction, and cell regeneration. Its secretion from the pituitary is regulated by the neurosecretory nuclei of the hypothalamus, which can release Growth hormone-releasing hormone (GHRH or somatocrinin) and Growth hormone-inhibiting hormone (GHIH or somatostatin) into the hypophyseal portal venous blood surrounding the pituitary. GH is secreted in a pulsatile manner, which is one of the reasons why an isolated measurement of its blood concentration is not meaningful.

label: Adrenal insufficiency
definition: Insufficient production of steroid hormones (primarily cortisol) by the adrenal glands.

label: Abnormality of adrenal physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the adrenal glands.

label: Increased circulating renin concentration
definition: An increased level of renin in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating renin concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of renin in the blood, a central hormone in the control of blood pressure and various other physiological functions.

label: Congenital hypothyroidism
definition: A type of hypothyroidism with congenital onset.

label: Pseudohypoparathyroidism
definition: A condition characterized by resistance to the action of parathyroid hormone, in which there is hypocalcemia, hyperphosphatemia, and (appropriately) high levels of parathyroid hormone.

label: Goiter
definition: An enlargement of the thyroid gland.

label: Abnormal thyroid morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the thyroid gland.

label: Thyroid adenoma
definition: The presence of a adenoma of the thyroid gland.

label: Neoplasm of the thyroid gland
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the thyroid gland.

label: Irregular menstruation
definition: Abnormally high variation in the amount of time between periods.

label: Increased circulating aldosterone concentration
definition: Overproduction of the mineralocorticoid aldosterone by the adrenal cortex.

label: Parathyroid hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the parathyroid gland.

label: Parathyroid dysgenesis
definition: Abnormal embryonic development of the parathyroid gland.

label: Central diabetes insipidus
definition: A form of diabetes insipidus related to a failure of vasopressin (AVP) release from the hypothalamus.

label: Diabetes insipidus
definition: A state of excessive water intake and hypotonic (dilute) polyuria. Diabetes insipidus may be due to failure of vasopressin (AVP) release (central or neurogenic diabetes insipidus) or to a failure of the kidney to respond to AVP (nephrogenic diabetes insipidus).

label: Abnormality of the hypothalamus-pituitary axis
definition: Abnormality of the pituitary gland (also known as hypophysis), which is an endocrine gland that protrudes from the bottom of the hypothalamus at the base of the brain. The pituitary gland secretes the hormones ACTH, TSH, PRL, GH, endorphins, FSH, LH, oxytocin, and antidiuretic hormone. The secretion of hormones from the anterior pituitary is under the strict control of hypothalamic hormones, and the posterior pituitary is essentially an extension of the hypothalamus, so that hypothalamus and pituitary gland may be regarded as a functional unit.

label: Euthyroid goiter
definition: A goiter that is not associated with functional thyroid abnormalities.

label: Secondary hyperparathyroidism
definition: Secondary hyperparathyroidism refers to the production of higher than normal levels of parathyroid hormone in the presence of hypocalcemia.

label: Increased circulating prolactin concentration
definition: The presence of abnormally increased levels of prolactin in the blood. Prolactin is a peptide hormone produced by the anterior pituitary gland that plays a role in breast development and lactation during pregnancy.

label: Panhypopituitarism
definition: A pituitary functional deficit affecting all the anterior pituitary hormones (growth hormone, thyroid-stimulating hormone, follicle-stimulating hormone, luteinizing hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, and prolactin).

label: Hashimoto thyroiditis
definition: A chronic, autoimmune type of thyroiditis associated with hypothyroidism.

label: Autoimmunity
definition: The occurrence of an immune reaction against the organism's own cells or tissues.

label: Thyroiditis
definition: Inflammation of the thyroid gland.

label: Oligomenorrhea
definition: Infrequent menses (less than 6 per year or more than 35 days between cycles).

label: 11 pairs of ribs
definition: Presence of only 11 pairs of ribs.

label: Missing ribs
definition: A developmental anomaly with absence of one or more ribs.

label: Short sternum
definition: Decreased inferosuperior length of the sternum.

label: Hypoplastic scapulae
definition: Underdeveloped scapula.

label: Thin ribs
definition: Ribs with a reduced diameter.

label: Broad ribs
definition: Increased width of ribs

label: Deformed rib cage
definition: Malformation of the rib cage.

label: Cupped ribs
definition: Wide, concave rib end.

label: Horizontal ribs
definition: A horizontal (flat) conformation of the ribs, the long curved bones that form the rib cage and normally progressively oblique (slanted) from ribs 1 through 9, then less slanted through rib 12.

label: Abnormal clavicle morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the clavicles (collar bones).

label: Long clavicles
definition: Increased length of the clavicles.

label: Supernumerary ribs
definition: The presence of more than 12 rib pairs.

label: Bifid ribs
definition: A bifid rib refers to cleavage of the sternal end of a rib, usually unilateral. Bifid ribs are usually asymptomatic, and are often discovered incidentally by chest x-ray.

label: Bulging of the costochondral junction
definition: Abnormal outward curving (protuberance) of the junction of ribs and costal cartilage.

label: Abnormality of the costochondral junction
definition: Any anomaly of the costochondral junction. The costochondral junctions are located between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum.

label: Short clavicles
definition: Reduced length of the clavicles.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the clavicles
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the clavicles (collar bones).

label: Lateral clavicle hook
definition: An excessive upward convexity of the lateral clavicle.

label: Rib exostoses
definition: Multiple circumscribed bony excrescences located in the ribs.

label: Exostoses
definition: An exostosis is a benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface. It is capped by cartilage, and arises from a bone that develops from cartilage.

label: Rachitic rosary
definition: A row of beadlike prominences at the junction of a rib and its cartilage (i.e., enlarged costochondral joints), resembling a rosary. Note that rachitic rosary would have one bead per rib (a swelling at the costochondral junction), while beaded ribs in the context of multiple rib fractures have multiple beads (fractures) along the same rib.

label: Thickened ribs
definition: Increased thickness (diameter) of ribs.

label: Rib fusion
definition: Complete or partial merging of adjacent ribs.

label: Flaring of rib cage
definition: The presence of wide, concave anterior rib ends.

label: Progressive clavicular acroosteolysis
definition: Progressive bone resorption in the distal part of the clavicle.

label: Osteolysis
definition: Osteolysis refers to the destruction of bone through bone resorption with removal or loss of calcium.

label: Anterior rib cupping
definition: Wide, concave anterior rib end.

label: Flat glenoid fossa
definition: Abnormally flat configuration of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus.

label: Abnormality of the glenoid fossa
definition: An anomaly of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus.

label: Sprengel anomaly
definition: A congenital skeletal deformity characterized by the elevation of one scapula (thus, one scapula is located superior to the other).

label: Posterior rib fusion
definition: Complete or partial merging of the posterior part of adjacent ribs.

label: Shield chest
definition: A broad chest.

label: Pectus excavatum of inferior sternum
definition: Pectus excavatum (defect of the chest wall characterized by depression of the sternum) affecting primarily the inferior region of the sternum.

label: Broad clavicles
definition: Increased width (cross-sectional diameter) of the clavicles.

label: Superior pectus carinatum
definition: Pectus carinatum affecting primarily the superior part of the sternum.

label: Scapular exostoses
definition: The presence of multiple exostoses on the scapula. An exostosis is a benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface. It is capped by cartilage.

label: Enlargement of the costochondral junction
definition: Abnormally increased size of the costochondral junctions, which are located between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum.

label: Posterior rib cupping
definition: Wide, concave posterior rib end.

label: Abnormality of the skeletal system
definition: An abnormality of the skeletal system.

label: Abnormality of the musculoskeletal system
definition: An anomaly of the musculoskeletal system, which consists of the bones of the skeleton, muscles, cartilage, tendons, ligaments, joints, and other connective tissue. The musculoskeletal system supports the weight of the body, maintains body position and produces movements of the body or of parts of the body.

label: Abnormality of the vertebral column
definition: Any abnormality of the vertebral column.

label: Platyspondyly
definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates.

label: Abnormal form of the vertebral bodies
definition: Abnormal morphology of vertebral body.

label: Abnormality of skeletal maturation
definition: The bones of the skeleton undergo a series of characteristic changes in size, shape, and calcification from fetal life until puberty. An abnormality of this process can include delayed or accelerated skeletal maturation, or deviation of some, but not all bones from the expected patterns of maturation.

label: Abnormal musculoskeletal physiology
definition: An abnormality of the function of the skeletal system.

label: Elevated imprint of the transverse sinuses
Abnormal skull base morphology
definition: An abnormality of the base of the skull, which forms the floor of the cranial cavity and separates the brain from other facial structures. The skull base is made up of five bones: the ethmoid, sphenoid, occipital, paired frontal, and paired parietal bones, and is subdivided into 3 regions: the anterior, middle, and posterior cranial fossae. The petro-occipital fissure subdivides the middle cranial fossa into 1 central component and 2 lateral components.

label: Thinning and bulging of the posterior fossa bones
Abnormal posterior cranial fossa morphology
definition: An abnormality of the fossa cranii posterior (the posterior fossa), which is made up primarily of the occipital bone and which surrounds to the foramen magnum.

label: Posterior fossa cyst at the fourth ventricle
Posterior fossa cyst
definition: A discrete posterior fossa cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) collection that does not communicate directly with the fourth ventricle.

label: Chondrocalcinosis
definition: Radiographic evidence of articular calcification that represent calcium pyrophosphate depositions in soft tissue surrounding joints and at the insertions of tendons near joints (Entheses/Sharpey fibers) .

label: Abnormal joint morphology
definition: An abnormal structure or form of the joints, i.e., one or more of the articulations where two bones join.

label: Ectopic calcification
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in a tissue or location in which calcification does not normally occur.

label: Abnormal Sharpey fiber morphology
definition: An abnormality of Sharpey's fibers (bone fibers, or perforating fibers), which are a matrix of connective tissue consisting of bundles of strong collagenous fibers connecting periosteum to bone.

label: Thickened cortex of long bones
definition: Abnormal thickening of the cortex of long bones.

label: Abnormal long bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of size or shape of the long bones.

label: Thickened cortex of bones
definition: An Abnormality of cortical bone leading to an abnormal thickness of the cortex of affected bones.

label: Osteopenia
definition: Osteopenia is a term to define bone density that is not normal but also not as low as osteoporosis. By definition from the World Health Organization osteopenia is defined by bone densitometry as a T score -1 to -2.5.

label: Reduced bone mineral density
definition: A reduction of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones.

label: Osteoporosis
definition: Osteoporosis is a systemic skeletal disease characterized by low bone density and microarchitectural deterioration of bone tissue with a consequent increase in bone fragility. According to the WHO criteria, osteoporosis is defined as a BMD that lies 2.5 standard deviations or more below the average value for young healthy adults (a T-score below -2.5 SD).

label: Abnormal diaphysis morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure or form of the diaphysis, i.e., of the main or mid-section (shaft) of a long bone.

label: Abnormal limb bone morphology
definition: Any abnormality of bones of the arms or legs.

label: Abnormal skeletal morphology
definition: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.

label: Abnormal metaphysis morphology
definition: An abnormality of one or more metaphysis, i.e., of the somewhat wider portion of a long bone that is adjacent to the epiphyseal growth plate and grows during childhood.

label: Hypoplastic ilia
definition: Underdevelopment of the ilium.

label: Abnormal ilium morphology
definition: An abnormality of the ilium, the largest and uppermost bone of the pelvis.

label: Dumbbell-shaped long bone
definition: An abnormal appearance of the long bones with resemblance to a dumbbell, a short bar with a weight at each end. That is, the long bone is shortened and displays flaring (widening) of the metaphyses.

label: Metaphyseal widening
definition: Abnormal widening of the metaphyseal regions of long bones.

label: Abnormality of the skin
definition: An abnormality of the skin.

label: Abnormality of the integument
definition: An abnormality of the integument, which consists of the skin and the superficial fascia.

label: Jaundice
definition: Yellow pigmentation of the skin due to bilirubin, which in turn is the result of increased bilirubin concentration in the bloodstream.

label: Cholestasis
definition: Impairment of bile flow due to obstruction in bile ducts.

label: Hyperpigmentation of the skin
definition: A darkening of the skin related to an increase in melanin production and deposition.

label: Abnormality of skin pigmentation
definition: An abnormality of the pigmentation of the skin.

label: Single transverse palmar crease
definition: The distal and proximal transverse palmar creases are merged into a single transverse palmar crease.

label: Abnormality of the palmar creases
definition: An abnormality of the creases of the skin of palm of hand.

label: Acanthosis nigricans
definition: A dermatosis characterized by thickened, hyperpigmented plaques, typically on the intertriginous surfaces and neck.

label: Epidermal thickening
definition: Thickening of the epidermal layer of the skin.

label: Cafe-au-lait spot
definition: Cafe-au-lait spots are hyperpigmented lesions that can vary in color from light brown to dark brown with smooth borders and having a size of 1.5 cm or more in adults and 0.5 cm or more in children.

label: Hypermelanotic macule
definition: A hyperpigmented circumscribed area of change in normal skin color without elevation or depression of any size.

label: Dry skin
definition: Skin characterized by the lack of natural or normal moisture.

label: Abnormal skin morphology
definition: Any morphological abnormality of the skin.

label: Sacral dimple
definition: A cutaneous indentation resulting from tethering of the skin to underlying structures (bone) of the intergluteal cleft.

label: Sacrococcygeal pilonidal abnormality
definition: The presence of a cyst, fistula, or abscess in the sacrococcygeal region (gluteal crease) characteristically accompanied by hair and skin folds.

label: Skin dimple
definition: Skin dimples are cutaneous indentations that are the result of tethering of the skin to underlying structures (bone) causing an indentation.

label: Cyanosis
definition: Bluish discoloration of the skin and mucosa due to poor circulation or inadequate oxygenation of arterial or capillary blood.

label: Thin skin
definition: Reduction in thickness of the skin, generally associated with a loss of suppleness and elasticity of the skin.

label: Eczematoid dermatitis
definition: Eczema is a form of dermatitis that is characterized by scaly, pruritic, erythematous lesions located on flexural surfaces.

label: Inflammatory abnormality of the skin
definition: The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes.

label: Cutis marmorata
definition: A reticular discoloration of the skin with cyanotic (reddish-blue appearing) areas surrounding pale central areas due to dilation of capillary blood vessels and stagnation of blood within the vessels. Cutis marmorata generally occurs on the legs, arms and trunk and is often more severe in cold weather.

label: Hypohidrosis
definition: Abnormally diminished capacity to sweat.

label: Petechiae
definition: Petechiae are pinpoint-sized reddish/purple spots, resembling a rash, that appear just under the skin or a mucous membrane when capillaries have ruptured and some superficial bleeding into the skin has happened. This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to developing petechiae.

label: Macular purpura
definition: Purpura that is flat (non-palpable, not raised).

label: Ectodermal dysplasia
definition: Ectodermal dysplasia is a group of conditions in which there is abnormal development of the skin, hair, nails, teeth, or sweat glands.

label: Generalized abnormality of skin
definition: An abnormality of the skin that is not localized to any one particular region.

label: Abnormality of fluid regulation
definition: An abnormality of the regulation of body fluids.

label: Anhidrosis
definition: Inability to sweat.

label: Abnormality of skin adnexa physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands.

label: Abnormal sweat gland morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the sweat gland.

label: Abnormal skin adnexa morphology
definition: An abnormality of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands.

label: Palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Abnormal thickening of the skin localized to the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot.

label: Plantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Hyperkeratosis affecting the sole of the foot.

label: Palmar hyperkeratosis
definition: Abnormal thickening of the skin localized to the palm of the hand.

label: Cutis laxa
definition: Wrinkled, redundant, inelastic and sagging skin.

label: Hyperextensible skin
definition: A condition in which the skin can be stretched beyond normal, and then returns to its initial position.

label: Hyperhidrosis
definition: Abnormal excessive perspiration (sweating) despite the lack of appropriate stimuli like hot and humid weather.

label: Soft skin
definition: Subjective impression of increased softness upon palpation of the skin.

label: Abnormal elasticity of skin
