definition: Any abnormal increase or reduction in skin elasticity.

label: Bruising susceptibility
definition: An ecchymosis (bruise) refers to the skin discoloration caused by the escape of blood into the tissues from ruptured blood vessels. This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to bruising. The corresponding phenotypic abnormality is generally elicited on medical history as a report of frequent ecchymoses or bruising without adequate trauma.

label: Subcutaneous hemorrhage
definition: This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to bruising (purpura, petechiae, or ecchymoses).

label: Purpura
definition: Purpura (from Latin: purpura, meaning purple) is the appearance of red or purple discolorations on the skin that do not blanch on applying pressure. They are caused by bleeding underneath the skin. This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to developing purpura. Purpura are larger than petechiae.

label: Pallor
definition: Abnormally pale skin.

label: Palmoplantar keratoderma
definition: Abnormal thickening of the skin of the palms of the hands and the soles of the feet.

label: Atypical scarring of skin
definition: Atypically scarred skin .

label: Localized skin lesion
definition: A lesion of the skin that is located in a specific region rather than being generalized.

label: Skin rash
definition: A red eruption of the skin.

label: Pruritus
definition: Pruritus is an itch or a sensation that makes a person want to scratch. This term refers to an abnormally increased disposition to experience pruritus.

label: Abnormality of skin physiology
definition: Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin.

label: Xanthomatosis
definition: The presence of multiple xanthomas (xanthomata) in the skin. Xanthomas are yellowish, firm, lipid-laden nodules in the skin.

label: Cutaneous photosensitivity
definition: An increased sensitivity of the skin to light. Photosensitivity may result in a rash upon exposure to the sun (which is known as photodermatosis). Photosensitivity can be diagnosed by phototests in which light is shone on small areas of skin.

label: Molluscoid pseudotumors
definition: Bluish-grey, spongy nodules associated with scars over pressure points and easily traumatized areas like the elbows and knees.

label: Melanocytic nevus
definition: A oval and round, colored (usually medium-to dark brown, reddish brown, or flesh colored) lesion. Typically, a melanocytic nevus is less than 6 mm in diameter, but may be much smaller or larger.

label: Nevus
definition: A nevus is a type of hamartoma that is a circumscribed stable malformation of the skin.

label: Facial capillary hemangioma
definition: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells with small endothelial spaces, occurring in the face.

label: Capillary hemangioma
definition: The presence of a capillary hemangioma, which are hemangiomas with small endothelial spaces.

label: Axillary freckling
definition: The presence in the axillary region (armpit) of an increased number of freckles, small circular spots on the skin that are darker than the surrounding skin because of deposits of melanin.

label: Freckling
definition: The presence of an increased number of freckles, small circular spots on the skin that are darker than the surrounding skin because of deposits of melanin.

label: Hypertrichosis
definition: Hypertrichosis is increased hair growth that is abnormal in quantity or location.

label: Abnormal hair quantity
definition: An abnormal amount of hair.

label: Pyoderma
definition: Any manifestation of a skin disease associated with the production of pus.

label: Recurrent bacterial skin infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to bacterial infections of the skin, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infectious dermatitis.

label: Multiple lentigines
definition: Presence of an unusually high number of lentigines (singular: lentigo), which are flat, tan to brown oval spots.

label: Lymphedema
definition: Localized fluid retention and tissue swelling caused by a compromised lymphatic system.

label: Hirsutism
definition: Abnormally increased hair growth referring to a male pattern of body hair (androgenic hair).

label: Abnormality of dermal melanosomes
definition: An abnormality of the melanosomes, i.e., of the cellular organelles in which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored within melanocytes (the cells that produce pigment in the dermis).

label: Telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectasias refer to small dilated blood vessels located near the surface of the skin or mucous membranes, measuring between 0.5 and 1 millimeter in diameter. Telangiectasia are located especially on the tongue, lips, palate, fingers, face, conjunctiva, trunk, nail beds, and fingertips.

label: Hypopigmentation of the skin
definition: A reduction of skin color related to a decrease in melanin production and deposition.

label: Multiple lipomas
definition: The presence of multiple lipomas (a type of benign tissue made of fatty tissue).

label: Eruptive xanthomas
definition: Eruptive xanthomas are yellow-orange-to-red-brown papules that are often surrounded by an erythematous halo. They appear in crops on the buttocks, extensor surfaces of the extremities, and flexural creases. Acutely, variable amounts of pruritus and pain occur.

label: Angiokeratoma
definition: Angiokeratomas are hyperkeratotic papules that are characterized histologically by superficial ectatic (i.e., dilated) blood vessels with epidermal proliferation. Clinically, angiokeratoma presents as a small, raised, dark-red spot.

label: Prominent superficial veins
definition: A condition in which superficial veins (i.e., veins just under the skin) are more conspicuous or noticeable than normal.

label: Abnormal venous morphology
definition: An anomaly of vein.

label: Anemic pallor
definition: A type of pallor that is secondary to the presence of anemia.

label: Abnormal palmar dermatoglyphics
definition: An abnormality of the dermatoglyphs, i.e., an abnormality of the patterns of ridges of the skin of palm of hand.

label: Abnormal dermatoglyphics
definition: An abnormality of dermatoglyphs (fingerprints), which are present on fingers, palms, toes, and soles.

label: Abnormal skin morphology of the palm
definition: An abnormality of the skin of the palm, that is, the skin of the front of the hand.

label: Erythroderma
definition: An inflammatory exfoliative dermatosis involving nearly all of the surface of the skin. Erythroderma develops suddenly. A patchy erythema may generalize and spread to affect most of the skin. Scaling may appear in 2-6 days and be accompanied by hot, red, dry skin, malaise, and fever.

label: Albinism
definition: An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation (reduced or absent) of skin, hair and eye (iris and retina).

label: Skin dimple over apex of long bone angulation
Urticaria
definition: Raised, well-circumscribed areas of erythema and edema involving the dermis and epidermis. Urticaria is intensely pruritic, and blanches completely with pressure.

label: Skin ulcer
definition: A discontinuity of the skin exhibiting complete loss of the epidermis and often portions of the dermis and even subcutaneous fat.

label: Soft, doughy skin
definition: A skin texture that is unusually soft (and may feel silky), and has a malleable consistency resembling that of dough.

label: Vascular neoplasm
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumor) originating in the vascular system.

label: Poikiloderma
definition: Poikiloderma refers to a patch of skin with (1) reticulated hypopigmentation and hyperpigmentation, (2) wrinkling secondary to epidermal atrophy, and (3) telangiectasias.

label: Fragile skin
definition: Skin that splits easily with minimal injury.

label: Subcutaneous lipoma
definition: The presence of subcutaneous lipoma.

label: Neoplasm of the skin
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skin.

label: Absent distal interphalangeal creases
definition: Absence of the distal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fingers.

label: Absent phalangeal crease
definition: Absence of one or more interphalangeal creases (i.e., of the transverse lines in the skin between the phalanges of the fingers).

label: Flushing
definition: Recurrent episodes of redness of the skin together with a sensation of warmth or burning of the affected areas of skin.

label: Macule
definition: A flat, distinct, discolored area of skin less than 1 cm wide that does not involve any change in the thickness or texture of the skin.

label: Parakeratosis
definition: Abnormal formation of the keratinocytes of the epidermis characterized by persistence of nuclei, incomplete formation of keratin, and moistness and swelling of the keratinocytes.

label: Pterygium
definition: Pterygia are 'winglike' triangular membranes occurring in the neck, eyes, knees, elbows, ankles or digits.

label: Facial erythema
definition: Redness of the skin of the face, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.

label: Erythema
definition: Redness of the skin, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.

label: Abnormal scalp morphology
definition: Any anomaly of the scalp, the skin an subcutaneous tissue of the head on which head hair grows.

label: Intermittent jaundice
definition: Jaundice that is sometimes present, sometimes not.

label: Atopic dermatitis
definition: Atopic dermatitis (AD) or atopic eczema is an itchy, inflammatory skin condition with a predilection for the skin flexures. It is characterized by poorly defined erythema with edema, vesicles, and weeping in the acute stage and skin thickening (lichenification) in the chronic stage.

label: Cavernous hemangioma
definition: The presence of a cavernous hemangioma. A hemangioma characterized by large endothelial spaces (caverns) is called a cavernous hemangioma.

label: Absent dorsal skin creases over affected joints
Abnormal finger flexion crease
definition: Anomalous flexion crease (i.e., a transverse line that crosses the skin of a finger).

label: Seborrheic dermatitis
definition: Seborrheic dermatitis is a form of eczema which is closely related to dandruff. It causes dry or greasy peeling of the scalp, eyebrows, and face, and sometimes trunk.

label: Nevus flammeus
definition: A congenital vascular malformation consisting of superficial and deep dilated capillaries in the skin which produce a reddish to purplish discolouration of the skin.

label: Capillary malformation
definition: A capillary malformation is a flat, sharply defined vascular stain of the skin. It may cover a large surface area or it may be scattered and appear as little islands of color. In a capillary maformation, the predominant vessels are small, slow-flow vessels (i.e., arterioles and postcapillary venules).

label: Erysipelas
definition: Increased susceptibility to erysipelas, as manifested by a medical history of repeated episodes of erysipelas, which is a superficial infection of the skin, typically involving the lymphatic system.

label: Milia
definition: Presence of multiple small cysts containing keratin (skin protein) and presenting as tiny pearly-white bumps just under the surface of the skin.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin in multiple or solitary non-inflammatory, well-demarcated, oval or circular ulcers with a diameter of about 1 to 2 cm. Aplasia cutis congenita most commonly occurs on the scalp, but may present in the face, trunk, or limbs.

label: Poor wound healing
definition: A reduced ability to heal cutaneous wounds.

label: Regional abnormality of skin
definition: An abnormality of the skin that is restricted to a particular body region.

label: Axillary pterygium
definition: Presence of a cutaneous membrane (flap) in the armpit.

label: Acne
definition: A skin condition in which there is an increase in sebum secretion by the pilosebaceous apparatus associated with open comedones (blackheads), closed comedones (whiteheads), and pustular nodules (papules, pustules, and cysts).

label: Atypical nevus
definition: A large pigmented lesion measuring 5-15 mm in diameter with irregular, notched, and ill defined border and with color that may range from tan to dark brown to pink.

label: Acrocyanosis
definition: Bluish discoloration of the skin of the hands or feet.

label: Peripheral cyanosis
definition: Bluish discoloration of the distal extremities in the absence of cold temperature or stress. Peripheral cyanosis can involve hands, fingertips, or toes, and sometimes circumoral and periorbital areas. Mucous membranes are generally not involved.

label: Striae distensae
definition: Thinned, erythematous, depressed bands of atrophic skin. Initially, striae appear as flattened and thinned, pinkish linear regions of the skin. Striae tend to enlarge in length and become reddish or purplish. Later, striae tend to appear as white, depressed bands that are parallel to the lines of skin tension. Striae distensae occur most often in areas that have been subject to distension such as the lower back, buttocks, thighs, breast, abdomen, and shoulders.

label: Dermal atrophy
definition: Partial or complete wasting (atrophy) of the skin.

label: Neurofibroma
definition: A benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor that generally appears as a soft, skin-colored papule or small subcutaneous nodule. Individuals with neurofibromatosis can have numerous neurofibromas.

label: Neoplasm of the peripheral nervous system
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumor) of the peripheral nervous system.

label: Episodic hyperhidrosis
definition: Intermittent episodes of abnormally increased perspiration.

label: Mottled pigmentation
definition: Patchy and irregular skin pigmentation.

label: Angiokeratoma corporis diffusum
definition: Angiokeratoma corporis diffusum (ACD) is typically characterized by innumerable small red to black papules which occur in clusters and are situated symmetrically in the bathing trunks area. The number of lesions and the extension of the body increase steadily with time so that generalization and mucosal involvement are common. The single lesion begins with a minute reddish papule which enlarges to up to 10 mm in diameter, becomes dark red to black with a discrete keratotic overgrowth. Histologically, the papules are characterized by superficial dilated capillaries in papillary dermis with epidermal proliferation.

label: Thickened skin
definition: Laminar thickening of skin.

label: Cigarette-paper scars
definition: Thin (atrophic) and wide scars.

label: Atrophic scars
definition: Scars that form a depression compared to the level of the surrounding skin because of damage to the collagen, fat or other tissues below the skin.

label: Atypical nevi in non-sun exposed areas
Biliary tract abnormality
definition: An abnormality of the biliary tree.

label: Abnormality of the biliary system
definition: An abnormality of the biliary system.

label: Cholelithiasis
definition: Hard, pebble-like deposits that form within the gallbladder.

label: Abnormal gallbladder morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the gallbladder.

label: Cholecystitis
definition: The presence of inflammatory changes in the gallbladder.

label: Abnormal gallbladder physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the gallbladder.

label: Ectopia lentis
definition: Dislocation or malposition of the crystalline lens of the eye. A partial displacement (or dislocation) of the lens is described as a subluxation of the lens, while a complete displacement is termed luxation of the lens. A complete displacement occurs if the lens is completely outside the patellar fossa of the lens, either in the anterior chamber, in the vitreous, or directly on the retina. If the lens is partially displaced but still contained within the lens space, then it is termed subluxation.

label: Corneal arcus
definition: A hazy, grayish-white ring about 2 mm in width located close to but separated from the limbus (the corneoscleral junction). Corneal arcus generally occurs bilaterally, and is related to lipid deposition in the cornea. Corneal arcus can occur in elderly persons as a part of the aging process but may be associated with hypercholesterolemia in people under the age of 50 years.

label: Peripheral opacification of the cornea
definition: Reduced transparency of the peripheral region of the cornea.

label: Papilledema
definition: Papilledema refers to edema (swelling) of the optic disc secondary to any factor which increases cerebral spinal fluid pressure.

label: Brushfield spots
definition: The presence of whitish spots in a ring-like arrangement at the periphery of the iris.

label: Iris atrophy
definition: Loss of iris tissue (atrophy)

label: Absent lacrimal punctum
definition: No identifiable superior and/or inferior lacrimal punctum.

label: Abnormal lacrimal punctum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lacrimal punctum, an opening on the eyelid close to the medial canthus that drains tears from the conjunctival sac into the lacrimal duct in the same eyelid.

label: Optic nerve dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the optic nerve.

label: Iridocyclitis
definition: A type of anterior uveitis, in which there is Inflammation of the iris and the ciliary body.

label: Anterior uveitis
definition: Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the anterior chamber.

label: Keratoconjunctivitis
definition: Inflammation of the cornea and conjunctiva.

label: Keratoconjunctivitis sicca
definition: Dryness of the eye related to deficiency of the tear film components (aqueous, mucin, or lipid), lid surface abnormalities, or epithelial abnormalities. Keratoconjunctivitis sicca often results in a scratchy or sandy sensation (foreign body sensation) in the eyes, and may also be associated with itching, inability to produce tears, photosensitivity, redness, pain, and difficulty in moving the eyelids.

label: Heterochromia iridis
definition: Heterochromia iridis is a difference in the color of the iris in the two eyes.

label: Asymmetry of iris pigmentation
definition: Asymmetry between the two irides or asymmetry between different parts of one iris.

label: Iritis
definition: Inflammation of the iris.

label: Angioid streaks of the fundus
definition: Irregular lines in the deep retina that are typically configured in a radiating fashion and emanate from the optic disc. Angioid streaks are crack-like dehiscences in abnormally thickened and calcified Bruch's membrane, resulting in atrophy of the overlying retinal pigment epithelium. They may be associated with a number of endocrine, metabolic, and connective tissue abnormalities but are frequently idiopathic.

label: Macular hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the macula lutea.

label: Retinal atrophy
definition: Well-demarcated area(s) of partial or complete depigmentation in the fundus, reflecting atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium with associated retinal photoreceptor loss.

label: Periorbital hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased pigmentation of the skin in the region surrounding the orbit of the eye.

label: Ocular albinism
definition: An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation (reduced or absent) of the iris and retina.

label: Iris hypopigmentation
definition: An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation of the iris.

label: Leber optic atrophy
definition: Degeneration of retinal ganglion cells and their axons.

label: Xanthelasma
definition: The presence of xanthomata in the skin of the eyelid.

label: Nodular changes affecting the eyelids
definition: Nodular changes affecting the eyelids may have many different causes such as cystic lesions (chalaziae, hordeolae), lipogranulomas, melanomas, infectious diseases (Molluscum contagiosum) and many more.

label: Posterior polar cataract
definition: A polar cataract that affects the posterior pole of the lens.

label: Polar cataract
definition: A type of Congenital cataract in which the opacities occupy the subcapsular cortex at the anterior or posterior pole of the lens.

label: Macular coloboma
definition: A congenital defect of the macula distinct from coloboma associated with optic fissure closure defects. Macular coloboma is characterized by a sharply defined, rather large defect in the central area of the fundus that is oval or round, and coarsely pigmented.

label: Sudden loss of visual acuity
definition: Severe loss of visual acuity within hours or days. This is characteristic of Leber hereditary optic neuropathy.

label: Juvenile cataract
definition: A type of cataract that is not apparent at birth but that arises in childhood or adolescence.

label: Keratoglobus
definition: Limbus-to-limbus corneal thinning, often greatest in the periphery, with globular protrusion of the cornea.

label: Transient unilateral blurring of vision
definition: Transient blurring of vision associated with the aura phase of migraine.

label: Cryptophthalmos
definition: Cryptophthalmos is a condition of total absence of eyelids and the skin of forehead is continuous with that of cheek, in which the eyeball is completely concealed by the skin, which is stretched over the orbital cavity.

label: Trichiasis
definition: Inversion and rubbing of the eyelashes against the globe of the eye.

label: Corneal dystrophy
definition: The term corneal dystrophy embraces a heterogenous group of bilateral genetically determined non-inflammatory corneal diseases that are restricted to the cornea.

label: Lens subluxation
definition: Partial dislocation of the lens of the eye.

label: Constriction of peripheral visual field
definition: An absolute or relative decrease in retinal sensitivity extending from edge (periphery) of the visual field in a concentric pattern. The visual field is the area that is perceived simultaneously by a fixating eye.

label: Anterior polar cataract
definition: A polar cataract that affects the anterior pole of the lens.

label: Retinal arteriolar tortuosity
definition: The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of the retinal arterioles.

label: Alternating esotropia
definition: Esotropia in which either eye may be used for fixation.

label: Limbal dermoid
definition: A benign tumor typically found at the junction of the cornea and sclera (limbal epibullar dermoid).

label: Severely reduced visual acuity
definition: Severe reduction of the ability to see. On the 6m visual acuity scale, severe reduction is defined as less than 6/60 but at least 3/60. On the 20ft visual acuity scale, severe reduction is defined as less than 20/200 but at least 20/400. On the decimal visual acuity scale, severe reduction is defined as less than 0.1 but at least 0.05.

label: Lenticonus
definition: A conical projection of the anterior or posterior surface of the lens, occurring as a developmental anomaly.

label: Abnormality of lens shape
definition: An abnormal shape of the lens.

label: Orbital cyst
definition: Presence of a cyst in the region of the periorbital tissues. Orbital cysts can be derived from epithelial or glandular tissue within or surrounding the orbit (lacrimal glands, salivary glands, conjunctival, oral, nasal, or sinus epithelium).

label: Retinal exudate
definition: Fluid which has escaped from retinal blood vessels with a high concentration of lipid, protein, and cellular debris with a typically bright, reflective, white or cream colored appearance on the surface of the retina.

label: Lattice corneal dystrophy
definition: The presence of fine, branching linear opacities in Bowman's layer in the central area that may spread to the periphery in the clinical course. The deep corneal stroma may be involved but the process does not reach Descemet's membrane. Recurrent corneal erosion may occur. Histologic examination reveals amyloid deposits in the collagen fibers of the cornea.

label: Impaired horizontal smooth pursuit
definition: An abnormality of ocular smooth pursuit characterized by an impairment of the ability to track horizontally moving objects.

label: Impaired smooth pursuit
definition: An impairment of the ability to track objects with the ocular smooth pursuit system, a class of rather slow eye movements that minimizes retinal target motion.

label: Saccadic smooth pursuit
definition: An abnormality of tracking eye movements in which smooth pursuit is interrupted by an abnormally high number of saccadic movements.

label: Abnormality of the hand
definition: An abnormality affecting one or both hands.

label: Abnormality of the upper limb
definition: An abnormality of the arm.

label: Brachydactyly
definition: Digits that appear disproportionately short compared to the hand/foot. The word brachydactyly is used here to describe a series distinct patterns of shortened digits (brachydactyly types A-E). This is the sense used here.

label: Short digit
definition: One or more digit that appears disproportionately short compared to the hand/foot, whereby either the entire digit or a specific phalanx is shortened.

label: Syndactyly
definition: Webbing or fusion of the fingers or toes, involving soft parts only or including bone structure. Bony fusions are referred to as bony" syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a radio-ulnar axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers or toes in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as "symphalangism"."

label: Abnormal digit morphology
definition: A morphological abnormality of a digit, i.e., of a finger or toe.

label: Hand polydactyly
definition: A kind of polydactyly characterized by the presence of a supernumerary finger or fingers.

label: Duplication of phalanx of hand
definition: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

label: Polydactyly
definition: A congenital anomaly characterized by the presence of supernumerary fingers or toes.

label: Postaxial hand polydactyly
definition: Supernumerary digits located at the ulnar side of the hand (that is, on the side with the fifth finger).

label: Abnormal 5th finger morphology
definition: An abnormality affecting one or both 5th fingers.

label: Postaxial polydactyly
definition: A form of polydactyly in which the extra digit or digits are localized on the side of the fifth finger or fifth toe.

label: Arachnodactyly
definition: Abnormally long and slender fingers (spider fingers).

label: Slender finger
definition: Fingers that are disproportionately narrow (reduced girth) for the hand/foot size or build of the individual.

label: Long fingers
definition: The middle finger is more than 2 SD above the mean for newborns 27 to 41 weeks EGA or above the 97th centile for children from birth to 16 years of age AND the five digits retain their normal length proportions relative to each other (i.e., it is not the case that the middle finger is the only lengthened digit), or, Fingers that appear disproportionately long compared to the palm of the hand.

label: Abnormal finger morphology
definition: An anomaly of a finger.

label: Broad palm
definition: For children from birth to 4 years of age the palm width is more than 2 SD above the mean; for children from 4 to 16 years of age the palm width is above the 95th centile; or, the width of the palm appears disproportionately wide for the length.

label: Abnormal palm morphology
definition: An abnormality of the palm, that is, of the front of the hand.

label: Split hand
definition: A condition in which middle parts of the hand (fingers and metacarpals) are missing giving a cleft appearance. The severity is very variable ranging from slightly hypoplastic middle fingers over absent middle fingers as far as oligo- or monodactyl hands.

label: Abnormal hand morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the hand.

label: Ectrodactyly
definition: A condition in which middle parts of the hands and/or feet (digits and meta-carpals and -tarsals) are missing giving a cleft appearance. The severity is very variable ranging from slightly hypoplastic 3rd toe/fingers over absent 2nd or 3rd toes/fingers as far as oligo- or monodactyl hands and/or feet.

label: Abnormal thumb morphology
definition: An abnormal structure of the first digit of the hand.

label: Preaxial hand polydactyly
definition: Supernumerary digits located at the radial side of the hand. Polydactyly (supernumerary digits) involving the thumb occurs in many distinct forms of high variability and severity. Ranging from fleshy nubbins over varying degrees of partial duplication/splitting to completely duplicated or even triplicated thumbs or preaxial (on the radial side of the hand) supernumerary digits.

label: Preaxial polydactyly
definition: A form of polydactyly in which the extra digit or digits are localized on the side of the thumb or great toe.

label: Ulnar claw
definition: An abnormal hand position characterized by hyperextension of the fourth and fifth fingers at the metacarpophalangeal joints and flexion of the interphalangeal joints of the same fingers such that they are curled towards the palm.

label: Adducted thumb
definition: In the resting position, the tip of the thumb is on, or near, the palm, close to the base of the fourth or fifth finger.

label: Tapered finger
definition: The gradual reduction in girth of the finger from proximal to distal.

label: Hyperextensibility of the finger joints
definition: The ability of the finger joints to move beyond their normal range of motion.

label: Hand clenching
definition: An abnormal hand posture in which the hands are clenched to fists. All digits held completely flexed at the metacarpophalangeal and interphalangeal joints. In prenatal sonography of the fetal clenched hand, the index finger overlaps a clenched fist formed by the other digits. The proximal interphalangeal articulation of the index finger is flexed and ulnarly deviated, and the thumb is adducted.

label: Abnormal carpal morphology
definition: An abnormality affecting the carpal bones of the wrist (scaphoid, lunate, triquetral, pisiform, trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, hamate).

label: Abnormality of the wrist
definition: Abnormality of the wrist, the structure connecting the hand and the forearm.

label: Ulnar deviation of the hand or of fingers of the hand
Deviation of the hand or of fingers of the hand
definition: Displacement of the hand or of fingers of the hand from their normal position.

label: Abnormalities of placenta or umbilical cord
definition: An abnormality of the placenta (the organ that connects the developing fetus to the uterine wall) or of the umbilical cord (the cord that connects the fetus to the placenta).

label: Abnormality of prenatal development or birth
definition: An abnormality of the fetus or the birth of the fetus, excluding structural abnormalities.

label: Single umbilical artery
definition: Single umbilical artery (SUA) is the absence of one of the two umbilical arteries surrounding the fetal bladder and in the fetal umbilical cord.

label: Abnormal fetal cardiovascular morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the fetal circulation system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Abnormal umbilical cord blood vessel morphology
Short umbilical cord
definition: Decreased length of the umbilical cord.

label: Abnormality of the umbilical cord
definition: An abnormality of the umbilical cord, which is the cord connecting the developing embryo or fetus to the placenta.

label: Triphalangeal thumb
definition: A thumb with three phalanges in a single, proximo-distal axis. Thus, this term applies if the thumb has an accessory phalanx, leading to a digit like appearance of the thumb.

label: Abnormality of thumb phalanx
definition: A structural anomaly of one or more phalanges of the thumb.

label: Distal symphalangism of hands
definition: The term distal symphalangism refers to a bony fusion of the distal and middle phalanges of the digits of the hand, in other words the distal interphalangeal joint (DIJ) is missing which can be seen either on x-rays or as an absence of the distal interphalangeal finger creases.

label: Finger symphalangism
definition: An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones of the fingers. The synonymous term symphalangism of the hand" may be translated as fusions of bones of varying digree
column5: that involve at least one phalangeal bone of the hand. If bony fusions are referred to as "Symphalangism" the fusion occurs in a proximo-distal axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers in a radio-ulnar axis are referred to as "bony" Syndactyly."

label: Symphalangism affecting the phalanges of the hand
definition: Fusion of two or more phalangeal bones of the hand.

label: Abnormal distal phalanx morphology of finger
definition: Any anomaly of distal phalanx of finger.

label: Abnormal fingertip morphology
definition: An abnormal structure of the tip (end) of a finger.

label: Prominent fingertip pads
definition: A soft tissue prominence of the ventral aspects of the fingertips. The term persistent fetal fingertip pads" is often used as a synonym
column5: but should better not be used because it implies knowledge of history of the patient which often does not exist."

label: Prominent digit pad
definition: A soft tissue prominence of the ventral aspects of the fingertips or toe tips.

label: Camptodactyly of 2nd-5th fingers
definition: The distal interphalangeal joint and/or the proximal interphalangeal joint of the second to fifth fingers cannot be extended to 180 degrees by either active or passive extension.

label: Camptodactyly of finger
definition: The distal interphalangeal joint and/or the proximal interphalangeal joint of the fingers cannot be extended to 180 degrees by either active or passive extension.

label: Delayed ossification of carpal bones
definition: Ossification of carpal bones occurs later than age-adjusted norms.

label: Clubbing
definition: Broadening of the soft tissues (non-edematous swelling of soft tissues) of the digital tips in all dimensions associated with an increased longitudinal and lateral curvature of the nails.

label: Autoamputation
definition: Auto-amputation is the spontaneous detachment of an appendage from the body due to long standing pathology.

label: Interphalangeal joint contracture of finger
definition: Chronic loss of joint motion in an interphalangeal joint of a finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue.

label: Flexion contracture of finger
definition: Chronic loss of joint motion in a finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue.

label: Spatulate thumbs
definition: Spoon-shaped, broad thumbs.

label: Broad thumb
definition: Increased thumb width without increased dorso-ventral dimension.

label: Pointed proximal second through fifth metacarpals
definition: All of the metacarpal bones of the hand have a pointed proximal appearance.

label: Proximal tapering of metacarpals
definition: Some or all of the metacarpal bones (i.e., metacarpal II to V) have a pointed proximal appearance.

label: Abnormality of the thenar eminence
definition: An abnormality of the thenar eminence, i.e., of the muscle on the palm of the human hand just beneath the thumb.

label: Abnormality of the musculature of the hand
Broad metacarpals
definition: Abnormally broad metacarpal bones.

label: Abnormal metacarpal morphology
definition: Any abnormal shape or structure of the metacarpal bones.

label: Abnormal fingernail morphology
definition: An abnormality of the fingernails.

label: Abnormal nail morphology
definition: Abnormal structure or appearance of the nail.

label: Nail bed telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectases in the area of the nails.

label: 2-3 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the second to the third fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: Cutaneous finger syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints, or a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two fingers that lies significantly distal to the flexion crease that overlies the metacarpophalangeal joint of the adjacent fingers.

label: Hitchhiker thumb
definition: With the hand relaxed and the thumb in the plane of the palm, the axis of the thumb forms an angle of at least 90 degrees with the long axis of the hand.

label: Radial deviation of finger
definition: Bending or curvature of a finger toward the radial side (i.e., towards the thumb). The deviation is at the metacarpal-phalangeal joint, and this finding is distinct from clinodactyly.

label: Deviation of the thumb
definition: Displacement of the thumb from its normal position.

label: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the thumb
definition: Any anomaly of the distal phalanx of thumb.

label: Wrist flexion contracture
definition: A chronic loss of wrist joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevent normal movement of the joints of the wrist.

label: Upper-limb joint contracture
definition: A limitation in the passive range of motion of a joint of the upper limb resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin.

label: Carpal synostosis
definition: Synostosis (bony fusion) involving one or more bones of the carpus (scaphoid, lunate, triquetrum, trapezium, trapezoid, capitate, hamate, pisiform).

label: Small thenar eminence
definition: Underdevelopment of the thenar eminence with reduced palmar soft tissue mass surrounding the base of the thumb.

label: Short tubular bones of the hand
definition: Decreased length of the tubular bones of the hand, that is, the phalanges and metacarpals.

label: Short long bone
definition: One or more abnormally short long bone.

label: Intellectual disability
definition: Intellectual disability, previously referred to as mental retardation, is characterized by subnormal intellectual functioning that occurs during the developmental period. It is defined by an IQ score below 70.

label: Neurodevelopmental abnormality
definition: A deviation from normal of the neurological development of a child, which may include any or all of the aspects of the development of personal, social, gross or fine motor, and cognitive abilities.

label: Seizure
definition: A seizure is an intermittent abnormality of nervous system physiology characterized by a transient occurrence of signs and/or symptoms due to abnormal excessive or synchronous neuronal activity in the brain.

label: Ataxia
definition: Cerebellar ataxia refers to ataxia due to dysfunction of the cerebellum. This causes a variety of elementary neurological deficits including asynergy (lack of coordination between muscles, limbs and joints), dysmetria (lack of ability to judge distances that can lead to under- or overshoot in grasping movements), and dysdiadochokinesia (inability to perform rapid movements requiring antagonizing muscle groups to be switched on and off repeatedly).

label: Lethargy
definition: A state of fatigue, either physical or mental slowness and sluggishness, with difficulties in initiating or performing simple tasks. Distinguished from apathy which implies indifference and a lack of desire or interest in the task. A person with lethargy may have the desire, but not the energy to engage in personal or socially relevant tasks.

label: Intellectual disability, mild
definition: Mild intellectual disability is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 50-69.

label: Spasticity
definition: A motor disorder characterized by a velocity-dependent increase in tonic stretch reflexes with increased muscle tone, exaggerated (hyperexcitable) tendon reflexes.

label: Hypertonia
definition: A condition in which there is increased muscle tone so that arms or legs, for example, are stiff and difficult to move.

label: Upper motor neuron dysfunction
definition: A functional anomaly of the upper motor neuron. The upper motor neurons are neurons of the primary motor cortex which project to the brainstem and spinal chord via the corticonuclear, corticobulbar and corticospinal (pyramidal) tracts. They are involved in control of voluntary movements. Dysfunction leads to weakness, impairment of fine motor movements, spasticity, hyperreflexia and abnormal pyramidal signs.

label: Spastic paraplegia
definition: Spasticity and weakness of the leg and hip muscles.

label: Lower limb spasticity
definition: Spasticity (velocity-dependent increase in tonic stretch reflexes with increased muscle tone and hyperexcitable tendon reflexes) in the muscles of the lower limbs, hips, and pelvis.

label: Paraplegia
definition: Severe or complete weakness of both lower extremities with sparing of the upper extremities.

label: Coma
definition: The complete absence of wakefulness and consciousness, which is evident through a lack of response to any form of external stimuli.

label: Reduced consciousness
definition: Abnormally diminished level of attention, responsiveness, or wakefulness.

label: Dysarthria
definition: Dysarthric speech is a general description referring to a neurological speech disorder characterized by poor articulation. Depending on the involved neurological structures, dysarthria may be further classified as spastic, flaccid, ataxic, hyperkinetic and hypokinetic, or mixed.

label: Excessive daytime somnolence
definition: A state of abnormally strong desire for sleep during the daytime.

label: Sleep abnormality
definition: An abnormal pattern in the quality, quantity, or characteristics of sleep.

label: Global developmental delay
definition: A delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child, including motor skills, speech and language, cognitive skills, and social and emotional skills. This term should only be used to describe children younger than five years of age.

label: Spastic diplegia
definition: Spasticity (neuromuscular hypertonia) primarily in the muscles of the legs, hips, and pelvis.

label: Appendicular spasticity
definition: A type of spasticity that affects one or more limbs (arms or legs).

label: Hyporeflexia
definition: Reduction of neurologic reflexes such as the knee-jerk reaction.

label: Reduced tendon reflexes
definition: Diminution of tendon reflexes, which is an invariable sign of peripheral nerve disease.

label: Choreoathetosis
definition: Involuntary movements characterized by both athetosis (inability to sustain muscles in a fixed position) and chorea (widespread jerky arrhythmic movements).

label: Chorea
definition: Chorea (Greek for 'dance') refers to widespread arrhythmic involuntary movements of a forcible, jerky and restless fashion. It is a random-appearing sequence of one or more discrete involuntary movements or movement fragments. Movements appear random because of variability in timing, duration or location. Each movement may have a distinct start and end. However, movements may be strung together and thus may appear to flow randomly from one muscle group to another. Chorea can involve the trunk, neck, face, tongue, and extremities.

label: Athetosis
definition: A slow, continuous, involuntary writhing movement that prevents maintenance of a stable posture. Athetosis involves continuous smooth movements that appear random and are not composed of recognizable sub-movements or movement fragments. In contrast to chorea, in athetosis, the same regions of the body are repeatedly involved. Athetosis may worsen with attempts at movement of posture, but athetosis can also occur at rest.

label: Cognitive impairment
definition: Abnormal cognition is characterized by deficits in thinking, reasoning, or remembering.

label: Hemiparesis
definition: Loss of strength in the arm, leg, and sometimes face on one side of the body. Hemiplegia refers to a complete loss of strength, whereas hemiparesis refers to an incomplete loss of strength.

label: Hemiplegia/hemiparesis
definition: Loss of strength in the arm, leg, and sometimes face on one side of the body. Hemiplegia refers to a severe or complete loss of strength, whereas hemiparesis refers to a relatively mild loss of strength.

label: Motor delay
definition: A type of Developmental delay characterized by a delay in acquiring motor skills.

label: Polyneuropathy
definition: A generalized disorder of peripheral nerves.

label: Cerebellar atrophy
definition: Cerebellar atrophy is defined as a cerebellum with initially normal structures, in a posterior fossa with normal size, which displays enlarged fissures (interfolial spaces) in comparison to the foliae secondary to loss of tissue. Cerebellar atrophy implies irreversible loss of tissue and result from an ongoing progressive disease until a final stage is reached or a single injury, e.g. an intoxication or infectious event.

label: Abnormal cerebellum morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the cerebellum.

label: Abnormal corpus callosum morphology
definition: Abnormality of the corpus callosum.

label: Abnormal cerebral white matter morphology
definition: An abnormality of the cerebral white matter.

label: Agenesis of corpus callosum
definition: Absence of the corpus callosum as a result of the failure of the corpus callosum to develop, which can be the result of a failure in any one of the multiple steps of callosal development including cellular proliferation and migration, axonal growth or glial patterning at the midline.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the corpus callosum
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the corpus callosum.

label: Orthostatic hypotension
definition: A form of hypotension characterized by a sudden fall in blood pressure that occurs when a person assumes a standing position.

label: Hypotension
definition: Low Blood Pressure, vascular hypotension.

label: Abnormal autonomic nervous system physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the autonomic nervous system.

label: Syncope
definition: Syncope is a syndrome in which loss of consciousness is of relatively sudden onset, temporary (usually less than 1 to 2 minutes), self-terminating, and of usually rapid recovery. Syncope leads to a generalized weakness of muscles with loss of postural tone, inability to stand upright, and loss of consciousness. Once the patient is in a horizontal position, blood flow to the brain is no longer hindered by gravitation and consciousness is regained. Unconsciousness usually lasts for seconds to minutes. Headache and drowsiness (which usually follow seizures) do not follow a syncopal attack. Syncope results from a sudden impairment of brain metabolism usually due to a reduction in cerebral blood flow.

label: Abnormal cardiovascular system physiology
definition: Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.

label: Tetany
definition: A condition characterized by intermittent involuntary contraction of muscles (spasms) related to hypocalcemia or occasionally magnesium deficiency.

label: Abnormal muscle physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

label: Bulbar palsy
definition: Bulbar weakness (or bulbar palsy) refers to bilateral impairment of function of the lower cranial nerves IX, X, XI and XII, which occurs due to lower motor neuron lesion either at nuclear or fascicular level in the medulla or from bilateral lesions of the lower cranial nerves outside the brain-stem. Bulbar weakness is often associated with difficulty in chewing, weakness of the facial muscles, dysarthria, palatal weakness and regurgitation of fluids, dysphagia, and dysphonia.

label: Areflexia
definition: Absence of neurologic reflexes such as the knee-jerk reaction.

label: Spastic tetraparesis
definition: Spastic weakness affecting all four limbs.

label: Tetraparesis
definition: Weakness of all four limbs.

label: Meningitis
definition: Inflammation of the meninges.

label: Unusual CNS infection
definition: A type of infection of the central nervous system that can be regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection.

label: Gait disturbance
definition: The term gait disturbance can refer to any disruption of the ability to walk.

label: Confusion
definition: Lack of clarity and coherence of thought, perception, understanding, or action.

label: Generalized hypotonia
definition: Generalized muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone).

label: Abnormal cranial nerve morphology
definition: Structural abnormality affecting one or more of the cranial nerves, which emerge directly from the brain stem.

label: Stroke
definition: Sudden impairment of blood flow to a part of the brain due to occlusion or rupture of an artery to the brain.

label: Abnormal cerebral vascular morphology
definition: An anomaly of the cerebral blood vessels.

label: Encephalopathy
definition: Encephalopathy is a term that means brain disease, damage, or malfunction. In general, encephalopathy is manifested by an altered mental state.

label: Parkinsonism
definition: Characteristic neurologic anomaly resulting from degeneration of dopamine-generating cells in the substantia nigra, a region of the midbrain, characterized clinically by shaking, rigidity, slowness of movement and difficulty with walking and gait.

label: Abnormality of extrapyramidal motor function
definition: A neurological condition related to lesions of the basal ganglia leading to typical abnormalities including akinesia (inability to initiate changes in activity and perform volitional movements rapidly and easily), muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement), chorea (widespread arrhythmic movements of a forcible, rapid, jerky, and restless nature), athetosis (inability to sustain the muscles of the fingers, toes, or other group of muscles in a fixed position), and akathisia (inability to remain motionless).

label: Pachygyria
definition: Pachygyria is a malformation of cortical development with abnormally wide gyri with sulci 1,5-3 cm apart and abnormally thick cortex measuring more than 5 mm (radiological definition). See also neuropathological definitions for 2-, 3-, and 4-layered lissencephaly.

label: Lissencephaly
definition: A spectrum of malformations of cortical development caused by insufficient neuronal migration that subsumes the terms agyria, pachygyria and subcortical band heterotopia. See also neuropathological definitions for 2-, 3-, and 4-layered lissencephaly.

label: Torsion dystonia
definition: Sustained involuntary muscle contractions that produce twisting and repetitive movements of the body.

label: Dystonia
definition: An abnormally increased muscular tone that causes fixed abnormal postures. There is a slow, intermittent twisting motion that leads to exaggerated turning and posture of the extremities and trunk.

label: Dandy-Walker malformation
definition: A congenital brain malformation typically characterized by incomplete formation of the cerebellar vermis, dilation of the fourth ventricle, and enlargement of the posterior fossa. In layman's terms, Dandy Walker malformation is a cyst in the cerebellum (typically symmetrical) that is involved with the fourth ventricle. This may interfere with the ability to drain cerebrospinal fluid from the brain, resulting in hydrocephalus. Dandy Walker cysts are formed during early embryonic development, while the brain forms. The cyst in the cerebellum typically has several blood vessels running through it connecting to the brain, thereby prohibiting surgical removal.

label: Cerebellar vermis hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the vermis of cerebellum.

label: Dilated fourth ventricle
definition: An abnormal dilatation of the fourth cerebral ventricle.

label: Enlarged posterior fossa
definition: Abnormal increased size of the posterior cranial fossa.

label: Tongue fasciculations
definition: Fasciculations or fibrillation affecting the tongue muscle.

label: Fasciculations
definition: Fasciculations are observed as small, local, involuntary muscle contractions (twitching) visible under the skin. Fasciculations result from increased irritability of an axon (which in turn is often a manifestation of disease of a motor neuron). This leads to sporadic discharges of all the muscle fibers controlled by the axon in isolation from other motor units.

label: Muscle fibrillation
definition: Fine, rapid twitching of individual muscle fibers with little or no movement of the muscle as a whole as ascertained by electromyography (EMG). If a motor neuron or its axon is destroyed, the muscle fibers it innervates undergo denervation atrophy. This leads to hypersensitivity of individual muscle fibers to acetyl choline so that they may contract spontaneously. Isolated activity of individual muscle fibers is generally so fine it cannot be seen through the intact skin, although it can be recorded as a short-duration spike in the EMG.

label: Dysmetria
definition: A type of ataxia characterized by the inability to carry out movements with the correct range and motion across the plane of more than one joint related to incorrect estimation of the distances required for targeted movements.

label: Abnormal nervous system electrophysiology
definition: An abnormality of the function of the electrical signals with which nerve cells communicate with each other or with muscles as measured by electrophysiological investigations.

label: Giant somatosensory evoked potentials
definition: An abnormal enlargement (i.e. increase in measured voltage) of somatosensory evoked potentials.

label: Abnormality of somatosensory evoked potentials
definition: An abnormality of somatosensory evoked potentials (SSEP), i.e., of the electrical signals of sensation going from the body to the brain in response to a defined stimulus. Recording electrodes are placed over the scalp, spine, and peripheral nerves proximal to the stimulation site. Clinical studies generally use electrical stimulation of peripheral nerves to elicit potentials. SSEP testing determines whether peripheral sensory nerves are able to transmit sensory information like pain, temperature, and touch to the brain. Abnormal SSEPs can result from dysfunction at the level of the peripheral nerve, plexus, spinal root, spinal cord, brain stem, thalamocortical projections, or primary somatosensory cortex.

label: Abnormal reflex
definition: Any anomaly of a reflex, i.e., of an automatic response mediated by the nervous system (a reflex does not need the intervention of conscious thought to occur).

label: Abnormal metencephalon morphology
definition: An abnormality of the metencephalon. The metencephalon is the part of the hindbrain that consists of the pons and the cerebellum.

label: Neonatal hypotonia
definition: Muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone) manifesting in the neonatal period.

label: Cerebellar hypoplasia
definition: Cerebellar hypoplasia is a descriptive term implying a cerebellum with a reduced volume, but a normal shape and is stable over time.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cerebellar vermis
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the vermis of cerebellum.

label: Hypoglycemic coma
definition: Coma induced by low blood sugar.

label: EEG with irregular generalized spike and wave complexes
definition: EEG shows spikes (<80 ms) and waves, which are recorded over the entire scalp and do not have a specific frequency.

label: EEG with spike-wave complexes
definition: Complexes of spikes (<70 ms) and sharp waves (70-200 ms), which are sharp transient waves that have a strong association with epilepsy, in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: Photosensitive myoclonic seizure
definition: Generalised myoclonic seizure provoked by flashing or flickering light.

label: Generalized myoclonic seizure
definition: A generalized myoclonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by bilateral, sudden, brief (<100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal). Myoclonus is less regularly repetitive and less sustained than is clonus.

label: Visually-induced seizure
definition: Seizures evoked by visual stimuli. This includes clinical seizures induced by strobe lighting, television and other screens, flickering environmental lighting and self-induction by causing a strobe effect.

label: Specific learning disability
definition: Impairment of certain skills such as reading or writing, coordination, self-control, or attention that interfere with the ability to learn. The impairment is not related to a global deficiency of intelligence.

label: Absent septum pellucidum
definition: Absence of the septum pellucidum (meaning translucent wall in Latin - SP), also known as the ventricle of Sylvius. The septum pellucidum is a thin, triangular double membrane separating the frontal horns of the right and left lateral ventricles of the brain. It extends between the anterior portion of the corpus callosum, and the body of the fornix and its width varies from 1.5 to 3.0 mm.

label: Abnormal septum pellucidum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the septum pellucidum, which is a thin, triangular, vertical membrane separating the lateral ventricles of the brain.

label: Communicating hydrocephalus
definition: A form of hydrocephalus in which there is no visible obstruction to the flow of the cerebrospinal fluid between the ventricles and subarachnoid space.

label: Bimanual synkinesia
definition: Involuntary movements of one hand that accompany and mirror intentional movements of the opposite hand.

label: Synkinesis
definition: Unintentional movement in one area of the body produced during intentional movement of another area of the body.

label: Myoclonus
definition: Very brief, involuntary random muscular contractions occurring at rest, in response to sensory stimuli, or accompanying voluntary movements.

label: Involuntary movements
definition: Involuntary contractions of muscle leading to involuntary movements of extremities, neck, trunk, or face.

label: Tremor
definition: An unintentional, oscillating to-and-fro muscle movement about a joint axis.

label: Partial agenesis of the corpus callosum
definition: A partial failure of the development of the corpus callosum.

label: Abnormal cortical gyration
definition: An abnormality of the gyri (i.e., the ridges) of the cerebral cortex of the brain.

label: Enhancement of the C-reflex
definition: Increase in amplitude of a long-loop response upon somatosensory evoked potential testing, representing an electrically evoked myoclonic response.

label: Abnormal olfactory lobe morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the olfactory lobe, the structure within the brain that receives neural input from the nasal cavity and thereby processes the sense of smell.

label: Cerebral hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage into the parenchyma of the brain.

label: Intracranial hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage occurring within the skull.

label: Kernicterus
definition: Damage to cerebral nuclei caused in infants by highly increased levels of unconjugated bilirubin. The basal ganglia and brainstem nuclei could be shown to have a yellow staining historically in infants who died of kernicterus, that is, kernicterus is strictly speaking a pathological diagnosis. The presence of kernicterus may be inferred in infants with characteristic acute or chronic bilirubin-induced neurological dysfunction.

label: Abnormal brain morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the brain, which has as its parts the forebrain, midbrain, and hindbrain.

label: Absent speech
definition: Complete lack of development of speech and language abilities.

label: Psychotic mentation
definition: A pattern of thinking and perceiving characterized by a loss of contact with reality, leading to significant changes in thoughts, perceptions, and behaviors.

label: Hyperreflexia
definition: Hyperreflexia is the presence of hyperactive stretch reflexes of the muscles.

label: Brisk reflexes
definition: Tendon reflexes that are noticeably more active than usual (conventionally denoted 3+ on clinical examination). Brisk reflexes may or may not indicate a neurological lesion. They are distinguished from hyperreflexia by the fact that hyerreflexia is characterized by hyperactive repeating (clonic) reflexes, which are considered to be always abnormal.

label: Facial diplegia
definition: Facial diplegia refers to bilateral facial palsy (bilateral facial palsy is much rarer than unilateral facial palsy).

label: Facial palsy
definition: Facial nerve palsy is a dysfunction of cranial nerve VII (the facial nerve) that results in inability to control facial muscles on the affected side with weakness of the muscles of facial expression and eye closure. This can either be present in unilateral or bilateral form.

label: Slurred speech
definition: Abnormal coordination of muscles involved in speech.

label: Jerk-locked premyoclonus spikes
definition: Jerk-locked averaging (JLA) is used to record the timing and distribution of brain activity preceding brisk involuntary movements such as those observed in patients with myoclonus. JLA is capable of revealing a premyoclonus spike in the absence of paroxysmal activity in the routine EEG.

label: Abnormality of central nervous system electrophysiology
Megalencephaly
definition: Diffuse enlargement of the entire cerebral hemispheres leading to macrocephaly (with or without overlying cortical dysplasia).

label: Abnormal cerebral morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the telencephalon, which is also known as the cerebrum.

label: Plagiocephaly
definition: Asymmetric head shape, which is usually a combination of unilateral occipital flattening with ipsilateral frontal prominence, leading to rhomboid cranial shape.

label: Holoprosencephaly
definition: Holoprosencephaly is a structural anomaly of the brain in which the developing forebrain fails to divide into two separate hemispheres and ventricles.

label: Nystagmus-induced head nodding
definition: Head movements associated with nystagmus, that may represent an attempt to compensate for the involuntary eye movements and to improve vision.

label: Calvarial skull defect
definition: A localized defect in the bone of the skull resulting from abnormal embryological development. The defect is covered by normal skin. In some cases, skull x-rays have shown underlying lytic bone lesions which have closed before the age of one year.

label: Craniosynostosis
definition: Craniosynostosis refers to the premature closure of the cranial sutures. Primary craniosynostosis refers to the closure of one or more sutures due to abnormalities in skull development, and secondary craniosynostosis results from failure of brain growth.

label: Arthritis
definition: Inflammation of a joint.

label: Rheumatoid arthritis
definition: Inflammatory changes in the synovial membranes and articular structures with widespread fibrinoid degeneration of the collagen fibers in mesenchymal tissues, as well as atrophy and rarefaction of bony structures.

label: Flexion contracture
definition: A flexion contracture is a bent (flexed) joint that cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement of joints.

label: Joint contracture
definition: A limitation in the passive range of motion of a joint resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin. A contracture prevents movement of the associated body part.

label: Joint dislocation
definition: Displacement or malalignment of joints.

label: Hip dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the hip.

label: Hip dislocation
definition: Displacement of the femur from its normal location in the hip joint.

label: Limitation of joint mobility
definition: A reduction in the freedom of movement of one or more joints.

label: Abnormality of joint mobility
definition: An abnormality in the range and ease of motion of joints across their normal range.

label: Limited elbow extension
definition: Limited ability to straighten the arm at the elbow joint.

label: Joint hypermobility
definition: The capability that a joint (or a group of joints) has to move, passively and/or actively, beyond normal limits along physiological axes.

label: Abnormal hip joint morphology
definition: An abnormality of the hip joint.

label: Abnormal hip bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the hip bone.

label: Joint stiffness
definition: Joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in a joint or joints when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity. Joint stiffness typically subsides over time.

label: Abnormality of the liver
definition: An abnormality of the liver.

label: Abnormality of the abdominal organs
definition: An abnormality of the viscera of the abdomen.

label: Cirrhosis
definition: A chronic disorder of the liver in which liver tissue becomes scarred and is partially replaced by regenerative nodules and fibrotic tissue resulting in loss of liver function.

label: Abnormal liver morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the bile-secreting organ that is important for detoxification, for fat, carbohydrate, and protein metabolism, and for glycogen storage.

label: Hepatic fibrosis
definition: The presence of excessive fibrous connective tissue in the liver. Fibrosis is a reparative or reactive process.

label: Hepatic steatosis
definition: Steatosis is a term used to denote lipid accumulation within hepatocytes.

label: Decreased liver function
definition: Reduced ability of the liver to perform its functions.

label: Abnormal intrahepatic bile duct morphology
definition: An abnormality of the intrahepatic bile duct.

label: Hepatocellular carcinoma
definition: A kind of neoplasm of the liver that originates in hepatocytes and presents macroscopically as a soft and hemorrhagic tan mass in the liver.

label: Neoplasm of the liver
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the liver.

label: Macrovesicular hepatic steatosis
definition: A form of hepatic steatosis characterized by the presence of large, lipid-laden vesicles in the affected hepatocytes.

label: Hepatic necrosis
definition: The presence of cell death (necrosis) affecting the liver.

label: Periportal fibrosis
definition: The presence of fibrosis affecting the interlobular stroma of liver.

label: Intrahepatic cholestasis
definition: Impairment of bile flow due to obstruction in the small bile ducts within the liver.

label: Abnormal liver physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the liver.

label: Bile duct proliferation
definition: Proliferative changes of the bile ducts.

label: Abnormal biliary tract morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the biliary tree.

label: Portal hypertension
definition: Increased pressure in the portal vein.

label: Abnormality of the hepatic vasculature
definition: An abnormality of the hepatic vasculature.

label: Abnormality of hepatobiliary system physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the hepatobiliary system

label: Enteroviral hepatitis
definition: Inflammation of the liver due to infection with enterovirus.

label: Viral hepatitis
definition: Inflammation of the liver due to infection with a virus.

label: Micronodular cirrhosis
definition: A type of cirrhosis characterized by the presence of small regenerative nodules.

label: Microvesicular hepatic steatosis
definition: A form of hepatic steatosis characterized by the presence of small, lipid-laden vesicles in the affected hepatocytes.

label: X-linked inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on the X chromosome.

label: X-linked recessive inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for recessive traits related to a gene encoded on the X chromosome. In the context of medical genetics, X-linked recessive disorders manifest in males (who have one copy of the X chromosome and are thus hemizygotes), but generally not in female heterozygotes who have one mutant and one normal allele.

label: Abnormality of the musculature of the upper limbs
X-linked dominant inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for dominant traits related to a gene encoded on the X chromosome. In the context of medical genetics, X-linked dominant disorders tend to manifest very severely in affected males. The severity of manifestation in females may depend on the degree of skewed X inactivation.

label: Non-Mendelian inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that depends on genetic determinants in more than one gene.

label: Mitochondrial inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on the mitochondrial genome. Because the mitochondrial genome is essentially always maternally inherited, a mitochondrial condition can only be transmitted by females, although the condition can affect both sexes. The proportion of mutant mitochondria can vary (heteroplasmy).

label: Abnormality of the musculature of the lower limbs
Hepatosplenomegaly
definition: Simultaneous enlargement of the liver and spleen.

label: Splenomegaly
definition: Abnormal increased size of the spleen.

label: Hepatomegaly
definition: Abnormally increased size of the liver.

label: Abnormality of the shoulder girdle musculature
Abnormality of the foot musculature
definition: An anomaly of the musculature of foot.

label: Abnormality of the lower limb
definition: An abnormality of the leg.

label: Abnormality of the musculature of the limbs
Abnormal abdomen morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the abdomen ('belly'), that is, the part of the body between the pelvis and the thorax.

label: Abnormal metatarsal morphology
definition: Abnormalities of the metatarsal bones (i.e. of five tubular bones located between the tarsal bones of the hind- and mid-foot and the phalanges of the toes).

label: Synostosis involving bones of the feet
Typified by somatic mosaicism
definition: Description of conditions in which affected individuals typically display somatic mosaicism, i.e., genetically distinct populations of somatic cells in a given organism caused by DNA mutations, epigenetic alterations of DNA, chromosomal abnormalities or the spontaneous reversion of inherited mutations. In many conditions typified by somatic mosaicism, constitutive mutation is lethal and cases are exclusively or predominantly mosaic.

label: Inheritance qualifier
definition: The terms in this hierarchy can be used to specify the context in which inheritance of a disease is typically observed.

label: Abnormal morphology of the pelvis musculature
Duplication involving bones of the feet
Y-linked inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that is observed for traits related to a gene encoded on the Y chromosome.

label: Abnormality of the musculature of the upper arm
1-3 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes one to three.

label: Toe syndactyly
definition: Webbing or fusion of the toes, involving soft parts only or including bone structure. Bony fusions are referred to as bony" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a radio-ulnar axis. Fusions of bones of the toes in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as "Symphalangism"."

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the skeletal musculature
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the musculature.

label: Abnormality of muscle size
definition: Abnormalities of the overall muscle bulk based on clinical observation.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the shoulder musculature
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the muscles of the shoulder.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the musculature of the upper limbs
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the musculature of the upper limbs.

label: Contiguous gene syndrome
definition: A syndrome caused by the effects of abnormality (typically a deletion or duplication) of 2 or more adjacent genes

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the musculature of the extremities
Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the musculature of the upper arm
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the muscles of the upper arm.

label: Sex-limited expression
definition: Sex limitation is used to refer to a monogenic trait linked to an autosomal locus in which the phenotypic effects of allelic differences are expressed only in one sex.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the musculature of the pelvis
Metatarsal osteolysis
definition: Osteolysis involving metatarsal bones.

label: Osteolysis involving bones of the feet
Sclerotic scapulae
definition: Increased density of the bony tissue of the scapula.

label: Increased bone mineral density
definition: An abnormal increase of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones which is often referred to as osteosclerosis. Osteosclerosis can be detected on radiological examination as an increased whiteness (density) of affected bones.

label: Male-limited expression
definition: Used to refer to a monogenic trait linked to an autosomal locus in which the phenotypic effects of allelic differences are expressed only in the male sex.

label: Delayed closure of the anterior fontanelle
definition: A delay in closure (ossification) of the anterior fontanelle, which generally undergoes closure around the 18th month of life.

label: Compensatory chin elevation
definition: A tendency to hold the chin elevated by about 20 to 30 degrees to compensate for a limitation of eye movement.

label: Compensatory head posture
definition: A compensatory head posture occurs when the head is deviated out of the normal primary straight head position in order to compensate for an ocular problem.

label: Subcutaneous nodule
definition: Slightly elevated lesions on or in the skin with a diameter of over 5 mm.

label: Skin nodule
definition: Morphologically similar to a papule, but greater than either 10mm in both width and depth, and most frequently centered in the dermis or subcutaneous fat.

label: Eye poking
definition: Repetitive pressing, poking, and/or rubbing in the eyes.

label: Stereotypic movements of face and head
definition: Abnormal movements of face and head.

label: Posterior vitreous detachment
definition: Separation of the vitreous humor from the retina.

label: Abnormal vitreous humor morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the vitreous body.

label: Congenital fibrosis of extraocular muscles
definition: Congenital non-progressive ophthalmoplegia with multiple extraocular muscle restrictions. Typically, there is ptosis and variable degrees of restriction of horizontal and vertical eye movements.

label: Abnormality of the extraocular muscles
definition: An abnormality of an extraocular muscle.

label: Axenfeld anomaly
definition: Axenfeld's anomaly is a bilateral disorder characterized by a prominent, anteriorly displaced Schwalbe's line (posterior embryotoxon) and peripheral iris strands which span the anterior chamber angle to attach to Schwalbe's line.

label: Falciform retinal fold
definition: An area of the retina that is buckled so that a sector-shaped sheet of retina lies in front of the normal retina. This feature is of congenital onset.

label: Retinal fold
definition: A wrinkle of retinal tissue projecting outward from the surface of the retina and visible as a line on fundoscopy.

label: Carpal osteolysis
definition: Osteolysis affecting carpal bones.

label: Osteolysis involving bones of the upper limbs
Carpal bone hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of one or more carpal bones.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the carpal bones
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the carpal bones.

label: Broad finger
definition: Increased width of a non-thumb digit of the hand.

label: Supernumerary metacarpal bones
definition: The presence of more than the normal number of metacarpal bones.

label: Failure to thrive
definition: Failure to thrive (FTT) refers to a child whose physical growth is substantially below the norm.

label: Decreased body weight
definition: Abnormally low body weight.

label: Intrauterine growth retardation
definition: An abnormal restriction of fetal growth with fetal weight below the tenth percentile for gestational age.

label: Obesity
definition: Accumulation of substantial excess body fat.

label: Increased body weight
definition: Abnormally increased body weight.

label: Small for gestational age
definition: Smaller than normal size according to sex and gestational age related norms, defined as a weight below the 10th percentile for the gestational age.

label: Disproportionate tall stature
definition: A tall and slim body build with increased arm span to height ratio (>1.05) and a reduced upper-to-lower segment ratio (<0.85), i.e., unusually long arms and legs. The extremities as well as the hands and feet are unusually slim.

label: Large for gestational age
definition: The term large for gestational age applies to babies whose birth weight lies above the 90th percentile for that gestational age.

label: Death in infancy
definition: Death within the first 24 months of life.

label: Age of death
definition: The age group when the cessation of life happens.

label: Hemihypertrophy
definition: Overgrowth of only one side of the body.

label: Asymmetric growth
definition: A growth pattern that displays an abnormal difference between the left and the right side.

label: Mild postnatal growth retardation
definition: A mild degree of slow or limited growth after birth, being between two and three standard deviations below age- and sex-related norms.

label: Postnatal growth retardation
definition: Slow or limited growth after birth.

label: Slender build
definition: Asthenic habitus refers to a slender build with long limbs, an angular profile, and prominent muscles or bones.

label: Umbilical hernia
definition: Protrusion of abdominal contents through a defect in the abdominal wall musculature around the umbilicus. Skin and subcutaneous tissue overlie the defect.

label: Abnormal umbilicus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure or appearance of the umbilicus.

label: Protuberant abdomen
definition: A thrusting or bulging out of the abdomen.

label: Abdominal distention
definition: Distention of the abdomen.

label: Omphalocele
definition: A midline anterior incomplete closure of the abdominal wall in which there is herniation of the abdominal viscera into the base of the abdominal cord.

label: Diastasis recti
definition: A separation of the rectus abdominis muscle into right and left halves (which are normally joined at the midline at the linea alba).

label: Abnormal morphology of the abdominal musculature
definition: An abnormality of the abdominal musculature.

label: Ascites
definition: Accumulation of fluid in the peritoneal cavity (between the layers of the peritoneum that lines the abdomen).

label: Gastroschisis
