definition: A type of congenital ventral incomplete closure of the abdominal wall in which the intestines and sometimes other organs extend freely into the amniotic fluid space through a small opening in the abdomen, usually to the right of the umbilicus.

label: Abdominal wall defect
definition: An incomplete closure of the abdominal wall.

label: Prominent umbilicus
definition: Abnormally prominent umbilicus (belly button).

label: Anteriorly placed anus
definition: Anterior malposition of the anus.

label: Ectopic anus
definition: Abnormal displacement or malposition of the anus.

label: Overgrowth
definition: Excessive postnatal growth which may comprise increased weight, increased length, and/or increased head circumference.

label: Abnormal small intestine morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the small intestine.

label: Abnormality of the abdominal wall
definition: The presence of any abnormality affecting the abdominal wall.

label: Barrel-shaped chest
definition: A rounded, bulging chest that resembles the shape of a barrel. That is, there is an increased anteroposterior diameter and usually some degree of kyphosis.

label: Asymmetry of the thorax
definition: Lack of symmetry between the left and right halves of the thorax.

label: Prenatal movement abnormality
definition: An abnormality of fetal movement.

label: Abnormal fetal physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the fetus.

label: Decreased fetal movement
definition: An abnormal reduction in quantity or strength of fetal movements.

label: Abnormality of the amniotic fluid
definition: Abnormality of the amniotic fluid, which is the fluid contained in the amniotic sac surrounding the developing fetus.

label: Polyhydramnios
definition: The presence of excess amniotic fluid in the uterus during pregnancy.

label: Oligohydramnios
definition: Diminished amniotic fluid volume in pregnancy.

label: Fetal polyuria
definition: Abnormally increased production of urine by the fetus resulting in polyhydramnios.

label: Widely-spaced maxillary central incisors
definition: Increased distance between the maxillary central permanent incisor tooth.

label: Multiple impacted teeth
definition: The presence of multiple impacted teeth.

label: Impacted tooth
definition: A tooth that has not erupted because of local impediments (overcrowding or fibrous gum overgrowth).

label: Macrodontia
definition: Increased size of the teeth, which can be defined as a mesiodistal tooth diameter (width) more than 2 SD above mean for age. Alternatively, an apparently increased maximum width of the tooth.

label: Primary hypercortisolism
definition: Hypercortisolemia associated with a primary defect of the adrenal gland leading to overproduction of cortisol.

label: Increased circulating cortisol level
definition: Overproduction of the hormone of cortisol by the adrenal cortex, resulting in a characteristic combination of clinical symptoms termed Cushing syndrome, with truncal obesity, a round, full face, striae atrophicae and acne, muscle weakness, and other features.

label: Recurrent skin infections
definition: Infections of the skin that happen multiple times.

label: Redundant skin
definition: Loose and sagging skin often associated with loss of skin elasticity.

label: Rotary nystagmus
definition: A form of nystagmus in which the eyeball makes rotary motions around the axis.

label: Vesicovaginal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula connecting the urinary bladder to the vagina.

label: Bladder fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula connecting the urinary bladder to another organ or the skin. The fistula can involve the bowel, the vagina, or rarely, the skin.

label: Bell-shaped thorax
definition: The rib cage has the shape of a wide mouthed bell. That is, the superior portion of the rib cage is constricted, followed by a convex region, and the inferior portion of the rib cage expands again to have a large diameter.

label: Selective tooth agenesis
definition: Agenesis specifically affecting one of the classes incisor, premolar, or molar.

label: Maxillary lateral incisor microdontia
definition: Decreased size of the maxillary permanent incisor.

label: Abnormal incisor morphology
definition: An abnormality of morphology of the incisor tooth.

label: Alopecia
definition: A noncongenital process of hair loss, which may progress to partial or complete baldness.

label: Concave nail
definition: The natural longitudinal (posterodistal) convex arch is not present or is inverted.

label: Nail dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the nail.

label: Abnormality of the larynx
definition: An abnormality of the larynx.

label: Laryngomalacia
definition: Laryngomalacia is a congenital abnormality of the laryngeal cartilage in which the cartilage is floppy and prolapses over the larynx during inspiration.

label: Abnormal larynx morphology
definition: Any anomaly of the structure of the larynx.

label: Laryngeal stenosis
definition: Stricture or narrowing of the larynx that may be associated with symptoms of respiratory difficulty depending on the degree of laryngeal narrowing.

label: Vocal cord paresis
definition: Decreased strength of the vocal folds.

label: Vocal cord paralysis
definition: A loss of the ability to move the vocal folds.

label: Paralysis
definition: Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Motor paralysis results from deficits of the upper motor neurons (corticospinal, corticobulbar, or subcorticospinal). Motor paralysis is often accompanied by an impairment in the facility of movement.

label: Vocal cord dysfunction
definition: Any functional anomaly of the vocal cord.

label: Hoarse voice
definition: Hoarseness refers to a change in the pitch or quality of the voice, with the voice sounding weak, very breathy, scratchy, or husky.

label: Hypernasal speech
definition: A type of speech characterized by the presence of an abnormally increased nasal airflow during speech associated with structural abnormality of the nasal passages.

label: Abnormal cry
definition: Any anomaly of the vocalizing of an infant's crying, i.e.,the typically loud voice production that is accompanied by tears and agitation.

label: Dysphonia
definition: Difficulty in speaking due to a physical disorder of the mouth, tongue, throat, or vocal cords. Associated with a known physical or neurological cause.

label: Abnormally high-pitched voice
definition: A persistent (minutes to hours) abnormal increase in the pitch (frequency) of the voice for the context or social situation or significantly different from baseline of the individual.

label: Abnormal pitch
definition: Persistently abnormally high or low-pitched vocalization or speech than is considered the norm for the context of social situation or significantly different from baseline of the individual.

label: Weak voice
definition: Reduced intensity (volume) of speech.

label: Premature birth
definition: The birth of a baby of less than 37 weeks of gestational age.

label: Breech presentation
definition: A position of the fetus at delivery in which the fetus enters the birth canal with the buttocks or feet first.

label: Abnormal delivery
definition: An abnormality of the birth process.

label: Abnormality of the cardiovascular system
definition: Any abnormality of the cardiovascular system.

label: Abnormal heart morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the heart.

label: Abnormal cardiovascular system morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the heart and blood vessels.

label: Ventricular septal defect
definition: A hole between the two bottom chambers (ventricles) of the heart. The defect is centered around the most superior aspect of the ventricular septum.

label: Abnormal ventricular septum morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the interventricular septum.

label: Atrial septal defect
definition: Atrial septal defect (ASD) is a congenital abnormality of the interatrial septum that enables blood flow between the left and right atria via the interatrial septum.

label: Abnormal cardiac atrium morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a cardiac atrium.

label: Abnormal atrial septum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the interatrial septum.

label: Abnormal mitral valve morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the mitral valve.

label: Abnormal atrioventricular valve morphology
definition: An abnormality of an atrioventricular valve.

label: Mitral valve prolapse
definition: One or both of the leaflets (cusps) of the mitral valve bulges back into the left atrium upon contraction of the left ventricle.

label: Congestive heart failure
definition: The presence of an abnormality of cardiac function that is responsible for the failure of the heart to pump blood at a rate that is commensurate with the needs of the tissues or a state in which abnormally elevated filling pressures are required for the heart to do so. Heart failure is frequently related to a defect in myocardial contraction.

label: Tetralogy of Fallot
definition: A congenital cardiac malformation comprising pulmonary stenosis, overriding aorta, ventricular septum defect, and right ventricular hypertrophy. The diagnosis of TOF is made if at least three of the four above mentioned features are present.

label: Conotruncal defect
definition: A congenital malformation of the outflow tract of the heart. Conotruncal defects are thought to result from a disturbance of the outflow tract of the embryonic heart, and comprise truncus arteriosus, tetralogy of Fallot, interrupted aortic arch, transposition of the great arteries, and double outlet right ventricle.

label: Abnormal myocardium morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the muscle layer of the heart wall.

label: Cardiomyopathy
definition: A myocardial disorder in which the heart muscle is structurally and functionally abnormal, in the absence of coronary artery disease, hypertension, valvular disease and congenital heart disease sufficient to cause the observed myocardial abnormality.

label: Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
definition: Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM) is defined by the presence of increased ventricular wall thickness or mass in the absence of loading conditions (hypertension, valve disease) sufficient to cause the observed abnormality.

label: Cardiomegaly
definition: Increased size of the heart, clinically defined as an increased transverse diameter of the cardiac silhouette that is greater than or equal to 50% of the transverse diameter of the chest (increased cardiothoracic ratio) on a posterior-anterior projection of a chest radiograph or a computed tomography.

label: Abnormal pulmonary valve morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the pulmonary valve.

label: Abnormal heart valve morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a cardiac valve.

label: Pulmonic stenosis
definition: A narrowing of the right ventricular outflow tract that can occur at the pulmonary valve (valvular stenosis), below the pulmonary valve (infundibular stenosis), or above the pulmonary valve (supravalvar stenosis).

label: Abnormal pulmonary valve physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the pumonary valve.

label: Patent ductus arteriosus
definition: In utero, the ductus arteriosus (DA) serves to divert ventricular output away from the lungs and toward the placenta by connecting the main pulmonary artery to the descending aorta. A patent ductus arteriosus (PDA) in the first 3 days of life is a physiologic shunt in healthy term and preterm newborn infants, and normally is substantially closed within about 24 hours after bith and completely closed after about three weeks. Failure of physiologcal closure is referred to a persistent or patent ductus arteriosus (PDA). Depending on the degree of left-to-right shunting, PDA can have clinical consequences.

label: Congenital malformation of the great arteries
definition: Defect or defects of the morphogenesis of the aorta and pulmonary arteries.

label: Dilated cardiomyopathy
definition: Dilated cardiomyopathy (DCM) is defined by the presence of left ventricular dilatation and left ventricular systolic dysfunction in the absence of abnormal loading conditions (hypertension, valve disease) or coronary artery disease sufficient to cause global systolic impairment. Right ventricular dilation and dysfunction may be present but are not necessary for the diagnosis.

label: Sudden cardiac death
definition: The heart suddenly and unexpectedly stops beating resulting in death within a short time period (generally within 1 h of symptom onset).

label: Cardiac arrest
definition: An abrupt loss of heart function.

label: Sudden death
definition: Rapid and unexpected death.

label: Abnormal aortic valve morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the aortic valve.

label: Bicuspid aortic valve
definition: The presence of an aortic valve with two instead of the normal three cusps (flaps). Bicuspid aortic valvue is a malformation of a commissure (small space between the attachment of each cusp to the aortic wall) and the adjacent parts of the two corresponding cusps forming a raphe (the fused area of the two underdeveloped cusps turning into a malformed commissure between both cusps; the raphe is a fibrous ridge that extends from the commissure to the free edge of the two underdeveloped, conjoint cusps).

label: Abnormal aortic valve cusp morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the aortic valve leaflets.

label: Cor pulmonale
definition: Right-sided heart failure resulting from chronic hypertension in the pulmonary arteries and right ventricle.

label: Abnormal right ventricle morphology
definition: An abnormality of the right ventricle of the heart.

label: Tachycardia
definition: A rapid heartrate that exceeds the range of the normal resting heartrate for age.

label: Arrhythmia
definition: Any cardiac rhythm other than the normal sinus rhythm. Such a rhythm may be either of sinus or ectopic origin and either regular or irregular. An arrhythmia may be due to a disturbance in impulse formation or conduction or both.

label: Aortic valve stenosis
definition: The presence of a stenosis (narrowing) of the aortic valve.

label: Dextrocardia
definition: The heart is located in the right hand sided hemithorax. That is, there is a left-right reversal (or mirror reflection") of the anatomical location of the heart in which the heart is locate on the right side instead of the left."

label: Abnormal anatomic location of the heart
definition: Developmental defect characterized by an anomalous anatomic location of the heart.

label: Mitral regurgitation
definition: An abnormality of the mitral valve characterized by insufficiency or incompetence of the mitral valve resulting in retrograde leaking of blood through the mitral valve upon ventricular contraction.

label: Abnormal mitral valve physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the mitral valve.

label: Atrioventricular valve regurgitation
definition: Regurgitation of a heart valve that controls blood flow from a an atrium to a ventricle, including mitral, tricuspid, or, rarely, single atrioventicular valve.

label: Patent foramen ovale
definition: Failure of the foramen ovale to seal postnatally, leaving a potential conduit between the left and right cardiac atria.

label: Prolonged QT interval
definition: Increased time between the start of the Q wave and the end of the T wave as measured by the electrocardiogram (EKG).

label: Abnormal QT interval
definition: Any anomaly of the time interval between the start of the Q wave and the end of the T wave as measured by the electrocardiogram (EKG).

label: Myocardial infarction
definition: Necrosis of the myocardium caused by an obstruction of the blood supply to the heart and often associated with chest pain, shortness of breath, palpitations, and anxiety as well as characteristic EKG findings and elevation of serum markers including creatine kinase-MB fraction and troponin.

label: Acute coronary syndrome
definition: The term acute coronary syndrome (ACS) refers to any group of clinical symptoms compatible with acute myocardial ischemia and includes unstable angina (UA), non-ST-segment elevation myocardial infarction (NSTEMI), and ST-segment elevation myocardial infarction (STEMI).

label: Aortic regurgitation
definition: An insufficiency of the aortic valve, leading to regurgitation (backward flow) of blood from the aorta into the left ventricle.

label: Truncus arteriosus
definition: A single arterial trunk arises from the cardiac mass. The pulmonary arteries, aorta and coronary arteries arise from this single trunk with no evidence of another outflow tract.

label: Bradycardia
definition: A slower than normal heart rate (in adults, slower than 60 beats per minute).

label: Ventricular fibrillation
definition: Uncontrolled contractions of muscles fibers in the left ventricle not producing contraction of the left ventricle. Ventricular fibrillation usually begins with a ventricular premature contraction and a short run of rapid ventricular tachycardia degenerating into uncoordinating ventricular fibrillations.

label: Torsade de pointes
definition: A type of ventricular tachycardia characterized by polymorphioc QRS complexes that change in amplitue and cycle length, and thus have the appearance of oscillating around the baseline in the EKG.

label: Right ventricular hypertrophy
definition: In this case the right ventricle is more muscular than normal, causing a characteristic boot-shaped (coeur-en-sabot) appearance as seen on anterior- posterior chest x-rays. Right ventricular hypertrophy is commonly associated with any form of right ventricular outflow obstruction or pulmonary hypertension, which may in turn owe its origin to left-sided disease. The echocardiographic signs are thickening of the anterior right ventricular wall and the septum. Cavity size is usually normal, or slightly enlarged. In many cases there is associated volume overload present due to tricuspid regurgitation, in the absence of this, septal motion is normal.

label: Ventricular hypertrophy
definition: Enlargement of the cardiac ventricular muscle tissue with increase in the width of the wall of the ventricle and loss of elasticity. Ventricular hypertrophy is clinically differentiated into left and right ventricular hypertrophy.

label: Transposition of the great arteries
definition: A complex congenital heart defect in which the aorta arises from the morphologic right ventricle and the pulmonary artery arises from the morphologic left ventricle.

label: Abnormal ventriculoarterial connection
definition: An abnormality of the circulatory connection between the ventricles and the pulmonary artery and aorta.

label: Asymmetric septal hypertrophy
definition: Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with an asymmetrical pattern of hypertrophy, with a predilection for the interventricular septum and myocyte disarray.

label: Abnormal cardiac septum morphology
definition: An anomaly of the intra-atrial or intraventricular septum.

label: Complete atrioventricular canal defect
definition: A congenital heart defect characterized by a specific combination of heart defects with a common atrioventricular valve, primum atrial septal defect and inlet ventricular septal defect.

label: Atrioventricular canal defect
definition: A defect of the atrioventricular septum of the heart.

label: Coronary artery atherosclerosis
definition: Reduction of the diameter of the coronary arteries as the result of an accumulation of atheromatous plaques within the walls of the coronary arteries, which increases the risk of myocardial ischemia.

label: Atherosclerosis
definition: A condition characterized by patchy atheromas or atherosclerotic plaques which develop in the walls of medium-sized and large arteries and can lead to arterial stenosis with reduced or blocked blood flow.

label: Abnormal coronary artery morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the coronary arteries.

label: Arterial stenosis
definition: Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of an artery.

label: Atrioventricular block
definition: Delayed or lack of conduction of atrial depolarizations through the atrioventricular node to the ventricles.

label: Abnormal atrioventricular conduction
definition: An impairment of the electrical continuity between the atria and ventricles.

label: Heart block
definition: Impaired conduction of cardiac impulse occurring anywhere along the conduction pathway.

label: Abnormal aortic morphology
definition: An abnormality of the aorta.

label: Abnormal morphology of the great vessels
definition: A structural anomaly affecting a blood vessel involved in the circulation of the heart, i.e., the superior or inferior vena cava, the pulmonary arteries, the pulmonary veins, and the aorta.

label: Coarctation of aorta
definition: Coarctation of the aorta is a narrowing or constriction of a segment of the aorta.

label: Angina pectoris
definition: Paroxysmal chest pain that occurs with exertion or stress and is related to myocardial ischemia.

label: Subvalvular aortic stenosis
definition: A fixed form of obstruction to blood flow across the left-ventricular outflow tract related to stenosis (narrowing) below the level of the aortic valve.

label: Abnormal left ventricular outflow tract morphology
definition: An abnormality of the outflow tract of the left ventricle.

label: Ectopia cordis
definition: Congenital malformation of the ventral wall with partial or total evisceration of the heart outside the thoracic cavity and through the defect in the ventral wall.

label: Secundum atrial septal defect
definition: A kind of atrial septum defect arising from an enlarged foramen ovale, inadequate growth of the septum secundum, or excessive absorption of the septum primum.

label: Myocardial fibrosis
definition: Myocardial fibrosis is characterized by dysregulated collagen turnover (increased synthesis predominates over unchanged or decreased degradation) and excessive diffuse collagen accumulation in the interstitial and perivascular spaces as well as by phenotypically transformed fibroblasts, termed myofibroblasts.

label: Sinus bradycardia
definition: Bradycardia related to a mean resting sinus rate of less than 50 beats per minute.

label: Abnormal electrophysiology of sinoatrial node origin
definition: An abnormality of the sinoatrial (SA) node in the right atrium. THe SA node acts as the pacemaker of the heart.

label: Muscular subvalvular aortic stenosis
definition: A type of subvalvular aortic stenosis resulting from thickening of the musculature of the interventricular septum, which results in obstruction to blood flow through the left-ventricular outflow tract.

label: Atrial arrhythmia
definition: A type of supraventricular tachycardia in which the atria are the principal site of electrophysiologic disturbance.

label: Supraventricular arrhythmia
definition: A type of arrhythmia that originates above the ventricles, whereby the electrical impulse propagates down the normal His Purkinje system similar to normal sinus rhythm.

label: Cardiac shunt
definition: Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system.

label: Abnormality of blood circulation
definition: An abnormality of blood circulation.

label: Right-to-left shunt
definition: Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from the right side of the heart to the left.

label: Situs inversus totalis
definition: A left-right reversal (or mirror reflection) of the anatomical location of the major thoracic and abdominal organs.

label: Abnormal spatial orientation of the cardiac segments
definition: Abnormality of the spatial relationship of the cardiac segments to other components of the heart.

label: Abnormal pericardium morphology
definition: An abnormality of the pericardium, i.e., of the fluid filled sac that surrounds the heart and the proximal ends of the aorta, vena cava, and the pulmonary artery.

label: Pericardial effusion
definition: Accumulation of fluid within the pericardium.

label: Constitutional symptom
definition: A symptom or manifestation indicating a systemic or general effect of a disease and that may affect the general well-being or status of an individual.

label: Myocardial necrosis
definition: Irreversible damage to heart tissue (myocardium) due to lack of oxygen after a heart attack (myocardial infarction).

label: Pericarditis
definition: Inflammation of the sac-like covering around the heart (pericardium).

label: Serositis
definition: Inflammation in any serous cavity.

label: Abnormal tricuspid valve morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the tricuspid valve.

label: Tricuspid valve prolapse
definition: One or more of the leaflets (cusps) of the tricuspid valve bulges back into the right atrium upon contraction of the right ventricle.

label: Right ventricular outlet tract obstruction
definition: An obstruction to the forward flow of blood in the outflow tract of the right ventricle.

label: Abnormal right ventricular function
definition: Anomalous physiology (function) of the right ventricle.

label: Endocardial fibroelastosis
definition: Diffuse thickening of the ventricular endocardium and by associated myocardial dysfunction

label: Abnormal endocardium morphology
definition: An abnormality of the endocardium.

label: Abnormal cardiac ventricle morphology
definition: An abnormality of a cardiac ventricle.

label: Right ventricular failure
definition: Reduced ability of the right ventricle to perform its function (to receive blood from the right atrium and to eject blood into the pulmonary artery), often leading to pitting peripheral edema, ascites, and hepatomegaly.

label: Third degree atrioventricular block
definition: Third-degree atrioventricular (AV) block (also referred to as complete heart block) is the complete dissociation of the atria and the ventricles. Third-degree AV block exists when more P waves than QRS complexes exist and no relationship (no conduction) exists between them.

label: Abnormal left ventricle morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the left ventricle of the heart.

label: Left ventricular hypertrophy
definition: Enlargement or increased size of the heart left ventricle.

label: Wolff-Parkinson-White syndrome
definition: A disorder of the cardiac conduction system of the heart characterized by ventricular preexcitation due to the presence of an abnormal accessory atrioventricular electrical conduction pathway.

label: Ventricular preexcitation
definition: An abnormality in which the cardiac ventricles depolarize too early as a result of an abnormality of cardiac conduction pathways such as an accessory pathway.

label: Coronary artery calcification
definition: An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in a coronary artery.

label: Arterial calcification
definition: Pathological deposition of calcium salts in one or more arteries.

label: Mitral stenosis
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the orifice of the mitral valve.

label: Double outlet right ventricle
definition: Double outlet right ventricle (DORV) is a type of ventriculoarterial connection in which both great vessels arise entirely or predominantly from the right ventricle.

label: Congenital malformation of the right heart
definition: Defect or defects of the morphogenesis of the right heart identifiable at birth.

label: High-output congestive heart failure
definition: A form of heart failure characterized by elevated cardiac output. This may be seen in patients with heart failure and hyperthyroidism, anemia, pregnancy, arteriovenous fistulae, and others.

label: Restrictive cardiomyopathy
definition: Restrictive left ventricular physiology is characterized by a pattern of ventricular filling in which increased stiffness of the myocardium causes ventricular pressure to rise precipitously with only small increases in volume, defined as restrictive ventricular physiology in the presence of normal or reduced diastolic volumes (of one or both ventricles), normal or reduced systolic volumes, and normal ventricular wall thickness.

label: Thromboembolic stroke
definition: A cerebrovascular accident (stroke) that occurs because of thromboembolism.

label: Thromboembolism
definition: The formation of a blood clot inside a blood vessel that subsequently travels through the blood stream from the site where it formed to another location in the body, generally leading to vascular occlusion at the distant site.

label: Abnormality of the pancreas
definition: An abnormality of the pancreas.

label: Pancreatitis
definition: The presence of inflammation in the pancreas.

label: Abnormality of pancreas physiology
definition: An anomaly of the function of the pancreas.

label: Annular pancreas
definition: A congenital anomaly in which the pancreas completely (or sometimes incompletely) encircles the second portion of duodenum and occasionally obstructs the more proximal duodenum.

label: Acute pancreatitis
definition: A acute form of pancreatitis.

label: Pancreatic cysts
definition: A cyst of the pancreas that possess a lining of mucous epithelium.

label: Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency
definition: Impaired function of the exocrine pancreas associated with a reduced ability to digest foods because of lack of digestive enzymes.

label: Abnormality of exocrine pancreas physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the acinar gland portion of the pancreas that secretes digestive enzymes.

label: Abnormal nasopharynx morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the nasopharynx.

label: Abnormal pharynx morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the pharynx.

label: Phimosis
definition: The male foreskin cannot be fully retracted from the head of the penis.

label: Abnormal preputium morphology
definition: An abnormality of the retractable fold of skin that covers the tip of the penis.

label: Nasal congestion
definition: Reduced ability to pass air through the nasal cavity often leading to mouth breathing.

label: Abnormality of the spleen
definition: An abnormality of the spleen.

label: Visceromegaly
definition: Abnormal increased size of the viscera of the abdomen.

label: Abnormal spleen morphology
definition: Any anomaly of the structure of the spleen.

label: Asplenia
definition: Absence (aplasia) of the spleen.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the spleen
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the spleen.

label: Accessory spleen
definition: An accessory spleen is a round, iso-echogenic, homogenic and smooth structure and is seen as a normal variant mostly on the medial contour of the spleen, near the hilus or around the lower pole. This has no pathogenic relevance.

label: Supernumerary spleens
definition: The presence of two or more accessory spleens.

label: Polysplenia
definition: Polysplenia is a congenital disease manifested by multiple small accessory spleens.

label: Single ventricle
definition: The presence of only one working lower chamber in the heart, usually with a virtual absence of the ventricular septum and usually present in conjunction with double inlet left or right ventricle.

label: Abnormal vestibular function
definition: An abnormality of the functioning of the vestibular apparatus.

label: Vestibular hyporeflexia
definition: A general descriptive term that describes impaired functioning of the vestibular apparatus that leads to manifestations such as dizziness or postural imbalance

label: High-frequency sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A form of sensorineural hearing impairment that affects primarily the higher frequencies.

label: Abnormal foot morphology
definition: An abnormality of the skeleton of foot.

label: Pes cavus
definition: An increase in height of the medial longitudinal arch of the foot that does not flatten on weight bearing (i.e., a distinctly hollow form of the sole of the foot when it is bearing weight).

label: Talipes equinovarus
definition: Talipes equinovarus (also called clubfoot) typically has four main components: inversion and adduction of the forefoot; inversion of the heel and hindfoot; equinus (limitation of extension) of the ankle and subtalar joint; and internal rotation of the leg.

label: Talipes
definition: A deformity of foot and ankle that has different subtypes that are talipes equinovarus, talipes equinovalgus, talipes calcaneovarus and talipes calcaneovalgus.

label: Pes planus
definition: A foot where the longitudinal arch of the foot is in contact with the ground or floor when the individual is standing; or, in a patient lying supine, a foot where the arch is in contact with the surface of a flat board pressed against the sole of the foot by the examiner with a pressure similar to that expected from weight bearing; or, the height of the arch is reduced.

label: Hammertoe
definition: Hyperextension of the metatarsal-phalangeal joint with hyperflexion of the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joint.

label: Toe deformity
definition: Abnormal positioning of toe phalanges. Deformities of the lesser toes often occur gradually, though they can be brought on by trauma. The main adult sagittal plane deformities consist of claw toes, hammer toes and mallet toes. Axial plane deformities include crossover toes.

label: Broad foot
definition: A foot for which the measured width is above the 95th centile for age; or, a foot that appears disproportionately wide for its length.

label: Abnormal toe morphology
definition: An anomaly of a toe.

label: Achilles tendon contracture
definition: A contracture of the Achilles tendon.

label: Abnormality of the Achilles tendon
definition: An abnormality of the Achilles tendon.

label: Foot joint contracture
definition: Contractures of one or more joints of the feet meaning chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in non-bony tissue.

label: Talipes equinovalgus
definition: A deformity of foot and ankle in which the foot is bent down and outwards.

label: Short foot
definition: A measured foot length that is more than 2 SD below the mean for a newborn of 27 - 41 weeks gestation, or foot that is less than the 3rd centile for individuals from birth to 16 years of age (objective). Alternatively, a foot that appears disproportionately short (subjective).

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving bones of the feet
Abnormal talus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the talus.

label: Bilateral talipes equinovarus
definition: Bilateral clubfoot deformity.

label: Bulbous tips of toes
definition: An abnormality of the morphology of the toes, such that the tips of the toes are prominent and bulbous.

label: Broad metatarsal
definition: Increased side-to-side width of a metatarsal bone.

label: Abnormal ankle morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the ankle.

label: Narrow foot
definition: A foot for which the measured width is below the 5th centile for age; or, a foot that appears disproportionately narrow for its length.

label: Premature rupture of membranes
definition: Premature rupture of membranes (PROM) is a condition which occurs in pregnancy when the amniotic sac ruptures more than an hour before the onset of labor.

label: Hydrops fetalis
definition: The abnormal accumulation of fluid in two or more fetal compartments, including ascites, pleural effusion, pericardial effusion, and skin edema.

label: Abnormal fetal morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the fetus.

label: Nonimmune hydrops fetalis
definition: A type of hydrops fetalis in which there is no identifiable circulating antibody to red blood cell antigens .

label: Fetal ascites
definition: Accumulation of fluid in the peritoneal cavity during the fetal period.

label: Abnormal fetal gastrointestinal system morphology
definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal gastrointestinal system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Small nail
definition: A nail that is diminished in length and width, i.e., underdeveloped nail.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nails
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the nail.

label: Hyperconvex nail
definition: When viewed on end (with the digit tip pointing toward the examiner's eye) the curve of the nail forms a tighter curve of convexity.

label: Anonychia
definition: Aplasia of the nail.

label: Short nail
definition: Decreased length of nail.

label: Hypoplastic toenails
definition: Underdevelopment of the toenail.

label: Aplastic/hypoplastic toenail
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the toenail.

label: Absent toenail
definition: Congenital absence of the toenail.

label: Nail pits
definition: Small (typically about 1 mm or less in size) depressions on the dorsal nail surface.

label: Abnormal nail surface
definition: An anomaly of the surface of the nail.

label: Hypoplastic fingernail
definition: Underdevelopment of a fingernail.

label: Onychogryposis
definition: Nail that appears thick when viewed on end.

label: Onycholysis
definition: Detachment of the nail from the nail bed.

label: Abnormal nail attachment
definition: An anomaly of the connection of the nail to the nailbed.

label: Ridged nail
definition: Longitudinal, linear prominences in the nail plate.

label: Fragile nails
definition: Nails that easily break.

label: Split nail
definition: A nail plate that has a longitudinal separation and the two sections of the nail share the same lateral radius of curvature.

label: Dystrophic toenail
definition: Toenail changes apart from changes of the color of the toenail (nail dyschromia) that involve partial or complete disruption of the various keratinous layers of the nail plate.

label: Abnormal toenail morphology
definition: An anomaly of the toenail.

label: Nail dystrophy
definition: Onychodystrophy (nail dystrophy) refers to nail changes apart from changes of the color (nail dyschromia) and involves partial or complete disruption of the various keratinous layers of the nail plate.

label: Hyperconvex fingernails
definition: When viewed on end (with the finger tip pointing toward the examiner's eye) the curve of the fingernail forms a tighter curve of convexity.

label: Deep-set nails
definition: Deeply placed nails.

label: Thin nail
definition: Nail that appears thin when viewed on end.

label: Absent fingernail
definition: Absence of a fingernail.

label: Paronychia
definition: The nail disease paronychia is an often-tender bacterial or fungal hand infection or foot infection where the nail and skin meet at the side or the base of a finger or toenail. The infection can start suddenly (acute paronychia) or gradually (chronic paronychia).

label: Abnormality of the periungual region
definition: An abnormality of the region around the nails of the fingers or toes.

label: Leukonychia
definition: White discoloration of the nails.

label: Abnormality of nail color
definition: An anomaly of the color of the nail.

label: Broad nail
definition: Increased width of nail.

label: Hallux valgus
definition: Lateral deviation of the great toe (i.e., in the direction of the little toe).

label: Deviation of the hallux
definition: Displacement of the big toe from its normal position.

label: Weight loss
definition: Reduction of total body weight.

label: Foot polydactyly
definition: A kind of polydactyly characterized by the presence of a supernumerary toe or toes.

label: Postaxial foot polydactyly
definition: Polydactyly of the foot most commonly refers to the presence of six toes on one foot. Postaxial polydactyly affects the lateral ray and the duplication may range from a well-formed articulated digit to a rudimentary digit.

label: Abnormal fifth toe morphology
definition: An anomaly of the little toe.

label: Short toe
definition: A toe that appears disproportionately short compared to the foot.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of toe
definition: Absence or hypoplasia of toes.

label: Long foot
definition: Increased back to front length of the foot.

label: Camptodactyly of toe
definition: Camptodactyly is a painless flexion contracture of the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joint that is usually gradually progressive. This term refers to camptodactyly of one or more toes.

label: Flexion contracture of toe
definition: One or more bent (flexed) toe joints that cannot be straightened actively or passively.

label: Camptodactyly
definition: The distal interphalangeal joint and/or the proximal interphalangeal joint of the fingers or toes cannot be extended to 180 degrees by either active or passive extension.

label: Broad toe
definition: Visible increase in width of the non-hallux digit without an increase in the dorso-ventral dimension.

label: Rocker bottom foot
definition: The presence of both a prominent heel and a convex contour of the sole.

label: Split foot
definition: A condition in which middle parts of the foot (toes and metatarsals) are missing giving a cleft appearance. The severity is very variable ranging from slightly hypoplastic 3rd toe over absent 2nd or 3rd toes as far as oligo- or monodactyl feet.

label: Metatarsus adductus
definition: The metatarsals are deviated medially (tibially), that is, the bones in the front half of the foot bend or turn in toward the body.

label: Preaxial foot polydactyly
definition: Duplication of all or part of the first ray.

label: Abnormal hallux morphology
definition: This term applies for all abnormalities of the big toe, also called hallux.

label: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the toes
Overlapping toe
definition: Describes a foot digit resting on the dorsal surface of an adjacent digit when the foot is at rest. Initially clawing may be dynamic and only noticeable on walking. Over time the plantar plate tears, subluxation occurs at the metatarsophalangeal joint (MTPJ), and the deformity becomes permanent.

label: Long hallux
definition: Increased length of the big toe.

label: Long toe
definition: Toes that appear disproportionately long compared to the foot.

label: Calcaneovalgus deformity
definition: This is a postural deformity in which the foot is positioned up against the tibia. The heel (calcaneus) is positioned downward (that is, the ankle is flexed upward), and the heel is turned outward (valgus).

label: Abnormality of the calcaneus
definition: An abnormality of the calcaneus, also known as the heel bone, one of the or heel bone, one of the components of the tarsus of the foot which make up the heel.

label: Foot oligodactyly
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of toes.

label: Absent toe
definition: Aplasia of a toe. That is, absence of all phalanges of a non-hallux digit of the foot and the associated soft tissues.

label: Oligodactyly
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of digits.

label: Abnormality of the tarsal bones
definition: An abnormality of the tarsus are the cluster of seven bones in the foot between the tibia and fibula and the metatarsus, including the calcaneus (heel) bone and the talus (ankle) bone.

label: Sandal gap
definition: A widely spaced gap between the first toe (the great toe) and the second toe.

label: Podagra
definition: Gout affecting the Metatarsophalangeal joint of big toe.

label: Gout
definition: Recurrent attacks of acute inflammatory arthritis of a joint or set of joints caused by elevated levels of uric acid in the blood which crystallize and are deposited in joints, tendons, and surrounding tissues.

label: Short distal phalanx of toe
definition: Short distance from the end of the toe to the most distal interphalangeal crease or distal interphalangeal joint flexion point, i.e., abnormally short distal phalanx of toe.

label: Shortening of all phalanges of the toes
definition: Developmental hypoplasia (shortening) of all phalanges of the foot.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the distal phalanges of the toes
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the distal phalanges of the toes.

label: Symphalangism affecting the phalanges of the toes
Synostosis involving bones of the toes
Toe clinodactyly
definition: Bending or curvature of a toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe).

label: Clinodactyly
definition: An angulation of a digit at an interphalangeal joint in the plane of the palm (finger) or sole (toe).

label: Clinodactyly of the 5th toe
definition: Bending or curvature of a fifth toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe).

label: Autoamputation of foot
definition: The spontaneous detachment of a foot from the body due to long standing pathology.

label: Deep plantar creases
definition: The presence of unusually deep creases (ridges/wrinkles) on the skin of sole of foot.

label: Abnormality of the plantar skin of foot
definition: An abnormality of the plantar part of foot, that is of the soles of the feet.

label: Osteolytic defects of the distal phalanges of the toes
Abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues
definition: An abnormality of the hematopoietic system.

label: Abnormality of thrombocytes
definition: An abnormality of platelets.

label: Thrombocytopenia
definition: A reduction in the number of circulating thrombocytes.

label: Abnormal platelet count
definition: Abnormal number of platelets per volume of blood. In a healthy adult, a normal platelet count is between 150,000 and 450,000 per microliter of blood.

label: Abnormality of neutrophils
definition: A neutrophil abnormality.

label: Abnormal granulocyte morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality or abnormal count of granulocytes.

label: Neutropenia
definition: An abnormally low number of neutrophils in the peripheral blood.

label: Abnormal neutrophil count
definition: A deviation from the normal range of neutrophil cell counts in the circulation.

label: Pancytopenia
definition: An abnormal reduction in numbers of all blood cell types (red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets).

label: Abnormality of multiple cell lineages in the bone marrow
Abnormal erythrocyte morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of erythrocytes (red-blood cells).

label: Hemolytic anemia
definition: A type of anemia caused by premature destruction of red blood cells (hemolysis).

label: Anemia due to reduced life span of red cells
definition: A type of anemia related to a reduction in the average life span of red blood cells in the peripheral circulation, which is normally around 120 days.

label: Abnormal eosinophil morphology
definition: An abnormal count or structure of eosinophils.

label: Eosinophilia
definition: Increased count of eosinophils in the blood.

label: Leukocytosis
definition: An abnormal increase in the number of leukocytes in the blood.

label: Abnormal eosinophil count
definition: Any deviation from the normal number of eosinophils per volume in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal leukocyte morphology
definition: An abnormality of leukocytes.

label: Abnormal cellular immune system morphology
definition: An abnormality of the morphology or counts of the cells that make up the immune system.

label: Leukopenia
definition: An abnormal decreased number of leukocytes in the blood.

label: Abnormal leukocyte count
definition: Number of leukocytes per volume of blood beyond normal limits.

label: Positional foot deformity
definition: A foot deformity resulting due to an abnormality affecting the muscle and soft tissue. In contrast if the bones of the foot are affected the term structural foot deformity applies.

label: Talipes calcaneovalgus
definition: Talipes calcaneovalgus is a flexible foot deformity (as opposed to a rigid congenital vertical talus foot deformity) that can either present as a positional or structural foot deformity depending on severity and/or causality. The axis of calcaneovalgus deformity is in the tibiotalar joint, where the foot is positioned in extreme hyperextension. On inspection, the foot has an up and out" appearance
column5: with the dorsal forefoot practically touching the anterior aspect of the ankle and lower leg."

label: Short 2nd toe
definition: Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the second toe.

label: Foot osteomyelitis
definition: An infection of bone of the foot.

label: Osteomyelitis
definition: Osteomyelitis is an inflammatory process accompanied by bone destruction and caused by an infecting microorganism.

label: Lymphopenia
definition: A reduced number of lymphocytes in the blood.

label: Abnormal lymphocyte count
definition: Any abnormality in the total number of lymphocytes in the blood.

label: Megaloblastic anemia
definition: Anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal (megaloblasts).

label: Macrocytic anemia
definition: A type of anemia characterized by increased size of erythrocytes with increased mean corpuscular volume (MCV) and increased mean corpuscular hemoglobin (MCH).

label: Autoimmune hemolytic anemia
definition: An autoimmune form of hemolytic anemia.

label: Hypochromic anemia
definition: A type of anemia characterized by an abnormally low concentration of hemoglobin in the erythrocytes.

label: Thrombocytosis
definition: Increased numbers of platelets in the peripheral blood.

label: Anemia of inadequate production
definition: A kind of anemia characterized by inadequate production of erythrocytes.

label: Reticulocytopenia
definition: A reduced number of reticulocytes in the peripheral blood.

label: Abnormal reticulocyte morphology
definition: A reticulocyte abnormality.

label: Normocytic anemia
definition: A kind of anemia in which the volume of the red blood cells is normal.

label: Increased red blood cell mass
definition: The presence of an increased mass of red blood cells in the circulation.

label: Polycythemia
definition: Polycythemia is diagnosed if the red blood cell count, the hemoglobin level, and the red blood cell volume all exceed the upper limits of normal.

label: Increased hematocrit
definition: An elevation above the normal ratio of the volume of red blood cells to the total volume of blood.

label: Abnormal hematocrit
definition: Any deviation from the normal ratio of the volume of red blood cells to the total volume of blood.

label: Increased circulating hemoglobin concentration
definition: Concentration of hemoglobin in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal hemoglobin concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of hemoglobin in the blood.

label: Giant platelets
definition: Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers. The term giant platelet is used when the platelet is larger than the size of the average red cell in the field. (Description adapted from College of American Pathologists, Hematology Manual, 1998).

label: Increased mean platelet volume
definition: Average platelet volume above the upper limit of the normal reference interval.

label: Anemia
definition: A reduction in erythrocytes volume or hemoglobin concentration.

label: Neutropenia in presence of anti-neutropil antibodies
definition: A type of neutropenia that is observed in the presence of granulocyte-specific antibodies.

label: Congenital thrombocytopenia
definition: Thrombocytopenia with congenital onset.

label: Abnormal thrombosis
definition: Venous or arterial thrombosis (formation of blood clots) of spontaneous nature and which cannot be fully explained by acquired risk (e.g. atherosclerosis).

label: Hypoplastic anemia
definition: Anemia with varying degrees of erythrocytic hypoplasia without leukopenia or thrombocytopenia.

label: Leukemia
definition: A cancer of the blood and bone marrow characterized by an abnormal proliferation of leukocytes.

label: Hematological neoplasm
definition: Neoplasms located in the blood and blood-forming tissue (the bone marrow and lymphatic tissue).

label: Abnormal myeloid leukocyte morphology
definition: An abnormality of myeloid leukocytes.

label: Abnormal basophil morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality or abnormal count of basophils.

label: Granulocytopenia
definition: An abnormally reduced number of granulocytes in the blood.

label: Abnormal granulocyte count
definition: Any deviation from the normal cell count per volume of granulocytes in the blood circulation.

label: Aplastic anemia
definition: Aplastic anemia is defined as pancytopenia with a hypocellular marrow.

label: Renal amyloidosis
definition: A form of amyloidosis that affects the kidney. On hematoxylin and eosin stain, amyloid is identified as extracellular amorphous material that is lightly eosinophilic. These deposits often stain weakly for periodic acid Schiff (PAS), demonstrate a blue-to-gray hue on the trichrome stain and are typically negative on the Jones methenamine silver (JMS) stain. These tinctorial properties contrast with the histologic appearance of collagen, a major component of basement membranes, mesangial matrix and areas of sclerosis, which demonstrates strong positivity for PAS and JMS (See Figure 1 of PMID:25852856).

label: Amyloidosis
definition: The presence of amyloid deposition in one or more tissues. Amyloidosis may be defined as the extracellular deposition of amyloid in one or more sites of the body.

label: Acute kidney injury
definition: Sudden loss of renal function, as manifested by decreased urine production, and a rise in serum creatinine or blood urea nitrogen concentration (azotemia).

label: Renal artery stenosis
definition: The presence of stenosis of the renal artery.

label: Abnormal renal artery morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the renal artery.

label: Vacuolated lymphocytes
definition: The presence of clear, sharply defined vacuoles in the lymphocyte cytoplasm.

label: Abnormal lymphocyte morphology
definition: An abnormality of lymphocytes.

label: Reticulocytosis
definition: An elevation in the number of reticulocytes (immature erythrocytes) in the peripheral blood circulation.

label: Sideroblastic anemia
definition: Sideroblastic anemia results from a defect in the incorporation of iron into the heme molecule. A sideroblast is an erythroblast that has stainable deposits of iron in cytoplasm (this can be demonstrated by Prussian blue staining).

label: Acanthocytosis
definition: Acanthocytosis is a type of poikilocytosis characterized by the presence of spikes on the cell surface. The cells have an irregular shape resembling many-pointed stars.

label: Poikilocytosis
definition: The presence of abnormally shaped erythrocytes.

label: Abnormality of coagulation
definition: An abnormality of the process of blood coagulation. That is, altered ability or inability of the blood to clot.

label: Reduced factor XI activity
definition: Decreased activity of coagulation factor XI. Factor XI, also known as plasma thromboplastin antecedent, is a serine proteinase that activates factor IX.

label: Abnormality of the intrinsic pathway
definition: An abnormality of the intrinsic pathway (also known as the contact activation pathway) of the coagulation cascade.

label: Microcytic anemia
definition: A kind of anemia in which the volume of the red blood cells is reduced.

label: Acidosis
definition: Abnormal acid accumulation or depletion of base.

label: Abnormality of acid-base homeostasis
definition: An abnormality of the balance or maintenance of the balance of acids and bases in bodily fluids, resulting in an abnormal pH.

label: Metabolic acidosis
definition: Metabolic acidosis (MA) is characterized by a fall in blood pH due to a reduction of serum bicarbonate concentration. This can occur as a result of either the accumulation of acids (high anion gap MA) or the loss of bicarbonate from the gastrointestinal tract or the kidney (hyperchloremic MA). By definition, MA is not due to a respirary cause.

label: Hypoglycemia
definition: A decreased concentration of glucose in the blood.

label: Abnormal blood glucose concentration
definition: An abnormality of the concentration of glucose in the blood.

label: Fever
definition: Body temperature elevated above the normal range.

label: Abnormality of temperature regulation
definition: An abnormality of temperature homeostasis.

label: Ketosis
definition: Presence of elevated levels of ketone bodies in the body.

label: Renal tubular acidosis
definition: Acidosis owing to malfunction of the kidney tubules with accumulation of metabolic acids and hyperchloremia, potentially leading to complications including hypokalemia, hypercalcinuria, nephrolithiasis and nephrocalcinosis.

label: Alkalosis
definition: Depletion of acid or accumulation base in the body fluids.

label: Respiratory alkalosis
definition: Alkalosis due to excess loss of carbon dioxide from the body.

label: Abnormal circulating nitrogen compound concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a nitrogen compound in the blood circulation.

label: Diabetic ketoacidosis
definition: A type of diabetic metabolic abnormality with an accumulation of ketone bodies.

label: Ketoacidosis
definition: Acidosis resulting from accumulation of ketone bodies.

label: Recurrent fever
definition: Periodic (episodic or recurrent) bouts of fever.

label: Unexplained fevers
definition: Episodes of fever for which no infectious cause can be identified.

label: Truncal obesity
definition: Obesity located preferentially in the trunk of the body as opposed to the extremities.

label: Polydipsia
definition: Excessive thirst manifested by excessive fluid intake.

label: Abnormal drinking behavior
definition: Abnormal consumption of fluids with excessive or insufficient consumption of fluid or any other abnormal pattern of fluid consumption.

label: Metabolic alkalosis
definition: Metabolic alkalosis is defined as a disease state where the pH is elevated to greater than 7.45 secondary to some metabolic process.

label: Palpitations
definition: A sensation that the heart is pounding or racing, which is a non-specific sign but may be a manifestation of arrhythmia.

label: Abnormal speech discrimination
definition: A type of hearing impairment prominently characterized by a difficulty in understanding speech, rather than an inability to hear speech. Poor speech discrimination is a very common symptom of high frequency hearing loss.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of metatarsal bones
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the metatarsal bones.

label: Abnormal glomerular mesangium morphology
definition: An abnormality of the mesangium, i.e., of the central part of the renal glomerulus between capillaries.

label: Diffuse mesangial sclerosis
definition: Diffuse sclerosis of the mesangium, as manifestated by diffuse mesangial matrix expansion.

label: Abnormal tubulointerstitial morphology
definition: An abnormality that involves the tubules and interstitial tissue of the kidney.

label: Abnormal renal insterstitial morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the interstitium of the kidney. The renal interstitium is defined as the intertubular, extraglomerular, extravascular space of the kidney. It is bounded on all sides by tubular and vascular basement membranes and is filled with cells, extracellular matrix, and interstitial fluid.

label: Tubulointerstitial nephritis
definition: A form of inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules.

label: Hypersplenism
definition: A malfunctioning of the spleen in which it prematurely destroys red blood cells.

label: Abnormal spleen physiology
definition: Any anomaly of the function of the spleen.

label: Autoimmune thrombocytopenia
definition: The presence of thrombocytopenia in combination with detection of antiplatelet antibodies.

label: Decreased platelet glycoprotein IIb-IIIa
definition: Decreased cell membrane concentration of glycoprotein IIb-IIIa.

label: Abnormal platelet membrane protein expression
definition: Presence of reduced amount of a membrane protein on the cell membrane of platelets. This feature is typically measured by flow cytometry.

label: Reduced antithrombin III activity
definition: An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of antithrombin-III.

label: Abnormality of the extrinsic pathway
definition: An abnormality of the extrinsic pathway (also known as the tissue factor pathway) of the coagulation cascade.

label: Extramedullary hematopoiesis
definition: The process of hematopoiesis occurring outside of the bone marrow (in the liver, thymus, and spleen) in the postnatal organisms.

label: Megaloblastic bone marrow
definition: Abnormal increased number of megaloblasts in the bone marrow.

label: Schistocytosis
definition: The presence of an abnormal number of fragmented red blood cells (schistocytes) in the blood.

label: Sea-blue histiocytosis
definition: An abnormality of histiocytes, in which the cells take on a sea blue appearance due to abnormally increased lipid content. Histiocytes are a type of macrophage. Sea-blue histiocytes are typically large macrophages from 20 to 60 micrometers in diameter with a single eccentric nucleus whose cytoplasm if packed with sea-blue or blue-green granules when stained with Wright-Giemsa.

label: Abnormal macrophage morphology
definition: An abnormality of macrophages.

label: Reduced lymphocyte surface expression of CD43
definition: A reduction in the expression of CD43 on the cell surface of lymphocytes.

label: Abnormal lymphocyte surface marker expression
definition: Abnormal amount of a protein that is normally present on the cell surface of lymphocytes.

label: Food intolerance
definition: A detrimental reaction to a food, beverage, food additive, or compound found in foods that produces symptoms in one or more body organs and systems that is not mediated by an immune reaction.

label: Hypoketotic hypoglycemia
definition: A decreased concentration of glucose in the blood associated with a reduced concentration of ketone bodies.

label: Hyperammonemia
definition: An increased concentration of ammonia in the blood.

label: Azotemia
definition: An increased concentration of nitrogen compounds in the blood.

label: Recurrent hypoglycemia
definition: Recurrent episodes of decreased concentration of glucose in the blood.

label: Fetal akinesia sequence
definition: Decreased fetal activity associated with multiple joint contractures, facial anomalies and pulmonary hypoplasia. Ultrasound examination may reveal polyhydramnios, ankylosis, scalp edema, and decreased chest movements (reflecting pulmonary hypoplasia).

label: Organic aciduria
definition: Excretion of non-amino organic acids in urine.

label: Aciduria
definition: Excretion of urine with an acid pH, i.e., having an increased hydrogen ion concentration.

label: Renal Fanconi syndrome
definition: An inability of the tubules in the kidney to reabsorb small molecules, causing increased urinary loss of electrolytes (sodium, potassium, bicarbonate), minerals, glucose, amino acids, and water.

label: Abnormal renal tubular resorption
definition: An abnormality of renal absorption.

label: Hyperchloremic acidosis
definition: Acidosis (pH less than 7.35) that develops with an increase in ionic chloride.

label: Chronic metabolic acidosis
definition: Longstanding metabolic acidosis.

label: Chronic acidosis
definition: Longstanding abnormal acid accumulation or depletion of base.

label: Short columella
definition: Reduced distance from the anterior border of the naris to the subnasale.

label: Abnormal columella morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the columella.

label: Deep philtrum
definition: Accentuated, prominent philtral ridges giving rise to an exaggerated groove in the midline between the nasal base and upper vermillion border.

label: Tessier cleft
definition: A congenital malformation with a cleft (gap or opening) in the face.

label: Frontal bossing
definition: Bilateral bulging of the lateral frontal bone prominences with relative sparing of the midline.

label: Abnormal shape of the frontal region
definition: An abnormal shape of the frontal part of the head.

label: Potter facies
definition: A facial appearance characteristic of a fetus or neonate due to oligohydramnios experienced in the womb, comprising ocular hypertelorism, low-set ears, receding chin, and flattening of the nose.

label: Morphological central nervous system abnormality
definition: A structural abnormality of the central nervous system.

label: Vomiting
definition: Forceful ejection of the contents of the stomach through the mouth by means of a series of involuntary spasmic contractions.

label: Nausea and vomiting
definition: Nausea is a commonly encountered symptom that has been defined as an unpleasant painless subjective feeling that one will imminently vomit. Vomiting has been defined as the forceful expulsion of the contents of the stomach, duodenum, or jejunum through the oral cavity. While nausea and vomiting are often thought to exist on a temporal continuum, this is not always the case. There are situations when severe nausea may be present without emesis and less frequently, when emesis may be present without preceding nausea.

label: Diarrhea
definition: Abnormally increased frequency (usually defined as three or more) loose or watery bowel movements a day.

label: Abdominal symptom
definition: A subjective manifestation of disease localized to the abdomen.

label: Dysphagia
definition: Difficulty in swallowing.

label: Abnormal esophagus physiology
definition: Any physiological abnormality of the esophagus.

label: Nausea
definition: A sensation of unease in the stomach together with an urge to vomit.

label: Constipation
definition: Infrequent or difficult evacuation of feces.

label: Gastroesophageal reflux
definition: A condition in which the stomach contents leak backwards from the stomach into the esophagus through the lower esophageal sphincter.

label: Pyloric stenosis
definition: Pyloric stenosis, also known as infantile hypertrophic pyloric stenosis, is an uncommon condition in infants characterized by abnormal thickening of the pylorus muscles in the stomach leading to gastric outlet obstruction. Clinically infants are well at birth. Then, at 3 to 6 weeks of age, the infants present with projectile vomiting, potentially leading to dehydration and weight loss.

label: Abnormality of the pylorus
definition: An abnormality of the pylorus.

label: Anal atresia
definition: Congenital absence of the anus, i.e., the opening at the bottom end of the intestinal tract.

label: Abnormal anus morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the anus.

label: Malabsorption
definition: Impaired ability to absorb one or more nutrients from the intestine.

label: Abnormality of digestive system physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the digestive system.

label: Anal stenosis
definition: Abnormal narrowing of the anal opening.

label: Abdominal pain
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen.

label: Pain
definition: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.

label: Chronic diarrhea
definition: The presence of chronic diarrhea, which is usually taken to mean diarrhea that has persisted for over 4 weeks.

label: Abnormal esophagus morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the esophagus.

label: Abnormal gastrointestinal tract morphology
definition: Abnormal structure of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Esophageal atresia
definition: A developmental defect resulting in complete obliteration of the lumen of the esophagus such that the esophagus ends in a blind pouch rather than connecting to the stomach.

label: Poor suck
definition: An inadequate sucking reflex, resulting in the difficult of newborns to be breast-fed.

label: Feeding difficulties in infancy
definition: Impaired feeding performance of an infant as manifested by difficulties such as weak and ineffective sucking, brief bursts of sucking, and falling asleep during sucking. There may be difficulties with chewing or maintaining attention.

label: Abnormal rectum morphology
definition: An abnormaltiy of the rectum, the final segment of the large intestine that stores solid waste until it passes through the anus.

label: Abnormal large intestine morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the large intestine.

label: Anorectal anomaly
definition: An abnormality of the anus or rectum.

label: Rectal prolapse
definition: Protrusion of the rectal mucous membrane through the anus.

label: Hiatus hernia
definition: The presence of a hernia in which the upper part of the stomach, i.e., mainly the gastric cardia protrudes through the diaphragmatic esophageal hiatus.

label: Abnormal stomach morphology
definition: An abnormality of the stomach.

label: Inflammation of the large intestine
definition: Inflammation, or an inflammatory state in the large intestine.

label: Gastrointestinal inflammation
definition: Inflammation of the alimentary part of the gastrointestinal system.

label: Anorexia
definition: Anorexia, or the loss of appetite for food, is a medical condition.

label: Abnormal consumption behavior
definition: Recurrent abnormal consumption of food, liquids, or objects that could have negative consequences for the individual.

label: Esophageal varix
definition: Extreme dilation of the submucusoal veins in the lower portion of the esophagus.

label: Esophageal stricture
definition: A pathological narrowing of the esophagus that is caused by the development of a ring of scar tissue that constricts the esophageal lumen.

label: Esophageal stenosis
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the lumen of the esophagus.

label: Zollinger-Ellison syndrome
definition: A condition in which there is increased production of gastrin by a gastrin-secreting tumor (usually located in the pancreas, duodenum, or abdominal lymph nodes) that stimulates the gastric mucosa to maximal activity, with consequent gastrointestinal mucosal ulceration.

label: Neoplasm of the gastrointestinal tract
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Hypothermia
definition: Reduced body temperature due to failed thermoregulation.

label: Heat intolerance
definition: The inability to maintain a comfortable body temperature in warm or hot weather.

label: Malignant hyperthermia
definition: Malignant hyperthermia is characterized by a rapid increase in temperature to 39-42 degrees C. Malignant hyperthermia may occur in response to either inhalational anesthetics such as halothane, to muscle relaxants such as succinylcholine, or to exercise.

label: Renal cortical atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the cortex of the kidney.

label: Renal atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the kidney.

label: Proximal renal tubular acidosis
definition: A type of renal tubular acidosis characterized by a failure of the proximal tubular cells to reabsorb bicarbonate, leading to urinary bicarbonate wasting and subsequent acidemia.

label: Curved linear dimple below the lower lip
Abnormality of the glabella
definition: An abnormality of the glabella.

label: Prominent glabella
definition: Forward protrusion of the glabella.

label: Myopathic facies
definition: A facial appearance characteristic of myopathic conditions. The face appears expressionless with sunken cheeks, bilateral ptosis, and inability to elevate the corners of the mouth, due to muscle weakness.

label: Cerebral atrophy
definition: Atrophy (wasting, decrease in size of cells or tissue) affecting the cerebrum.

label: Atrophy/Degeneration affecting the cerebrum
definition: The presence of atrophy (wasting) of the cerebrum, also known as the telencephalon, the largest and most highly developed part of the human brain.

label: Abnormal forebrain morphology
definition: An abnormality of the forebrain, which has as its parts the telencephalon, diencephalon, lateral ventricles and third ventricle.

label: Abnormal pyramidal tract morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the pyramidal tract, whose chief element, the corticospinal tract, is the only direct connection between the brain and the spinal cord. In addition to the corticospinal tract, the pyramidal system includes the corticobulbar, corticomesencephalic, and corticopontine tracts.

label: Rigidity
definition: Continuous involuntary sustained muscle contraction. When an affected muscle is passively stretched, the degree of resistance remains constant regardless of the rate at which the muscle is stretched. This feature helps to distinguish rigidity from muscle spasticity.

label: Spastic gait
definition: Spasticity is manifested by increased stretch reflex which is intensified with movement velocity. This results in excessive and inappropriate muscle activation which can contribute to muscle hypertonia. Spastic gait is characterized by manifestations such as muscle hypertonia, stiff knee, and circumduction of the leg.

label: Gait ataxia
definition: A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to coordinate the movements required for normal walking. Gait ataxia is characteirzed by a wide-based staggering gait with a tendency to fall.

label: Bradykinesia
definition: Bradykinesia literally means slow movement, and is used clinically to denote a slowness in the execution of movement (in contrast to hypokinesia, which is used to refer to slowness in the initiation of movement).

label: Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure
definition: A bilateral tonic-clonic seizure is a seizure defined by a tonic (bilateral increased tone, lasting seconds to minutes) and then a clonic (bilateral sustained rhythmic jerking) phase.

label: Limb ataxia
definition: A kind of ataxia that affects movements of the extremities.

label: Increased neuronal autofluorescent lipopigment
definition: Lipofuscin, a generic term applied to autofluorescent lipopigment, is a mixture of protein and lipid that accumulates in most aging cells, particularly those involved in high lipid turnover (e.g., the adrenal medulla) or phagocytosis of other cell types (e g., the retinal pigment epithelium or RPE; macrophage). This term pertains if there is an increase in the neuronal accumulation of lipofuscin (also known as autofluorescent lipoprotein) more than expected for the age of the patient.

label: Increased cerebral lipofuscin
definition: Lipofuscin (age pigment) is a brown-yellow, electron-dense, autofluorescent material that accumulates progressively over time in lysosomes of postmitotic cells, such as neurons and cardiac myocytes. This term pertains if there is an increase in the accumulation of lipofuscin (also known as autofluorescent lipoprotein) more than expected for the age of the patient.

label: Dysdiadochokinesis
definition: A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to perform rapidly alternating movements, such as pronating and supinating his or her hand on the dorsum of the other hand as rapidly as possible.

label: Migraine
definition: Migraine is a chronic neurological disorder characterized by episodic attacks of headache and associated symptoms.

label: Headache
definition: Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.

label: Migraine with aura
definition: A type of migraine in which there is an aura characterized by focal neurological phenomena that usually proceed, but may accompany or occur in the absence of, the headache. The symptoms of an aura may include fully reversible visual, sensory, and speech symptoms but not motor weakness. Visual symptoms may include flickering lights, spots and lines and/or loss of vision and/or unilateral sensory symptoms such as paresthesias or numbness. At least one of the symptoms of an aura develops gradually over 5 or more minutes and/or different symptoms occur in succession.

label: Truncal ataxia
definition: Truncal ataxia is a sign of ataxia characterized by instability of the trunk. It usually occurs during sitting.

label: Hypoplasia of the corpus callosum
definition: Underdevelopment of the corpus callosum.

label: Intention tremor
definition: A type of kinetic tremor that occurs during target directed movement is called intention tremor. That is, an oscillatory cerebellar ataxia that tends to be absent when the limbs are inactive and during the first part of voluntary movement but worsening as the movement continues and greater precision is required (e.g., in touching a target such as the patient's nose or a physician's finger).

label: Kinetic tremor
definition: Tremor that occurs during any voluntary movement. It may include visually or non-visually guided movements. Tremor during target directed movement is called intention tremor.

label: Migraine without aura
definition: Repeated headache attacks lasting 4-72 h fulfilling at least two of the following criteria: 1) unilateral location, 2) pulsating quality, 3) moderate or severe pain intensity, and 4) aggravation by or causing avoidance of routine physical activity such as climbing stairs. Headache attacks are commonly accompanied by nausea, vomiting, photophobia, or phonophobia.

label: Encephalocele
definition: A neural tube defect characterized by sac-like protrusions of the brain and the membranes that cover it through openings in the skull.

label: Cephalocele
definition: A congenital defect in the skull, whereby there is a protrusion of part of the cranial contents through a congenital defect in the cranium, usually covered with skin or mucous membrane. The term encephalocele refers to a subclass of these lesions in which brain tissue protrudes through the defect.

label: Open neural tube defect
definition: A type of neural tube defect that is not covered by skin.

label: Occipital encephalocele
definition: A type of encephalocele (that is, a a protrusion of part of the cranial contents including brain tissue through a congenital opening in the cranium, typically covered with skin or mucous membrane) in the occipital region of the skull. Occipital encephalocele presents as a midline swelling over the occipital bone. It is usually covered with normal full-thickness scalp.

label: Abnormality of the respiratory system
definition: An abnormality of the respiratory system, which include the airways, lungs, and the respiratory muscles.

label: Abnormal respiratory system morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the respiratory system.

label: Abnormal lung morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the lung.

label: Pneumonia
definition: Inflammation of any part of the lung parenchyma.

label: Respiratory tract infection
definition: An infection of the upper or lower respiratory tract.

label: Restrictive ventilatory defect
definition: A functional defect characterized by reduced total lung capacity (TLC) not associated with abnormalities of expiratory airflow or airway resistance. Spirometrically, a restrictive defect is defined as FEV1 (forced expiratory volume in 1 second) and FVC (forced vital capacity) less than 80 per cent.
