definition: A carotid body tumor (also called paraganglionoma or chemodectoma) is a tumor found in the upper neck at the branching of the carotid artery. They arise from the chemoreceptor organ (paraganglion) located in the adventitia of the carotid artery bifurcation.

label: Osteosarcoma
definition: A malignant bone tumor that usually develops during adolescence and usually affects the long bones including the tibia, femur, and humerus. The typical symptoms of osteosarcoma comprise bone pain, fracture, limitation of motion, and tenderness or swelling at the site of the tumor.

label: Neoplasm of the skeletal system
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skeleton.

label: Sarcoma
definition: A connective tissue neoplasm formed by proliferation of mesodermal cells. Bone and soft tissue sarcomas are the main types of sarcoma. Sarcoma is usually highly malignant.

label: Basal cell carcinoma
definition: The presence of a basal cell carcinoma of the skin.

label: Coxa valga
definition: Coxa valga is a deformity of the hip in which the angle between the femoral shaft and the femoral neck is increased compared to age-adjusted values (about 150 degrees in newborns gradually reducing to 120-130 degrees in adults).

label: Abnormal femoral neck morphology
definition: An abnormality of the femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft).

label: Cloverleaf skull
definition: Trilobar skull configuration when viewed from the front or behind.

label: Small foramen magnum
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the foramen magnum.

label: Abnormal foramen magnum morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the foramen magnum.

label: Abnormal sella turcica morphology
definition: Abnormality of the sella turcica, a saddle-shaped depression in the sphenoid bone at the base of the human skull.

label: J-shaped sella turcica
definition: A deformity of the sella turcica whereby the sella extends further anterior than normal such that the anterior clinoid process appears to overhang it, giving the appearance of the letter J on imaging of the skull.

label: Broad skull
definition: Increased width of the skull.

label: Thickened calvaria
definition: The presence of an abnormally thick calvaria.

label: Pregnancy history
definition: Medical history of maternal diseases, exposures, or other relevant findings during the pregnancy of which the index person was the product.

label: Past medical history
definition: In a medical encounter, the physician generally will interview the patient about his or her current problem, and may perform additional testing. The past medical history (PMH) in contrast records information about the patient's medical, personal and family history that might be relevant to the presenting illness or to provide optimal clinical management. The PMH generally includes (if relevant) other major illnesses, hospitalizations, surgeries, injuries, allergies, gynecologic and obstetric history, family history, personal history including occupational history, alcohol and drug use, etc.

label: Abnormality of frontal sinus
definition: An abnormality of the frontal sinus, one of the mucosa-lined, normally air-filled paranasal sinuses of the bones of the skull. The frontal sinus is located within the frontal bone.

label: Absent frontal sinuses
definition: Aplasia of frontal sinus.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the frontal sinuses
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of frontal sinus.

label: Absent paranasal sinuses
definition: Aplasia of the paranasal sinuses.

label: Absent/hypoplastic paranasal sinuses
definition: Aplasia or hypoplasia of the paranasal sinuses.

label: Large sella turcica
definition: An abnormal enlargement of the sella turcica.

label: Platybasia
definition: A developmental malformation of the occipital bone and upper end of the cervical spine, in which the latter appears to have pushed the floor of the occipital bone upward such that there is an abnormal flattening of the skull base.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of facial bones
definition: A developmental defect characterized by absence or underdevelopment of one or more facial bone.

label: Sclerosis of skull base
definition: Increased bone density of the skull base without significant changes in bony contour.

label: Parietal foramina
definition: The presence of symmetrical and circular openings (foramina) in the parietal bone ranging in size from a few millimeters to several centimeters wide.

label: Large foramen magnum
definition: An abnormal increase in the size of the foramen magnum.

label: Abnormality of skull ossification
definition: An abnormality of the process of ossification of the skull.

label: High, narrow palate
definition: The presence of a high and narrow palate.

label: Palate telangiectasia
definition: The presence of small (ca. 0.5-1.0 mm) dilated blood vessels near the surface of the mucous membranes of the palate.

label: Prominent median palatal raphe
definition: Unusual prominence of the median palatal raphe, which is the ridge formed by the fusion of the two plates of the skull that form the hard palate.

label: Commissural lip pit
definition: A depression located at an oral commissure.

label: Lip pit
definition: A depression located on a lip.

label: Exaggerated median tongue furrow
definition: Increased depth of the median tongue furrow.

label: Downturned corners of mouth
definition: A morphological abnormality of the mouth in which the angle of the mouth is downturned. The oral commissures are positioned inferior to the midline labial fissure.

label: Abnormality of the immune system
definition: An abnormality of the immune system.

label: Lymphadenopathy
definition: Enlargement (swelling) of a lymph node.

label: Abnormal lymph node morphology
definition: A structural lymph node abnormality.

label: Recurrent bacterial infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to bacterial infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of bacterial infection.

label: Unusual infection
definition: A type of infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection. There are five general subtypes. (i) Opportunistic infection, meaning infection by a pathogen that is not normally able to cause infection in a healthy host (e.g., pneumonia by Pneumocystis jirovecii or CMV); (ii) Unusual location (focus) of an infection (e.g., an aspergillus brain abscess); (iii) a protracted course or lack of adequate response to treatment (e.g., chronic rhinosinusitis); (iv) Unusual severity or intensity of an infection; and (v) unusual recurrence of infections.

label: Decreased circulating IgA concentration
definition: Decreased levels of immunoglobulin A (IgA).

label: Decreased circulating antibody concentration
definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin in blood.

label: Abnormal circulating IgA concentration
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgA immunoglobulin in blood.

label: Immunodeficiency
definition: Failure of the immune system to protect the body adequately from infection, due to the absence or insufficiency of some component process or substance.

label: Abnormality of immune system physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the immune system.

label: Recurrent abscess formation
definition: An increased susceptibility to abscess formation, as manifested by a medical history of recurrent abscesses.

label: Absence of bactericidal oxidative respiratory burst in phagocytes
definition: An absence of the phase of elevated metabolic activity, during which oxygen consumption increases, that occurs in neutrophils, monocytes, and macrophages shortly after phagocytosing material. An enhanced uptake of oxygen leads to the production, by an NADH dependent system, of hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), superoxide anions and hydroxyl radicals, which play a part in microbiocidal activity.

label: Abnormal phagocytosis
definition: An abnormal functioning of phagocytosis. Phagocytosis is an elegant but complex process for the ingestion and elimination of pathogens, but it is also important for the elimination of apoptotic cells and hence fundamental for tissue homeostasis. Phagocytosis can be divided into four main steps: (i) recognition of the target particle, (ii) signaling to activate the internalization machinery, (iii) phagosome formation, and (iv) phagolysosome maturation.

label: Recurrent Aspergillus infections
definition: An increased susceptibility to Aspergillus infections, as manifested by a history of recurrent episodes of Aspergillus infections.

label: Recurrent fungal infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to fungal infections, as manifested by multiple episodes of fungal infection.

label: Systemic lupus erythematosus
definition: A chronic, relapsing, inflammatory, and often febrile multisystemic disorder of connective tissue, characterized principally by involvement of the skin, joints, kidneys, and serosal membranes.

label: Recurrent Staphylococcus aureus infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to Staphylococcus aureus infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of Staphylococcus aureus infection.

label: Recurrent staphylococcal infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to staphylococcal infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of staphylococcal infections.

label: Chronic mucocutaneous candidiasis
definition: Recurrent or persistent superficial Candida infections of the skin, mucous membranes, and nails.

label: Recurrent cutaneous fungal infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to cutaneous fungal infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of cutaneous fungal infections.

label: Follicular hyperplasia
definition: Lymphadenopathy (enlargement of lymph nodes) owing to hyperplasia of follicular (germinal) centers.

label: Chronic noninfectious lymphadenopathy
definition: A chronic form of lymphadenopathy that is not related to infection.

label: Decreased lymphocyte apoptosis
definition: A reduction in the rate of apoptosis in lymphocytes.

label: Abnormal lymphocyte apoptosis
definition: A anomaly in the rate of programmed cell death (apoptosis) in lymphocytes.

label: Lymph node hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the lymph nodes.

label: Hypoplastic frontal sinuses
definition: Underdevelopment of frontal sinus.

label: Recurrent E. coli infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to infections with Escherichia coli, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection with this agent.

label: Recurrent gram-negative bacterial infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to infection by gram-negative bacteria, as manifested by a medical history of repeated or frequent infections by these agents.

label: Recurrent Serratia marcescens infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to Serratia marcescens infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of Serratia marcescens infection.

label: Recurrent Klebsiella infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to Klebsiella infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of Klebsiella infection.

label: Recurrent enteroviral infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to enteroviral infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of enteroviral infection.

label: Recurrent viral infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to viral infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of viral infection.

label: Oral leukoplakia
definition: A thickened white patch on the oral mucosa that cannot be rubbed off.

label: White lesion of the oral mucosa
definition: White lesions of the oral mucosa are generally caused by a condition that increases the thickness of the epithelium. This increases the distance to the vascular bed and thereby tends to change the usual reddish color of the oral mucosa to white. Common causes include hyperkeratosis (thickening of the keratin layer), acanthosis (thickening of the spinous cell layer), increased edema in the epithelium (leukoedema), and reduced vascularity of the underlying lamina propria. Additionally, fibrin caps or surface ulcerations and collapsed bullae can appear white.

label: Respiratory insufficiency due to muscle weakness
Rickets
definition: Rickets is divided into two major categories including calcipenic and phosphopenic. Hypophosphatemia is described as a common manifestation of both categories. Hypophosphatemic rickets is the most common type of rickets that is characterized by low levels of serum phosphate, resistance to ultraviolet radiation or vitamin D intake. There are several issues involved in hypophosphatemic rickets such as calcium, vitamin D, phosphorus deficiencies. Moreover, other disorder can be associated with its occurrence such as absorption defects due to pancreatic, intestinal, gastric, and renal disorders and hepatobiliary disease. Symptoms are usually seen in childhood and can be varied in severity. Severe forms may be linked to bowing of the legs, poor bone growth, and short stature as well as joint and bone pain. Hypophosphatemic rickets are associated with renal excretion of phosphate, hypophosphatemia, and mineral defects in bones. The familial type of the disease is the most common type of rickets.

label: Osteomalacia
definition: Osteomalacia is a general term for bone weakness owing to a defect in mineralization of the protein framework known as osteoid. This defective mineralization is mainly caused by lack in vitamin D. Osteomalacia in children is known as rickets.

label: Delayed skeletal maturation
definition: A decreased rate of skeletal maturation. Delayed skeletal maturation can be diagnosed on the basis of an estimation of the bone age from radiographs of specific bones in the human body.

label: Kyphoscoliosis
definition: An abnormal curvature of the spine in both a coronal (lateral) and sagittal (back-to-front) plane.

label: Kyphosis
definition: Exaggerated anterior convexity of the thoracic vertebral column.

label: Abnormal trabecular bone morphology
definition: Abnormal structure or form of trabecular bone.

label: Thin bony cortex
definition: Abnormal thinning of the cortical region of bones.

label: Abnormal cortical bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of compact bone (also known as cortical bone), which forms the dense surface of bones.

label: Pathologic fracture
definition: A pathologic fracture occurs when a bone breaks in an area that is weakened secondarily to another disease process such as tumor, infection, and certain inherited bone disorders. A pathologic fracture can occur without a degree of trauma required to cause fracture in healthy bone.

label: Recurrent fractures
definition: The repeated occurrence of bone fractures (implying an abnormally increased tendency for fracture).

label: Osteoarthritis
definition: Degeneration (wear and tear) of articular cartilage, i.e., of the joint surface. Joint degeneration may be accompanied by osteophytes (bone overgrowth), narrowing of the joint space, regions of sclerosis at the joint surface, or joint deformity.

label: Generalized joint hypermobility
definition: Joint hypermobility (ability of a joint to move beyond its normal range of motion) affecting many or all joints of the body. In individuals with Joint hypermobility at multiple sites (usually five or more), the term generalized joint hypermobility is preferred.

label: Multiple exostoses
definition: Presence of more than one exostosis. An exostosis is a benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface. It is capped by cartilage, and arises from a bone that develops from cartilage.

label: Abnormal cartilage morphology
definition: Any morphological abnormality of cartilage.

label: Stippled chondral calcification
definition: Punctate (speckled, dot-like) deposition of calcium of calcium salts in the articular cartilage (cartilage located in joints).

label: Calcific stippling
definition: An abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) pattern of calcifications in soft tissues within or surrounding bones (as observed on radiographs).

label: Calcification of cartilage
definition: The presence of calcium deposition in cartilage.

label: Bronchomalacia
definition: Weakness or softness of the cartilage in the walls of the bronchial tubes.

label: Upper airway obstruction
definition: Increased resistance to the passage of air in the upper airway.

label: Airway obstruction
definition: Obstruction of conducting airways of the lung.

label: Recurrent lower respiratory tract infections
definition: An increased susceptibility to lower respiratory tract infections as manifested by a history of recurrent lower respiratory tract infections.

label: Tracheobronchomalacia
definition: Weakness of the cartilage in the trachea and the bronchi, resulting in a floppy (non-rigid) airway. Affected persons may have difficulties to maintain patency of the airways.

label: Tracheal calcification
definition: Calcification (abnormal deposits of calcium) in the tracheal tissues.

label: Recurrent upper respiratory tract infections
definition: An increased susceptibility to upper respiratory tract infections as manifested by a history of recurrent upper respiratory tract infections (running ears - otitis, sinusitis, pharyngitis, tonsillitis).

label: Tachypnea
definition: Very rapid breathing.

label: Hypoventilation
definition: A reduction in the amount of air transported into the pulmonary alveoli by breathing, leading to hypercapnia (increase in the partial pressure of carbon dioxide).

label: Reduced vital capacity
definition: An abnormal reduction on the vital capacity, which is defined as the total lung capacity (volume of air in the lungs at maximal inflation) less the residual volume (i.e., volume of air in the lungs following maximal exhalation) of the lung.

label: Abnormal bone structure
definition: Any anomaly in the composite material or the layered arrangement of the bony skeleton.

label: Congenital contracture
definition: One or more flexion contractures (a bent joint that cannot be straightened actively or passively) that are present at birth.

label: Arthrogryposis multiplex congenita
definition: Multiple congenital contractures in different body areas.

label: Accelerated skeletal maturation
definition: An abnormally increased rate of skeletal maturation. Accelerated skeletal maturation can be diagnosed on the basis of an estimation of the bone age from radiographs of specific bones in the human body.

label: Coxa vara
definition: Coxa vara includes all forms of decrease of the femoral neck shaft angle (the angle between the neck and the shaft of the femur) to less than 120 degrees.

label: Abnormality of the knee
definition: An abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures.

label: Genu recurvatum
definition: An abnormally increased extension of the knee joint, so that the knee can bend backwards.

label: Hyperextensibility of the knee
definition: The ability of the knee joint to extend beyond its normal range of motion (the lower leg is moved beyond a straight position with respect to the thigh).

label: Abnormal morphology of the radius
definition: An abnormality of the radius.

label: Abnormal femur morphology
definition: Any anomaly of the structure of the femur.

label: Caudal appendage
definition: The presence of a tail-like skin appendage located adjacent to the sacrum.

label: Abnormal coccyx morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the coccyx.

label: Halberd-shaped pelvis
definition: An anomalous radiographic appearance of the developing pelvis, in which the greater ischiadic noth (incisura ischiadica major) is shallow and the pelvis takes on the appearance said to resemble a halberd (a weapon especially of the 15th and 16th centuries consisting typically of a battle-ax and pike mounted on a handle).

label: Lower extremity joint dislocation
definition: Displacement or malalignment of one or more joints in the lower extremity (leg).

label: Arthralgia
definition: Joint pain.

label: Cystic angiomatosis of bone
definition: Disseminated multifocal hemangiomatous or lymphangiomatous lesions of the skeleton. The lesions are lytic, well-defined, round or oval lesions within the medullary cavity, and they have an intact cortex, and manifest variable peripheral sclerosis and may exhibit endosteal scalloping.

label: Bone cyst
definition: A fluid filled cavity that develops with a bone.

label: Abnormal femoral metaphysis morphology
definition: An anomaly of the femoral metaphysis.

label: Flared lower limb metaphysis
definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of one or more long bones of the leg.

label: Aspiration
definition: Inspiration of a foreign object into the airway.

label: Bladder exstrophy
definition: Eversion of the posterior bladder wall through the congenitally absent lower anterior abdominal wall and anterior bladder wall.

label: Exstrophy
definition: Eversion of a hollow organ and exposure, inside out, and protruded through the abdominal wall.

label: Recurrent bronchitis
definition: An increased susceptibility to bronchitis as manifested by a history of recurrent bronchitis.

label: Bronchitis
definition: Inflammation of the large airways in the lung including any part of the bronchi from the primary bronchi to the tertiary bronchi.

label: Urinary bladder sphincter dysfunction
definition: Abnormal function of a sphincter of the urinary bladder.

label: Lymphadenitis
definition: Inflammation of a lymph node.

label: Unusual fungal infection
definition: An unusual fungal infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection by a fungal agent.

label: Recurrent Burkholderia cepacia infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to infections with Burkholderia cepacia, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection with this agent.

label: Abnormal T cell morphology
definition: An abnormality of T cells.

label: Abnormal B cell morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of B cells.

label: Impaired memory B cell generation
definition: Impaired production of memory cells, the B cells that persist for years or an entire lifetime and which confer rapid and enhanced response to secondary challenge.

label: Abnormality of B cell physiology
definition: An abnormality of the physiological functioning of B cells.

label: Decreased specific anti-polysaccharide antibody level
definition: The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against bacterial polysaccharides.

label: Decreased circulating level of specific antibody
definition: The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against a specific antigen or microorganism.

label: Absence of lymph node germinal center
definition: Absence of germinal centers in lymph nodes. Germinal centers are the parts of lymph nodes in which B lymphocytes proliferate, differentiate, mutate through somatic hypermutation and class switch during antibody responses.

label: Decreased circulating total IgM
definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin M (IgM) in blood.

label: Abnormal circulating IgM concentration
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgM immunoglobulin in blood.

label: Elevated proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative, alpha-beta regulatory T cells
definition: An abnormally increased proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative (double negative or DN) alpha-beta regulatory T cells (Tregs) as compared to total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of double-negative alpha-beta regulatory T cell
definition: An abnormal proportion of CD4-negative, CD8-negative (double negative or DN) alpha-beta regulatory T cells (Tregs) as compared to total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of HLA DR+ T cells
definition: An elevated proportion of T cells that express human leukocyte antigen (HLA)-DR. HLA-DR is an MHC class II cell surface receptor that presents antigens (peptides of at least 9 amino acids), thereby constituting a ligand for the T-cell receptor. HLA-DR can be upregulated in response to immune stimulation.

label: Abnormal T cell subset distribution
definition: Any abnormality in the proportion T cells subsets relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Genu valgum
definition: The legs angle inward, such that the knees are close together and the ankles far apart.

label: Bowing of the legs
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature affecting a long bone of the leg.

label: Abnormal knee morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures.

label: Meningioma
definition: The presence of a meningioma, i.e., a benign tumor originating from the dura mater or arachnoid mater.

label: Benign neoplasm of the central nervous system
Neoplasm of striated muscle
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumor) originating in striated muscle, either skeletal muscle or cardiac muscle.

label: Soft tissue sarcoma
definition: A type of sarcoma (A connective tissue neoplasm formed by proliferation of mesodermal cells) that develops from soft tissues like fat, muscle, nerves, fibrous tissues, blood vessels, or deep skin tissues.

label: Squamous cell carcinoma
definition: The presence of squamous cell carcinoma of the skin.

label: Melanoma
definition: The presence of a melanoma, a malignant cancer originating from pigment producing melanocytes. Melanoma can originate from the skin or the pigmented layers of the eye (the uvea).

label: Neoplasm by histology
definition: Neoplasm categorized according to type of histological abnormality.

label: Bladder carcinoma
definition: The presence of a carcinoma of the urinary bladder.

label: Bladder neoplasm
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the urinary bladder.

label: Myelodysplasia
definition: Clonal hematopoietic stem cell disorders characterized by dysplasia (ineffective production) in one or more hematopoietic cell lineages, leading to anemia and cytopenia.

label: Medullary thyroid carcinoma
definition: The presence of a medullary carcinoma of the thyroid gland.

label: Thyroid carcinoma
definition: The presence of a carcinoma of the thyroid gland.

label: Hypoplastic iliac wing
definition: Underdevelopment of the ilium ala.

label: Abnormal iliac wing morphology
definition: An anomaly of the ilium ala. This is the large expanded portion of the ilum which bounds the greater pelvis laterally.

label: Narrow iliac wing
definition: Decreased width of the wing (or ala) of the ilium (which is the large expanded portion which bounds the greater pelvis laterally).

label: Flared iliac wing
definition: Widening of the ilium ala, that is of the wing of the ilium, combined with external rotation, leading to a flared appearance of the iliac wing.

label: Obstructive sleep apnea
definition: Obstructive Sleep Apnea is a condition characterized by the obstruction of the airway and pauses in breathing during sleep, which occur multiple times throughout the night. It is related to the relaxation of muscle tone that typically happens during sleep, leading to a partial collapse of the soft tissues in the airway and causing airflow obstruction.

label: Sleep apnea
definition: An intermittent cessation of airflow at the mouth and nose during sleep is known as sleep apnea. Apneas that last at least 10 seconds are considered significant, but individuals with sleep apnea may experience apneas lasting from 20 seconds up to 2 or 3 minutes. Patients may have up to 15 events per hour of sleep.

label: Central apnea
definition: Apnea resulting from depression of the respiratory centers in the medulla oblongata. There is a lack of respiratory effort rather than obstruction of airflow.

label: Apneic episodes precipitated by illness, fatigue, stress
definition: Recurrent episodes of apnea that are precipitated by factors such as illness, fatigue, or stress.

label: Exertional dyspnea
definition: Perceived difficulty to breathe that occurs with exercise or exertion and improves with rest.

label: Episodic tachypnea
definition: Episodes of very rapid breathing.

label: Nocturnal hypoventilation
definition: An abnormal reduction in alveolar ventilation occurring during sleep. This is characterized by a rise in arterial carbon dioxide.

label: Respiratory failure
definition: A severe form of respiratory insufficiency characterized by inadequate gas exchange such that the levels of oxygen or carbon dioxide cannot be maintained within normal limits.

label: Anisospondyly
definition: Abnormally increased variability of the size of the vertebral bodies.

label: Sudden episodic apnea
definition: Recurrent bouts of sudden, severe apnea that may be life-threatening.

label: Hyperventilation
definition: Hyperventilation refers to an increased pulmonary ventilation rate that is faster than necessary for the exchange of gases. Hyperventilation can result from increased frequency of breathing, an increased tidal volume, or both, and leads to an excess intake of oxygen and the blowing off of carbon dioxide.

label: Hepatoblastoma
definition: A kind of neoplasm of the liver that originates from immature liver precursor cells and macroscopically is composed of tissue resembling fetal or mature liver cells or bile ducts.

label: Medulloblastoma
definition: A rapidly growing embryonic tumor arising in the posterior part of the cerebellar vermis and neuroepithelial roof of the fourth ventricle in children. More rarely, medulloblastoma arises in the cerebellum in adults.

label: Malignant neoplasm of the central nervous system
definition: A tumor that originates in the pineal gland, has moderate cellularity and tends to form rosette patterns.

label: Vagal paraganglioma
definition: A tumor that develops in the retrostyloid compartment of the parapharyngeal space, arising from an island of paraganglion tissue derived from the neural crest that is located on the vagus nerve.

label: Ependymoma
definition: The presence of an ependymoma of the central nervous system.

label: Glioma
definition: The presence of a glioma, which is a neoplasm of the central nervous system originating from a glial cell (astrocytes or oligodendrocytes).

label: Uterine leiomyosarcoma
definition: The presence of a leiomyosarcoma of the uterus.

label: Leiomyosarcoma
definition: A smooth muscle connective tissue tumor, which is rare type of cancer that is a malignant neoplasm of smooth muscle. When such a neoplasm is benign, it is called a leiomyoma.

label: Pituitary adenoma
definition: A benign epithelial tumor derived from intrinsic cells of the adenohypophysis (anterior pituitary).

label: Neoplasm of the anterior pituitary
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the adenohypophysis, which is also known as the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland.

label: Neoplasm of the pancreas
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the pancreas.

label: Digestive system neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the digestive system.

label: Papillary thyroid carcinoma
definition: The presence of a papillary adenocarcinoma of the thyroid gland.

label: Parathyroid adenoma
definition: A benign tumor of the parathyroid gland that can cause hyperparathyroidism.

label: Neoplasm of the parathyroid gland
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the parathyroid gland.

label: Hypokalemia
definition: An abnormally decreased potassium concentration in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating calcium concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of calcium in the blood circulation.

label: Hyponatremia
definition: An abnormally decreased sodium concentration in the blood.

label: Abnormal blood sodium concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of sodium.

label: Hyperbilirubinemia
definition: An increased amount of bilirubin in the blood.

label: Hyperphosphatemia
definition: An abnormally increased phosphate concentration in the blood.

label: Microscopic hematuria
definition: Microscopic hematuria detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine.

label: Generalized aminoaciduria
definition: An increased concentration of all types of amino acid in the urine.

label: Aminoaciduria
definition: An increased concentration of an amino acid in the urine.

label: Elevated circulating hepatic transaminase concentration
definition: Elevations of the levels of SGOT and SGPT in the serum. SGOT (serum glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase) and SGPT (serum glutamic pyruvic transaminase) are transaminases primarily found in the liver and heart and are released into the bloodstream as the result of liver or heart damage. SGOT and SGPT are used clinically mainly as markers of liver damage.

label: Abnormal circulating hepatic transaminase concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of alanine aminotransferase or aspartate aminotransferase.

label: Methylmalonic acidemia
definition: Increased concentration of methylmalonic acid in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating dicarboxylic acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a dicarboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

label: Acidemia
definition: An abnormally low blood pH (usually defined as less than 7.35).

label: Myoglobinuria
definition: Presence of myoglobin in the urine.

label: Abnormal urine metabolite level
definition: Any deviation from the normal amount of a metabolite in urine.

label: Hyperchloriduria
definition: An increased concentration of chloride in the urine.

label: Abnormal urine chloride concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of chloride in the urine.

label: Abnormality of chromosome segregation
definition: An abnormality of chromosome segregation.

label: Abnormal cellular physiology
definition: An abnormality in a cellular process.

label: Hypomagnesemia
definition: An abnormally decreased magnesium concentration in the blood.

label: Abnormal magnesium concentration
definition: An abnormality of magnesium ion homeostasis.

label: Hypermagnesemia
definition: An abnormally increased magnesium concentration in the blood.

label: Ketonuria
definition: High levels of ketone bodies (acetoacetic acid, beta-hydroxybutyric acid, and acetone) in the urine. Ketone bodies are insignificant in the blood and urine of normal individuals in the postprandial or overnight-fasted state.

label: Decreased circulating ACTH concentration
definition: The concentration of corticotropin, also known as adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), is below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating adrenocorticotropin concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of corticotropin in the blood.

label: Increased CSF protein concentration
definition: Increased concentration of protein in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Abnormal CSF protein concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal range of a protein concentration in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Rheumatoid factor positive
definition: The presence in the serum of an autoantibody directed against the Fc portion of IgG.

label: Autoimmune antibody positivity
definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against the organism's own cells or tissues.

label: Elevated circulating thyroid-stimulating hormone concentration
definition: Increased concentration of thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal thyroid-stimulating hormone level
definition: Any deviation from the normal amount of the thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH), which is produced by the anterior pituitary gland and stimulates the function of the thyroid gland.

label: Histidinuria
definition: An increased concentration of histidine in the urine.

label: Increased proteinogenic amino acid level in urine
definition: An elevated level of a proteinogenic amino acid in the urine. These are the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine.

label: Decreased activity of the pyruvate dehydrogenase complex
Abnormality of mitochondrial metabolism
definition: A functional anomaly of mitochondria.

label: Impaired sensitivity to thyroid hormone
definition: Reduced sensitivity of end organs to thyroid hormone characterized by elevated serum levels of free thyroid hormone with nonsuppressed thyroid stimulating hormone.

label: Aldehyde oxidase deficiency
definition: A reduction in aldehyde oxidase level.

label: Ventral hernia
definition: Ventral hernia refers to a condition in which abdominal contents protrude through a weakened portion of the abdominal wall.

label: Distal sensory impairment
definition: An abnormal reduction in sensation in the distal portions of the extremities.

label: Somatic sensory dysfunction
definition: An abnormality of the primary sensation that is mediated by peripheral nerves (pain, temperature, touch, vibration, joint position). The word hypoesthesia (or hypesthesia) refers to a reduction in cutaneous sensation to a specific type of testing.

label: Hemivertebrae
definition: Absence of one half of the vertebral body.

label: Vertebral segmentation defect
definition: An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation during development.

label: Lumbar hyperlordosis
definition: An abnormal accentuation of the inward curvature of the spine in the lumbar region.

label: Hyperlordosis
definition: Abnormally increased curvature (anterior concavity) of the lumbar or cervical spine.

label: Thoracic kyphosis
definition: Over curvature of the thoracic region, leading to a round back or if sever to a hump.

label: Abnormal thoracic spine morphology
definition: An abnormality of the thoracic vertebral column.

label: Intervertebral space narrowing
definition: Decreased height of the intervertebral disk.

label: Abnormal intervertebral disk morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the intervertebral disk.

label: Supernumerary bones of the axial skeleton
Abnormal number of vertebrae
definition: A deviation from the normal number of vertebrae in the spinal column.

label: Cervical kyphosis
definition: Exaggerated convexity of the cervical vertebral column, causing the cervical spine to bow outwards and take on a rounded appearance.

label: Abnormal cervical curvature
definition: The presence of an abnormal curvature of the cervical vertebral column.

label: Vertebral fusion
definition: A developmental defect leading to the union of two adjacent vertebrae.

label: Synostosis of joints
definition: The abnormal fusion of neighboring bones across a joint.

label: Fused cervical vertebrae
definition: A congenital anomaly characterized by a joining (fusion) of two or more cervical vertebral bodies with one another.

label: Partial absence of cerebellar vermis
definition: Congenital absence of a part of the vermis of cerebellum.

label: Abnormal vertebral morphology
definition: An abnormality of one or more of the vertebrae.

label: Granulomatosis
definition: A granulomatous inflammation leading to multiple granuloma formation, which is a specific type of inflammation. A granuloma is a focal compact collection of inflammatory cells, mononuclear cells predominating, usually as a result of the persistence of a non-degradable product and of active cell mediated hypersensitivity.

label: Immune dysregulation
definition: Altered immune function characterized by lymphoid proliferation, immune activation, and excessive autoreactivity often leading to autoimmune/inflammatory complications.

label: Impaired Ig class switch recombination
definition: An impairment of the class-switch recombination process that normally leads B lymphocytes to produce IgG, IgA, or IgE.

label: Dysgammaglobulinemia
definition: Selective deficiency of one or more, but not all, classes of immunoglobulins.

label: Abnormal delayed hypersensitivity skin test
definition: Delay in cutaneous immune reaction to specific antigens mediated not by antibodies but by cells. The delayed hypersensitivity test is an immune function test measuring the presence of activated T cells that recognize a specific antigen and is performed by injecting a small amount of the antigen into the skin. The area of the injection is examined 48-72 hours thereafter.

label: Abnormality of T cell physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of T cells.

label: Cutaneous anergy
definition: Inability to react to a delayed hypersensitivity skin test.

label: Cubitus valgus
definition: Abnormal positioning in which the elbows are turned out.

label: Abnormality of the elbow
definition: An anomaly of the joint that connects the upper and the lower arm.

label: Genu varum
definition: A positional abnormality marked by outward bowing of the legs in which the knees stay wide apart when a person stands with the feet and ankles together.

label: Absent microvilli on the surface of peripheral blood lymphocytes
definition: Absence of the fingerlike protrusive, actin-dependent structures found on the surface of peripheral blood lymphocytes.

label: Reduced delayed hypersensitivity
definition: Decreased ability to react to a delayed hypersensitivity skin test.

label: Abnormal forearm morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lower arm.

label: Radioulnar synostosis
definition: An abnormal osseous union (fusion) between the radius and the ulna.

label: Abnormal morphology of ulna
definition: Any structural anomaly of the ulna, a bone of the forearm the extends from the elbow to the little finger.

label: Synostosis involving bones of the upper limbs
definition: An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones of the upper limbs.

label: Abnormality of the calf
definition: An abnormality of the calf, i.e. of the posterior part of the lower leg.

label: Bowing of the long bones
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of a long bone.

label: Femoral bowing
definition: Bowing (abnormal curvature) of the femur.

label: Tibial bowing
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of the tibia.

label: Abnormal tibia morphology
definition: Abnormality of the tibia (shinbone).

label: Micromelia
definition: The presence of abnormally small extremities.

label: Limb undergrowth
definition: Limb shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the extremities.

label: Hypoplasia of the radius
definition: Underdevelopment of the radius.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the radius
definition: A small/hypoplastic or absent/aplastic radius.

label: Forearm undergrowth
definition: Forearm shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the forearm.

label: Radial bowing
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of the radius.

label: Bowed forearm bones
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature affecting either the radius, the ulna, or both.

label: Elbow flexion contracture
definition: An elbow contracture that limits the ability of the elbow joint to be extended (straightened), meaning that the elbow is fixed in an flexed (bent) position.

label: Elbow contracture
definition: A limitation in the passive range of motion of the elbow resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin.

label: Fibular aplasia
definition: Absence of the fibula.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fibula
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the fibula.

label: Abnormal fibula morphology
definition: An anomaly of the calf bone (fibula), one of the two bones of the calf.

label: Patellar dislocation
definition: The kneecap normally is located within the groove termed trochlea on the distal femur and can slide up and down in it. Patellar dislocation occurs if the patella fully dislocates out of the groove.

label: Abnormal patella morphology
definition: Abnormality of the patella (knee cap).

label: Breast carcinoma
definition: The presence of a carcinoma of the breast.

label: Neoplasm of the breast
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the breast.

label: Ganglioneuroma
definition: A benign neoplasm that usually arises from the sympathetic trunk in the mediastinum, representing a tumor of the sympathetic nerve fibers arising from neural crest cells.

label: Neoplasm of the autonomic nervous system
definition: A tumor that arises from an element of the autonomic nervous system.

label: Neuroblastoma
definition: Neuroblastoma is a solid tumor that originate in neural crest cells of the sympathetic nervous system. Most neuroblastomas originate in the abdomen, and most abdominal neuroblastomas originate in the adrenal gland. Neuroblastomas can also originate in the thorax, usually in the posterior mediastinum.

label: Neuroblastic tumor
definition: A family of tumors arising in the embryonal remnants of the sympathetic nervous system, which includes neuroblastoma, ganglioneuroblastoma, and ganglioneuroma.

label: Peripheral primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm
definition: A primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm that occurs extracranially in soft tissue and bone.

label: Prolonged bleeding time
definition: Prolongation of the time taken for a standardized skin cut of fixed depth and length to stop bleeding.

label: Abnormality of the musculature
definition: Abnormality originating in one or more muscles, i.e., of the set of muscles of body.

label: Bulging epiphyses
definition: A morphological abnormality of epiphyses whereby they are abnormally outwardly curving (protuberant).

label: Enlarged epiphyses
definition: Increased size of epiphyses.

label: Flared metaphysis
definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of one or more long bones.

label: Metaphyseal cupping
definition: Metaphyseal cupping refers to an inward bulging of the metaphyseal profile giving the metaphysis a cup-like appearance.

label: Hypoplasia of the ulna
definition: Underdevelopment of the ulna.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the ulna
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the ulna.

label: Bowing of limbs due to multiple fractures
definition: Curvature of the shafts of the long bones due to multiple fractures.

label: Metaphyseal irregularity
definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the metaphyses.

label: Mesomelia
definition: Shortening of the middle parts of the limbs (forearm and lower leg) in relation to the upper and terminal segments.

label: Abnormality of the ankle
definition: An anomaly of the joint that connects the foot with the leg.

label: Ulnar bowing
definition: Bending of the diaphysis (shaft) of the ulna.

label: Diaphyseal sclerosis
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more diaphyses. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Increased density of long bones
definition: An abnormal increase in the bone density of the long bones.

label: Enlarged joints
definition: Increase in size of one or more joints.

label: Fibular hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the fibula.

label: Humeroradial synostosis
definition: An abnormal osseous union (fusion) between the radius and the humerus.

label: Abnormal humerus morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the structure of the humerus (i.e., upper arm bone).

label: Elbow dislocation
definition: Dislocation of the distal humerus out of the elbow joint, where the radius, ulna, and humerus meet.

label: Upper extremity joint dislocation
definition: Displacement or malalignment of one or more joints in the upper extremity (arm).

label: Abnormal shoulder morphology
definition: An abnormality of the shoulder, which is defined as the structures surrounding the shoulder joint where the humerus attaches to the scapula.

label: Shoulder flexion contracture
definition: Chronic reduction in active and passive mobility of the shoulder joint due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement.

label: Shoulder contracture
definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the shoulder joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

label: Radial head subluxation
definition: Partial dislocation of the head of the radius.

label: Joint subluxation
definition: A partial dislocation of a joint.

label: Enlarged metaphyses
definition: Abnormal increase in size of one or more metaphyses.

label: Tetraamelia
definition: Amelia of all four limbs.

label: Amelia
definition: Congenital absence (aplasia) of one or more limbs.

label: Patellar hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the patella.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the patella
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the patella.

label: Limited knee extension
definition: Reduced ability to extend (straighten) the knee joint.

label: Limitation of knee mobility
definition: An abnormal limitation of knee joint mobility.

label: Madelung deformity
definition: An anomaly related to partial closure, or failure of development of the ulnar side of the distal radial growth plate, which results in an arrest of epiphyseal growth of the medial and volar portions of the distal radius. This leads to shortening of the radius and relative overgrowth of the ulna.

label: Ankylosis
definition: A reduction of joint mobility resulting from changes involving the articular surfaces.

label: Flattened epiphysis
definition: Abnormal flatness (decreased height) of epiphyses.

label: Hypercalcemia
definition: An abnormally increased calcium concentration in the blood.

label: Hypoalbuminemia
definition: Reduction in the concentration of albumin in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating albumin concentration
definition: Deviation from normal concentration of albumin in the blood.

label: Hyperglycemia
definition: An increased concentration of glucose in the blood.

label: Hypoproteinemia
definition: A decreased concentration of protein in the blood.

label: Glycosuria
definition: An increased concentration of glucose in the urine.

label: Abnormal urinary organic compound level
definition: The amount of an organic compound in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal. An organic compound is defined here as a chemical compound that contains a carbon-hydrogen or carbon-carbon bond, although some other definitions exist. Examples of organic compounds includes alkanes, alkenes, alkynes, aromatic compounds, alcohols, ketones, aldehydes, carboxylic acids, and esters.

label: Abnormal circulating lipid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation.

label: Defective DNA repair after ultraviolet radiation damage
Abnormality of DNA repair
definition: An abnormality of the process of DNA repair, that is, of the process of restoring DNA after damage.

label: Hydroxyprolinuria
definition: An increased concentration of 4-hydroxy-L-proline in the urine.

label: Increased urinary non-proteinogenic amino acid level
definition: An increased level in the urine of an alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

label: Increased urinary potassium
definition: An increased concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine.

label: Dislocated radial head
definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint.

label: Recurrent long bone fractures
definition: An increased tendency to fractures of the long bones (Mainly, the femur, tibia, fibula, humerus, radius, and ulna).

label: Long-bone fracture
definition: A partial or complete breakage of a lone bone (e.g., the femur, tibia, fibula, humerus, radius, and ulna).

label: Long fibula
definition: Disproportionately long fibulae.

label: Acromesomelia
definition: Small hands and feet.

label: Lower-limb joint contracture
definition: A limitation in the passive range of motion of a joint of the lower limb resulting from loss of elasticity in the periarticular tissues owing to structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules or skin.

label: Hypoplasia of the capital femoral epiphysis
definition: Underdevelopment of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the capital femoral epiphysis
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Trophic limb changes
definition: Trophic changes occurring in a limb.

label: Trophic changes related to pain
definition: Trophic changes is a term used to describe abnormalities in the area of pain that include primarily wasting away of the skin, tissues, or muscle, thinning of the bones, and changes in how the hair or nails grow, including thickening or thinning of hair or brittle nails.

label: Limited hip extension
definition: Limitation of the extension of the hip, i.e., decreased ability to straighten the hip joint and thereby increase the angle between torso and thigh; moving the thigh or top of the pelvis backward.

label: Limited hip movement
definition: A decreased ability to move the femur at the hip joint associated with a decreased range of motion of the hip.

label: Short femur
definition: An abnormal shortening of the femur.

label: Aplasia/hypoplasia of the femur
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the femur.

label: Fibular overgrowth
definition: Relatively increased growth of the fibula compared to that of the tibia.

label: Slender long bone
definition: Reduced diameter of a long bone.

label: Increased carrying angle
definition: An abnormal increase in the carrying angle, which is the angle he long axis of the extended forearm as it lies lateral to the long axis of the arm.

label: Protuberances at ends of long bones
definition: The presence of multiple protuberances (bulges, or knobs) at the ends of the long bones.

label: Subperiosteal bone resorption
definition: Loss of bone mass occurring beneath the periosteum (the periosteum is the connective-tissue membrane that surrounds all bones except at the articular surfaces). This process may create a serrated and lace-like appearance in periosteal cortical bone.

label: Abnormal circulating cholesterol concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of cholesterol in the blood circulation.

label: Hyperglycinuria
definition: An increased concentration of glycine in the urine.

label: Increased serine family amino acid in urine
definition: An increased level of a serine family amino acid in the urine.

label: Hyperphosphaturia
definition: An increased excretion of phosphates in the urine.

label: Abnormality of urine homeostasis
definition: An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components.

label: Abnormal blood ion concentration
definition: Abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of a monoatomic ion.

label: Abnormal circulating metabolite concentration
definition: An abnormal level of an analyte measured in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating amino acid concentration
definition: The presence of an abnormal decrease or increase of one or more amino acids in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating carboxylic acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

label: Hypochloremia
definition: An abnormally decreased chloride concentration in the blood.

label: Abnormal blood chloride concentration
definition: An abnormality of chloride homeostasis or concentration in the body.

label: Abnormal EKG
definition: Abnormal rhythm of the heart.

label: Abnormality of cardiovascular system electrophysiology
definition: An anomaly of the electrical conduction physiology of the heart.

label: Abnormal circulating hormone concentration
definition: Concentration of a hormone in the blood circulation outside of normal limits.

label: Abnormality of circulating cortisol level
definition: An abnormality of the concentration of cortisol in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating organic compound concentration
definition: Any deviation of the concentration of an orrganic compound from the normal range. An organic compound is defined as any compound that contains a carbon atom.

label: Limb joint contracture
definition: A contracture (chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin) that prevent normal movement of one or more joints of the limbs.

label: Hypercholesterolemia
definition: An increased concentration of cholesterol in the blood.

label: Reduced factor VIII activity
definition: Reduced activity of coagulation factor VIII. Factor VIII (fVIII) is a cofactor in the intrinsic clotting cascade that is activated to fVIIIa in the presence of minute quantities of thrombin. fVIIIa acts as a receptor, for factors IXa and X.

label: Abnormal factor VIII activity
definition: A deviation from the normal activity of coagulation factor VIII. Factor VIII (fVIII) is a cofactor in the intrinsic clotting cascade that is activated to fVIIIa in the presence of minute quantities of thrombin. fVIIIa acts as a receptor, for factors IXa and X.

label: Low-molecular-weight proteinuria
definition: Excretion in urine of proteins of a size smaller than albumin (molecular weight 69 kD).

label: Hypocalciuria
definition: An abnormally decreased calcium concentration in the urine.

label: Lactic acidosis
definition: An abnormal buildup of lactic acid in the body, leading to acidification of the blood and other bodily fluids.

label: Abnormal peripheral myelination
definition: An abnormality of the myelination of motor and sensory peripheral nerves. These are axons for motor nerves and dendrites for sensory nerves in the strict anatomic sense.

label: Abnormal myelination
definition: Any anomaly in the process by which myelin sheaths are formed and maintained around neurons.

label: Cystinuria
definition: An increased concentration of cystine in the urine.

label: Abnormality of peripheral nerve conduction
definition: An abnormality of the conduction of electrical impulses by peripheral (motor or sensory) nerves. This finding is elicited by a nerve conduction study (NCS).

label: Abnormality of peripheral nervous system electrophysiology
definition: An abnormality of the function of the electrical signals with which peripheral nerve cells communicate with each other or with muscles.

label: Prolinuria
definition: Level of proline in the urine anove the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased blood urea nitrogen
definition: An increased amount of nitrogen in the form of urea in the blood.

label: Abnormal blood urea nitrogen concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of urea nitrogen in the blood.

label: Panhypogammaglobulinemia
definition: A reduction in the circulating levels of all the major classes of immunoglobulin. is characterized by profound decreases in all classes of immunoglobulin with an absence of circulating B lymphocytes.

label: T-wave inversion in the right precordial leads
T-wave inversion
definition: An inversion of the T-wave (which is normally positive).

label: Increased LDL cholesterol concentration
definition: An elevated concentration of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

label: Hyperlipoproteinemia
definition: An abnormal increase in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

label: Abnormal LDL cholesterol concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal homeostasis
definition: An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.

label: Increased serum serotonin
definition: A increased concentration of serotonin in the blood.

label: Decreased circulating adenosylcobalamin concentration
definition: The concentration of adenosylcobalam in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal. Adenosylcobalamin is one of the active forms of vitamin B12.

label: Abnormal circulating vitamin B12 concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of cobalamin (vitamin B12) in the blood. Vitamin B12 is one of the eight B vitamins.

label: Hypocholesterolemia
definition: An decreased concentration of cholesterol in the blood.

label: Hyperuricosuria
definition: An abnormally high level of uric acid in the urine.

label: Abnormality of urinary uric acid level
definition: Abnormal amount of urate in the urine.

label: Glutaric aciduria
definition: The concentration of glutaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Dicarboxylic aciduria
definition: An increased concentration of dicarboxylic acid in the urine.

label: Cystathioninuria
definition: An elevated urinary concentration of cystathionine.

label: Increased circulating ACTH level
definition: An abnormal increased in the concentration of corticotropin, also known as adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), in the blood.

label: Elevated circulating alkaline phosphatase concentration
definition: Abnormally increased serum levels of alkaline phosphatase activity.

label: Abnormality of alkaline phosphatase level
definition: An abnormality of alkaline phosphatase level.

label: Hyposthenuria
definition: An abnormally low urinary specific gravity, i.e., reduced concentration of solutes in the urine.

label: Abnormal urine osmolality
definition: A deviation from the normal range of concentration of particles in urine.

label: Hyperoxaluria
definition: Increased excretion of oxalates in the urine.

label: Abnormal isoelectric focusing of serum transferrin
definition: Glycosylated transferrin concentrations can be measured in serum as a marker of N-linked glycosylation fidelity. In the traditional nomenclature for congenital disorders of glycosylation, absence of entire glycans was designated type I, and loss of one or more monosaccharides as type II. These terms are retained for historical reasons but for new annotations the precise glycosylation defect should be recorded.

label: Abnormal protein N-linked glycosylation
definition: An anomaly of protein N-linked glycosylation, i.e., an abnormality of the protein glycosylation process in which a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit is added to a protein via a nitrogen atom in an amino acid residue in a protein.

label: 4-Hydroxyphenylpyruvic aciduria
definition: Increased relative concentration of 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvic acid in the urine.

label: Elevated urinary carboxylic acid
definition: An increased amount of carboxylic acid in the urine.

label: Elevated urinary delta-aminolevulinic acid
definition: An increased concentration of 5-aminolevulinic acid (CHEBI:17549) in the urine.

label: Abnormal hypothalamus physiology
definition: An abnormal functionality of the hypothalamus.

label: Abnormal gonadotropin-releasing hormone concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal circulating concentration of the normal gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH). Intermittent GnRH secretion from the hypothalamus acts upon its receptor in the anterior pituitary to regulate the production and release of the gonadotropins, follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH).

label: Elevated circulating parathyroid hormone level
definition: An abnormal increased concentration of parathyroid hormone.

label: Abnormal circulating calcium-phosphate regulating hormone concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of a hormone that is involved in the regulation of phosphate and calcium.

label: Increased urinary taurine
definition: Increased concentration of taurine in the urine.

label: Increased urine proteinogenic amino acid derivative level
definition: An elevated urine level of a compound that is derived from an amino acid.

label: Carnosinuria
definition: An increased concentration of carnosine in the urine.

label: Dibasicaminoaciduria
definition: An increased level of a dibasic amino acid in the urine. Dibasic amino acids are usually referred to simply as basic aminoacids because they contain basic side chains at neutral pH. These are arginine (Arg), lysine (Lys), and histidine (His).

label: Abnormal acetabulum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the acetabulum, i.e., the Acetabular part of hip bone, which together with the head of the femur forms the hip joint.

label: Abnormal pubic bone morphology
definition: An anomaly of the the pubic bone, i.e., of the ventral and anterior of the three principal components (pubis, ilium, ischium) of the hip bone.

label: Hypoplastic pubic bone
definition: Underdevelopment of the pubis, which together with the ilium and the ischium, is one of the three bones that make up the hip bone.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the pubic bone
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the pubic bone.

label: Abnormal ischium morphology
definition: An anomaly of the ischium, which forms the lower and back part of the hip bone.

label: Hypoplastic ischia
definition: Underdevelopment of the ischium, which forms the lower and back part of the hip bone.

label: Squared iliac bones
definition: A shift from the normally round (convex) appearance of the iliac wing towards a square-like appearance.

label: Protrusio acetabuli
definition: Intrapelvic bulging of the medial acetabular wall.

label: Flat acetabular roof
definition: Flattening of the superior part of the acetabulum, which is a cup-shaped cavity at the base of the hipbone into which the ball-shaped head of the femur fits. The acetabular roof thereby appears horizontal rather than arched, as it normally does.

label: Wide pubic symphysis
definition: Abnormally increased width of the pubic symphysis is the midline cartilaginous joint uniting the superior rami of the left and right pubic bones.

label: Decreased hip abduction
definition: Reduced ability to move the femur outward to the side.

label: Short greater sciatic notch
definition: The sacroiliac joint in the bony pelvis connects the sacrum and the ilium of the pelvis, which are joined by strong ligaments. The notch is located directly superior to the joint. This term refers to a reduction in the height of the notch.

label: Abnormal greater sciatic notch morphology
definition: An abnormality of the sacrosciatic notch, i.e., the deep indentation in the posterior border of the hip bone at the point of union of the ilium and ischium.

label: Inverted nipples
definition: The presence of nipples that instead of pointing outward are retracted inwards.

label: Breast hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the breast.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the breasts
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the breasts.

label: Long nose
definition: Distance from nasion to subnasale more than two standard deviations above the mean, or alternatively, an apparently increased length from the nasal root to the nasal base.

label: Cleft ala nasi
definition: The presence of a notch in the margin of the ala nasi.

label: Allergic rhinitis
definition: It is characterized by one or more symptoms including sneezing, itching, nasal congestion, and rhinorrhea.

label: Allergy
definition: An allergy is an immune response or reaction to substances that are usually not harmful.

label: Short nasal bridge
definition: Decreased superior-inferior length of the nasal bridge, which is the saddle-shaped area that includes the nasal root and the lateral aspects of the nose.

label: Short nose
definition: Distance from nasion to subnasale more than two standard deviations below the mean, or alternatively, an apparently decreased length from the nasal root to the nasal tip.

label: Myopathy
definition: A disorder of muscle unrelated to impairment of innervation or neuromuscular junction.

label: Ragged-red muscle fibers
definition: An abnormal appearance of muscle fibers observed on muscle biopsy. Ragged red fibers can be visualized with Gomori trichrome staining as irregular and intensely red subsarcolemmal zones, whereas the normal myofibrils are green. The margins of affect fibers appear red and ragged. The ragged-red is due to the accumulation of abnormal mitochondria below the plasma membrane of the muscle fiber, leading to the appearance of a red rim and speckled sarcoplasm.

label: Abnormal muscle fiber morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the skeletal muscle cell. Muscle fibers are subdivided into two types. Type I fibers are fatigue-resistant and rich in oxidative enzymes (they stain light with the myosin ATPase reaction), and type II fibers are fast-contracting, fatigue-prone, and rich in glycolytic enzymes (these fibers stain darkly). Normal muscle tissue has a random distribution of type I and type II fibers.

label: Rhabdomyolysis
definition: Breakdown of muscle fibers that leads to the release of muscle fiber contents (myoglobin) into the bloodstream.

label: Skeletal muscle atrophy
definition: The presence of skeletal muscular atrophy (which is also known as amyotrophy).

label: Impaired oxidative burst
definition: In the NBT test, neutrophils change the colorless compound NBT into a compound with a deep blue color. If this test is negative (i.e., no blue color is produced), then this indicates a defect in superoxide-generating NADPH oxidase activity with inability to efficiently kill phagocytized bacteria.

label: Impaired neutrophil bactericidal activity
definition: A reduction in the ability of neutrophils to kill bacteria.

label: Intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
definition: The intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent storage material.

label: Curvilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
definition: An intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material in a curved pattern.

label: Vascular calcification
definition: Abnormal calcification of the vasculature.

label: Fingerprint intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
definition: An intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material in a trabecular or fingerprint-like pattern.

label: Decreased pyruvate carboxylase activity
definition: A decreased rate of pyruvate carboxylase activity.

label: Decreased methylmalonyl-CoA mutase activity
definition: An abnormality of Krebs cycle metabolism that is characterized by a decreased rate of methylmalonyl-CoA mutase activity.

label: Increased circulating IgE concentration
definition: An abnormally increased overall level of immunoglobulin E in blood.

label: Increased circulating antibody concentration
definition: An increased level of gamma globulin (immunoglobulin) in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating IgE concentration
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgE immunoglobulin in blood.

label: Deficient excision of UV-induced pyrimidine dimers in DNA
Prolonged G2 phase of cell cycle
Abnormality of the cell cycle
definition: An abnormality of the cell cycle.

label: Generalized amyloid deposition
definition: A diffuse form of amyloidosis.

label: Hyperglutaminemia
definition: An increased concentration of glutamine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating glutamine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of glutamine in the blood circulation.

label: Oroticaciduria
definition: An increased concentration of orotic acid in the urine.

label: Abnormal urine carboxylic acid level
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the urine.

label: Ethylmalonic aciduria
definition: The concentration of ethylmalonic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormality of chromosome stability
definition: A type of chromosomal aberration characterized by reduced resistance of chromosomes to change or deterioration.

label: Chromosomal breakage induced by crosslinking agents
definition: Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with DNA cross-linking agents such as diepoxybutane and mitomycin C.

label: Chromosome breakage
definition: Elevated rate of chromosomal breakage or interchanges occurring either spontaneously or following exposure to various DNA-damaging agents. This feature may be assayed by treatment of cultured lymphocytes with agents such as chemical mutagens, irradiation, and alkylating agents.

label: Decreased circulating methylcobalamin concentration
definition: The concentration of methylcobalamin in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal. Methylcobalamin is a form of vitamin B12.

label: Increased cellular sensitivity to UV light
Reduced coagulation factor V activity
definition: Decreased activity of coagulation factor V.

label: Abnormal coagulation factor V activity
definition: Any deviation from the activity of coagulation factor V.

label: Rectilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
definition: An intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material in a straight or rectilinear pattern.

label: Hypernatremia
definition: An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the blood.

label: Hypertyrosinemia
definition: An increased concentration of tyrosine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating tyrosine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of tyrosine in the blood circulation.

label: Decreased HDL cholesterol concentration
definition: An decreased concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

label: Hypolipoproteinemia
definition: An abnormal decrease in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

label: Abnormal HDL cholesterol concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL) in the blood.

label: Decreased circulating carnitine concentration
definition: Concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Abnormal circulating carnitine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation.

label: Hypermethioninemia
definition: An increased concentration of methionine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating methionine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of methionine in the blood circulation.

label: Elevated circulating creatine kinase concentration
definition: An elevation of the level of the enzyme creatine kinase (also known as creatine phosphokinase (CK; EC 2.7.3.2) in the blood. CK levels can be elevated in a number of clinical disorders such as myocardial infarction, rhabdomyolysis, and muscular dystrophy.

label: Abnormal circulating creatine kinase concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal circulating creatine kinase concentration.

label: Increased circulating IgG concentration
definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin G in blood.

label: Abnormal circulating IgG concentration
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgG immunoglobulin in blood.

label: Phosphoethanolaminuria
definition: An increased level of phosphoethanolamine (synonym: O-phosphoethanolamine) in the urine.

label: Increased phosphoribosylpyrophosphate synthetase level
definition: Abnormally elevated level of the enzyme phosphoribosyl pyrophosphatesynthetase, which catalyzes the synthesis of PP-ribose-P from ATP and ribose-5-phosphate.

label: Abnormal phosphoribosylpyrophosphate synthetase level
definition: Any deviation from the normal level of the enzyme phosphoribosyl pyrophosphatesynthetase, which catalyzes the synthesis of PP-ribose-P from ATP and ribose-5-phosphate.

label: Penile hypospadias
definition: Location of the urethral opening on the inferior aspect of the penis.

label: Prominent scrotal raphe
definition: Increased size of the ridge of tissue that extends along the midline of the scrotum.

label: Gonadal tissue inappropriate for external genitalia or chromosomal sex
Aplasia of the vagina
definition: Aplasia of the vagina.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the vagina
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the vagina.

label: Abnormality of the coagulation cascade
definition: An abnormality of the coagulation cascade, which is comprised of the contact activation pathway (also known as the intrinsic pathway) and the tissue factor pathway (also known as the extrinsic pathway) as well as cofactors and regulators.

label: Elevated circulating creatinine concentration
definition: An increased amount of creatinine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating creatinine concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of creatinine in the blood.

label: Hydroxyprolinemia
definition: An increased concentration of hydroxyproline in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating proline concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of proline or a proline metabolite in the blood circulation.

label: Increased circulating IgA concentration
definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin A in blood.

label: Anti-smooth muscle antibody positivity
definition: The presence in serum of antibodies against smooth muscle.

label: Neonatal hyperbilirubinemia
definition: A type of hyperbilirubinemia with neonatal onset.

label: Reduced orotidine 5-prime phosphate decarboxylase level
definition: An abnormal decrease in orotidine 5'-phosphate decarboxylase level.

label: Argininuria
definition: A increased concentration of arginine in the urine.

label: Increased glutamine family amino acid level in urine
definition: An elevated level of an glutamine family amino acid in the urine.

label: Hip contracture
definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the hip joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

label: Hypoplastic acetabulae
definition: Underdeveloped acetabulae.

label: Narrow pelvis bone
definition: Reduced side to side width of the pelvis.

label: Pelvic bone exostoses
definition: A benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface of the pelvis. Exostoses are capped by cartilage, and arise from a bone that develops from cartilage.

label: Square pelvis bone
definition: An abnormally squared appearance of the bony pelvis, a normally rounded or basin-shaped structure.

label: Coxa magna
definition: Widening of the femoral head and neck.

label: Increased circulating ferritin concentration
definition: Increased concentration of ferritin in the blood circulation.

label: Acute phase response
definition: Presence of one or more manifestations of the acute phase response. Acute phase proteins (APP) are blood proteins primarily synthesized by hepatocytes as part of the acute phase response (APR). The APR is part of the early-defense or innate immune system, which is triggered by different stimuli including trauma, infection, stress, neoplasia, and inflammation. The APR results in a complex systemic reaction with the goal of reestablishing homeostasis and promoting healing.

label: Abnormal circulating ferritin concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal circulating concentration of ferritin. Ferritin concentration can be measured in serum or plasma.

label: Low alkaline phosphatase
definition: Abnormally reduced serum levels of alkaline phosphatase.

label: Cystathioninemia
