definition: A partial dislocation of some or all of the small joints of the hand.

label: Abnormal hand cortical bone morphology
definition: An anomaly of the outer shell (cortex) of a hand bone.

label: Duplication of bones involving the upper extremities
Exostoses of hand bones
definition: Abnormal formation of new bone on the surface of a bone of the hand.

label: Synostosis involving bones of the hand
definition: An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones of the hand.

label: Short palm
definition: Short palm.

label: Narrow palm
definition: For children from birth to 4 years of age, the palm width is more than 2 SD below the mean; for children from 4 to 16 years of age the palm width is below the 5th centile; or, the width of the palm appears disproportionately narrow for its length.

label: Abnormal hand epiphysis morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the epiphyses of the phalanges or metacarpal bones.

label: Sclerosis of hand bones with transverse striations
Synostosis of second metacarpal-trapezoid
definition: Fusion of the second metacarpal-trapezoid.

label: Carpometacarpal synostosis
definition: Fusion involving carpal and metacarpal bones.

label: Subluxation of metacarpal phalangeal joints
definition: A partial dislocation affecting some or all of the metacarpophalangeal joints.

label: Abnormal metacarpophalangeal joint morphology
definition: An anomaly of a metacarpophalangeal joint.

label: Abnormal circulating immunoglobulin concentration
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in blood.

label: Decreased circulating IgG concentration
definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin G (IgG) in blood.

label: Decreased circulating aldosterone concentration
definition: Abnormally reduced levels of aldosterone.

label: Urogenital fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula affecting the genitourinary system.

label: Abnormality of body weight
definition: An abnormal increase or decrease of weight or an abnormal distribution of mass in the body.

label: Cachexia
definition: Severe weight loss, wasting of muscle, loss of appetite, and general debility related to a chronic disease.

label: Decreased skull ossification
definition: A reduction in the magnitude or amount of ossification of the skull.

label: Bone-marrow foam cells
definition: The presence of foam cells in the bone marrow, generally demonstrated by bone-marrow aspiration or biopsy. Foam cells have a vacuolated appearance due to the presence of complex lipid deposits, giving them a foamy or soap-suds appearance.

label: Myelin outfoldings
definition: The presence of excessive redundant myelin in the peripheral nerve sheath.

label: Peripheral hypermyelination
definition: Increased amount of peripheral myelination.

label: Abnormality of amino acid metabolism
definition: Abnormality of an amino acid metabolic process.

label: Abnormal metabolism
definition: An abnormality in the function of the chemical reactions related to processes including conversion of food to enter, synthesis of proteins, lipids, nucleic acids, and carbohydrates, or the elimination of waste products.

label: Abnormal circulating aromatic amino acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a aromatic amino acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating proteinogenic amino acid concentration
definition: An elevated level of a proteinogenic amino acid in the blood circulation. These are the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine.

label: Abnormal circulating sulfur amino acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a sulfur amino acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormality of vitamin metabolism
definition: An anomaly in the metabolism of a vitamin.

label: Abnormal galactosidase enyzme activity
definition: Abnormality of galactoside metabolism. A galactoside is a glycoside (a sugar moiety bound to some other moiety) containing galactose.

label: Abnormal glycosphingolipid metabolism
definition: An abnormality of glycosphingolipid metabolism.

label: Abnormality of glycolipid metabolism
definition: An abnormality of glycolipid metabolism.

label: Abnormality of bone mineral density
definition: This term applies to all changes in bone mineral density which (depending on severity) can be seen on x-rays as a change in density and or structure of the bone. Changes may affect all bones of the organism, just certain bones or only parts of bones and include decreased mineralisation as may be seen in osteoporosis or increased mineralisation and or ossification as in osteopetrosis, exostoses or any kind of atopic calicfications of different origin and distribution. The overall amount of mineralization of the bone-organ can be measured as the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones, usually measured by densitometry of the lumbar spine or hip. The measurements are usually reported as g/cm3 or as a Z-score (the number of standard deviations above or below the mean for the patient's age and sex). Note that measurement with this method does not reflect local changes in other bones, and as such might not be correct with regard the hole bone-organ.

label: Abnormal circulating purine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a purine in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating pyrimidine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a pyrimidine in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating leucine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal circulation of leucine in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating branched chain amino acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a branched chain family amino acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating fatty-acid concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of a fatty acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal enteric nervous system morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of nerves of the enteric nervous system.

label: Abnormal blood inorganic cation concentration
definition: An abnormality of divalent inorganic cation homeostasis.

label: Abnormal circulating tryptophan concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of tryptophan in the blood circulation.

label: Increased circulating purine concentration
definition: Abnormally elevated concentration of a purine compound. Purine compounds are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.

label: Decreased circulating purine concentration
definition: Abnormally reduced concentration of a purine compound. Purine compounds are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.

label: Abnormality of glycosaminoglycan metabolism
definition: Abnormality of glycosaminoglycan metabolism.

label: Weakness due to upper motor neuron dysfunction
definition: Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Paralysis due to lesions of the principle motor tracts is related to a lesion in the corticospinal, corticobulbar or brainstem descending (subcorticospinal) neurons.

label: Neoplasm of the nervous system
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the nervous system.

label: Neoplasm by anatomical site
definition: Neoplasm categorized according to the anatomical site of origin of the neoplasm.

label: Abnormality of the anus
definition: Abnormality of the anal canal.

label: Aortic valve calcification
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in the aortic valve.

label: Cardiac valve calcification
definition: Abnormal calcification of a cardiac valve.

label: Supravalvular aortic stenosis
definition: A pathological narrowing in the region above the aortic valve associated with restricted left ventricular outflow.

label: Mitral valve calcification
definition: Abnormal calcification of the mitral valve.

label: Hypoplastic left heart
definition: Underdevelopment of the left side of the heart. May include atresia of the aortic or mitral orifice and hypoplasia of the ascending aorta.

label: Congenital malformation of the left heart
definition: Defect or defects of the morphogenesis of the left heart identifiable at birth.

label: Type I truncus arteriosus
definition: Truncus arteriosus (single great artery leaving the base of the heart, giving rise to the coronary, pulmonary, and systemic arteries) with a short pulmonary trunk arises from the truncus arteriosus, giving rise to both pulmonary arteries.

label: Enterocolitis
definition: An inflammation of the colon and small intestine. However, most conditions are either categorized as Enteritis (inflammation of the small intestine) or Colitis (inflammation of the large intestine).

label: Microcolon
definition: A colon of abnormally small caliber.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the colon
definition: Congenital absence or underdevelopment of the colon.

label: Intestinal pseudo-obstruction
definition: A functional rather than mechanical obstruction of the intestines, associated with manifestations that resemble those caused by an intestinal obstruction, including distension, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, constipation or diarrhea, in an individual in whom a mechanical blockage has been excluded.

label: Hamartomatous polyposis
definition: Polyp-like protrusions which are histologically hamartomas. These can occur throughout the gastrointestinal tract. Hamartomatous polyps are composed of the normal cellular elements of the gastrointestinal tract, but have a markedly distorted architecture.

label: Intestinal polyp
definition: A discrete abnormal tissue mass that protrudes into the lumen of the intestine and is attached to the intestinal wall either by a stalk, pedunculus, or a broad base.

label: Hamartoma
definition: A disordered proliferation of mature tissues that is native to the site of origin, e.g., exostoses, nevi and soft tissue hamartomas. Although most hamartomas are benign, some histologic subtypes, e.g., neuromuscular hamartoma, may proliferate aggressively such as mesenchymal cystic hamartoma, Sclerosing epithelial hamartoma, Sclerosing metanephric hamartoma.

label: Prune belly
definition: A kind of congenital defect of the anterior abdominal wall in which the intestines are evident through the thin, lax, and protruding abdominal wall in affected infants.

label: Neoplasm of the stomach
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the stomach.

label: Malnutrition
definition: A deficiency in the intake of energy and nutrients.

label: Poor appetite
definition: A reduced desire to eat.

label: Congenital pyloric atresia
definition: Congenital atresia of the pylorus.

label: Meconium ileus
definition: Obstruction of the intestine due to abnormally thick meconium.

label: Fullness of paranasal tissue
definition: Increased bulk of tissue alongside the nose. The fullness can be caused by both bony and soft tissues.

label: Hyposmia
definition: A decreased sensitivity to odorants (that is, a decreased ability to perceive odors).

label: Deviated nasal septum
definition: Positioning of the nasal septum to the right or left in contrast to the normal midline position of the nasal septum.

label: Abnormality of the pulmonary artery
definition: An abnormality of the pulmonary artery.

label: Pulmonary artery stenosis
definition: An abnormal narrowing or constriction of the pulmonary artery, in the main pulmonary artery and/or in the left or right pulmonary artery branches.

label: Abnormal pulmonary artery morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure of the pulmonary artery.

label: Intermittent claudication
definition: Intermittent claudication is a symptom of peripheral arterial occlusive disease. After having walked over a distance which is individually characteristic, the patients experience pain or cramps in the calves, feet or thighs which typically subsides on standing still.

label: Abnormal arterial physiology
definition: An anomaly of arterial function.

label: Recurrent thrombophlebitis
definition: Repeated episodes of inflammation of a vein associated with venous thrombosis (blood clot formation within the vein).

label: Arterial thrombosis
definition: The formation of a blood clot inside an artery.

label: Elevated systolic blood pressure
definition: Abnormal increase in systolic blood pressure.

label: Biparietal narrowing
definition: A narrowing of the biparietal diameter (i.e., of the transverse distance between the protuberances of the two parietal bones of the skull).

label: Cranium bifidum occultum
definition: Cranium bifidum occultum, also known as Catlin mark, is a congenital midline skull defect presenting as an enlarged posterior fontanelle in the upper posterior angle of the parietal bone close to the intersection of the sagittal and lambdoid sutures. Cranium bifidum occultum occurs due to a defect in intramembranous ossification, a process through which skull bones (frontal, parietal, squamous temporal and occipital bones superior to the mendosal suture) ossify under a vascularized membrane toward the midline to cover the brain. Unlike cranium bifidum cysticum, cranium bifidum occultum does not have herniation of intracranial contents. As the skull grows, the midline cranium bifidum occultum defect is separated into bilateral enlarged parietal foramina (EPF) by a midline osseous bridge.

label: Flat forehead
definition: A forehead with abnormal flatness.

label: Elfin facies
definition: This is a description previously used to describe a facial form characterized by a short, upturned nose, wide mouth, widely spaced eyes, and full cheeks. Because of the imprecision in this definition it is preferable to describe these features precisely. This term is retained because it was often used in the past, but it should not be used for new annotations.

label: Severe combined immunodeficiency
definition: A type of primary immune deficiency that is characterized by a more severe defect in both the T- and B-lymphocyte systems.

label: Combined immunodeficiency
definition: A group of phenotypically heterogeneous genetic disorders characterized by profound deficiencies of T- and B-cell function, which predispose the patients to both infectious and noninfectious complications.

label: Reduced circulating complement concentration
definition: An immunodeficiency defined by the absent or suboptimal functioning of one of the complement system proteins.

label: Abnormality of complement system
definition: An abnormality of the complement system.

label: Agammaglobulinemia
definition: A lasting absence of total IgG and total IgA and total IgM in the blood circulation, whereby at most trace quantities can be measured.

label: Secretory IgA deficiency
definition: Deficiency of secretory IgA (polymers of 2-4 IgA monomers are linked by two additional chains) and is the primary antibody response at the mucosal level, where it forms immune complexes with pathogens and allergens.

label: Decreased immunoglobulin level in body fluid
definition: An reduction from normal levels of immunoglobulins in body fluids, such as mucous.

label: Decreased circulating complement C8 concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component C8 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating terminal complement component concentration
definition: Concentration below the lower limit of normal of one or more components of the the terminal membrane attack complex (MAC) portion of complement, which represents the lytic, pore-forming part of the system. The MAC comprises seven components: C5b, C6, C7, C8 (a heterotrimer composed of C8alpha, C8beta and C8gamma) and multiple copies of C9.

label: Cranial hyperostosis
definition: Excessive growth of the bones of cranium, i.e., of the skull.

label: Hyperostosis
definition: Excessive growth or abnormal thickening of bone tissue.

label: Hyperostosis frontalis interna
definition: Bony overgrowth of the internal (endosteal) surface of the frontal bone.

label: Craniofacial dysostosis
definition: A characteristic appearance resulting from defective ossification of craniofacial bones.

label: Coronal craniosynostosis
definition: Premature closure of the coronal suture of skull.

label: Sagittal craniosynostosis
definition: A kind of craniosynostosis affecting the sagittal suture.

label: Lambdoidal craniosynostosis
definition: A kind of craniosynostosis affecting the lambdoidal suture.

label: Spherocytosis
definition: The presence of erythrocytes that are sphere-shaped.

label: Elliptocytosis
definition: The presence of elliptical, cigar-shaped erythrocytes on peripheral blood smear.

label: Stomatocytosis
definition: The presence of erythrocytes with a mouth-shaped (stoma) area of central pallor on peripheral blood smear.

label: Fulminant hepatic failure
definition: Hepatic failure refers to the inability of the liver to perform its normal synthetic and metabolic functions, which can result in coagulopathy and alteration in the mental status of a previously healthy individual. Hepatic failure is defined as fulminant if there is onset of encephalopathy within 4 weeks of the onset of symptoms in a patient with a previously healthy liver.

label: Acute hepatic failure
definition: Hepatic failure refers to the inability of the liver to perform its normal synthetic and metabolic functions, which can result in coagulopathy and alteration in the mental status of a previously healthy individual. Hepatic failure is defined as acute if there is onset of encephalopathy within 8 weeks of the onset of symptoms in a patient with a previously healthy liver.

label: Preauricular skin furrow
definition: A groove of the skin immediately in front of the ear.

label: Postauricular skin tag
definition: A rudimentary tag of ear tissue often containing a core of cartilage and located just in back of the auricle (outer part of the ear).

label: Abnormality of the middle ear ossicles
definition: An abnormality of the middle-ear ossicles (three small bones called malleus, incus, and stapes) that are contained within the middle ear and serve to transmit sounds from the air to the fluid-filled labyrinth (cochlea).

label: Overfolding of the superior helices
definition: A condition in which the superior portion of the helix is folded over to a greater degree than normal.

label: Dilatated internal auditory canal
definition: The presence of a dilated inner part of external acoustic meatus.

label: Abnormality of the internal auditory canal
definition: An abnormality of the Internal acoustic meatus, i.e., of the canal in the petrous part of the temporal bone through which the cranial nerve VII and cranial nerve VIII traverse.

label: Exostosis of the external auditory canal
definition: A benign bony growth projecting outward from a bone surface within the external auditory canal.

label: Neoplasm of the outer ear
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the outer ear.

label: Congenital earlobe sinuses
definition: Pits in the earlobes at the location where ears are typically pierced for earrings.

label: Absent brainstem auditory responses
definition: Lack of measurable response to stimulation of auditory evoked potentials.

label: Abnormal auditory evoked potentials
definition: An abnormality of the auditory evoked potentials, which are used to trace the signal generated by a sound, from the cochlear nerve, through the lateral lemniscus, to the medial geniculate nucleus, and to the cortex.

label: Postauricular pit
definition: Benign congenital lesion of the postauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit.

label: Periauricular skin pits
definition: Benign congenital lesions of the periauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit.

label: Delayed brainstem auditory evoked response conduction time
definition: An abnormal increase (delay) in the conduction time of the brainstem auditory-evoked response.

label: Preauricular pit
definition: Small indentation anterior to the insertion of the ear.

label: Anomalous tracheal cartilage
definition: An abnormality of the C-shaped rings of hyaline cartilage, normally 16 to 20 in number, that occupy the anterior two-thirds of the circumference of the trachea (the posterior portion of the ring is completed by fibrous and smooth muscle tissue).

label: Chronic bronchitis
definition: Chronic inflammation of the bronchi.

label: Atretic occipital cephalocele
definition: A congenital defect in the occipital region of the skull, covered by skin of the scalp and containing meninges or remnants of glial or neural tissues.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita over the scalp vertex
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the scalp vertex, often just lateral to the midline.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita of scalp
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the scalp.

label: Mandibular hyperostosis
definition: Hyperostosis (bony overgrowth) of the mandible.

label: Facial hyperostosis
definition: Excessive growth (overgrowth) of the facial bones, that is of the facial skeleton.

label: Persistent open anterior fontanelle
definition: The anterior fontanelle generally ossifies by around the 18th month of life. A persistent open anterior fontanelle is diagnosed if closure is delayed beyond this age.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita over parietal area
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the scalp in the parietal area.

label: Progressive macrocephaly
definition: The progressive development of an abnormally large skull.

label: Relative macrocephaly
definition: A relatively mild degree of macrocephaly in which the head circumference is not above two standard deviations from the mean, but appears dysproportionately large when other factors such as body stature are taken into account.

label: Craniofacial asymmetry
definition: Asymmetry of the bones of the skull and the face.

label: Cessation of head growth
definition: Stagnation of head growth seen as flattening of the head circumference curve.

label: Acrobrachycephaly
definition: An abnormality of head shape characterized by the presence of a short, wide head as well as a pointy or conical form of the top of the head owing to premature closure of the coronal and lambdoid sutures.

label: Macrocephaly at birth
definition: The presence of an abnormally large skull with onset at birth.

label: Calvarial hyperostosis
definition: Excessive growth of the calvaria.

label: Large posterior fontanelle
definition: An enlargement of the posterior fontanelle relative to age-dependent norms.

label: Widely patent fontanelles and sutures
definition: An abnormally increased width of the cranial fontanelles and sutures.

label: Wide cranial sutures
definition: An abnormally increased width of the cranial sutures for age-related norms (generally resulting from delayed closure).

label: Craniofacial hyperostosis
definition: Excessive growth of the craniofacial bones.

label: Chronic rhinitis due to narrow nasal airway
Bilateral choanal atresia
definition: Bilateral absence (atresia) of the posterior nasal aperture (choana).

label: Pancreatic islet-cell hyperplasia
definition: Hyperplasia of the islets of Langerhans, i.e., of the regions of the pancreas that contain its endocrine cells.

label: Abnormality of the pancreatic islet cells
definition: An abnormality of the islet of Langerhans, i.e., of the regions of the pancreas that contain its endocrine cells. These are the alpha cells, which produce glucagon, the beta cells, which produce insulin and amylin, the delta cells, which produce somatostatin, the PP cells, which produce pancreatic polypeptide, and the epsilon cells, which produce ghrelin.

label: Long eyebrows
definition: Increased length of the hairs of the eyebrows.

label: Temporal hypotrichosis
definition: Reduced or lacking hair growth in the temporal region (i.e., around the temples on the side of the skull).

label: Congenital abnormal hair pattern
definition: A congenital abnormality of the distribution of hair growth.

label: Large clumps of pigment irregularly distributed along hair shaft
Generalized hypotrichosis
definition: Reduced or lacking hair growth in a generalized distribution.

label: Sacral hypertrichosis
definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the sacral region.

label: Anterior cervical hypertrichosis
definition: Anterior cervical hypertrichosis (ACH) or 'hairy throat' refers to the presence of a tuft of terminal hair on the anterior neck, just above the laryngeal prominence.

label: Congenital, generalized hypertrichosis
definition: A confluent, generalized overgrowth of silvery blonde to gray lanugo hair at birth.

label: Generalized hypertrichosis
definition: Generalized excessive, abnormal hairiness.

label: Cervical platyspondyly
definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates affecting the cervical spine.

label: Abnormal cervical spine morphology
definition: Any morphological abnormality of the cervical vertebral column.

label: Beaking of vertebral bodies
definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the vertebral bodies.

label: Increased spinal bone density
definition: Increased bone density affecting the bones of the spine (vertebral column).

label: Pear-shaped vertebrae
definition: Bulbous appearance of the anterior vertebral bodies, such that the vertebral bodies have the greatest vertical height anteriorly as well as bulbous anterior superior-inferior contours.

label: Increased vertebral height
definition: Increased top to bottom height of vertebral bodies.

label: Anterior wedging of T11
definition: An abnormality of the shape of the thoracic vertebra T11 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front).

label: Vertebral wedging
definition: An abnormal shape of the vertebral bodies whereby the vertebral bodies are thick on one side and taper to a thin edge at the other.

label: Sclerotic vertebral endplates
definition: Sclerosis (increased density) affecting vertebral end plates.

label: Anterior scalloping of vertebral bodies
definition: An excessive concavity of the anterior surface of one or more vertebral bodies.

label: Hypoplastic sacrum
definition: A developmental defect characterized by undergrowth of the sacrum, which is a large, triangular bone at the base of the spine that forms by the fusing of the sacral vertebrae (S1-S5).

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the sacrum
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the sacral bone.

label: Thoracic platyspondyly
definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates affecting the thoracic spine.

label: Hump-shaped mound of bone in central and posterior portions of vertebral endplate
Supernumerary vertebral ossification centers
definition: Three ossification sites are present in typical vertebral bodies (C3-L5): a single ossification center in the vertebral body, and one each in the two neural arches. This term applies if there are additional vertebral ossification centers present during the development and maturation of the spine.

label: Abnormally ossified vertebrae
definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of one or more vertebrae.

label: Absent or minimally ossified vertebral bodies
Spina bifida occulta at L5
definition: The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of the vertebra L5 with intact overlying skin.

label: Cervical C2/C3 vertebral fusion
definition: Fusion of cervical vertebrae at C2 and C3, caused by a failure in the normal segmentation or division of the cervical vertebrae during the early weeks of fetal development, leading to a short neck with a low hairline at the back of the head, and restricted mobility of the upper spine.

label: Absent vertebral body mineralization
definition: A lack of bone mineralization of the vertebral bodies.

label: Unossified vertebral bodies
definition: A lack of ossification of the vertebral bodies.

label: Anterior beaking of lower thoracic vertebrae
definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the lower thoracic vertebral bodies.

label: Anteriorly placed odontoid process
definition: Anterior mislocalization of the dens of the axis.

label: Lumbar spinal canal stenosis
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the lumbar spinal canal.

label: Spina bifida occulta at S1
definition: The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of S1 with intact overlying skin.

label: Cleft vertebral arch
definition: A discontinuity of the vertebral arch, i.e., of the posterior part of a vertebra.

label: Vertebral arch anomaly
definition: A morphological abnormality of the vertebral arch, i.e., of the posterior part of a vertebra.

label: Butterfly vertebral arch
definition: Butterfly vertebrae have a cleft through the body of the vertebrae and a funnel shape at the ends.

label: Lumbar kyphosis
definition: Over curvature of the lumbar region.

label: Enlarged vertebral pedicles
definition: Increased size of the vertebral pedicle.

label: Abnormal vertebral pedicle morphology
definition: Abnormal morphology of a vertebral pedical.

label: Progressive intervertebral space narrowing
definition: A progressive form of decreased height of the intervertebral disk.

label: Biconvex vertebral bodies
definition: Presence of abnormal convexity of the upper and lower end plates of the vertebrae, i.e., an exaggerated bulging out of the upper and lower vertebral end plates.

label: Small cervical vertebral bodies
definition: Reduced size of cervical vertebrae.

label: Anterior beaking of thoracic vertebrae
definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of thoracic vertebral bodies.

label: Decreased cervical spine flexion due to contractures of posterior cervical muscles
Cervical segmentation defect
definition: An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation of cervical vertebrae during development.

label: Lower thoracic kyphosis
definition: Over curvature of the lower thoracic region, leading to a round back or if sever to a hump.

label: Cervical C5/C6 vertebrae fusion
definition: Fusion of the C5 and C6 cervical vertebrae.

label: Elevated amniotic fluid alpha-fetoprotein
definition: An elevation of alpha-feto protein measured in the amniotic fluid.

label: Elevated circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
definition: Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Hypoplasia of the nasal bone
definition: Underdevelopment of the nasal bone.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nasal bone
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the nasal bone.

label: Hypoplasia of facial musculature
definition: Underdevelopment of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Frontalis muscle weakness
definition: Reduced strength of the frontalis muscle (which is located on the forehead).

label: Abnormal frontalis muscle physiology
definition: Abnormal function of the frontalis muscle, which covers parts of the forehead and is responsible for raising the eyebrows.

label: Facial midline hemangioma
definition: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, occurring in the midline region of the face.

label: Deep longitudinal plantar crease
definition: Narrow, paramedian longitudinal depressions in the plantar skin of the forefoot.

label: Talipes valgus
definition: Outward turning of the heel, resulting in clubfoot with the person walking on the inner part of the foot.

label: Short third metatarsal
definition: Underdevelopment of the Third metatarsal bone leading to a short (hypoplastic) third metatarsal bone.

label: Abnormality of the third metatarsal bone
definition: An abnormality of the third metatarsal bone.

label: Short metatarsal
definition: Diminished length of a metatarsal bone, with resultant proximal displacement of the associated toe.

label: Short fourth metatarsal
definition: Short fourth metatarsal bone.

label: Abnormality of the fourth metatarsal bone
Thickened Achilles tendon
definition: An abnormal thickening of the Achilles tendon.

label: 2-3 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes two and three.

label: 4-5 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes four and five.

label: Calcaneal epiphyseal stippling
definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the calcaneus.

label: Osteoporotic metatarsal
definition: Decrease in mass and density of the metatarsal bones.

label: Short fifth metatarsal
definition: Short (hypoplastic) fifth metatarsal bone.

label: Abnormality of the fifth metatarsal bone
definition: An anomaly of the fifth metatarsal bone.

label: Renal malrotation
definition: An abnormality of the normal developmental rotation of the kidney leading to an abnormal orientation of the kidney.

label: Reversible renal failure
definition: Acute renal failure with resolution of manifestations.

label: Axial malrotation of the kidney
definition: An abnormality of the normal developmental rotation of the kidney leading to an abnormal axial orientation of the kidney.

label: Hyperechogenic kidneys
definition: An increase in amplitude of waves returned in ultrasonography of the kidney, which is generally displayed as increased brightness of the signal.

label: Abnormal renal echogenicity
definition: Anomalous echogenicity of the kidney on ultrasound examination.

label: Thickened glomerular basement membrane
definition: Prominent glomerular basement membrane (GBM), reflecting an increase in thickness (subjective estimate) of the basal lamina of the glomerulus of the kidney.

label: Abnormal glomerular basement membrane morphology
definition: Any abnormal sttructure of the glomerular basement membrane.

label: Calcium nephrolithiasis
definition: The presence of calcium-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

label: Impaired renal concentrating ability
definition: A defect in the ability to concentrate the urine.

label: Acute tubulointerstitial nephritis
definition: Acute inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules.

label: Impaired renal uric acid clearance
definition: A reduction in the ability of the kidneys to remove uric acid from the serum.

label: Abnormality of renal excretion
definition: An altered ability of the kidneys to void urine and/or specific substances.

label: Renal cortical microcysts
definition: Cysts of microscopic size confined to the cortex of the kidney.

label: Crossed fused renal ectopia
definition: A developmental anomaly in which the kidneys are fused and localized on the same side of the midline. This anomaly is thought to result from disruption of the normal embryologic migration of the kidneys.

label: Global glomerulosclerosis
definition: Obliteration of the glomerular capillary lumen by increased collagenous matrix, with or without hyalinosis or foam cells. Sclerosis involves 100% of the glomerular tuft. Relative to other patent glomeruli in the sample, glomerular size is preserved, or increased/decreased by no more than 50%.

label: Chronic tubulointerstitial nephritis
definition: Chronic inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules.

label: Glomerular subendothelial electron-dense deposits
definition: Electron dense deposits at the glomerular basement membrane,

label: Atrial flutter
definition: A type of atrial arrhythmia characterized by atrial rates of between 240 and 400 beats per minute and some degree of atrioventricular node conduction block. Typically, the ventricular rate is half the atrial rate. In the EKG; atrial flutter waves are observed as sawtooth-like atrial activity. Pathophysiologically, atrial flutter is a form of atrial reentry in which there is a premature electrical impulse creates a self-propagating circuit.

label: Paroxysmal ventricular tachycardia
definition: Episodes of ventricular tachycardia that have a sudden onset and ending.

label: Ventricular tachycardia
definition: A tachycardia originating in the ventricles characterized by rapid heart rate (over 100 beats per minute) and broad QRS complexes (over 120 ms).

label: Congenital atrioventricular dissociation
definition: A form of atrioventricular (AV) dissociation (i.e., the atria and the ventricles are under the control of two separate pacemakers) with congenital onset.

label: Atrioventricular dissociation
definition: Atrioventricular (AV) dissociation is present if the atria and the ventricles are under the control of two separate pacemakers. AV dissociation can occur in the absence of a primary AV conduction disturbance.

label: Permanent atrial fibrillation
definition: Atrial fibrillation (AF) that cannot be successfully terminated by cardioversion, and longstanding (more than 1 year) AF, where cardioversion is not indicated or has not been attempted, is termed permanent.

label: Atrial fibrillation
definition: An atrial arrhythmia characterized by disorganized atrial activity without discrete P waves on the surface EKG, but instead by an undulating baseline or more sharply circumscribed atrial deflections of varying amplitude an frequency ranging from 350 to 600 per minute.

label: Supraventricular tachycardia
definition: Supraventricular tachycardia (SVT) is an abnormally increased heart rate (over 100 beats per minute at rest) with origin above the level of the ventricles.

label: Paroxysmal atrial fibrillation
definition: Episodes of atrial fibrillation that typically last for several hours up to one day and terminate spontaneously.

label: Effort-induced polymorphic ventricular tachycardia
definition: Polymorphic ventricular arrhythmias of varying morphologythat do not exist under resting conditions but appear only upon physical exercise or catecholamine administration.

label: Hypoplasia of right ventricle
definition: Underdevelopment or reduced size of the heart right ventricle, often due to a reduced number of cells.

label: Paroxysmal supraventricular tachycardia
definition: An episodic form of supraventricular tachycardia with abrupt onset and termination.

label: Myxomatous mitral valve degeneration
definition: Myxomatous mitral valve is defined as the presence of excess leaflet tissue and leaflet thickening greater than 5 mm, resulting in a prolapse greater than 2 mm into the left atrium on parasternal long axis view.

label: Sparse anterior scalp hair
definition: Decreased number of head hairs per unit area on the anterior region of the scalp.

label: Brittle scalp hair
definition: Fragile, easily breakable scalp hair.

label: Elbow hypertrichosis
definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the elbow region.

label: Duodenal polyposis
definition: Presence of multiple polyps in the duodenum.

label: Small intestinal polyposis
definition: The presence of multiple polyps in the small intestine.

label: Juvenile gastrointestinal polyposis
definition: The presence of multiple juvenile polyps in the stomach and intestine. The term juvenile polyps refer to a special histopathology and not the age of onset as the polyp might be diagnosed at all ages. The juvenile polyp has a spherical appearance and is microscopically characterized by overgrowth of an oedematous lamina propria with inflammatory cells and cystic glands. Juvenile polyps are a specific type of hamartomatous polyps.

label: Malrotation of colon
definition: An anatomical anomaly that results from an abnormal rotation of the gut as it returns to the abdominal cavity during embryogenesis.

label: Fulminant hepatitis
definition: Acute hepatitis complicated by acute liver failure with hepatic encephalopathy occurring less than 8 weeks after the onset of jaundice.

label: Hepatitis
definition: Inflammation of the liver.

label: Intestinal lymphedema
definition: Fluid retention and edema in the intestine caused by a compromised lymphatic system.

label: Intestinal edema
definition: Accumulation of cell free, noninflammatony fluid within the wall of the intestinal tract producing uniform thickening of the mucosal folds.

label: Lactose intolerance
definition: An inability to digest lactose.

label: Hypoplasia of the small intestine
definition: Underdevelopment of the small intestine.

label: Intestinal hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the intestine.

label: Esophageal ulceration
definition: Defect in the epithelium of the esophagus, essentially an open sore in the lining of the esophagus.

label: Rectoperineal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula between the perineum and the rectum.

label: Perineal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula between the bowel and the perineum.

label: Malrotation of small bowel
definition: A deviation from the normal rotation of the midgut during embryologic development with mislocalization of the small bowel.

label: Hamartomatous stomach polyps
definition: Polyp-like protrusions which are histologically hamartomas located in the stomach.

label: Multiple small bowel atresias
definition: The presence of multiple areas of atresia affecting the small intestine.

label: Recurrent infection of the gastrointestinal tract
definition: Recurrent infection of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Episodic hemolytic anemia
definition: A form of hemolytic anemia that occurs in repeated episodes.

label: Congenital hemolytic anemia
definition: A form of hemolytic anemia with congenital onset.

label: Acute myeloid leukemia
definition: A form of leukemia characterized by overproduction of an early myeloid cell.

label: Neonatal alloimmune thrombocytopenia
definition: Low platelet count associated with maternal platelet-specific alloantibodies.

label: Congenital hypoplastic anemia
definition: A type of hypoplastic anemia with congenital onset.

label: B Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia
definition: A type of ALL characterized by elevated levels of B-cell lymphoblasts in the bone marrow and the blood.

label: Acute lymphoblastic leukemia
definition: A form of acute leukemia characterized by excess lympoblasts.

label: Post-transfusion thrombocytopenia
definition: Sudden onset of thrombocytopenia (reduced platelet count) within 5-10 days of the transfusion of blood products. The clinical presentation is post-transfusion purpura (PTP), wigth severe thrmbocytopenia, epistaxis, and hemorrhages.

label: Fava bean-induced hemolytic anemia
definition: A kind of hemolytic anemia that is induced by the ingestion of fava beans.

label: Drug-sensitive hemolytic anemia
definition: A form of hemolytic anemia that is triggered by ingestion of certain drugs.

label: Normocytic hypoplastic anemia
definition: A type of hypoplastic anemia in which the erythrocytes have a normal cell volume (the mean corpuscular volume is within normal limits).

label: Acute myelomonocytic leukemia
definition: An acute leukemia characterized by the proliferation of both neutrophil and monocyte precursors.

label: Myeloid leukemia
definition: A leukemia that originates from a myeloid cell, that is the blood forming cells of the bone marrow.

label: Hypersegmentation of neutrophil nuclei
definition: An excessive division of the lobes of the nucleus of a neutrophil.

label: Abnormal neutrophil morphology
definition: An abnormal form or size of neutrophils.

label: Anisopoikilocytosis
definition: A type of poikilocytosis characterized by the presence in the blood of erythrocytes of varying sizes and abnormal shapes.

label: Increased hemoglobin oxygen affinity
definition: An abnormal increase in the binding affinity of hemoglobin for oxygen.

label: Abnormal erythrocyte physiology
definition: Any functional abnormality of erythrocytes (red-blood cells).

label: Folate-unresponsive megaloblastic anemia
definition: A type of megaloblastic anemia that does not improve upon administration of folate. Since vitamin B12 acts by promoting recycling of folate, administration of vitamin B12 also does not improve this type of anemia.

label: Refractory anemia with ringed sideroblasts
definition: A type of myelodysplastic syndrome characterized by less than 5% myeloblasts in the bone marrow, but with 15% or greater red cell precursors in the marrow being abnormal iron-stuffed cells called ringed sideroblasts.

label: Abnormal erythroid lineage cell morphology
definition: An anomaly of erythroid lineage cells, that is, of the erythropoietic cells in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes.

label: Single lineage myelodysplasia
definition: Abnormality/dysplasia of a single myeloid cell (erythroid, granulocytic, or megakaryocytic).

label: Recurrent thromboembolism
definition: Repeated episodes of obstruction of blood flow due to an embolus, i.e., blood clot that has traveled from its point of origin within the blood stream.

label: Microspherocytosis
definition: The presence of erythrocytes that are sphere-shaped and reduced in size.

label: Acute promyelocytic leukemia
definition: A type of acute myeloid leukemia in which abnormal promyelocytes predominate.

label: Pyropoikilocytosis
definition: A form of severe hemolytic anemia characterized by erythrocyte morphology reminiscent of that seen in patients after a thermal burn.

label: Hypochromic microcytic anemia
definition: A type of anemia characterized by an abnormally low concentration of hemoglobin in the erythrocytes and lower than normal size of the erythrocytes.

label: Reduced factor XII activity
definition: Decreased activity of coagulation factor XII. Factor XII (fXII) is part of the intrinsic coagulation pathway and binds to exposed collagen at site of vessel wall injury, activated by high-MW kininogen and kallikrein, thereby initiating the coagulation cascade.

label: Coombs-positive hemolytic anemia
definition: A type of hemolytic anemia in which the Coombs test is positive.

label: Acute monocytic leukemia
definition: The accumulation of transformed primitive hematopoietic blast cells, which lose their ability of normal differentiation and proliferation.

label: Prolonged bleeding after surgery
definition: Bleeding that persists longer than the normal time following a surgical procedure.

label: Prolonged bleeding following procedure
definition: Prolonged or protracted bleeding following an invasive procedure or intervention.

label: Ph-positive acute lymphoblastic leukemia
definition: A subset of acute lymphoblastic leukemia that results from a reciprocal translocation between the ABL-1 oncogene and a breakpoint cluster region (BCR), resulting in a fusion gene, BCR-ABL, that encodes an oncogenic protein with constitutively active tyrosine kinase activity.

label: Recurrent deep vein thrombosis
definition: Repeated episodes of the formation of a blot clot in a deep vein.

label: Folate-responsive megaloblastic anemia
definition: A type of megaloblastic anemia (i.e., anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal) that improves upon the administration of folate.

label: Reduced leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
definition: Decreased alkaline phosphatase measured within leukocytes.

label: Intermittent thrombocytopenia
definition: Reduced platelet count that occurs sporadically, i.e., it comes and goes.

label: Reduced protein S activity
definition: An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of vitamin K-dependent protein S. Protein S is a cofactor of protein C.

label: Abnormality of the protein C anticoagulant pathway
definition: An anomaly of the protein C anticoagulant pathway, which serves as a major system for controlling thrombosis, limiting inflammatory responses, and potentially decreasing endothelial cell apoptosis in response to inflammatory cytokines and ischemia. A natural anticoagulant system denoted the protein C pathway exerts its anticoagulant effect by regulating the activity of FVIIIa and FVa. The vitamin K-dependent protein C is the key component of the pathway. Activated protein C (APC) cleaves and inhibits coagulation cofactors FVIIIa and FVa, which result in downregulation of the activity of the coagulation system. The endothelial protein C receptor stimulates the T-TM-mediated activation of protein C on the endothelial cell surface. The two cofactors, protein S and the intact form of FV, enhance the anticoagulant activity of APC.

label: Normochromic microcytic anemia
definition: A type of anemia characterized by an normal concentration of hemoglobin in the erythrocytes and lower than normal size of the erythrocytes.

label: Hyperchromic macrocytic anemia
definition: A type of anemia characterized by abnormally large erythrocytes with abnormally high amounts of hemoglobin.

label: Amegakaryocytic thrombocytopenia
definition: Thrombocytopenia related to lack of or severe reduction in the count of megakaryocytes.

label: Thiamine-responsive megaloblastic anemia
definition: A type of megaloblastic anemia (i.e., anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal) that improves upon the administration of thiamine.

label: Elevated bone marrow ring sideroblast count
definition: Count of ring sideroblasts in the bone marrow above the upper limit of normal. Ring sideroblasts are nucleated erythroblasts with a pathologic accumulation of iron granules in the mitochondrial matrix. They can be detected by Prussian blue staining as blue perinuclear aggregates in bone marrow aspirate erythroblasts.

label: Impaired ADP-induced platelet aggregation
definition: Abnormal platelet response to ADP as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of ADP.

label: Chronic hemolytic anemia
definition: An chronic form of hemolytic anemia.

label: Incisional hernia
definition: An abdominal hernia that occurs at a site of weakness in the abdominal wall resulting from an incompletely-healed surgical wound.

label: Inspiratory stridor
definition: Inspiratory stridor is a high pitched sound upon inspiration that is generally related to laryngeal abnormalities.

label: Spontaneous neonatal pneumothorax
definition: Pneumothorax occurring neonatally without traumatic injury to the chest or lung.

label: Intercostal muscle weakness
definition: Lack of strength of the intercostal muscles, i.e., of the muscle groups running along the ribs that create and move the chest wall.

label: Intermittent hyperventilation
definition: Episodic hyperventilation.

label: Respiratory infections in early life
definition: Increased susceptibility to respiratory infections in early life, as manifested by recurrent episodes of respiratory infections.

label: Respiratory failure requiring assisted ventilation
definition: A state of respiratory distress that requires a life saving intervention in the form of gaining airway access and instituting positive pressure ventilation.

label: Intermittent episodes of respiratory insufficiency due to muscle weakness
Elevated pulmonary artery pressure
definition: An abnormally elevated blood pressure in the circulation of the pulmonary artery.

label: Recurrent infections due to aspiration
definition: Increased susceptibility to infections due to aspiration, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infections due to aspiration.

label: Stress/infection-induced lactic acidosis
definition: A form of lactic acidemia that occurs in relation to stress or infection.

label: Persistent lactic acidosis
definition: A continuous form of lactic acidemia.

label: Severe lactic acidosis
definition: A severe form of lactic acidemia.

label: Exercise-induced lactic acidemia
definition: A form of lactic acidemia that occurs following exercise or exertion.

label: Congenital lactic acidosis
definition: A form of lactic acidemia with congenital onset.

label: Maturity-onset diabetes of the young
definition: The term Maturity-onset diabetes of the young (MODY) was initially used for patients diagnosed with fasting hyperglycemia that could be treated without insulin for more than two years, where the initial diagnosis was made at a young age (under 25 years). Thus, MODY combines characteristics of type 1 diabetes (young age at diagnosis) and type 2 diabetes (less insulin dependence than type 1 diabetes). The term MODY is now most often used to refer to a group of monogenic diseases with these characteristics. Here, the term is used to describe hyperglycemia diagnosed at a young age with no or minor insulin dependency, no evidence of insulin resistance, and lack of evidence of autoimmune destruction of the beta cells.

label: Reduced circulating vitamin A concentration
definition: Concentration of vitamin A below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating vitamin A concentration
definition: Concentration of vitamin A in the blood circulation outside limits of normal.

label: Episodic metabolic acidosis
definition: Repeated transient episodes of metabolic acidosis, that is, of the buildup of acid or depletion of base due to accumulation of metabolic acids.

label: Intermittent lactic acidemia
definition: An intermittent (discontinuous) form of lactic acidemia.

label: Recurrent infantile hypoglycemia
definition: Recurrent episodes of decreased concentration of glucose in the blood occurring during the infantile period.

label: Impairment of galactose metabolism
definition: An impairment of galactose metabolism.

label: Distal renal tubular acidosis
definition: A type of renal tubular acidosis characterized by a failure of acid secretion by the alpha intercalated cells of the cortical collecting duct of the distal nephron. The urine cannot be acidified below a pH of 5.3, associated with acidemia and hypokalemia.

label: Hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis
definition: A form of metabolic acidosis with increased serum chloride levels.

label: Hyperphenylalaninemia
definition: An increased concentration of L-phenylalanine in the blood.

label: Abnormal oral glucose tolerance
definition: An abnormal resistance to glucose, i.e., a reduction in the ability to maintain glucose levels in the blood stream within normal limits following oral administration of glucose.

label: Impaired glucose tolerance
definition: An abnormal resistance to glucose, i.e., a reduction in the ability to maintain glucose levels in the blood stream within normal limits following oral or intravenous administration of glucose.

label: Chronic lactic acidosis
definition: A chronic form of lactic acidemia.

label: Orthostatic hypotension due to autonomic dysfunction
Pulmonary artery dilatation
definition: An abnormal widening of the diameter of the pulmonary artery.

label: Arteriosclerosis of small cerebral arteries
definition: Arteriosclerosis (increased thickness, increased stiffness, loss of elasticity) of the small arteries of the brain.

label: Ascending aortic dissection
definition: A separation of the layers within the wall of the ascending aorta. Tears in the intimal layer result in the propagation of dissection (proximally or distally) secondary to blood entering the intima-media space.

label: Abnormal ascending aorta morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the portion of the aorta that arises from the base of the left ventricle and extends upward to the aortic arch and from which the coronary arteries arise.

label: Cardiovascular calcification
definition: Abnormal calcification in the cardiovascular system.

label: Pulmonary artery atresia
definition: A congenital anomaly with a narrowing or complete absence of the opening between the right ventricle and the pulmonary artery.

label: Pulmonary artery aneurysm
definition: An aneurysm (severe localized balloon-like outward bulging) in the pulmonary artery.

label: Tortuous cerebral arteries
definition: Excessive bending, twisting, and winding of a cerebral artery.

label: Generalized arterial calcification
definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts, affecting arteries distributed throughout the body.

label: Extrahepatic portal hypertension
definition: Increased pressure in the pre-hepatic portal vein.

label: Aortic aneurysm
definition: Aortic dilatation refers to a dimension that is greater than the 95th percentile for the normal person age, sex and body size. In contrast, an aneurysm is defined as a localized dilation of the aorta that is more than 150 percent of predicted (ratio of observed to expected diameter 1.5 or more). Aneurysm should be distinguished from ectasia, which represents a diffuse dilation of the aorta less than 50 percent of normal aorta diameter.

label: Accelerated atherosclerosis
definition: Atherosclerosis which occurs in a person with certain risk factors (e.g., SLE, diabetes, smoking, hypertension, hypercholesterolaemia, family history of early heart disease) at an earlier age than would occur in another person without those risk factors.

label: Dilatation of the cerebral artery
definition: The presence of a localized dilatation or ballooning of a cerebral artery.

label: Extracranial internal carotid artery dissection
definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the extracranial portion of the internal carotid artery wall.

label: Arterial dissection
definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of an artery.

label: Internal carotid artery dissection
definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the internal carotid artery wall.

label: Vascular tortuosity
definition: Abnormal twisting of arteries or veins.

label: Peripheral arterial stenosis
definition: Narrowing of peripheral arteries with reduction of blood flow to the limbs. This feature may be quantified as an ankle-brachial index of less than 0.9, and may be manifested clinically as claudication.

label: Pulmonary arteriovenous fistulas
definition: A rare vascular anomaly with a direct communication between pulmonary artery and pulmonary vein without an intervening capillary bed.

label: Generalized arterial tortuosity
definition: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of arteries affecting most or all arteries.

label: Descending thoracic aorta aneurysm
definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the descending thoracic aorta.

label: Absent pulmonary artery
definition: A congenital defect with aplasia (absence) of one of the right or left pulmonary artery.

label: Pulmonary artery sling
definition: An anomalous origin of the left pulmonary artery, such that it arises from the posterior aspect of the right pulmonary artery and passes between the trachea and esophagus to reach the left hilum.

label: Thoracic aorta calcification
definition: An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in the thoracic aorta.

label: Calcification of the aorta
definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the aorta.

label: Pulmonary arterial medial hypertrophy
definition: Increase in mass of the tunica media of the arteries in the pulmonary circulation.

label: Medial calcification of large arteries
definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of large (conduit) arteries.

label: Medial arterial calcification
definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of arteries.

label: Recurrent cerebral hemorrhage
definition: Recurrent bleeding into the parenchyma of the brain.

label: Peripheral pulmonary artery stenosis
definition: Stenosis of a peripheral branch of the pulmonary artery.

label: Ascending tubular aorta aneurysm
definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the tubular part of the ascending aorta.

label: Pulmonary artery hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the pulmonary artery.

label: Elevated mean arterial pressure
definition: An abnormal increase in the average blood pressure in an individual during a single cardiac cycle.

label: Coarctation of abdominal aorta
definition: Coarctation of the aorta is a narrowing or constriction of a segment of the abdominal aorta.

label: Erlenmeyer flask deformity of the femurs
definition: Flaring of distal femur.

label: Abnormal knee physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the knee joint.

label: Bilateral radial aplasia
definition: Missing radius bone on both sides associated with congenital failure of development.

label: Metaphyseal sclerosis
definition: Abnormally increased density of metaphyseal bone.

label: Metaphyseal rarefaction
definition: Reduction in density of metaphyseal bony tissue.

label: Mesomelic leg shortening
definition: Shortening of the middle parts of the leg in relation to the upper and terminal segments.

label: Rhizomelic arm shortening
definition: Disproportionate shortening of the proximal segment of the arm (i.e. the humerus).

label: Rhizomelia
definition: Disproportionate shortening of the proximal segment of limbs (i.e. the femur and humerus).

label: Slender long bones with narrow diaphyses
definition: Reduced diameter of a long bone with a more pronounced reduction of the diameter of the diaphysis of the long bones.

label: Multicentric ossification of proximal humeral epiphyses
Recurrent patellar dislocation
definition: Patellar dislocation occurring repeated times.

label: Recurrent joint dislocation
definition: Dislocation of a given joint repeated times.

label: Flattened proximal radial epiphyses
definition: An abnormally flat form of the proximal epiphysis of the radius.

label: Abnormality of the distal radial epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the radius.

label: Femoral bowing present at birth, straightening with time
definition: Congenital onset bending or abnormal curvature of the femur that normalizes with age.

label: Dumbbell-shaped humerus
definition: The humerus is shortened and displays flaring (widening) of the metaphyses.

label: Osteomyelitis leading to amputation due to slow healing fractures
Mesomelic arm shortening
definition: Shortening of the middle parts of the arm in relation to the upper and terminal segments.

label: Dysplastic distal radial epiphyses
definition: Abnormally developed (dysplastic) distal epiphysis of the radius.

label: Diaphyseal undertubulation
definition: Tubulation refers to the size and shape of tubular bones. In children and adolescents, the modeling process regulates normal bone growth. Final shaft (tube) diameter depends on appositional bone growth and the equilibrium between periosteal and endosteal bone resorption and formation. Undertubulation refers to a broad, widened form of the shafts (diaphyses) of long bones.

label: Hypoplastic distal humeri
definition: Underdevelopment of the distal portion of the humerus.

label: Distal ulnar hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the distal portion of the ulna.

label: Unilateral ulnar hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the ulna on only one side.

label: Proximal radio-ulnar synostosis
definition: An abnormal osseous union (fusion) between the proximal portions of the radius and the ulna.

label: Multiple long-bone exostoses
definition: Multiple exostoses originating in long bones.

label: Irregular capital femoral epiphysis
definition: Irregular surface of the normally relatively smooth capital femoral epiphysis.

label: Proximal humeral metaphyseal irregularity
definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the metaphysis at the proximal end of the humerus (at the shoulder).

label: Diaphyseal cortical sclerosis
definition: An elevation in bone density of the cortex of one or more diaphyses. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Anterolateral radial head dislocation
definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an anterolateral direction.

label: Cone-shaped epiphyses fused within their metaphyses
Proximal fibular overgrowth
definition: Overgrowth of the proximal part of the fibula.

label: Proximal radial head dislocation
definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an proximal direction.

label: Wrist hypermobility
definition: The ability of the wrist joints to move beyond their normal range of motion.

label: Small joint hypermobilty
definition:
The capability that a small joint (or a group of joints) has to move, passively and/or actively, beyond normal limits along physiological axes. Small joints include metacarpophalangeal joints, proximal interphalangeal joints, 
second to fifth metatarsophalangeal joints, and wrists.

label: Anterior radial head dislocation
definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an anterior direction.

label: Limited knee flexion/extension
definition: A limited ability of the knee joint to perform extension and flexion.

label: Lateral femoral bowing
definition: A lateral bending or abnormal curvature of the femur.

label: Streaky metaphyseal sclerosis
definition: The presence of streaks (bands) of abnormally increased density of metaphyseal bone.

label: Absent proximal radial epiphyses
definition: Absence of the proximal radial epiphysis.

label: Abnormality of the proximal radial epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the radius.

label: Distal femoral bowing
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of the distal portion of the femur.

label: Premature birth following premature rupture of fetal membranes
High-frequency hearing impairment
definition: A type of hearing impairment affecting primarily the higher frequencies of sound (3,000 to 6,000 Hz).

label: Cochlear degeneration
definition: Deterioration or loss of the tissues of the cochlea.

label: Calcification of the auricular cartilage
definition: Ossification affecting the external ear cartilage.

label: Hypoplastic nasal septum
definition: Underdevelopment of the nasal septum.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nasal septum
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the nasal septum.

label: Abnormal tendon morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure or form of the tendons, also often called sinews.

label: Abdominal aortic aneurysm
definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the abdominal aorta.

label: Aortic arch aneurysm
definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the aortic arch.

label: Elevated diastolic blood pressure
definition: Abnormal increase in diastolic blood pressure.

label: Posterior scalloping of vertebral bodies
definition: An excessive concavity of the posterior surface of one or more vertebral bodies.

label: Pericardial constriction
definition: Compression of the heart caused by rigid, thickened, or fused pericardial membranes.

label: Right ventricular dilatation
definition: Enlargement of the chamber of the right ventricle, which can be defined echocardiographically as a right ventricular to left ventricular ratio greater than 1:1.

label: Absence of the pulmonary valve
definition: Refers to the specific combination of defects with a severely dysplastic pulmonary valve and massively dilated branch pulmonary arteries.

label: Abnormal T-wave
definition: An abnormality of the T wave on the electrocardiogram, which mainly represents the repolarization of the ventricles.

label: Mitral annular calcification
definition: Mitral annular calcification (MAC) results from progressive calcium deposition along and beneath the mitral valve annulus.

label: Anomalous origin of right pulmonary artery from ascending aorta
definition: The right pulmonary artery originates from the ascending aorta in the presence of a pulmonary valve and main pulmonary artery.

label: Anomalous origin of one pulmonary artery from ascending aorta
definition: Anomalous origin of one pulmonary artery from the ascending aorta with the contralateral pulmonary artery arising from the right ventricle.

label: Ventricular septal hypertrophy
definition: The dividing wall between left and right sides of the heart, thickens and bulges into the left ventricle.

label: Coronary artery stenosis
definition: Abnormal narrowing of the coronary artery.

label: Premature ventricular contraction
definition: Premature ventricular contractions (PVC) or ventricular extrasystoles are premature contractions of the heart that arise in response to an impulse in the ventricles rather than the normal impulse from the sinoatrial (SA) node.

label: Pulmonary valve defects
definition: Any defect in the valve connecting the heart and the pulmonary artery.

label: Cardiac conduction abnormality
definition: Any anomaly of the progression of electrical impulses through the heart.

label: Preductal coarctation of the aorta
definition: Narrowing or constriction of the aorta localized proximal to the ductus arteriosus, i.e., to the preductal region of aortic arch.

label: Coarctation of the descending aortic arch
definition: Narrowing or constriction of the aorta localized to the region of the descending trunk of arch of aorta.

label: Histiocytoid cardiomyopathy
definition: A type of cardiomyopathy characterized pathologically by hamartomatous lesions of cardiac Purkinje cells.

label: Ventricular escape rhythm
definition: A ventricular escape rhythm occurs whenever higher-lever pacemakers in AV junction or sinus node fail to control ventricular activation. Escape rate is usually 20-40 bpm, often associated with broad QRS complexes (at least 120 ms).

label: Hypoplastic left atrium
definition: Underdeveloped, small left heart atrium

label: Abnormal left atrium morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the left atrium.

label: Concentric hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
definition: Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with an symmetrical and concentric pattern of hypertrophy.

label: Total anomalous pulmonary venous return
definition: Total anomalous pulmonary venous return refers to a congenital malformation in which all four pulmonary veins do not connect normally to the left atrium, but instead drain abnormally to the right atrium.

label: Anomalous pulmonary venous return
definition: A developmental defect characterized by abnormal connection of one or more pulmonary veins to the superior or inferior vena cava, the right atrium, or the coronary sinus, resulting in a left-to-right shunt of oxygenated blood.

label: Abnormal left ventricular function
definition: Inability of the left ventricle to perform its normal physiologic function. Failure is either due to an inability to contract the left ventricle or the inability to relax completely and fill with blood during diastole.

label: Abnormal cardiac ventricular function
definition: An abnormality of the cardiac ventricular function.

label: Dysplastic pulmonary valve
definition: A congenital malformation of the pulmonary valve characterized by leaflet deformation.

label: Shortened PR interval
definition: Reduced time for the PR interval (beginning of the P wave to the beginning of the QRS complex). In adults, normal values are 120 to 200 ms long.

label: Abnormal PR interval
definition: An anomaly of the PR interval, which is the portion of the ECG from the onset of the P wave to the beginning of the QRS complex. A normal PR interval in adults is 0.12-0.2 seconds.

label: Elevated right atrial pressure
definition: An abnormal increase in magnitude of the pressure in the right atrium.

label: Abnormal cardiac atrial physiology
definition: An abnormality of the function of the cardiac atria.

label: Complete heart block with broad QRS complexes
definition: A type of third degree heart block in which the escape rhythm arises at a relatively low part of the conduction system (below the atrioventricular node), which produces a wide QRS complex.

label: Left posterior fascicular block
definition: Conduction block in the posterior division of the left bundle branch of the bundle of His.

label: Left bundle branch block
definition: A conduction block of the left branch of the bundle of His. This manifests as a generalized disturbance of QRS morphology on EKG.

label: Membranous subvalvular aortic stenosis
definition: Subvalvular stenosis is caused by a diaphragm-like membrane. The stenosis is clinically manifested like any other form of aortic stenosis but is often associated with some aortic insufficiency.

label: Dysplastic aortic valve
definition: A congenital malformation of the aortic valve characterized by leaflet deformation.

label: Premature arteriosclerosis
definition: Arteriosclerosis occurring at an age that is younger than usual.

label: Complete heart block with narrow QRS complexes
definition: A type of third degree heart block in which the escape rhythm arises at the atrioventricular node, which produces a narrow QRS complex.

label: Tricuspid regurgitation
definition: Failure of the tricuspid valve to close sufficiently upon contraction of the right ventricle, causing blood to regurgitate (flow backward) into the right atrium.

label: Abnormal tricuspid valve physiology
definition: Any functional defect of the tricuspid valve.

label: Premature coronary artery atherosclerosis
definition: Reduction of the diameter of the coronary arteries as the result of an accumulation of atheromatous plaques within the walls of the coronary arteries before age of 45.

label: Bicuspid pulmonary valve
definition: The presence of a bicuspid pulmonary valve.

label: Abnormal pulmonary valve cusp morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the pulmonary valve leaflets.

label: Pericardial lymphangiectasia
definition: An abnormal dilatation of lymph vessels in the pericardium.

label: Prolonged QTc interval
definition: A longer than normal interval (corrected for heart rate) between the Q and T waves in the heart's cycle. Prolonged QTc can cause premature action potentials during late phase depolarizations thereby leading to ventricular arrhythmias and ventricular fibrillations.

label: Global systolic dysfunction
definition: A reduced ejection fraction and an enlarged left ventricle chamber, the latter by an increased resistance to filling with increased filling pressures. Systolic dysfunction is clinically associated with left ventricular failure in the presence of marked cardiomegaly.

label: Synovial lining hyperplasia
definition: Synovial hyperplasia involves proliferation of mesenchymal stromal/stem cells and leads to synovial thickening, which can be observed radiographically.

label: Abnormal synovial membrane morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the synovium, which is a membrane that lines the cavity of synovial joints and consists of a lining layer of macrophage-like synoviocytes and fibroblast-like synoviocytes, as well as a sublining of connective tissue. Synovial cells are thought to contribute to joint homeostasis by secreting various factors such as hyaluronic acid and lubricin important for joint lubrication and function, as well as disposing of the waste products.

label: Flattened metatarsal heads
definition: Abnormally flat shape of the heads of the metatarsal bones.

label: Generalized morning stiffness
definition: A sensation of stiffness in the joints that occurs following waking up in the morning.

label: Stiff interphalangeal joints
definition: Interphalangeal joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in the interphalangeal joints when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity.

label: Aplasia of the abdominal wall musculature
definition: Absence of the abdominal musculature.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the abdominal wall musculature
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the abdominal musculature.

label: Abnormal portal venous system morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the portal venous system, which comprises all of the veins draining the abdominal part of the digestive tract, including the lower esophagus but excluding the lower anal canal. The portal vein conveys blood from viscera and ramifies like an artery at the liver, ending at the sinusoids. Tributaries of the portal vein, which make up the portal venous system, are the splenic, superior mesenteric, left gastric, right gastric, paraumbilical, and cystic veins.

label: Helicobacter pylori infection
definition: A recurrent infection of the GI tract with helicobacter pylori, a gram-negative, microaerophilic bacterium usually found in the stomach.

label: Spontaneous esophageal perforation
definition: The occurrence of the full-thickness tear (perforation) of the wall of the esophagus.

label: Pancreatic pseudocyst
definition: Cyst-like space not lined by epithelium and contained within the pancreas. Pancreatic pseudocysts are often associated with pancreatitis.

label: Gastric hypertrophy
definition: Hypertrophy of the stomach.

label: Secretory diarrhea
definition: Watery voluminous diarrhea resulting from an imbalance between ion and water secretion and absorption.

label: Intrahepatic bile duct cysts
definition: The presence of cyst of the intrahepatic bile duct.

label: Hypoplastic colon
definition: Underdevelopment of the colon.

label: Anal mucosal leukoplakia
definition: Leukoplakia is a precancerous dermatosis of mucous membranes analogous Leukoplakia is basically a chronic inflammatory hypertrophy in which anaplasia and malignant dyskeratosis may develop and subsequently advance to an invasive squamous cell cancer. The clinical diagnosis of primary anal leukoplakia is indicated by single or multiple slightly raised,irregular, marginated, grayish-white keratinized' patches in the anal canal. Tissue biopsy is necessary for confirmation.

label: Anal neoplasm
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that affects the anal canal or anal margin.

label: Pancreatic calcification
definition: The presence of abnormal calcium deposition lesions in the pancreas.

label: Frequent Giardia lamblia infestation
definition: Increased susceptibility to Giardia lamblia infection of the intestine, as manifested by a medical history of multiple episodes of Giardia lamblia intestinal infection.

label: Impaired mastication
definition: An abnormal reduction in the ability to masticate (chew), i.e., in the ability to crush and ground food in preparation for swallowing.

label: Abnormal oral physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).

label: Anoperineal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula (abnormal tunnel) between the anal canal and the perineum.

label: Anal fistula
definition: An abnormal connection between the epithelialised surface of the anal canal and the perianal skin.

label: Absence of intrinsic factor
definition: Absence of gastric intrinsic factor, which is normally produced by the parietal cells of the stomach, and is required for the absorption of vitamin B12.

label: Intestinal duplication
definition: A developmental disorder in which there is a duplication the entire intestine or of a portion of the intestine.

label: Rectal abscess
definition: A collection of pus in the area of the rectum.

label: Abscess
