definition: An abscess is a localized collection of purulent material surrounded by inflammation and granulation.

label: Adenomatous colonic polyposis
definition: Presence of multiple adenomatous polyps in the colon.

label: Large intestinal polyposis
definition: The presence of multiple polyps in the large intestine.

label: Abnormal jejunum morphology
definition: An abnormality of the jejunum, i.e., of the middle section of the small intestine.

label: Biliary tract obstruction
definition: Obstruction affecting the biliary tree.

label: Chronic gastritis
definition: A chronic form of gastritis.

label: Pancreatic dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the pancreas.

label: Hypoplasia of the gallbladder
definition: The presence of a hypoplastic gallbladder.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the gallbladder
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the gallbladder.

label: Jejunal atresia
definition: A developmental defect resulting in abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the jejunum.

label: Chronic calcifying pancreatitis
definition: A form of chronic pancreatitis that is characterized by calcification.

label: Degenerative liver disease
definition: The presence of degenerative changes of the liver.

label: Intestinal polyposis
definition: The presence of multiple polyps in the intestine.

label: Total intestinal aganglionosis
definition: A congenital defect characterized by the lack of ganglion cells in the entire intestine, i.e., the aganglionic segment comprises the entire large and small bowel.

label: Extrahepatic biliary duct atresia
definition: Atresia in the extrahepatic bile duct.

label: Biliary atresia
definition: Atresia of the biliary tree.

label: Partial abdominal muscle agenesis
definition: Failure to form of portions of the abdominal musculature.

label: Giant hypertrophic gastritis
definition: A type of gastritis characterized by excessive proliferation of the gastric mucosa and diffuse thickening of the gastric mucosal folds.

label: Hypoplasia of the abdominal wall musculature
definition: Underdevelopment of the abdominal musculature.

label: Intrahepatic biliary atresia
definition: Atresia in the intrahepatic bile duct.

label: Absence of pectoralis minor muscle
definition: Aplasia (congenital absence) of the pectoralis minor.

label: Abnormal pectoral muscle morphology
definition: An abnormality of the pectoral muscle, comprising the pectoralis major, a thick, fan-shaped muscle of the anterior chest and the pectoralis minor, a thin, triangular muscle situated underneath the pectoralis major.

label: Unilateral absence of pectoralis major muscle
definition: Aplasia (congenital absence) of the pectoralis minor on only one side of the chest.

label: Abnormal facility in opposing the shoulders
definition: Increased range of shoulder movement related to aplasia or hypoplasia of the clavicles that results in the ability to approximate the shoulders in front of the chest.

label: Joint hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage occurring within a joint.

label: Abnormality of the gallbladder
definition: An abnormality of the gallbladder.

label: Premature delivery because of cervical insufficiency or membrane fragility
Miscarriage
definition: A pregnancy that ends at a stage in which the fetus is incapable of surviving on its own, defined as the spontaneous loss of a fetus before the 22th week of pregnancy.

label: Prominent nasolabial fold
definition: Exaggerated bulkiness of the crease or fold of skin running from the lateral margin of the nose, where nasal base meets the skin of the face, to a point just lateral to the corner of the mouth (cheilion, or commissure).

label: Absent nasal septal cartilage
definition: Lack of the cartilage of the nasal septum.

label: Abnormality nasal septum cartilage morphology
definition: An abnormality of a cartilage of nasal septum.

label: Depressed nasal bridge
definition: Posterior positioning of the nasal root in relation to the overall facial profile for age.

label: Abnormal internal carotid artery morphology
definition: An abnormality of an internal carotid artery.

label: Vasculitis by histology
definition: Vasculitis categorized according to type of histological abnormality.

label: Intimal thickening in the coronary arteries
Pseudocoarctation of the aorta
definition: Pseudocoarctation is a congenital anomaly of kinking, or buckling, of the aorta without a pressure gradient across the lesion. It is characterized by elongation and kinking of the aorta at the level of the ligamentum arteriosum.

label: Abnormal aortic arch morphology
definition: An anomaly of the arch of aorta.

label: Premature occlusive vascular stenosis
definition: Peripheral arterial stenosis with onset before the age of 50 years.

label: Persistent left superior vena cava
definition: A rare congenital vascular anomaly that results when the left superior cardinal vein caudal to the innominate vein fails to regress.

label: Abnormal superior vena cava morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the principal vein draining blood from the upper portion of the body and delivering it to the right ventricle of the heart.

label: Carotid artery tortuosity
definition: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of the carotid arteries.

label: Abnormal carotid artery morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the carotid arteries, including the common carotid artery and its' arterial branches.

label: Aortic arch calcification
definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the arch of aorta.

label: Abnormal pulmonary vein morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure of the pulmonary veins.

label: Cerebral venous thrombosis
definition: Formation of a blood clot (thrombus) inside a cerebral vein, causing the obstruction of blood flow.

label: Abnormal pulmonary artery physiology
definition: An abnormality of the function of the pulmonary artery.

label: Large vessel vasculitis
definition: A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) affecting large arteries such as the aorta and branches of the aorta.

label: Vasculitis by anatomical site
definition: Vasculitis categorized according to the anatomical site where the finding is localized.

label: Agenesis of pulmonary vessels
definition: A developmental defect characterized by the lack of formation of the pulmonary blood vessels.

label: Pulmonary aterial intimal fibrosis
definition: Formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in the tunica intima (innermost layer) of arteries in the pulmonary circulation.

label: Arterial fibromuscular dysplasia
definition: An arterial lesion that is characterized by either intimal fibroplasia, with neointimal lesions of cells and matrix deposition, or medial fibroplasia, in which there is loss of smooth muscle cells and increased deposition of collagen and proteoglycans in the medial layer.

label: Anomalous branches of internal carotid artery
Increased pulmonary vascular resistance
definition: Pulmonary vascular resistance (PVR) more than 3 wood units, as defined by the current definition of pulmonary hypertension. 95% of individuals have a PVR of less than 2.4 wood units.

label: Cerebral vasculitis
definition: Inflammation of the blood vessels within the brain.

label: Mandibulofacial dysostosis
definition: A type of craniofacial dysostosis associated with abnormalities of the external ears, mirognathia, macrostomia, coloboma of the lower eyelid, and cleft palate. This is a bundled term that is left in the HPO now for convenience with legacy annotations but should not be used for new annotations.

label: Hemifacial hypertrophy
definition: Unilateral overgrowth of facial tissues, including muscles, bones and skin.

label: Extension of hair growth on temples to lateral eyebrow
definition: A pattern of hair growth in which there is hair extending from the temples to the lateral eyebrows.

label: Hypoplastic philtrum
definition: Underdevelopment of the philtrum.

label: Progeroid facial appearance
definition: A degree of wrinkling of the facial skin that is more than expected for the age of the individual, leading to a prematurely aged appearance.

label: Recurrent mandibular subluxations
definition: Recurrent partial dislocations of the mandible.

label: Sparse lateral eyebrow
definition: Decreased density/number and/or decreased diameter of lateral eyebrow hairs.

label: Sparse eyebrow
definition: Decreased density/number of eyebrow hairs.

label: Abnormality of humoral immunity
definition: An abnormality of the humoral immune system, which comprises antibodies produced by B cells as well as the complement system.

label: Autonomic bladder dysfunction
definition: Abnormal bladder function (increased urge or frequency of urination or urge incontinence) resulting from abnormal functioning of the autonomic nervous system.

label: Hypoplasia of the bladder
definition: Underdevelopment of the urinary bladder.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the bladder
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the urinary bladder.

label: Abnormal vena cava morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure of the veins that return deoxygenated blood from the body into the heart, i.e., the superior vena cava and the inferior vena cava.

label: Tracheal cartilaginous sleeve
definition: Tracheal cartilaginous sleeve (TCS) is a rare congenital airway malformation in which distinct tracheal rings are replaced by a continuous cartilaginous segment. Vertically fused C- or O-shaped cartilaginous rings can extend from the subglottis to the carina or bronchus with little to no pars membranacea posteriorly. Comment:Tracheal cartilaginous sleeve has been associated with various craniosynostosis syndromes.

label: Stridor
definition: Stridor is a high pitched sound resulting from turbulent air flow in the upper airway.

label: Hypoplasia of the epiglottis
definition: Hypoplasia of the epiglottis.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the Epiglottis
definition: This term applies if the Epiglottis is absent or hypoplastic.

label: Severe T-cell immunodeficiency
definition: A primary immune deficiency that is characterized by defects or deficiencies of T-lymphocytes that causes specific susceptibility to intracellular micro-organisms.

label: Cellular immunodeficiency
definition: An immunodeficiency characterized by defective cell-mediated immunity or humoral immunity.

label: Recurrent herpes
definition: Increased susceptibility to herpesvirus, as manifested by recurrent episodes of herpesvirus.

label: Unusual virus reactivation
definition: Reactivation is the mechanism whereby a latent virus that has infected a host cell switches to a lytic stage, undergoing productive viral replication and allowing the virus to spread. This term refers to reactivation regarded as unusual because of frequency, intensity, location, or nature of the virus, in the sense that the reactivation would not be observed in an immunocompetent host.

label: Lack of T cell function
definition: Complete inability of T cells to perform their functions in cell-mediated immunity.

label: Decreased circulating complement factor I concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component factor I in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Defective B cell differentiation
definition: Reduced functionality of the process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a B cell. A B cell is a lymphocyte of B lineage with the phenotype CD19-positive and capable of B cell mediated immunity.

label: Defective B cell activation
definition: A reduced ability of a B cell to become activated, i.e., the change in morphology and behavior of

label: Aplasia of the thymus
definition: Absence of the thymus. This feature may be appreciated by the lack of a thymic shadow upon radiographic examination.

label: Susceptibility to chickenpox
definition: Increased susceptibility to chicken pox, as manifested by recurrent episodes of chicken pox.

label: Humoral immunodeficiency
definition: A general term referring to a defect in immunity resulting from impaired antibody production.

label: Severe B lymphocytopenia
definition: A severe form of B lymphocytopenia in which the count of B cells is very low or absent.

label: B lymphocytopenia
definition: An abnormal decrease from the normal count of B cells.

label: Recurrent streptococcus pneumoniae infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to streptococcus pneumoniae infections as manifested by a history of recurrent infections by streptococcus pneumoniae.

label: Recurrent streptococcal infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to streptococcal infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of streptococcal infections.

label: Decreased circulating complement factor H concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component factor H in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Abnormal lymphocyte physiology
definition: Any anomaly of lymphocyte function.

label: Recurrent Haemophilus influenzae infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to Haemophilus influenzae infections as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection by Haemophilus influenzae.

label: Recurrent meningococcal disease
definition: Recurrent infections by Neisseria meningitidis (one of the most common causes of bacterial meningitis), which is also known as meningococcus.

label: Recurrent Neisserial infections
definition: Recurrent infections by bacteria of the genus Neisseria, including N. meningitidis (one of the most common causes of bacterial meningitis).

label: Recurrent protozoan infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to protozoan infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of protozoan infection.

label: Depletion of components of the alternative complement pathway
definition: An abnormal reduction in the components of the alternative complement pathway, such as the C3 protein or its cleavage products.

label: Abnormality of the alternative complement pathway
definition: A deviation in any aspect of the alternative complement pathway.

label: Recurrent opportunistic infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to opportunistic infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection by opportunistic agents, i.e., by microorganisms that do not usually cause disease in a healthy host, but are able to infect a host with a compromised immune system.

label: Opportunistic infection
definition: An infection that is caused by a pathogen that would generally not be able to cause an infection in a host with a normal immune system. Such pathogens take advantage of the opportunity, so to speak, that is provided by a weakened immune system.

label: Susceptibility to coronavirus 229e
definition: Increased susceptibility to coronavirus 229e, as manifested by recurrent episodes of coronavirus 229e.

label: Reduction of neutrophil motility
definition: An abnormal reduction of the cell motility of neutrophils.

label: Abnormality of neutrophil physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of neutrophils.

label: Recurrent candida infections
definition: An increased susceptibility to candida infections, as manifested by a history of recurrent episodes of candida infections.

label: T lymphocytopenia
definition: An abnormally low count of T cells.

label: Abnormal T cell count
definition: A deviation from the normal count of T cells.

label: Increased B cell count
definition: An abnormal increase from the normal count of B cells.

label: Abnormal B cell count
definition: A deviation from the normal count of B cells, i.e., the cells that are formed in the bone marrow, migrate to the peripheral lymphatic system, and mature into plasma cells or memory cells.

label: Lymphocytosis
definition: Increase in the number or proportion of lymphocytes in the blood.

label: Decreased proportion of CD4-positive helper T cells
definition: A decreased proportion of circulating CD4-positive helper T cells relative to total T cell count.

label: Decreased proportion of CD4-positive T cells
definition: A reduction in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive helper T cells
definition: An abnormal proportion of circulating CD4-positive helper T cells relative to total T cell count.

label: Chronic intestinal candidiasis
definition: Persistent overgrowth of Candida albicans in the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Increased alpha-globulin
definition: An abnormally increased level of circulating alpha-globulin. Alpha globulins are a group of serum proteins defined by their mobility on serum electrophoresis. The alpha1-protein fraction is comprised of alpha1-antitrypsin, thyroid-binding globulin, and transcortin. Ceruloplasmin, alpha2-macroglobulin, and haptoglobin contribute to the alpha2-protein band. The alpha2 component is increased as an acute-phase reactant.

label: Increased circulating globulin level
definition: An abnormally elevated concentration of globulins in the blood.

label: Decreased proportion of CD8-positive T cells
definition: A decreased proportion of circulating CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells relative to total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive T cells
definition: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased circulating complement factor B concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component factor B in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased T cell activation
definition: Decreased or impaired activation of T cells in response to a mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or an antigen for which it is specific.

label: Abnormal T cell activation
definition: Any abnormality in the activation of T cells, i.e. the change in morphology and behavior of a mature or immature T cell resulting from exposure to a mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or an antigen for which it is specific.

label: Decreased circulating complement C3 concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component C3 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Absence of CD8-positive T cells
definition: Lack of detectible CD8-positive T cells

label: Dysfunctional alternative complement pathway
definition: An abnormality of the functioning of any aspect of the alternative complement pathway.

label: Absent specific antibody response
definition: Absence of specific immunoglobulins directed against a specific antigen or microorganism.

label: Recurrent sinopulmonary infections
definition: An increased susceptibility to infections involving both the paranasal sinuses and the lungs, as manifested by a history of recurrent sinopulmonary infections.

label: Recurrent systemic pyogenic infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to systemic pyogenic infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of systemic pyogenic infections.

label: Transient hypogammaglobulinemia of infancy
definition: At birth, newborns are endowed with maternal antibodies. IgG production normally begins at the age of two months. A delay in recovery from this physiological hypogammaglobulinemia between the 3rd and the 6th month of life, and of recovery period between 18 and 36 months defines transient newborn hypogammaglobulinemia.

label: Impaired T cell function
definition: Abnormally reduced ability of T cells to perform their functions in cell-mediated immunity.

label: Recurrent infections in infancy and early childhood
definition: Recurrent infections at an early age with improvement in later childhood.

label: Maxillozygomatic hypoplasia
definition: Hypoplasia of the maxillozygomatic complex.

label: Hypoplasia of the zygomatic bone
definition: Underdevelopment of the zygomatic bone. That is, a reduction in size of the zygomatic bone, including the zygomatic process of the temporal bone of the skull, which forms part of the zygomatic arch.

label: Sclerotic cranial sutures
definition: An increased density in the cranial sutures following obliteration.

label: Widely patent coronal suture
definition: The presence of a coronal suture (the cranial suture that separates the frontal and parietal bones) that is not ossified but rather wide open at an age when it is normally closed.

label: Obtuse angle of mandible
definition: Abnormally flat (obtuse) angle of the mandible. The angle of the mandibular, located at the junction between the body and the ramus of the mandible, is normally close to being a right angle. This terms describes an abnormal increase of this angle such that the mandible appears flatter than normal.

label: Calvarial osteosclerosis
definition: An increase in bone density affecting the calvaria (roof of the skull).

label: Craniofacial osteosclerosis
definition: Abnormally increased density of craniofacial bone tissue.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the sinuses
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of a cranial sinus or sinuses.

label: Absent ethmoidal sinuses
definition: Lack (aplasia) of the ethmoidal sinus.

label: Abnormality of ethmoid sinus
definition: An abnormality of an ethmoid sinus.

label: Premature closure of fontanelles
definition: Normally, the posterior and lateral fontanelles are obliterated by about six months after birth, the anterior fontanelle closes by about the middle of the second year. This term refers to the situation in which the fontanelles close at an inappropriately early time point.

label: Calcification of falx cerebri
definition: The presence of calcium deposition in the falx cerebri.

label: Abnormality of the falx cerebri
definition: An abnormality of the Falx cerebri.

label: Hypoplasia of the frontal bone
definition: Underdevelopment of the frontal bone.

label: Flat occiput
definition: Reduced convexity of the occiput (posterior part of skull).

label: Fusion of middle ear ossicles
definition: Bony fusion of malleus, incus, and stapes.

label: Decreased calvarial ossification
definition: Abnormal reduction in ossification of the calvaria (roof of the skull consisting of the frontal bone, parietal bones, temporal bones, and occipital bone).

label: Widely patent sagittal suture
definition: The presence of a sagittal suture (the cranial suture that separates the left and right parietal bones) that is not ossified but rather wide open at an age when it is normally closed.

label: Progressive sclerosis of skull base
definition: Progressively increasing bone density of the skull base without significant changes in bony contour.

label: Decreased circulating IgE concentration
definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin E (IgE) in blood.

label: Abnormal epiglottis morphology
definition: An abnormality of the epiglottis.

label: Small fontanelle
definition: A fontanelle that is small for age.

label: Prominent metopic ridge
definition: Vertical bony ridge positioned in the midline of the forehead.

label: Abnormality of the metopic suture
definition: The frontal suture divides the two halves of the frontal bone of the skull in infants and children and generally undergoes fusion by the age of six. A persistent frontal suture is referred to as a metopic suture"."

label: Postnatal macrocephaly
definition: The postnatal development of an abnormally large skull (macrocephaly).

label: Metopic suture patent to nasal root
definition: The frontal suture divides the two halves of the frontal bone in infants and usually fuses by the age of six years. The suture runs from the bregma (the point on the skull at which the coronal suture is intersected perpendicularly by the sagittal suture) to the nasion or nasal root. This term applies if the suture is widely patent from bregma to nasal root.

label: Midline skin dimples over anterior/posterior fontanelles
Chronic myelogenous leukemia
definition: A myeloproliferative disorder characterized by increased proliferation of the granulocytic cell line without the loss of their capacity to differentiate.

label: Chronic leukemia
definition: A slowly progressing leukemia characterized by a clonal (malignant) proliferation of maturing and mature myeloid cells or mature lymphocytes. When the clonal cellular population is composed of myeloid cells, the process is called chronic myelogenous leukemia. When the clonal cellular population is composed of lymphocytes, it is classified as chronic lymphocytic leukemia, hairy cell leukemia, or T-cell large granular lymphocyte leukemia.

label: Hemoglobin Barts
definition: Normal adult hemoglobin is composed of two chains each of alpha and beta globin. Hb Barts (Hemoglobin Barts) is a tetramer with four gamma globin chains, and is essentially pathognomonic for one or another form of alpha thalassemia. Hb Barts has an extremely high affinity for oxygen, resulting in almost no oxygen delivery to the tissues.

label: Abnormal hemoglobin
definition: Anomaly in the level or the function of hemoglobin, the oxygen-carrying protein of erythrocytes.

label: Monoclonal immunoglobulin M proteinemia
definition: Presence of a monoclonal immunoglobulin M protein in the serum.

label: Paraproteinemia
definition: An abnormal immunoglobulin or part of an Ig (light chain) in the circulation. Paraproteins are typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.

label: Transient erythroblastopenia
definition: A transient reduction in the number of erythroblasts in the circulation.

label: Heinz body anemia
definition: Anemia characterized by abnormal intracellular inclusions, composed of denatured hemoglobin, found on the membrane of red blood cells.

label: Impaired neutrophil killing of staphylococci
definition: A reduction in the ability of neutrophils to kill the gram-positive bacteria, staphylococcus, which is commonly known as staph.

label: Increased megakaryocyte count
definition: Increased megakaryocyte number, i.e., of platelet precursor cells, present in the bone marrow.

label: Abnormal megakaryocyte morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of megakaryocytes. Mature blood platelets are released from the cytoplasm of megakaryocytes, which are bone-marrow resident cells.

label: T-cell lymphoma/leukemia
definition: A type of T-cell lymphoma in which cancerous T-cells may present in the blood (leukemia), lymph nodes (lymphoma), skin or in multiple areas.

label: T-cell lymphoma
definition: A type of lymphoma that originates in T-cells.

label: Increased mean corpuscular volume
definition: Larger than normal size of erythrocytes.

label: Abnormal mean corpuscular volume
definition: A deviation from normal of the mean corpuscular volume, or mean cell volume (MCV) of red blood cells, usually taken to be 80 to 100 femtoliters.

label: Chronic disseminated intravascular coagulation
definition: A chronic form of disseminated intravascular coagulation in which a persistent weak or intermittent activating stimulus is present and destruction and production of coagulation factors and platelets are balanced.

label: Disseminated intravascular coagulation
definition: Disseminated intravascular coagulation is characterized by the widespread activation of coagulation, which results in the intravascular formation of fibrin and ultimately thrombotic occlusion of small and midsize vessels.

label: Pyridoxine-responsive sideroblastic anemia
definition: A type of sideroblastic anemia that is alleviated by pyridoxine (vitamin B-6) treatment.

label: Lymphoid leukemia
definition: A malignant lymphocytic neoplasm of B-cell or T-cell lineage involving primarily the bone marrow and the peripheral blood. This category includes precursor or acute lymphoblastic leukemias and chronic leukemias.

label: Reduced kininogen activity
definition: Reduction in the amount of kininogen, which functions as a cofactor in the contact phase of the intrinsic blood coagulation cascade.

label: Bone marrow hypocellularity
definition: A reduced number of hematopoietic cells present in the bone marrow relative to marrow fat.

label: Biphenotypic acute leukemia
definition: A type of actue leukemia with features characteristic of both the myeloid and lymphoid lineages. These leukemias are for this reason are designated mixed-lineage, hybrid or biphenotypic acute leukemias.

label: Transient myeloproliferative syndrome
definition: A unique clonal neoplastic disorder that is linked to trisomy 21, is restricted to neonatal period, and spontaneously regresses. It often has characteristics of megakaryocytic lineage and is associated with GATA1 mutations in myeloblasts.

label: Myeloproliferative disorder
definition: Proliferation (excess production) of hemopoietically active tissue or of tissue which has embryonic hemopoietic potential.

label: Exercise-induced hemolysis
definition: A form of hemolytic anemia that can be triggered by exertion.

label: Decreased mean platelet volume
definition: Average platelet volume below the lower limit of the normal reference interval.

label: Abnormal platelet volume
definition: Anomalous size of platelets. Most normal sized platelets are 1.5 to 3 micrometers in diameter. Large platelets are 4 to 7 micrometers. Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers.

label: T cell chronic lymphocytic lymphoma/leukemia
definition: A form of lymphoid leukemia or lymphoma in which too many T-cell lymphoblasts are found in the blood, bone marrow, and tissues. Leukemia or lymphoma classification depends on which feature is more prominent.

label: Red blood cell keratocytosis
definition: A form of poikilocytosis in which the abnormally shaped erythrocytes have notches that results in projections that look like horns.

label: Congenital agranulocytosis
definition: Congenital onset of a marked decrease in the number of granulocytes.

label: Agranulocytosis
definition: Marked decrease in the number of granulocytes.

label: Prolonged whole-blood clotting time
definition: An abnormal prolongation (delay) in the time required by whole blood to produce a visible clot.

label: Reduced protein C activity
definition: An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of vitamin K-dependent protein C. Protein C is activated to protein Ca by thrombin bound to thrombomodulin. Activated protein C degrades factors VIIIa and Va.

label: Megakaryocytopenia
definition: A reduced count of megakaryocytes.

label: Chronic lymphatic leukemia
definition: A chronic lymphocytic/lymphatic/lymphoblastic leukemia (CLL) is a neoplastic disease characterized by proliferation and accumulation (blood, marrow and lymphoid organs) of morphologically mature but immunologically dysfunctional lymphocytes. A CLL is always a B-cell lymphocytic leukemia as there are no reports of cases of T-cell lymphocytic leukemias.

label: Abnormal zygomatic arch morphology
definition: An abnormality of the zygomatic arch, also known as the cheek bone.

label: Imbalanced hemoglobin synthesis
definition: Normal hemoglobin synthesis is characterized by production of equal amounts of alpha and beta globins. This term refers to a deviation from this pattern and is the main characteristic of the various forms of thalassemia.

label: Abnormal bone marrow cell morphology
definition: An anomaly of the form or number of cells in the bone marrow.

label: Multiple renal cysts
definition: The presence of many cysts in the kidney.

label: Decreased numbers of nephrons
definition: A reduction in the count of nephrons per kidney.

label: Absence of renal corticomedullary differentiation
definition: A lack of differentiation between renal cortex and medulla on diagnostic imaging.

label: Abnormal renal corticomedullary differentiation
definition: An abnormality of corticomedullary differentiation (CMD) on diagnostic imaging such as magnetic resonance imaging, computer tomography, or sonography. CMD is a difference in the visualization of cortex and medulla.

label: Reduced renal corticomedullary differentiation
definition: Reduced differentiation between renal cortex and medulla on diagnostic imaging.

label: Renal magnesium wasting
definition: High urine magnesium in the presence of hypomagnesemia.

label: Abnormal urine magnesium concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of magnesium the urine.

label: Non-acidotic proximal tubulopathy
definition: A type of proximal renal tubulopathy characterized by resorption defects leading to glycosuria, aminoaciduria, tubular proteinuria, renal hypophosphatemia, and urate tubular hyporeabsorption without bicarbonate loss.

label: Hemolytic-uremic syndrome
definition: A thrombotic microangiopathy with presence of non-immune, intravascular hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia and acute kidney injury. A vicious cycle of complement activation, endothelial cell damage, platelet activation, and thrombosis is the hallmark of the disease.

label: Tubulointerstitial fibrosis
definition: A progressive detrimental connective tissue deposition (fibrosis) on the kidney parenchyma involving the tubules and interstitial tissue of the kidney. Tubulointerstitial injury in the kidney is complex, involving a number of independent and overlapping cellular and molecular pathways, with renal interstitial fibrosis and tubular atrophy (IF/TA) as the final common pathway. However, IF and TA are separable, as shown by the profound TA in renal artery stenosis, which characteristically has little or no fibrosis (or inflammation). For new annotations it is preferable to annotate to the specific HPO terms for Renal interstitial fibrosis and/or Renal tubular atrophy.

label: Renal fibrosis
definition: Renal fibrosis is the consequence of an excessive accumulation of extracellular matrix that occurs in virtually every type of chronic kidney disease.

label: Impaired renal tubular reabsorption of chloride
definition: Any impairment of reabsorption of chloride by the kidney.

label: Duplication of renal pelvis
definition: A duplication of the renal pelvis.

label: Abnormal renal pelvis morphology
definition: An abnormality of the renal pelvis.

label: Tubular basement membrane disintegration
definition: DIsruption and breaking up of the basement membrane of the tubules of the kidney.

label: Abnormal tubular basement membrane morphology
definition: Abnormal structure of the basement membrane of the renal tubulus.

label: Renal cell carcinoma
definition: A type of carcinoma of the kidney with origin in the epithelium of the proximal convoluted renal tubule.

label: Renal neoplasm
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the kidney.

label: Patchy palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: A focal type of palmoplantar keratoderma in which only certain areas of the palms and soles are affected.

label: Giant melanosomes in melanocytes
definition: The presence of large spherical melanosomes (1 to 6 micrometer in diameter) in the cytoplasm of melanocytes.

label: Macular hypopigmented whorls, streaks, and patches
Congenital alopecia totalis
definition: Loss of all scalp hair with congenital onset.

label: Alopecia totalis
definition: Loss of all scalp hair.

label: Facial telangiectasia in butterfly midface distribution
definition: Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin in a butterfly midface distribution.

label: Facial telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin of the face.

label: Congenital giant melanocytic nevus
definition: The giant congenital nevus is greater than 8 cm in size, pigmented and often hairy. A giant congenital nevus is smaller in infants and children, but it usually continues to grow with the child.

label: Large cafe-au-lait macules with irregular margins
definition: Large hypermelanotic macules with jagged borders.

label: Bilobate gallbladder
definition: The presence of a bilobed gallbladder, related to a duplication of the gallbladder primordium.

label: Septate gallbladder
definition: Septate gallbladder is characterized by the presence of a septum that divides the gallbladder in two chambers. When the septum dividing the gallbladder lies longitudinally it is called bilobed gallbladder and when there is a transverse septum separating the fundus from the rest of the gallbladder it is called an hour-glass gallbladder.

label: Distal arthrogryposis
definition: An inherited primary limb malformation disorder characterized by congenital contractures of two or more different body areas and without primary neurologic and/or muscle disease that affects limb function.

label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the lower limbs
definition: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the bones of the lower limbs.

label: Abnormal lumbar spine morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the lumbar vertebral column.

label: Hypermobility of interphalangeal joints
definition: The ability of the interphalangeal joints to move beyond their normal range of motion.

label: Trapezoidal vertebral body
definition: An anomalous trapezoidal appearance of a vertebral body. A trapezoid is a four-sided shape that has two sides that are parallel and two sides that are not parallel. In this case, the two lateral sides of the vertebra are parallel, and the top and the bottom are slanted with respect to each other such that the vertebra is shorter in the front or back than on the other side.

label: Absent ossification of calvaria
definition: Acalvaria is an extremely rare congenital malformation characterized by an absence of flat bones of skull, dura mater, and associated muscles in the presence of normal cranial contents and facial bones.

label: Osteoporosis of vertebrae
definition: Osteoporosis affecting predominantly the vertebrae.

label: Posterior fusion of lumbosacral vertebrae
definition: Bony fusion of the posterior part of the L5 vertebral body with the sacrum.

label: Type D brachydactyly
definition: This type of brachydactyly is characterized by short and broad terminal phalanges of the thumbs and big toes.

label: Decreased anterioposterior diameter of lumbar vertebral bodies
Narrow anterio-posterior vertebral body diameter
definition: An abnormal reduction of the anterioposterior diameter of the vertebral body.

label: Hyperextensible hand joints
definition: The ability of the joints of the hand to move beyond their normal range of motion.

label: Short 3rd toe
definition: Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the third toe.

label: Intervertebral disk calcification
definition: The presence of abnormal calcium deposition of the intervertebral disk.

label: Bilateral ulnar hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the ulna on both sides.

label: 2-5 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the second to the fifth fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: Cortical sclerosis
definition: Sclerosis (abnormal hardening) of cortical bone, characterized by increased radiodensity.

label: Moderate generalized osteoporosis
definition: Moderate osteoporosis.

label: Multiple digital exostoses
definition: Multiple exostoses originating in the fingers and toes.

label: Salmonella osteomyelitis
definition: Osteomyelitis caused by infection with the bacteria, salmonella.

label: Massively thickened long bone cortices
definition: Extreme thickening of the cortex of long bones.

label: Os odontoideum
definition: Separation of the odontoid process from the body of the axis.

label: Bilateral intracerebral calcifications
definition: Deposition of calcium salts on both sides of the cerebrum.

label: Dupuytren contracture
definition: An abnormality of the hand resulting from contracture of the palmar fascia with a fixed flexion deformity of the metacarpophalangeal (MCP) joints and the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joints.

label: Joint contracture of the hand
definition: Contractures of one ore more joints of the hands meaning chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in non-bony tissue.

label: Tongue-like lumbar vertebral deformities
definition: A tongue-like protusion from the anterior aspect of lumbar vertebral bodies.

label: Anterior beaking of lumbar vertebrae
definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the vertebral bodies of the lumbar spine.

label: Tarsal synostosis
definition: Synostosis (bony fusion) involving one or more bones of the tarsus (calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, cuneiiform bones).

label: Patchy osteosclerosis
definition: Patchy (irregular) increase in bone density. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

label: Patchy changes of bone mineral density
definition: Patchy (irregular) changes in bone mineral density. These changes can either be patchy reduction or increase of mineral density as seen on x-rays. Depending on the pathomechanism and the underlying disease, these changes can either appear solely as reduction or increase or as a combination of both (patches of bone showing an increased density while others are affected by reduction of mineral density).

label: Dysplastic distal thumb phalanges with a central hole
Partial fusion of proximal row of carpal bones
Postaxial polydactyly type A
definition: Supernumerary digits located at the ulnar side of the hand with a complete extra finger and extra metacarpal.

label: Increased bone density with cystic changes
Enchondroma
definition: A solitary, benign, intramedullary cartilage tumor that is often found in the short tubular bones of the hands and feet, distal femur, and proximal humerus.

label: Bilateral triphalangeal thumbs
definition: A bilateral form of triphalangeal thumb.

label: Cutaneous syndactyly of toes
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between adjacent foot digits that involves at least half of the proximodistal length of one of the two involved digits; or, a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two digits of the foot that does not meet the prior objective criteria.

label: Shortening of all metacarpals
definition: Abnormal reduction in length of all metacarpal bones.

label: Short metacarpal
definition: Diminished length of one or more metacarpal bones in relation to the others of the same hand or to the contralateral metacarpal.

label: Hyperextensible thumb
definition: The ability of the thumb joints to move beyond their normal range of motion.

label: Nonopposable triphalangeal thumb
definition: A form of triphalangeal thumb that cannot be placed opposite the fingers of the same hand.

label: Short thumb
definition: Hypoplasia (congenital reduction in size) of the thumb.

label: Spinal stenosis with reduced interpedicular distance
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the spinal canal related to a reduction in the interpedicular distance (i.e., the distance measured between the pedicles on frontal [coronal] imaging).

label: Short tibia
definition: Underdevelopment (reduced size) of the tibia.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tibia
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the tibia.

label: Posterior subluxation of radial head
definition: Partial dislocation of the head of the radius in the posterior direction.

label: Avascular necrosis of the capital femoral epiphysis
definition: Avascular necrosis of the proximal epiphysis of the femur occurring in growing children and caused by an interruption of the blood supply to the head of the femur close to the hip joint. The necrosis is characteristically associated with flattening of the femoral head, for which reason the term coxa plana has been used to refer to this feature in the medical literature.

label: Juvenile aseptic necrosis
definition: Juvenile aseptic necrosis comprises a group of orthopedic diseases characterized by interruption of the blood supply of a bone, followed by localized bony necrosis most often of the epiphyses of bones of children or teenagers.

label: Osteosclerosis of the base of the skull
definition: An increase in bone density affecting the basicranium (base of the skull).

label: Neonatal epiphyseal stippling
definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more epiphyses during the neonatal period.

label: Basilar impression
definition: Abnormal elevation of the floor of the posterior fossa including occipital condyles and foramen magnum.

label: Small flat posterior fossa
definition: An abnormally small and flat configuration of the posterior cranial fossa.

label: 2-4 toe cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the toes 2, 3, and 4.

label: Fifth finger distal phalanx clinodactyly
definition: Bending or curvature of the distal phalanx of little finger in the radial direction (i.e., towards the 4th finger).

label: Short forearm
definition: Underdevelopment of both forearm bones, the ulna and the radius, resulting in a shortened forearm.

label: Absent fourth finger distal interphalangeal crease
definition: Absence of the distal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fourth finger.

label: Lumbar platyspondyly
definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates affecting the lumbar spine.

label: Generalized osteosclerosis
definition: An abnormal increase of bone mineral density with generalized involvement of the skeleton.

label: Abnormal mandible condylar process morphology
definition: An abnormality of a mandible condylar process.

label: Cortical thickening of long bone diaphyses
definition: Abnormal thickening of the cortex of the diaphyseal region of long bones.

label: Short humerus
definition: Underdevelopment of the humerus.

label: Shortening of all distal phalanges of the toes
definition: Abnormally short distal phalanx of toe of all toes.

label: Posterior radial head dislocation
definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an posterior direction.

label: Absent distal phalanges
definition: Aplasia (absence) of the distal phalanges.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the distal phalanges of the hand
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the distal phalanges.

label: Postaxial polysyndactyly of foot
definition: Combined syndactyly and polydactyly of the foot on the lateral side (i.e., on the side of the little toe).

label: Short finger
definition: Abnormally short finger associated with developmental hypoplasia.

label: Short phalanx of finger
definition: Short (hypoplastic) phalanx of finger, affecting one or more phalanges.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the middle phalanges of the hand
Clinodactyly of the 2nd toe
definition: Bending or curvature of a second toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe).

label: Flexion contracture of digit
definition: A bent (flexed) finger or toe joint that cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement of joints.

label: Toe joint contracture
definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of a toe joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

label: Dysharmonic delayed bone age
definition: A type of dysharmonic skeletal maturation in which there is a delay in skeletal maturation whose degree differs markedly in different bones.

label: Calcific stippling of infantile cartilaginous skeleton
Rounded middle phalanx of finger
definition: An abnormally round shape of the middle phalanx of the finger.

label: Abnormal middle phalanx morphology of the hand
definition: An anomaly of middle phalanx of finger.

label: Diffuse cerebral calcification
definition: Generalized deposition of calcium salts within the cerebrum.

label: Multiple prenatal fractures
definition: The presence of bone fractures in the prenatal period that are diagnosed at birth or before.

label: Ulnar radial head dislocation
definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an ulnar direction.

label: Type E brachydactyly
definition: In type E brachydactyly, shortening of the fingers is mainly in the metacarpals and metatarsals.

label: Pseudoarthrosis
definition: A pathologic entity characterized by a developmental defect in a long bone leading to bending and pathologic fracture, with inability to form a normal bony callus with subsequent fibrous nonunion, leading to the pseudarthrosis (or false joint")."

label: Opposable triphalangeal thumb
definition: A form of triphalangeal thumb that can be placed opposite the fingers of the same hand.

label: Metaphyseal enchondromatosis
definition: An enchondroma is a benign growth of cartilage that develops within the medullary cavity of bone. Enchondromatosis refers to the presence of multiple enchondromas, and this term refers to the presence of multiple enchondromas within the medulla of metaphyseal bone. Radiographically an enchondroma presents a an oval, linear, or pyramidal osteolytic (radiolucent) lesion with well defined margins.

label: Metaphyseal chondrodysplasia
definition: An abnormality of skeletal development characterized by a disturbance of the metaphysis and its histological structure with relatively normal epiphyses and vertebrae.

label: Metaphyseal dysplasia
definition: The presence of dysplastic regions in metaphyseal regions.

label: Brachytelomesophalangy
definition: Disproportionately short middle and distal phalanges compared to the hand/foot.

label: Polysyndactyly of hallux
definition: Combined syndactyly and polydactyly of the great toe.

label: Progressive flexion contractures
definition: Progressively worsening joint contractures.

label: Enlarged sagittal diameter of the cervical canal
Congenital finger flexion contractures
definition: Multiple bent (flexed) finger joints that cannot be straightened actively or passively.

label: Metacarpophalangeal synostosis
definition: Fusion of a metacarpal bone with the proximal phalanx of the finger distal to it across the corresponding metacarpophalangeal joint.

label: Metacarpal synostosis
definition: Fusion involving two or more metacarpal bones (A synostosis of the first metacarpal and the proximal phalanx of the thumb can also be observed, note that the first metacarpal bone corresponds to a proximal phalanx).

label: Absent ossification of cervical vertebral bodies
definition: A lack of bone mineralization of one or more body of cervical vertebra.

label: Aphalangy of the hands
definition: Absence of a digit or of one or more phalanges of a finger.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the hand
definition: Small or missing phalangeal bones of the fingers of the hand.

label: Hyperostosis cranialis interna
definition: Bony overgrowth of the internal (endosteal) surface of the calvaria and the base of skull.

label: Progressive forearm bowing
definition: Progressive bending or abnormal curvature of the forearm skeleton.

label: Progressive bowing of long bones
definition: Progressive bending or abnormal curvature of a long bone.

label: Proximal tibial and fibular fusion
definition: A developmental defect characterized by the abnormal fusion of the proximal tibia and fibula.

label: Double first metacarpals
definition: Duplication of the metacarpal I bones.

label: Radial deviation of thumb terminal phalanx
Severe generalized osteoporosis
definition: Severe degree of osteoporosis.

label: Fifth metacarpal with ulnar notch
definition: Presence of an angular or V -shaped indentation on the ulnar side of the fifth metacarpal bone (i.e., on the sides towards the fifth finger).

label: Abnormal 5th metacarpal morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the fifth metacarpal bone.

label: Delayed pneumatization of the mastoid process
definition: An abnormally reduced degree of pneumatization (i.e., formation of air cells) in the mastoid process with respect to age-dependent norms.

label: Rhomboid or triangular shaped 5th finger middle phalanx
definition: Rhomboid or triangular shaped 5th (little) finger middle phalanx.

label: Triangular shaped middle phalanx of the 5th finger
definition: Triangular shaped middle phalanx of the 5th (little) finger. A triangular or so called delta shaped phalanx is a typical result after a bracket epiphysis of the affected phalanx.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the metacarpal bones
definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the metacarpal bones.

label: Abnormal epiphysis morphology of the phalanges of the hand
definition: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand. Note that this includes the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits).

label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the upper limbs
definition: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the bones of the upper limbs.

label: Synostosis involving bones of the lower limbs
definition: An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones lower limbs.

label: Abnormal respiratory motile cilium morphology
definition: Abnormal arrangement of the structures of the motile cilium.

label: Abnormal respiratory epithelium morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the pseudostratified ciliated epithelium that lines much of the conducting portion of the airway, including part of the nasal cavity and larynx, the trachea, and bronchi.

label: Desquamative interstitial pneumonitis
definition: Diffuse filling of the distal airspaces of the lungs, the alveoli, with macrophages. Desquamative interstitial pneumonitis (DIP) is characterized additionally by thickened alveolar septa and by a sparse inflammatory infiltrate that often includes plasma cells and occasional eosinophils. The alveoli are lined by plump cuboidal pneumocytes. Lymphoid aggregates may be present.

label: Bilateral lung agenesis
definition: Bilateral lack of development of the lungs.

label: Laryngeal obstruction
definition: Blockage of the upper airway at the level of the larynx often accompanied by respiratory distress.

label: Ventilator dependence with inability to wean
Decreased sensitivity to hypoxemia
definition: Reduced tendency to respond to a reduced concentration of oxygen in the blood by increasing respiration.

label: Multiple pulmonary cysts
definition: The presence of multiple lung cysts.

label: Pulmonary cyst
definition: A round circumscribed space within a lung that is surrounded by an epithelial or fibrous wall of variable thickness. A cyst usually has a thin and regular wall (less than 2 mm) and contains air, although some may contain fluid.

label: Apneic episodes in infancy
definition: Recurrent episodes of apnea occurring during infancy.

label: Laryngeal web
definition: A membrane-like structure that extends across the laryngeal lumen close to the level of the vocal cords.

label: Anteroposteriorly shortened larynx
definition: Abnormal shortening of the larynx in the anteroposterior (front to back) axis.

label: Impaired gluconeogenesis
definition: An impairment of gluconeogenesis.

label: Hypoargininemia
definition: A decreased concentration of arginine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating arginine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of arginine in the blood circulation.

label: Intermittent hypothermia
definition: Episodes of reduced body temperature.

label: Temperature instability
definition: Disordered thermoregulation characterized by an impaired ability to maintain a balance between heat production and heat loss, with resulting instability of body temperature.

label: Respiratory acidosis
definition: Acidosis because of respiratory retention of carbon dioxide.

label: Fructose intolerance
definition: Reduced intestinal absorption of fructose. Breath testing after ingestion of fructose has been widely adopted as a standard method of identifying fructose malabsorption and intolerance. A dose of 25 g of fructose dissolved in a 10% solution is generally accepted as the appropriate dose of fructose for clinical use of H2 and CH4 breath testing. High levels of hydrogen in exhaled breath subsequent hours indicate fructose intolerance. Presence of malabsorption and reproduction of symptoms during a breath test provides the best objective evidence and symptom correlation for fructose intolerance.

label: Impairment of fructose metabolism
definition: An impairment of a fructose metabolic process.

label: Episodic ketoacidosis
definition: Intermittent episodes of ketoacidosis.

label: Type II diabetes mellitus
definition: A type of diabetes mellitus initially characterized by insulin resistance and hyperinsulinemia and subsequently by glucose interolerance and hyperglycemia.

label: Metabolic ketoacidosis
definition: A metabolic acidosis due to accumulation of ketone bodies generally observed in the setting of poor nutritional intake.

label: Reduced phenylalanine hydroxylase level
definition: A reduction in phenylalanine 4-monooxygenase level.

label: Abnormal neck physiology
definition: Any functional anomaly of the neck region.

label: Multinodular goiter
definition: Enlargement of the thyroid gland related to multiple nodules in the thyroid gland.

label: Nodular goiter
definition: Enlargement of the thyroid gland related to one or more nodules in the thyroid gland.

label: Congenital muscular torticollis
definition: A congenital form of torticollis resulting from shortening of the sternocleidomastoid muscle and leading to a limited range of motion in both rotation and lateral bending.

label: Redundant neck skin
definition: Excess skin around the neck, often lying in horizontal folds.

label: Thyroid hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the thyroid gland.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the thyroid gland
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the thyroid gland.

label: Limited neck flexion
definition: Reduced ability to lower the chin towards the chest by bending the neck.

label: Decreased adipose tissue around neck
definition: Reduced amount of adipose tissue in the region of the neck.

label: Ureteral atresia
definition: A developmental defect defined by the failure of the formation of the lumen (tube) of the ureter.

label: Hypotrophy of the small hand muscles
Broad phalanx
definition: Increased side-to-side width of one or more phalanges of the fingers or toes.

label: Cuboidal metacarpal
definition: Severely shortened metacarpal with a cuboidal appearance.

label: Delayed phalangeal epiphyseal ossification
definition: Delay in the process of formation and maturation of the epiphysis of one or more phalanx.

label: Metaphyseal cupping of metacarpals
definition: Metaphyseal cupping affecting the metacarpal bones.

label: Cone-shaped epiphyses of the phalanges of the hand
definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphyses of the fingers of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of a phalanx.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 2nd metacarpal
definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 2nd metacarpal.

label: Y-shaped metacarpals
definition: Y-shaped metacarpals are the result of a partial fusion of two metacarpal bones, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Y-shaped metacarpals may be seen in combination with polydactyly.

label: Distal widening of metacarpals
definition: Abnormal increase in width of the distal region of the metacarpal bones.

label: Abnormal periosteum morphology
definition: An anomalous structure of the periosteum, i.e., of the membrane that covers the outer surface of bones.

label: Ulnar deviation of the hand
definition: Divergence of the longitudinal axis of the hand at the wrist in a posterior (ulnar) direction (i.e., towards the little finger).

label: Cone-shaped metacarpal epiphyses
definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphyses of the metacarpal bones, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphyses are located at the distal ends of the metacarpal bones.

label: Abnormal proximal phalanx morphology of the hand
Multiple carpal ossification centers
definition: A delay in the process of formation and maturation of the epiphysis of one or more long bones.

label: Metacarpophalangeal joint contracture
definition: A chronic loss of joint motion in metacarpophalangeal joints due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement.

label: Absent proximal finger flexion creases
definition: Absence of the proximal interphalangeal flexion creases of the fingers.

label: Malaligned carpal bone
definition: Malalignement of carpal bone angles either with respect to each other, to the corresponding metacarpals or with respect to the wrist (radius and ulna).

label: 3-4 finger osseus syndactyly
definition: Fusion of the third (middle) and fourth (ring) finger, involving soft parts and including fusion of individual finger bones.

label: Osseous finger syndactyly
definition: Webbing or fusion of the fingers, involving soft parts and including fusion of individual finger bones.

label: Metacarpophalangeal joint hyperextensibility
definition: Increased mobility of one ore more metacarpophalangeal joint.

label: Finger syndactyly
definition: Webbing or fusion of the fingers, involving soft parts only or including bone structure. Bony fusions are referred to as bony" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a radio-ulnar axis. Fusions of bones of the fingers in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as "Symphalangism"."

label: Fingerpad telangiectases
definition: Telangiectasia (small dilated blood vessels) located in the fingerpads at the tips of the fingers.

label: Telangiectasia of the skin
definition: Presence of small, permanently dilated blood vessels near the surface of the skin, visible as small focal red lesions.

label: Tapered metacarpals
definition: Metacarpal that becomes thinner toward the distal end.

label: Shortening of all middle phalanges of the fingers
definition: Short, hypoplastic middle phalanx of finger, affecting all fingers.

label: Expanded phalanges with widened medullary cavities
Broad phalanges of the hand
definition: Increased width of the phalanges of the hand.

label: Multiple palmar creases
definition: The presence of multiple creases on the palm of the hand (more than the normal three major creases (distal transverse crease, proximal transverse crease, and thenar crease).

label: Shortening of all distal phalanges of the fingers
definition: Hypoplasia of all of the distal phalanx of finger.

label: Acral ulceration
definition: A type of digital ulcer that manifests as an open sore on the surface of the skin at the tip of a finger or toe.

label: Digital ulcer
definition: An open sore on the surface of the skin of a finger or toe.

label: Long proximal phalanx of finger
definition: Increased length of the proximal phalanx of finger.

label: Long phalanx of finger
definition: Increased length of multiple or a single phalanx of finger.

label: Drumstick terminal phalanges
definition: Rounding and broadening of the tufts of the distal phalanges.

label: Enlarged metacarpal epiphyses
definition: Abnormally large size of one or more growth plates (epiphyses) of the metacarpal bones (i.e., the tubular bones of the hand between the carpus and the phalanges).

label: Premature fusion of phalangeal epiphyses
definition: Fusion of the epiphysis and metaphysis of one or more phalanges prior to the normal age or stage of growth.

label: Shortening of all proximal phalanges of the fingers
definition: Congenital hypoplasia of proximal phalanx of finger or all fingers.

label: Short proximal phalanx of finger
definition: Congenital hypoplasia of one or more proximal phalanx of finger.

label: Central Y-shaped metacarpal
definition: A central Y-shaped metacarpal is the result of a partial fusion of two central metacarpals (i.e., metacarpals 2-4) of the hand, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Central Y-shaped metacarpals may be seen as a result of a central polydactyly with partial fusion of the duplicated metacarpal.

label: Broad metacarpal epiphyses
definition: Increased side-to-side width of the metacarpal epiphyses.

label: Swan neck-like deformities of the fingers
definition: A swan neck deformity describes a finger with a hyperextended PIP joint and a flexed DIP joint. The most common cause for a swan neck-like deformity is a disruption of the end of the extensor tendon. Conditions that loosen the PIP joint and allow it to hyperextend, for example conditions that weaken the volar plate, can produce a swan neck deformity of the finger. One example is rheumatoid arthritis. Another cause are conditions that tighten up the small (intrinsic) muscles of the hand and fingers, for example hand trauma or nerve disorders, such as cerebral palsy, Parkinson's disease, or stroke.

label: Proximal symphalangism of hands
definition: The term proximal symphalangism refers to a bony fusion of the middle and proximal phalanges of the digits of the hand, in other words the proximal interphalangeal joint (PIJ) is missing which can be seen either on x-rays or as an absence of the proximal interphalangeal finger creases.

label: Ulnar deviation of thumb
definition: Bending or curvature of a thumb towards the ulnar side (towards the ring finger).

label: Ulnar deviation of finger
definition: Bending or curvature of a finger toward the ulnar side (i.e., away from the thumb). The deviation is at the metacarpal-phalangeal joint, and this finding is distinct from clinodactyly.

label: Mesoaxial hand polydactyly
definition: The presence of a supernumerary finger (not a thumb) involving the third or fourth metacarpal with associated osseous syndactyly.

label: Mesoaxial polydactyly
definition: The presence of a supernumerary finger or toe (not a thumb or hallux) involving the third or fourth metacarpal/tarsal with associated osseous syndactyly.

label: Irregular metacarpals
definition: Irregular morphology of one or more metacarpal bones.

label: Short metacarpals with rounded proximal ends
Soft tissue swelling of interphalangeal joints
Aplasia/Hypoplasia of fingers
definition: Small/hypoplastic or absent/aplastic fingers.

label: Chess-pawn distal phalanges
definition: A morphological abnormality of distal phalanges such that they have the appearance of chess pawns.

label: Flattened, squared-off epiphyses of tubular bones
Metacarpal diaphyseal endosteal sclerosis
definition: Increase in bone density in the diaphyseal (shaft) region of a metacarpal bone.

label: Two carpal ossification centers present at birth
Metacarpal pseudoepiphysis
definition: A pseudoepiphysis is a secondary ossification center distinct from the normal epiphysis. The normal metacarpal epiphyses are located at the distal ends of the metacarpal bones. Accessory epiphyses (which are also known as pseudoepiphyses) can also occasionally be observed at the proximal ends of the metacarpals, usually involving the 2nd metacarpal bone.

label: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the 2nd metacarpal
definition: Any abnormality of the epiphysis of the second metacarpal bone.

label: Decreased palmar creases
definition: Poorly defined or shallow palmar creases.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the palmar creases
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the palmar creases.

label: Deep palmar crease
definition: Excessively deep creases of the palm.

label: Tapered phalanx of finger
definition: Phalanges of the fingers becoming thinner toward the distal end.

label: Thimble-shaped middle phalanges of hand
definition: The middle phalanx of finger resembles a thimble, a small metal cap to protect the finger while sewing that has a broad (proximal) base and narrower top, whereby both base and top are flat.

label: Osteolytic defects of the hand bones
Decreased movement range in interphalangeal joints
Irregular phalanges
definition: Alteration of the normally smooth radiographic contour of phalanges producing an irregular appearance.

label: Hypersegmentation of proximal phalanx of second finger
definition: Presence of an additional phalanx-like bone, producing an extra, wedge-shaped bone at the base of the proximal phalanx of the second finger.

label: Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
Metaphyseal cupping of proximal phalanges
definition: Metaphyseal cupping affecting the proximal phalanges.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 5th finger
definition: A small/hypoplastic or absent/aplastic 5th finger.

label: Thin proximal phalanges with broad epiphyses of the hand
Single interphalangeal crease of fifth finger
definition: Presence of only one (instead of two, as normal) interphalangeal crease of the fifth finger.

label: Limited mobility of proximal interphalangeal joint
Tapering pointed ends of distal finger phalanges
definition: A reduction in diameter of the distal phalanx of finger towards the distal end such that the tip of the phalanx comes to a point (this feature can be observed on radiograms).

label: Tapered distal phalanges of finger
definition: A reduction in diameter of the distal phalanx of finger towards the distal end.

label: Osteoarthritis of the first carpometacarpal joint
Expanded metacarpals with widened medullary cavities
Osteoarthritis of the distal interphalangeal joint
Osteolysis involving tarsal bones
definition: An increased resorption of bone matrix by osteoclasts leading to bony defects involving the tarsal bones.

label: Slender metacarpals
definition: Decreased width of the metacarpal bones (that is, reduced diameter).

label: Shortening of all middle phalanges of the toes
definition: Abnormal shortening of all middle phalanges of toes.

label: Limited wrist movement
definition: An abnormal limitation of the mobility of the wrist.

label: Abnormal circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
definition: Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the blood circulation outside normal limits.

label: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the 2nd finger
definition: Abnormality of one or all of the epiphyses of the proximal, middle, and distal phalanges of the 2nd finger.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 2nd finger
definition: A small/hypoplastic or absent/aplastic 2nd finger.

label: Small placenta
definition: Reduced size of the placenta.

label: Abnormal placental size
definition: A deviation from normal size of the placenta.

label: Large placenta
definition: Increased size of the placenta.

label: Fluctuating splenomegaly
definition: Intermittently increased size of the spleen.

label: Hypoplastic spleen
definition: Underdevelopment of the spleen.

label: Pancreatic lymphangiectasis
definition: The presence of lymphangiectasis in the pancreas.

label: Reduced pancreatic beta cells
definition: Reduced number of beta cells in the pancreatic islets of Langerhans.

label: Pancreatic hyperplasia
definition: Hyperplasia of the pancreas.

label: Abnormal pancreas size
definition: A deviation from the normal size of the pancreas.

label: Ectopic pancreatic tissue
definition: The presence of pancreatic tissue outside the normal pancreas, in many cases along the foregut and proximal midgut.

label: Chronic pancreatitis
definition: A chronic form of pancreatitis.

label: Generalized hypoplasia of dental enamel
definition: A generalized form of developmental hypoplasia of the dental enamel.

label: Enamel hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the dental enamel.

label: Multiple unerupted teeth
definition: The presence of multiple embedded tooth germs which have failed to erupt.

label: Enamel hypomineralization
definition: A decreased amount of enamel mineralization. Hypomineralized enamel has a brown discoloration and brittle aspect.

label: Agenesis of central incisor
definition: Agenesis of one or more central incisors, i.e., of lower secondary incisor, lower primary incisor, upper secondary incisor, or of upper central primary incisor.

label: Agenesis of incisor
definition: Agenesis of incisor.

label: Discolored lateral incisors
definition: The presence of discolored lateral incisors.

label: Marked delay in eruption of permanent teeth
Agenesis of maxillary central incisor
definition: Agenesis of upper secondary incisor or of upper central primary incisor.

label: Prolonged bleeding after dental extraction
definition: Prolonged bleeding post dental extraction sufficient to require medical intervention.

label: Dagger-shaped pulp calcifications
definition: Dagger-shaped calcifications in the dental pulp.

label: Generalized microdontia
definition: A generalized form of microdontia.

label: Widely spaced primary teeth
definition: Increased space between the primary teeth. Note this phenotype should be distinguished from increased space due purely to microdontia.

label: Solitary median maxillary central incisor
definition: A single maxillary central incisor positioned in the midline with morphological symmetry of the crown and bordered by lateral incisors.

label: Abnormal number of incisors
definition: The presence of an altered number of the incisor teeth.

label: Irregularly spaced teeth
definition: Irregular distribution of the teeth along the dental arch, i.e., and irregular spatial pattern of teeth.

label: Premature loss of primary teeth
definition: Loss of the primary (also known as deciduous) teeth before the usual age.

label: Premature loss of teeth
definition: Exfoliation of a tooth more than 2 SD earlier than the normal age for the deciduous teeth and not related to traume or neglect. Exfoliation of a permanent tooth is per se abnormal.

label: Alveolar process hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the alveolar process (also known as alveolar bone).

label: Misalignment of incisors
definition: Misaligned incisor.

label: Supernumerary maxillary incisor
definition: The presence of a supernumerary, i.e., extra, maxillary incisor, either the primary maxillary incisor or the permanent maxillary incisor.

label: Supernumerary tooth
definition: The presence of one or more teeth additional to the normal number.

label: Crowded maxillary incisors
definition: A type of dental misalignment with crowded central incisors, i.e., of maxillary secondary incisor, or of maxillary central primary incisor.

label: Hypoplasia of the primary teeth
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the primary teeth.

label: Persistence of primary teeth
definition: Persistence of the primary teeth beyond the age by which they normally are shed and replaced by the permanent teeth.

label: Short dental root
definition: Tooth root length more than 2 SD below mean, or subjectively apparently decreased tooth root length.

label: Abnormal size of the dental root
Premature eruption of permanent teeth
definition: Premature tooth eruption of the permanent dentition.

label: Malformation of mandibular premolar
definition: An abnormality of the morphology of secondary premolar tooth.

label: Abnormal premolar morphology
definition: An abnormality of morphology of premolar tooth.

label: Conical mandibular incisor
definition: An abnormal conical morphology of the primary or permanent mandibular incisors.

label: Conical incisor
definition: An abnormal conical morphology of the incisor tooth.

label: Peg-shaped maxillary lateral incisors
definition: A tooth crown with its mesial and distal sides converging or tapering toward the incisal edge causing severe reduction of mesiodistal diameter

label: Abnormal primary molar morphology
definition: An abnormality of morphology of primary molar.

label: Abnormal molar morphology
definition: An abnormality of morphology of molar tooth.

label: Screwdriver-shaped incisors
definition: An abnormality of morphology of the incisor tooth in which the tooth is shaped like a screwdriver blade, i.e., having a rhomboid shape.

label: Microdontia of primary teeth
definition: Decreased size of the primary teeth.

label: Agenesis of permanent teeth
definition: A congenital defect characterized by the absence of one or more permanent teeth, including oligodontia, hypodontia, and adontia of the of permanent teeth.

label: Abnormal number of permanent teeth
definition: The presence of an altered number of of permanent teeth.

label: Pulp obliteration
definition: Mineralized substance filling the entire dental pulp space.

label: Failure of eruption of permanent teeth
definition: Lack of tooth eruption of the secondary dentition.

label: Hypoplasia of the tooth germ
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the tooth germ, i.e., of the structure that forms in odontogenesis that will develop into a tooth.

label: Agenesis of mandibular central incisor
definition: Agenesis of lower secondary incisor or lower primary incisor.

label: Premature loss of permanent teeth
definition: Premature loss of the permanent teeth.

label: Shovel-shaped maxillary central incisors
definition: A tooth with a crown with marked lingual or palatal marginal ridges causing scooped lingual or palatal surfaces.

label: Abnormal femoral epiphysis morphology
definition: An anomaly of a growth plate of a femur.

label: Crumpled long bones
definition: An crumpled radiographic appearance of the long bones, as if the long bone had been crushed together producing irregularities. This feature is the result of multiple fractures and repeated rounds of ineffective healing, as can be seen for instance in severe forms of osteogenesis imperfecta.

label: Irregular patellae
definition: An alteration of the normally relatively smooth margins of the kneecap in radiographic images leading to an irregular contour.

label: Distal ulnar epiphyseal stippling
definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the distal epiphysis of the ulna.

label: Abnormal distal ulnar epiphysis morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the ulna.

label: Broad long bone diaphyses
definition: Increased width of the diaphysis of long bones.

label: Dumbbell-shaped femur
definition: The femur is shortened and displays flaring (widening) of the metaphyses.

label: Osteolysis involving bones of the lower limbs
Knee flexion contracture
definition: A type of knee joint contracture in which the knee is in a fixed bent (flexed) configuration such that it cannot be straightened actively or passively.

label: Knee contracture
definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the knee joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

label: Rudimentary fibula
definition: Absent or nearly absent fibula. (Does not include aplastic)

label: Club-shaped distal femur
definition: An abnormal conformation of the femur that becomes gradually enlarged towards the distal end. This feature affects the distal femoral metaphysis and epiphysis.

label: Short lower limbs
definition: Shortening of the legs related to developmental hypoplasia of the bones of the leg.

label: Lower limb undergrowth
definition: Leg shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the lower extremity.

label: Hypoplastic distal radial epiphyses
definition: Underdevelopment of the distal epiphysis of the radius.

label: Wide distal femoral metaphysis
definition: Increased width of the distal part of the shaft (metaphysis) of the femur.
