label: Abnormal distal femoral metaphysis morphology
definition: An anomaly of the metaphysis of the distal femur (close to the knee).

label: Limited knee flexion
definition: Reduced ability to flex (bend) the knee joint.

label: Anterior tibial bowing
definition: An abnormal anterior bending or curvature of the tibia.

label: Overtubulated long bones
definition: Overconstriction, or narrowness of the diaphysis and metaphysis of long bones.

label: Limited pronation/supination of forearm
definition: A limitation of the ability to place the forearm in a position such that the palm faces anteriorly (supination) and to place the forearm in a position such that the palm faces posteriorly (pronation).

label: Flat distal femoral epiphysis
definition: An abnormal flattening of the distal epiphysis of femur.

label: Abnormality of the distal femoral epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Club-shaped proximal femur
definition: An abnormal conformation of the femur that becomes gradually enlarged towards the proximal end. This feature affects the proximal femoral metaphysis and epiphysis.

label: Irregular distal femoral epiphysis
definition: Anomaly of the contour of the Distal epiphysis of femur such that its normally smooth appearance is irregular.

label: Progressive leg bowing
definition: Progressive bending or abnormal curvature of the leg.

label: Distal tibial bowing
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of the distal portion of the tibia.

label: Cortically dense long tubular bones
definition: Increased density of the compact bone of long bone.

label: Asymmetric radial dysplasia
definition: The presence of asymmetric developmental dysplasia of the radius.

label: Peg-like central prominence of distal tibial metaphyses
Elongated radius
definition: Increased length of the radius.

label: Broad femoral neck
definition: An abnormally wide femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft).

label: Hypoplasia of proximal radius
definition: Proximal radial shortening owing to a congenital defect of development.

label: Disproportionate prominence of the femoral medial condyle
Enlargement of the distal femoral epiphysis
definition: An abnormal enlargement of the distal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Radioulnar dislocation
definition: A dislocation is a separation of the radius and ulna bones where they normally meet. The radioulnar joints are two locations, proximal and distal, in which the radius and ulna articulate in the forearm. Both can dislocate.

label: Increased density of long bone diaphyses
Hypoplasia of proximal fibula
definition: Underdevelopment or shortening of the end of the fibula (calf bone) nearest the knee.

label: Patellar aplasia
definition: Absence of the patella.

label: Multicentric ossification of proximal femoral epiphyses
Abnormal ossification involving the femoral head and neck
Lateral displacement of the femoral head
definition: A developmental anomaly with lateral displacement of the femoral head.

label: Delayed patellar ossification
definition: Formation of bone in the patella later than normal.

label: Irregular proximal tibial epiphyses
definition: Anomaly of the contour of the proximal epiphysis of the tibia such that its normally smooth appearance is irregular.

label: Abnormality of the proximal tibial epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the tibia.

label: Dorsal subluxation of ulna
definition: Partial dislocation of the ulna in the dorsal direction.

label: Abnormal ankle physiology
definition: A functional anomaly of the ankle.

label: Proximal femoral epiphysiolysis
definition: Slipped capital femoral epiphysis is defined as a posterior and inferior slippage of the proximal epiphysis of the femur onto the metaphysis (femoral neck), occurring through the physeal plate during the early adolescent growth spurt.

label: Generalized bone demineralization
definition: A generalized decrease in bone mineral density.

label: Periosteal thickening of long tubular bones
definition: Thickening of the periosteum of long bone.

label: Limited shoulder movement
definition: A limitation of the range of movement of the shoulder joint.

label: Abnormal shoulder physiology
definition: Anopmalous function of the shoulder. The shoulder is a ball-and-socket joint that is made up of humerus, scapula and clavicle, which are connected by the sternoclavicular joint (SC), the acromioclavicular joint (AC), the glenohumeral joint (GH), and the scapulothoracic joint (ST). The GH, AC and SC joints link the upper extremity to the axial skeleton at the thorax and enable movement at the shoulder joint: flexion, extension, and rotation of the arm.

label: Thin long bone diaphyses
definition: Decreased width of the diaphysis of long bones.

label: Anterior bowing of long bones
definition: An abnormal anterior curvature of a long bone.

label: Abnormality of endocrine pancreas physiology
definition: A function abnormality of the endocrine pancreas.

label: Abnormal number of teeth
definition: The presence of an altered number of of teeth.

label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the extremities
Abnormal lower limb epiphysis morphology
definition: An anomaly of one or more epiphyses of one or both legs.

label: Diverticulosis of trachea
definition: Tracheal diverticula are blind-ended outpouchings arising from the trachea. They are usually an incidental finding. Occasionally they can mimic pneumomediastinum. Tracheal diverticula are either congenital or acquired, in the latter case the most common causes are prolonged increased intraluminal pressure, e.g. chronic cough, COPD, tracheomalacia, and iatrogenic (e.g. post-surgical).

label: Chronic pulmonary obstruction
definition: An anomaly that is characterized progressive airflow obstruction that is only partly reversible, inflammation in the airways, and systemic effects or comorbities.

label: Laryngeal stridor
definition: An abnormal high-pitched noisy sound, occurring during inhalation or exhalation caused by the incomplete obstruction in the throat.

label: Abnormal larynx physiology
definition: Any anomaly of the function of the larynx.

label: Abnormal pulmonary alveolar system morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the pulmonary acinus, alveolar parenchyma, or alveoli.

label: Hypersensitivity pneumonitis
definition: Hypersensitivity pneumonitis involves inhalation of an antigen. This leads to an exaggerated immune response and a following inflammation of the alveoli within the lungs. The main feature of chronic hypersensitivity pneumonitis on lung biopsies is expansion of the interstitium by lymphocytes accompanied by an occasional multinucleated giant cell or loose granuloma. After exposure to the provoking antigen, following symptoms can be seen: fever, chills, malaise, cough, hemoptysis, chest tightness, dyspnea, rash, swelling and headache and can be completely reversible, based on the duration of the illness, categorized as acute (HP:0011009), subacute (HP:0011011), and chronic (HP:0011010).

label: Intraalveolar phospholipid accumulation
definition: Accumulation of amorphous PAS-positive material in the space between alveolar macrophages, sometimes as condensed form (oval bodies) are typically found in alveolar proteinosis.

label: Abnormal bronchoalveolar lavage fluid morphology
definition: Abnormal type or counts of nucleated immune cells and acellular components in bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL) fluid. BAL us performed with a fiberoptic bronchoscope in the wedged position within a selected bronchopulmonary segment. BAL is commonly used to inform the differential diagnosis of interstitial lung disease or to monitor therapeutic interventions.

label: Pulmonary venous occlusion
definition: Substantial narrowing or blockage of small pulmonary veins as a result of disorganized smooth muscle hypertrophy and collagen matrix deposition.

label: Alveolar cell carcinoma
definition: Adenocarcinoma of the Bronchus.

label: Pulmonary lymphangiectasia
definition: Abnormal dilatation of the pulmonary lymphatic vessels. Lymphatic fluid in the lung is derived from normal leakage of fluid out of the blood capillaries in the lung. In pulmonary lymphangiectasia, the pulmonary lymphatics are not properly connected and become dilated with fluid.

label: Abnormal pulmonary lymphatics
definition: An abnormality of the pulmonary lymphatic chain.

label: Lymphocytic interstitial pneumonia
definition: Lymphocytic interstitial pneumonitis is a benign lymphoproliferative disorder of the lung that is characterized by the presence of a dense, predominantly lymphocytic interstitial infiltrate (lymphocytes, plasma cells, other elements of the lymphoreticular system) that expands the alveolar septa.

label: Pulmonary interstitial lymphocyte infiltration
definition: Abnormal accumulation of lymphocytes in the interstitium of the lung.

label: Chronic lung disease
definition: According to the definitions of the American and British Thoracic Societies, including pulmonary functional tests, X-rays, and CT scans for items such as fibrosis, bronchiectasis, bullae, emphysema, nodular or lymphomatous abnormalities.

label: Recurrent pneumonia
definition: An increased susceptibility to pneumonia as manifested by a history of recurrent episodes of pneumonia.

label: Recurrent intrapulmonary hemorrhage
definition: A recurrent hemorrhage occurring within the lung.

label: Pulmonary hemorrhage
definition: Pulmonary hemorrhage is a bleeding within the lungs. Older children and adults may spit blood or bloody sputum. Neonates, infants and young children usually do not spit up blood. Anemia, pulmonary infiltrates, increasingling bloody return on BAL and the presence of hemosiderin-laden macrophages in broncho-alveolar lavage (BAL) fluid or lung biopsy can diagnose lung bleeding. Alveolar macrophages contain phagocytosed red blood cells and stain positive for hemosiderin, a product of hemoglobin degradation, after about 48-72 hours following pulmonary hemorraghe. Previous or recurrent bleeding can thus be distinguished from fresh events. A differentiation into local or diffuse is of importance. Also differentiate if pulmonary hemorrhage is due to a primary lung disorder or a manifestation of a systemic disease.

label: Recurrent bronchopulmonary infections
definition: An increased susceptibility to bronchopulmonary infections as manifested by a history of recurrent bronchopulmonary infections.

label: Extrapulmonary lobar sequestration
definition: A type of pulmonary sequestration that is completely enclosed in its own pleural sac, occurring above, within, or below the diaphragm, and without communication with the tracheobronchial tree.

label: Pulmonary sequestration
definition: The presence of a piece lung tissue which is not attached to the pulmonary blood supply and does not communicate with the other lung tissue (not connected to the standard bronchial airways and not performing a function in respiration).

label: Pulmonary arteriovenous malformation
definition: Pulmonary arteriovenous malformation, a condition most commonly associated with hereditary hemorrhagic telangiectasia, is an abnormal communication between the pulmonary artery and pulmonary vein without an intervening capillary communication. HRCT images usually show a coarse spidery appearance of the peripheral vascular markings in the lungs. More specific findings are obtained in the pulmonary angiogram where the normally invisible capillary phase is replaced by irregular vascular channels bridging the peripheral branches of pulmonary arteries and veins.

label: Diffuse hepatic steatosis
definition: A diffuse form of hepatic steatosis.

label: Decreased mitochondrial complex III activity in liver tissue
definition: Decreased activity of complex III of the mitochondrion in the liver.

label: Hepatic calcification
definition: The presence of abnormal calcium deposition in the liver.

label: Biliary hyperplasia
definition: Hyperplasia of the biliary tree, as manifested by increased size of bile ducts, dilated lumen, and histologically by an increased number of epithelial cells or hyperplasia.

label: Storage in hepatocytes
definition: Hepatocytes (liver parenchymal cells) exhibit a bloated appearance because of expansion of the cytoplasm by accumulated material.

label: Malformation of the hepatic ductal plate
Fluctuating hepatomegaly
definition: Intermittently increased size of the liver.

label: Increased hepatocellular lipid droplets
definition: An abnormal increase in the amount of intracellular lipid droplets in hepatocytes.

label: Increased hepatic glycogen content
definition: An increase in the amount of glycogen stored in hepatocytes compared to normal.

label: Abnormal hepatic glycogen storage
definition: Change in normal glycogen storage content.

label: Reduced number of intrahepatic bile ducts
definition: The presence of reduced numbers of intrahepatic bile duct than normal.

label: Acute hepatic steatosis
definition: An acute form of hepatic steatosis.

label: Macronodular cirrhosis
definition: A type of cirrhosis characterized by the presence of large regenerative nodules.

label: Prolonged neonatal jaundice
definition: Neonatal jaundice refers to a yellowing of the skin and other tissues of a newborn infant as a result of increased concentrations of bilirubin in the blood. Neonatal jaundice affects over half of all newborns to some extent in the first week of life. Prolonged neonatal jaundice is said to be present if the jaundice persists for longer than 14 days in term infants and 21 days in preterm infants.

label: Portal fibrosis
definition: Fibroblast proliferation and fiber expansion from the portal areas to the lobule.

label: Depletion of mitochondrial DNA in liver
definition: An abnormal reduction in the number of mitochondria in hepatocytes.

label: Mitochondrial depletion
definition: An abnormal reduction in mitochondrial DNA content of cells.

label: Reye syndrome-like episodes
definition: Repeated occurrences of acute noninflammatory encephalopathy and fatty degenerative liver failure.

label: Congenital pseudoarthrosis of the clavicle
definition: The two portions of the clavicle (corresponding to the two primary ossification centers of the clavicle) are connected by a fibrous bridge that is contiguous with the periosteum, and a synovial membrane develops, resulting in a clavicle with a bipartite appearance radiographically. Congenital pseudarthrosis of the clavicle generally presents as a painless mass or swelling over the clavicle.

label: Straight clavicles
definition: An abnormally straight configuration of the clavicle, a tubular bone which normally is doubly curved .

label: Premature sternal synostosis
definition: Prematurely closed sternal sutures.

label: Absent glenoid fossa
definition: Lack of development of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus.

label: Scapulohumeral synostosis
definition: Bony fusion between the humerus and scapula, leading to an impairment in mobility of the affected shoulder joint.

label: Diaphragmatic paralysis
definition: The presence of a paralyzed diaphragm.

label: Diaphragmatic weakness
definition: A decrease in the strength of the diaphragm.

label: Irregular ossification at anterior rib ends
Abnormal rib ossification
definition: An anomaly of the process of rib bone formation.

label: Irregular chondrocostal junctions
definition: Irregular surface of the normally relatively smooth border between the distal part of the ribs and the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage that connect the ribs to the sternum.

label: Precocious costochondral ossification
definition: Early ossification of the costochondral junction, which is the joint between the ribs and costal cartilage in the front of the rib cage.

label: Midclavicular hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the middle portion of the clavicle.

label: Wide intermamillary distance
definition: A larger than usual distance between the left and right nipple.

label: Decreased number of sternal ossification centers
definition: A less than normal number of sternal ossification centers. The sternum is initially formed from bilateral sternal plates that chondrify and begin to fuse with ribs at 10 weeks gestational age. Ossification starts in the manubrium and upper part of the sternal body at the 6th month, in the middle of the sternal body at the 7th month, in the lower part of the body during the 1st postnatal year and in the xiphoid process between years 5 and 18. The number of ossification centers vary up to six, and it is the ossification centers that are visualized by prenatal ultrasound. This term describes a reduction in the number of ossification centers compared with age-related norms.

label: Abnormal sternal ossification
definition: Any anomaly in the formation of the bony substance of the sternum.

label: Absent in utero rib ossification
definition: Lack of formation and mineralization of the ribs in utero.

label: Anterior rib punctate calcifications
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in point-like foci within the anterior portion of one or more ribs.

label: Costochondral joint sclerosis
definition: Abnormal increase in density of the tissue at the costochondral junctions.

label: Multifocal breast carcinoma
definition: Breast carcinoma that is bilateral or otherwise multifocal.

label: Absent sternal ossification
definition: Lack of formation of mineralized bony tissue of the sternum.

label: Glenoid fossa hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the glenoid fossa, which is the cavity in the lateral part of the scapula which articulates with the head of the humerus.

label: Osteosclerosis of ribs
definition: Osteosclerosis of ribs (increased density related to increased bone mass).

label: Midclavicular aplasia
definition: Developmental defect resulting in congenital absence of the middle portion of the clavicle.

label: Multiple rib fractures
definition: More than one fracture of the ribs. Callus formation around multiple rib fractures can produce a row of multiple rounded expansions (beadlike prominences) giving the appearance of beaded ribs. Note that rachitic rosary would have one bead per rib (a swelling at the costochondral junction), while beaded ribs in the context of multiple rib fractures have multiple beads (fractures) along the same rib.

label: Thin clavicles
definition: Abnormally reduced diameter (cross section) of the clavicles.

label: Costal cartilage calcification
definition: Calcification of the costal cartilages, which are bars of hyaline cartilage found at the anterior ends of the ribs which serve to prolong the ribs forward and contribute to the elasticity of the walls of the thorax.

label: Costochondral pain
definition: Chest wall pain in the area of the costochondral junctions.

label: Thickening of the lateral border of the scapula
Aplastic clavicle
definition: Absence of the clavicles as a developmental defect.

label: Coat hanger sign of ribs
definition: An abnormal morphology of the ribs consisting of shorted, abnormally curved ribs. On posteroanterior chest radiography, the ribs show a curvature resembling that of a coat hanger (clothes hanger).

label: Prolonged QRS complex
definition: Increased time for the complex comprised of the Q wave, R wave, and S wave as measured by the electrocardiogram (EKG).. In adults, normal values are 0.06 - 0.10 sec.

label: Abnormal QRS complex
definition: An anomaly of the complex formed by the Q, R, and S waves, which occur in rapid succession on the electrocardiogram.

label: Granulomatous coronary arteritis
definition: Inflammation of the coronary arteries involving a granulomatous response, i.e., a non-specific inflammatory response involving granulomas, defined as a compact organized collection of mature mononuclear phagocytes including epithelioid and giant cells.

label: Arteritis
definition: Arterial inflammation.

label: Abnormal ventricular filling
definition: An abnormality of filling of a ventricle with blood during diastole.

label: Ventricular preexcitation with multiple accessory pathways
definition: A form of ventricular preexcitation due to the presence of multiple accessory pathways for cardiac conduction.

label: Endocardial fibrosis
definition: The presence of excessive connective tissue in the endocardium.

label: Aortic tortuosity
definition: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of the aorta.

label: Bacterial endocarditis
definition: A bacterial infection of the endocardium, the inner layer of the heart, which usually involves the heart valves.

label: Endocarditis
definition: An inflammation of the endocardium, the inner layer of the heart, which usually involves the heart valves.

label: Myocardial calcification
definition: Calcium deposition in the myocardium.

label: Pulmonic valve myxoma
definition: A benign tumor of connective tissue containing mucous or gelatinous material (myxoma) localized in the pumonic valve.

label: Short chordae tendineae of the tricuspid valve
definition: Abnormally short chordae tendineae of the tricuspid valve.

label: Abnormal tricuspid chordae tendinae morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the chordae tendinae of the tricuspid valve. The chordae tendineae connect the papillary muscles to the tricuspid valve.

label: Myocardial steatosis
definition: Steatosis in the myocardium.

label: Early progressive calcific cardiac valvular disease
Dilatation of the ventricular cavity
definition: A localized outpouching of ventricular cavity that is generally associated with dyskinesia and paradoxical expansion during systole.

label: Premature atrial contractions
definition: A type of cardiac arrhythmia with premature atrial contractions or beats caused by signals originating from ectopic atrial sites.

label: Coronary artery dissection
definition: Acute occurrence of a dissection (tear within the tunica intima and entry of blood into the tunica media) of a coronary artery.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving bones of the thorax
Aplasia/hypoplasia affecting bones of the axial skeleton
definition: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of bones of the axial skeleton.

label: Neoplasm of the large intestine
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the large intestine.

label: Carcinoid tumor
definition: A tumor formed from the endocrine (argentaffin) cells of the mucosal lining of a variety of organs including the stomach and intestine. These cells are from neuroectodermal origin.

label: Neoplasm of the small intestine
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the small intestine.

label: Pancreatic adenocarcinoma
definition: The presence of an adenocarcinoma of the pancreas.

label: T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemias
definition: Acute lymphoblastic leukemia of T-cell origin. It comprises about 15% of childhood cases and 25% of adult cases. It is more common in males than females.

label: Retroperitoneal paraganglioma
definition: A paraganglioma (previously referred to as chemodectoma) located in the retroperitoneal space. Paragangliomas (also known as extra-adrenal pheochromocytomas) are rare tumors that arise from extra-adrenal chromaffin cells. Paragangliomas are characterized by secretions of excessive catecholamines, including epinephrine, norepinephrine and dopamine, which may lead to clinical symptoms, including episodic hypertension, tachycardia and diaphoresis. However, between 40 and 50% of paragangliomas are non-functional.

label: Neoplasm of the endocrine system
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the endocrine system.

label: Follicular thyroid carcinoma
definition: The presence of an follicular adenocarcinoma of the thyroid gland.

label: Papillary renal cell carcinoma type 2
definition: A type of papillary renal cell carcinoma in which the papillae are covered by large eosinophilic cells with pleomorphic nuclei, prominent nucleoli, and nuclear pseudostratification.

label: Papillary renal cell carcinoma
definition: The presence of renal cell carcinoma in the renal papilla.

label: Acute megakaryocytic leukemia
definition: A rare subtype of acute myeloid leukemia evolving from primitive megakaryoblasts.

label: Renal cortical adenoma
definition: The presence of an adenoma in the cortex of the kidney.

label: Extraadrenal pheochromocytoma
definition: Pheochromocytoma not originating from the adrenal medulla but from another source such as from chromaffin cells in or about sympathetic ganglia.

label: Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin
definition: Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin is a malignant tumor of squamous epithelium.

label: Transitional cell carcinoma of the bladder
definition: The presence of a carcinoma of the urinary bladder with origin in a transitional epithelial cell.

label: Adrenocortical carcinoma
definition: A malignant neoplasm of the adrenal cortex that may produce hormones such as cortisol, aldosterone, estrogen, or testosterone.

label: Neoplasm of the adrenal cortex
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the adrenal cortex.

label: Adrenal pheochromocytoma
definition: Pheochromocytoma originating from the adrenal medulla.

label: Neoplasm of the adrenal medulla
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the adrenal medulla.

label: Paraspinal neurofibroma
definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized adjacent to the spine.

label: Neurofibroma by anatomical location
definition: Neurofibroma categorized according to the anatomical site of origin.

label: Cutaneous leiomyosarcoma
definition: The presence of leiomyosarcoma of the skin.

label: Soft tissue neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) that arises from the soft tissue. The most common types are lipomatous (fatty), vascular, smooth muscle, fibrous, and fibrohistiocytic neoplasms.

label: Malignant genitourinary tract tumor
definition: The presence of a malignant neoplasm of the genital system.

label: Neoplasm of the genitourinary tract
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genitourinary system.

label: Renal pelvic carcinoma
definition: The presence of a carcinoma in the renal pelvis.

label: Chondrosarcoma
definition: A slowly growing malignant neoplasm derived from cartilage cells.

label: Pituitary prolactin cell adenoma
definition: A type of pituitary adenoma originating in prolactin secreting cells. This kind of adenoma is characterized by overproduction of prolactin, and may cause loss of menstrual periods and breast milk production in women.

label: Clear cell renal cell carcinoma
definition: A subtype of renal cell carcinoma thought to originate from mature renal tubular cells in the proximal tubule of the nehpron.

label: Duodenal adenocarcinoma
definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the duodenum.

label: Adenocarcinoma of the small intestine
definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the small intestine.

label: Renal angiomyolipoma
definition: A benign renal neoplasm composed of fat, vascular, and smooth muscle elements.

label: Renal hamartoma
definition: A disordered proliferation of mature tissues that are native to the kidneys.

label: Ovarian papillary adenocarcinoma
definition: The presence of a papillary adenocarcinoma of the ovary.

label: Multiple myeloma
definition: A malignant plasma cell tumor growing within soft tissue or within the skeleton.

label: Benign genitourinary tract neoplasm
definition: A non-malignant neoplasm of the genitourinary system.

label: Parathyroid carcinoma
definition: A malignancy of the parathyroid glands. Parathyroid carcinoma usually secretes parathyroid hormone, leading to hyperparathyroidism.

label: Hurthle cell thyroid adenoma
definition: A kind of thyroid adenoma characterized by the presence of oxyphil cells.

label: Paranasal sinus hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the paranasal sinuses.

label: Limb-girdle muscular dystrophy
definition: Muscular dystrophy affecting the muscles of the limb girdle (the hips and shoulders).

label: Loss of ability to walk in first decade
Vivid hallucination
definition: Perceptual experiences that are vivid, intense, and sensory in nature occur in the absence of corresponding stimuli from the external environment.

label: Cerebral hypomyelination
definition: Reduced amount of myelin in the nervous system resulting from defective myelinogenesis in the white matter of the central nervous system.

label: White mater abnormalities in the posterior periventricular region
Focal hemiclonic seizure
definition: A type of focal clonic seizure characterized by sustained rhythmic jerking rapidly involves one side of the body at seizure onset.

label: 4-layered lissencephaly
definition: A form of lissencephaly in which the cortex is thickened and has four more or less disorganized layers rather than six normal layers resulting from incomplete neuronal migration during brain development. At neuropathological examination, a 4-layered cortex consists of an upper molecular layer, a second thin cellular layer containing pyramidal neurons usually observed in layer V, a third pale poorly cellular layer and a fourth thick deep layer made up of neurons which had failed to migrate. Radiologocally would manifest as agyria or pachygyria with cortical thickness greater than 10 mm.

label: Frontal polymicrogyria
definition: A type of polymicrogyria with a gradient of severity (anterior more severe than posterior) extending from frontal poles posteriorly to precentral gyrus and inferiorly to frontal operculum.

label: Abnormal cranial nerve physiology
definition: A functional abnormality affecting one or more of the cranial nerves, which emerge directly from the brain stem.

label: Pallor of dorsal columns of the spinal cord
definition: An abnormally pale appearance of the dorsal portion of the gray substance of the spinal cord. This finding can be observed by histological examination.

label: Abnormality of the dorsal column of the spinal cord
definition: An abnormality of the dorsal columns, i.e., of the dorsal portion of the gray substance of the spinal cord. The dorsal column consists of the fasciculus gracilis and fasciculus cuneatus and itself is part of the dorsal funiculus.

label: Severe muscular hypotonia
definition: A severe degree of muscular hypotonia characterized by markedly reduced muscle tone.

label: Developmental stagnation at onset of seizures
definition: A cessation of the development of a child in the areas of motor skills, speech and language, cognitive skills, and social and/or emotional skills, following the onset of epilepsy.

label: Developmental stagnation
definition: A cessation of the development of a child in the areas of motor skills, speech and language, cognitive skills, and social and/or emotional skills.

label: Congenital Horner syndrome
definition: A type of Horner syndrome with congenital onset.

label: Absent patellar reflexes
definition: Absence of the knee jerk reflex, which can normally be elicited by tapping the patellar tendon with a reflex hammer just below the patella.

label: Hypodysplasia of the corpus callosum
definition: Developmental defect characterized by a small and malformed corpus callosum.

label: Hypoplasia of the ventral pons
definition: Underdevelopment of the ventral portion of the pons.

label: Hypoplasia of the pons
definition: Underdevelopment of the pons.

label: Symmetric spinal nerve root neurofibromas
definition: Multiple neurofibromas of the spinal nerve roots with a symmetric distribution.

label: Spinal neurofibroma
definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the spine.

label: Episodic generalized hypotonia
definition: The occurrence of repeated episodes of generalized muscular hypotonia.

label: Cerebellar vermis atrophy
definition: Wasting (atrophy) of the vermis of cerebellum.

label: Impaired distal proprioception
definition: A loss or impairment of the sensation of the relative position of parts of the body and joint position occurring at distal joints.

label: Severe expressive language delay
definition: A severe delay in the acquisition of the ability to use language to communicate needs, wishes, or thoughts.

label: Sensorimotor polyneuropathy affecting arms more than legs
Multiple central nervous system lipomas
definition: The presence of multiple lipomas located in the central nervous system.

label: Lobar holoprosencephaly
definition: A type of holoprosencephaly in which most of the right and left cerebral hemispheres and lateral ventricles are separated but the most rostral aspect of the telencephalon, the frontal lobes, are fused, especially ventrally.

label: Cerebral hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the cerebrum.

label: Symmetrical progressive peripheral demyelination
definition: A symmetric and progressive loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system.

label: Symmetric peripheral demyelination
definition: A symmetric loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system.

label: Pontocerebellar atrophy
definition: Atrophy affecting the pons and the cerebellum.

label: Abnormal pons morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the pons.

label: Cerebellar hemangioblastoma
definition: A hemangioblastoma of the cerebellum.

label: Hemangioblastoma
definition: A hemangioblastoma is a benign vascular neoplasm that arises almost exclusively in the central nervous system. Hemangioblastomas consist of a tightly packed cluster of small blood vessels forming a mass of up to 1 or 2 cm in diameter.

label: Diffuse peripheral demyelination
definition: A diffuse loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system.

label: Impaired distal vibration sensation
definition: A decrease in the ability to perceive vibration in the distal portions of the limbs.

label: Intellectual disability, progressive
definition: The term progressive intellectual disability should be used if intelligence decreases/deteriorates over time.

label: Intellectual disability, borderline
definition: Borderline intellectual disability is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 70-85.

label: Frontotemporal cerebral atrophy
definition: Atrophy (wasting, decrease in size of cells or tissue) affecting the frontotemporal cerebrum.

label: Hypnopompic hallucination
definition: Brief hallucinations that occur as you wake up in the morning, in a state that falls somewhere between dreaming and being fully awake.

label: Abnormal hypnopompia
definition: Abnormal transition of consciousness from sleeping to wakefulness.

label: Abducens palsy
definition: Malfunction of the abducens nerve as manifested by impairment of the ability of the affected eye to be moved outward. Patients who develop abducens nerve palsy often present with binocular horizontal diplopia, which is a double vision when looking at objects side by side. There will be a notable weakness of the ipsilateral lateral rectus muscle leading to a deficit in of eye abduction on the affected side. Some patients may present with a constant head turning movement to maintain binocular fusion and to lessen the degree of diplopia.

label: Congenital intracerebral calcification
definition: The presence of calcium deposition within brain structures that is present already at the time of birth.

label: Frontal cortical atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the frontal cortex.

label: Intraaxonal accumulation of curvilinear autofluorescent lipopigment storage material
definition: Curvilinear intracellular accumulation of autofluorescent lipopigment storage material within axons.

label: Axial muscle stiffness
definition: Stiffness (a condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm) of the axial musculature.

label: Abnormal axial muscle morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the muscles of the trunk and head.

label: Unilateral polymicrogyria
definition: Excessive number of small gyri (convolutions) on the surface of one side of the brain.

label: Hypoglycemic encephalopathy
definition: Brain damage related to a lowering of blood glucose below a critical level (around 30 mg/dl), which may lead to confusion, lethargy and delirium followed by seizures and coma. Prolonged hypoglycemia may lead to irreversible brain damage.

label: Frontoparietal cortical dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the cortex of frontal lobe and the cortex of parietal lobe.

label: Pericallosal lipoma
definition: Pericallosal lipomas are congenital soft masses of adipose cells encapsulated by a thin layer of fibrous tissue, appearing adjacent to the corpus callosum of the brain.

label: Transient psychotic episodes
definition: Relatively short-lived periods of psychosis are characterized by the sudden onset of severe disturbances in perception, thinking, and behavior. These episodes typically last for a brief duration, generally ranging from a few days to a few weeks, and are often triggered by a significant stressor or traumatic event.

label: Congenital nystagmus
definition: Nystagmus dating from or present at birth.

label: Impaired distal tactile sensation
definition: A reduced sense of touch (tactile sensation) on the skin of the distal limbs. This is usually tested with a wisp of cotton or a fine camel's hair brush, by asking patients to say 'now' each time they feel the stimulus.

label: Impaired tactile sensation
definition: A reduced sense of touch (tactile sensation). This is usually tested with a wisp of cotton or a fine camel's hair brush, by asking patients to say 'now' each time they feel the stimulus.

label: Impaired vibration sensation at ankles
definition: A decrease in the ability to perceive vibration at the ankles. Clinically, this is usually tested with a tuning fork which vibrates at 128 Hz and is applied to the malleoli of the ankles.

label: Abolished vibration sense
definition: A complete loss of the ability to perceive vibration.

label: Recurrent meningitis
definition: An increased susceptibility to meningitis as manifested by a medical history of recurrent episodes of meningitis.

label: Olivopontocerebellar hypoplasia
definition: Hypoplasia of the cerebellum, pontine nuclei, and inferior olivary nucleus.

label: Abnormal lateral ventricle morphology
definition: A morphological anomaly of the lateral ventricle.

label: Proximal spinal muscular atrophy
definition: Proximal spinal muscular atrophy, i.e., muscular weakness and atrophy related to loss of the motor neurons of the spinal cord and brainstem.

label: Spinal muscular atrophy
definition: Muscular weakness and atrophy related to loss of the motor neurons of the spinal cord and brainstem.

label: Choroid plexus calcification
definition: The presence of calcium deposition in the choroid plexus.

label: Gait instability, worse in the dark
Periventricular leukomalacia
definition: Periventricular leukomalacia is characterized by diffuse injury of deep cerebral white matter, accompanied in its most severe form by focal necrosis. The neuropathologic hallmarks of PVL are microglial activation and focal and diffuse periventricular depletion of premyelinating oligodendroglia.

label: Necrotizing encephalopathy
definition: A type of encephalopathy (brain disease, damage, or malfunction accompanied by an altered mental state) that is characterized by evidence of necrosis of brain tissue.

label: Deficit in grammar
definition: Deficit in grammar, including syntax and morphology.

label: Sleep-wake cycle disturbance
definition: Any abnormality of an individual's circadian rhythm that affects the timing of sleeping and being awake is referred to as a sleep-wake disorder.

label: Progressive leukoencephalopathy
definition: Leukoencephalopathy that gets more severe with time.

label: Alobar holoprosencephaly
definition: A type of holoprosencephaly characterized by the presence of a single ventricle and no separation of the cerebral hemisphere. The single midline ventricle is often greatly enlarged.

label: Dysplastic corpus callosum
definition: Dysplasia and dysgenesis of the corpus callosum are nonspecific descriptions that imply defective development of the corpus callosum. The term dysplasia is applied when the morphology of the corpus callosum is altered as a congenital trait. For instance, the corpus callosum may be hump-shaped, kinked, or a striped corpus callosum that lacks an anatomically distinct genu and splenium.

label: Myelin-dependent gliosis
definition: A type of gliosis that occurs in the vicinity of injured neurons.

label: Anterior encephalocele
definition: A type of congenital malformation in which brain tissue protrudes through a defect in the anterior (front) part of the skull.

label: Basal ganglia gliosis
definition: Focal proliferation of glial cells in the basal ganglia.

label: Loss of Purkinje cells in the cerebellar vermis
Motor axonal neuropathy
definition: Progressive impairment of function of motor axons with muscle weakness, atrophy, and cramps. The deficits are length-dependent, meaning that muscles innervated by the longest nerves are affected first, so that for instance the arms are affected at a later age than the onset of deficits involving the lower leg.

label: Cavitation of the basal ganglia
definition: The formation of small cavities in the tissue of the basal ganglia.

label: Poor fine motor coordination
definition: An abnormality of the ability (skills) to perform a precise movement of small muscles with the intent to perform a specific act. Fine motor skills are required to mediate movements of the wrists, hands, fingers, feet, and toes.

label: Fourth cranial nerve palsy
definition: Paralysis of the fourth cranial (trochlear) nerve manifested as weakness of the superior oblique muscle which causes vertical diplopia that is maximal when the affected eye is adducted and directed inferiorly.

label: Poor gross motor coordination
definition: An abnormality of the ability (skills) to perform a precise movement of large muscles with the intent to perform a specific act. Gross motor skills are required to mediate movements of the arms, legs, and other large body parts.

label: Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder
definition: Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) manifests at age 2-3 years or by first grade at the latest. The main symptoms are distractibility, impulsivity, hyperactivity, and often trouble organizing tasks and projects, difficulty going to sleep, and social problems from being aggressive, loud, or impatient.

label: Pain insensitivity
definition: Inability to perceive painful stimuli.

label: Impaired pain sensation
definition: Reduced ability to perceive painful stimuli.

label: Antenatal intracerebral hemorrhage
definition: Cerebral hemorrhage that occurs before birth.

label: Pseudobulbar paralysis
definition: Bilateral impairment of the function of the cranial nerves 9-12, which control musculature involved in eating, swallowing, and speech. Pseudobulbar paralysis is characterized clinically by dysarthria, dysphonia, and dysphagia with bifacial paralysis, and may be accompanied by Pseudobulbar behavioral symptoms such as enforced crying and laughing.

label: Poorly formed metencephalon
definition: A morphological abnormality of the metencephalon.

label: Cerebral berry aneurysm
definition: A small, sac-like aneurysm (outpouching) of a cerebral blood vessel.

label: Cerebellar dysplasia
definition: Cerebellar dysplasia (abnormal growth or development) is defined by abnormal cerebellar foliation, white matter arborization, and gray-white matter junction. Cerebellar dysplasia is a neuroimaging finding that describes abnormalities of both the cerebellar cortex and white matter and is associated with variable neurodevelopmental outcome. Dysplasia may globally involve the cerebellum or affect only one cerebellar hemisphere. In addition, cerebellar dysplasia may be associated with cortical/subcortical cysts.

label: Symmetric lesions of the basal ganglia
Chronic lymphocytic meningitis
definition: Meningitis that persists for more than 4 weeks, and lymphocytes are present in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Atrophy of the dentate nucleus
definition: Partial or complete wasting (loss) of dentate nucleus.

label: Large basal ganglia
definition: Increased size of the basal ganglia.

label: Proximal hyperreflexia
definition: Hyperactive stretch reflexes of muscles that move proximal joints (elbow, knee).

label: Generalized cerebral atrophy/hypoplasia
definition: Generalized atrophy or hypoplasia of the cerebrum.

label: Aplasia of the inferior half of the cerebellar vermis
Progressive language deterioration
definition: Progressive loss of previously present language abilities.

label: Disorganization of the anterior cerebellar vermis
Proximal limb muscle stiffness
definition: Stiffness of the limbs (a condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm) occurring in the proximal limb muscle.

label: Distal peripheral sensory neuropathy
definition: Peripheral sensory neuropathy affecting primarily distal sensation.

label: Inferior cerebellar vermis hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the inferior portion of the vermis of cerebellum.

label: Thick corpus callosum
definition: Increased vertical dimension of the corpus callosum. This feature can be visualized by sagittal sections on magnetic resonance tomography imaging of the brain.

label: Extrapyramidal muscular rigidity
definition: Muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement).

label: Decreased amplitude of sensory action potentials
definition: A reduction in the amplitude of sensory nerve action potential. This feature is measured by nerve conduction studies.

label: Abnormal peripheral action potential amplitude
definition: An anomaly in the magnitude of the action potential along a peripheral nerve, that is, of the rapid rise and fall of the electrical membrane potential of the nerve.

label: Dilated third ventricle
definition: An increase in size of the third ventricle.

label: Abnormal third ventricle morphology
definition: An abnormality of the third ventricle.

label: Facial-lingual fasciculations
definition: Fasciculations affecting the tongue muscle and the musculature of the face.

label: Paroxysmal choreoathetosis
definition: Episodes of choreoathetosis that can occur following triggers such as quick voluntary movements.

label: Chiari type I malformation
definition: Arnold-Chiari type I malformation refers to a relatively mild degree of herniation of the posteroinferior region of the cerebellum (the cerebellar tonsils) into the cervical canal with little or no displacement of the fourth ventricle. It is characterized by one or both pointed (not rounded) cerebellar tonsils that project 5 mm below the foramen magnum, measured by a line drawn from the basion to the opisthion (McRae Line)

label: Hypointensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
definition: A darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the cerebral white matter.

label: Infantile encephalopathy
definition: Encephalopathy with onset in the infantile period.

label: Segmental peripheral demyelination
definition: A loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers from segments of the peripheral nervous system.

label: Demyelinating peripheral neuropathy
definition: Demyelinating neuropathy is characterized by slow nerve conduction velocities with reduced amplitudes of sensory/motor nerve conduction and prolonged distal latencies.

label: Temporal cortical atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the temporal cortex.

label: Naso-orbital encephalocele
definition: A type of encephalocele that occurs along the medial orbit wall at the level of the frontal process of the maxilla and the ethmoid-lacrimal bone junction.

label: Frontoethmoidal encephalocele
definition: A type of anterior encephalocele in which there is a protrusion of the contents of the skull through a breach at the point where the frontal and ethmoidal bones meet. Frontoethmoidal encephalocele can be divided further into three distinct categories: nasofrontal, nasoethmoidal, and nasoorbital.

label: Subcortical dementia
definition: A particular type of dementia characterized by a pattern of mental defects consisting prominently of forgetfulness, slowness of thought processes, and personality or mood change.

label: Proximal amyotrophy
definition: Amyotrophy (muscular atrophy) affecting the proximal musculature.

label: Acute demyelinating polyneuropathy
definition: Acute progressive areflexic weakness and mild sensory changes resulting from myelin breakdown and axonal degeneration.

label: Pallidal degeneration
definition: Neurodegeneration involving the globus pallidus,a part of the basal ganglia that is involved in the regulation of voluntary movement.

label: Subcortical cerebral atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the cerebral subcortical white and gray matter, termed subcortical atrophy, reflects loss of nerve cells in the basal ganglia or fibers in the deep white matter.

label: Distal upper limb amyotrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy of distal arm muscles.

label: Upper limb amyotrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy involving the muscles of the upper limbs.

label: Asymmetric limb muscle stiffness
definition: Stiffness of the limbs (a condition in which muscles cannot be moved quickly without accompanying pain or spasm) occurring in an asymmetric pattern.

label: Progressive extrapyramidal muscular rigidity
definition: A progressive degree of muscular rigidity (continuous contraction of muscles with constant resistance to passive movement).

label: Fluctuations in consciousness
definition: Changes in one's level of awareness and responsiveness to their environment.

label: Diffuse demyelination of the cerebral white matter
definition: A diffuse loss of myelin from nerve fibers in the central nervous system.

label: Periventricular heterotopia
definition: A form of gray matter heterotopia were the mislocalized gray matter is typically located periventricularly, also sometimes called subependymal heterotopia. Periventricular means beside the ventricles. This is by far the most common location for heterotopia. Subependymal heterotopia present in a wide array of variations. There can be a small single node or a large number of nodes, can exist on either or both sides of the brain at any point along the higher ventricle margins, can be small or large, single or multiple, and can form a small node or a large wavy or curved mass.

label: Paroxysmal dyskinesia
definition: Episodic bouts of involuntary movements with dystonic, choreic, ballistic movements, or a combination thereof. There is no loss of consciousness during the attacks.

label: Absent smooth pursuit
definition: A complete lack of the ability to track objects with the ocular smooth pursuit system, a class of rather slow eye movements that minimizes retinal target motion.

label: Peripheral hypomyelination
definition: Reduced amount of myelin in the nervous system resulting from defective myelinogenesis in the peripheral nervous system.

label: Focal T2 hyperintense basal ganglia lesion
definition: A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the basal ganglia.

label: Abnormal basal ganglia MRI signal intensity
definition: A deviation from normal signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia.

label: Loss of consciousness
definition: Loss of alertness and orientation to place and time.

label: Focal lissencephaly
definition: A congenital absence of the convolutions of the cerebral cortex and a poorly formed sylvian fissure that affects a particular part of the cortex.

label: Congenital facial diplegia
definition: Facial diplegia (that is, bilateral facial palsy) with congenital onset.

label: Neuronal loss in the cerebral cortex
Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure on awakening
definition: Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure of either generalized or focal onset occurring on or soon after wakening (typically within 90 minutes of waking, regardless of the time of day).

label: Episodic hypersomnia
definition: Recurrent episodes of severe hypersomnia are accompanied by cognitive and behavioral disturbances, including confusion, derealization, apathy, compulsive eating, and hypersexuality.

label: Hypersomnia
definition: Excessive sleepiness or feeling of sleepiness, or difficulty staying awake despite having had adequate sleep, which persists over several days.

label: Cerebral artery atherosclerosis
definition: The formation of the formation of fibrofatty lesions in the wall of an artery located in the brain.

label: Hemimegalencephaly
definition: Enlargement of all or parts of one cerebral hemisphere.

label: Photosensitive tonic-clonic seizure
definition: Generalized-onset tonic-clonic seizures that are provoked by flashing or flickering light.

label: Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure with generalized onset
definition: A bilateral tonic-clonic seizure with generalized onset is a type of bilateral tonic-clonic seizure characterized by generalized onset; these seizures rapidly engage networks in both hemispheres at the start of the seizure.

label: Irregular myelin loops
definition: Presence of irregular redundant loops of focally folded myelin in a peripheral nerve.

label: Facial paralysis
definition: Complete loss of ability to move facial muscles innervated by the facial nerve (i.e., the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Weakness of facial musculature
definition: Reduced strength of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Lower limb amyotrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy affecting the lower limb.

label: Periodic hyperkalemic paralysis
definition: Episodes of muscle weakness associated with elevated levels of potassium in the blood.

label: Demyelinating motor neuropathy
definition: Demyelination of peripheral motor nerves.

label: Intracerebral periventricular calcifications
definition: The presence of calcium deposition in the cerebral white matter surrounding the cerebral ventricles.

label: Decreased distal sensory nerve action potential
definition: A reduction in the amplitude of sensory nerve action potential in distal nerve segments. This feature is measured by nerve conduction studies.

label: Spinocerebellar tract disease in lower limbs
Clusters of axonal regeneration
definition: Groups of small caliber axons in peripheral nerve biospies indicative of axonal regeneration.

label: Progressive gait ataxia
definition: A type of gait ataxia displaying progression of clinical severity.

label: Decreased number of small peripheral myelinated nerve fibers
Recurrent external ophthalmoplegia
definition: Alternating and recurrent weakness of the external ocular muscles.

label: Severe demyelination of the white matter
definition: A severe loss of myelin from nerve fibers in the central nervous system.

label: Type II lissencephaly
definition: A form of lissencephaly characterized by an uneven cortical surface with a so called 'cobblestone' appearace. There are no distinguishable cortical layers.

label: Spinocerebellar atrophy
definition: Atrophy affecting the cerebellum and the spinocerebellar tracts of the spinal cord.

label: Absent mesencephalon
definition: Agenesis of the midbrain.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the midbrain
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the midbrain (mesencephalon).

label: Cerebral dysmyelination
definition: Defective structure and function of myelin sheaths of the white matter of the brain.

label: Chronic axonal neuropathy
definition: An abnormality characterized by chronic impairment of the normal functioning of the axons.

label: Atypical absence seizure
definition: An atypical absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by interruption of ongoing activities and reduced responsiveness. In comparison to a typical absence seizure, changes in tone may be more pronounced, onset and/or cessation may be less abrupt, and the duration of the ictus and post-ictal recovery may be longer. Although not always available, an EEG often demonstrates slow (<3 Hz), irregular, generalized spike-wave activity.

label: Recurrent bacterial meningitis
definition: An increased susceptibility to bacterial meningitis as manifested by a medical history of recurrent episodes of bacterial meningitis.

label: Paucity of anterior horn motor neurons
Facial palsy secondary to cranial hyperostosis
definition: Paralysis of the facial nerves on the basis of overgrowth of the cranial bones causing impingement upon the seventh cranial nerve.

label: Horizontal jerk nystagmus
definition: Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements, in which the movement in one direction is faster than in the other.

label: Limb fasciculations
definition: Fasciculations affecting the musculature of the arms and legs.

label: Oromotor apraxia
definition: Oral-motor apraxia is the inability to volitionally sequence oral movements of the speech structure for nonspeech tasks in the absence of neuromuscular deficits such as paralysis or muscle weakness. Oral-motor apraxia is diagnosed when, despite intact sensory motor function an individual is unable to use these effector systems under voluntary control.

label: Bipolar affective disorder
definition: Bipolar disorder is an illness of mood characterized by alternating episodes of elevated and depressed moods, which are interspersed with euthymic periods.

label: Deep white matter hypodensities
definition: Multiple areas of darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the deep cerebral white matter.

label: Generalized dystonia
definition: A type of dystonia that affects all or most of the body.

label: Focal hemifacial clonic seizure
definition: Focal seizure characterized at onset by clonic movements affecting half of the face.

label: Hypoplasia of the frontal lobes
definition: Underdevelopment of the frontal lobe of the cerebrum.

label: Bilateral tonic-clonic seizure with focal onset
definition: A bilateral tonic-clonic seizure with focal onset is a focal-onset seizure which progresses into a bilateral tonic-clonic phase.

label: Recurrent encephalopathy
definition: Recurrent episodes of brain dysfunction that may be triggered by factors such as metabolic disturbances or infections.

label: Hypermetric saccades
definition: A saccade that overshoots the target with the dynamic saccade.

label: Lower limb muscle weakness
definition: Weakness of the muscles of the legs.

label: Diffuse swelling of cerebral white matter
Abnormal morphology of the limbic system
definition: Any structural anomaly of the limbic system, a set of midline structures surrounding the brainstem of the mammalian brain, originally described anatomically, e.g., hippocampal formation, amygdala, hypothalamus, cingulate cortex. Although the original designation was anatomical, the limbic system has come to be associated with the system in the brain subserving emotional functions. As such, it is very poorly defined and doesn't correspond closely to the anatomical meaning any longer. [BirnLex].

label: Upper limb hyperreflexia
definition: Increased intensity of the a reflex in the arm.

label: Upper limb postural tremor
definition: A type of tremors that is triggered by holding an arm in a fixed position.

label: Thin corpus callosum
definition: An abnormally thin corpus callous, due to atrophy, hypoplasia or agenesis. This term is intended to be used in situations where it is not known if thinning of the corpus callosum (for instance, as visualized by magnetic resonance tomography) is due to abnormal development (e.g. a leukodystrophy) or atrophy following normal development (e.g. neurodegeneration).

label: Corpus callosum atrophy
definition: The presence of atrophy (wasting) of the corpus callosum.

label: Cerebral white matter atrophy
definition: The presence of atrophy (wasting) of the cerebral white matter.

label: Abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
definition: An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Hypoplastic sweat glands
definition: Underdevelopment of the sweat glands.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the sweat glands
definition: Absence or developmental hypoplasia of the sweat glands.

label: Postnatal-onset ichthyosiform erythroderma
definition: A type of ichthyosiform erythroderma with postnatal onset.

label: Ichthyosis
definition: An abnormality of the skin characterized the presence of excessive amounts of dry surface scales on the skin resulting from an abnormality of keratinization.

label: Early cutaneous photosensitivity
definition: Photosensitivity of the skin occurring early in life.

label: Axillary apocrine gland hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the apocrine sweat glands in the region of the axilla.

label: Macular atrophy
definition: Well-demarcated area(s) of partial or complete depigmentation in the macula, reflecting atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium with associated retinal photoreceptor loss.

label: Areas of hypopigmentation and hyperpigmentation that do not follow Blaschko lines
Mixed hypo- and hyperpigmentation of the skin
Nonepidermolytic palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles charactersized by hyperkeratosis of the stratum corneum with no evidence of epidermolysis characteristic of epidermolytic hyperkeratosis.

label: Excessive skin wrinkling on dorsum of hands and fingers
Tegumentary leishmaniasis susceptibility
definition: Increased susceptibility to infection by the protozan parasite of the genus Leishmania.

label: Palmoplantar hyperhidrosis
definition: An abnormally increased perspiration on palms and soles.

label: Nevus flammeus of the forehead
definition: Naevus flammeus localized in the skin of the forehead.

label: Neonatal wrinkled skin of hands and feet
Discoid lupus rash
definition: Cutaneous lesion that develops as a dry, scaly, red patch that evolves to an indurated and hyperpigmented plaque with adherent scale. Scarring may result in central white patches (loss of pigmentation) and skin atrophy.

label: Spontaneous hematomas
definition: Spontaneous development of hematomas (hematoma) or bruises without significant trauma.

label: Telangiectases of the cheeks
definition: Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located near the surface of the skin of the cheeks.

label: Telangiectasia of the oral mucosa
definition: Telangiectasia (that is, the presence of small dilated superficial blood vessels) of the oral mucosa.

label: Few cafe-au-lait spots
definition: The presence of two to five cafe-au-lait macules.

label: Generalized edema
definition: Generalized abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body.

label: Congenital ichthyosiform erythroderma
definition: An ichthyosiform abnormality of the skin with congenital onset.

label: Papule
definition: A circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid, varying in size from a pinhead to less than 10mm in diameter at the widest point.

label: Plaque-like facial hemangioma
definition: Hemangioma is a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells. This term refers to facial hemangiomas that have a plaque-like morphology.

label: Multiple cutaneous leiomyomas
definition: The presence of multiple leiomyomas of the skin.

label: Mottled pigmentation of the trunk and proximal extremities
Partial albinism
definition: Absence of melanin pigment in various areas, which is found at birth and is permanent. The lesions are known as leucoderma and are often found on the face, trunk, or limbs.

label: Palmoplantar blistering
definition: A type of blistering that affects the skin of the palms of the hands and the soles of the feet.

label: Blistering by anatomical location
definition: Blistering (presence of multiple fluid filled blisters) categorized according to the body site where they occur.

label: Diffuse palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Diffuse abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles.

label: Hypopigmented macule
definition: A white or lighter patch of skin that may appear anywhere on the body and are caused by decreased skin pigmentation.

label: Increased groin pigmentation with raindrop depigmentation
Ipsilateral lack of facial sweating
definition: Inability to sweat on the same side of the face that is affected by ptosis and miosis. This is a feature of Horner syndrome.

label: Flexural lichenification
definition: Lichenification affecting primarily flexural areas of the skin.

label: Lichenification
definition: Thickening and hardening of the epidermis seen with exaggeration of normal skin lines.

label: Prominent veins on trunk
definition: Prominent thoracic and abdominal veins.

label: Autoamputation of digits
definition: The spontaneous detachment of a digit (finger or toe) from the body due to long standing pathology.

label: Bitot spots of the conjunctiva
definition: Keratinization of the bulbar conjunctiva near the limbus (corneoscleral junction), resulting in a raised spot.

label: Sparse facial hair
definition: Reduced number or density of facial hair.

label: Honeycomb palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles with an honeycomb pattern.

label: Perifollicular hyperkeratosis
definition: Increased amount of keratin (visible as white scales) surrounding hair follicles.

label: Abnormal perifollicular morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly in the areas surrounding the hair follicles.

label: Palmoplantar cutis gyrata
definition: Cutis gyrata of palms and soles.

label: Periarticular subcutaneous nodules
definition: Subcutaneous nodules that are located in the vicinity of joints.

label: Axillary and groin hyperpigmentation and hypopigmentation
Congenital bullous ichthyosiform erythroderma
definition: An ichthyosiform abnormality of the skin that presents at birth or shortly thereafter with generalized erythema, blistering, erosions, and peeling. In the subsequent months, erythema and blistering improves but patients go on to develop hyperkeratotic scaling that is especially prominent along the joint flexures, neck, hands and feet.

label: Congenital nonbullous ichthyosiform erythroderma
definition: The term collodion baby applies to newborns who appear to have an extra layer of skin (known as a collodion membrane) that has a collodion-like quality. It is a descriptive term, not a specific diagnosis or disorder (as such, it is a syndrome). Affected babies are born in a collodion membrane, a shiny waxy outer layer to the skin. This is shed 10-14 days after birth, revealing the main symptom of the disease, extensive scaling of the skin caused by hyperkeratosis. With increasing age, the scaling tends to be concentrated around joints in areas such as the groin, the armpits, the inside of the elbow and the neck. The scales often tile the skin and may resemble fish scales.

label: Decreased sweating due to autonomic dysfunction
Absence of subcutaneous fat
definition: Lack of subcutaneous adipose tissue.

label: Diffuse telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) with a diffuse localization.

label: Linear arrays of macular hyperkeratoses in flexural areas
Discrete 2 to 5-mm hyper- and hypopigmented macules
Focal friction-related palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Hyperkeratosis affecting the palm of the hand and the sole of the foot in areas exposed to friction.

label: Decreased number of sweat glands
definition: The presence of fewer than normal sweat glands.

label: Streaks of hyperkeratosis along each finger onto the palm
Follicular hyperkeratosis
definition: A skin condition characterized by excessive development of keratin in hair follicles, resulting in rough, cone-shaped, elevated papules resulting from closure of hair follicles with a white plug of sebum.

label: Congenital absence of skin of limbs
Punctate palmar hyperkeratosis
definition: Tiny bumps of thickened skin (hyperkeratosis) on the palms of the hands.

label: Edema of the dorsum of hands
definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin on the back of the hands.

label: Redundant skin on fingers
definition: Loose and sagging skin of the fingers.

label: Palmoplantar cutis laxa
definition: Loose, wrinkled skin of hands and feet.

label: Yellow subcutaneous tissue covered by thin, scaly skin
Congenital posterior occipital alopecia
definition: Loss of hair in the occipital region of the scalp with congenital onset.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita of midline scalp vertex
Severe photosensitivity
definition: A severe degree of photosensitivity of the skin.

label: Frontal cutaneous lipoma
definition: Presence of a cutaneous lipoma on the forehead.

label: Lipoma
definition: Benign neoplasia derived from lipoblasts or lipocytes of white or brown fat. May be angiomatous or hibernomatous.

label: Absent pigmentation of the ventral chest
definition: Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the anterior chest.

label: Absent pigmentation of chest
definition: Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the chest.

label: Piebald skin depigmentation
definition: Congenital large depigmented (white) macule of irergular rhomboid shape. Piebald skin depigmentation generally presents with multiple such macules in the affected individual. There may be smaller (5-15mm), discrete, skin-colored and hyperpigmented macules interspersed within the depigmented macules.

label: Congenital palmoplantar hyperkeratosis
definition: Abnormal thickening of the skin on the palms and soles that is present at birth.

label: Desquamation of skin soon after birth
Abnormal fetal skin morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the skin of the fetus or newborn. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Confetti hypopigmentation pattern of lower leg skin
Multiple cafe-au-lait spots
definition: The presence of six or more cafe-au-lait spots.

label: Generalized seborrheic dermatitis
definition: Seborrheic dermatitis that is not localized to any one particular region.

label: Hyperkeratosis lenticularis perstans
definition: Hyperkeratosis lenticularis perstans (HLP), also known as Flegel disease, is a keratinization abnormality characterized by small, asymptomatic erythematous papules that leave characteristic punctate bleeding when they become detached. The lesions generally occur symmetrically along the top of the foot and on the legs, appearing more rarely on the arms, forearms, palms, and soles, and even on the oral mucosa.

label: Late onset atopic dermatitis
definition: A form of atopic dermatitis with onset in adulthood characterized by atopic red face, chronic lichenified eczema on the trunk, subacute or psoriasiform dermatitis.

label: Palmar neurofibroma
definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the palm of the hand.

label: Reticular hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased pigmentation of the skin with a netlike (reticular) pattern.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita on trunk or limbs
definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the trunk or the limbs.

label: Aplasia cutis congenita over posterior parietal area
Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the eccrine sweat glands
definition: Absence or developmental hypoplasia of the eccrine sweat glands.

label: Painful subcutaneous lipomas
definition: The presence of multiple subcutaneous lipoma that cause pain.

label: Bilateral single transverse palmar creases
definition: The distal and proximal transverse palmar creases are merged into a single transverse palmar crease on both hands.

label: Hypoproteinemic edema
definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body because of decreased osmotic pressure of plasma (hypoproteinemia).

label: Spinous keratoses of palms and soles
Nevus flammeus nuchae
definition: Naevus flammeus localized in the skin of the neck. This is one of the most common birthmarks and present in approximately 25% of all newborns.

label: Subcutaneous calcification
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in subcutaneous tissue (i.e., the the lowermost layer of the integument).

label: Cutaneous leiomyoma
definition: The presence of leiomyoma of the skin.

label: Mandibular osteomyelitis
definition: Osteomyelitis of the lower jaw.

label: Bilateral microphthalmos
definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by abnormal smallness of both eyes.

label: Nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
definition: An acute condition characterized by sudden visual loss (usually discovered in the morning), optic disc edema at onset, optic disc-related visual field defects. Nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy can be associated with flame hemorrhages on the swollen disk or nearby neuroretinal layer, and sometimes with nearby cotton-wool exudates.

label: Congenital stationary night blindness
definition: A nonprogressive (i.e., stationary) form of difficulties with night blindness with congenital onset.

label: Peripheral tractional retinal detachment
definition: Tractional retinal detachment at the periphery of the retina.

label: Tractional retinal detachment
definition: A type of retinal detachment arising due to a combination of contracting retinal membranes, abnormal vitreoretinal adhesions, and vitreous changes. It is usually seen in the context of diseases that induce a fibrovascular response, e.g. diabetes.

label: Absent lower eyelashes
definition: Lack of eyelashes on the lower lid.

label: Congenital extraocular muscle anomaly
definition: Congenital abnormality of the extraocular muscles.

label: Punctate cataract
definition: A type of cataract with punctate opacities of the lens.

label: Zonular cataract
definition: Zonular cataracts are defined to be cataracts that affect specific regions of the lens.

label: Congenital hypertrophy of retinal pigment epithelium
definition: Sharply demarcated, congenital hyperpigmentation of the retinal pigment epithelium.

label: Hyperpigmentation of the fundus
definition: Increased pigmentation of the fundus

label: Eversion of lateral third of lower eyelids
Lacrimal gland aplasia
definition: A congenital defect of development characterized by absence of the lacrimal gland.

label: Aplastic/hypoplastic lacrimal glands
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the lacrimal gland.

label: Diffuse nuclear cataract
definition: Opacity of the entire lens nucleus.

label: Nuclear cataract
definition: A nuclear cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the lens nucleus. That is, a nuclear cataract is one that is located in the center of the lens. The nucleus tends to darken changing from clear to yellow and sometimes brown.

label: Curly eyelashes
definition: Abnormally curly or curved eyelashes.

label: Peripheral cystoid retinal degeneration
definition: Degenerative changes of the peripheral retina consisting of close-packed tiny cystic spaces at the outer plexiform/inner nuclear retinal level. The degeneration is very common in adult eyes and starts adjacent to the ora serrata and extends circumferentially and posteriorly.

label: Abnormal vestibulo-ocular reflex
definition: An abnormality of the vestibulo-ocular reflex (VOR). The VOR attempts to keep the image stable on the retina. Ideally passive or active head movements in one direction are compensated for by eye movements of equal magnitude.

label: Vitelliform-like macular lesions
definition: Vitelliform maculopathy is a sharply demarcated lesion caused by the accumulation of material, often lipofuscin in the subretinal space underlying the macula.

label: Lacrimal duct stenosis
definition: Narrowing of a tear duct (lacrimal duct).

label: Hypopigmentation of the fundus
definition: Reduced pigmentation of the fundus, typically generalized. Fundoscopy may reveal a low level pigment in both RPE and choroid with clear visibility of choroidal vessels (pale/albinoid) or low pigment level in the RPE with deep pigment in choroid so that visible choroidal vessels are separated by deeply pigmented zones (tesselated/tigroid).

label: Unilateral ptosis
definition: A unilateral form of ptosis.

label: Undetectable light- and dark-adapted electroretinogram
definition: Absence of the combined rod-and-cone response on electroretinogram.

label: Abnormal pupillary light reflex
definition: An abnormality of the reflex that controls the diameter of the pupil, in response to the intensity of light that falls on the retina of the eye.

label: Hypoplasia of the lower eyelids
definition: Underdevelopment of the lower eyelid.

label: Hypoplasia of eyelid
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the eyelid.

label: Paroxysmal involuntary eye movements
definition: Sudden-onset episode of abnormal, involuntary eye movements.

label: Congenital aphakia
definition: Absence of the crystalline lens of the eye as a result of a developmental defect.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the lens
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the lens.

label: Band-shaped corneal dystrophy
definition: A type of genetically determined disease of the cornea with corneal lesions with a band-like shape.

label: Uveal melanoma
definition: A malignant melanoma originating within the eye. The tumor originates from the melanocytes in the uvea (which comprises the iris, ciliary body, and choroid).

label: Neoplasm of the eye
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the eye.

label: Chronic irritative conjunctivitis
definition: A chronic irritative conjunctivitis, which commonly presents with general irritation and redness of the eyes, with a burning, dry, or foreign-body sensation of the eyes.

label: Flat cornea
definition: Cornea plana is an abnormally flat shape of the cornea such that the normal protrusion of the cornea from the sclera is missing. The reduced corneal curvature can lead to hyperopia, and a hazy corneal limbus and arcus lipoides may develop at an early age.

label: Saccular conjunctival dilatations
definition: Presence of multiple dilatations (sac-like outpouchings) in the blood vessels of the conjunctiva.

label: Retinal pigment epithelial atrophy
definition: Atrophy (loss or wasting) of the retinal pigment epithelium observed on fundoscopy or fundus imaging.

label: Opacification of the corneal epithelium
definition: Lack of transparency of the corneal epithelium.

label: Congenital miosis
definition: Abnormal (non-physiological) constriction of the pupil of congenital onset.

label: Chorioretinal dysplasia
definition: Abnormal development of the choroid and retina.

label: Lacrimal gland hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the lacrimal gland.

label: Enlarged lacrimal glands
definition: Abnormally big lacrimal glands.

label: Abnormal lacrimal gland morphology
definition: Abnormality of the lacrimal gland, i.e., of the almond-shaped gland that secretes the aqueous layer of the tear film for each eye.

label: Bone spicule pigmentation of the retina
