definition: Pigment migration into the retina in a bone-spicule configuration (resembling the nucleated cells within the lacuna of bone).

label: Hypoplasia of the fovea
definition: Underdevelopment of the fovea centralis.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fovea
definition: Congenital absence or underdevelopment of the fovea centralis.

label: Macular dystrophy
definition: Macular dystrophy is a nonspecific term for premature retinal cell aging and cell death, generally confied to the macula in which no clear extrinsic cause is evident.

label: Abnormal corneal stroma morphology
definition: An abnormality of the stroma of cornea, also known as the substantia propria of cornea.

label: Punctate opacification of the cornea
definition: Punctate opacification (reduced transparency) of the corneal stroma.

label: Pericentral scotoma
definition: A scotoma (area of diminished vision within the visual field) that surrounds the central fixation point.

label: Retinal telangiectasia
definition: Dilatation of small blood vessels of the retina.

label: Deep anterior chamber
definition: Increased depth of the anterior chamber, i.e., the anteroposterior distance between the cornea and the iris is increased.

label: Optic disc hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the optic disc, that is of the optic nerve head, where ganglion cell axons exit the eye to form the optic nerve.

label: Central retinal vessel vascular tortuosity
definition: The presence of an increased number of twists and turns of retinal blood vessels (arteries, arterioles, veins, venules).

label: Vitreoretinopathy
definition: Ocular abnormality characterized by premature degeneration of the vitreous and the retina that may be associated with increased risk of retinal detachment.

label: Hypoplasia of the ciliary body
definition: Underdevelopment of the ciliary body.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia affecting the uvea
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the uvea, the pigmented middle layer of the eye consisting of the iris and ciliary body together with the choroid.

label: Abnormal ciliary body morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the ciliary body.

label: Chorioretinal scar
definition: Fibrous connective tissue resulting from incomplete healing of a wound (i.e., a scar) located in the choroid and retina or the eye.

label: Posterior retinal neovascularization
definition: A type of retinal neovascularization that affects the posterior pole of the retina.

label: Retinal neovascularization
definition: In wound repair, neovascularization (NV) involves the sprouting of new vessels from pre-existent vessels to repair or replace damaged vessels. In the retina, NV is a response to ischemia. The NV adheres to the inner surface of the retina and outer surface of the vitreous. NV are deficient in tight junctions and hence leak plasma into surrounding tissue including the vitreous. Plasma causes the vitreous gel to degenerate, contract, and eventually collapse which pulls on the retina. Since retinal NV is adherent to both retina and vitreous, as the vitreous contracts the NV may be sheared resulting in vitreous hemorrhage or the NV may remain intact and pull the retina with the vitreous resulting in retinal elevation referred to as traction retinal detachment.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia affecting the anterior segment of the eye
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the anterior segment of the eye.

label: Cortical pulverulent cataract
definition: A type of cataract characterized by punctate, dust-like opacities within the cortical region of the lens.

label: Pulverulent cataract
definition: A kind of congenital cataract that is characterized by a hollow sphere of punctate opacities involving the fetal nucleus and that usually occurs bilaterally.

label: Posterior subcapsular cataract
definition: A type of cataract affecting the posterior pole of lens immediately adjacent to ('beneath') the Lens capsule.

label: Patchy atrophy of the retinal pigment epithelium
definition: Wasting (atrophy) of the retinal pigment epithelium present in small, isolated areas.

label: Granular macular appearance
definition: Mottled (spotted or blotched with different shades) pigmentary abnormality of the macula lutea.

label: Retinal pigment epithelial mottling
definition: Mottling (spots or blotches with different shades) of the retinal pigment epithelium, i.e., localized or generalized fundal pigment granularity associated with processes at the level of the retinal pigment epithelium.

label: Abnormality of macular pigmentation
definition: Abnormality of macular or foveal pigmentation.

label: Anterior cortical cataract
definition: A cataract that affects the anterior part of the cortex of the lens.

label: Cortical cataract
definition: A cataract which affects the layer of the lens surrounding the nucleus, i.e., the lens cortex. It is identified by its unique wedge or spoke appearance.

label: Conjunctival whitish salt-like deposits
definition: The presence of whitish deposits in the conjunctiva resembling salt. May be related to calcinosis.

label: Increased axial length of the globe
definition: Abnormal largeness of the eye with an axial length > 2.5 standard deviations from population mean.

label: Granular corneal dystrophy
definition: The presence of central, fine, whitish granular lesions in the stroma of the cornea. This type of corneal dystrophy is usually asymptomatic and begins in childhood and shows a slow progression. Later in the course, the corneal epithelium and Bowman's layer may be affected. Histologically, the cornea shows a uniform deposition of hyaline material.

label: Monochromacy
definition: Complete color blindness, a complete inability to distinguish colors. Affected persons cannot perceive colors, but only shades of gray.

label: Horizontal pendular nystagmus
definition: Nystagmus consisting of horizontal to-and-fro eye movements of equal velocity.

label: Pendular nystagmus
definition: Rhythmic, involuntary sinusoidal oscillations of one or both eyes. The waveform of pendular nystagmus may occur in any direction.

label: Herpetiform corneal ulceration
definition: The presence of one or more dendritic corneal epithelial ulcers characterized by a treelike branching linear pattern with feathery edges and terminal bulbs. Herpetiform corneal ulcers can be identified by fluorescein staining.

label: Corneal ulceration
definition: Disruption of the epithelial layer of the cornea with involvement of the underlying stroma.

label: Nongranulomatous uveitis
definition: A form of uveitis that is not associated with the formation of granulomas.

label: Abnormal distribution of retinal arterioles and venules
Horizontal supranuclear gaze palsy
definition: A supranuclear gaze palsy is an inability to look in a horizontal direction as a result of cerebral impairment. There is a loss of the voluntary aspect of eye movements, but, as the brainstem is still intact, all the reflex conjugate eye movements are normal.

label: Central heterochromia
definition: The presence of distinct colors in the central (pupillary) zone of the iris than in the mid-peripheral (ciliary) zone.

label: Presenile cataracts
definition: Presenile cataract is a kind of cataract that occurs in early adulthood, that is, at an age that is younger than usual.

label: Lacrimal punctal atresia
definition: Congenital absence or closure of the opening of the lacrimal punctum.

label: Total ophthalmoplegia
definition: Paralysis of both the extrinsic and intrinsic ocular muscles.

label: Generalized opacification of the cornea
definition: Generalized reduced transparency of the stroma of the cornea.

label: Adult-onset night blindness
definition: Inability to see well at night or in poor light with onset in adulthood.

label: Nonprogressive restrictive external ophthalmoplegia
definition: Nonprogressive restriction of movement of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position. Residual eye movements are significantly limited.

label: Progressive cataract
definition: A kind of cataract that progresses with age.

label: Abnormal shape of the palpebral fissure
definition: The presence of an abnormal shape of the palpebral fissure.

label: Progressive ptosis
definition: A progressive form of ptosis.

label: Long upper eyelashes
definition: Increased length of the upper eyelashes.

label: Amyloid deposition in the vitreous humor
definition: Deposition of hyaline extracellular material (amyloid) into the vitreous humor, which can manifest as vitreous opacities and reduced visual acuity.

label: Chorioretinal lacunae
definition: Punched out lesions in the pigmented layer of the retina.

label: Congenital horizontal nystagmus
definition: Horizontal nystagmus dating from or present at birth.

label: Retinal calcification
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in the retina.

label: Restrictive partial external ophthalmoplegia
definition: Fibrosis of only some of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position.

label: Restrictive external ophthalmoplegia
definition: Fibrosis of the external ocular muscles such that the eyes of affected individuals are partially or completely fixed in a strabismic position. Residual eye movements are significantly limited.

label: Choroidal hemangioma
definition: The presence of multiple hemangiomas in the choroid. These are generally reddish or orange or can have increased pigmentation maiking them difficult to distinguish from choroidal melanomas.

label: Abnormal morphology of the choroidal vasculature
Almond-shaped palpebral fissure
definition: A shape created by an acute downward arching of the upper eyelid and upward arching of the lower eyelid, toward the medial canthus, which gives the outline of the palpebral fissures the configuration of an almond. Thus, the maximum distance between the fissures is offset from, and medial to, the center point.

label: Congenital blindness
definition: Blindness with onset at birth.

label: Allergic conjunctivitis
definition: Allergic Conjunctivitis is an allergic inflammation of the conjunctiva.

label: Slowed horizontal saccades
definition: An abnormally slow velocity of horizontal saccadic eye movements.

label: Absent extraocular muscles
definition: Congenital absence of the extraocular muscles.

label: Iridescent posterior subcapsular cataract
definition: A type of posterior subcapsular cataract characterized by an iridescent color.

label: Hypoplasia of the lacrimal punctum
definition: Underdevelopment of the lacrimal puncta.

label: Abnormality of fundus pigmentation
definition: Any anomaly of the pigmentation of the fundus, the posterior part of the eye including the retina and optic nerve.

label: Retinal nonattachment
definition: Failure of attachment of the retina during development.

label: Vitreous hemorrhage
definition: Bleeding within the vitreous compartment of the eye.

label: Paravenous chorioretinal atrophy
definition: Chorioretinal atrophy along the retinal veins.

label: Abnormality of the vasculature of the eye
Ocular hypertension
definition: Intraocular pressure that is 2 standard deviations above the population mean.

label: Asymmetry of intraocular pressure
definition: A difference in the amount of intraocular pressure in the right and left eye.

label: Reticular retinal dystrophy
definition: A type of of patterned retinal dystrophy that shows a reticular pattern of pigmentation.

label: Pattern dystrophy of the retina
definition: A spectrum of fundoscopic appearances characterized by the development of a variety of patterns of deposits predominantly in the macular area. The deposits are typically bilateral, relatively symmetrical, yellow/white and associated with changes at the level of the retinal pigment epithelium. With time, retinal atrophy may occur. A number of pattern dystrophy subtypes have been described including butterfly-shaped dystrophy, reticular dystrophy (net-like pattern) and fundus pulverulentus (granular, mottled pigmentation).

label: Polymorphous posterior corneal dystrophy
definition: This corneal dystrophy affects the posterior limiting membrane of the cornea and is characterized by polymorphous plaques of calcium deposits in the deep stromal layers of the cornea, and occasionally by vesicular lesions of the endothelium and edema of the deep corneal stroma.

label: Abnormal migration of corneal endothelium
definition: Abnormal migration of corneal endothelium.

label: Reduced number of corneal endothelial cells
definition: A reduction in the number of corneal endothelial cells.

label: Abnormal retinal nerve fiber layer morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the retinal nerve fiber layer

label: Lacrimal duct aplasia
definition: A congenital defect resulting in absence of the lacrimal duct.

label: Abnormal flash visual evoked potentials
definition: Anomaly of the visual evoked potentials elicited by a flash stimulus, generally a flash of light subtending an angle of at least 20 degrees of the visual field and presented in a dimly lit room.

label: Peripheral retinal detachment
definition: Separation of the inner layers of the retina (neural retina) from the pigment epithelium occurring near the outer limit (periphery) of the retina.

label: Bilateral congenital mydriasis
definition: Congenital abnormal dilation of the pupil on both sides.

label: Mydriasis
definition: Abnormal dilatation of the iris.

label: Broad lateral eyebrow
definition: Regional increase in the width (height) of the lateral eyebrow.

label: Broad eyebrow
definition: Regional increase in the width (height) of the eyebrow.

label: Reticular pigmentary degeneration
definition: A type of retinal reticular pigmentation that forms a polygonal, netlike arrangement of hyperpigmented lines forming geometric patterns in the fundus.

label: Blue cone monochromacy
definition: A form of monochromacy in which vision is derived from the remaining preserved blue (S) cones and rod photoreceptors.

label: Cone monochromacy
definition: The condition of having both rods and cones, but only a single kind of cone. Affected individuals have good pattern vision in daylight, but cannot distinguish between colors.

label: Limited extraocular movements
definition: Limited mobility of the eye within its socket.

label: Internal ophthalmoplegia
definition: Paralysis of the iris and ciliary apparatus.

label: Congenital stapes ankylosis
definition: A form of stapes ankylosis with congenital onset.

label: Unilateral narrow palpebral fissure
definition: A fixed reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids with short palpebral fissures on one side only.

label: Pericentral retinitis pigmentosa
definition: A subtype of retinitis pigmentosa in which, instead of the pathology starting in the mid-periphery like typical retinitis pigmentosa, the disease starts in the near periphery closer to the vascular arcades and tends to spare the far periphery.

label: Dense posterior cortical cataract
definition: A type of posterior cortical cataract characterized by dense lenticular opacities.

label: Posterior cortical cataract
definition: A cataract that affects the posterior part of the cortex of the lens.

label: Peripapillary chorioretinal atrophy
definition: Chorioretinal atrophy concentrated around the optic papilla (i.e., the optic nerve head).

label: Optic atrophy from cranial nerve compression
Remnants of the hyaloid vascular system
definition: Persistence of the hyaloid artery, which is the embryonic artery that runs from the optic disc to the posterior lens capsule may persist; the site of attachment may form an opacity. The hyaloid artery is a branch of the ophthalmic artery, and usually regresses completely before birth. This features results from a failure of regression of the hyaloid vessel, which supplies the primary vitreous during embryogenesis and normally regresses in the third trimester of pregnancy, leading to a particular form of posterior cataract.

label: Lamellar cataract
definition: A congenital cataract in which opacity is limited to layers of the lens external to the nucleus (i.e., the perinuclear region), i.e., between the nuclear and cortical layers of the lens.

label: Retinal dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the retina.

label: Hypometric horizontal saccades
definition: Saccadic undershoot of horizontal saccadic eye movements, i.e., a horizontal saccadic eye movement that has less than the magnitude that would be required to gain fixation of the object.

label: Cerulean cataract
definition: Cerulean cataracts are a kind of congenital cataract having peripheral bluish and white opacifications in concentric layers with occasional central lesions arranged radially. Although the opacities may be observed during fetal development and childhood, usually visual acuity is only mildly reduced until adulthood, when lens extraction is generally necessary.

label: Gaze-evoked horizontal nystagmus
definition: Horizontal nystagmus made apparent by looking to the right or to the left.

label: Electronegative electroretinogram
definition: A dark-adapted bright flash electroretinogram in which the b-wave that is of markedly lower amplitude than the associated a-wave (source: Holder GE., Inherited Chorioretinal Dystrophies: A Textbook and Atlas; 2014; p.17; ISBN 978-3-540-69466-3).

label: Abnormal amplitude of dark-adapted bright flash electroretinogram
Retinal arteriolar occlusion
definition: Blockage of retinal arteriole, generally associated with interruption of blood flow and oxygen delivery to affected regions of the retina.

label: Macular hypopigmentation
definition: Decreased amount of pigmentation in the macula lutea.

label: Intraretinal exudate
definition: Retinal exudate within the retinal tissue itself.

label: Hypoplastic iris stroma
definition: Underdevelopment of the stroma of iris.

label: Malformed lacrimal duct
definition: Congenital malformation of the lacrimal duct associated with incomplete development of the bony nasolacrimal canal or craniofacial anomalies.

label: Peripheral visual field loss
definition: Loss of peripheral vision with retention of central vision, resulting in a constricted circular tunnel-like field of vision.

label: Decreased corneal reflex
definition: An abnormally reduced response to stimulation of the cornea (by touch, foreign body, blowing air). The corneal reflex (also known as the blink reflex, normally results in an involuntary blinking of the eyelids.

label: Abnormal corneal reflex
definition: An anomaly of the corneal reflex that normally induces involuntary blinking of the eyelids following contact of the cornea.

label: Foveal hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased amount of pigmentation in the fovea centralis.

label: Abnormality of foveal pigmentation
definition: An anomaly of the pigmentation in the fovea centralis.

label: Central fundal arteriolar microaneurysms
definition: Microscopic aneurysms of the retinal arterioles near the central part of the fundus, visible as small round dark red dots on the retinal surface (not arising from visible vessels) that are by definition less than the diameter of the major optic veins as they cross the optic disc.

label: Retinal microaneurysm
definition: A localized dilation of microvasculature formed due to disruption of the internal elastic lamina of a retinal capillary blood vessel. The lesions present as small circular, red dots having distinct margins and are no larger than a blood vessel width at the disk margin. This expansion disturbs the normal flow pattern, changing shear force and pressure along the vessel. Shear force plays a key role in promoting the differentiation and proliferation of endothelial cells.

label: Superior lens subluxation
definition: Partial dislocation of the lens in a superior direction.

label: Cone dystrophy
definition: Inherited progressive cone degeneration.

label: Cystoid macular degeneration
definition: A form of macular degeneration characterized by the presence of multiple cysts in the macula.

label: Retinal vasculitis
definition: Inflammation of retinal blood vessels as manifested by perivascular sheathing or cuffing, vascular leakage and/or occlusion.

label: Posterior Y-sutural cataract
definition: A type of sutural cataract in which the opacity follows the posterior Y suture.

label: Sutural cataract
definition: A type of congenital cataract in which the opacity follows the anterior or posterior Y suture.

label: Retinitis pigmentosa inversa
definition: Retinitis pigmentosa inversa is form of retinal degeneration characterized by areas of retinal/chorioretinal degeneration with pigment migration in the macular area (in contrast to retinitis pigmentosa which, at early disease stages, predominantly affects the retinal periphery).

label: Absent anterior chamber of the eye
definition: Absence of the anterior chamber of the eye owing to a developmental defect.

label: Retinal arteriolar constriction
definition: Decreased retinal arteriolar diameters, which may decrease blood flow and slow oxygen delivery to regions of the retina.

label: Abnormal amplitude of flash visual evoked potentials
Abnormality of the palpebral fissures
definition: An anomaly of the space between the medial and lateral canthi of the two open eyelids.

label: Abnormal blistering of the skin
definition: The presence of one or more bullae on the skin, defined as fluid-filled blisters more than 5 mm in diameter with thin walls.

label: Maternal hypertension
definition: Increased blood pressure during a pregnancy.

label: Toxemia of pregnancy
definition: Pregnancy-induced toxic reactions of the mother that can be as harmless as slight Maternal hypertension or as life threatening as Eclampsia.

label: Maternal virilization in pregnancy
definition: Virilization (deepening of voice, facial hirsutism and scalp hair loss) with onset during pregnancy (usually towards the end of the first trimester) and regression several months post-partum.

label: Low maternal circulating estriol concentration
definition: An abnormally low concentration of serum conjugated estriol as compared to normal values for gestational-age.

label: Abnormal maternal serum screening
definition: An abnormally elevated or decreased level of a maternal serum marker analytes used in screening for aneuploidy.

label: Osteoporotic tarsals
definition: Reduction in bone mineral density affecting any or all of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones.

label: Abnormal tarsal bone mineral density
definition: This term applies to all changes in bone mineral density of the tarsal bones, which (depending on severity) can be seen on x-rays as a change in density and or structure of the bone.

label: Absent fifth metatarsal
definition: A developmental abnormality characterized by the absence of the fifth metatarsal bone.

label: Absent metatarsal bone
definition: A developmental abnormality characterized by the absence (aplasia) of a metatarsal bone.

label: Hallux varus
definition: Medial deviation of the great toe owing to a deformity of the great toe joint causing the hallux to deviate medially.

label: Pes valgus
definition: An outward deviation of the foot at the talocalcaneal or subtalar joint.

label: Nonossified fifth metatarsal
definition: The presence of a fifth metatarsal bone that has not undergone ossification at an age when ossification is usually visible.

label: Abnormal metatarsal ossification
definition: Any abnormal process of ossification of the metatarsal bones, which normally are each ossified from two centers: one for the body, and one for the head (metatarsal II,III,IV, and V) and one for the body and one for the base (metatarsal I). The ossification process begins in the center of the body about the ninth week, and extends toward either extremity. The center for the base of the first metatarsal appears about the third year, and the centers for the heads of the other bones between the fifth and eighth years. They join the bodies between the eighteenth and twentieth years.

label: Short 4th toe
definition: Underdevelopment (hypoplasia) of the fourth toe.

label: Widely spaced toes
definition: An overall widening of the spaces between the digits.

label: Osteolysis of talus
definition: Osteolysis affecting the talus.

label: Medially deviated second toe
definition: Medial deviation of the second toe.

label: Expanded metatarsals with widened medullary cavities
Delayed tarsal ossification
definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones.

label: Abnormal tarsal ossification
definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones.

label: Plantar crease between first and second toes
definition: The presence of unusually deep creases (ridges/wrinkles) on the skin of sole of foot located between the first and second toe.

label: Advanced tarsal ossification
definition: Precocious (accelerated) maturation and calcification of any of the tarsal bones, seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones.

label: Broad hallux
definition: Visible increase in width of the hallux without an increase in the dorso-ventral dimension.

label: Plantar flexion contracture
definition: A type of contracture in which the plantar flexion muscles are contracted.

label: Metatarsal diaphyseal endosteal sclerosis
definition: Osteosclerosis of the endosteal surface of the diaphyses (shafts) of the metatarsal bones.

label: Sclerosis of foot bone
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more foot bones. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Clinodactyly of the 3rd toe
definition: Bending or curvature of a third toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe).

label: Flexion limitation of toes
definition: Limitation of the ability to bend the toes.

label: Calcaneonavicular fusion
definition: Synostosis of the calcaneus with the navicular bone.

label: Talipes calcaneovarus
definition: A congenital deformity characterized by a dorsiflexed, inverted, and adducted foot, i.e., a combination of talipes calcaneus and talipes varus.

label: Bipartite calcaneus
definition: A two-part calcaneus, a finding that probably results from delayed coalescence of two primary calcaneal centers of ossification.

label: Tarsal stippling
definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more tarsal bones.

label: Tarsal sclerosis
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more tarsal bones of the foot. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Medial rotation of the medial malleolus
Irregular tarsal ossification
definition: Defective ossification in an irregular pattern of the seven bones of the foot comprising the calcaneus, talus, cuboid, navicular, and the cuneiform bones.

label: Equinus calcaneus
definition: Abnormal plantar flexion of the calcaneus relative to the longitudinal axis of the tibia. This results in the angle between the long axis of the tibia and the long axis of the heel bone (calcaneus) being greater than 90 degrees.

label: Delayed calcaneal ossification
definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of the calcaneus.

label: Impaired epinephrine-induced platelet aggregation
definition: Abnormal response to epinephrine as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of epinephrine.

label: Elevated serum transaminases during infections
definition: Elevations of the levels of SGOT (serum glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase) and SGPT (serum glutamic pyruvic transaminase) that occur during infections.

label: Prolonged prothrombin time
definition: Increased time to coagulation in the prothrombin time test, which is a measure of the extrinsic pathway of coagulation. The results of the prothrombin time test are often expressed in terms of the International normalized ratio (INR), which is calculated as a ratio of the patient's prothrombin time (PT) to a control PT standardized for the potency of the thromboplastin reagent developed by the World Health Organization (WHO) using the formula: INR is equal to Patient PT divided by Control PT.

label: Abnormal prothrombin time
definition: Any deviation from the normal amount of time to coagulation in the prothrombin time test, which is a measure of the extrinsic pathway of coagulation. The results of the prothrombin time test are often expressed in terms of the International normalized ratio (INR), which is calculated as a ratio of the patient's prothrombin time (PT) to a control PT standardized for the potency of the thromboplastin reagent developed by the World Health Organization (WHO) using the formula: INR is equal to Patient PT divided by Control PT.

label: Periodic hypokalemic paresis
definition: Episodes of muscle weakness associated with reduced levels of potassium in the blood.

label: Hyperapobetalipoproteinemia
definition: Hyperapobetalipoproteinemia is defined as the combination of a normal low density lipoprotein (LDL) cholesterol in the face of an increased LDL apolipoprotein B (apoB) protein.

label: 3-hydroxydicarboxylic aciduria
definition: The concentration of 2-hydroxydicarboxylic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Absent leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
definition: Alkaline phosphatase levels measured within leukocytes is below detectable levels.

label: Asymptomatic hyperammonemia
definition: An increased concentration of ammonia in the blood not associated with symptoms such as encephalopathy.

label: Decreased circulating cortisol level
definition: Abnormally reduced concentration of cortisol in the blood.

label: Decreased helper T cell proportion
definition: Reduced proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal helper T cell proportion
definition: Abnormal proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased beta-galactosidase activity
definition: Abnormally decreased rate of beta-galactosidase activity. Beta-galactosidase activity can be measured in leukocyte, fibroblast, or plasma.

label: Very long chain fatty acid accumulation
Abnormal tissue metabolite concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a metabolite in a tissue.

label: Reduced factor VII activity
definition: Reduced activity of coagulation factor VII. Factor VII is part of the extrinsic coagulation pathway, which is initiated at the site of injury in response to the release of tissue factor (fIII). Tissue factor and activated factor VII catalyze the activation of factor X.

label: Decreased Arden ratio of electrooculogram
definition: An abnormal reduction in the Arden ratio, which is the ratio between the light peak and the dark trough of the smoothed (physiologic) EOG record.

label: Abnormal electrooculogram
definition: The clinical electro-oculogram (EOG) is an electrophysiological test of function of the outer retina and retinal pigment epithelium (RPE) in which changes in electrical potential across the RPE are recorded during successive periods of dark and light adaptation.

label: Abetalipoproteinemia
definition: An absence of low-density lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

label: Precocious puberty in males
definition: The onset of puberty before the age of 9 years in boys.

label: Adrenocortical cytomegaly
definition: The presence of large polyhedral cells with eosinophilic granular cytoplasm and enlarged nuclei in the adrenal cortex.

label: Absence of secondary sex characteristics
definition: No secondary sexual characteristics are present at puberty.

label: Thyroid dysgenesis
definition: Thyroid dysgenesis is a descriptive term that should be avoided if more precise information is available. However, the HPO keeps retains this term because it is commonly used in the medical literature. In humans, the process of thyroid morphogenesis occurs from the 3rd to 16th week of gestation. Alterations occurring during this period may result in a thyroid gland that is absent (thyroid agenesis or athyreosis), hypoplastic (thyroid hypoplasia), or located in an unusual position (thyroid ectopy). All these entities are grouped under the term thyroid dysgenesis.

label: Insulin insensitivity
definition: Decreased sensitivity toward insulin.

label: Thyroid agenesis
definition: The congenital absence of the thyroid gland.

label: Multiple pancreatic beta-cell adenomas
definition: The presence of multiple pancreatic islet cell adenomas.

label: Pancreatic islet cell adenoma
definition: The presence of an adenoma of the pancreas with origin in a pancreatic B cell.

label: Congenital hypoparathyroidism
definition: Deficiency of parathyroid hormone with congenital onset.

label: Primary hyperparathyroidism
definition: A type of hyperparathyroidism caused by a primary abnormality of the parathyroid glands (e.g., adenoma, carcinoma, hyperplasia). Primary hyperparathyroidism is associated with hyercalcemia.

label: Reduced circulating prolactin concentration
definition: A reduced level of prolactin in the blood circulation. Prolactin is a protein hormone that is secreted by lactotrophs in the anterior pituitary and that stimulates mammary gland development and milk production.

label: Precocious puberty with Sertoli cell tumor
Sertoli cell neoplasm
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the testis with origin in a Sertoli cell.

label: Insulin-dependent but ketosis-resistant diabetes
definition: Ketosis-resistant diabetes is a synonym for type II diabetes. This term thus refers to a form of type II diabetes in which patients are dependent on insulin.

label: Primary adrenal insufficiency
definition: Insufficient production of steroid hormones (primarily cortisol) by the adrenal glands as a result of a primary defect in the glands themselves.

label: Parathyroid hyperplasia
definition: Hyperplasia of the parathyroid gland.

label: Abnormal parathyroid morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the parathyroid gland.

label: Premature ovarian insufficiency
definition: Amenorrhea due to loss of ovarian function before the age of 40. Primary ovarian insuficiency (POI) is a state of female hypergonadotropic hypogonadism. It can manifest as primary amenorrhea with onset before menarche or secondary amenorrhea.

label: Parathyroid agenesis
definition: Aplasia of the parathyroid gland.

label: Gonadotropin deficiency
definition: A reduced ability to secrete gonadotropins, which are protein hormones secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary gland, including the hormones follitropin (FSH) and luteinizing hormone (LH).

label: Decreased serum estradiol
definition: A reduction below normal concentration of estradiol in the circulation.

label: Abnormal serum estradiol
definition: A deviation from normal concentrations of estradiol in the circulation.

label: Adrenal gland dysgenesis
definition: Abnormal development of the adrenal gland.

label: Adrenal hyperplasia
definition: Enlargement of the adrenal gland.

label: Compensated hypothyroidism
definition: Condition associated with a raised serum concentration of thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) but a normal serum free thyroxine (FT4).

label: Thyroid hyperplasia
definition: Hyperplasia of the thyroid gland.

label: Androgen insufficiency
definition: Insufficient amount of androgenic activity.

label: Pituitary resistance to thyroid hormone
definition: A condition in which the pituitary gland is partially resistant to thyroid hormone, so that it continues to secrete thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) until the blood level of thyroid hormone rises higher than normal.

label: Abnormality of the anterior pituitary
definition: An abnormality of the adenohypophysis, which is also known as the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland.

label: Thyroid lymphangiectasia
definition: The presence of lymphangiectasis of the thyroid gland.

label: Elevated circulating follicle stimulating hormone level
definition: An elevated concentration of follicle-stimulating hormone in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating follicle-stimulating hormone concentration
definition: An anomaly of the circulating level of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

label: Decreased circulating progesterone
definition: An reduced concentration of progesterone in the blood.

label: Hypothalamic hypothyroidism
definition: A type of hypothyroidism that results from a defect in thyrotropin-releasing hormone activity.

label: Central hypothyroidism
definition: A type of hypothyroidism due to an insufficient stimulation of an otherwise normal thyroid gland. Central hypothyroidism is caused by either pituitary (secondary hypothyroidism) or hypothalamic (tertiary hypothyroidism) defects.

label: Adrenal medullary hypoplasia
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the adrenal medulla.

label: Pseudohypoaldosteronism
definition: A state of renal tubular unresponsiveness or resistance to the action of aldosterone.

label: Congenital adrenal hypoplasia
definition: A type of adrenal hypoplasia with congenital onset.

label: Pituitary hypothyroidism
definition: A type of hypothyroidism that results from a defect in thyroid-stimulating hormone secretion.

label: Euthyroid hyperthyroxinemia
definition: Increased levels of thyroxine without evidence of clinical thyroid disease.

label: Congenital goiter
definition: An enlargement of the thyroid gland with congenital onset.

label: Adrenocortical adenoma
definition: Adrenocortical adenomas are benign tumors of the adrenal cortex.

label: Congenital adrenal hyperplasia
definition: A type of adrenal hyperplasia with congenital onset.

label: Adrenocorticotropin receptor defect
definition: Adrenal insufficiency secondary to a defect in the ACTH receptor.

label: Central adrenal insufficiency
definition: A form of adrenal insufficiency related to a lack of ACTH, which leads to a decrease in the production of cortisol by the adrenal glands. Aldosterone production is not usually affected.

label: Pancreatic endocrine tumor
definition: A neuroendocrine tumor originating in a hormone-producing cell (islet cell) of the pancreas.

label: Thyroid defect in oxidation and organification of iodide
Neutrophil inclusion bodies
definition: The presence of intracellular inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in neutrophils. Cytoplasmic neutrophil inclusions (oval, basophilic) are also known as Doehle bodies.

label: Increased red cell hemolysis by shear stress
Abnormal cartilage collagen
definition: Abnormal morphology of collagen fibers in cartilage. In cartilage, collagen II, actually a collagen II:IX:XI heterofibril, is by far the most important type of collagen. A number of abnormalities may be appreciated by electron micrography or biochemical investigations, including sparse collagen fibers in the cartilage matrix.

label: Abnormal blood zinc concentration
definition: An abnormality of zinc ion homeostasis.

label: Abnormal blood transition element cation concentration
definition: An abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of transition element cation.

label: Cerebellar cortical atrophy
definition: Atrophy (wasting) of the cerebellar cortex.

label: Acute hyperammonemia
definition: An increased concentration of ammonia in the blood with sudden onset.

label: Unconjugated hyperbilirubinemia
definition: An increased amount of unconjugated (indirect) bilurubin in the blood.

label: Fasting hyperinsulinemia
definition: An increased concentration of insulin in the blood in the fasting state, i.e., not as the response to food intake.

label: Partial complement factor H deficiency
definition: A partial reduction in level of the complement component Factor H in circulation.

label: Pituitary corticotropic cell adenoma
definition: A type of pituitary adenoma that produces adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH).

label: Long-chain dicarboxylic aciduria
definition: An increase in the level of long-chain dicarboxylic acid in the urine.

label: Transient hyperphenylalaninemia
definition: A condition of not having consistently high levels of phenylalanine in the blood but of experiencing temporary hyperphenylalaninemia following ingestion of large quantities of phenylalanine (for instance, following an oral loading test with phenylalanine).

label: Dermatan sulfate excretion in urine
definition: An increased concentration of dermatan sulfate in the urine.

label: Olivary degeneration
definition: Degeneration of the olivary bodies, prominent oval structures in the medulla oblongata.

label: Abnormal medulla oblongata morphology
definition: An abnormality of the medulla oblongata, the lower half of the brainstem.

label: Exercise-induced myoglobinuria
definition: Presence of myoglobin in the urine following exercise.

label: Medium chain dicarboxylic aciduria
definition: An increase in the level of medium chain dicarboxylic acid in the urine.

label: Spinal cord posterior columns myelin loss
Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex II
definition: A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex II, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria.

label: Decreased activity of mitochondrial respiratory chain
definition: Decreased activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain.

label: Decreased plasma free carnitine
definition: A decreased concentration of free (unbound) carnitine in the blood.

label: Abnormal mitochondria in muscle tissue
definition: An abnormality of the mitochondria in muscle tissue.

label: Elevated leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
definition: Increased alkaline phosphatase measured within leukocytes.

label: Impaired collagen-induced platelet aggregation
definition: Abnormal response to collagen or collagen-mimetics as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition collagen or collagen-mimetics.

label: Reduced factor X activity
definition: Reduced activity of coagulation factor X. The extrinsic and intrinsic pathways converge at factor X (fX). The extrinsic pathway activates fX by means of d factor VII with its cofactor, tissue factor. The intrinsic pathway activates fX by means of the tenase complex (Ca2+ and factors VIIIa, IXa and X) on the surface of activated platelets. Factor Xa in turn activates prothrombin (factor II) to thrombin (factor IIa).

label: Abnormality of the common coagulation pathway
definition: An abnormality of blood coagulation, common pathway.

label: Abnormal mitochondrial morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the mitochondria.

label: Reduced circulating vitamin B6 circulating
definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of vitamin B6 in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating vitamin B6 concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of vitamin B6 in the blood circulation.

label: Microscopic nephrocalcinosis
definition: The presence of microscopic crystalline calcium precipitates in the form of oxalate and/or phosphate in the renal parenchyma.

label: Reduced von Willebrand factor activity
definition: Decreased activity of von Willebrand factor. Von Willebrand factor mediates the adhesion of platelets to the collagen exposed on endothelial cell surfaces.

label: Abnormality of von Willebrand factor
definition: Decreased quantity or activity of von Willebrand factor. Von Willebrand factor mediates the adhesion of platelets to the collagen exposed on endothelial cell surfaces.

label: Partial functional complement factor D deficiency
definition: A partial reduction in level of the complement component Factor D in circulation.

label: Diaminoaciduria
definition: An increased urine level of any amino acid carrying two amino groups (Asparagine, glutamine and lysine, cystine, ornithine).

label: Elevated circulating branched chain amino acid concentration
definition: Concentration of a branched chain amino acid in the blood above the upper limit of normal.

label: Hypoplasia of the iris dilator muscle
definition: Underdevelopment of the dilatator pupillae.

label: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex IV
definition: A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex IV, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria.

label: Decreased circulating IgG2 concentration
definition: A reduction in immunoglobulin levels of the IgG2 subclass in the blood circulation.

label: Decreased circulating IgG subclass concentration
definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of a subclass of immunoglobulin G (IgG) in the blood.

label: Impaired platelet adhesion
definition: An abnormality of adhesion of thrombocytes. Normally, platelets adhere to collagen in the vascular subendothelium within seconds of injury via a receptor made up of glycoprotein Ia and IIa and GPVI and to vWF via receptor GPIb/IX/V. The adherent platelets then release granules that lead to platelet activation and aggregation.

label: Abnormal platelet function
definition: Any anomaly in the function of thrombocytes.

label: Neutral hyperaminoaciduria
definition: The presence of an abnormally increased concentration of neutral amino acids in the urine. The neutral amino acids are tryptophan, alanine, asparagine, glutamine, histidine, isoleucine, leucine, phenylalanine, serine, threonine, tyrosine and valine.

label: Factor X activation deficiency
definition: Reduced ability to transform factor X into its activated form factor Xa.

label: Reduced factor XIII activity
definition: Decreased activity of coagulation factor XIII (also known as fibrin stabilizing factor). Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot.

label: Hyperprolinemia
definition: An increased concentration of proline in the blood.

label: Neonatal hypoproteinemia
definition: A neonatal decreased concentration of proteins in the blood.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the hallux
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the big toe.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tarsal bones
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the tarsal bones.

label: Synostosis of carpals/tarsals
definition: The carpus consists of the scaphoid, lunate, triquetal, pisiform, captitate, hamate, trapezoid, and trapezium bones. The tarsus consists of the talus, calcaneus, cuboid, cuneiform, and navicular bones. This term applies if there is any fusion among the bones of the carpus or tarsus.

label: Abnormal foot bone ossification
definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any bone of the skeleton of foot.

label: Slow-growing nails
definition: Nails whose growth is slower than normal.

label: Abnormal nail growth
definition: Nail whose growth pattern or speed deviates from normal.

label: Recurrent loss of toenails and fingernails
definition: Repeated loss, or shedding, of the nails of the fingers and toes.

label: Dystrophic fingernails
definition: The presence of misshapen or partially destroyed nail plates, often with accumulation of soft, yellow keratin between the dystrophic nail plate and nail bed, resulting in elevation of the nail plate.

label: Subungual hyperkeratosis
definition: A thickening of the stratum corneum in the region beneath the nails.

label: Abnormality of the subungual region
definition: A lesion located beneath a fingernail or toenail.

label: Congenital curved nail of fourth toe
Chronic monilial nail infection
definition: Chronic infection of the nails by Candida species.

label: Hypoplastic fifth fingernail
definition: A nail of the fifth finger that is diminished in length and width, i.e., underdeveloped nail of little finger.

label: Circumungual hyperkeratosis
definition: A thickening of the stratum corneum, the outer layer of the skin, in the region surrounding the nails.

label: Onycholysis of distal fingernails
definition: Detachment of the distal fingernails from the nail bed.

label: Onychogryposis of toenails
definition: Thickened toenails.

label: Ridged fingernail
definition: Longitudinal, linear prominences in the fingernail plate.

label: Vertebral hypoplasia
definition: Small, underdeveloped vertebral bodies.

label: Intervertebral disk degeneration
definition: The presence of degenerative changes of intervertebral disk.

label: Punctate vertebral calcifications
definition: The presence of punctiform calcification of the bone of the vertebral bodies.

label: Spinal dysplasia
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the vertebral column.

label: Anterior wedging of L1
definition: An abnormality of the shape of the lumbar vertebra L1 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front).

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cervical spine
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the cervical vertebral column.

label: Absent in utero ossification of vertebral bodies
Lumbar hemivertebrae
definition: Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the lumbar spine.

label: Herniation of intervertebral nuclei
definition: The presence of one or more herniated nucleus pulposus of intervertebral disk.

label: Vertebral hyperostosis
definition: Excessive growth of the bones of the vertebral bodies.

label: Neuropathic spinal arthropathy
definition: A progressive disorder of vertebral joint degeneration that occurs in the setting of any condition characterized by decreased afferent innervation, involving loss of deep pain and proprioceptive sensation in the vertebral column. Patients most commonly present with symptoms of lower back pain, sitting imbalance, progressive spinal deformity (usually kyphosis), and an audible clicking sound on changing postures.

label: Posterior wedging of vertebral bodies
definition: An abnormality of the shape of vertebrae, such that they are wedge-shaped (narrow towards the back).

label: Cervical spinal canal stenosis
definition: An abnormal narrowing of the cervical spinal canal.

label: Narrow vertebral interpedicular distance
definition: A reduction of the distance between vertebral pedicles, which are the two short, thick processes, which project backward, one on either side, from the upper part of the vertebral body, at the junction of its posterior and lateral surfaces.

label: Dysplastic sacrum
definition: A developmental defect of the sacrum characterized by partial or disordered development of the sacrum in which portions of the sacrum, which normally is formed by fusion of five sacral vertebrae S1-S5, fail to form or fail to form normally.

label: C2-C3 subluxation
definition: A partial dislocation of the intervertebral joint between the second and third cervical vertebrae.

label: Caudal interpedicular narrowing
definition: Narrowing (becoming gradually narrower) of the distance between vertebral pedicles that gets progressively more severe towards to caudal (lower) end of the vertebral column. Note that normally, the interpedicular distances get progressively wider as one proceeds down the spine.

label: Progressive congenital scoliosis
definition: A progressive form of scoliosis with congenital onset.

label: Cervical vertebral agenesis
definition: Agenesis of one or more vertebrae of the cervical vertebral column.

label: Absent spinous processes of lower thoracic and lumbar vertebrae
Abnormality of the vertebral spinous processes
Absent vertebra
definition: A developmental defect characterized by agenesis of one or more vertebral bodies.

label: Thoracic hemivertebrae
definition: Absence of one half of the vertebral body in the thoracic spine.

label: Abnormal sacral segmentation
definition: An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation of sacral vertebrae during development.

label: Cervical vertebral dysplasia
definition: Dysplasia of the cervical vertebral column.

label: Lower thoracic interpediculate narrowness
definition: A reduction of the distance between the lower thoracic vertebral pedicles.

label: Poorly ossified cervical vertebrae
definition: Decreased ossification of the cervical vertebral bodies, i.e., of the Cervical vertebrae set.

label: Poorly ossified vertebrae
definition: Decreased ossification of the vertebral bodies.

label: Morbus Scheuermann
definition: A developmental growth retardation of the vertebral end plates that may lead to secondary destruction of the vertebral end plates and protrusion of the nucleus pulposus into the vertebral body (so called Schmorl's nodes as seen on x-rays).

label: Cervical spondylosis
definition: Arthrosis, i.e., of degenerative joint disease, affecting the cervical vertebral column.

label: Abnormality of spinal facet joint
definition: An anomaly of the small joints located between and behind adjacent vertebrae.

label: Cervical vertebral bodies with decreased anteroposterior diameter
Thoracolumbar interpediculate narrowness
definition: A reduction of the distance between thoracolumbar vertebral pedicles.

label: Lumbar interpedicular narrowing
definition: Narrowing (becoming gradually narrower) of the distance between lumbar vertebral pedicles that gets progressively more severe towards to caudal (lower) end of the vertebral column.

label: Spondylolisthesis at L5-S1
definition: Complete bilateral fractures of the pars interarticularis resulting in the anterior slippage of the fifth lumbar vertebral body (L5) onto the sacrum (level S1).

label: Premature anterior fontanel closure
definition: Early closure (ossification) of the anterior fontanelle, which generally undergoes closure around the 18th month of life.

label: Inferior lens subluxation
definition: Partial displacement of the lens in the inferior direction.

label: High hypermetropia
definition: A severe form of hypermetropia with over +5.00 diopters.

label: Moderate sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: The presence of a moderate form of sensorineural hearing impairment.

label: Moderate hearing impairment
definition: The presence of a moderate form of hearing impairment.

label: Central posterior corneal opacity
definition: Reduced transparency of the central posterior portion of the corneal stroma.

label: Bilateral conductive hearing impairment
definition: A bilateral type of conductive hearing impairment.

label: Posterior helix pit
definition: Permanent indentation on the posteromedial aspect of the helix that may be sharply or indistinctly delineated.

label: Congenital sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A type of hearing impairment caused by an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve with congenital onset.

label: Long hairs growing from helix of pinna
Absence of acoustic reflex
definition: Absence of the acoustic reflex, an involuntary contraction of the stapedius muscle that occurs in response to high-intensity sound stimuli.

label: Abnormality of the acoustic reflex
definition: An abnormality in the reflexive contraction of the middle-ear muscles in response to sound stimulation.

label: Cleft at the superior portion of the pinna
Cleft helix
definition: A notched form of the helix of the ear. That is, a defect in the continuity of the helix, which may occur at any point along its length.

label: Low-frequency hearing loss
definition: A type of hearing impairment affecting primarily the low frequencies of sound (125 Hz to 1000 Hz).

label: Microtia
definition: Underdevelopment of the external ear.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the external ear
definition: The presence of aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of all or part of the external ear.

label: Cochlear malformation
definition: The presence of a malformed cochlea.

label: Absent vestibular function
definition: Complete lack of functioning of the vestibular apparatus.

label: Hypoplastic helices
definition: Underdevelopment of the helix, i.e., of the outer rim of the pinna.

label: Vestibular areflexia
definition: Vestibular areflexia can be measured as the absence of the caloric nystagmus response in electronystagmography.

label: Microtia, second degree
definition: Median longitudinal length of the ear more than two standard deviations below the mean in the presence of some, but not all, parts of the normal ear.

label: Low-frequency sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A form of sensorineural hearing impairment that affects primarily the lower frequencies.

label: Underfolded helix
definition: Underdevelopment of the helix that either affects the entire helix, or is localized.

label: Underfolded superior helices
definition: A condition in which the superior portion of the helix is folded over to a lesser degree than normal.

label: Hypoplasia of the cochlea
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the cochlea.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cochlea
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the cochlea, a spiral shaped cavity in the inner ear, owing to a developmental defect.

label: Mild neurosensory hearing impairment
definition: The presence of a mild form of sensorineural hearing impairment.

label: Mild hearing impairment
definition: The presence of a mild form of hearing impairment.

label: Slit-like opening of the exterior auditory meatus
definition: A type of stenosis of the external auditory meatus in which the opening of the external auditory meatus appears as a vertical slit.

label: Congenital conductive hearing impairment
definition: A type of conductive deafness with congenital onset.

label: Prominent antitragus
definition: Increased anterosuperior prominence of the area between the bottom of the incisura and the inner margin of the antihelix.

label: Abnormal antitragus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the antitragus, which is a small tubercle opposite to the tragus of the ear. The antitragus and the tragus are separated by the intertragic notch.

label: Postlingual sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A form of sensorineural hearing impairment with onset after the acquisition of speech.

label: Mild conductive hearing impairment
definition: A mild form of conductive hearing impairment.

label: Supraauricular pit
definition: Benign congenital lesion of the supraauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit.

label: Progressive conductive hearing impairment
definition: A progressive type of conductive deafness.

label: Infantile sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A form of sensorineural hearing impairment with infantile onset.

label: Adult onset sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: The presence of sensorineural deafness with late onset.

label: Bilateral sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A bilateral form of sensorineural hearing impairment.

label: Severe sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: A severe form of sensorineural hearing impairment.

label: Severe hearing impairment
definition: A severe form of hearing impairment.

label: Pulsatile tinnitus
definition: Pulsatile tinnitus is generally classified a kind of objective tinnitus, meaning that it is not only audible to the patient but also to the examiner on auscultation of the auditory canal and/or of surrounding structures with use of an auscultation tube or stethoscope. Usually, pulsatile tinnitus is heard as a lower pitched thumping or booming, a rougher blowing sound which is coincidental with respiration, or as a clicking, higher pitched rhythmic sensation.

label: Ureteral dysgenesis
definition: A developmental anomaly of the ureter.

label: Agonadism
definition: Absence of sex glands (gonads are the organs that produce gametes; testis in males and ovary in females).

label: Urinary bladder wall hypertrophy
definition: Increase in thickness of the wall of the urinary bladder. This finding may be seen in conditions such as bladder outlet obstruction and may be accompanied by increased trabeculation of the bladder wall musculature.

label: Nephroblastomatosis
definition: Presence of persistent islands of renal blastema in the postnatal kidney. Nephroblastomatosis represents a complex abnormality of nephrogenesis and has been defined as the persistence of metanephricblastema into infancy and childhood.

label: Uric acid urolithiasis independent of gout
Autonomic erectile dysfunction
definition: Impotence (inability to develop or maintain an erection) resulting from abnormal functioning of the autonomic nervous system.

label: Crescentic glomerulonephritis
definition: A type of extracapillary glomerulonephritis characterized by the formation of crescent-like cellular proliferation.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fallopian tube
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the fallopian tube.

label: Abnormal fallopian tube morphology
definition: An abnormality of the fallopian tube.

label: Multiple small medullary renal cysts
definition: The presence of many cysts in the medulla of the kidney.

label: Renotubular dysgenesis
definition: A developmental defect characterized by absence or poor development of proximal renal tubules.

label: Urethral stenosis
definition: Abnormal narrowing of the urethra.

label: Renal sarcoma
definition: A sarcoma of the kidney.

label: Clitoral hypertrophy
definition: Hypertrophy of the clitoris.

label: Gonadal dysgenesis, male
definition: Unusual gonadal development in a person with a 46,XY male karyotype, leading to an unassigned sex differentiation.

label: Calcium oxalate nephrolithiasis
definition: The presence of calcium- and oxalate-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

label: Congenital megaureter
definition: A developmental disturbance with extreme ureteral dilatation.

label: Congenital nephrotic syndrome
definition: Nephrotic syndrome with onset within the first three months of life.

label: Renal tubular epithelial necrosis
definition: Coagulative necrosis of tubular epithelial cells, defined as cells with increased cytoplasmic eosinophilia and nucleus that has a condensed chromatin pattern with fuzzy nuclear contour or has barely visible nuclear basophilic staining. The extent of cortical tubular necrosis is scoredsemiquantitatively as none, mild (less than 25% tubules with necrosis), moderate (25-50 percent), and severe (over 50%).

label: Renal necrosis
definition: Cell death (necrosis) affecting one or more parts of the kidney.

label: Enlarged labia minora
definition: Increase in size of the folds of skin between the outer labia.

label: Bilateral cryptorchidism
definition: Absence of both testes from the scrotum owing to failure of the testis or testes to descend through the inguinal canal to the scrotum.

label: Solitary bladder diverticulum
definition: Presence of a single diverticulum (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urinary bladder.

label: Hypoplasia of the fallopian tube
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the fallopian tube.

label: Gonadal calcification
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in gonadal tissue.

label: Absent scrotum
definition: Congenital absence of the scrotum.

label: Partial development of the penile shaft
Benign prostatic hyperplasia
definition: The presence of non-malignant hyperplasia of the prostate.

label: Urethrovaginal fistula
definition: The presence of a fistula between the vagina and the urethra.

label: Urethral fistula
definition: The presence of an abnormal connection between the urethra and another organ or the skin.

label: Unilateral renal atrophy
definition: A unilateral form of atrophy of the kidney.

label: Unilateral renal dysplasia
definition: A unilateral form of developmental dysplasia of the kidney.

label: Urethral diverticulum
definition: The presence of a diverticulum (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urethra.

label: Gonadal dysgenesis with female appearance, male
definition: Unusual gonadal development in a person with a 46,XY male karyotype, leading to a more female sex differentiation.

label: Hypoplasia of the ovary
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the ovary.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the ovary
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the ovary.

label: Hypoplasia of the vagina
definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the vagina.

label: Female external genitalia in individual with 46,XY karyotype
definition: The presence of female external genitalia in a person with a male karyotype.

label: Renal hypophosphatemia
definition: Renal hypophosphatemia is defined as reduced serum phosphate (e.g., below 0.70 mmol/l) and an inappropriately high renal phosphate excretion.

label: Decreased testicular size
definition: Reduced volume of the testicle (the male gonad).

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the testes
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the testes.

label: Partially duplicated kidney
definition: The presence of a partially duplicated kidney.

label: Longitudinal vaginal septum
definition: The presence of a longitudinal vaginal septum, thereby creating a vaginal duplication.

label: Coronal hypospadias
definition: A mild form of hypospadias in which the urethra opens just under the corona glandis.

label: Abnormal aryepiglottic fold morphology
definition: An abnormality of the aryepiglottic fold.

label: Cartilaginous ossification of larynx
definition: Ossification affecting the set of cartilages of larynx.

label: Laryngeal hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the larynx.

label: Laryngeal atresia
definition: Congenital absence of the lumen of the larynx. Laryngeal atresia is a rare condition. If the laryngeal opening fails to develop, fluid secreted by the lungs cannot be expelled. In a fetus with laryngeal atresia, the lungs are either normal or hyperplastic, not hypoplastic. Mortality is reported as 100%. At obstetric US examination, views of the fetal neck demonstrate a dilated trachea filled with trapped fluid. Views of the fetal chest show enlarged, hyperechoic lungs, with dilated fluid-filled bronchi. Fetal ascites is usually present.

label: Laryngeal cleft
definition: Presence of a gap in the posterior laryngotracheal wall with a continuity between the larynx and the esophagus.

label: Laryngeal cartilage malformation
definition: A malformation of the laryngeal cartilage.

label: Aplasia of the epiglottis
definition: Absence of the epiglottis.

label: Laryngeal calcification
definition: Calcification (abnormal deposits of calcium) in the laryngeal tissues.

label: Bowing of the vocal cords
definition: Bowing (abnormal curvature) of the vocal folds.

label: Abnormal vocal cord morphology
definition: An abnormality of the vocal cord.

label: Unilateral vocal cord paralysis
definition: A loss of the ability to move the vocal fold on one side.

label: Violent behavior
definition: Conduct and/or behavior, both verbal and non-verbal, including but not limited to verbal and/or physical aggression, attacks, threats, harassment, intimidation, and other disruptive behaviors in any form or through any medium, that cause or have the potential to cause a reasonable person to fear physical harm from any individual(s) or group(s) towards any person(s) or property. This is commonly defined as a violent act characterized by the use of physical force, anger, or sudden intense activity.

label: No social interaction
definition: Lack of intentional participation in interactions with another person.

label: Abnormal relationship
definition: The state of having abnormal relationships with others. This does not describe specific aspects of one's social aptitudes but rather a state which may come about from these aptitudes, such as lacking peer relationships, lacking close friends, or having a relational network that is abnormal given one's cultural context.

label: Auditory hallucination
definition: Perception of sounds without auditory stimulus.

label: Self-mutilation of tongue and lips due to involuntary movements
definition: Uncontrolled movements result in tissue damage to the tongue and lips.

label: Abnormal sexual behavior
definition: A deviation of sexual behaviors from the personal norms of the individual in the context of socially and culturally recognized patterns of human sexual behaviors.

label: Obsessive-compulsive trait
definition: The presence of one or more obsessive-compulsive personality traits. Obsessions refer to persistent intrusive thoughts, and compulsions to intrusive behaviors, which the affected person experiences as involuntary, senseless, or repugnant.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the ear
definition: The presence of aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the ear.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the middle ear
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of all or part of the middle ear.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the inner ear
definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the inner ear.

label: Abnormal intrarenal artery morphology
definition: An anomalous structure of an artery located in the kidney.

label: Wide proximal femoral metaphysis
definition: Increased width of the proximal part of the shaft (metaphysis) of the femur.

label: Wide capital femoral epiphyses
definition: Abnormally wide morphology of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Delayed ossification of pubic rami
definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of the rami (branches) of the pubic bone.

label: Abnormal ossification of the pubic bone
definition: Abnormal ossification (bone tissue formation) affecting the pubic bone, also known as the pubis.

label: Iliac crest serration
definition: Irregularities of the iliac crest that produce the appearance of a lace border around it.

label: Delayed pubic bone ossification
definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of the pubic bone.

label: Cone-shaped capital femoral epiphysis
definition: A cone-shaped deformity of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Dysplastic iliac wing
definition: A general term that describes a congenital defect in the iliac wing resulting from abnormal development.

label: Femoral retroversion
definition: An abnormal backward rotation of the hip relative to the knee such that the hips are externally rotated with the foot pointed outward instead of straight ahead (out-toeing).

label: Abnormal femoral torsion
definition: Femoral torsion, also known as femoral rotation or femoral version, refers to the twist between the proximal and distal parts of the femur on the transverse plane. Femoral anteversion averages between 30-40 degrees at birth, and between 8-14 degrees in adults. This term applies if the amount of femoral torsion deviates from this range.

label: Early ossification of capital femoral epiphyses
definition: Developmental acceleration of ossification of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Widened greater sciatic notch
definition: The sacroiliac joint in the bony pelvis connects the sacrum and the ilium of the pelvis, which are joined by strong ligaments. The notch is located directly superior to the joint. This term refers to a increase in the lateral dimension of the notch.

label: Hypoplasia of the lesser trochanter
definition: Underdevelopment of the lesser trochanter.

label: Hypoplasia of the femoral head
definition: Underdevelopment of the femoral head.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the femoral head and neck
Broad femoral head
definition: Increased width of the femoral head.

label: Acetabular dysplasia
definition: A smaller than normal acetabulum that has insufficient femoral head coverage leading to abnormal hip joint contact pressures, instability and pain.

label: High iliac wing
definition: Increased height of the wing (or ala) of the ilium (which is the large expanded portion which bounds the greater pelvis laterally).

label: Flattened femoral head
definition: An abnormally flattened femoral head.

label: Aplastic pubic bone
definition: A developmental defect characterized by lack of development of the pubis bone.

label: Large iliac wing
definition: Increased size of the ilium ala.

label: Narrow femoral neck
definition: An abnormally reduced diameter of the femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft).

label: Absent ossification of capital femoral epiphysis
definition: Lack of ossification of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Hypoplastic ischiopubic ramus
definition: Underdevelopment of the ischiopubic ramus, which is comprised of the inferior pubic ramus and the inferior ramus of the ischium.

label: Inferior pubic ramus hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the lower branch of the pubis bone (inferior pubic ramus).

label: Hypoplastic pubic ramus
definition: Underdevelopment of a ramus (branch) of the pubic bone.

label: Hypoplastic iliac body
definition: Underdevelopment of the body of ilium.

label: Delayed proximal femoral epiphyseal ossification
definition: Developmental delay of ossification of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Delayed femoral head ossification
definition: Delayed ossification of the femoral head.

label: Multicentric femoral head ossification
definition: There is normally one ossification center in the head of the femur. This term applies if there are multiple such centers.

label: Hypoplastic pelvis
definition: Underdevelopment of the bony pelvis.

label: Mesomelic short stature
definition: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by disproportionate shortening of the medial parts of the extremities (forearm or lower leg).

label: Disproportionate short-limb short stature
definition: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short limbs but an average-sized trunk.

label: Severe intrauterine growth retardation
definition: Intrauterine growth retardation that is 4 or more standard deviations below average, corrected for sex and gestational age.

label: Moderately short stature
definition: A moderate degree of short stature, more than -3 SD but not more than -4 SD from mean corrected for age and sex.

label: Severe postnatal growth retardation
definition: Severely slow or limited growth after birth, being four standard deviations or more below age- and sex-related norms.

label: Moderate postnatal growth retardation
definition: A moderate degree of slow or limited growth after birth, being between three and four standard deviations below age- and sex-related norms.

label: Neonatal short-trunk short stature
definition: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short trunk but a average-sized limbs with congenital onset recognizable at birth.

label: Failure to thrive secondary to recurrent infections
definition: Insufficient weight gain or inappropriate weight loss for a child, that is attributed to an endogenous recurrent infections.

label: Severe infection
definition: A type of infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection because of unusual severity or intensity of the infection.

label: Feeding difficulties
definition: Impaired ability to eat related to problems gathering food and getting ready to suck, chew, or swallow it.

label: Mild intrauterine growth retardation
definition: Intrauterine growth retardation that is at least 2 standard deviations (SD) below average, but not as low as 3 SD, corrected for sex and gestational age.

label: Childhood-onset truncal obesity
definition: Truncal obesity with onset during childhood, defined as between 2 and 10 years of age.

label: Neonatal short-limb short stature
definition: A type of short-limbed dwarfism that is manifest beginning in the neonatal period.

label: Childhood-onset short-trunk short stature
definition: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short trunk but a average-sized limbs with onset in childhood.

label: Generalized neonatal hypotonia
definition: Muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone) manifesting in the neonatal period and affecting the entire musculature.

label: Axial hypotonia
definition: Muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone) affecting the musculature of the trunk.

label: Generalized lymphadenopathy
definition: A generalized form of lymphadenopathy.

label: Acute rhabdomyolysis
definition: An acute form of rhabdomyolysis.

label: Distal lower limb amyotrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy of distal leg muscles.

label: Loss of ability to walk in early childhood
Pelvic girdle amyotrophy
definition: Atrophy of the muscles of the pelvic girdle (also known as hip girdle), i.e., the gluteal muscles, the lateral rotators, the adductors, the psoas major and the iliacus muscle.

label: Infantile muscular hypotonia
definition: Muscular hypotonia (abnormally low muscle tone) manifesting in infancy.

label: Proximal upper limb amyotrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy affecting proximally located muscles of the arms.

label: Shoulder muscle hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of muscles of the shoulder.

label: Hypoplasia of the musculature
definition: Underdevelopment of the musculature.

label: Pectoralis major hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the pectoralis major.

label: Intrinsic hand muscle atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the intrinsic muscle groups of the hand, comprising the thenar and hypothenar muscles; the interossei muscles; and the lumbrical muscles.

label: Progressive distal muscular atrophy
definition: Progressive muscular atrophy affecting muscles in the distal portions of the extremities.

label: Proximal lower limb amyotrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy affecting proximally located muscles of the legs, i.e., of the thigh.

label: Distal upper limb muscle weakness
definition: Reduced strength of the distal musculature of the arms.

label: Calf muscle hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the muscuklature of the calf.

label: Tibialis muscle weakness
definition: Muscle weakness affecting the tibialis anterior muscle.

label: Distal lower limb muscle weakness
definition: Reduced strength of the distal musculature of the legs.

label: Nonprogressive muscular atrophy
definition: Muscular atrophy that does not display a progression in severity with time.

label: Exercise-induced muscle stiffness
definition: A type of muscle stiffness that occurs following physical exertion.

label: Abnormal activity of mitochondrial respiratory chain
definition: An increased or decreased activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain.

label: Calf muscle hypertrophy
definition: Muscle hypertrophy affecting the calf muscles.

label: Neck muscle hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of muscles of the neck.

label: Increased intramuscular fat
definition: An abnormal increase in the amount of intramuscular fat tissue.

label: Agenesis of the diaphragm
definition: Congenital lack, i.e., aplasia of the diaphragm.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the diaphragm
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the diaphragm.

label: Exercise-induced leg cramps
definition: Sudden and involuntary contractions of one or more muscles of the leg brought on by physical exertion.

label: Increased intraabdominal fat
definition: An abnormal increase in the amount of intraabdominal fat tissue.

label: Proximal muscle weakness in upper limbs
definition: A lack of strength of the proximal muscles of the arms.

label: Pectoralis hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the pectoral muscle.

label: Loss of truncal subcutaneous adipose tissue
definition: Loss (reduction of previously present) of subcutaneous adipose tissue in the region of the trunk.

label: Increased subcutaneous truncal adipose tissue
definition: The presence of an abnormally increased amount of subcutaneous adipose tissue in the trunk of the body.

label: Weakness of the intrinsic hand muscles
Biceps hypoplasia
