label: Aplasia/hypoplasia of the 1st metatarsal
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the first metatarsal bone.

label: Broad first metatarsal
definition: Increased side-to-side width of the first metatarsal bone.

label: Bullet-shaped 1st metatarsal
definition: An abnormal morphology of the firstmetatarsal bone, which is short and wide and tapers distally, and lacks the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Curved 1st metatarsal
definition: A deviation from the normal straight shape of a proximal phalanx of the 1st metatarsal bone.

label: Osteolytic defects of the 1st metatarsal
definition: Dissolution or degeneration of bone tissue of the first metatarsal.

label: Patchy sclerosis of proximal toe phalanx
definition: Patchy (irregular) increase in bone density of one or more of the proximal phalanges of the toes. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

label: Duplication of the 1st metatarsal
definition: A developmental defect consisting in the duplication of the first metatarsal bone.

Broad distal phalanx of the hallux

label: Bullet-shaped distal phalanx of the hallux

label: Bullet-shaped distal toe phalanx

label: Bullet-shaped proximal phalanx of the hallux
definition: An abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the big toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped proximal toe phalanx
definition: An abnormal morphology of one or more of the proximal phalanges of the toes, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

This term applies to abnormalities of the epiphysis of the first metatarsal bone.

This term applies to abnormalities affecting the proximal phalanx of the hallux.

label: Bracket epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the hallux

label: Stippling of the epiphysis of the 1st metatarsal
Abnormality of the epiphyses of the feet
definition: Any abnormality of the epiphyses of the feet.

label: Phalangeal cone-shaped epiphyses
definition: Cone-shaped epiphyses of the phalanges of the hands or feet. Cone-shaped epiphyses (also known as coned epiphyses) are epiphyses that invaginate into cupped metaphyses. That is, the epiphysis has a cone-shaped distal extension resulting from increased growth of the central portion of the epiphysis relative to its periphery.

label: Sclerosis of toe phalanx
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Abnormality of toe proximal phalanx
definition: A morphological anomaly of one or more proximal phalanges of one or more toes.

label: Sclerosis of distal toe phalanx
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more distal phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Broad middle phalanges of the toes
Bullet-shaped middle toe phalanx
definition: An abnormal morphology of one or more middle phalanges of the toes, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Curved middle toe phalanx
definition: A deviation from the normal straight form of one or more middle toe phalanges.

label: Sclerosis of middle toe phalanx
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more middle phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Aplasia/hypoplasia of proximal toe phalanx
definition: Absence (agenesis) or underdevelopment of the proximal phalanx of the toe.

label: Osteolytic defect of the proximal toe phalanx
definition: Dissolution or degeneration of bone tissue of the proximal toe phalanx.

label: Sclerosis of proximal toe phalanx
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more proximal phalanges of the toes. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Symphalangism affecting the proximal phalanges of the toes
Triangular shaped proximal phalanges of the toes
Duplication of proximal phalanx of toe
definition: Partial/complete duplication of a proximal phalanx of toe.

label: Flexion contracture of the hallux
definition: One or more bent (flexed) joints of the first (big) toe that cannot be straightened actively or passively.

label: Contracture of the tarsometatarsal joint of the hallux
definition: Chronic loss of joint motion in the tarsometatarsal joint of the hallux due to structural changes in non-bony tissue. The tarsometatarsal joints of the feet are also called Lisfranc's joints.

label: Contracture of the interphalangeal joint of the hallux
definition: The interphalangeal joint of the big toe cannot be straightened actively or passively.

label: Contractures of the metatarsophalangeal joint of the hallux
definition: The joint between the first metatarsal and the proximal phalanx of the first (big) toe cannot be straightened actively or passively.

label: Structural foot deformity
definition: A foot deformity resulting due to an abnormality affecting the bones of the foot (as well as muscle and soft tissue). In contrast if only the muscle and soft tissue are affected the term positional foot deformity applies.

label: Abnormal 3rd metacarpal epiphysis morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the epiphysis of the third metacarpal bone.

label: Pseudoepiphysis of the 3rd metacarpal
definition: The normal epiphysis of the third metacarpal is localized at the distal end of the metacarpal bone. This term applies if an accessory epiphysis, located at the proximal end of the metacarpal bone, is present.

label: Abnormal 4th metacarpal epiphysis morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the epiphysis of the 4th metacarpal bone.

label: Pseudoepiphysis of the 4th metacarpal
definition: The normal epiphysis of the fourth metacarpal is localized at the distal end of the metacarpal bone. This term applies if an accessory epiphysis, located at the proximal end of the metacarpal bone, is present.

label: Abnormal 5th metacarpal epiphysis morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the epiphysis of the fifth metacarpal bone.

label: Pseudoepiphysis of the 5th metacarpal
definition: The normal epiphysis of the fifth metacarpal is localized at the distal end of the metacarpal bone. This term applies if an accessory epiphysis, located at the proximal end of the metacarpal bone, is present.

label: Stomatitis
definition: Stomatitis is an inflammation of the mucous membranes of any of the structures in the mouth.

label: Cleft lower lip
definition: A gap in the lower lip.

label: Thin lower lip vermilion
definition: Height of the vermilion of the medial part of the lower lip more than 2 SD below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently reduced height of the vermilion of the lower lip in the frontal view (subjective).

label: Intra-oral hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased pigmentation, either focal or generalized, of the mucosa of the mouth.

label: Abnormal pigmentation of the oral mucosa
definition: An abnormality of the pigmentation of the mucosa of the mouth.

label: Oral synechia
definition: Fibrous band between the mucosal surfaces of the upper and lower alveolar ridges.

label: Abnormality of the submandibular glands
definition: Any abnormality of the submandibular glands, which are the salivary glands that are located beneath the floor of the mouth, superior to the digastric muscles.

label: Abnormality of the sublingual glands
definition: Any abnormality of the sublingual glands, which are the salivary glands that are located beneath the floor of the mouth anterior to the submandibular glands.

label: Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge
definition: A gap (cleft) affecting one of the alveolar ridges, which are the protuberances in the mouth that contain the sockets (alveoli) of the teeth. An alveolar cleft can affect all structures of the alveolar ridge, including the gingiva, other mucosa, periosteum, alveolar bone, and teeth. Alveolar cleft occurs in response to divergence from normal development during frontonasal prominence growth, contact, and fusion. The most common alveolar portion of the cleft is located between the lateral incisor and the canine.

label: Short hard palate
definition: Distance between the labial point of the incisive papilla to the midline junction of the hard and soft palate more than 2 SD below the mean (objective) or apparently decreased length of the hard palate (subjective).

label: Prominent palatine ridges
definition: Increased size and/or number of soft tissue folds on the palatal side of the maxillary alveolar ridge.

label: Absent uvula
definition: Lack of the uvula.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the uvula
definition: Underdevelopment or absence of the uvula.

label: Palate fistula
definition: A fistula which connects the oral cavity and the pharyngeal area via the aspects of the soft palate.

label: Ankyloglossia
definition: Short or anteriorly attached lingual frenulum, associated with limited mobility of the tongue.

label: Bifid tongue
definition: Tongue with a median apical indentation or fork.

label: Smooth tongue
definition: Glossy appearance of the entire tongue surface.

label: Abnormally low-pitched voice
definition: A persistent (minutes to hours) abnormal decrease in the pitch of the voice for the context or social situation or significantly different from the baseline of the individual.

label: Neural tube defect
definition: A neural tube defect arises when the neural tube, the embryonic precursor of the brain and spinal cord, fails to close during neurulation. The cranial region (anencephaly) or the low spine (open spina bifida; myelomeningocele) are most commonly affected although, in the severe NTD craniorachischisis, almost the entire neural tube remains open, from midbrain to low spine.

label: Neoplasm of the central nervous system
definition: A neoplasm of the central nervous system.

label: Spinal meningeal diverticulum
definition: An outpouching of the spinal meninges.

label: Absence of the sacrum
definition: Absence (aplasia) of the sacrum.

label: Short thorax
definition: Reduced inferior to superior extent of the thorax.

label: Abnormal breath sound
definition: An anomalous (adventitious) sound produced by the breathing process.

label: Asternia
definition: The congenital absence of the sternum.

label: Bifid sternum
definition: The sternal cleft is a rare congenital anomaly resulting from a fusion failure of the sternum.

label: Chylothorax
definition: Accumulation of excessive amounts of lymphatic fluid (chyle) in the pleural cavity.

label: Asymmetry of the breasts
definition: The presence of asymmetrical breasts.

label: Breast hypertrophy
definition: The presence of hypertrophy of the breast.

label: Premature thelarche
definition: Premature development of the breasts.

label: Ebstein anomaly of the tricuspid valve
definition: Ebstein's anomaly refers to an abnormally placed and deformed tricuspid valve characterized by apical displacement of the septal and posterior tricuspid valve leaflets, leading to atrialization of the right ventricle with a variable degree of malformation and displacement of the anterior leaflet.

label: Scapular aplasia

label: Ectopic accessory toe-like appendage
definition: In contrast to forms of polydactyly where the supernumerary digit (this can either be a rudimentary or a completely 'normal' digit) is either located postaxial (on the fibular side of the foot, next top the little toe), preaxial (on the tibial side of the foot, next to the big toe) or mesoaxial (somewhere central, between big and little toe), a supernumerary digit may also be placed ectopically, meaning anywhere else except post-,meso- or preaxial. In the literature this is sometimes referred to as Disorganisation-like Syndrome (OMIM223200).

label: Ectopic accessory finger-like appendage
definition: In contrast to forms of polydactyly where the supernumerary digit (this can either be a rudimentary or a completely 'normal' digit) is either located postaxial (on the ulnar side of the hand, next to the little finger), preaxial (on the radial side of the hand, next to the thumb) or mesoaxial (somewhere central, between thumb and little finger), a supernumerary digit may also be placed ectopically, meaning anywhere else except post-,meso- or preaxial. In the literature this is sometimes referred to as Disorganisation-like Syndrome (OMIM223200).

label: Bifid femur
definition: A bifid or bifurcated appearance of the femur as seen on x-rays, possible appearing as a more or less severe bowing of the upper leg. Might be associated with hip dysplasia on the affected side.

label: Pulmonic regurgitation
definition: The retrograde (backwards) flow of blood through the pulmonary valve into the right ventricle during diastole.

label: Primum atrial septal defect
definition: An ostium primum atrial septal defect is located in the most anterior and inferior aspect of the atrial septum. The ostium primum refers to an anterior and inferior opening (ostium) within the septum primum, which divides the rudimentary atrium during fetal development. The ostium primum is normally sealed by fusion of the superior and inferior endocardial cushions around 5 weeks' gestation. Ostium primum defects result from a failure of the fusion of the embryologic endocardial cushion and septum primum.

label: Tricuspid stenosis
definition: A narrowing of the orifice of the tricuspid valve of the heart.

label: Intestinal fistula
definition: An abnormal connection between the gut and another hollow organ, such as the bladder, urethra, vagina, or other regions of the gastrointestinal tract.

label: Colonic atresia
definition: A developmental defect resulting in complete obliteration of the lumen of the colon. That is, there is an abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the colon.

label: Ectopia of the spleen
definition: An abnormal (non-anatomic) location of the spleen.

label: Pelvic bone asymmetry
definition: Pelvic asymmetry refers to asymmetric positioning of landmarks on the two sides of the pelvis and may have a structural or functional etiology.

label: Acetabular spurs
definition: The presence of osteophytes (bone spurs), i.e., of bony projections originating from the acetabulum.

label: Steep acetabular roof
definition: An exaggeration of the normal arched form of the acetabular roof such that it takes on a steep appearance.

label: Female pseudohermaphroditism
definition: Hermaphroditism refers to a discrepancy between the morphology of the gonads and that of the external genitalia. In female pseudohermaphroditism, the genotype is female (XX) and the gonads are ovaries, but the external genitalia are virilized.

label: True hermaphroditism
definition: The presence of both ovarian and testicular tissues either in the same or in opposite gonads. Affected persons have ambiguous genitalia and may have 46,XX or 46,XY karyotypes or 46,XX/XY mosaicism.

label: Aplasia of the ovary
definition: Aplasia, that is failure to develop, of the ovary.

label: Streak ovary
definition: A developmental disorder characterized by the progressive loss of primordial germ cells in the developing ovaries of an embryo, leading to hypoplastic ovaries composed of wavy connective tissue with occasional clumps of granulosa cells, and frequently mesonephric or hilar cells.

label: Precocious puberty in females
definition: The onset of puberty before the age of 8 years in girls.

label: Absent testis
definition: Testis not palpable in the scrotum or inguinal canal.

label: Supernumerary testes
definition: The presence of more than two testes.

label: Oligosacchariduria
definition: Increased urinary excretion of oligosaccharides (low molecular weight carbohydrate chains composed of at least three monosaccharide subunits), derived from a partial degradation of glycoproteins.

label: Abnormal urine carbohydrate level
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carbohydrate in the urine.

label: Abnormal circulating porphyrin concentration
definition: An abnormality in the synthesis or catabolism of heme. Heme is composed of ferrous iron and protoporphyrin IX and is an essential molecule as the prosthetic group of hemeproteins such as hemoglobin, myoglobin, mitochondrial and microsomal cytochromes.

label: Porphyrinuria
definition: Abnormally increased excretion of porphyrins in the urine.

label: Bladder stones
definition: Buildups of minerals that form in the urinary bladder.

label: Cloacal exstrophy
definition: Cloacal exstrophy is a severe anterior abdominal wall defect in which the two hemibladders are visible and are separated by a midline intestinal plate, an omphalocele, and an imperforate anus.

label: Cloacal abnormality
definition: A developmental anomaly associated with the failure of rectum, vagina, and bladder to separate.

label: Aplasia of the bladder
definition: Aplasia (absence) of the urinary bladder.

label: Abnormality of the urachus
definition: Abnormality of the urachus.

label: Patent urachus
definition: Persistence of the urachal canal resulting in a canal between the bladder and the umbilicus.

label: Urethral valve
definition: The presence of an abnormal membrane obstructing the urethra.

label: Acromelia of the upper limbs
definition: Shortening of the arms predominantly affecting terminal parts of the arm in relation to the upper and middle limb segments.

label: Acromelia
definition: Shortening of the extremities affecting primarily the distal parts of the limbs (hands and feet) in relation to the other segments of the limbs.

label: Amniotic constriction rings of arms
definition: Amniotic constriction rings affecting the arms.

label: Hypertrophy of the upper limb
definition: Abnormal increase in size of the upper limbs (due to an increase of the size of cells).

label: Hyperextensibility at elbow
definition: The ability of the elbow joint to move beyond its normal range of motion.

label: Abnormality of the hypothenar eminence
definition: An abnormality of the hypothenar eminence, i.e., of the muscles on the ulnar side of the palm of the hand (i.e., on the side of the little finger).

label: Small hypothenar eminence
definition: Reduced muscle mass on the ulnar side of the palm, that is, reduction in size of the hypothenar eminence.

label: Absent palmar crease
definition: The absence of the major creases of the palm (distal transverse crease, proximal transverse crease, or thenar crease).

label: Digital constriction ring
definition: A narrow segment of significantly reduced circumference of a digit.

label: Long metacarpals
definition: An abnormally increased length of the metacarpal bones.

label: Acromelia of the lower limbs
definition: Shortening of the legs predominantly affecting terminal parts of the leg in relation to the upper and middle arm segments.

label: Amniotic constriction rings of legs
definition: Amniotic constriction rings affecting the legs.

label: Hypertrophy of the lower limb
definition: Abnormal increase in size of the lower limbs (due to an increase of the size of cells).

label: Sirenomelia
definition: A developmental defect in which the legs are fused together.

label: Bipartite patella
definition: A developmental defect that occurs if the two halves of the patella fail to fuse in early childhood.

label: Patellar subluxation
definition: The kneecap normally is located within the groove termed trochlea on the distal femur and can slide up and down in it. Patellar subluxation refers to an unstable kneecap that does not slide centrally within its groove, i.e., a partial dislocation of the patella.

label: Fibular bowing
definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of the fibula.

label: Fibular duplication
definition: Duplication of the fibula. This may occur as a part of diplopodia (accessory tarsal or metatarsal bone). Diplopodia with double fibula is an extremely rare condition.

label: Increased length of the tibia
definition: An abnormal increase in the length of the tibia.

label: Limitation of movement at ankles
definition: An abnormal limitation of the mobility of the ankle joint.

label: Abnormal plantar dermatoglyphics
definition: An abnormality of dermatoglyphs on the toes and soles, i.e., an abnormality of the patterns of ridges of the skin of sole of foot.

label: Foot asymmetry
definition: A difference in size or shape between the left and right foot.

label: Metatarsus valgus
definition: A condition in which the anterior part of the foot rotates outward away from the midline of the body and the heel remains straight.

label: Aplasia of the tarsal bones
definition: Absence of the tarsal bones.

label: Hypermobility of toe joints
definition: An ability of the toe joints to move beyond their normal range of motion.

label: Adrenal calcification
definition: Calcification within the adrenal glands.

label: Pituitary calcification
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in the pituitary gland.

label: Thymus hyperplasia
definition: Enlargement of the thymus.

label: Ectopic thymus tissue
definition: The presence of ectopic thymus tissue. Normally, cells of the ventral bud of the third pharyngeal pouch detach and migrate in the eighth gestational week caudally and medially towards the location of the mature thyroid. They migrate further retrosternally into the superior mediastinum. There are two main ways ectopic thymus tissue can develop. Either cells detach along the descensus path and proliferate, thereby forming accessory thymus tissue, or the entire gland fails to descend.

label: Thyroglossal cyst
definition: An abnormality of the thyroid gland owing to the presence of a fibrous cyst resulting from the persistence of the thyroglossal duct.

label: Increased fetal movement
definition: An abnormal increase in quantity or strength of fetal movements.

label: Gait apraxia
definition: Gait apraxia affecting the ability to make walking movements with the legs.

label: Dyslexia
definition: A learning disorder characterized primarily by difficulties in learning to read and spell. Dyslectic children also exhibit a tendency to read words from right to left and to confuse letters such as b and d whose orientation is important for their identification. Children with dyslexia appear to be impaired in phonemic skills (the ability to associate visual symbols with the sounds they represent).

label: Alexia
definition: An acquired type of sensory aphasia where damage to the brain leads to the loss of the ability to read.

label: Disturbed sensory perception
definition: Alteration or impairment in the processing or interpretation of sensory information can lead to abnormal perceptions or experiences.

label: Disturbed perception with a stimulus
definition: A perceptual experience in which an individual's perception of sensory stimuli is altered or disrupted in some way, resulting in abnormal or distorted sensory perceptions despite the presence of actual external stimuli.

label: Finger agnosia
definition: The examiner identified the inability to name, move, or touch specific fingers.

label: Dysgraphia
definition: A writing disability in the absence of motor or sensory deficits of the upper extremities, resulting in an impairment in the ability to write regardless of the ability to read and not due to intellectual impairment.

label: Astereognosis
definition: Tactile agnosia refers to the inability to recognize objects by touch, while the inability to discriminate shape and size by touch is also a related condition.

label: Tactile agnosia
definition: The inability to recognize objects by touch is called tactile agnosia.

label: Prosopagnosia
definition: Inability to recognize faces of familiar persons.

label: Echolalia
definition: Echolalia is the automatic imitative repetition of sounds, words, or phrases in the absence of explicit awareness. The repeated words or phrases are typically odd or used in a non-social manner. These can be words or phrases that the affected individual has heard or invented.

label: Involuntary vocalization
definition: Production of sound done without will or conscious control. Involuntary vocalizations include tics, stereotypies vocalizations as part of dystonia or chorea, continuous vocalizing behaviors such as groaning or grunting, pathological laughter and crying, and others. These vocalizations are not recognized as socially or culturally appropriate.

label: Palatal tremor
definition: Palatal tremor (PT) is an involuntary, rhythmic and oscillatory movement of the soft palate. PT is a rare type of tremor involving the soft palate. It can be unilateral or bilateral.

label: Spinal myoclonus
definition: Spinal myoclonus is generally due to a tumor, infection, injury, or degenerative process of the spinal cord, and is characterized by involuntary rhythmic muscle contractions, usually at a rate of more than one per second. Myoclonus occurs synchronously in several muscles and can be increased in severity and frequency by fatigue or stress, but is usually unaffected by sensory stimuli. Spinal myoclonus ceases during sleep or anesthesia.

label: Paroxysmal vertigo
definition: Paroxysmal episodes of vertigo.

label: Spasmus nutans
definition: The combination of pendular nystagmus, head nodding, and torticollis.

label: Transient global amnesia
definition: A paroxysmal, transient loss of memory function with preservation of immediate recall and remote memory but with a severe impairment of memory for recent events and ability to retain new information.

label: Sleep-related breathing disorders
definition: Conditions of abnormal and difficult respiration during sleep, including chronic snoring and sleep apnea.

label: Central sleep apnea
definition: Sleep apnea results from a temporary loss of the central drive to the muscles responsible for breathing.

label: Small sella turcica
definition: An abnormally small sella turcica.

label: Thin calvarium
definition: The presence of an abnormally thin calvarium.

label: Advanced pneumatization of cranial sinuses
definition: A degree of pneumatization that is increased compared to age-related norms.

label: Cutis gyrata of scalp
definition: The presence of convoluted folds and furrows formed from thickened skin of the scalp, resembling cerebriform pattern. The scalp has convoluted and elevated folds, 1 to 2 cm in thickness. The convolutions generally cannot be flattened by traction.

label: Vestibular nystagmus
definition: Nystagmus due to disturbance of the vestibular system; eye movements are rhythmic, with slow and fast components.

label: Opsoclonus
definition: Bursts of large-amplitude multidirectional saccades without intersaccadic interval

label: Saccadic oscillation
definition: An involuntary abnormality of fixation in which there is an abnormal saccade away from fixation followed by an immediate corrective saccade.

label: Vertical nystagmus
definition: Vertical nystagmus may present with either up-beating or down-beating eye movements or both. When present in the straight-ahead position of gaze it is referred to as upbeat nystagmus or downbeat nystagmus.

label: Downbeat nystagmus
definition: Downbeat nystagmus is a type of fixation nystagmus with the fast phase beating in a downward direction. It generally increases when looking to the side and down and when lying prone.

label: Oculogyric crisis
definition: An acute dystonic reaction with blepharospasm, periorbital twitches, and protracted fixed staring episodes. There may be a maximal upward deviation of the eyes in the sustained fashion. Oculogyric crisis can be triggered by a number of factors including neuroleptic medications.

label: Cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two digits that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints, or a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two digits that lies significantly distal to the flexion crease that overlies the metacarpophalangeal or metatarsophalangeal joint of the adjacent digits.

label: Overlapping fingers
definition: A finger resting on the dorsal surface of an adjacent digit when the hand is at rest.

label: Abnormality of the clivus
definition: An abnormality of the clivus, which is the inclined bony region of the posterior cranial fossa located between the sella turcica and the foramen magnum.

label: Vertical clivus
definition: An abnormal vertical orientation of the clivus (which normally forms a kind of slope from the sella turcica down to the region of the foramen magnum).

label: Undulate clavicles
definition: An abnormally wavy surface or edge of the clavicles.

label: Undulate ribs
definition: An abnormally wavy surface or edge of the ribs.

label: Bifid epiglottis
definition: A midline anterior-posterior cleft of the epiglottis that involves at least two-thirds of the epiglottic leaf. It is a useful feature for clinical diagnosis because it appears to be very rare in syndromes other than Pallister-Hall-Syndrome and is also rare as an isolated malformation.

label: Y-shaped metatarsals
definition: Y-shaped metatarsals are the result of a partial fusion of two metatarsal bones, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Y-shaped metatarsals may be seen in combination with polydactyly.

label: Hamartoma of the orbital region
definition: A hamartoma (disordered proliferation of mature tissues) which can originate from any tissue of the orbital region.

label: Elevated circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
definition: Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
definition: Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal.

label: Low maternal circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
definition: An abnormally low concentration of serum alpha-fetoprotein as compared to normal values for gestational-age.

label: Elevated circulating phytanic acid concentration
definition: An abnormal elevation of phytanic acid.

label: Abnormal circulating phytanic acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of phytanic acid in the blood circulation.

label: Dysplasia of the femoral head
definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the femoral head.

label: Central nervous system cyst
definition: A fluid-filled sac (cyst) located within the central nervous system.

label: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion
definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at each end of a long bone, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

label: Abnormality of the distal tibial epiphysis
Abnormality of the proximal fibular epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the fibula.

label: Abnormality of the distal fibular epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the fibula.

label: Abnormality of the proximal humeral epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the humerus.

label: Abnormality of the distal humeral epiphysis
definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the humerus.

label: Abnormal proximal ulnar epiphysis morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the ulna.

label: Type 2 muscle fiber predominance
definition: An abnormal predominance of type II muscle fibers (in general, this feature can only be observed on muscle biopsy).

label: Odontogenic keratocysts of the jaw
definition: A benign uni- or multicystic, intraosseous tumor of odontogenic origin, with a characteristic lining of parakeratinized stratified squamous epithelium and potential for aggressive, infiltrative behavior.

label: Odontogenic neoplasm
definition: Neoplasm involving odontogenic cells, an odontogenic tumor.

label: Epidermoid cyst
definition: Nontender, round and firm, but slightly compressible, intradermal or subcutaneous cyst measuring 0.5-5 cm in diameter. Epidermal cysts are intradermal or subcutaneous tumors, grow slowly and occur on the face, neck, back and scrotum. They usually appear at or around puberty, and as a rule an affected individual has one solitary or a few cysts.

label: Chalazion
definition: A chronic epithelioid cell granulomatous inflammation of the meibomian gland caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland. A chalazion or meibomian cyst appears as a painless tuberous swelling in the upper lid without loss of eyelashes.

label: Hordeolum
definition: An acute purulent infection of the sebaceous glands of Zeis at the base of the eyelashes, of the apocrine sweat glands of Moll or the meibomian sebacious glands often caused by staphylococcus infections. Hordeola can either occur as Hordeola externa affecting the sebaceous glands of Zeis or the apocrine sweat glands of Moll or as Hordeola interna affecting the meibomian sebacious glands. In contrast to chalazia, hordeola are extremely painful and can cause extreme local swelling.

label: Hordeolum externum
definition: Hordeola externa are acute purulent infections affecting the sebaceous glands of Zeis or the apocrine sweat glands of Moll, often caused by staphylococcus infections. In contrast to chalazia, hordeola are extremely painfull and can cause extreme local swelling.

label: Hordeolum internum
definition: Hordeola interna are acute purulent infections affecting the meibomian sebacious glands, often caused by staphylococcus infections. In contrast to chalazia (chronic epithelioid cell granulomatous inflammation of the meibomian gland caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland), hordeola are extremely painfull and can cause extreme local swelling.

label: Skin pit
definition: A small, skin-lined tract that leads from the surface to deep within the tissues.

label: Plantar pits
definition: The presence of multiple pits (small, pinpoint-large indentations on the surface of the skin) located on the skin of sole of foot.

label: Fibrous tissue neoplasm
definition: Any neoplasm composed of fibrous tissue.

label: Lung fibroma
definition: The presence of a lung fibroma, a benign neoplasm that can present as a mass causing airway obstruction, cough, and hemoptysis, or present without symptoms as a solitary pulmonary nodule.

label: Neoplasm of the lung
definition: Tumor of the lung.

label: Cardiac fibroma
definition: A fibroma of the heart.

label: Ovarian fibroma
definition: The presence of a fibroma of the ovary.

label: Fibroadenoma of the breast
definition: A benign biphasic tumor of the breast with epithelial and stromal components.

label: Malar prominence
definition: Prominence of the malar process of the maxilla and infraorbital area appreciated in profile and from in front of the face.

label: Anterior pituitary dysgenesis
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the anterior pituitary gland, also known as the adenohypophysis.

label: Anterior pituitary agenesis
definition: Absence of the anterior pituitary gland resulting from a developmental defect.

label: Anterior pituitary hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the anterior pituitary gland.

label: Abnormal seventh cranial physiology
definition: Abnormality of the seventh cranial nerve sometimes also referred to as the facial nerve.

label: Total anosmia
definition: Inability to detect any qualitative olfactory sensation.

label: Partial anosmia
definition: Inability to perceive certain odorants (implies that the sense of smell is maintained for other classes of odorants).

label: Total hyposmia
definition: Reduced ability to detect any qualitative olfactory sensation.

label: Partial hyposmia
definition: Reduced ability to perceive certain odorants (implies that the sense of smell is maintained for other classes of odorants).

label: Schizencephaly
definition: The presence of a cleft in the cerebral cortex unilaterally or bilaterally, usually located in the frontal area.

label: Conjunctival amyloidosis
definition: A form of amyloidosis that affects the conjunctiva.

label: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of hepatic origin
definition: An abnormally increased level of liver isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

label: Elevated tissue non-specific alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

label: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of bone origin
definition: An abnormally increased level of bone isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

label: Abnormal nasal cavity morphology
definition: Abnormality of the nasal cavity (the cavity includes and starts at the nares and reaches all the way through to the and includes the choanae, the posterior nasal apertures).

label: Abnormality of the midnasal cavity
definition: Abnormality of the midnasal cavity which includes the cavity between the nares and the choanae.

label: Midnasal atresia
definition: Absence or abnormal closure of the midnasal cavity.

label: Midnasal stenosis
definition: Abnormal narrowing (stenosis) of the midnasal cavity, i.e., of the middle nasal meatus, which in neonates can cause respiratory distress.

label: Cervical spine instability
definition: An abnormal lack of stability of the cervical spine.

label: Dermal translucency
definition: An abnormally increased ability of the skin to permit light to pass through (translucency) such that subcutaneous structures such as veins display an increased degree of visibility.

label: Flat nasal alae
definition: An abnormal degree of flatness of the Ala of nose, which can be defined as a reduced nasal elevation index (lateral depth of the nose from the tip of the nose to the insertion of the nasal ala in the cheek x 100 divided by the side-to-side breadth of the nasal alae).

label: Hypoplasia of the premaxilla
definition: An abnormality of the premaxilla (the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla) causing it to appear relatively small in size compared to the other parts of the maxilla or other facial structures.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the premaxilla
definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the premaxilla.

label: Aplasia of the falx cerebri
definition: A developmental defect characterized by aplasia of the Falx cerebri.

label: Patchy reduction of bone mineral density
definition: Patchy (irregular) reduction in bone density. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

label: Patchy variation in bone mineral density
definition: Patchy (irregular) changes in bone mineral density with patches of bone showing an increased density side to side with patches that are affected by reduction of mineral density. This is sometimes referred to as a moth-eaten appearance on x-rays.

label: Absence of the third cerebral ventricle
definition: A developmental defect characterized by the absence of the third ventricle.

label: Abnormal diencephalon morphology
definition: An abnormality of the Diencephalon, which together with the cerebrum (telencephalon) makes up the forebrain.

label: Abnormal thalamus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the thalamus.

label: Fusion of the left and right thalami
definition: A developmental defect characterized by fusion of the left and right halves of the thalamus.

label: Bilateral coxa valga
definition: The presence of bilateral coxa valga.

label: Hypoplasia of the anterior nasal spine
definition: Underdevelopment of the anterior nasal spine of maxilla.

label: Aplasia of the maxilla
definition: A congenital defect characterized by absence of the Maxilla.

label: Enuresis nocturna
definition: Enuresis occurring during sleeping hours.

label: Enuresis diurna
definition: Enuresis occurring during waking hours of the day.

label: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of renal origin
definition: An abnormally increased level of kidney isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

label: Elevated intestinal alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, intestinal type in the blood.

label: Elevated placental alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, placental type in the blood.

label: Low tissue non-specific alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

label: Low alkaline phosphatase of bone origin
definition: An abnormally reduced level of bone isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood.

label: Low alkaline phosphatase of renal origin
definition: An abnormally reduced level of kidney isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood.

label: Low alkaline phosphatase of hepatic origin
definition: An abnormally reduced level of liver isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood.

label: Low intestinal alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, intestinal type in the blood.

label: Low placental alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, placental type in the blood.

label: Mirror image polydactyly
definition: A hand or foot with more than five digits that has a recognizable A/P axis of symmetry. The axis can lie within a normally formed or partially duplicated digit resembling a middle finger, index finger, thumb, toe, or hallux. Alternatively, the axis can be in an interdigital space with a flanking pair of digits that resemble a middle finger, index finger, thumb, toe or hallux. The most lateral digits on each side of the hand/foot typically resemble fifth fingers/toes.

label: Mirror image hand polydactyly
definition: Mirror image duplication of digits affecting the hands only.

label: Mirror image foot polydactyly
definition: Mirror image duplication of digits affecting the feet.

label: Lamellar pulverulent cataract
definition: A Lamellar cataract with a pulverulent (punctate, dust-like" opacities) appearance."

label: Anterior pyramidal cataract
definition: A type of anterior polar cataract which projects as a conical opacity into the anterior chamber.

label: Nuclear pulverulent cataract
definition: A type of nuclear cataract involving congenital dust-like (pulverulent) opacity of the embryonal and fetal nucleus.

label: Triangular nuclear cataract
definition: A nuclear cataract with a triangular form.

label: 1-2 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the thumb to the index finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: 4-5 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the fourth (ring) to the fifth (little) finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: 1-3 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the thumb to the middle finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: 1-4 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the thumb to the ring finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: 1-5 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the thumb to the little finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints (complete syndactyly of all fingers of the hand).

label: 2-4 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the second (index) to the fourth (ring) finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: 3-5 finger syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the middle to little fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: 1-2 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes one and two.

label: 1-4 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes one to four.

label: 1-5 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes one to five (complete syndactyly of all toes of the foot).

label: 2-4 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes two to four.

label: 2-5 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes two to five.

label: 3-5 toe syndactyly
definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes three to five.

label: Osseous syndactyly of toes
definition: Webbing or fusion of the toes, involving soft parts and including fusion of individual bones of the toes. Bony fusions are referred to as bony" Syndactyly if the fusion occurs in a tibial-fibular axis. Fusions of bones of the toes in a proximo-distal axis are referred to as "Symphalangism"."

label: Abnormal hair pattern
definition: An abnormality of the distribution of hair growth.

label: Asymmetry of the ears
definition: An asymmetriy, i.e., difference in size, shape or position between the left and right ear.

label: Advanced pneumatization of the mastoid process
definition: An abnormally advanced degree of pneumatization (i.e., formation of air cells) in the mastoid process with respect to age-dependent norms.

label: Prominent corneal nerve fibers
definition: Abnormal prominence of the corneal nerve fibers.

label: Spontaneous rupture of the globe
definition: Rupture of the eyeball not due to trauma.

label: Aplasia of the retina
definition: A developmental defect characterized by absence of the retina.

label: Cherry red spot of the macula
definition: Pallor of the perifoveal macula of the retina with appearance of a small circular reddish choroid shape as seen through the fovea centralis due to relative transparency of the macula.

label: Double eyebrow
definition: This may present as a partial or complete duplication of the eyebrows.

label: Extension of eyebrows towards upper eyelid
definition: The eyebrows extend towards - or even all the way down to - the margin of the upper eyelid.

label: Naevus flammeus of the eyelid
definition: Naevus flammeus localized in the skin of the eyelid.

label: Fibrous dysplasia of the bones
definition: Tumor-like growths that consist of replacement of the medullary bone with fibrous tissue, causing the expansion and weakening of the areas of bone involved. Especially when involving the skull or facial bones, the lesions can cause externally visible deformities. The skull is often, but not necessarily, affected, and any other bone or bones may be involved. Fibrous dysplasia can either effect isolated bones (Monostotic fibrous dysplasia) or also generalized all bones of the body (Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia).

label: Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia
definition: Fibrous dysplasia of the bones were lesions are localized in many bones throughout of the body. Polyostotic fibrous dysplasia is a cardinal feature of McCune-Albright syndrome.

label: Monostotic fibrous dysplasia
definition: Fibrous dysplasia of the bones were lesions are localized in only one bone.

label: Osteopoikilosis
definition: Osteopoikilosis is a benign, asymptomatic sclerotic dysplasia of the bones. It affects both male and female and may be seen at any age. Radiographically sclerotic circular or ovoid lesions are usually symmetrically distributed in a periarticular location. Lesions can increase or decrease in size and number in serial radiographs or even disappear and do not have increased bone radiotracer uptake.

label: Osteopathia striata
definition: A lamellar pattern visible on radiographs and mainly localized at the metaphyses of the long tubular bones. Pathologic-anatomical studies revealed that these benign signs on x-rays are the result of a juvenile metaphyseal bone necrosis. Calcifications in the necrotic marrow lead to this lamellar or lattice-like appearance.

label: Metaphyseal striations
definition: Longitudinal densities on radiographs located in a metaphysis (the narrow region of a long bone between the epiphysis and the diaphysis).

label: Pedal edema
definition: An abnormal accumulation of excess fluid in the lower extremity resulting in swelling of the feet and extending upward to the lower leg.

label: Edema of the upper limbs
definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin of the arms.

label: Medial flaring of the eyebrow
definition: An abnormal distribution of eyebrow hair growth in the medial direction.

label: Ectopic lacrimal punctum
definition: Positioning of a lacrimal punctum other than at the medial margins of the eyelid.

label: Blepharochalasis
definition: Blepharochalasis is characterized by recurrent, non-painful, nonerythematous episodes of eyelid edema. It has been divided into hypertrophic and atrophic forms. In the hypertrophic form recurrent edema results in orbital fat herniation through a weakened orbital septum. Most patients who have blepharochalasis present in an atrophic condition with atrophy of redundant eyelid skin and superior nasal fat pads.

label: Palpebral edema
definition: Edema in the region of the eyelids.

label: Dermatochalasis
definition: Loss of elasticity of the upper and lower eyelids causing the skin to sag and bulge.

label: Dimple chin
definition: A persistent midline depression of the skin over the fat pad of the chin.

label: Cleft mandible
definition: Midline deficiency of the mandible and some or all overlying tissues.

label: Abnormality of the temporomandibular joint
definition: An anomaly of the temporomandibular joint.

label: Asymmetry of the maxilla
definition: Asymmetry between the left and right sides of the maxilla.

label: Abnormality of the premaxilla
definition: An abnormality of the premaxilla, the most anterior part of the maxilla that usually bears the central and lateral incisors and includes the anterior nasal spine and inferior aspect of the piriform rim. The premaxilla contains the bone and teeth of the primary palate.

label: Aplasia of the premaxilla
definition: Absence of the premaxilla, which is the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla.

label: Prominence of the premaxilla
definition: Prominent positioning of the premaxilla in relation to the rest of the maxilla, the facial skeleton, or mandible. Not necessarily caused by an increase in size (hypertrophy of) the premaxilla.

label: Broad columella
definition: Increased width of the columella.

label: Chordoma
definition: A chordoma is a tumor that arises from embryonic remnants of the notochord along the length of the neuraxis. Chordomas generally occur in the sacrum, intracranially at the clivus, or along the spinal axis.

label: Low insertion of columella
definition: Insertion of the posterior columella below the nasal base.

label: Short eyelashes
definition: Decreased length of the eyelashes (subjective).

label: Pilonidal sinus
definition: A sinus in the coccygeal region (the region of the intergluteal cleft). A pilonidal sinus often contains hair and skin debris.

label: Pilonidal abscess
definition: A hair-containing cyst or sinus usually in the coccygeal region.

label: Partial anomalous pulmonary venous return
definition: A form of anomalous pulmonary venous return in which not all pulmonary veins drain abnormally. Partial anomalous pulmonary venous return frequently involves one or both of the veins from one lung.

label: Cor triatriatum
definition: The presence of an additional membrane in the left or right cardiac atrium which results in the subdivision of the affected atrium (and thus in total three atria, whence the name).

label: Vascular ring
definition: A developmental defect of the aortic arch system in which the trachea and esophagus are completely encircled by connected segments of the aortic arch and its branches. This occurs if the normal process of regression and persistence of the bilateral embryonic aortic arches fails.

label: Abnormal branching pattern of the aortic arch
definition: A deviance from the norm of the origin or course of the right brachiocephalic artery, the left common carotid artery, the left subclavian artery or the proximal vertebral arteries.

label: Tracheobronchmegaly
definition: Marked widening of the trachea and major bronchi that may be predispose to chronic respiratory tract infection.

label: Bronchomegaly
definition: Marked widening of the major bronchi that may be predispose to chronic respiratory tract infection.

label: Tracheomegaly
definition: Marked widening of the trachea.

label: Large pelvis bone
definition: The presence of an abnormally large pelvis.

label: Hyperacusis
definition: Over-sensitivity to certain frequency ranges of sound.

label: Shoulder dimple
definition: A subtype of skin dimples occurring in the shoulder region.

label: Female reproductive system neoplasm
definition: A neoplasm that affects the female reproductive system.

label: Gonadal neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of a gonad.

label: Genital neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the genital system.

label: Neoplasm of the male external genitalia
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the male external genitalia.

label: Hypoplasia of the Leydig cells
definition: Underdevelopment of the interstitial (Leydig) cells of the testis. These cells produce testosterone.

label: Hyperplasia of the Leydig cells
definition: Hypertrophy or overdevelopment of the interstitial (Leydig) cells of the testis. These cells produce testosterone.

label: Bifid nail
definition: A digit with two nails, with at least some soft tissue between them.

label: Impaired visuospatial constructive cognition
definition: Reduced ability affecting mainly visuospatial cognition which may be tested using pattern construction (for example by Differential Ability Scales, which test a person's strengths and weaknesses across a range of intellectual abilities).

label: Cerebellar glioma
definition: A glioma affecting the cerebellum.

label: Brainstem glioma
definition: A glioma affecting the brainstem.

label: Lip freckle
definition: Increased focal pigmentation of the vermilion of the lips.

label: Pinealoma
definition: A neoplasm of the pineal gland.

label: Supratentorial neoplasm
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that occurs within the intracranial cavity above the tentorium cerebelli.

label: Absent cupid's bow
definition: Lack of paramedian peaks and median notch of the upper lip vermilion.

label: Underdeveloped nasolabial fold
definition: Reduced bulkiness of the crease or fold of skin running from the lateral margin of the nose, where nasal base meets the skin of the face, to a point just lateral to the corner of the mouth (cheilion or commissure).

label: Perioral hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased pigmentation, either focal or generalized, of the skin surrounding the vermilion of the lips.

label: Everted upper lip vermilion
definition: Inner aspect of the upper lip vermilion (normally apposing the teeth) visible in a frontal view, i.e., the presence of an everted upper lip.

label: Tented upper lip vermilion
definition: Triangular appearance of the oral aperture with the apex in the midpoint of the upper vermilion and the lower vermilion forming the base.

label: Upturned corners of mouth
definition: Oral commissures positioned superior to the midline labial fissure.

label: U-Shaped upper lip vermilion
definition: Gentle upward curve of the upper lip vermilion such that the center is placed well superior to the commissures.

label: Protruding tongue
definition: Tongue extending beyond the alveolar ridges or teeth at rest.

label: Broad uvula
definition: Increased width of the uvula (subjective finding).

label: Long uvula
definition: Increased length of the uvula.

label: Narrow uvula
definition: Decreased width of the uvula.

label: Short uvula
definition: Decreased length of the uvula.

label: Abnormal number of hair whorls
definition: More than two clockwise hair whorls.

label: Abnormal position of hair whorl
definition: Hair growth from a single point on the scalp in any location other than lateral to the midline and close to the vertex of the skull.

label: Nevus sebaceous
definition: A congenital, hairless plaque consisting of overgrown epidermis, sebaceous glands, hair follicles, apocrine glands and connective tissue. They are a variant of epidermal naevi. Sebaceous naevi most often appear on the scalp, but they may also arise on the face, neck or forehead. At birth, a sevaceous nevus typically appears as a solitary, smooth, yellow-orange hairless patch. Sebaceous naevi become more pronounced around adolescence, often appearing bumpy, warty or scaly.

label: Epidermal nevus
definition: Epidermal naevi are due to an overgrowth of the epidermis and may be present at birth (50%) or develop during childhood.

label: Linear nevus sebaceous
definition: A type of nevus sebaceous with a linear form, raised borders and yellowish color.

label: Generalized tonic seizure
definition: A generalized tonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, often with neck stiffening without a subsequent clonic phase. The tonic activity can be a sustained abnormal posture, either in extension or flexion, sometimes accompanied by tremor of the extremities.

label: Tonic seizure
definition: A tonic seizure is a type of motor seizure characterized by unilateral or bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, often with neck stiffening.

label: Atonic seizure
definition: Atonic seizure is a type of motor seizure characterized by a sudden loss or diminution of muscle tone without apparent preceding myoclonic or tonic event lasting about 1 to 2 seconds, involving head, trunk, jaw, or limb musculature.

label: Motor seizure
definition: A motor seizure is a type of seizure that is characterized at onset by involvement of the skeletal musculature. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement.

label: Focal emotional seizure with crying
definition: Focal emotional seizure with crying (dacrystic) is characterized by the presence of stereotyped crying, this may be accompanied by lacrimation, sad facial expression and sobbing. The subjective emotion of sadness may or may not be present.

label: Focal emotional seizure
definition: Seizures presenting with an emotion or the appearance of having an emotion as an early prominent feature, such as fear, spontaneous joy or euphoria, laughing (gelastic), or crying, (dacrystic). These emotional seizures may occur with or without objective clinical signs of a seizure evident to the observer.

label: Focal emotional seizure with laughing
definition: Focal emotional seizure with laughing (gelastic) is characterized by bursts of laughter or giggling, usually without appropriate related emotion of happiness, and described as 'mirthless'.

label: Scintillating scotoma
definition: A scintillating scotoma is a common visual aura that can precede a migraine, whereby a spot of flickering light near the center of the visual fields occurs. The spot prevents vision, and is thus termed scotoma. The scotoma can extend into one or more shimmering arcs of white or colored flashing lights.

label: Ridged cranial sutures
definition: An overlap of the bony plates of the skull in an infant, with or without early closure.

label: Abnormal fifth cranial nerve morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the fifth cranial nerve.

label: Abnormality of the eleventh cranial nerve
definition: Abnormality of the eleventh cranial nerve.

label: Abnormality of the twelfth cranial nerve
definition: Abnormality of the twelfth cranial nerve.

label: Abnormal lingual nerve morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of a lingual nerve.

label: Hemifacial spasm
definition: Intermittent clonic or tonic contraction of muscles supplied by facial nerve. Muscles are relaxed in between contractions.

label: Impaired temperature sensation
definition: A reduced ability to discriminate between different temperatures.

label: Spontaneous pain sensation
definition: Spontaneous pain is a kind of neuropathic pain which occurs without an identifiable trigger.

label: Dissociated sensory loss
definition: A pattern of sensory loss with selective loss of touch sensation and proprioception without loss of pain and temperature, or vice-versa.

label: Abnormal circulating copper concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of copper.

label: Decreased circulating ceruloplasmin concentration
definition: Decreased concentration of ceruloplasmin in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating ceruloplasmin concentration
definition: Any deviation of the concentration of ceruloplasmin in the blood from the normal range.

label: High nonceruloplasmin-bound serum copper
definition: An increased concentration of non ceruloplasmin bound copper in the blood.

label: Increased urinary copper concentration
definition: An increased concentration of copper in the urine.

label: Multifocal epileptiform discharges
definition: An abnormality in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG) and being identified at multiple locations (foci).

label: EEG with focal epileptiform discharges
definition: EEG discharges recorded in particular areas of a localized (focal) abnormality in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with focal slow activity
definition: Focal (localized) slow activity reflects focal dysfunction, not diffuse dysfunction (i.e., encephalopathy).

label: EEG with abnormally slow frequencies
definition: EEG with abnormally slow frequencies.

label: EEG with multifocal slow activity
definition: Multifocal slowing of cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with generalized slow activity
definition: Diffuse slowing of cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with persistent abnormal rhythmic activity
EEG with constitutional variants
definition: An EEG with constitutional variants contains waves that are rare or unusual but not generally pathologic.

label: EEG with spike-wave complexes (<2.5 Hz)
definition: The presence of complexes of slow spikes and slow waves (<2.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with spike-wave complexes (2.5-3.5 Hz)
definition: The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (2.5-3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with spike-wave complexes (>3.5 Hz)
definition: The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (>3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with burst suppression
definition: The burst suppression pattern in electroencephalography refers to a characteristic periodic pattern of low voltage (<10 microvolts) suppressed background and a relatively shorter pattern of higher amplitude slow, sharp, and spiking complexes.

label: EEG with photoparoxysmal response
definition: EEG abnormalities (epileptiform discharges) evoked by flashing lights or black and white striped patterns.

label: EEG with periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges
definition: Periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges (PLEDs)are periodic, lateralized, and epileptiform. PLEDs show a relatively constant interval between discharges (0.5 to 3 seconds).

label: Focal epileptiform discharges with limited propagation to contralateral hemisphere
definition: Focal epileptiform discharges with spreading to contralateral hemisphere but without secondary generalization.

label: EEG with generalized low amplitude activity
definition: An abnormal generalized reduction in amplitude of the cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with changes in voltage
definition: EEG with abnormal amplitude.

label: EEG with localized low amplitude activity
definition: An abnormal localized reduction in amplitude of the cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with periodic complexes
definition: Periodically occurring generalized periodic complexes.

label: EEG with periodic abnormalities
definition: Periodically recurring abnormalities in the EEG.

label: EEG with generalized polymorphic epileptiform discharges
definition: Generalized epileptiform discharges of different shapes and frequencies.

label: EEG with hyperventilation-induced epileptiform discharges
definition: Epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: Interictal epileptiform activity
definition: Epileptiform activity refers to distinctive EEG waves or complexes distinguished from background activity found in in a proportion of human subjects with epilepsy, but which can also be found in subjects without seizures. Interictal epileptiform activity refers to such activity that occurs in the absence of a clinical or subclinical seizure.

label: Frank breech presentation
definition: A kind of breech presentation in which the hips are flexed and the knees are extended.

label: Complete breech presentation
definition: A kind of breech presentation in which the hips are flexed and the knees are flexed.

label: Incomplete breech presentation
definition: A kind of breech presentation in which one or both hips are extended and one or both of the fetus' feet are pointing down and entering the birth canal.

label: Delayed fine motor development
definition: A type of motor delay characterized by a delay in acquiring the ability to control the fingers and hands.

label: Receptive language delay
definition: A delay in the acquisition of the ability to understand the speech of others.

label: Intellectual disability, severe
definition: Severe mental retardation is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 20-34.

label: Oppositional defiant disorder
definition: An enduring pattern of uncooperative, defiant, and hostile behavior towards authority figures that does not involve major antisocial violations, is not accounted for by the child's developmental stage, and results in significant functional impairment. A certain level of oppositional behavior is common in children and adolescents.

label: Dyssynergia
definition: A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to smoothly perform the elements of a voluntary movement in the appropriate order and speed. With dyssynergia, a voluntary movement appears broken down into its component parts.

label: Ocular dyssynergia
definition: A type of dyssynergia affecting eye movements and characterized by the inability to smoothly follow a visual target across the visual field.

label: Asynergia
definition: A type of dyssynergy characterized by the lack of the ability to smoothly perform the elements of a voluntary movement in the appropriate order and speed.

label: Sensory ataxia
definition: Incoordination of movement caused by a deficit in the sensory nervous system. Sensory ataxia can be distinguished from cerebellar ataxia by asking the patient to close his or her eyes. Persons with cerebellar ataxia show only a minimal worsening of symptoms, whereas persons with sensory ataxia show a marked worsening of symptoms.

label: Cervical spinal cord atrophy
definition: Atrophy of the cervical segment of the spinal cord.

label: Tendon xanthomatosis
definition: The presence of xanthomas (intra-and extra-cellular accumulations of cholesterol) extensor tendons (typically over knuckles, Achilles tendon, knee, and elbows).

label: Chaddock reflex
definition: A diagnostic reflex elicited by stimulation of the skin over the surface of the lateral malleolus of the foot. The Chaddock refelx is present if there is extension of one or more or all of the toes with or without fanning of them when the external inframalleolar skin is stimulated. The Chaddock sign, similar to the Babinski sign, is taken to be an indication of disease of the spinocortical (pyramidal) tract.

label: Monocular strabismus
definition: A type of strabismus in which the fixating eye is always the same one, while the other eye is constantly deviated. Monocular strabismus is to be distinguished from alternating strabismus, in which either of the eyes 'squints' at different times.

label: Fetal cystic hygroma
definition: The presence during the prenatal period of a cystic mass with multiple septa with multiple, asymmetric, thin-walled cysts near the posterior aspect of the neck. Fetal cystic hygroma can be defined as nuchal translucency with or without septations measuring greater than 3.0 mm. Increased NT refers to a measurement above the 95th centile, and the term is used irrespective of whether the collection of fluid is septated or not, and whether it is confined to the neck or envelopes the whole fetus. After 14 weeks, increased NT usually resolves, but in some cases it evolves into nuchal edema or cystic hygromas.

label: Increased nuchal translucency
definition: Nuchal translucency is the sonographic appearance of subcutaneous accumulation of liquid in the back of the fetal neck in the first trimester of pregnancy (11-14 gestational weeks of pregnancy).

label: Pulmonary valve atresia
definition: A congenital disorder of the pulmonary valve in which the orifice of the valve fails to develop.

label: Aortic valve atresia
definition: A congenital disorder of the aortic valve in which the orifice of the valve fails to develop.

label: Avascular necrosis
definition: A disease where there is cellular death (necrosis) of bone components due to interruption of the blood supply.

label: Osteochondritis dissecans
definition: A joint disorder caused by blood deprivation in the subchondral bone causing the subchondral bone to die in a process called avascular necrosis. The bone is then reabsorbed by the body, leaving the articular cartilage it supported prone to damage. The result is fragmentation (dissection) of both cartilage and bone, and the free movement of these osteochondral fragments within the joint space, causing pain and further damage.

label: Osteochondrosis
definition: Abnormal growth ossification centers in children. Initially a degeneration/ necrosis followed by regeneration or recalcification.

label: Morbus Koehler
definition: Morbus Koehler is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Os naviculare pedis.

label: Abnormality of the os naviculare pedis
Morbus Kienboeck
definition: Morbus Kienboeck is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Os lunatum.

label: Morbus Osgood-Schlatter
definition: Morbus Osgood-Schlatter is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Tuberositas tibiae.

label: Abnormal circulating serine family amino acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a serine family amino acid in the blood circulation.

label: Hypersarcosinemia
definition: An elevated plasma concentration of sarcosine.

label: Abnormal circulating sarcosine concentration
definition: An deviation from the normal concentration of sarcosine in the blood circulation.

label: Hypersarcosinuria
definition: An elevated urinary concentration of sarcosine.

label: Abnormal circulating aspartate family amino acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of an aspartate family amino acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating glutamine family amino acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a glutamine family amino acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating histidine concentration
definition: An abnormality of a histidine metabolic process.

label: Hyperhistidinemia
definition: An increased concentration of histidine in the blood.

label: Hypervalinemia
definition: An increased concentration of valine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating valine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal circulation of valine in the blood circulation.

label: Hyperleucinemia
definition: An increased concentration of leucine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating isoleucine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of isoleucine in the blood circulation.

label: Hyperisoleucinemia
definition: An increased concentration of isoleucine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating pyruvate family amino acid concentration
definition: An abnormality of a pyruvate family amino acid metabolic process.

label: Abnormal circulating cysteine concentration
definition: An abnormality of a cysteine metabolic process.

label: Coralliform cataract
definition: A 'coral-like' pattern of opacity in the lens of the eye. That is, a cataract with an irregular, stellate form.

label: Membranous cataract
definition: A form of cataract in which the lens substance has shrunk, leaving a collapsed, flattened capsule with little or no cortex or epithelium on the lens.

label: Anterior subcapsular cataract
definition: A type of cataract affecting the anterior pole of lens immediately adjacent to ('beneath') the lens capsule.

label: Aculeiform cataract
definition: A kind of nuclear cataract characterized by fiberglasslike or needlelike crystals projecting in different directions, through or close to the axial region of the lens.

label: Abnormal blood cation concentration
definition: An abnormality of cation homeostasis.

label: Abnormal blood monovalent inorganic cation concentration
definition: An abnormality of monovalent inorganic cation homeostasis.

label: Hyperxanthinemia
definition: An increased level of xanthine in the blood circulation.

label: Xanthinuria
definition: An increased concentration of xanthine in the urine.

label: Abnormal nasal skeleton morphology
definition: An abnormality of the nasal skeleton.

label: Abnormal nasal bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the nasal bone, comprising the left nasal bone and the right nasal bone.

label: Aplasia of the nasal bone
definition: Absence of the nasal bone.

label: Echogenic intracardiac focus
definition: A finding of a focus of increased echogenicity upon prenatal ultrasound examination of the fetus. The foci may be present in one or both ventricles. Echogenic intracardiac focus (EICF) is defined as a focus of echogenicity comparable to bone, in the region of the papillary muscle in either or both ventricles of the fetal heart.

label: Echogenic fetal bowel
definition: Echogenic bowel is defined as fetal bowel with homogenous areas of echogenicity that are equal to or greater than that of surrounding bone.

label: Fetal pyelectasis
definition: Mild pyelectasis is defined as a hypoechoic spherical or elliptical space within the renal pelvis that measures at least 5mm and not more than 10 mm. The measurement is taken on a transverse section through the fetal renal pelvis using the maximum anterior-to-posterior measurement.

label: Abnormal fetal genitourinary system morphology
definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal genitourinary system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Abnormality of ductus venosus blood flow
definition: A first-trimester prenatal ultrasound finding of abnormal blood flow in the ductus venosus.

label: Abnormal fetal cardiovascular physiology
definition: Abnormal functionality of the fetal cardiovascular system.

label: Abnormality of umbilical vein blood flow
definition: A first-trimester prenatal ultrasound finding of abnormal blood flow in the umbilical vein.

label: Mild fetal ventriculomegaly
definition: A kind of ventriculomegaly occurring in the fetal period and usually diagnosed by prenatal ultrasound. Cerebral ventriculomegaly is defined by atrial measurements 10 mm or more. Mild ventriculomegaly (MVM) is defined as measurements between 10 and 15 mm. Measurements are obtained from an axial plane at the level of the thalamic nuclei just below the standard image to measure the BPD (PMID:16100637).

label: Abnormal fetal central nervous system morphology
definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal central nervous system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Noncommunicating hydrocephalus
definition: A form of hydrocephalus in which the flow of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) within the cerebral ventricular system or in the outlets of the CSF to the arachnoid space is obstructed.

label: Hypoplastic right heart
definition: Underdevelopment of the right-sided structures of the heart.

label: Fetal megacystis
definition: Fetal megacystis is an abnormally enlarged bladder identified at any gestational age.

label: Congenital posterior urethral valve
definition: A developmental defect resulting in an obstructing membrane in the posterior male urethra.

label: Urethrovesical occlusion
definition: Blockage of the flow of urine from the bladder into the urethra.

label: Bilateral renal agenesis
definition: A bilateral form of agenesis of the kidney.

label: Congenital pulmonary airway malformation
definition: Congenital pulmonary airway malformation (CPAM) - previously known as congenital cystic adenomatoid malformation (CCAM) - is a relatively rare developmental malformation of the lower respiratory tract. It is a hamartomatous, dysplastic developmental abnormality of the lung characterized by abnormal airway patterning during lung branching morphogenesis and is formed by abnormal branching of the immature bronchioles.

label: Abnormal fetal pulmonary morphology
definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal lungs. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Absence of stomach bubble on fetal sonography
definition: By the 14th week of gestation it is nearly always possible to visualized the fluid-filled fetal stomach bubble on prenatal sonography. This term refers to the absence of a normal fetal stomach bubble on fetal ultrasonography performed at around 16 to 20 weeks' gestation.

label: Abnormal circulating fatty-acid anion concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a fatty acid anion in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormality of liposaccharide metabolism
definition: An abnormality of liposaccharide metabolism.

label: Blood group antigen abnormality
definition: An abnormality of an erythrocyte cell surface molecule.

label: Absence of Lutheran antigen on erythrocytes
definition: Absence of the Lutheran antigen (a type I integral membrane glycoprotein) from the surface of red blood cells.

label: Abnormality of lipoprotein cholesterol concentration
definition: An abnormal increase or decrease in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

label: Polygenic inheritance
definition: A mode of inheritance that depends on a mixture of major and minor genetic determinants possibly together with environmental factors. Diseases inherited in this manner are termed complex diseases.

label: Oligogenic inheritance
