definition: A type of multifactorial inheritance governed by the simultaneous action of a few gene loci. It is recommended this term be used for traits governed by three loci, although it is noted that usage of this term in the literature is not uniform.

label: Digenic inheritance
definition: A type of multifactorial inheritance governed by the simultaneous action of two gene loci.

label: Stress urinary incontinence
definition: Involuntary urine leakage synchronous with exertion, or actions such as sneezing, or coughing.

label: Chromosomal breakage induced by ionizing radiation
definition: Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with ionizing radiation.

label: Increased susceptibility to spontaneous sister chromatid exchange
definition: An increase in the number of spontaneous sister chromatid exchanges observed in cell culture of lymphocytes or other cells.

label: Osteopetrosis
definition: Abnormally increased formation of dense trabecular bone tissue. Despite the increased density of bone tissue, osteopetrotic bones tend to be more fracture-prone than normal.

label: High myopia
definition: A severe form of myopia with greater than -6.00 diopters.

label: Mixed cirrhosis
definition: A type of cirrhosis characterized by the presence of regenerative nodules of a variety of sizes.

label: Acute
definition: Sudden appearance of disease manifestations over a short period of time.

label: Chronic
definition: Slow, creeping onset, slow progress and long continuance of disease manifestations.

label: Subacute
definition: Somewhat rapid onset and change of disease manifestations.

label: Abnormal circulating polysaccharide concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of a polysaccharide in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating carbohydrate concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of a carbohydrate in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal cellular phenotype
definition: An anomaly of cellular morphology or physiology.

label: Abnormal circulating unsaturated fatty acid concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of an unsaturated fatty acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating eicosanoid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of an icosanoid (also known as eicosanoids). These are signaling molecules derived from oxidation of 20-carbon fatty acids. Most are produced from arachidonic acid, a 20-carbon polyunsaturated fatty acid (5,8,11,14-eicosatetraenoic acid).

label: Abnormality of iron homeostasis
definition: An abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of iron cation.

label: Decreased urine output
definition: A decreased rate of urine production.

label: Agenesis of permanent maxillary central incisor
definition: Agenesis of upper secondary incisor.

label: Agenesis of primary maxillary central incisor
definition: Agenesis of upper central primary incisor.

label: Agenesis of primary mandibular central incisor
definition: Agenesis of lower primary incisor.

label: Agenesis of permanent mandibular central incisor
definition: Agenesis of lower secondary incisor.

label: Agenesis of primary maxillary lateral incisor
definition: Agenesis of one or more maxillary lateral incisor, comprising the maxillary lateral primary incisor.

label: Agenesis of permanent maxillary lateral incisor
definition: Agenesis of one or more upper lateral secondary incisor.

label: Agenesis of premolar
definition: Agenesis of premolar tooth.

label: Abnormality of premolar
definition: An abnormality of premolar tooth.

label: Agenesis of maxillary premolar
definition: Agenesis of maxillary premolar.

label: Agenesis of mandibular premolar
definition: Agenesis of mandibular premolar.

label: Agenesis of molar
definition: Agenesis of molar tooth.

label: Abnormality of molar
definition: An abnormality of molar tooth.

label: Agenesis of permanent molar
definition: Agenesis of secondary molar tooth.

label: Agenesis of first permanent molar tooth
definition: Agenesis of either maxillary first permanent molar or mandibular first permanent molar or both.

label: Agenesis of second permanent molar
definition: Agenesis of either mandibular second permanent molar or maxillary second permanent molar.

label: Generalized periodontitis
definition: A generalized form of periodontitis.

label: Localized periodontitis
definition: A localized form of periodontitis.

label: Dentinogenesis imperfecta limited to primary teeth
definition: Developmental dysplasia of dentin affecting only the primary dentition.

label: Mesiodens
definition: A supernumerary tooth in the midline between the maxillary central incisors.

label: Odontoma
definition: The presence of an odontoma.

label: Localized hypoplasia of dental enamel
definition: A localized form of developmental hypoplasia of the dental enamel.

label: Green teeth
definition: A green staining of teeth.

label: Abnormality of canine
definition: An abnormality of canine tooth.

label: Conical primary incisor
definition: An abnormal conical morphology of the primary incisor.

label: Conical maxillary incisor
definition: An abnormal conical morphology of either maxillary primary incisor tooth or maxillary permanent incisor tooth or both.

label: Hypocalcification of dental enamel
definition: A form of hypomineralization of enamel characterized by reduced calcification.

label: Hypomature dental enamel
definition: A form of hypomineralization of enamel characterized by a chalky appearance of the enamel with orange, brown, or white color.

label: Dentinogenesis imperfecta of primary and permanent teeth
definition: Developmental dysplasia of dentin or both the primary dentition and the permanent dentition.

label: Talon cusp
definition: Talon cusp is an accessory cusp located near the cingulum (the portion of the lingual or palatal aspect of the tooth that forms a convex protuberance at the cervical third of the anatomic crown).

label: Supernumerary cusp
definition: Additional cusps of a dental crown.

label: Dens in dente
definition: An abnormality of the incisor characterized by invagination of the enamel, giving a radiographic appearance that suggests a tooth within a tooth.

label: Double tooth
definition: Fusion of two adjacent teeth.

label: Fused teeth
definition: The union of two separately developing tooth germs typically leading to one less tooth than normal in the affected dental arch.

label: Gemination
definition: The development of two teeth from a single tooth bud, leading to a larger fused tooth.

label: Mulberry molar
definition: Mulberry molars are irregular teeth generally affecting the first molars and are characterized by a grossly deformed crown imitating, as the name implies, the surface of a mulberry.

label: Molarization of premolar
definition: Increased size and molar morphology of premolar tooth.

label: Increased overbite
definition: Maxillary teeth cover the mandibular teeth when biting to an increased degree. The feature is defined as a vertical overlap of the maxillary incisors over the mandibular incisors that exceeds 2 mm.

label: Overjet
definition: An abnormal anteroposterior extension of the maxillary teeth beyond the plane of the mandibular teeth upon jaw closure.

label: Epileptic spasm
definition: A sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that is usually more sustained than a myoclonic movement but not as sustained as a tonic seizure. Limited forms may occur: Grimacing, head nodding, or subtle eye movements. Epileptic spasms frequently occur in clusters. Infantile spasms are the best known form, but spasms can occur at all ages

label: Speech apraxia
definition: A type of apraxia that is characterized by difficulty or inability to execute speech movements because of problems with coordination and motor problems, leading to incorrect articulation. An increase of errors with increasing word and phrase length may occur.

label: Spastic hemiparesis
definition: Unilateral paresis (weakness) with spasticity of the affected muscles and increased tendon reflexes.

label: Ileal atresia
definition: An abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the ileum.

label: Abnormality of blood volume homeostasis
definition: An abnormality in the amount of volume occupied by intravascular blood.

label: Hypervolemia
definition: An increase in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood.

label: Hypovolemia
definition: An decrease in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood.

label: Recurrent aphthous stomatitis
definition: Recurrent episodes of ulceration of the oral mucosa, typically presenting as painful, sharply circumscribed fibrin-covered mucosal defects with a hyperemic border.

label: Recurrent sinusitis
definition: A recurrent form of sinusitis.

label: Chronic sinusitis
definition: A chronic form of sinusitis.

label: Recurrent tonsillitis
definition: Inflammation of the tonsils that has occurred repeatedly. The definition of recurrent may vary somewhat, but the criteria used recently as a measure of severity were five or more episodes of true tonsillitis per year, symptoms recurring for at least a year, and episodes that are disabling and that prevent normal functioning. In some cases recurrent tonsillitis may be related to immunosusceptibility. Evidence exists for a genetic predisposition for recurrent tonsillitis.

label: Abnormality of the tonsils
definition: An abnormality of the tonsils.

label: Abnormal immune serum protein physiology
definition: An abnormality of the concentration or function of circulating immune proteins.

label: Abnormal circulating cytokine concentration
definition: Abnormality of the cytokine levels in the blood, i.e., an abnormality of any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells.

label: Abnormality of cytokine secretion
definition: An abnormality in the production or cellular release of a cytokine (i.e., any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells).

label: Defective production of NFKB1-dependent cytokines
definition: An impairment in the production by leukocytes of NFKB1-dependent cytokines such as tumor necrosis factor-alpha and interferon-alpha.

label: Abnormal circulating chemokine concentration
definition: An abnormality in the production or cellular release of a chemokine (a class of cytokines).

label: Abnormal circulating interferon concentration
definition: The concentration of an interferon is outside the limits of normal.

label: Abnormal circulating interleukin concentration
definition: The concentration of an interleukin (a class of cytokines) is outside the limits of normal.

label: Abnormality of tumor necrosis factor secretion
definition: An abnormality in the production or cellular release of tumor necrosis factor.

label: Concave nasal ridge
definition: Nasal ridge curving posteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip.

label: Abnormal epidermal morphology
definition: An abnormality of the morphology of the epidermis.

label: Nephroptosis
definition: A significant descent of the kidney as the patient moves from the supine to the erect position.

label: Perioral eczema
definition: A type of eczema that occurs in the lips and perioral area.

label: Acute esophageal necrosis
definition: A condition characterized by necrosis of the mucosal and submucosal layers of the esophagus not related to ingestion of caustic or other injurious agents. Endoscopically, there is a dark lesion ('black esophagus') distributed in a circumferential manner in the distal one-third of the esophagus with or without exudates. There is involvement of the distal esophagus ending sharply at the gastroesophageal junction.

label: Bilateral fetal pyelectasis
definition: A bilateral form of fetal pyelectasis.

label: Abnormal renal calyx morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the morphology of the major calices or minor calices of the kidney.

label: Perianal dermatitis
definition: The presence of a rash (change of color and texture) of the perianal skin.

label: Chronic furunculosis
definition: A furuncle (boil) is a skin infection involving an entire hair follicle and nearby skin tissue. Chronic furunculosis refers to recurrent episodes of furuncles, often caused by recurrent staphylococcus infection.

label: Increased sensitivity to ionizing radiation
definition: An abnormally increased sensitivity to the effects of ionizing radiation.

label: Low-grade fever
definition: Mild fever that does not exceed 38.5 degrees centigrade.

label: Aplasia of the sweat glands
definition: Absence of the sweat glands.

label: Non-pruritic urticaria
definition: Pale reddish slightly elevated papules and plaques of 0.5-3 cm in diameter and not accompanied by pruritus.

label: Gastric duplication
definition: Gastric duplication is a usually cystic malformation of gastrointestinal tract, usually attached to the greater curvature of the stomach and has no communication with the stomach.

label: Gastrointestinal duplication
definition: A spherical hollow structure with a smooth muscle coat, lined by a mucous membrane, and attached to any part of the gastrointestinal tract, from the base of the tongue to the anus.

label: Age-related cataract
definition: A type of cataract (opacification of the lens) that forms during the course of aging.

label: Age-related nuclear cataract
definition: A type of age-related cataract that primarily affects the nucleus of the lens.

label: Age-related cortical cataract
definition: A type of age-related cataract that primarily affects the cortex of the lens.

label: Age-related posterior subcapsular cataract
definition: A type of age-related cataract consisting of granular opacities occurring mainly in the central posterior cortex just under the posterior capsule.

label: Typical absence seizure
definition: A typical absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by its sudden onset, interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare, possibly a brief upward deviation of the eyes. Usually the patient will be unresponsive when spoken to. Duration is a few seconds to half a minute with very rapid recovery. Although not always available, an EEG would usually show 3 Hz generalized epileptiform discharges during the event.

label: Absence seizure with eyelid myoclonia
definition: An absence with eyelid myoclonia seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by forced upward jerking of the eyelids during an absence seizure.

label: Eyelid myoclonia seizure
definition: An eyelid myoclonia seizure is a type of generalized myoclonic seizure which may or may not be associated with loss of awareness.

label: Myoclonic absence seizure
definition: Myoclonic absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by an interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare and rhythmic three-per-second myoclonic movements, causing ratcheting abduction of the upper limbs leading to progressive arm elevation, and associated with 3 Hz generalized spike-wave discharges on the electroencephalogram. Duration is typically 10-60 s. Whilst impairment of consciousness may not be obvious the ILAE classified this seizure as a generalized non-motor seizure in 2017.

label: Atypical absence status epilepticus
definition: Atypical absence status epilepticus is a type of generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma that is semiologically a prolonged atypical absence seizure.

label: Generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma
definition: Generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma is a type of status epilepticus without prominent motor signs, which is electrographically generalized. It is a prolonged absence seizure.

label: Early onset absence seizures
definition: Typical absence seizures starting before the age of 4 years.

label: Focal autonomic seizure
definition: An autonomic seizure is a type of focal non-motor seizure characterized by alteration of autonomic nervous system function as the initial semiological feature.

label: Focal non-motor seizure
definition: A type of focal-onset seizure characterized by non-motor signs or symptoms (or behavior arrest) as its initial semiological manifestation.

label: Focal sensory seizure
definition: A focal sensory seizure is a type seizure beginning with a subjective sensation.

label: Epileptic aura
definition: An epileptic aura is a purely subjective clinical manifestation of an epileptic seizure. If an epileptic aura is not followed by loss of awareness or propagation to a bilateral tonic-clonic seizure then it is a type of focal aware non-motor seizure.

label: Focal sensory seizure with auditory features
definition: A seizure characterized by elementary auditory phenomena including buzzing, ringing, drumming or single tones as its first clinical manifestation.

label: Focal autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation/nausea/vomiting/other gastrointestinal phenomena
definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by symptoms or signs pertaining to the gastrointestinal system as the initial semiological feature.

label: Focal sensory seizure with gustatory features
definition: A seizure characterized by taste phenomena including acidic, bitter, salty, sweet, or metallic tastes as its first clinical manifestation.

label: Focal sensory seizure with olfactory features
definition: Seizures characterized by olfactory phenomena as its first clinical manifestation.

label: Phantosmia
definition: Perception of an odor in the absence of any stimuli in the surrounding environment that could emit the odor.

label: Focal sensory seizure with somatosensory features
definition: A seizure characterized by sensory phenomena including tingling, numbness, electric-shock like sensation, pain, sense of movement, or desire to move as its first clinical manifestation.

label: Focal sensory seizure with visual features
definition: A seizure characterized by elementary visual hallucinations such as flashing or flickering lights/colors, or other shapes, simple patterns, scotomata, or amaurosis as its first clinical manifestation.

label: Focal myoclonic seizure
definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sudden, brief (<100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction(s) of muscles(s) or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal). Myoclonus is less regularly repetitive and less sustained than is clonus.

label: Focal tonic seizure
definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sustained increase in muscle contraction, lasting a few seconds to minutes.

label: Focal seizure with eyelid myoclonia
definition: Focal seizure with eyelid myoclonia, not eyelid myoclonias in the context of absence seizures.

label: Generalized clonic seizure
definition: Generalized clonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by sustained bilateral jerking, either symmetric or asymmetric, that is regularly repetitive and involves the same muscle groups.

label: Generalized myoclonic-atonic seizure
definition: A generalized myoclonic-atonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by a myoclonic jerk followed by an atonic motor component.

label: Simple febrile seizure
definition: A short generalized seizure, of a duration of <15 min, not recurring within 24 h, occurring during a febrile episode not caused by an acute disease of the nervous system intracranial infection or severe metabolic disturbance.

label: Complex febrile seizure
definition: A febrile seizure that has any of the following features: focal semiology (or associated with post-ictal neurologic abnormalities beyond drowsiness, such as a Todd's paresis), prolonged seizure beyond 15 minutes, or recurring (occurring more than once) in a 24 hour period.

label: Focal behavior arrest seizure
definition: A type of focal non-motor seizure characterized by an arrest or pause of activities, freezing, or immobilization as the predominant semiological feature throughout the seizure.

label: Focal hyperkinetic seizure
definition: A focal seizure characterized at onset by predominantly proximal limb or axial muscles producing irregular sequential ballistic movements, such as pedaling, pelvic thrusting, thrashing, rocking movements.

label: Focal motor seizure with version
definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sustained, forced conjugate ocular, cephalic, and/or truncal rotation or lateral deviation from the midline as the initial semiological manifestation.

label: EEG with 4-5/second background activity
definition: EEG background activity at 4-5/second.

label: Alpha-EEG
definition: EEG dominated by diffuse alpha-waves (8-13Hz).

label: Beta-EEG
definition: EEG dominated by diffuse beta-waves (>13 Hz).

label: EEG with diffuse acceleration
definition: EEG frequency is abnormally increased.

label: Partial beta-EEG
definition: EEG dominated by diffuse beta waves (>13 Hz) with occipitally localized alpha waves (8-13 Hz).

label: Low voltage EEG
definition: EEG with an amplitude less than 30 microvolts without observable occipital alpha rhythm (8-13 Hz).

label: EEG with hyperventilation-induced focal epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: EEG with hyperventilation-induced generalized epileptiform discharges
definition: Generalized epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

label: Focal EEG discharges with propagation to ipsilateral hemisphere
definition: Focal epileptiform discharges with spreading to the hemisphere on the same side of the brain.

label: Focal EEG discharges with secondary generalization
definition: Focal EEG discharges that secondarily spread to both hemispheres and can then be recorded over the entire scalp.

label: Bilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
definition: Epileptiform discharges being identified at multiple locations in both hemispheres.

label: Uni- and bilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
definition: Epileptiform discharges identified at multiple locations temporarily in both hemispheres and temporarily in one hemisphere.

label: Unilateral multifocal epileptiform discharges
definition: Epileptiform discharges being identified at multiple locations in one hemisphere.

label: Polymorphic focal epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform discharges of different shapes and frequencies.

label: EEG with focal spikes
definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec.

label: EEG with series of focal spikes
definition: Focal spikes occurring for several seconds.

label: EEG with focal sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with focal sharp waves
definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec.

label: EEG with focal spike waves
definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with generalized sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with generalized sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with continuous slow activity
definition: EEG showing diffuse slowing without interruption.

label: EEG with intermittent slow activity
definition: Non-continuous diffuse slowing of electroencephalographic patterns.

label: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 1
definition: Slowing at frequencies between 7.5 and 8.5 Hz.

label: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 2
definition: Generalized slowing of EEG activity at frequencies between 4-7 Hz.

label: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 3
definition: Generalized slowing of EEG activity at frequencies between 0.5-3 Hz.

label: EEG with generalized slow activity grade 4
definition: EEG without electrical activity.

label: EEG with occipital slowing
definition: Slowing in occipital areas of the scalp EEG.

label: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade I
definition: Occurrence of epileptiform discharges in occipital regions during photic stimulation.

label: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade II
definition: Occurrence of epileptiform discharges in occipital and central regions during photic stimulation.

label: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade III
definition: Occurrence of epileptiform discharges in occipital, central, temporal and parietal regions during photic stimulation.

label: EEG with photoparoxysmal response grade IV
definition: Occurrence of generalized epileptiform discharges during photic stimulation.

label: Hemihypsarrhythmia
definition: Hypsarrhythmia occurring in one hemisphere.

label: Abnormal occipital bone morphology
definition: Abnormality of the occipital bone of the skull.

label: Abnormal frontal bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the frontal bone.

label: Short face
definition: Facial height (length) is more than two standard deviations below the mean (objective); or an apparent decrease in the height (length) of the face (subjective).

label: Prominent forehead
definition: Forward prominence of the entire forehead, due to protrusion of the frontal bone.

label: Vertical forehead creases
definition: Vertical soft tissue creases in the midline of the forehead, often extending from the hairline to the brow, and seen with facial expression or when the face is at rest.

label: Depressed glabella
definition: Posterior positioning of the glabella, i.e., of the midline forehead between the supraorbital ridges.

label: Metopic depression
definition: Linear vertical groove in the midline of the forehead, extending from hairline to glabella.

label: Ablepharon
definition: Absent eyelids.

label: Epiblepharon
definition: Redundant eyelid skin pressing the eyelashes against the cornea and/or conjunctiva.

label: Elevated circulating C-reactive protein concentration
definition: An abnormal elevation of the C-reactive protein level in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating C-reactive protein concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of C-reactive protein in the blood circulation.

label: Horizontal eyebrow
definition: An eyebrow that extends straight across the brow, without curve.

label: Laterally extended eyebrow
definition: An eyebrow that extends laterally beyond the orbital rim rather than turning gently downward at that location.

label: Prominent eyelashes
definition: Eyelashes that draw the attention of the viewer due to increased density and/or length and/or curl without meeting the criteria of trichomegaly.

label: Infra-orbital fold
definition: Elevated ridge(s) of skin starting well below the medial aspect of the lower lid that curves gradually upward toward and/or across the nasal bridge.

label: Antihelical shelf
definition: Antihelix protrusion directed more anteriorly than laterally, forming a shelf overlying the posterior concha.

label: Absent antihelix
definition: No discernible ridge between concha and triangular fossa and helix.

label: Additional crus of antihelix
definition: Supernumerary ridge or crus of the ear arising from the antihelix.

label: Angulated antihelix
definition: Antihelical ridge that forms an acute angle between the antitragus and its bifurcation (stem) instead of a gently curving arc.

label: Broad inferior crus of antihelix
definition: Increased width of the inferred cross-section of the inferior crus.

label: Abnormality of inferior crus of antihelix
definition: An abnormality of the inferior crus of the antihelix is the lower cartilaginous ridge arising at the bifurcation of the antihelix that ends beneath the fold of the ascending helix, and separates the concha from the triangular fossa.

label: Prominent inferior crus of antihelix
definition: Increased protrusion of the inferior crus relative to the prominence of the antihelix stem.

label: Underdeveloped inferior crus of antihelix
definition: Decreased protrusion of the inferior crus relative to the prominence of the antihelix stem.

label: Prominent stem of antihelix
definition: Increased protrusion of the antihelical ridge, proximal to its bifurcation, relative to the prominence of the helix.

label: Abnormality of stem of antihelix
definition: An abnormality of the stem of the antihelix, which is the part below the bifurcation of the antihelix into the inferior and superior crura.

label: Serpiginous stem of antihelix
definition: Posterior curving of the antihelix from its origin at the antitragus, traveling initially almost perpendicular to the descending helix and obscuring some of the concha.

label: Underdeveloped stem of antihelix
definition: Decreased protrusion of the antihelical ridge, proximal to its bifurcation, relative to the prominence of a normal helix.

label: Abnormality of superior crus of antihelix
definition: An abnormality of the superior crus of the antihelix is the upper cartilaginous ridge arising at the bifurcation of the antihelix that ends beneath the fold of the ascending helix, and separates the concha from the triangular fossa.

label: Underdeveloped superior crus of antihelix
definition: Decreased protrusion of the superior crus relative to the prominence of a normal antihelix stem.

label: Prominent superior crus of antihelix
definition: Increased protrusion of the superior crus relative to the prominence of a normal antihelix stem.

label: Everted antitragus
definition: Positioning of the antitragus at an angle perpendicular to the plane of the ear (oriented away from the plane of the ear).

label: Absent antitragus
definition: Absence of the anterosuperior prominence of the area between the bottom of the incisura and the inner margin of the antihelix.

label: Bifid antitragus
definition: Double rather than single peak of the antitragus.

label: Underdeveloped antitragus
definition: Reduction in the anterosuperior prominence of the area between the bottom of the incisura and the inner margin of the antihelix.

label: Cryptotia
definition: Invagination of the superior part of the auricle under a fold of temporal skin.

label: Type I cryptotia
definition: A type of cryptotia associated with reduction in size of the antihelix and superior crus.

label: Type II cryptotia
definition: A type of cryptotia associated with reduction in size of the antihelix and inferior crus that are affected.

label: Absent crus of helix
definition: Continuum between the tragus and ascending helix, without any evidence of a posterior extension (crus) towards the concha.

label: Crus of helix connected to antihelix
definition: Extension of the ridge of the crus helix across the ear and connection of the crus to the antihelix.

label: Serpiginous crus of helix
definition: Curving course of the crus of the helix, approaching or joining the antitragus.

label: Tragal bridge of crus of helix
definition: The anterior origin of the crus encompasses the superior margin of the tragus, the crus overrides the upper portion of the conchal cavum and ends at the antihelix.

label: Expanded terminal portion of crus of helix
definition: Widening, rather than tapering, of the crus at its posterior border near the antihelix.

label: Darwin notch of helix
definition: Small defect of the helical fold that lies at the junction of the superior and descending portions of the helix.

label: Darwin tubercle of helix
definition: Small expansion of the helical fold at the junction of the superior and descending portions of the helix.

label: Crimped helix
definition: Linear, circumferential indentation in the convexity of the outer surface of the helix.

label: Forward facing earlobe
definition: Positioning of the anterior surface of the ear lobe in a more coronal plane than the remainder of the ear.

label: Discontinuous ascending root of helix
definition: Interruption between the ascending helix and the crus helix, allowing the ascending helix to be attached directly to the mastoid.

label: Cleft earlobe
definition: Discontinuity in the convexity of the inferior margin of the lobe.

label: Microtia, first degree
definition: Presence of all the normal ear components and the median longitudinal length more than two standard deviations below the mean.

label: Microtia, third degree
definition: Presence of some auricular structures, but none of these structures conform to recognized ear components.

label: Absent tragus
definition: Lack of convexity or prominence of the contour of the ridge between the bottom of the incisura and the confluence of the ascending helix and crus helix.

label: Bifid tragus
definition: Increased height of the tragal ridge with a shallow indentation at the apex, giving the appearance of a double peak.

label: Duplicated tragus
definition: A complete or partial duplication of the tragus; expected to lie anterior to the normal tragus.

label: Prominent tragus
definition: Increase posterolateral protrusion of the tragus.

label: Underdeveloped tragus
definition: Decreased posterolateral protrusion of the tragus.

label: Anisocytosis
definition: Abnormally increased variability in the size of erythrocytes.

label: Recurrent mycobacterial infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to mycobacterial infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of mycobacterial infection.

label: Recurrent mycobacterium avium complex infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to mycobacterial avium complex infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of mycobacterial infection.

label: Intrapulmonary lobar sequestration
definition: A type of pulmonary sequestration that occurs within the visceral pleura of normal lung tissue, usually without communication with the tracheobronchial tree.

label: Abnormality of urine catecholamine level
definition: An abnormal amount of urinary catecholamine concentration.

label: Abnormal hindbrain morphology
definition: An abnormality of the hindbrain, also known as the rhombencephalon.

label: Short-segment aganglionic megacolon
definition: A type of aganglionic megacolon in which the aganglionic segment does not extend beyond the upper sigmoid.

label: Long-segment aganglionic megacolon
definition: A type of aganglionic megacolon in which the aganglionic segment extends proximal to the sigmoid.

label: Total colonic aganglionosis
definition: A type of aganglionic megacolon in which the aganglionic segment comprises the entire colon.

label: EEG with occipital sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with sharp slow waves in the occipital region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with occipital epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform EEG discharges recorded in the occipital region.

label: EEG with parietal sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with sharp slow waves in the parietal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with parietal epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform EEG discharges recorded in the parietal region.

label: EEG with temporal sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with sharp slow waves in the temporal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with temporal epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform EEG discharges recorded in the temporal region.

label: EEG with frontal sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with sharp slow waves in the frontal region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with frontal epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform EEG discharges recorded in the frontal region.

label: EEG with central sharp slow waves
definition: EEG with sharp slow waves in the central region. Sharp slow waves are focal sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec followed by a slow wave.

label: EEG with central epileptiform discharges
definition: Focal epileptiform EEG discharges recorded in the central region.

label: EEG with occipital sharp waves
definition: EEG with sharp waves in the occipital region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec.

label: EEG with central sharp waves
definition: EEG with sharp waves in the central region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec.

label: EEG with frontal sharp waves
definition: EEG with sharp waves in the frontal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec.

label: EEG with parietal sharp waves
definition: EEG with sharp waves in the parietal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec.

label: EEG with temporal sharp waves
definition: EEG with sharp waves in the temporal region, i.e., sharp transient waves of a duration between 80 and 200 msec.

label: Partial absence of finger
definition: The absence of a phalangeal segment of a finger.

label: Broad fingertip
definition: Increased width of the distal segment of a finger.

label: Absent foot
definition: The total absence of the foot, with no bony elements distal to the tibia or fibula.

label: Long palm
definition: For children from birth to 16 years of age the length of the palm is more than the 97th centile; or, the length of the palm appears relatively long compared to the finger length or the limb length.

label: Convex contour of sole
definition: The contour of the foot in lateral profile has a convex shape.

label: Partial absence of toe
definition: The absence of a phalangeal segment of a toe or hallux.

label: Splayed toes
definition: Divergence of digits along the anteroposterior axis (in the plane of the sole).

label: Slender toe
definition: Toes that are disproportionately narrow (reduced girth) for the hand/foot size or build of the individual.

label: Tapered toe
definition: The gradual reduction in girth of the toe from proximal to distal.

label: Bridged palmar crease
definition: A crease that connects the proximal and distal transverse palmar creases.

label: Sydney crease
definition: Extension of the proximal transverse crease (five finger crease) to the ulnar edge of the palm.

label: Fused nails
definition: A nail plate that has a longitudinal separation with partially separated nails, each with a separate lateral radius of curvature.

label: Narrow nail
definition: Decreased width of nail.

label: Unicoronal synostosis
definition: Synostosis affecting only one of the coronal sutures.

label: Left unicoronal synostosis
definition: Synostosis affecting only the left coronal suture.

label: Right unicoronal synostosis
definition: Unicoronal synostosis affecting only the right coronal suture.

label: Bicoronal synostosis
definition: Synostosis affecting the right and the left coronal suture.

label: Bilambdoid synostosis
definition: Premature synostosis of both lambdoid sutures.

label: Unilambdoid synostosis
definition: Premature synostosis of only one lambdoid suture.

label: Left unilambdoid synostosis
definition: Premature synostosis of only the left lambdoid suture.

label: Right unilambdoid synostosis
definition: Premature synostosis of only the right lambdoid suture.

label: Cleft of chin
definition: Incomplete fusion of the chin, resulting from a developmental defect and manifesting as a midline cleft or fissure of the chin.

label: Multiple suture craniosynostosis
definition: Craniosynostosis involving at least 2 cranial sutures, where the exact pattern of sutures fused has not been precisely specified.

label: Pansynostosis
definition: Craniosynostosis of all calvarial sutures.

label: Anterior plagiocephaly
definition: Asymmetry of the anterior part of the skull.

label: Posterior plagiocephaly
definition: Asymmetry of the posterior part of the skull.

label: Metopic synostosis
definition: Premature fusion of the metopic suture.

label: Hemifacial atrophy
definition: Unilateral atrophy of facial tissues, including muscles, bones and skin.

label: Hemifacial hypoplasia
definition: Unilateral underdevelopment of the facial tissues, including muscles and bones.

label: Asymmetric crying face
definition: Asymmetry observed in the face of a neonate or infant whose face appears symmetric at rest and asymmetric during crying as the mouth is pulled downward on one side while not moving on the other side.

label: Frontal hirsutism
definition: Excessive amount of hair growth on forehead.

label: Bitemporal forceps marks
definition: Bilateral temporal scarlike defects, which are said to resemble forceps marks.

label: Incomplete cleft of the upper lip
definition: Cleft of the upper lip that does not go all the way from the bottom of the upper lip until the nasal cavity.

label: Long upper lip
definition: Increased width of the upper lip.

label: Mild global developmental delay
definition: A mild delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child.

label: Moderate global developmental delay
definition: A moderate delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child.

label: Severe global developmental delay
definition: A severe delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child.

label: Moderate expressive language delay
definition: A moderate delay in the acquisition of the ability to use language to communicate needs, wishes, or thoughts.

label: Mild expressive language delay
definition: A mild delay in the acquisition of the ability to use language to communicate needs, wishes, or thoughts.

label: Abnormal sixth cranial nerve morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the abducens nerve.

label: Mild receptive language delay
definition: A mild delay in the acquisition of the ability to understand the speech of others.

label: Moderate receptive language delay
definition: A moderate delay in the acquisition of the ability to understand the speech of others.

label: Severe receptive language delay
definition: A severe delay in the acquisition of the ability to understand the speech of others.

label: Arterial intimal fibrosis
definition: Formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in the tunica intima (innermost layer) of arteries.

label: Dry hair
definition: Hair that lacks the luster (shine or gleam) of normal hair.

label: White hair
definition: Hypopigmented hair that appears white.

label: Yellow nails
definition: Yellowish discoloration of the nails.

label: Mongolian blue spot
definition: Congenital deep dermal melanosis in the sacral area.

label: Recurrent viral skin infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to viral skin infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of viral skin infections.

label: Aplasia of the inner ear
definition: Absence of the inner ear due to a developmental defect.

label: Incomplete partition of the cochlea type I
definition: Incomplete partition I is also known as cystic cochleovestibular malformation, where the cochlea has no bony modiolus, resulting in an empty cystic cochlea. This is accompanied by a dilated cystic vestibule with developmental arrest at the fifth week of gestation.

label: Cochlear aplasia
definition: Absence of the cochlea, a spiral shaped cavity in the inner ear, owing to a developmental defect.

label: Abnormal morphology of the vestibule of the inner ear
definition: A morphological abnormality of the vestibule, the central part of the osseous labyrinth that is situated medial to the tympanic cavity, behind the cochlea, and in front of the semicircular canals.

label: Aplasia of the vestibule
definition: Complete absence of the vestibule of the inner ear.

label: Hypoplasia of the vestibule of the inner ear
definition: Underdevelopment of the vestibule of the inner ear.

label: Dilated vestibule of the inner ear
definition: Dilatation of the vestibule of the inner ear.

label: Abnormal semicircular canal morphology
definition: An abnormality of the morphology of the semicircular canal.

label: Aplasia of the semicircular canal
definition: Absence of the semicircular canal.

label: Hypoplasia of the semicircular canal
definition: Underdevelopment of the semicircular canal.

label: Enlarged semicircular canal
definition: Increased size of the semicircular canal.

label: Absent internal auditory canal
definition: Aplasia of the internal auditory canal.

label: Narrow internal auditory canal
definition: Reduction in diameter of the internal auditory canal.

label: Enlarged vestibular aqueduct
definition: Increased size of the vestibular aqueduct.

label: Enlarged cochlear aqueduct
definition: Increased size of the cochlear duct, i.e., of a duct that communicates between the perilymphatic space and the subarachnoid space, and transmits a vein from the cochlea to join the internal jugular.

label: Aplasia of the vestibular nerve.
definition: Absence of the vestibular nerve

label: Hypoplasia of the vestibular nerve
definition: Underdevelopment of the vestibular nerve.

label: Abnormality of the cochlear nerve
definition: Any anomaly of the cohclear nerve, which is the part of the vestibulocochlear nerve that is responsible for transmitting auditory signals from the inner ear to the cochlear nuclei within the brainstem and ultimately to the primary auditory cortex within the temporal lobe.

label: Tibialis anterior muscle atrophy
definition: Wasting of the tibialis anterior muscle.

label: Delayed peripheral myelination
definition: Delayed myelination in the peripheral nervous system.

label: Demyelinating sensory neuropathy
definition: Demyelination of peripheral sensory nerves.

label: Lethal short-trunk short stature
definition: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short trunk but a average-sized limbs that is lethal at birth.

label: Infancy onset short-trunk short stature
definition: A type of disproportionate short stature characterized by a short trunk but a average-sized limbs with onset in infancy.

label: Moderate intrauterine growth retardation
definition: Intrauterine growth retardation that is at least 3 standard deviations (SD) below average, but not as low as 4 SD, corrected for sex and gestational age.

label: Caesarian section
definition: Delivery of a fetus through surgical incisions made through the abdominal wall (laparotomy) and the uterine wall (hysterotomy).

label: Ventouse delivery
definition: Delivery of newborn by means of a ventouse, a vacuum device used to assist the delivery of a baby when the second stage of labor has not progressed adequately.

label: Shoulder dystocia
definition: Shoulder dystocia occurs when the fetal anterior shoulder impacts against the maternal symphysis following delivery of the vertex.

label: Hydropic placenta
definition: An abnormality of the placenta in which there are numerous cystic spaces within the placenta as well as placental enlargement.

label: Abnormal placenta morphology
definition: An abnormality of the placenta, the organ that connects the developing fetus to the uterine wall to enable nutrient uptake, waste elimination, and gas exchange.

label: Long umbilical cord
definition: Increased length of the umbilical cord.

label: Abnormal insertion of umbilical cord
definition: Anomalous location of the insertion of umbilical cord in the placenta. Normally, the insertion is at least two centimers distant from the edge of the placenta.

label: Placental abruption
definition: Separation of the placenta from the uterus wall before delivery.

label: Death in adolescence
definition: Death during adolescence, the period between childhood and adulthood (roughly between the ages of 10 and 19 years).

label: Hyperchloremia
definition: An abnormally increased chloride concentration in the blood.

label: Increased serum zinc
definition: An increased concentration of zinc in the blood.

label: Fetal choroid plexus cysts
definition: Fetal choroid plexus cysts (CPCs) are sonographically discrete, small cysts found in the choroid plexus within the lateral cerebral ventricles of the developing fetus at 14 to 24 weeks gestation. Imaging of the choroid plexus is performed in the transverse plane of the fetal head at the same level that the lateral cerebral ventricle is evaluated. The choroid plexus should be inspected bilaterally for the presence of cysts. The size of CPCs is not of clinical relevance (PMID:16100637).

label: Enlarged fetal cisterna magna
definition: The cisterna magna is measured on a transaxial view of the fetal head angled 15 degrees caudal to the canthomeatal line. The anterior/posterior diameter is taken between the inferior/posterior surface of the vermis of the cerebellum to the inner surface of the cranium. An enlarged cisternal magna is defined by an anterior/posterior diameter of 10 mm or more (PMID:16100637).

label: Short fetal femur length
definition: A short femur length is defined as either a measurement below the 2.5th percentile for gestational age or a measurement that is less than 0.9 of that predicted by the measured biparietal diameter. The femur should be measured with the bone perpendicular to the ultrasound beam and with epiphyseal cartilages visible but not included in the measurement (PMID:16100637).

label: Abnormal fetal skeletal morphology
definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal skeleton. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other terms from the skeletal hierarchy can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

label: Short fetal humerus length
definition: A short humerus length is defined as a length below the 2.5th percentile for gestational age or as a measurement less than 0.9 of that predicted by the measured biparietal diameter. The humerus should be measured with the bone perpendicular to the ultrasound beam and with epiphyseal cartilages visible but not included in the measurement (PMID:16100637).

label: Hypoplasia of fetal nasal bone
definition: On prenatal ultrasound, the nasal bone is a thin echogenic line within the bridge of the fetal nose. The fetus is imaged facing the transducer with the fetal face strictly in the midline. The angle of insonation is 90 degrees, with the longitudinal axis of the nasal bone as the reference line. Calibres are placed at each end of the nasal bone. Absence of the nasal bone or measurements below 2.5th percentile are considered significant (PMID:16100637).

label: Fetal fifth finger clinodactyly
definition: Fifth finger clinodactyly is defined by a hypoplastic or absent mid-phalanx of the fifth digit. Ultrasound identification of the fetal hand must first be undertaken and then appropriate magnification accomplished. The evaluation requires stretching of the 5 fingers. The diagnosis is established when the middle phalanx of the fifth finger is markedly smaller than normal or absent, which often causes the finger to be curved inward (PMID:16100637).

label: Elevated maternal circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
definition: Increase in the levels of maternal serum alpha-fetoprotein levels during pregnancy.

label: High maternal circulating chorionic gonadotropin concentration
definition: An abnormally high concentration of maternal serum human chorionic gonadotropin as compared to normal values for gestational-age.

label: Low maternal circulating chorionic gonadotropin concentration
definition: An abnormally low concentration of maternal serum human chorionic gonadotropin as compared to normal values for gestational-age.

label: Low maternal circulating PAPP-A concentration
definition: An abnormally low concentration of serum PAPP-A (pregnancy associated plasma protein A), as compared to normal values for gestational-age.

label: Maternal autoimmune disease
definition: A medical history of a fetus or child born to a mother with an autoimmune disease.

label: Maternal teratogenic exposure
definition: A medical history of exposure of the mother of a child or fetus to a teratogenic substance during pregnancy.

label: Pregnancy exposure
definition: Exposure of pregnant women to toxins from any source, such as environmental toxins or chemicals, that may potentially cause problems such as miscarriage, preterm delivery, low birth weight, and, in some cases, developmental delays in infants.

label: Anesthetic-induced rhabdomylosis
definition: Rhabdomyolysis induced by anesthesia.

label: Alcohol-induced rhabdomyolysis
definition: Rhabdomyolysis induced by intake of alcohol.

label: Decorticate rigidity
definition: A type of rigidity in which the arms are in flexion and adduction and the legs are extended. This signifies a lesion in the cerebral white matter, internal capsules, or thalamus.

label: Athetoid cerebral palsy
definition: A type of cerebral palsy characterized by slow, involuntary muscle movement and mixed muscle tone.

label: Hyposegmentation of neutrophil nuclei
definition: Hyposegmented (hypolobulated) or bilobed neutrophil nuclei.

label: Ankle clonus
definition: Clonus is an involuntary tendon reflex that causes repeated flexion and extension of the foot. Ankle clonus is tested by rapidly flexing the foot upward.

label: Knee clonus
definition: Clonus is an involuntary tendon reflex that causes repeated flexion and extension of the foot. Knee clonus can be tested by rapidly pushing the patella towards the toes.

label: Unusual infection by anatomical site
definition: An unusual infection classified by the affected body part.

label: Primary microcephaly
definition: Head circumference below 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender at birth.

label: Abnormal incus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the incus, an ossicle in the middle ear.

label: Abnormal malleus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the malleus, an ossicle in the middle ear.

label: Absent malleus
definition: Aplasia of the malleus.

label: Absent stapes
definition: Aplasia of the stapes.

label: Loss of eyelashes
definition: This term refers to the loss of eyelashes that were previously present.

label: Esophageal carcinoma
definition: The presence of a carcinoma of the esophagus.

label: Esophageal neoplasm
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the esophagus.

label: Embryonal onset
definition: Onset of disease at up to 8 weeks following fertilization (corresponding to 10 weeks of gestation).

label: Antenatal onset
definition: Onset prior to birth.

label: Fetal onset
definition: Onset prior to birth but after 8 weeks of embryonic development (corresponding to a gestational age of 10 weeks).

label: Young adult onset
definition: Onset of disease at the age of between 16 and 40 years.

label: Childhood onset
definition: Onset of disease at the age of between 1 and 5 years.

label: Aganglionosis of the small intestine
definition: A lack of intestinal ganglion cells (i.e., an aganglionic section of bowel) affecting the small intestine.

label: Duodenal aganglionosis
definition: A lack of intestinal ganglion cells (i.e., an aganglionic section of bowel) affecting the duodenum.

label: Absent gallbladder
definition: A developmental defect in which the gallbladder fails to form.

label: Facial tics
definition: Sudden, repetitive, nonrhythmic motor movements (spasms), involving the eyes and muscles of the face.

label: Nasal regurgitation
definition: Regurgitation of milk through the nose.

label: Nasogastric tube feeding in infancy
definition: Feeding problem necessitating nasogastric tube feeding.

label: Tube feeding
definition: Feeding problem necessitating food and nutrient delivery via a tube.

label: Gastrostomy tube feeding in infancy
definition: Feeding problem necessitating gastrostomy tube feeding.

label: Abnormal small intestinal mucosa morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the mucous lining of the small intestine.

label: Villous atrophy
definition: The enteric villi are atrophic or absent.

label: Persistent stapedial artery
definition: Persistence of the stapedial artery, which normally regresses during embryonic life.

label: Profound sensorineural hearing impairment
definition: Complete loss of hearing related to a sensorineural defect.

label: Profound hearing impairment
definition: A profound (essentially complete) form of hearing impairment.

label: Upbeat nystagmus
definition: In primary position, the eyes drift slowly downward and then spontaneously beat upward. Upward gaze accentuates the nystagmus. The associated oscillopsias are often very irritating, but the symptoms are usually transient.

label: True anophthalmia
definition: Absence of globe, optic nerve, chiasm and optic tracts. No evidence of ocular tissue on MRI scan or examination.

label: Unilateral microphthalmos
definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by abnormal smallness of one eye.

label: Anterior synechiae of the anterior chamber
definition: Adhesions between the iris and the cornea.

label: Posterior synechiae of the anterior chamber
definition: Adhesions between the iris and the lens.

label: Corneolenticular adhesion
definition: Developmental abnormality in which the lens and cornea are not separated.

label: Abnormal corneal thickness
definition: An abnormal anteroposterior thickness of the cornea.

label: Increased corneal thickness
definition: A increased anteroposterior thickness of the cornea.

label: Abnormal corneal endothelium morphology
definition: Abnormality of the corneal endothelium, that is, the single layer of cells on the inner surface of the cornea.

label: Abnormal Descemet membrane morphology
definition: Abnormality of Descemet's membrane, which is the basement membrane of the corneal endothelium.

label: Corneal neovascularization
definition: Ingrowth of new blood vessels into the cornea.

label: Rubeosis iridis
definition: Formation of new blood vessels on the iris. The new vessels do not display the typical radially symmertic growth pattern of normal iris blood vessels, but rather appear disorganized. Rubeosis usually starts from the pupillary border with tiny tufts of dilated capillaries or red spots that can only be appreciated with high magnification.

label: Polycoria
definition: Multiple pupils.

label: Anterior lenticonus
definition: A conical projection of the anterior surface of the lens, occurring as a developmental anomaly.

label: Posterior lenticonus
definition: A conical projection of the posterior surface of the lens, occurring as a developmental anomaly.

label: Aplasia of the fovea
definition: Congenital absence of the fovea.

label: Bull's eye maculopathy
definition: Progressive maculopathy characterized by concentric regions of hyper- and hypo-pigmentation.

label: Cystoid macular edema
definition: Cystoid macular edema (CME) is any type of macular edema that involves cyst formation.

label: Macular edema
definition: Thickening of the retina that takes place due to accumulation of fluid in the macula as a nonspecific response to blood-retinal barrier breakdown. Macular edema is a common pathological response to a wide variety of ocular insults, most commonly after intraocular (e.g. cataract) surgery or in association with retinal vascular (e.g. diabetic eye disease, retinal vein occlusion) or inflammatory (e.g. uveitis) disease.

label: Choroidal neovascularization
definition: Choroidal neovascularization (CNV) is the creation of new blood vessels in the choroid layer of the eye.

label: Macular flecks
definition: Pale often indistinct lesions of the macula.

label: Macular hole
definition: A macular hole is a small break in the macula, located in the center of the retina.

label: Retinal perforation
definition: A small hole through the whole thickness of the retina.

label: Macular hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased amount of pigmentation in the macula lutea.

label: Drusen
definition: Drusen (singular, 'druse') are tiny yellow or white accumulations of extracellular material (lipofuscin) that build up in Bruch's membrane of the eye.

label: Macular schisis
definition: Splitting of the retina in the macular region.

label: Macular thickening
definition: Abnormal increase in retinal thickness in the macular area observed on fundoscopy or fundus imaging.

label: Retinal cavernous hemangioma
definition: A benign tumor of the retina that appears as a grouping of blood-filled saccules within the inner retinal layers or on the surface of the optic disc. Retinal cavernous angioma are described as having a 'cluster of grapes' appearance.

label: Abnormal stereopsis
definition: Inability to make fine depth discriminations from parallax provided by the two eyes' different positions on the head.

label: Achromatopsia
definition: A condition where the retina contains no functional cone cells, so that in addition to the absence of color discrimination, vision in lights of normal intensity is difficult.

label: Dichromacy
definition: Individuals affected by dichromacy possess only two types of cones, instead of three.

label: Deuteranomaly
definition: A type of anomalous trichromacy associated with abnormal M photopigment, such that the absorption spectrum is shifted toward L wavelengths. Affected individuals have difficulties distinguishing between red and green.

label: Deuteranopia
definition: Complete lack of the M photopigment, which is replaced with the L photopigment. Affected individuals tend to confuse red and green.

label: Protanopia
definition: Blue and green cones only; no functional red cones.

label: Iris cyst
definition: An iris cyst is composed of a single cell layer of epithelium and is filled with fluid.

label: Iris melanoma
definition: Malignant tumor of melanocytes affecting the iris.

label: Iris nevus
definition: A benign brown pigmented area over the iris representing proliferation of melanocyte cells in the stromal layer of the iris. An iris nevus can be flat or occasionally slightly elevated.

label: Lentiglobus
definition: Exaggerated curvature of the lens of the eye, producing an anterior or posterior spherical bulging.

label: Solitary congenital hypertrophy of retinal pigment epithelium
definition: Sharply demarcated hyperpigmentation which is congenital found in around 3-5% of the population and of no functional significance.

label: Multiple bilateral congenital hypertrophy of retinal pigment epithelium
definition: Sharply demarcated hyperpigmentation which is congenital.

label: Retinal hole
definition: A small break in the retina.

label: Vitritis
definition: Inflammation of the vitreous body, characterized by the presence of inflammatory cells and protein exudate in the vitreous cavity.

label: Subretinal exudate
definition: A type of retinal exudate located in the subretinal space between the sensory retina and the retinal pigment epithelium.

label: Snowflake vitreoretinal degeneration
definition: The appearance of yellow/white crystalline-like (hence the name) spots in the retina and thickening of the peripheral part of the vitreous.

label: Abnormal atrial arrangement
definition: Abnormality of the spatial relationship of the atria to other components of the heart.

label: Right atrial isomerism
definition: Right atrial isomerism is characterized by bilateral triangular, morphologically right atrial, appendages, both joining the atrial chamber along a broad front with internal terminal crest.

label: Right isomerism
definition: A type of heterotaxy where some paired structures on opposite sides of the left-right axis of the body are symmetrical mirror images of each other, and have the morphology of the normal right-sided structures.

label: Left atrial isomerism
definition: In left atrial isomerism there is a bilateral small finger-shaped morphologically left atrial appendage joining the atrial chamber along a narrow front without an internal terminal crest.

label: Left Isomerism
definition: A type of heterotaxy where some paired structures on opposite sides of the left-right axis of the body are symmetrical mirror images of each other, and have the morphology of the normal left-sided structures.

label: Atrial situs inversus
definition: Mirror image atrial arrangement, with morphologic right atrium on the left hand side and morphologic left atrium on the right hand side.

label: Atrial situs ambiguous
definition: Common atrium without defining morphologic features.

label: Congenitally corrected transposition of the great arteries
definition: The essence of the lesion is the combination of discordant atrioventricular and ventriculo-arterial connections. Thus, the morphologically right atrium is connected to a morphologically left ventricle across the mitral valve, with the left ventricle then connected to the pulmonary trunk. The morphologically left atrium is connected to the morphologically right ventricle across the tricuspid valve, with the morphologically right ventricle connected to the aorta.

label: Criss-cross atrioventricular valves
definition: Crossing of the inflow streams of the two ventricles, due to an apparent twisting of the heart about its long axis.

label: Criss-cross atrioventricular valves with superior-inferior ventricles
definition: Criss-cross atrioventricular valves with a rare cardiac malformation characterized by the two ventricles lying one above the other instead of side by side.

label: Superior-inferior ventricles without criss-cross atrioventricular valves
Abnormal connection of the cardiac segments
definition: A deviance in the normal connections between two cardiac segments.

label: Abnormal atrioventricular connection
definition: An abnormality of the circulatory connection between atria and ventricles.

label: Absent left sided atrioventricular connection
definition: A defect where there is no connection between the left atrium and left ventricle.

label: Absent right sided atrioventricular connection
definition: A defect where there is no connection between the right atrium and right ventricle.

label: Univentricular heart with absent left sided atrioventricular connection
Biventricular heart with straddling right sided atrioventricular valve and absent left sided atrioventricular connection
Right sided atrium to left ventricle and absent left sided atrioventricular connection
Ambiguous atrioventricular connection
definition: With left or right cardiac isomerism in a biventricular, the atrioventricular connections are perforce ambiguous, in that one of the connections is concordant (e.g., right-sided morphologic right atrium connected to a morphologic right ventricle) and one of the connections is discordant (e.g., left-sided morphologic right atrium connected to a morphologic left ventricle).

label: Discordant atrioventricular connection
definition: Connection of the right atrium to the left ventricle and of the left atrium to the right ventricle in a biventricular heart.

label: Double inlet atrioventricular connection
definition: The condition in which both atria are joined to a single ventricle each by its own atrioventricular valve.

label: Double inlet left ventricle
definition: The condition in which both atria are joined to the left ventricle each by its own atrioventricular valve. Usually there is a hypoplastic right ventricle, which may be on the opposite side of the heart as usual.

label: Double inlet right ventricle
definition: The condition in which both atria are joined to the right ventricle each by its own atrioventricular valve. Usually, the left ventricle is hypoplastic.

label: Double inlet to single ventricle of indeterminate morphology
definition: The condition in which both atria are joined to a single ventricle each by its own atrioventricular valve. The morphology of this ventricle does not allow one to determine if it corresponds to the left or right ventricle.

label: Double inlet to single ventricle with common atrioventricular orifice
Double inlet to single ventricle with two atrioventricular valves
Mitral atresia
definition: A congenital defect with failure to open of the mitral valve orifice.

label: Overriding atrioventricular valve
definition: An atrioventricular valve that empties into both ventricles. The valve overrides the interventricular septum above a ventricular septum defect.

label: Straddling atrioventricular valve
definition: Anomalous insertion of the chordae tendinae or papillary muscles into the contralateral ventricle in the presence of a ventricular septum defect.

label: Mitral valve arcade
definition: Anomalous mitral valve arcade is diagnosed based on the following features (1) An adequately sized mitral valve orifice; (2) short, thick, and poorly differentiated chordae with direct union of the papillary muscles to the anterior leaflet; (3) narrow or nearly nonexistent spaces between the abnormal chordae; and (4) greater differentiation of the chordae attached to the posterior papillary muscle.

label: Common atrium
definition: Complete absence of the interatrial septum with common atrioventricular valve and two atrioventricular connections.

label: Cor triatriatum dexter
definition: A congenital anomaly with partitioning of the right atrium to form a triatrial heart caused by persistence of the right valve of the sinus venosus. Typically, the right atrial partition is due to exaggerated fetal eustachian and thebesian valves, which together form an incomplete septum across the lower part of the atrium. This septum may range from a reticulum to a substantial sheet of tissue.

label: Sinus venosus atrial septal defect
definition: An interatrial communication caused by a deficiency of the common wall between the superior vena cava (SVC) and the right-sided pulmonary veins. SVASD is commonly associated with anomalous pulmonary venous connection (APVC) of some or all of the pulmonary veins, which produces additional left-to-right shunting.

label: Double orifice mitral valve
definition: The left atrio-ventricular connection consists of two anatomically distinct orifices separated by accessory fibrous tissue.

label: Cleft anterior mitral valve leaflet
definition: Cleft in the anterior mitral valve leaflet not associated with an atrioventricular canal defect.

label: Abnormal mitral valve leaflet morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the leaflets (also known as cusps) of the mitral valve.

label: Congenital mitral stenosis
definition: Mitral stenosis with congenital onset.

label: Parachute mitral valve
definition: Abnormality of the mitral valve apparatus, whereby chordae attach to a single papillary muscle or hypoplastic papillary muscles.

label: Abnormal morphology of the chordae tendinae of the mitral valve
definition: A structural anomaly of the chordae tendinae of the mitral valve, whose main function is to transmit the contraction and relaxation of the papillary muscles during the cardiac cycle, thus ensuring the closing of the leaflets of the mitral valve.

label: Supramitral ring
definition: A congenital stenotic mitral valvular anomaly with a ring of tissue above the mitral valve.

label: Hypoplastic tricuspid valve
definition: Congenital defect characterized by underdevelopment of the tricuspid valve.

label: Imperforate atrioventricular valve
definition: An atrioventricular valve that has failed to open (atretic).

label: Imperforate tricuspid valve
definition: A tricuspid valve that has failed to open.

label: Intermediate atrioventricular canal defect
definition: A specific combination of heart defects with a primum atrial septal defect, cleft anterior mitral valve leaflet, and inlet ventricular defect. There is one valve annulus and two valve orifices.

label: Partial atrioventricular canal defect
definition: A specific combination of heart defects including a primum atrial septal defect and cleft anterior mitral valve leaflet. There is not an inlet ventricular septal defect present. There are two valve annuluses and two valve orifices.

label: Transitional atrioventricular canal defect
definition: A specific combination of heart defects with a primum atrial septal defect, cleft anterior mitral valve leaflet, and an inlet ventricular septal defect. There are two valve annuli and two valve orifices.

label: Unbalanced atrioventricular canal defect
definition: Anatomic features of unbalanced atrioventricular septal defect (AVSD) include varying amounts of ventricular hypoplasia, as well as malalignment of the atrioventricular junction. In complete AVSD, the common AV valve can be situated either equally over the right and left ventricles (balanced) or unequally over the ventricles (unbalanced).

label: Short chordae tendineae of the mitral valve
definition: Abnormally short chordae tendineae of the mitral valve.

label: Double outlet left ventricle
definition: A congenital defect of heart development characterized by origin of both pulmonary artery and aorta from the morphological left ventricle.

label: Abdominal ectopia cordis
definition: Displacement of the heart outside the thoracic cavity and into the abdomen.

label: Cervical ectopia cordis
definition: A type of ectopia cordis with the heart partially in the cervical region and without a defect of the sternum.

label: Thoracocervical ectopia cordis
definition: A type of ectopia cordis with the heart partially in the cervical region with a defect of the superior portion of the sternum.

label: Thoracic ectopia cordis
definition: Congenital malformation of the thoracic wall with partial or total displacement of the heart outside the thoracic cavity. This feature is associated with sternal cleft or absence of the sternum.

label: Thoracoabdominal ectopia cordis
definition: Congenital malformation of the ventral wall with partial or total evisceration of the heart outside the thoracic cavity and displacement partially into the abdominal cavity.

label: Cervical aortic arch
definition: The aortic arch extends into the soft tissues of the neck before turning down into to become the descending aorta.

label: Common origin of the right brachiocephalic artery and left common carotid artery
definition: The left common carotid artery has a common origin with the innominate artery.

label: Double aortic arch
definition: A conenital abnormality of the aortic arch in which the two embryonic aortc arches form a vascular ring that surrounds the trachea or esophagus and then join to form the descending aorta. Double aortic arch can cause symptoms because of compression of the esophagus (dysphagia, cyanosis while eating) or trachea (stridor).

label: Left aortic arch with cervical origin of the right subclavian artery
Abnormal branching pattern of left aortic arch
definition: A deviance from the norm of the origin or course of the right brachiocephalic artery, the left common carotid artery, the left subclavian artery or the proximal vertebral arteries, whereby the aortic arch descends on the left as normal (as opposed to right aortic arch).

label: Left aortic arch with isolated subclavian artery
definition: The subclavian artery arises from ductus arteriosus. While the ductus arteriosus is patent its blood supply comes from the ductus, hence from the pulmonary artery. After it closes, the blood supply is retrogradely from the vertebral artery via the circle of Willis.

label: Left aortic arch with retroesophageal diverticulum of Kommerell
definition: A patent ductus arteriosus or ductal ligament completes the ring.

label: Right aortic arch with retroesophageal diverticulum of Kommerell
definition: Aortic arch crosses the right mainstem bronchus. The left carotid artery is the first branch, right carotid artery the second branch and right subclavian artery as the third branch.

label: Left aortic arch with retroesophageal right subclavian artery
definition: Aortic arch crosses the left mainstem bronchus. The first branch is the right carotid artery, the second branch is the left carotid artery, the third branch is the subclavian artery, the fourth branch is the right subclavian artery arising from the posteromedial aspect of the distal aortic arch and continuing posterior to the esophagus to the right hand side of the body.

label: Left aortic arch with right descending aorta and right ductus arteriosus
definition: The ring may be completed by the ductal ligament.

label: Right aortic arch with left descending aorta and left ductus arteriosus
Right aortic arch with retroesophageal left subclavian artery
Mesocardia
definition: Mesocardia is an abnormal location of the heart in which the heart is in a midline position and the longitudinal axis of the heart lies in the mid-sagittal plane.

label: Abnormal direction of ventricular apex
definition: Abnormal plane of direction of the heart from the base to the apex. Left sided is normal.

label: Rightward direction of ventricular apex
definition: Abnormal plane of direction of the heart from the base to the apex towards the right. Left sided is normal.

label: Midline direction of ventricular apex
definition: Abnormal plane of direction of the heart from the base to the apex in the midline. Left sided is normal.

label: Aortopulmonary window
definition: A congenital anomaly with an abnormal connection between the aorta and the main pulmonary artery resulting in an aortopulmonary shunt.

label: Congenitally corrected transposition of the great arteries with ventricular septal defect
definition: A congenitally corrected transposition of the great arteries with a ventricular septal defect: a hole between the two bottom chambers (ventricles) of the heart. The ventricular septal defect is centered around the most superior aspect of the ventricular septum.

label: Type II truncus arteriosus
definition: Truncus arteriosus (single great artery leaving the base of the heart, giving rise to the coronary, pulmonary, and systemic arteries) with each pulmonary artery arising separate from each other on the posterior or lateral aspect of the truncus.

label: Type III truncus arteriosus
definition: Truncus arteriosus (single great artery leaving the base of the heart, giving rise to the coronary, pulmonary, and systemic arteries) whereby one of the two pulmonary artery branched does not arise from the common pulmonary trunk, but instead from the ductus arteriosus or directly from the aorta.

label: Type IV truncus arteriosus
definition: Truncus arteriosus (single great artery leaving the base of the heart, giving rise to the coronary, pulmonary, and systemic arteries) whereby the aortic arch is hypoplastic or interrupted, and a large patent ductus arteriosus is present.

label: Interrupted aortic arch
definition: Non-continuity of the arch of aorta with an atretic point or absent segment.

label: Interrupted aortic arch type A
definition: Non-continuity of the aortic arch with an atretic point or absent segment at the level of the isthmus.

label: Interrupted aortic arch type B
definition: Non-continuity of the aortic arch with an atretic point or absent segment between the left carotid and subclavian arteries.

label: Interrupted aortic arch type C
definition: Non-continuity of the aortic arch with an atretic point or absent segment between the innominate and left carotid arteries.

label: Abnormal pulmonary situs morphology
