label: Abnormal CSF dopamine concentration
definition: Abnormal concentration of dopamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Elevated CSF dopamine concentration
definition: Increased concentration of dopamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Reduced CSF dopamine concentration
definition: Decreased concentration of dopamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Abnormal brain positron emission tomography
definition: A functional brain anomaly detectable by positron emission tomography (PET). PET scanning is a method for functional brain imaging, and its measurements reflect the amount of brain activity in the various regions of the brain.

label: Brain imaging abnormality
definition: An anomaly of metabolism or structure of the brain identified by imaging.

label: Abnormal brain FDG positron emission tomography
definition: An anomaly detectable in [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) positron emission tomography (PET) brain scans. Glucose uptake measured with FDG-PET is a marker of neuronal metabolic activity.

label: Prefrontal hypometabolism in FDG PET
definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the prefrontal cortex as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

label: Thalamic hypometabolism in FDG PET
definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the thalamus as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

label: Hypothalamic hypometabolism in FDG PET
definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the hypothalamus as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

label: Parietal hypometabolism in FDG PET
definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the parietal cortex as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

label: Mildly reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
definition: A small reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle. The normal range in adults is at least 50 percent, and a mild reduction is defined as 40-49 percent.

label: Reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
definition: A diminution of the volumetric fraction of blood pumped out of the ventricle with each cardiac cycle.

label: Left ventricular systolic dysfunction
definition: Abnormality of left ventricular contraction, often defined operationally as an ejection fraction of less than 40 percent.

label: Abnormal left ventricular ejection fraction
definition: Any abnormality of the left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF), which is the fraction of chamber volume ejected in systole (stroke volume) in relation to the volume of the blood in the ventricle at the end of diastole (end-diastolic volume). Stroke volume (SV) is calculated as the difference between end-diastolic volume (EDV) and end-systolic volume (ESV). LVEF is calculated as [SV/EDV] in percent.

label: Moderately reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
definition: A medium reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle, defined as a left ventricular ejection fraction of 30-39 percent.

label: Severely reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
definition: A large reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle. The normal range in adults is at over 50 percent, and a severe reduction is defined as less than 30 percent.

label: Regional left ventricular wall motion abnormality
definition: An abnormal motion of a segment of the left ventricle during the cardiac cycle.

label: Vasovagal syncope
definition: A vasovagal episode or vasovagal syncope is the most common form of reflex syncope. Reflex syncope is a general term used to describe types of syncope resulting from a failure in autoregulation of blood pressure, and ultimately, in cerebral perfusion pressure resulting in transient loss of consciousness. The mechanisms responsible for this are complex and involve both depression of cardiac output as well as a decrease in vascular tone.

label: Carotid sinus syncope
definition: An exaggerated response to carotid sinus baroreceptor stimulation resulting in syncope from transient diminished cerebral perfusion.

label: Orthostatic syncope
definition: Syncope following a quick change in position from lying down to standing.

label: Abulia
definition: Abulia is characterized by difficulty in initiating and sustaining spontaneous movements; the person often appears frozen but will move hesitantly on request. There are frequently substantial reductions in emotional responsiveness, spontaneous speech, and social interaction. The individual appears to be content to remain still and inactive with minimal movement, but moves or reacts hesitantly in response to interactions.

label: Akinetic mutism
definition: The combined absence of spontaneous movement (akinesia) and speech (mutism). There may be eye movements consistent with visual tracking and the person may remember the events occurring at the time of the experience of stupor.

label: Aplasia of the upper vagina
definition: A failure to develop of the upper vagina.

label: Aplasia of the lower vagina
definition: A failure to develop of the lower part of the vagina.

label: Copper accumulation in brain
definition: An anomalous build up of copper (Cu) in the brain.

label: Iron accumulation in substantia nigra
definition: An anomalous build up of iron (Fe) in the substantia nigra.

label: Widened interpedicular distance
definition: An increase in the distance between vertebral pedicles, which are the two short, thick processes, which project backward, one on either side, from the upper part of the vertebral body, at the junction of its posterior and lateral surfaces.

label: Abnormality of the pineal gland
definition: An anomaly of the pineal gland,a small endocrine gland in the brain that produces melatonin.

label: Abnormal pineal morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the pineal gland.

label: Pineal gland calcification
definition: Accumulation of calcium salts in the pineal gland.

label: Pineal cyst
definition: A glial uniloculated or multiloculated fluid-filled sac that either reside within or completely replace the pineal gland.

label: Abnormal pineal volume
definition: An abnormal increase or decrease in the quantity of three-dimensional space taken up by the pineal gland.

label: Decreased pineal volume
definition: An abnormal reduction in the quantity of three-dimensional space taken up by the pineal gland.

label: Increased pineal volume
definition: An abnormal elevation in the quantity of three-dimensional space taken up by the pineal gland.

label: Agenesis of pineal gland
definition: Failure to develop of the pineal gland, defined clinically as the absence of the pineal gland with no indication of the pineal gland even having been present.

label: Abnormality of pineal physiology
definition: A functional abnormality of the pineal gland.

label: Abnormal pineal melatonin secretion
definition: An anomaly in the amount or timing of melatonin secretion by the pineal gland. Note that melatonin is also synthesized by multiple tissues outside of the pineal gland.

label: T2 hypointense thalamus
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus. This term refers to a diffuse hypointensity affecting the entire thalamus.

label: Abnormal thalamic MRI signal intensity
definition: A deviation from normal signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus.

label: Focal T2 hypointense thalamic lesion
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus. This term refers to a localized hypointensity affecting a particular region of the thalamus.

label: Focal T2 hyperintense thalamic lesion
definition: A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the thalamus. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the thalamus.

label: Abnormal thalamic size
definition: Deviation from the normal range of size of the thalamus.

label: Enlarged thalamic volume
definition: An increase in the quantity of space occupied by the thalamus.

label: Decreased thalamic volume
definition: A reduction in the quantity of space occupied by the thalamus.

label: Small basal ganglia
definition: Decreased size of the basal ganglia.

label: Cerebellar gliosis
definition: Focal proliferation of glial cells in the cerebellum.

label: Anomaly of lower limb diaphyses
definition: A structural abnormality of a diaphysis of the leg.

label: Bowel urgency
definition: A sudden, irresistible need to have a bowel movement.

label: Tenesmus
definition: A repeated, painful urge to defecate without excreting stool.

label: Widened subarachnoid space
definition: An increase in size of the anatomic space between the arachnoid membrane and pia mater.

label: Abnormal metabolic brain imaging by MRS
definition: An anomaly of metabolism in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Elevated brain choline level by MRS
definition: An increase in the level of choline-containing compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Abnormal brain choline level by MRS
definition: A deviation from normal in the level of choline-containing compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Elevated brain lactate level by MRS
definition: An increase in the level of lactate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Abnormal brain lactate level by MRS
definition: A deviation from normal of the level of lactate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Reduced brain N-acetyl aspartate level by MRS
definition: A decrease in the level of N-acetyl aspartate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Abnormal brain N-acetyl aspartate level by MRS
definition: A deviation from normal in the level of N-acetyl aspartate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Abnormal brain choline/creatine ratio by MRS
definition: A deviation from normal in the ratio of choline to creatine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Ingrown nail
definition: Excessive growth of a nail laterally into the nail fold.

label: Delayed ossification of vertebral epiphysis
definition: A delay in the process of formation and maturation of the epiphysis of one or more vertebrae.

label: Moderate conductive hearing impairment
definition: The presence of a moderate form of conductive hearing impairment.

label: Severe conductive hearing impairment
definition: A severe form of conductive hearing impairment.

label: Abnormal digestive system morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the digestive system.

label: Neoplasm of the nose
definition: Tumor (An abnormal mass of tissue resulting from abnormally dividing cells) of the nasal cavity.

label: Venous malformation
definition: A vascular malformation resulting from a developmental error of venous tissue composed of dysmorphic channels lined by flattened endothelium and exhibiting slow turnover. A venous malformation may present as a blue patch on the skin ranging to a soft blue mass. Venous malformations are easily compressible and usually swell in thewhen venous pressure increases (e.g., when held in a dependent position or when a child cries). They may be relatively localized or quite extensive within an anatomic region.

label: Sinoatrial block
definition: Disturbance in the atrial activation that is caused by transient failure of impulse conduction from the sinoatrial node to the cardiac atria.

label: Upper eyelid edema
definition: Edema in the region of the upper eyelid.

label: Episodic hypokalemia
definition: An abnormally decreased potassium concentration in the blood occurring periodically with a return to normal between the episodes.

label: Fusiform descending thoracic aortic aneurysm
definition: A concentric abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the descending thoracic aorta that involves the full circumference of the vessel wall

label: Saccular descending thoracic aortic aneurysm
definition: An eccentric abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the descending thoracic aorta that involves only a portion of the circumference of the vessel wall

label: Aglossia
definition: Absence of the tongue owing to a developmental abnormality.

label: Ectopic anterior pituitary gland
definition: Abnormal anatomic location of the anterior pituitary gland.

label: Ketotic hypoglycemia
definition: Low blood glucose is accompanied by elevated levels of ketone bodies in the body.

label: Cough
definition: A sudden, audible expulsion of air from the lungs through a partially closed glottis, preceded by inhalation.

label: Profound global developmental delay
definition: A profound delay in the achievement of motor or mental milestones in the domains of development of a child.

label: Small intestinal polyp
definition: A discrete abnormal tissue mass that protrudes into the lumen of the small intestine and is attached to the intestinal wall either by a stalk, pedunculus, or a broad base.

label: Agenesis of canine
definition: Agenesis of canine tooth.

label: Agenesis of the small intestine
definition: Failure to develop of the small intestine.

label: Papilloma
definition: A tumor of the skin or mucous membrane with finger-like projections.

label: Unilateral cryptorchidism
definition: Absence of a testis from the scrotum on one side owing to failure of the testis or testes to descend through the inguinal canal to the scrotum.

label: Thin fingernail
definition: Fingernail that appears thin when viewed on end.

label: Abdominal obesity
definition: Excessive fat around the stomach and abdomen.

label: Femoral aplasia
definition: Failure of the femur to develop.

label: Short palpebral fissure
definition: Distance between the medial and lateral canthi is more than 2 SD below the mean for age (objective); or, apparently reduced length of the palpebral fissures.

label: Thin toenail
definition: Toenail that appears thin when viewed on end.

label: Abnormal brainstem MRI signal intensity
definition: A deviation from normal signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem.

label: Focal T2 hyperintense brainstem lesion
definition: A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the brainstem.

label: Focal T2 hypointense brainstem lesion
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a localized hypointensity affecting a particular region of the brainstem.

label: T2 hypointense brainstem
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a diffuse hypointensity affecting the entire brainstem.

label: Focal T2 hypointense basal ganglia lesion
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a localized hypointensity affecting a particular region of the basal ganglia.

label: T2 hypointense basal ganglia
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the basal ganglia. This term refers to a diffuse hypointensity affecting all of the basal ganglia.

label: CNS hypermyelination
definition: Increased amount of myelin in the central nervous system.

label: Enlarged brainstem
definition: Abnormal increase in size of the brainstem.

label: CSF polymorphonuclear pleocytosis
definition: An increased polymorphonuclear cell count in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Absent mastoid
definition: A developmental anomaly in which the mastoid process fails to form and is thus found to be congenitally absent.

label: Paroxysmal dyspnea
definition: A sudden attack of dyspnea that occurs while the affected person is at rest.

label: Orthopnea
definition: A sensation of breathlessness in the recumbent position, relieved by sitting or standing.

label: Widened cerebellar subarachnoid space
definition: An increase in size of the anatomic space between the arachnoid membrane and pia mater in the region surrounding the cerebellum.

label: Widened cerebral subarachnoid space
definition: An increase in size of the anatomic space between the arachnoid membrane and pia mater in the region surrounding the cerebrum.

label: Neonatal asphyxia
definition: Respiratory failure in the newborn.

label: Abnormal arm span
definition: A deviation from normal of the length of the arm span (length from one end of an individual's arms measured at the fingertips to the other when raised parallel to the ground at shoulder height at a one-hundred eighty degree angle)

label: Reduced arm span
definition: Decreased length of the arm span (length from one end of an individual's arms measured at the fingertips to the other when raised parallel to the ground at shoulder height at a one-hundred eighty degree angle).

label: Increased arm span
definition: Increased length of the arm span (length from one end of an individual's arms measured at the fingertips to the other when raised parallel to the ground at shoulder height at a one-hundred eighty degree angle).

label: Abnormal upper to lower segment ratio
definition: A deviation from normal of the relation between the upper and the lower segment of the body, where the lower segment is defined as the length between the top of pubic symphysis to floor, and the upper segment is defined as the top of head to top of pubic symphysis.

label: Reduced upper to lower segment ratio
definition: Decreased ratio between the upper and the lower segment of the body, where the lower segment is defined as the length between the top of pubic symphysis to floor, and the upper segment is defined as the top of head to top of pubic symphysis. Consider the term Disproportionate tall stature (HP:0001519) if tall stature is also present.

label: Increased upper to lower segment ratio
definition: Elevated ratio between the upper and the lower segment of the body, where the lower segment is defined as the length between the top of pubic symphysis to floor, and the upper segment is defined as the top of head to top of pubic symphysis.

label: Stellate iris
definition: A lacy pattern or iris pigmentation that resembles the spokes of a bicycle wheel.

label: Retinal astrocytic hamartoma
definition: A glial tumor of the retinal nerve fiber layer arising from a retinal astrocyte.

label: Transient hearing impairment
definition: Hearing loss that occurs acutely and resolves completely.

label: Neoplasm of the ear
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ear.

label: Mid-frequency hearing loss
definition: A type of hearing impairment affecting primarily the middle frequencies of sound (1000 Hz to 3000 Hz).

label: Perilobar nephrogenic rest
definition: A type of nephrogenic rest associated with multiple lesions in the periphery of the renal lobe.

label: Nephrogenic rest
definition: Abnormally persistent clusters of embryonal cells, representing microscopic malformations (dysplasias) of the developing kidney.

label: Intralobar nephrogenic rest
definition: A type of nephrogenic rest usually representing single lesions within the renal lobe, renal sinus, or calyceal walls.

label: Perinephritis
definition: Inflammation of the connective and adipose tissues surrounding the kidney.

label: Finger joint contracture
definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of a finger joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

label: Recurrent cystitis
definition: Repeated infections of the urinary bladder.

label: Recurrent pyelonephritis
definition: Repeated episodes of pyelonephritis.

label: Reticulate pigmentation of oral mucosa
definition: A net-like pattern of increased pigmentation of the oral cavity.

label: Hypoplasia of the calcaneus
definition: Underdevelopment of the heel bone.

label: Abnormal intramembranous ossification
definition: An anomaly in the process of intramembranous ossification by which flat bones (cranial bones of the skull, i.e., the frontal, parietal, occipital, and temporal bones, and the clavicles) are formed.

label: Absent ossification of thoracic vertebral bodies
definition: A lack of bone mineralization of one or more body of thoracic vertebra.

label: Kinked brainstem
definition: A kinked appearance of the brainstem, i.e., an exaggerated flexure.

label: Periventricular white matter hypodensities
definition: Multiple areas of darker than expected signal on magnetic resonance imaging emanating from the cerebral white matter that surrounds the cerebral ventricles.

label: Increased cup-to-disc ratio
definition: An elevation in the ratio of the diameter of the cup of the optic disc to the total diameter of the disk. The optic disc has an orange-pink rim with a pale center (the cup) that does not contain neuroretinal tissue. An increase in this ratio therefore may indicate a decrease in the quantity of healthy neuroretinal cells.

label: Lymphatic vessel neoplasm
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm arising from the lymphatic vessels.

label: Pulmonary lymphangiomyomatosis
definition: Infiltration of smooth muscle-like cells in lymph vessels as well as the lung (pleura, alveolar septa, bronchi, pulmonary vessels and lymphatics as well as lymph nodes, especially in posterior mediastinum and retroperitoneum). Focal emphysema can develop because of airway narrowing, and the thoracic duct may be obliterated. Pulmonary lymphangiomyomatosis may lead to multiple small cysts with a hamartomatous proliferation of smooth muscle in their walls.

label: Unilateral facial palsy
definition: One-sided weakness of the muscles of facial expression and eye closure.

label: Accessory cranial suture
definition: A cranial suture that is in addition to canonical membrane-covered openings in the incompletely ossified skull of the fetus or newborn infant.

label: Narrow jaw
definition: Bigonial distance (lower facial width) more than 2 standard deviations below the mean (objective); or an apparently decreased width of the lower jaw (mandible) when viewed from the front (subjective).

label: Broad jaw
definition: Bigonial distance (lower facial width) more than 2 SD above the mean (objective); or an apparently increased width of the lower jaw (mandible) when viewed from the front (subjective).

label: Anisometropia
definition: Inequality of refractive power of the two eyes.

label: Iris transillumination defect
definition: Transmission of light through the iris as visualized upon slit lamp examination or infrared iris transillumination videography. The light passes through defects in the pigmentation of the iris.

label: Proboscis
definition: A fleshy, tube-like structure usually located in the midline of the face or just to one side of the midline.

label: High insertion of columella
definition: Insertion of the posterior columella superior to the nasal base.

label: Abnormal nasal base norphology
definition: An anomaly of the nasal base, which can be conceived of as an imaginary line between the most lateral points of the external inferior attachments of the alae nasi to the face.

label: Narrow nasal base
definition: Decreased distance between the attachments of the alae nasi to the face.

label: Wide nasal base
definition: Increased distance between the attachments of the alae nasi to the face.

label: Wide nasal ridge
definition: Increased width of the nasal ridge.

label: Unilateral breast hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the breast on one side only.

label: Bilateral breast hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the breast on both sides.

label: Right ventricular noncompaction cardiomyopathy
definition: A predominantly right ventricular variant of isolated noncompaction cardiomyopathy.

label: Biventricular noncompaction cardiomyopathy
definition: Noncompaction cardiomyopathy that affects both ventricles.

label: Myocarditis
definition: Inflammation of the myocardium.

label: Bilateral vocal cord paralysis
definition: A loss of the ability to move the vocal fold on both sides.

label: Unilateral vocal cord paresis
definition: Decreased strength of the vocal fold on one side.

label: Bilateral vocal cord paresis
definition: Decreased strength of the vocal fold on both sides.

label: Severity
definition: The intensity or degree of a manifestation.

label: Mild
definition: Having a relatively minor degree of severity. For quantitative traits, a deviation of between two and three standard deviations from the appropriate population mean.

label: Moderate
definition: Having a medium degree of severity. For quantitative traits, a deviation of between three and four standard deviations from the appropriate population mean.

label: Borderline
definition: Having a minor degree of severity that is considered to be on the boundary between the normal and the abnormal ranges. For quantitative traits, a deviation of that is less than two standard deviations from the appropriate population mean.

label: Severe
definition: Having a high degree of severity. For quantitative traits, a deviation of between four and five standard deviations from the appropriate population mean.

label: Profound
definition: Having an extremely high degree of severity. For quantitative traits, a deviation of more than five standard deviations from the appropriate population mean.

label: Position
definition: The anatomical localization of the specified phenotypic abnormality.

label: Laterality
definition: The localization with respect to the side of the body of the specified phenotypic abnormality.

label: Bilateral
definition: Being present on both sides of the body.

label: Unilateral
definition: Being present on only the left or only the right side of the body.

label: Right
definition: Being located on the right side of the body.

label: Left
definition: Being located on the left side of the body.

label: Spatial pattern
definition: The pattern by which a phenotype affects one or more regions of the body.

label: Generalized
definition: Affecting all regions without specificity of distribution.

label: Localized
definition: Being confined or restricted to a particular location.

label: Distal
definition: Localized away from the central point of the body.

label: Proximal
definition: Localized close to the central point of the body.

label: Skin appendage neoplasm
definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from the hair follicles, sebaceous glands, or sweat glands.

label: Hair follicle neoplasm
definition: An uncontrolled autonomous cell-proliferation originating in a hair follicle, which is an epidermal adnexal structures responsible for hair growth.

label: Trichilemmoma
definition: A benign tumor originating from the outer root sheath of the hair follicle.

label: Single trichilemmoma
definition: Presence of a unitary trichilemmoma, a benign tumor originating from the outer root sheath of the hair follicle.

label: Multiple trichilemmomata
definition: Presence of multiple trichilemmomata, a benign tumor originating from the outer root sheath of the hair follicle.

label: Epilepsia partialis continua
definition: Epilepsia partialis continua (also called Kojevnikov's or Kozhevnikov's epilepsia) is a type of focal motor status epilepticus characterized by repeated stereotyped simple motor manifestations such as jerks, typically of a limb or the face, recurring every few seconds or minutes for extended periods (days or years).

label: Focal motor status epilepticus
definition: Status epilepticus with focal motor signs originating within networks limited to one hemisphere. Involves musculature in any form. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement.

label: Small intestinal stenosis
definition: The narrowing or partial blockage of a portion of the small intestine.

label: Small intestinal bleeding
definition: Bleeding from the small intestine.

label: Small intestinal dysmotility
definition: Abnormal small intestinal contractions, such as spasms and intestinal paralysis related to the loss of the ability of the gut to coordinate muscular activity because of endogenous or exogenous causes.

label: Colonic stenosis
definition: A narrowing of a segment of colon whereby bowel continuity is maintained.

label: Hepatic bridging fibrosis
definition: Hepatic fibrosis that reaches from a portal area to another portal area.

label: Scrotal hypospadias
definition: Hypospadias with location of the urethral meatus in the scrotum.

label: Midshaft hypospadias
definition: Hypospadias with location of the urethral meatus in the middle of the inferior shaft of the penis.

label: Scrotal hyperpigmentation
definition: Increased pigmentation (skin color) of the scrotum.

label: Abnormal scrotal rugation
definition: Anomaly of the folded ridges (wrinkles) of skin of the scrotum.

label: Increased scrotal rugation
definition: Increased number or density of the folded ridges (wrinkles) of skin of the scrotum.

label: Decreased scrotal rugation
definition: Decreased number or density of the folded ridges (wrinkles) of skin of the scrotum.

label: Esophageal leukoplakia
definition: A white patch or plaque occurring on the surface of the esophageal mucous membranes that cannot be rubbed off and cannot be characterized clinically as any other disease.

label: Testicular fibrosis
definition: Formation of excess connective tissue in the testicle.

label: Ovotestis
definition: A gonad that contains both ovarian follicles and testicular tubular elements.

label: Abnormal germ cell morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of a reproductive cell.

label: Abnormal male germ cell morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of a male reproductive cell.

label: Abnormal sperm morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of sperm.

label: Abnormal sperm neck morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the sperm neck.

label: Abnormal sperm mid-piece morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the sperm mid-piece.

label: Abnormal sperm tail morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the sperm tail.

label: Acephalic spermatozoa
definition: Spermatozoa with very small cranial ends devoid of any nuclear material, that is, lacking a typical sperm head.

label: Vanishing testis
definition: A condition which is considered to be due to the subsequent atrophy and disappearance in fetal life of an initially normal testis. In the presence of spermatic cord structures is evidence of the presence of the testis in early intrauterine life. When associated with a blind-ending spermatic cord, this entity is named as his absence of a testis in an otherwise normal 46XY male is usually unilateral and is assumed to be a consequence of intrauterine or perinatal torsion or infarction.

label: Varicocele
definition: A varicocele is a widening of the veins along the spermatic cord, leading to enlarged, twisted veins in the scrotum, and manifested clinically by a painless testicle lump, scrotal swelling, or bulge in the scrotum.

label: Abnormal vas deferens morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the secretory duct of the testicle that carries spermatozoa from the epididymis to the prostatic urethra where it terminates to form ejaculatory duct.

label: Absent vas deferens
definition: Aplasia (congenital absence) of the vas deferens.

label: Abnormal ejaculation
definition: Abnormality in the process of ejection of semen (usually carrying sperm) from the male reproductive tract.

label: Premature ejaculation
definition: The emission of semen and seminal fluid during the act of preparation for sexual intercourse, i.e. before there is penetration, or shortly after penetration.

label: Retrograde ejaculation
definition: The emission of semen and seminal fluid into the bladder instead of through the penis during orgasm.

label: Retarded ejaculation
definition: Difficulty of a male in achieving orgasm.

label: Anejaculation
definition: Inability to ejaculate.

label: Hyperplastic labia majora
definition: Overgrowth of the outer labia.

label: Fallopian tube cyst
definition: A fluid filled sac located in the Fallopian tube.

label: Fallopian tube torsion
definition: A twisting of the Fallopian tube. Sudden onset with sharp, colicky pelvic pain associated with nausea, vomiting, bowel, and bladder symptoms is the usual presentation.

label: Fallopian tube duplication
definition: The presence of a supernumerary Fallopian tube.

label: Hemorrhagic ovarian cyst
definition: An abdominal mass formed by bleeding into a follicular ovarian cyst or corpus luteum cyst.

label: Ovarian serous cystadenoma
definition: A cystic tumor of the ovary, containing thin, clear, yellow serous fluid and varying amounts of solid tissue.

label: Abnormal uterine cervix morphology
definition: An anomaly of the neck of the uterus (lower part of the uterus), called the uterine cervix.

label: Cervical endometriosis
definition: Abnormal growth of endometrial cells (which are normally limited to the uterus) within the cervix.

label: Endometriosis
definition: The growth of endometrial tissue outside the uterus.

label: Posteriorly placed anus
definition: Posterior malposition of the anus.

label: High posterior hairline
definition: Hair on the neck extends less inferiorly than usual.

label: Facial muscle hypertrophy
definition: Hypertrophy of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

label: Neck muscle hypertrophy
definition: Muscle hypertrophy affecting the muscles of the neck.

label: Paraspinal muscle hypertrophy
definition: Muscle hypertrophy affecting the paraspinal muscles.

label: Scapular muscle hypertrophy
definition: Muscle hypertrophy affecting the scapular muscles.

label: Abnormal motor evoked potentials
definition: An anomaly identified by motor evoked potentials (MEPs). MEPs are measured following single-pulse or repetitive transcranial magnetic stimulation and can be used for the assessment of the excitability of the motor cortex and the integrity of conduction along the central and peripheral motor pathways.

label: Abnormal upper-limb motor evoked potentials
definition: An anomaly identified by motor evoked potentials (MEPs) in the arm.

label: Abnormal lower-limb motor evoked potentials
definition: An anomaly identified by motor evoked potentials (MEPs) in the leg.

label: Handgrip myotonia
definition: Difficulty releasing one's grip associated with prolonged first handgrip relaxation times.

label: Myotonia of the face
definition: Slowed relaxation of muscles in the face.

label: Myotonia of the jaw
definition: Slowed relaxation of muscles in the jaw.

label: Myotonia of the lower limb
definition: Slowed relaxation of muscles in the leg.

label: Myotonia of the upper limb
definition: Slowed relaxation of muscles in the arm.

label: Cold-sensitive myotonia
definition: An involuntary and painless delay in the relaxation of skeletal muscle following contraction or electrical stimulation that is induced by exposure to cold.

label: Euryblepharon
definition: Euryblepharon is a congenital eyelid anomaly characterized by horizontal enlargement of the palpebral fissure. The eyelid is shortened vertically compared with the horizontal dimension, with associated lateral canthal malpositioning and lateral ectropion abnormally wide lid opening.

label: Ciliary body coloboma
definition: A coloboma of the ciliary body.

label: Diffuse
definition: A spatial pattern that is spread out, i.e., not localized.

label: Lower limb dysmetria
definition: A lack of coordination of leg movement manifested by undershoot or overshoot of the intended position of the leg.

label: Upper limb dysmetria
definition: A lack of coordination of arm movement manifested by undershoot or overshoot of the intended position of the arm.

label: Astasia
definition: A postural abnormality characterized by the inability to stand without external support despite having sufficient muscle strength.

label: Vertebrobasilar dolichoectasia
definition: Elongation, dilatation, and/or tortuosity of the vertebrobasilar segment. The definition of VBD includes: (i) diameter of basilar or vertebral artery over 4.5 mm; or (ii) deviation of any portion more than 10 mm from the shortest expected course; and (iii) length of basilar artery over 29.5 mm or length of intracranial vertebral artery over 23.5 mm.

label: Abnormal vertebral artery morphology
definition: An anomaly of the vertebral artery, the major artery of the neck that originates from the subclavian artery and merges to form the single midline basilar artery in a complex called the vertebrobasilar system.

label: Double elevator palsy
definition: A type of incomitant strabismus in which both elevator muscles (i.e., the inferior oblique and superior rectus muscles) of the same eye are weak leading to restricted elevation and hypotropia.

label: Double depressor palsy
definition: An ocular movement abnormality characterized by simultaneous weakness of the inferior rectus muscle and superior oblique muscle of the same eye.

label: Vertical incomitant strabismus
definition: A type of incomitant strabismus in which the angle of deviation varies as the patient's gaze shifts upwards and/or downwards.

label: Accommodative esotropia
definition: A form of esotropia (convergent deviation of the eyes) associated with activation of the accommodative reflex.

label: Abnormal myeloid cell morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of a cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.

label: Reduced bone-marrow pro-B cell count
definition: A reduction in the numbers of pro-B cells (defined by coexpression of CD34 and CD19). Earlier B-cell precursors are defined by expressing surface CD34 and cytoplasmic TdT in the absence of CD19.

label: Anti-granulocyte-macrophage colony stimulating factor antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against granulocyte-macrophage colony stimulating factor.

label: Abnormal red blood cell count
definition: Any deviation from the normal number of red blood cells per volume in the circulation.

label: Increased red blood cell count
definition: An abnormal elevation above the normal number of red blood cells per volume in the circulation.

label: Decreased red blood cell count
definition: An abnormal reduction below the normal number of red blood cells per volume in the circulation.

label: Decreased hemoglobin concentration
definition: An abnormal reduction below normal hemoglobin concentration in the circulation.

label: Viremia
definition: The presence of virus in the blood.

label: Bloodstream infectious agent
definition: The presence of an infectious agent in the blood circulation.

label: Persistent EBV viremia
definition: Persistent presence of Epstein-Barr virus in the blood.

label: Persistent viremia
definition: Persistence of virus in the blood circulation longer than would be normal in an immunocompetent host.

label: Leucine crystalluria
definition: The presence of leucine crystals in the urine.

label: Wrist ganglion
definition: A benign soft tissue tumor of the wrist usually found in the dorsal aspect of the wrist and communicate with the joint via a pedicle. This pedicle usually originates not only at the scapholunate ligament, but also may arise from a number of other sites over the dorsal aspect of the wrist capsule.

label: Carnitinuria
definition: An elevated level of carnitine in the urine.

label: Alaninuria
definition: An increased level of alanine in the urine.

label: Beta-alaninuria
definition: The amount of beta-alanine in the urine, when normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Erythrocyte inclusion bodies
definition: Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates of substances in red blood cells.

label: Pappenheimer bodies
definition: A type of erythrocyte inclusion characterized by basophilic stippling of erythrocytes, that is, by numerous very small coarse or fine blue granules within the cytoplasm with the additional stipulation that the stippled particles are due to iron granules (demonstrable by the Prussian blue stain).

label: Heinz bodies
definition: A type of erythrocyte inclusion composed of denatured hemoglobin.

label: Furuncle
definition: An infection of a hair follicle that extends subcutaneously, forming an abscess.

label: Folliculitis
definition: Inflammatory cells within the wall and ostia of the hair follicle, creating a follicular-based pustule.

label: Carbuncle
definition: A pustular lesion of the skin emerging from group of infected hair follicles, characterized by a deep location and dissecting through tissue planes. A carbuncle is larger and deeper than a furuncle.

label: Infection following live vaccination
definition: An infection resulting from live attenuated vaccines (LAV), that is, a vaccine prepared from living viruses or bacteria that have been weakened under laboratory conditions. LAV vaccines will replicate in a vaccinated individual and produce an immune response but usually cause mild or no disease. are derived from disease-causing pathogens.

label: BCGitis
definition: Local or regional infection with Bacillus Calmette-Guerin (BCG) following vaccination.

label: BCGosis
definition: Distant, or disseminated infection with Bacillus Calmette-Guerin (BCG) following vaccination associated with failure to contain thebacillus Calmette-Guerin (BCG) following vaccination leading to spread of BCG to many sites in the body. The tuberculosis vaccine BCG contains live attenuated Mycobacterium bovis.

label: Post-vaccination measles
definition: Infection with the measles virus of the live-attenuated vaccine. This is an extremely rare event and may indicate immunocompromise in some cases.

label: Post-vaccination rubella
definition: Infection with the rubella virus of the live-attenuated vaccine.

label: Post-vaccination polio
definition: Infection with live attenuated polio vaccine following vaccination. This is an extremely rare event that may indicate immunocompromise.

label: Post-vaccination rotavirus infection
definition: Infection with live attenuated rotavirus vaccine following vaccination.

label: Recurrent deep organ abscess formation
definition: Repeated episodes of the formation of abscesses in organs. An abscess is a circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris in the parenchyma or an organ.

label: Prolonged need of intravenous antibiotic therapy
definition: Clinical assessment of a requirement to treat with intravenous antibiotics over an unusually prolonged period of time.

label: Infection due to encapsulated bacteria
definition: An infection by an encapsulated bacterial agent. Isolates which cause invasive disease are usually surrounded by a polysaccharide capsule, which is a major virulence factor and the key antigen in protective protein-polysaccharide conjugate vaccines.

label: Opportunistic bacterial infection
definition: An infection that is caused by a bacterium that would generally not be able to cause an infection in a host with a normal immune system. Such bacteria take advantage of the opportunity, so to speak, that is provided by a weakened immune system.

label: Severe norovirus infection
definition: An unusually severe course of infection with Human norovirus, previously known as Norwalk virus. Norovirus, an RNA virus of the family Caliciviridae, is a human enteric pathogen. Norovirus infection-associated illness may also be more prolonged and severe in immunocompromised individuals and may be associated with remarkably persistent viral excretion in some of these individuals.

label: Invasive fungal infection
definition: Fungal infection characterized by invasion of host tissues.

label: Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia
definition: An opportunistic disease caused by invasion of unicellular fungus Pneumocystis jirovecii. Transmission of P. jirovecii cysts takes place through the airborne route, and usually, its presence in lungs is asymptomatic. However, people with impaired immunity, especially those with CD4+ T cell count below 200/microliter, are still at risk of the development of Pneumocystis pneumonia due to P. jirovecii invasion. Symptoms induced by this disease are not specific: progressive dyspnea, non-productive cough, low-grade fever, arterial partial pressure of oxygen below 65 mmHg, and chest radiographs demonstrating bilateral, interstitial shadowing.

label: Opportunistic fungal infection
definition: An infection that is caused by a fungus that would generally not be able to cause an infection in a host with a normal immune system. Such fungi take advantage of the opportunity, so to speak, that is provided by a weakened immune system.

label: Invasive pulmonary aspergillosis
definition: Infection of the lungs with aspergillus. In the respiratory mucosa, the spores may germinate into hyphae, which in turn can invade the mucosa leading to invasive pulmonary aspergillosis.

label: Unusual protozoan infection
definition: An unusual protozoan infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection by a protozoal agent.

label: Severe toxoplasmosis
definition: Toxoplasmosis is a widespread parasitic infection that is frequently asymptomatic in immunocompetent patients. However, this obligate intracellular protozoan parasite can evade the immune system and persist for the life of its host in cyst form, predominantly in the brain, retina, and muscles. Reactivation of latent cysts may occur when the immune system fails to maintain cytokine pressure, which mainly relies on gamma interferon (IFN-gamma). Toxoplasmosis is a life-threatening infection in immunocompromised patients (ICPs).

label: Severe giardiasis
definition: An unusually severe infection due to Giardia lamblia, also called Giardia duodenalis or Giardia intestinalis, which is a protozoan parasite of the small intestine that causes extensive morbidity worldwide.

label: Unusual helminthic infection
definition: An unusual helminthic infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection by a worm (helminth).

label: Unusual parasitic infection
definition: An unusual parasitic infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection by a parasite.

label: Abnormal CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cell proportion
definition: A deviation from the normal proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.

label: Increased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells
definition: An abnormally increased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.

label: Decreased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells
definition: An abnormally decreased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.

label: Persistent human papillomavirus infection
definition: Human papillomaviruses (HPVs) are small oncogenic viruses. HPV has been shown to cause a variety of lesions and malignancies, which predominantly affect the anogenital region. Low-risk, non-oncogenic HPV types are associated with anogenital warts and recurrent respiratory papillomatosis while high-risk, oncogenic types are associated with cervical, penile, anal, vaginal, vulvar, and oropharyngeal cancers. Infection with anogenital HPV is usually asymptomatic and resolves spontaneously without consequences in the immunocompetent host. When disease does occur, the most common manifestation is genital warts, which may be small papules, or flat, smooth or pedunculated lesions. This resolution of HPV lesions is not generally seen in the immunosuppressed, resulting in severe, persistent and extensive manifestations of HPV disease.

label: Hypoplastic dermoepidermal hemidesmosomes
definition: Underdeveloped hemidesmosomes at the dermoepidermal junction. Hemidesmosomes are the specialized junctional complexes, that contribute to the attachment of epithelial cells to the underlying basement membrane in stratified and other complex epithelia, such as the skin.

label: Abnormal dermoepidermal hemidesmosome morphology
definition: An abnormal structure or appearance of hemidesmosomes, multiprotein complexes that facilitate the stable adhesion of basal epithelial cells to the underlying basement membrane.

label: Radial artery aplasia
definition: Congenital absence of the radial artery.

label: Abnormal radial artery morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the radial artery.

label: Retinal nerve fiber edema
definition: Swelling (edema) of the retinal nerve fibers.

label: Conception by assisted reproductive technology
definition: A history of conception by an assisted reproductive technology such as in vitro fertilization (IVF), intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI), and cryopreservation.

label: Bite cells
definition: Red blood cells that appear to have parts of them bitten away.

label: Tympanosclerosis
definition: A stiffening of the tympanic membrane due to calcification, typically presents as white plaque-like lesions, involving discrete regions of the tympanic membrane and/or middle ear.

label: Spontaneous conjunctival filtering bleb
definition: Avascular cystic elevations of the superior conjunctiva not related to ocular surgery or trauma.

label: Prostate mass
definition: A lump detected in the prostate. In this context, mass is a general term for a lump or growth that may be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes, or an immune reaction.

label: Periarticular soft-tissue mass
definition: A lump detected in the region that surrounds a joint. In this context, mass is a general term for a lump or growth that may be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes, or an immune reaction.

label: Aplasia of the olfactory tract
definition: Aplasia (congenital absence) of the olfactory tract, which causes anosmia, a complete loss of the sense of smell.

label: Increased urinary neutrophil gelatinase-associated lipocalin
definition: An increased concentration of neutrophil gelatinase-associated lipocalin in the urine (there is no generally accepted threshold, but some studies choose a threshold of above 150 nanogram per milliliter).

label: Thickening of the tubular basement membrane
definition: Increase in thickness of the basement membrane of the tubulus of the kidney.

label: Podocyte hypertrophy
definition: Increased visceral epithelial cell size, with or without cytoplasmic protein droplets.

label: Abnormal glomerular visceral epithelial cell morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the podocyte, which is a highly specialized cell of the Bowman capsule and which forms multiple interdigitating foot processes. Podocytes are interconnected by slit diaphragms and cover the exterior basement membrane surface of the glomerular capillary.

label: Increased urine neutrophil count
definition: Abnormally increased count of neutrophils in urine.

label: Myofibromatosis
definition: A mesenchymal neoplasm characterized by solitary or multiple nodules involving the skin, striated muscles, bones and, sometimes, viscera. It usually appears as a subcutaneous nodule, but can also appear as an ulcer, pedunculated lesion, or similar to a hemangioma. Histology shows well-circumscribed tapered cell lobes, resembling smooth muscle cells. At its center, perivascular round cells (hemangiopericitoides) are usually observed, giving a biphasic appearance.

label: Anticardiolipin IgG antibody positivity
definition: The presence of circulating IgG autoantibodies to cardiolipin.

label: Anticardiolipin IgM antibody positivity
definition: The presence of circulating IgM autoantibodies to cardiolipin.

label: History of recent animal bite
definition: Medical history of a recent bite injury due to an animal.

label: Recent past medical history
definition: History of events that precede the current presenting condition and are thought to be of potential relevance, having occurred in the hours, days, or weeks before the current condition.

label: History of recent insect bite
definition: Medical history of a recent bite injury due to an insect.

label: History of recent tick bite
definition: Medical history of a recent bite injury due to a tick.

label: Blood pressure substantially higher in legs than arms
definition: An abnormal blood pressure discrepancy between the upper and lower extremities with the blood pressure measured in the legs being much higher than the blood pressure measure in the arms. In healthy individuals, ankle systolic blood pressures are only slightly higher than the systolic blood pressure measured in the arm.

label: Blood pressure substantially higher in arms than legs
definition: An abnormal blood pressure discrepancy between the upper and lower extremities with the blood pressure measured in the arms being much higher than the blood pressure measure in the legs. In healthy individuals, ankle systolic blood pressures are only slightly higher than the systolic blood pressure measured in the arm.

label: Tracheal duplication cyst
definition: A cyst in the trachea, whose wall is made up by tissue similar to the bronchial tree, including cartilage and smooth muscle, and is lined by secretory respiratory epithelium composed of cuboid or columnar ciliated epithelium.

label: Calcium phosphate crystalluria
definition: The presence of calcium phosphate crystals in the urine.

label: Calcium oxalate crystalluria
definition: The presence of calcium oxalate crystals in the urine.

label: Calcium carbonate crystalluria
definition: The presence of calcium carbonate crystals in the urine.

label: 2-Methylbutyryl glycinuria
definition: Increased concentration of 2-methylbutyryl glycine in the urine.

label: Increased circulating mead acid level
definition: An abnormally elevated concentration od mead acid in the blood circulation.

label: Elevated circulating succinate
definition: An increase concentration of succinate in the blood circulation.

label: Elevated urinary uromodulin level
definition: The concentration of uromodulin (also known as Tamm Horsfall protein) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal urinary uromodulin level
definition: The concentration of uromodulin (also known as Tamm Horsfall protein) in the urine, normalized for usine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

label: Anti-dsDNA antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against double-stranded DNA.

label: Distal joint hypermobility
definition: Lack of stability of a distal joint (e.g., finger).

label: Positive blood 1,3 beta glucan test
definition: Beta-1,3-glucan is a major constituent of all of the characterized fungal cell walls, making up between 30-80 percent of the mass of the wall. It is a biomarker of fungal infections such as invasive pulmonary aspergillosis.

label: Blood xenobiotic
definition: The presence of a xenobiotic in blood.

label: Nevus comedonicus
definition: A type of epidermal nevus characterized by closely arranged, dilated follicular openings with keratinous plugs resembling classical comedones.

label: Abnormal oocyte morphology
definition: An abnormal structure of the female germ cell (egg cell).

label: Abnormal cell morphology
definition: Any anomaly of cell structure.

label: Abnormal zona pellucida morphology
definition: Abnormal structure of the oocyte extracellular matrix region known as the zona pellucida.

label: Thin zona pellucida
definition: Reduced thickness of the zona pellucida.

label: Increased circulating adrenic acid concentration
definition: An increased concentration of adrenic acid (also known as cis-7,10,13,16-Docosatetraenoic acid) in the blood circulation.

label: Reduced response to gonadotropin-releasing hormone stimulation test
definition: Failure of the gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) stimulation test to induce an appropriate increased in luteinizing hormone (LH), follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) levels.

label: Abnormal response to gonadotropin-releasing hormone stimulation test
definition: An abnormal response to the gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) stimulation test. This test typically involves intravenous administration of GnRH followed by repeated blood sampling at various time points to measure the levels of luteinizing hormone (LH) and follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

label: GM1-ganglioside accumulation
definition: Cellular accumulation of GM1 gangliosides.

label: Branch retinal artery occlusion
definition: Blockage of a branch of the retinal artery. This can cause loss of a section of visual field.

label: Retinal arterial occlusion
definition: Blockage of the retinal artery, generally associated with interruption of blood flow and oxygen delivery to the retina.

label: Cilioretinal artery occlusion
definition: Blockage of the cilioretinal artery. The central retinal artery supplies the inner retina and the surface of the optic nerve. In some individuals, the cilioretinal artery, a branch of the ciliary circulation, may supply a portion of the retina including the macula. In cilioretinal artery occlusion, vision loss results from cell death in the inner retinal layers (mainly ganglion cells) despite relative sparing of the outer layers.

label: Ophthalmic artery occlusion
definition: A partial or complete obstruction of the ophthalmic artery (branch of the internal carotid artery) that may lead to severe ischemia of the affected globe and associated ocular tissues. It can present with a similar picture to central retinal artery occlusion; however, profound choroidal ischaemia also occurs.

label: Branch retinal vein occlusion
definition: Blockage of a branch of the retinal vein. It may present with sudden-onset of painless vision loss or visual field defect correlating to the area of perfusion of the obstructed vessels.

label: Central retinal vein occlusion
definition: Central retinal vein occlusion is an occlusion of the main retinal vein posterior to the lamina cribrosa of the optic nerve and is typically caused by thrombosis.

label: Hemiretinal vein occlusion
definition: A variant of central retinal vein occlusions that involves the superior or inferior half of the retina.

label: Abnormal drug response
definition: An anomalous response to a medication related to individual variation in metabolic or immune response to drugs varying from potentially from potentially life-threatening adverse drug reactions to alteration of therapeutic efficacy.

label: Increased blood drug concentration
definition: High plasma concentration of a drug as compared to previously measured thresholds given the expected concentration for the applied dosage regime.

label: Decreased blood drug concentration
definition: Low plasma concentration of a drug as compared to previously measured thresholds given the expected concentration for the applied dosage regime.

label: Adverse drug response
definition: An unpleasant or harmful reaction resulting from treatment with a drug.

label: Reduced drug efficacy
definition: Decreased response to a drug intervention in comparison to the expected response.

label: Refractory drug response
definition: Absent or significantly reduced efficacy of drug intervention characterized by lack of measurable benefit or deterioration of disease course.

label: Reduced circulating cholinesterase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of cholinesterase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Cholesterol crystalluria
definition: The presence of cholesterol crystals in the urine.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
definition: An abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
definition: An abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with memory phenotype is CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Abnormal dendritic cell count
definition: A deviation from the normal count of dendritic cells in the peripheral blood circulation. Dendritic cells are of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation. These cells are lineage negative (CD3-negative, CD19-negative, CD34-negative, and CD56-negative).

label: Abnormal circulating haptoglobin concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of haptoglobin in the blood circulation.

label: Elevated haptoglobin level
definition: An abnormally high concentration of haptoglobin in the blood circulation. Haptoglobin is an acute-phase reactant whose levels can become elevated in the presence of infection and inflammation.

label: Reduced haptoglobin level
definition: An abnormally low concentration of haptoglobin in the blood circulation. Decreased haptoglobin in conjunction with increased reticulocyte count and anemia may indicate hemolysis. Decreased haptoglobin levels can also occur in the absence of hemolysis, due to cirrhosis of the liver, disseminated ovarian carcinomatosis, pulmonary sarcoidosis, and elevated estrogen state.

label: Abnormal circulating A-type atrial natriuretic peptide concentration
definition: A measurable change in circulating levels of Atrial natriuretic peptide hormone, a protein which plays an important role in the regulation of body fluid volume and blood pressure.

label: Abnormal circulating atrial natriuretic peptide pro-hormone concentration
definition: The concentration in the blood circulation of atrial natriuretic peptide pro-hormone or one of its processed fragments is outside of the range of normal.

label: Increased circulating A-type natriuretic peptide concentration
definition: A measurable elevation in circulating levels of Atrial natriuretic peptide hormone, a protein which plays an important role in the regulation of body fluid volume and blood pressure.

label: Decreased circulating A-type natriuretic peptide concentration
definition: A measurable reduction in circulating levels of Atrial natriuretic peptide hormone, a protein which plays an important role in the regulation of body fluid volume and blood pressure.

label: Superior cerebellar dysplasia
definition: Abnormal morphological development of the superior part of the cerebellum.

label: Multilobulated spleen
definition: The fetal spleen is lobulated, and these lobules normally disappear before the birth. Lobulation of the spleen may persist into adult life and be typically seen along the medial part of the spleen. A persisting lobule results in a variation in shape of the spleen.

label: Thick pachygyria
definition: Pachygyria with a very thick cerebral cortex measuring 10-20 mm. Note that cortical thickness cannot be measured reliably on scans done between 3 and 24 months of age.

label: Anterior predominant pachygyria with 5-10 mm cortical thickness
definition: Pachygyria with cortical thickness between 5 and 10 mm with and a posterior predominant severity gradient. The severity gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically over 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Posterior predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe other the occipital lobes but also includes a rare perisylvian-predominant pachygyria and a temporal predominant pachygyria.

label: Pachygyria with 5-10 mm cortical thickness
definition: Pachygyria with a mildly thickened cerebral cortex measuring 5-10 mm. Note that cortical thickness cannot be measured reliably on scans done between 3 and 24 months of age.

label: Posterior predominant thick cortex pachygyria
definition: Pachygyria with cortical thickness above 10 mm with and a posterior predominant severity gradient. The severity gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically wider than 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Posterior predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe other the occipital lobes but also includes a rare perisylvian-predominant pachygyria and a temporal predominant pachygyria.

label: Perisylvian predominant thick cortex pachygyria
definition: Pachygyria with cortical thickness greater than 10 mm and a perisylvian predominant severity gradient. The severity gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically wider than 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Perisylvian predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe other the occipital lobes but also includes a rare perisylvian-predominant pachygyria and a temporal predominant pachygyria.

label: Anterior predominant thick cortex pachygyria
definition: Pachygyria with cortical thickness greater than 10 mm and an anterior predominant severity gradient. The severity gradient is determined based on the gyral width, with gyri typically wider than 5mm over the more severely affected regions. Anterior predominant gradient indicates pachygyria more severe over the frontal and temporal lobes.

label: Prolonged reptilase time
definition: An abnormally increased duration of the reptilase time. Reptilase time is a functional plasma clotting assay, which is based on the enzymatic activity of batroxobin. By specifically cleaving fibrinogen A from fibrinogen, batroxobin leads to the formation of a stable fibrin clot. The time, starting from the addition of batroxobin to the plasma sample, until clot formation is the reptilase time and is given in seconds.

label: IgA heavy chain paraproteinemia
definition: An abnormal IgA heavy chain in the circulation and typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.

label: Heavy-chain paraproteinemia
definition: An abnormal immunoglobulin heavy chain in the circulation and typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.

label: IgG heavy chain paraproteinemia
definition: An abnormal IgG heavy chain in the circulation and typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.

label: IgM heavy chain paraproteinemia
definition: An abnormal IgM heavy chain in the circulation and typically produced by a clonal population of B-cell derived plasma cells.

label: Increased circulating arachidonic acid concentration
definition: An increased circulation of arachidonic acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating 18-hydroxycorticosterone level
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of 18-Hydroxycorticosterone level in the blood circulation.

label: Decreased circulating 18-hydroxycortisone level
definition: A subnormal concentration of 18-Hydroxycorticosterone level in the blood circulation.

label: Increased circulating 18-hydroxycortisone level
definition: An abnormally elevated concentration of 18-Hydroxycorticosterone level in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal sarcomere morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the sarcomere, which is unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z disks.

label: Abnormal Z disk morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the Z disk, which is the platelike region of a muscle sarcomere to which the plus ends of actin filaments are attached.

label: Z-band streaming
definition: Streaming or smearing of the Z band, which is then no longer confined to a narrow zone which bisects the I band. The Z disk may extend across the I band or the entire sarcomere in a zigzag manner. Focal thickening, smudging, and blurring of the Z band takes place concurrently. Myofibrillar disorganization is a frequent but not invariable accompanying change.

label: Tubulointerstitial bacterial infiltration
definition: Tubulointerstitial infiltration of bacteria identified on routine and/or special (Brown-Hopps) stains.

label: Tubulointerstitial microganismal infiltration
definition: Infiltration of microorganisms into renal tubulointerstitial tissues as observed by appropriate staining procedures, e.g., bacteria on a bacterial stain (Brown and Hopps) or fungi on PAS or silver stain.

label: Tubulointerstitial fungal infiltration
definition: Tubulointerstitial infiltration of yeast or hyphal-microrganisms identified on routine and/or special (PAS, silver) stains.

label: Simple ear
definition: The pinna has fewer folds and grooves than usual.

label: Reflex seizure
definition: Seizures precipitated by exogenous stimuli.

label: Eating-induced seizure
definition: A seizure precipitated by aspects of anticipating food, eating itself, or the post-prandial period.

label: Hot water-induced seizure
definition: A seizure precipitated by pouring cupfuls of very hot water (40 to 50 degrees Celsius) in rapid succession over the head. Bathing in this manner is the most common trigger.

label: Praxis-induced seizure
definition: A seizure precipitated by complex, cognition-guided tasks often involving visuomotor coordination and decision-making.

label: Proprioceptive-induced seizure
definition: A seizure precipitated by movement or a change in posture.

label: Reading-induced seizure
definition: A seizure precipitated by reading.

label: Somatosensory-induced seizure
definition: A somatosensory reflex seizure is a seizure precipitated by somatic stimulation of a specific part of the body in the absence of startle or surprise.

label: Startle-induced seizure
definition: Startle-induced seizures are triggered by multiple and non-specific stimuli (auditory, somatosensory, and rarely visual) and are characterized by their sudden unexpected nature. Sudden noise rather than pure sound is the most effective acoustic stimulus.

label: Thinking-induced seizure
definition: Seizures induced by thinking and decision-making.

label: Focal aware motor seizure
definition: A type of focal motor seizure in which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

label: Focal aware atonic seizure
definition: A type of focal atonic seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

label: Focal atonic seizure
definition: A focal seizure characterized at onset by sudden loss or diminution of muscle tone without apparent preceding myoclonic or tonic activity, typically lasting more than 500 ms but less than 2 seconds. It may involve the head, trunk, jaw or limb musculature.

label: Hypohomocysteinemia
definition: A decreased concentration of homocysteine in the blood.

label: Dermal sinus tract
definition: A dermal sinus tract is an abnormality present at birth over the dorsal midline where an abnormal epithelialized connection from the skin tracks inwards towards the spine, most commonly seen in the lumbosacral region.

label: Mammary duct ectasia
definition: A non-proliferative inflammatory disorder of the large duct (milk duct) of the breast; as such, it affects nipple and areola complex. The condition is characterized by focal dilatation of the lactiferous duct system is due to endoluminal changes, as well as the loss of duct wall elastin, leading to abnormally dilated and tortuous lactiferous ducts with associated periductal inflammation and fibrosis. Mammary duct ectasia may present with nipple discharge or palpable mass.

label: Breast abscess
definition: A circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris in the breast.

label: Nipple tenderness
definition: Pain or discomfort produced by touching the nipple.

label: Floating gallbladder
definition: An abnormal configuration in which the gallbladder is pedunculated, hanging free of the liver, and attached only by the cystic mesentery,

label: Biospecimen phenotypic feature
definition: A phenotypic abnormality obvserved in a biospecimen such as a biopsy or an extirpated tumor or tissue.

label: Abnormal lymph-node biospecimen
definition: Any abnormal phenotypic feature observed in a biospecimen derived from a lymph node, generally obtained by lymph node biopsy (removal of lymph node tissue for microscopic examination).

label: Abnormal lymph-node tissue architecture
definition: Any phenotypic abnormality of the architecture of the tissue of a lymph node.

label: Abnormal lymph-node cellular finding
definition: Any phenotypic abnormality within cells located in a lymph node.

label: Abnormal lymph-node cellular antigen expression
definition: Abnormal expression of an antigen (marker) that by cells located in a lymph node.

label: Altered lymph-node tissue architecture
definition: An alteration that affects multiple components of the architecture of a lymph node.

label: Effaced lymph-node architecture
definition: Effacement of architecture typically refers to a cellular infiltrate destroying the normal follicular architecture of a lymph node. This effacement may result in sheets of cells that do not form clear architecture (seen in many lymphomas) or may lead to replacement of the normal architecture by atypical architecture, for example effacement of normal lymph node architecture (including normal follicles and patent lymph node sinuses) by many abnormal follicles in follicular lymphoma.

label: Vaguely nodular lymph-node architecture
definition: In contrast to normal lymph node architecture or that of follicular lymphoma, where follicles are typically distinct and readily identifiable on H&E stained biopsy sections, the cells within an atypical lymph node may show what appear to groups of cells forming vague nodules but not forming clear follicles.

label: Lymph-node capsular invasion by lymphocytes
definition: Migration of substantial numbers of lymphocytes into the capsule of a lymph node.

label: Lymph-node extracapsular extension by lymph-node lymphocytes
definition: Migration of lymphocytes into the soft tissues surrounding the lymph node.

label: Increased lymph-node epithelioid histiocyte count
definition: Number of epithelioid histiocytes (histiocytes are tissue-resident macrophages) located within a lymph node above the upper limit of normal.

label: Scattered lymph node individual epithelioid histiocytes
definition: Many individual (not clustered) epithelioid histiocytes throughout at least part of a lymph node.

label: Clustered lymph node epithelioid histiocytes
definition: Formation of clusters (group of cells positioned near each other) of epithelioid histiocytes within a lymph node.

label: Abnormal lymph-node follicle architecture
definition: Any phenotypic abnormality of the architecture of follicles of a lymph node.

label: Floral-pattern lymph node follicles
definition: Atypical lymph node follicles that have mantle zone cells invaginating/infiltrating into the follicle centers, which is said to confer a flower-like appearance.

label: Colonization of follicles by lymphoma cells
definition: In contrast to follicular lymphoma, which typically is a lymphoma that forms follicles or potentially completely replaces normal follicles, some lymphomas (most commonly marginal zone lymphoma) can infiltrate normal follicles so both normal lymphocytes and the infiltrating lymphoma cells are present. This is called colonization of follicles by the lymphoma cells.

label: Crowded lymph-node follicles
definition: Reduction in the average distance between adjacent lymph node follicles.

label: Lymph-node follicular lysis
definition: An abnormal morphology of hyperplastic lymph node follicles characterized by distortion of the follicular architecture by tongues and clusters of dark blue mantle cells impinging on and invading the reactive germinal center (Mostly T cells and mantle-zone B cells).

label: Non-polarized lymph node germinal centers
definition: A loss of the typical polarization of the architecture of a lymph node germinal center.

label: Abnormal lymph-node germinal center morphology
definition: Any phenotypic abnormality of germinal centers of a lymph node.

label: Irregularly shaped lymph node germinal centers
definition: A deviation from the typically fairly round or oval form of a lymph node germinal center.

label: Abnormal lymph-node marginal or mantle zone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the structure of the mantle or marginal zone of a lymph node.

label: Abnormal lymph node marginal zone morphology
Abnormal lymph node mantle zone morphology
Lymph node with expanded mantle zones
definition: Enlargement of the typical outer ring of small lymphocytes (mantle zone) surrounding a germinal center of a lymph node.

label: Lymph node with poorly defined germinal center borders
definition: Reduced demarcation of the border between germinal centers and mantle zones. This border is typically seen as a crisp line on hematoxylin and eosin (H&E)-stained lymph node sections.

label: Mantle zone pattern
definition: This refers to an architectural pattern of infiltration where atypical lymphocytes surround germinal centers, often expanding the mantle zones but without effacing architecture.

label: Germinal centers with absent marginal zones
Poorly defined primary lymph-node follicles
definition: Lack of the typical easily recognized delineation of primary follicles within lymph nodes.

label: Progressive transformation of germinal centers
definition: This is a condition sometimes seen in a subset of germinal centers of reactive lymph nodes where germinal centers become enlarged and infiltrated by benign mantle zone cells and some T cells.

label: Absent germinal center tingible body macrophages
definition: Lack of observable tingible body macrophages (TBMs) in germinal centers (GCs) of secondary lymphoid follicles. TBMs represent unique, large phagocytic cells that reside and are a subset of mononuclear phagocytes.

label: Lack of germinal center mitotic figures
definition: Absence of extreme paucity of mitotic figures in a lymph node germinal center.

label: Non-polarized mantle zones
definition: Lack of the typical polarization of the outer ring of small lymphocytes (mantle zone) surrounding a germinal center of a lymph node.

label: Hyalinized lymph-node vessels
definition: Hyalinized means to become clear/translucent such as collagen becoming more pale staining (collagen is typically quite eosinophilic, meaning attracted to the pink/red dye eosin); however, with regard to vessels in the lymph node, hyalinization is often used to describe vessel walls that appear markedly thickened or surrounded by eosinophilic material such as collagen, not necessarily translucent appearing.

label: Lymph-node follicular sclerosis
definition: Collagen deposition, typically with decreased cellularity, within lymph-node follicles.

label: Compressed lymph-node sinuses
definition: Loss of the typical patency (openness) of lymph node sinuses.

label: Lymph-node proliferation centers
