definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by menopause.

label: Fluctuance on palpation
definition: Yielding to alternate pressure by palpating fingers so as to suggest that the area being felt contains fluid.

label: History of vasectomy
definition: A medical history of having undergone a vasectomy prior to the current presentation.

label: Pain in penis
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the penis.

label: Left ventricular thrombus
definition: A blood clot (thrombus) localized in the left ventricle. Left ventricular thrombus is a serious complication of acute myocardial infarction and also of non-ischemic cardiomyopathies.

label: Gelatinous ascites
definition: A type of ascites characterized by copious amounts of mucinous ascites and mucinous peritoneal implants, leading to progressive obliteration of the peritoneal cavity and intestinal obstruction.

label: Diffuse breast nodularity
definition: Breast tissue with a lumpy or ropelike texture.

label: Decreased urinary biopterin level
definition: The amount of biopterin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine guanidinoacetic acid level
definition: The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Decreased urinary neopterin level
definition: The amount of neopterin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary inosine level
definition: The amount of inosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary guanosine level
definition: The amount of guanosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Decreased urinary hypoxanthine level
definition: The concentration of hypoxanthine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Absent neutrophil lactoferrin
definition: The absence of lactoferrin in neutrophil granules, which could be caused by either an isolated failure of synthesis of this protein (or the production of an antigenically unrecognizable form of lactoferrin) or a complete deficiency of specific granule production.

label: Neutrophil nuclear clefts
definition: An abnormality of the nucleus of neutrophils, which presents as either a type I nuclear cleft, where the nuclear cleft may show a transition into a round/oval shape. The second type nuclear cleft, which runs perpendicular to the nuclear surface, and this type of cleft might be related to nuclear lobe formation.

label: Abnormality of neutrophil morphology in CSF
definition: An abnormal form or size of neutrophils in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Low neutrophil alkaline phosphatase
definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase in neutrophils, which could be due to absence of enzyme or the production of defective enzyme.

label: Increased neutrophil mitochondria
definition: An increased number of mitochondria detected in neutrophils.

label: Increased neutrophil ribosomes
definition: An increased number of ribosomes detected in neutrophils.

label: Bladder outlet obstruction
definition: A compression or resistance upon the bladder outflow channel at any location from the bladder neck to urethral meatus, which usually causes lower urinary tract symptoms (LUTS).

label: Decreased expression of GPI-anchored proteins on the cell surface
definition: A decrease in the protein expression of GPI-anchor proteins, such as CD55 and CD59, at the cell surface, which suggests a defect in GPI-anchor biosynthesis.

label: Starch intolerance
definition: An inability to digest starch.

label: Renal tubular cyst
definition: Tubular lumnal dilatation/prominence lined by simple layer of cuboidal-to-flat tublar epihelial cells.

label: Ageusia
definition: A rare condition that is characterized by a complete loss of taste function of the tongue.

label: Agenesis of putamen
definition: A developmental defect characterized by the absence of the putamen owing to its failure to develop.

label: Hot cross bun sign
definition: A cruciform-shaped hyperintensity within the pons found on T2-weighted magnetic resonance imaging (MRI).

label: Transient decreased circulating IgG4
definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood circulation.

label: Chronic decreased circulating IgG4
definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood.

label: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG4
definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG4 can be measured.

label: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG4
definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood.

label: Fractured calcaneus
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the calcaneus.

label: Fractured tarsal bone
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the tarsal bone.

label: Transient decreased circulating IgG2
definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood circulation.

label: Chronic decreased circulating IgG2
definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood.

label: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG2
definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG2 can be measured.

label: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG2
definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood.

label: Transient decreased circulating IgG1
definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood circulation.

label: Chronic decreased circulating IgG1
definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood.

label: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG1
definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG1 can be measured.

label: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG1
definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood.

label: Transient decreased circulating IgG3
definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G3 (IgG3) in the blood circulation.

label: Chronic decreased circulating IgG3
definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G3 (IgG3) in the blood.

label: Fractured thoracic vertebra
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the thoracic vertebra.

label: Fractured vertebra
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the vertebra.

label: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG3
definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G3 (IgG3) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG3 can be measured.

label: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG3
definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G3 (IgG3) in the blood.

label: Abnormal immunoglobulin level in body fluid
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in body fluids, such as mucous.

label: Increased immunoglobulin level in body fluid
definition: An elevation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in body fluids, such as mucous.

label: Decreased body fat percentage
definition: The percentage of fat as a part of total body weight below the norm, usually defined as less than 14% for females and less than 8% for males.

label: Fractured lower leg
definition: Bone fracture anywhere in the tibia, fibula, or ankle.

label: Fractured hindlimb bone
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the hindlimb bone.

label: Fractured skull
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the skull.

label: Fractured phalanx
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the phalanx.

label: Compression-fractured thoracic vertebra
definition: A fracture of the thoracic vertebra that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

label: Compression-fractured vertebra
definition: A fracture of the vertebra that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

label: Compression-fractured cervical vertebra
definition: A fracture of the cervical vertebra that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

label: Fractured cervical vertebra
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the cervical vertebra.

label: Compression-fractured lumbar vertebra
definition: A fracture of the lumbar vertebra that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

label: Fractured lumbar vertebra
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the lumbar vertebra.

label: Avulsion fractured humerus
definition: A fractured in which a fragment of the humerus tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

label: Avulsion fractured tibia
definition: A fractured in which a fragment of the tibia tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

label: Fractured tibia
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the tibia.

label: Pelvic avulsion fracture
definition: An avulsion fracture (i.e., a type of fracture in which a piece of bone tears away from the site where the muscle attaches to the bone) of a bone of the pelvis.

label: Pelvis fracture
definition: A break in one or more bones of the pelvis.

label: Avulsion fracture
definition: A type of fracture that is localied near to a a tendon or ligament and a small fragment of bone is separated from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

label: Avulsion fractured epiphysis of femur
definition: A fractured in which the fragment of the epiphysis of femur bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

label: Fractured epiphysis of femur
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the epiphysis of femur.

label: Emotional hypersensitivity
definition: Heightened emotional reactivity to environmental stimuli, including the emotions of others.

label: Beau's lines
definition: A nail dystrophy that is preseents as grooved lines that run from side to side on the fingernail or the toenail that may look like indentations or ridges on the nail plate. They are caused by temporary disruption in the growth of proximal nail matrix. Trauma is usually the initiating factor such as infections, severe medical illnesses, major surgery/anesthesia, medication side effects, and autoimmune disease.

label: Complete tracheal ring
definition: Continuous or nearly continuous configuration of the cartilaginous tracheal ring.

label: Decreased middle cerebral artery pulsatility index
definition: Abnormally reduced blood flow pulsatility in in the middle cerebral artery (MCA). The pulsatility index (PI) is calculated using the following equation PI = (peak systolic velocity-end-diastolic velocity)/mean velocity.

definition: A partial or complete breakage of the metaphysis of femur.

definition: A partial or complete breakage of the right clavicle.

definition: A partial or complete breakage of the mandible.

label: Abnormal neural tube morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the hollow epithelial tube found on the dorsal side of the vertebrate embryo that develops into the central nervous system (i.e. brain and spinal cord).

label: Aplasia of lymphatic vessels
definition: Aplasia (absence) of the lymphatic vessels.

label: Decreased urine bicarbonate concentration
definition: Abnormally decreased concentration of hydrogencarbonate in the urine.

label: Narrow palpebral fissure
definition: Reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids.

label: Microlissencephaly
definition: Severe microcephaly and lissencephaly with granular surfaces with immature cortical plate, reduced in thickness, with focal polymicrogyria and immature small neurons with rare processes, intermingled with a considerable number of glial elements.

label: Eosinophilic fasciitis
definition: Inflammation and thickening (localized fibrosis) of the fascia, the tissue under the skin and over the muscle, typically associated with a build up of eosinophils in the muscles and tissues.

label: Fasciitis
definition: Inflammation of fascia, the tissue under the skin and over the muscle.

label: Elevated urinary 3-aminoisobutyric acid
definition: An increased amount of 3-aminoisobutyric acid in the urine.

label: Gastric lymphoma
definition: Lymphoma that originates in the stomach itself.

label: Reduced circulating lactate dehydrogenase concentration
definition: Concentration of lactate dehydrogenase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating complement C4 concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component C4 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating complement C4a concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component C4a in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating complement C4b concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component C4b in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit concentration
definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit level in the blood circulation.

label: HbS hemoglobin
definition: Presence of an abnormal type of hemoglobin characterized by the substitution of a glutamic acid residue at position 7 following the initial methionine residue by a valine (the mutation causative of sickle cell disease). The mutation promotes the polymerization of the HbS under conditions of low oxygen concentration. HbS can be identified by multiple methodologies including hemoglobin electrophoresis and high-performance liquid chromatography.

label: Increased HbA2 hemoglobin
definition: An elevated concentration in the blood of hemoglobin A2 (HbA2), which is a normal variant of hemoglobin A that consists of two alpha and two delta chains and is normally present at low levels in adults but may be increased in beta thalassemia.

label: Abnormal DLCO
definition: An abnormal amount of oxygen passes into the blood from the lungs and/or an abnormal amount of carbon dioxide passes from the blood into the lungs.

label: Increased DLCO
definition: Increased ability of the lungs to transfer gas from inspired air to the bloodstream as measured by the diffusing capacity of the lungs for carbon monoxide (DLCO) test.

label: Decreased DLCO
definition: Reduced ability of the lungs to transfer gas from inspired air to the bloodstream as measured by the diffusing capacity of the lungs for carbon monoxide (DLCO) test.

label: Abnormality of the brachial nerve plexus
definition: Any abnormality of the brachial nerve plexus.

label: Abnormality of somatic nerve plexus
definition: Any abnormality of the somatic nerve plexus.

label: Abnormality of the lumbosacral nerve plexus
definition: Any abnormality of the lumbosacral nerve plexus.

label: Tiger tail banding
definition: An abnormal appearance of hair under polarizing microscopy (using crossed polarizers), whereby hair shafts show striking alternating bright and dark bands, often referred to as tiger tail banding.

label: Decreased circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
definition: Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Hyperkeratotic papule
definition: A circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid, varying in size from a pinhead to less than 10mm in diameter at the widest point that is composed of localized hyperkeratosis (the latter may be demonstrated histopathologically).

label: Increased PIVKA-II
definition: Des-gamma carboxyprothrombin (DCP) or pro-thrombin induced by vitamin K absence-II (PIVKA-II) is an abnormal prothrombin protein that is increased in the serum of patients with HCC. Generation of DCP is thought to be a result of an acquired defect in the post- translational carboxylation of the prothrombin precursor in malignant cells.

label: Thin eyebrow
definition: Decreased diameter of eyebrow hairs.

label: Distal femoral metaphyseal irregularity
definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the distal metaphysis of the femur.

label: Decreased proportion of CD3-positive T cells
definition: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD3-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased body mass index
definition: Abnormally decreased weight-to-height squared ratio, calculated by dividing the individual's weight in kilograms by the square of the individual's height in meters and used as an indicator of underweight compared to averages.

label: Abnormality of masseter muscle
definition: An abnormality of a masseter muscle.

label: Knee joint hypermobility
definition: The ability of the knee to move past its normal range of motion, (knee hyperextension is greater than 10 degrees).

label: Large joint hypermobilty
definition: The capability that a large joint (or a group of joints) has to move, passively and/or actively, beyond normal limits along physiological axes. Large joints include shoulders, elbows, hips, knees, and ankles.

label: Clinical relevance
definition: Subontology for annotating phenotypic features as distinctive or minor findings in patients. The subontology is intended to be used to annotate subjective clinical impressions of whether a certain finding is important for the differential diagnosis.

label: Distinctive finding
definition: In clinical parlance, findings are occasionally interpreted as being distinctive or minor, reflecting a subjective clinical impression of the importance of a feature for the differential diagnosis. A minor finding is taken to be one that is likely to have high utility in distinguishing the correct diagnosis from other candidates in the differential.

label: Minor finding
definition: In clinical parlance, findings are occasionally interpreted as being distinctive or minor, reflecting a subjective clinical impression of the importance of a feature for the differential diagnosis. A minor finding is taken to be one that is unlikely to help distinguish the correct diagnosis from other candidates in the differential.

label: Bradypnea
definition: Bradypnea is referring to breathing that is abnormally slow.

label: Malignant mesothelioma
definition: Malignant mesothelioma is a form of cancer that originates from the cells of the mesothelium, a thin tissue layer surrounding the body's internal organs. Malignant mesothelioma is almost exclusively caused by asbestos exposure, pleural mesothelioma being the most common form, affecting the lining of the lungs called the pleura. Other forms such as perioneal-, percardial- or testicular- mesothelioma are much rarer.

label: Pleural mesothelioma
definition: A malignant mesothelioma originating from cells of the pleura (the thin layer of mesothelium lining the lungs). Pleural mesothelioma is the most common form of mesothelioma.

label: Peritoneal mesothelioma
definition: A Malignant mesothelioma originating from cells of the peritoneum (the thin layer of mesothelium lining the abdomen). Peritoneal mesothelioma is the second most common form of mesothelioma after pleural mesothelioma.

label: Pericardial mesothelioma
definition: A Malignant mesothelioma originating from cells of the pericardium (the thin layer of mesothelium lining the heart).

label: Testicular mesothelioma
definition: A Malignant mesothelioma of the testis.

label: Epiretinal membrane
definition: An epiretinal membrane is a thin sheet of fibrous tissue that can develop on the surface of the macular area of the retina and cause a disturbance in vision. An epiretinal membrane area can develop on the thin macular area of the retin. An epiretinal membrane is also sometimes called a macular pucker, premacular fibrosis, surface wrinkling retinopathy or cellophane maculopathy.

label: Stahl ear
definition: The presence of a supernumerary, i.e. third, crus of the helix in the helix, arising at or above the normal bifurcation of the antihelix.

label: Capsular cataract
definition: A cataract that affects the capsule of the lens.

label: Posterior capsular cataract
definition: A cataract which is found in the back outer layer of the lens. This type often develops more rapidly.

label: Recurrent hand flapping
definition: A type of repetitive behavior in which the affected individual repeatedly waves the hands and/or arms rhythmically.

label: Stereotypic upper-extremity movements
definition: Abnormal movements of the upper extremities.

label: Conspicuously happy disposition
definition: An unusually happy demeanor over time, which can also be observed during inappropriate situations that should, for example, cause distress, fear, or anger.

label: Overfriendliness
definition: A form of hypersociability that presents as mostly inappropriate friendliness towards others.

label: Recurrent pancreatitis
definition: A recurrent form of pancreatitis.

label: Ectopic thyroid
definition: Mislocalised thyroid gland.

label: Lingual thyroid
definition: An aberrant thyroid gland or Ectopic thyroid located at the base of the tongue, just posterior to the foramen cecum as a result of a failure of the thyroid to descend.

label: Accessory ectopic thyroid tissue
definition: Accessory ectopic thyroid tissue arising from remnants of the thyroglossal duct anywhere along the path of the thyroglossal duct tract.

label: Tics
definition: Repeated, individually recognizable, intermittent movements or movement fragments that are almost always briefly suppressible and are usually associated with awareness of an urge to perform the movement.

label: Motor tics
definition: Movement-based tics affecting discrete muscle groups.

label: Phonic tics
definition: Tics are defined as movements or sounds that resemble physiological motor behaviors, but are typically inopportune to social context and appear sudden, repetitive, and often exaggerated. Tic vocalizations commonly termed vocal or phonic tics may include any possible sound (eg, sniffing, coughing, throat clearing, whistling, or grunting), word, or sentence and are most commonly encountered within the spectrum of primary tic disorders, as Tourette syndrome.

label: Pseudo-fractures
definition: A band of bone material of decreased density forming alongside the surface of the cortical bone with thickening of the periosteum. Callus formation in the affected area is common and gives the appearance of a false fracture.

label: Slow-growing scalp hair
definition: Scalp hair whose growth is slower than normal.

label: Broad 2nd toe
definition: A broad appearance of the second toe.

label: Broad 3rd toe
definition: A broad appearance of the third toe.

label: Broad 4th toe
definition: A broad appearance of the fourth toe.

label: Broad 5th toe
definition: A broad appearance of the fifth toe.

label: Fragmentation of the epiphyses of the 2nd toe
Ivory epiphyses of the 2nd toe
definition: Epiphyses of the 2nd toe are hard and dense like ivory. Such an epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs.

label: Stippling of the epiphyses of the 2nd toe
definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphyses of the 2nd toe.

label: Fragmentation of the epiphyses of the 3rd toe
Ivory epiphyses of the 3rd toe
definition: Epiphyses of the 3rd toe are hard and dense like ivory. Such an epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs.

label: Stippling of the epiphyses of the 3rd toe
definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphyses of the 3rd toe.

Ectopic respiratory mucosa
definition: Ectopic respiratory epithelium presenting as a superficial lesion in the skin usually localized unilateral in the skin of the forearm and associated with ipsilateral hand malformations.

label: Fibrosarcoma
definition: A fibroblastic sarcoma is a malignant tumor derived from fibrous connective tissue and characterized by immature proliferating fibroblasts or undifferentiated anaplastic spindle cells.

label: Gastrointestinal desmoid tumor
definition: Benign, slow-growing tumors without any metastatic potential. Despite their benign nature, they can damage nearby structures causing organ dysfunction. Histologically they resemble low-grade fibrosarcomas, but they are very locally aggressive and tend to recur even after complete resection. There is a tendency for recurrence in the setting of prior surgery and the most common localisation of these tumors is intraabdominal from smooth muscle cells of the instestine.

label: Desmoid tumor
definition: Desmoid tumors are rare, locally aggressive, fibroblastic soft-tissue tumors that are characterized by infiltrative growth and tendency to recur. Desmoid tumors do not metastasize but can arise in any part of the body: extra-abdominal (appear in the head and neck, chest, extremities), and abdominal wall or intra-abdominal (originating in tissue that connects abdominal organs).

label: Recurrent singultus
definition: A contraction of the diaphragm that repeats several times per minute. In humans, the abrupt rush of air into the lungs causes the epiglottis to close, creating a hic sound. Also known as synchronous diaphragmatic flutter (SDF), or singultus, from the Latin singult, the act of catching one's breath while sobbing. The hiccup is an involuntary action involving a reflex arc.

label: Hemiballismus
definition: Hemiballismus is a rare movement disorder that is caused primarily by damage to various areas in the basal ganglia. Hemiballismus is usually characterized by involuntary flinging motions of the extremities. The movements are often violent and have wide amplitudes of motion. They are continuous and random and can involve proximal and/or distal muscles on one side of the body, while some cases even include the facial muscles. The more a patient is active, the more the movements increase. With relaxation comes a decrease in movements.

label: Calcification of muscles
definition: Deposition of calcium salts in muscle tissue.

label: Meningeal calcification
definition: Calcium deposition affecting the Meninges.

label: Abnormality of the medullary cavity of the long bones
definition: An abnormality of the medullary cavity (medulla, innermost part), which is the central cavity of bone shafts where red bone marrow and/or yellow bone marrow (adipose tissue) is stored.

label: Stenosis of the medullary cavity of the long bones
Senile plaques
definition: Senile plaques are extracellular deposits of amyloid in the gray matter of the brain.

label: Upper lip pit
definition: Depression located on the vermilion of the upper lip, usually paramedian.

label: Abnormality of dorsoventral patterning of the limbs
definition: An abnormality resulting from a defect or disruption of dorsoventral patterning that normally happens during early development of the limbs. A disruption of the normal development of the dorsoventral axis may lead to a variable spectrum of different phenotypic abnormalities that may affect the nails and or palmar and dorsal side of the hands and/or feet, ultimately changing the normal dorsoventral appearance of the affected limbs.

label: Hyponasal speech
definition: Hyponasal speech is when there is an abnormally reduced nasal airflow during speech often in a setting of nasal obstruction or congestion.

label: Branchial sinus
definition: A congenital branchial sinus is a remnant of the embryonic branchial arches and their intervening clefts and pouches that has failed to regress completely. Sinuses typically have their external orifice inferior to the ramus of the mandible. They may traverse the parotid gland, and run in close vicinity to the facial nerve in the external auditory canal.

label: Gustatory lacrimation
definition: Gustatory lacrimation results from an aberrant innervation of fibers from the seventh cranial nerve to the pterygopalatine ganglion which are destined originally for the submandibular ganglion. This aberrant innervation leads to uncontrollable tearing while eating or in anticipation of a meal.

label: Diffuse cerebellar atrophy
definition: Diffuse unlocalised atrophy affecting the cerebellum.

label: Ulcerative colitis
definition: A chronic inflammatory bowel disease that includes characteristic ulcers, or open sores, in the colon. The main symptom of active disease is usually constant diarrhea mixed with blood, of gradual onset and intermittent periods of exacerbated symptoms contrasting with periods that are relatively symptom-free. In contrast to Crohn's disease this special form of colitis begins in the distal parts of the rectum, spreads continually upwards and affects only mucose and submucose tissue of the colon.

label: Chronic colitis
definition: A chronic inflammatory disease of the large intestine (colon, cecum and rectum).

label: Crohn's disease
definition: A chronic granulomatous inflammatory disease of the intestines that may affect any part of the gastrointestinal tract from mouth to anus, causing a wide variety of symptoms. It primarily causes abdominal pain, diarrhea which may be bloody, vomiting, or weight loss, but may also cause complications outside of the gastrointestinal tract such as skin rashes, arthritis, inflammation of the eye, tiredness, and lack of concentration. Crohn's disease is thought to be an autoimmune disease, in which the body's immune system attacks the gastrointestinal tract, causing inflammation.

label: Acute colitis
definition: An acute and self-limited inflammatory disease of the large intestine (colon, cecum and rectum).

label: EMG: continuous motor unit activity at rest
definition: Continuous electromyographic activity of motor units at rest, i.e., without voluntary movement of the muscles.

label: EMG: myotonic discharges
definition: High frequency discharges in electromyography (EMG) that vary in amplitude and frequency, waxing and waning continuously with firing frequencies ranging from 150/second down to 20/second and producing a sound that has been referred to as a dive bomber sound.

label: EMG: slow motor conduction
definition: The presence of reduced conduction velocity of motor nerves on electromyography.

label: EMG: myokymic discharges
definition: The presence of spontaneous bursts of rapidly firing potentials that recur at regular intervals of 2-10 per second and are unaffected by voluntary effort. This is an electromyographic (EMG) finding.

label: Abnormality of peripheral somatosensory evoked potentials
Delayed somatosensory central conduction time
definition: An abnormal increase (delay) in the somatosensory central conduction time (CCT), which can be measured from the peak of N13 to the peak of N20 (peak CCT) or from the onset of N11 to the onset of N20 (onset CCT).

label: Amyloidosis of peripheral nerves
definition: The presence of amyloid deposition in the nerves of the peripheral nervous system.

label: Hypertrophied muscle fibers
definition: The presence of an increased amount of muscle fibers with an increased diameter. This feature can be ascertained by microscopic examination of a muscle biopsy sample. Together with fiber size variation and atrophied muscle fibers, and hypertrophied muscle fibers are commonly found in myopathies.

label: Increased endomysial connective tissue
definition: An increased volume of the endomysium, which is a connective tissue sheath that surrounds each muscule fiber. Together, bundles of muscle fibers form a fasciculus, surrounded by another layer of connective tissue called the perimysium.

label: Muscle fiber tubular inclusions
definition: Unusual regions of densely packed membranous tubules known as tubular aggregates which present as membranous inclusions, derived from membranes of sarcoplasmic reticulum and mitochondria, containing miscellaneous proteins with a variety of enzymatic activities.

label: Muscle fiber intranuclear inclusion bodies
definition: The presence of inclusion bodies within the nucleus of muscle cells. Inclusion bodies are aggregates (deposits) or stainable material, usually misfolded proteins.

label: Ring fibers
definition: Ring fibers are formed by a bundle of peripheral myofibrils which are circumferentially oriented such that they encircle the internal portion of the sarcoplasm which is normal in structure and orientation.

label: Muscle fiber hyaline bodies
definition: Subsarcolemmal, eosinophilic glass-like regions in the cytoplasm of muscle fibers. Hyaline bodies show significant reactivity to myofibrillar ATPase after acid pre-incubation and with immunohistochemistry, show intense reactivity with only slow myosin heavy chain. Electron microscopy of the affected areas show a lack of myofibrils and a uniform, finely granular matrix, sometimes suggesting a filamentous nature, containing few scattered nuclei and mitochondria.

label: Cerebral cortical hemiatrophy
definition: Atrophy of one side of the brain, characterized by findings including thinning of the cerebral cortex, reduced volume of the cerebral white matter with abnormal myelination, and enlargement of the ispilateral fourth ventricle.

label: Subdural hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage occurring between the dura mater and the arachnoid mater.

label: Epidural hemorrhage
definition: Hemorrhage occurring between the dura mater and the skull.

label: Cerebral ventricular adhesions
definition: Bands of scar-like tissue that have formed within a cerebral ventricle.

label: Cerebral germinoma
definition: The presence of a germ cell tumor of the cerebrum.

label: Germinoma
definition: A type of undifferentiated germ cell tumor that may be benign or malignant.

label: Cerebral granulomatosis
definition: Cerebral inflammation involving a granulomatous response, i.e., a non-specific inflammatory response involving granulomas, defined as a compact organized collection of mature mononuclear phagocytes including epithelioid and giant cells.

label: Hirano bodies
definition: Intracellular aggregates of actin and actin-associated proteins within nerve cells.

label: Argyrophilic inclusion bodies
definition: Presence of abundant argyrophilic grains and coiled bodies on microscopic examination of brain tissue.

label: Lafora bodies
definition: An intraneuronal inclusion body composed of acid mucopolysaccharides.

label: Cerebral hyaline bodies
definition: Cerebral eosinophilic, discrete, intracytoplasmatic inclusions of unknown significance.

label: Rosenthal fibers
definition: Thick, elongated, worm-like or corkscrew eosinophilic bundle that are found on H&E staining of the brain in the presence of long standing gliosis, occasional tumors, and some metabolic disorders.

label: Scleroderma
definition: A chronic autoimmune phenomenon characterized by fibrosis (or hardening) and vascular alterations of the skin.

label: Cow milk allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against cow milk protein.

label: Dairy allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against dairy.

label: Unilateral cleft lip
definition: A non-midline cleft of the upper lip on one side only.

label: Non-midline cleft of the upper lip
definition: Clefting (gap or groove) of the upper lip affecting the lateral portions of the upper lip rather than the midline/median region.

label: Bilateral cleft lip
definition: A non-midline cleft of the upper lip on the left and right sides.

label: Bilateral cleft palate
definition: Nonmidline cleft palate on the left and right sides.

definition: The proximal interphalangeal joint of the 2nd toe cannot be straightened actively or passively.

Bullet-shaped middle phalanx of the 3rd toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the middle phalanx of the third toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped middle phalanx of the 4th toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the middle phalanx of the fourth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped middle phalanx of the 5th toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the middle phalanx of the fifth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped proximal phalanx of the 3rd toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the third toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped proximal phalanx of the 4th toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the fourth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped proximal phalanx of the 5th toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the fifth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped distal phalanx of the 3rd toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the distal phalanx of the third toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped distal phalanx of the 4th toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the distal phalanx of the fourth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Bullet-shaped distal phalanx of the 5th toe
definition: An abnormal morphology of the distal phalanx of the fifth toe, with a short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

label: Curved middle phalanx of the 3rd toe
definition: A deviation from the normal straight form of the middle phalanx of the third toe.

label: Curved proximal phalanx of the 4th toe

label: Curved proximal phalanx of the 5th toe

definition: A deviation from the normal straight form of the distal phalanx of the fourth toe.

label: Curved distal phalanx of the 5th toe
definition: A deviation from the normal straight form of the distal phalanx of the fifth toe.

Sclerosis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd toe
definition: An elevation in bone density in the middle phalanx of the third toe. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Patchy sclerosis of the middle phalanx of the 4th toe
definition: Uneven increase in bone density of the middle phalanx of the fourth toe. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

label: Sclerosis of the middle phalanx of the 4th toe
Patchy sclerosis of the middle phalanx of the 5th toe
definition: Uneven increase in bone density of the middle phalanx of the fifth toe. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

definition: An elevation in bone density in the proximal phalanx of the third toe. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Patchy sclerosis of the proximal phalanx of the 4th toe
definition: Uneven increase in bone density of the proximal phalanx of the fourth toe. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

Patchy sclerosis of the proximal phalanx of the 5th toe
definition: Uneven increase in bone density of the proximal phalanx of the fifth toe. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

definition: Uneven increase in bone density of the distal phalanx of the fourth toe. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

label: Hypoammonemia
definition: A decreased concentration of ammonia in the blood.

label: Abnormality of the vitamin B3 metabolism
Recurrent bronchiolitis
definition: An increased susceptibility to bronchiolitis as manifested by a history of recurrent bronchiolitis.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin B12 concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin B12 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin B1 concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin B1 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin B2 concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin B2 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin B5 concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin B5 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin B8 concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin B8 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced blood folate concentration
definition: A reduced circulating concentration of folic acid, which is also known as vitamin B9.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin C concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin C in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin D concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin D in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating vitamin E concentration
definition: A reduced concentration of vitamin E in the blood circulation. Vitamin E is a lipophilic vitamin that is also known as alpha-tocopherol.

label: Pollakisuria
definition: Increased frequency of urination.

label: Neoplasm of the urethra
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the urethra.

label: Dysuria
definition: Painful or difficult urination.

label: Anuria
definition: Absence of urine, clinically classified as below 50ml/day.

label: Oliguria
definition: Low output of urine, clinically classified as an output below 300-500ml/day.

label: Thymoma
definition: A tumor originating from the epithelial cells of the thymus.

label: Liver abscess
definition: A circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris in the liver.

label: Limb duplication
definition: Congenital duplication of all or part of a limb.

label: Urachus fistula
definition: Persistence of the urachal canal with drainage of urine from the bladder through the persistent allantois canal to the umbilicus.

label: Neoplasm of the respiratory system
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the respiratory system.

label: Pleuropulmonary blastoma
definition: A rare cancer originating in the lung or pleural cavity that occurs most often in infants and young children but also has been reported in adults. Pleuropulmonary blastoma is regarded as malignant.

label: Wind-swept deformity of the knees
definition: The appearance of abnormal valgus deformity in one knee in association with varus deformity in the other.

label: Scleritis
definition: Inflammation of the sclera.

label: Episcleritis
definition: Inflammation of the episclera, a thin layer of tissue covering the white part (sclera) of the eye.

label: Abnormality of the fascia
definition: An abnormality of fascia.

label: Periorbital edema
definition: Edema affecting the region situated around the orbit of the eye.

label: Femoral hernia
definition: A hernia which occurs just below the inguinal ligament, where abdominal contents pass through a naturally occurring weakness called the femoral canal.

label: Carotid artery stenosis
definition: Narrowing of the carotid arteries.

label: Tendon rupture
definition: Breakage (tear) of a tendon.

label: Hemihypertrophy of lower limb
definition: Overgrowth of only one leg.

label: Lower limb asymmetry
definition: A difference in length or diameter between the left and right leg.

label: Hemihypertrophy of upper limb
definition: Overgrowth of only one arm.

label: Upper limb asymmetry
definition: Difference in length or size between the right and left arm.

label: Hemiatrophy
definition: Undergrowth of the limbs that affects only one side.

label: Hemiatrophy of lower limb
definition: Unilateral atrophy (reduction in size) of a leg.

label: Hemiatrophy of upper limb
definition: Unilateral atrophy (reduction in size) of an arm.

label: Diplomyelia
definition: Duplication of the spinal cord.

label: Diastomatomyelia
definition: Coexistence of two hemicords, at variable levels, causing splaying of the posterior vertebral elements. Results in neurological deficits in lower limb or perineum.

label: Triplomyelia
definition: Triplication of the spinal cord - extremely rare.

label: Hydromyelia
definition: Dilation of central canal from incomplete fusion of the posterior columns or persistence of the primitive large canal of the embryo.

label: Amyelia
definition: Congenital absence of the spinal cord.

label: Cardiac diverticulum
definition: A cardiac diverticulum is a rare congenital malformation which is either fibrous or muscular.

label: Fibrous cardiac diverticulum
definition: A fibrous cardiac diverticulum refers to an aneurysm and usually appears as an isolated congenital anomaly.

label: Neoplasm of the gallbladder
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the gallbladder.

label: Amaurosis fugax
definition: A transient visual disturbance that is typically caused by a circulatory, ocular or neurological underlying condition.

label: Urinary bladder inflammation
definition: Inflammation of the urinary bladder.

label: Lipoatrophy
definition: Localized loss of fat tissue.

label: Barrett esophagus
definition: An abnormal change (metaplasia) in the cells of the inferior portion of the esophagus. The normal squamous epithelium lining of the esophagus is replaced by metaplastic columnar epithelium. Columnar epithelium refers to a cell type that is typically found in more distal parts of the gastrointestinal system.

label: Dilatation of renal calices
definition: An abnormal enlargement of the renal calices, the system of ducts of the kidney that collect urine.

label: Nasal polyposis
definition: Polypoidal masses arising mainly from the mucous membranes of the nose and paranasal sinuses. They are freely movable and nontender overgrowths of the mucosa that frequently accompany allergic rhinitis.

label: Corneal perforation
definition: A rupture of the cornea through which a portion of the iris protrudes.

label: Sterile pyuria
definition: Patients who routinely have greater than 20 leukocytes per microliter, but have abacterial urine, are said to have sterile pyuria.

label: Paraphimosis
definition: The foreskin becomes trapped behind the glans penis, and cannot be pulled back to its normal flaccid position covering the glans penis.

label: Esophageal web
definition: Thin (2-3mm) membranes of normal esophageal tissue consisting of mucosa and submucosa that can be congenital or acquired. Congenital webs commonly appear in the middle and inferior third of the esophagus, and they are more likely to be circumferential with a central or eccentric orifice. Acquired webs are much more common than congenital webs and typically appear in the cervical area (postcricoid). Clinical symptoms of this condition are selective (solid more than liquids) dysphagia, thoracic pain, nasopharyngeal reflux, aspiration, perforation and food impaction (the last two are very rare).

label: Camptocormia
definition: An abnormal forward-flexed posture e.g. forward flexion of the spine, which is noticeable when standing or walking but disappears when lying down. It is becoming an increasingly recognized feature of Parkinson's disease and dystonic disorders.

label: Absent nares
definition: The nostrils (the paired channels of the nose) are not present.

label: Pulmonary edema
definition: Fluid accumulation in the lungs.

label: Bifid penis
definition: Two penile structures, separated from the tip to the base of the shaft.

label: Penoscrotal transposition
definition: A partial or complete positional exchange between the penis and the scrotum, with positioning of the scrotum superior to the penis.

label: Eclampsia
definition: An acute and life-threatening complication of pregnancy, which is characterized by the appearance of tonic-clonic seizures, usually in a patient who had developed pre-eclampsia. Eclampsia includes seizures and coma that happen during pregnancy but are not due to preexisting or organic brain disorders.

label: Preeclampsia
definition: Pregnancy-induced hypertension in association with significant amounts of protein in the urine.

label: Neoplasm of the lip
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the lip.

label: Dysmenorrhea
definition: Pain during menstruation that interferes with daily activities.

label: Metrorrhagia
definition: Bleeding at irregular intervals.

label: Maternal hyperphenylalaninemia
definition: A medical history of exposure during the fetal period to hyperphenylalaninemia because the mother had phenylketonuria with inadequate control during pregnancy.

label: Multiple glomerular cysts
definition: The presence of many cysts in the glomerulus of the kidney related to dilatation of the Bowman's capsule.

label: Death in early adulthood
definition: Death between the age of 16 and 40 years.

label: Myositis
definition: A general term for inflammation of the muscles without respect to the underlying cause.

label: Testicular teratoma
definition: The presence of a teratoma of the testis.

label: Testicular seminoma
definition: The presence of a seminoma, an undifferentiated germ cell tumor of the testis.

label: Leydig cell neoplasia
definition: The presence of a neoplasm of the testis with origin in a Leydig cell.

label: Dysgerminoma
definition: The presence of a dysgerminoma, i.e., an undifferentiated germ cell tumor of the ovary.

label: Maternal seizure
definition: A seizure during pregnancy.

label: Abnormal corpus cavernosum morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the corpus cavernosum, the erectile tissue of the penis.

label: Esophageal diverticulum
definition: The presence of a diverticulum of the esophagus.

label: Esophagitis
definition: Inflammation of the esophagus.

label: Carotid paraganglioma
definition: A paraganglioma (a neuroendocrine neoplasm) originating in a carotid artery.

label: Pulmonary paraglioma
definition: A rare paranglioma of the lung, tumors that arise from extra-adrenal chromaffin cells.

label: Neoplasm of the pharynx
definition: A neoplasm originating in the pharynx.

label: Laryngeal cyst
definition: Presence of a cyst (sac-like structure) located in the larynx.

label: Melanonychia
definition: Brown or black discoloration of the nails.

label: Cystocele
definition: Anterior vaginal wall prolapse with bulging of the bladder into the vagina.

label: Vaginal hernia
definition: The presence of a hernia of the vagina.

label: Graves disease
definition: An autoimmune disease where the thyroid is overactive, producing an excessive amount of thyroid hormones (a serious metabolic imbalance known as hyperthyroidism and thyrotoxicosis). This is caused by autoantibodies to the TSH-receptor (TSHR-Ab) that activate that TSH-receptor (TSHR), thereby stimulating thyroid hormone synthesis and secretion, and thyroid growth (causing a diffusely enlarged goiter). The resulting state of hyperthyroidism can cause a dramatic constellation of neuropsychological and physical signs and symptoms, which can severely compromise the patients.

label: Type I diabetes mellitus
definition: A chronic condition in which the pancreas produces little or no insulin. Type I diabetes mellitus is manifested by the sudden onset of severe hyperglycemia with rapid progression to diabetic ketoacidosis unless treated with insulin.

label: Optic neuritis
definition: Inflammation of the optic nerve.

label: Retrobulbar optic neuritis
definition: Optic neuritis that occurs in the section of the optic nerve located behind the eyeball.

label: Thoracoabdominal wall defect
definition: Failure to close of the chest and abdominal wall likely caused by the failure of the ventral wall to close during week 4 of development.

label: Thoracoabdominal eventration
definition: Congenital protrusion of the abdominal or thoracic viscera, usually with a defect of the sternum and ribs as well as of the abdominal walls.

label: Cellulitis
definition: A bacterial infection and inflammation of the skin und subcutaneous tissues.

label: Trigeminal neuralgia
definition: A neuropathic disorder characterized by episodes of intense pain in the face, originating from the trigeminal nerve. One, two, or all three branches of the nerve may be affected.

label: Synotia
definition: A congenital malformation characterized by the union or approximation of the ears in front of the neck, often accompanied by the absence or defective development of the lower jaw.

label: Angioedema
definition: Rapid swelling (edema) of the dermis, subcutaneous tissue, mucosa and submucosal tissues of the skin of the face, normally around the mouth, and the mucosa of the mouth and/or throat, as well as the tongue during a period of minutes to several hours. The swelling can also occur elsewhere, typically in the hands. Angioedema is similar to urticaria, but the swelling is subcutaneous rather than on the epidermis.

label: Coarse metaphyseal trabecularization
definition: Coarse appearance of the components of the network of osseous tissue that makes up the cancellous structure of a bone, i.e., thickening of the (usually fine) white lines that are produced by trabeculae in radiograms.

label: Vaginal hydrocele
definition: A type of hydrocele testis in which the processus vaginalis remains patent only around the testes, and, as fluid accumulates, it renders the testes impalpable.

label: Vulval varicose vein
definition: Varicosity of veins in the vulval region.

label: Esophageal duplication
definition: A developmental disorder in which there is a duplication of a portion of the muscle and submucosa of the esophagus without epithelial duplication.

label: Tracheal atresia
definition: A congenital absence or considerable underdevelopment of the trachea such that communication between the larynx proximally and the alveoli of the lungs distally is lacking.

label: Polyotia
definition: The presence of an extra auricle on one or both sides of the head.

label: Iridodonesis
definition: Tremulousness of the iris on movement of the eye, occurring in subluxation of the lens.

label: Lipedema
definition: Excess deposit and expansion of adipose tissue in an unusual pattern which cannot be lost through diet and exercise .

label: Neurofibrosarcoma
definition: A form of malignant cancer of the connective tissue surrounding nerves. Given its origin and behavior, it is classified as a sarcoma.

label: Subcutaneous neurofibroma
definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the subcutis (subcutaneous region).

label: Abnormal pia mater
definition: An abnormality of the pia mater.

label: Tongue thrusting
definition: Pressing forward of the tongue in the mouth, a retained motoric habit from infantile swallowing patterns

label: Cerebral visual impairment
definition: A form of loss of vision caused by damage to the visual cortex rather than a defect in the eye.

label: Abnormal oligodendroglia morphology
definition: One of the three types of glia cells that, with the nerve cells, compose the central nervous system and are characterized by sheetlike processes that wrap around individual axons to form the myelin sheath of nerve fibers.

label: Abnormal microglia morphology
definition: An abnormality of the microglial cells. They are also known as brain-resident macrophages or Hortega cells.

label: Impulsivity
definition: Acting on the spur of the moment or on a momentary basis without consideration of outcomes; having difficulty establishing or following plans; experiencing a sense of urgency and engaging in behavior that is uninhibited, cannot be inhibited, and is uncontrolled. The possibility of repression is inconceivable.

label: Lens coloboma
definition: A sectoral indentation of the crystalline lens, usually due to zonular weakness or absence.

label: Mediastinal lymphadenopathy
definition: Swelling of lymph nodes within the mediastinum, the central compartment of the thoracic cavities that contains the heart and the great vessels, the esophagus, and trachea and other structures including lymph nodes.

label: Hypercoagulability
definition: An abnormality of coagulation associated with an increased risk of thrombosis.

label: Kaposi's sarcoma
definition: A systemic disease which can present with cutaneous lesions with or without internal involvement. Tumors are caused by Human herpesvirus 8 (HHV8), also known as Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus (KSHV).

label: Bronchogenic cyst
definition: A rare congenital cystic lesion of the lungs in the mediastinum.

label: Abnormal vertebral epiphysis morphology
definition: An anomaly of one or more epiphyses of one or more vertebrae.

label: Bulimia
definition: A form of anomalous eating behavior characterized by binge eating is followed by self-induced vomiting or other compensatory behavior intended to prevent weight gain (purging, fasting or exercising or a combination of these).

label: Macrodactyly of finger
definition: A type of Macrodactyly affecting one or several fingers.

label: Macrodactyly of toe
definition: A type of Macrodactyly affecting one or several toes.

label: Abnormal liver lobulation
definition: Formation of abnormal lobules (small masses of tissue) in the liver.

label: Schizophrenia
definition: A mental disorder characterized by a disintegration of thought processes and emotional responsiveness. It most commonly manifests as auditory hallucinations, paranoid or bizarre delusions, or disorganized speech and thinking. It is accompanied by significant social or occupational dysfunction. The onset of symptoms typically occurs in young adulthood, with a global lifetime prevalence of about 1%. This term is not a helpful parent term to describe abnormal experiences.

label: Mania
definition: A state of abnormally elevated or irritable mood, arousal, and/or energy levels.

label: Pancreatoblastoma
definition: A rare pediatric carcinoma of the pancreas.

label: Gangrene
definition: A serious and potentially life-threatening condition that arises when a considerable mass of body tissue dies (necrosis).

label: Clubbing of fingers
definition: Terminal broadening of the fingers (distal phalanges of the fingers).

label: Clubbing of toes
definition: Terminal broadening of the toes (distal phalanges of the toes).

label: Hemobilia
definition: Bleeding into the biliary tree.

label: Choriocarcinoma
definition: A malignant, trophoblastic and aggressive cancer, usually of the placenta. It is characterized by early hematogenous spread to the lungs and belongs to the far end of the spectrum of gestational trophoblastic disease (GTD), a subset of germ cell tumors.

label: Hyperperistalsis
definition: Excessively active peristalsis (wave of contraction of the tubular organs of the gastrointestinal tract) marked by excessive rapidity of the passage of food through the stomach and intestine.

label: Dural ectasia
definition: A widening or ballooning of the dural sac surrounding the spinal cord usually at the lumbosacral level.

label: Recurrent pharyngitis
definition: An increased susceptibility to pharyngitis as manifested by a history of recurrent pharyngitis.

label: Cryoglobulinemia
definition: Increased level of cryoglobulins in the blood. Cryoglobulins are abnormal immunoglobulins, especially IGG or IGM, that precipitate spontaneously when serum is cooled below 37 degrees Celsius.

label: Urogenital sinus anomaly
definition: A rare birth defect in women where the urethra and vagina both open into a common channel.

label: Conjunctival hamartoma
definition: A hamartoma (disordered proliferation of mature tissues) of the conjunctiva.

label: Breast aplasia
definition: Failure to develop and congenital absence of the breast.

label: Fused lips
definition: Lack of separation of the upper and lower lips.

label: Torus palatinus
definition: A bony protrusion present on the midline of the hard palate.

label: Acantholysis
definition: The loss of intercellular connections, such as desmosomes, resulting in loss of cohesion between keratinocytes.

label: Abnormally straight spine
definition: The absence of the normal curvature of the vertebral column.

label: Orchitis
definition: Testicular inflammation.

label: Toenail dysplasia
definition: An abnormality of the development of the toenails.

label: Fingernail dysplasia
definition: An abnormality of the development of the fingernails.

label: Pancreatic aplasia
definition: Aplasia of the pancreas.

label: Malposition of the stomach
definition: Abnormal anatomical location of the stomach. This feature may be due to intestinal malrotation.

label: Ungual fibroma
definition: Flesh-colored papule in or around the nail bed. Ungual fibromas may be periungual (arising under the proximal nail fold) or subungual (originating under the nail plate).

label: Neoplasm of the nail
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the nail.

label: Gastric diverticulum
definition: An outpouching of the gastric wall.

label: Scalp tenderness
definition: Pain or discomfort of the scalp elicited by palpation.

label: Testicular torsion
definition: Testicular torsion is when the spermatic cord to a testicle twists, cutting off the blood supply. The most common symptom is acute testicular pain.

label: Blue nevus
definition: A solitary, bluish, smooth surfaced macule, papule or plaque that is generally round or oval in shape. The histopathology of blue nevi varies by subtype, but general characteristics include a vertical wedge or bulbous shaped proliferation of spindle cells, dendritic melanocytes, and melanophages into a sclerotic dermis or subcutis.

label: Renovascular hypertension
definition: The presence of hypertension related to stenosis of the renal artery.

label: Long thorax
definition: Increased inferior to superior extent of the thorax.

label: Glomerulopathy
definition: Inflammatory or noninflammatory diseases affecting the glomeruli of the nephron.

label: Urethrocele
definition: The prolapse of the female urethra into the vagina.

label: Rectocele
definition: A Rectocele results from a tear in the rectovaginal septum (which is normally a tough, fibrous, sheet-like divider between the rectum and vagina). Rectal tissue bulges through this tear and into the vagina as a hernia. There are two main causes of this tear: childbirth, and hysterectomy.

label: Increased T cell count
definition: An abnormal increase in the total number of T cells detected in the blood.

label: Galactorrhea
definition: Spontaneous flow of milk from the breast, unassociated with childbirth or nursing.

label: Atrophodermia vermiculata
definition: Symmetrical vermiform facial atrophy that affects mainly the forehead, the chin, the ear lobes and helices. Atrophodermia vermiculata is characterized by erythema and follicular plugs on the cheeks, developing into painless reticular impressions.

label: Recurrent cutaneous abscess formation
definition: An increased susceptibility to cutaneous abscess formation, as manifested by a medical history of recurrent cutaneous abscesses.

label: Hepatic agenesis
definition: Absence of the liver owing to a failure of the liver to develop.

label: Microgastria
definition: A developmental anomaly with a small tubular or saccular midline stomach.

label: Septo-optic dysplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the optic nerve and absence of the septum pellucidum.

label: Anaphylactic shock
definition: An acute hypersensitivity reaction due to exposure to a previously encountered antigen.

label: Palmoplantar pustulosis
definition: A chronic, relapsing, pustular eruption that is localized to the palms and soles.

label: Pustule
definition: A small elevation of the skin containing cloudy or purulent material usually consisting of necrotic inflammatory cells.

label: Neoplasm of the scrotum
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the scrotum.

label: Neoplasm of the penis
definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the penis.

label: Hypoplastic areola
definition: Underdevelopment of the areola, the circular area of pigmented skin surrounding the nipple.

label: Triceps hypoplasia
definition: Hypoplasia of the triceps muscle.

label: Flat sella turcica
definition: An abnormally flat sella turcica.

label: Dilatation of celiac artery
definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the celiac artery.

label: Dilatation of superior mesenteric artery
definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the superior mesenteric artery .

label: Dilatation of Inferior mesenteric artery
definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the inferior mesenteric artery .

label: Sclerotic vertebral body
definition: Increase in bone density of the vertebral body.

label: Short femoral neck
definition: An abnormally short femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft).

label: Broad ischia
definition: Increased width of the ischium, which forms the lower and back part of the hip bone.

label: Short iliac bones
definition: Underdevelopment of the iliac bones.

label: Duodenal stenosis
definition: The narrowing or partial blockage of a portion of the duodenum.

label: Palmar telangiectasia
definition: The presence of telangiectases on the skin of palm of hand.

label: Plantar telangiectasia
definition: Telangiectases (small dilated blood vessels) located on the skin of sole of foot.

label: Thick hair
definition: Increased density of hairs, i.e., and elevated number of hairs per unit area.

label: Hemimacroglossia
definition: Increased length and width of one half of the tongue.

label: Infra-orbital crease
definition: Skin crease extending from below the inner canthus laterally along the malar process of the maxilla and zygoma.

label: Renal diverticulum
definition: Cystic, urine-containing intrarenal cavities lined with transitional cell epithelium that communicate through a narrow channel with the collecting system.

label: Congenital mesoblastic nephroma
definition: Congenital mesoblastic nephroma is a type of kidney tumor that is usually found before birth by ultrasound or within the first 3 months of life. It contains fibroblastic cells (connective tissue cells), and may spread to the other kidney or to nearby tissue.

label: Fibrous hamartoma
definition: A rare, benign soft tissue tumor that typically occurs within the first two years of life.

label: Chorangioma
definition: Hamartoma-like growth in the placenta consisting of blood vessels.

label: Compensatory scoliosis
definition: A scoliosis which is the results of a difference in leg length (which might be due to hemihypertrophy or hemihypotrophy of a leg) and the resulting tilting of the pelvis. If untreated this will lead to the development of scoliosis over time.

label: Lateral venous anomaly
definition: Persistence of the embryonic dorsal or sciatic vein system that normally should have involuted around the tenth to twelfth week of intrauterine life.

label: Abnormal ductus choledochus morphology
definition: An abnormality of the Common bile duct, a tube-like anatomic structure in the human gastrointestinal tract, formed by the union of the Common hepatic duct and the Cystic duct from the gall bladder.

label: Bifid xiphoid process
definition: A cleft of the xiphoid process of the sternum.

label: Abnormality of the xiphoid process
definition: An abnormality of the xiphoid process of the sternum.

label: Prominent xiphoid process
definition: Increased prominence of the xiphoid process of the sternum.

label: Broad xiphoid process
definition: Increased side-to-side width of the xiphoid process of the sternum.

label: Rectal polyposis
definition: The presence of multiple rectal hyperplastic/adenomatous polyps.

label: Clavicular sclerosis
definition: An increase in bone density within the clavicle.

label: Enlarged sylvian cistern
definition: An increase in size of the subarachnoid space associated with the lateral cerebral sulcus (Sylvian fissure).

label: Open operculum
definition: Underdevelopment of the operculum.

label: Narrow foramen obturatorium
definition: Decreased width of the foramen obturatorium. The foramen obturatorium (also known as the obturator foramen) is a hole located between the ischium and pubis bones of the pelvis.

label: Dense metaphyseal bands
definition: Dense radiopaque bands of bone which are thicker than the adjacent diaphyseal cortex and may form at the metaphysis of growing bones. They appear on radiographs as bone that is more radiopaque that the adjacent diaphyseal cortex.

label: Lateral ventricular asymmetry
definition: Abnormal difference in size between the left and right lateral cerebral ventricles.

label: Enlarged hippocampus
definition: Increase in size of the hippocampus.

label: Excessive shyness
definition: Atypically high degree of awkwardness or apprehension experienced when approaching or being approached by others.

label: Hyperesthesia
definition: Increased sensitivity to stimulation, excluding the special senses, which may refer to various modes of cutaneous sensibility including touch and thermal sensation without pain, as well as to pain.

label: Dysharmonic accelerated bone age
definition: A type of dysharmonic skeletal maturation in which there is an acceleration in skeletal maturation whose degree differs markedly in different bones.

label: Splayed epiphyses
definition: Flaring (widening) of the epiphysis.

label: Acrokeratosis
definition: Overgrowth of the stratum corneum characterized by flesh-coloured or slightly pigmented smooth or warty papules on the upper surface of hands and feet.

label: Cerebral white matter agenesis
definition: Congenital defect with failure of the development of the cerebral white matter.

label: Protanomaly
definition: A type of anomalous trichromacy associated with defective long-wavelength-sensitive (L) cones, causing the sensitivity spectrum to be shifted toward medium wavelengths. This leads to difficulties especially in distinguishing red and green.

label: Down-sloping shoulders
definition: Low set, steeply sloping shoulders.

label: Choroid plexus papilloma
definition: Choroid plexus papilloma is a histologically benign neoplasm located in the ventricular system of the choroid plexus.

label: Priapism
definition: A painful and harmful medical condition in which the erect penis doesn't return to its flaccid state, despite the absence of both physical and psychological stimulation, within four hours.

label: Mandibular pain
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the mandible.

label: Pretibial myxedema
definition: A diffuse, non-pitting edema and thickening of the skin usually on the anterior aspect of the lower legs spreading to the dorsum of the feet.

label: Vasculitis in the skin
definition: A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) that affects skeletal muscle tissue.

label: Kayser-Fleischer ring
definition: Grey-green or brownish-pigmented ring in the deep epithelial layers at the outer border of the cornea.

label: Skin erosion
definition: A discontinuity of the skin exhibiting incomplete loss of the epidermis, a lesion that is moist, circumscribed, and usually depressed.

label: Porokeratosis
definition: A clonal disorder of keratinization with one or multiple atrophic patches surrounded by a clinically and histologically distinctive hyperkeratotic ridgelike border called the cornoid lamella.

label: Cat cry
definition: The presence of a characteristic high-pitched cry that sounds similar to the meowing of a kitten.

label: Chondritis of pinna
definition: Inflammation of the cartilage of the external ear.

label: Upper limb hypertonia
definition: Increased muscle tone observed in the arms of the affected person.

label: Hemihypotrophy of lower limb
definition: Shortening of a leg affecting only one side.

label: Small hand
definition: Disproportionately small hand.

label: Marcus Gunn pupil
definition: An aberrant pupillary response characterized by (i) Constriction of pupils of both eyes when the light stimulus is applied to the normal eye, and (ii) Dilatation of pupils of both eyes when the light stimulus is rapidly transferred from the normal eye (after brief light exposure to the normal eye) to the affected eye.

label: Colorectal polyposis
definition: Multiple abnormal growths that arise from the lining of the large intestine (colon or rectum) and protrude into the intestinal lumen.

label: Recurrent spontaneous abortion
definition: Repeated episodes of abortion (Expulsion of the product of fertilization before completing the term of gestation) without deliberate interference.

label: Peripheral vitreoretinal degeneration
definition: A type of vitreoretinal degeneration with manifestations that are concentrated at the periphery of the retina.

label: Episodic quadriplegia
definition: Intermittent episodes of paralysis of all four limbs.

label: Respiratory insufficiency due to defective ciliary clearance
Giant cell hepatitis
definition: Chronic hepatitis characterized by parenchymal inflammation with formation of large multinucleated hepatocytes in response to a variety of insults to the liver.

label: Triangular-shaped open mouth
definition: A facial appearance characterized by a permanently or nearly permanently opened mouth, in which the upper lip is tented in a way that the opened mouth has the appearance of a triangle.

label: Oral mucosal blisters
definition: Blisters arising in the mouth.

label: Absent fifth fingernail
definition: Absence of nail of little finger.

label: Recurrent upper and lower respiratory tract infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to upper and lower respiratory tract infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of upper and lower respiratory tract infections.

label: Acute hepatitis
definition: Acute hepatic injury resulting from inflammation typically accompanied by increased serum alanine transaminase activity. Etiologies include viral hepatitis, drugs, toxins, and autoimmune disorders.

label: Chronic active hepatitis
definition: Chronic hepatitis associated with recurrent clinical exacerbations, extrahepatic manifestations, and progression to cirrhosis.

label: Chronic hepatitis
definition: Hepatitis that lasts for more than six months.

label: Chronic hepatitis due to cryptosporidium infection
definition: Chronic hepatitis associated with infection by cryptosporidia, as demonstrated (for example) by immunohistochemistry of liver tissue.

label: Atrial cardiomyopathy
definition: Any complex of structural, architectural, contractile or electrophysiological changes affecting the atria with the potential to produce clinically relevant manifestations.

label: Biventricular hypertrophy
definition: Thickening of the heart walls in both ventricles.

label: Epileptic encephalopathy
definition: A condition in which epileptiform abnormalities are believed to contribute to the progressive disturbance in cerebral function. Epileptic encephalaopathy is characterized by (1) electrographic EEG paroxysmal activity that is often aggressive, (2) seizures that are usually multiform and intractable, (3) cognitive, behavioral and neurological deficits that may be relentless, and (4) sometimes early death.

label: Neuronal loss in basal ganglia
definition: A reduction in the number of nerve cells in the basal ganglia.

label: Abnormal liver function tests during pregnancy
Increased serum bile acid concentration during pregnancy
Cutaneous mastocytosis
definition: Multifocal dense infiltrates of mast cells in cutaneous tissue.

label: Agenesis of permanent mandibular lateral incisor
Agenesis of primary mandibular lateral incisor
Tall chin
definition: Increased vertical distance from the vermillion border of the lower lip to the inferior-most point of the chin.

label: Chin with vertical crease
definition: Vertical crease fold situated below the vermilion border of the lower lip and above the fatty pad of the chin with the face at rest.

label: Extra concha fold
definition: Folds or ridges within the concha that are distinct from the crus helix.

label: Focal absence of the external ear
definition: Absence of a localized portion of the ear that cannot be described by a more precise term (e.g., absent ear lobe).

label: Long ear
definition: Median longitudinal ear length greater than two SD above the mean determined by the maximal distance from the superior aspect to the inferior aspect of the external ear.

label: Short ear
definition: Median longitudinal ear length less than two SD above the mean determined by the maximal distance from the superior aspect to the inferior aspect of the external ear.

label: Polymenorrhea
definition: Frequent menses; menstrual cycles lasting less than 21 days.

label: Menometrorrhagia
definition: Prolonged/excessive menses and bleeding at irregular intervals.

label: Abnormal vomer morphology
definition: An abnormality of the vomer.

label: Abnormality of ophthalmic artery
definition: Abnormality of the first branch of the internal carotid artery.

label: Abnormality of the somatic nervous system
definition: Any abnormality of the part of the peripheral nervous system associated with sensation and skeletal muscle voluntary control of body movements.

label: Abnormality of masticatory muscle
definition: Any abnormality of the masticatory muscle.

label: Abnormal mouth floor morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the mouth floor.

label: Abnormality of the submandibular region
definition: Any abnormality of the submandibular region, the region between the mandible and the hyoid bone contains the submandibular and sublingual glands, suprahyoid muscles, submandibular ganglion, and lingual artery.

label: Abnormal ganglion morphology
definition: An abnormality of nerve cell cluster or a group of nerve cell bodies located in the autonomic nervous system.

label: Abnormal peripheral nervous system ganglion morphology
definition: An abnormality of nerve cell cluster or a group of nerve cell bodies located in the peripheral autonomic nervous system.

label: Abnormal cranial ganglion morphology
definition: An abnormality of nerve cell cluster or a group of nerve cell bodies located in the autonomic nervous system of the cranium.

label: Otitis externa
definition: Inflammation or infection of the external auditory canal (EAC), the auricle, or both.

label: Recurrent ear infections
definition: Increased susceptibility to ear infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of ear infections.

label: Epigastric pain
definition: Pain that is localized to the region of the upper abdomen immediately below the ribs.

label: Fish odor
definition: Body odor characterized by an offensive body odor and the smell of rotting fish due to the excessive excretion of trimethylamine (TMA) in the urine, sweat, and breath of affected individuals.

label: Body odor
definition: A perceived unpleasant smell given off by the body.

label: Musty odor
definition: Pungent body odor.

label: Vaginal fish odor
