definition: A fish odor in the vaginal area, that is characteristic of bacterial vaginosis (BV), and is due to trimethylamine (TMA).

label: Abnormal distribution of cell junction proteins in buccal mucosal cells
definition: An anomalous amount or location of cell junction proteins such as plakoglobin or Cx43.

label: Abnormal buccal mucosa morphology
definition: An abnormality of a buccal mucosa.

label: Abnormal periodontium morphology
definition: Any abnormality of the periodontium.

label: Alveolar bone loss around teeth
definition: A decrease in the amount of alveolar bone around the root of a tooth.

label: Recurrent oral herpes
definition: Recurrent episodes of oral herpes, typically characterized by blisters or ulcers on the gums, lips and/or tongue caused by herpes virus.

label: Submucous cleft of soft and hard palate
definition: Soft and hard-palate submucous clefts are characterized by bony defects in the midline of the soft and hard palate that are covered by the lining (ie mucous membrane) of the roof of the mouth.

label: Unilateral alveolar cleft of maxilla
definition: One sided alveolar cleft of the maxilla.

label: Bilateral alveolar cleft of maxilla
definition: Nonmidline alveolar cleft of the maxilla.

label: Decreased level of 1,5 anhydroglucitol in serum
definition: A decrease in the level of 1,5 anhydroglucitol in the serum. 1,5-Anhydrosorbitol is a validated marker of short-term glycemic control. This substance is derived mainly from food, is well absorbed in the intestine, and is distributed to all organs and tissues.

label: Increased level of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaric acid in urine
definition: The concentration of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased level of allantoin in serum
definition: An increase in the level of allantoin in the serum.

label: Elevated circulating gamma-aminobutyric acid concentration
definition: An increase in the level of Gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) in the blood circulation.

label: Decreased circulating GABA concentration
definition: A decrease in the level of GABA in the serum.

label: Decreased level of erythritol in urine
definition: A decrease in the level of erythritol in the urine.

label: Decreased CSF erythritol concentration
definition: Concentration of erythritol in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

label: Increased level of D-threitol in plasma
definition: An increase in the level of D-threitol in the plasma.

label: Increased CSF D-threitol concentration
definition: The concentration of D-threitol in the cerebrospinal fluid is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased level of D-threitol in urine
definition: An increase in the level of D-threitol in the urine.

label: Decreased level of D-mannose in urine
definition: A decrease in the level of D-mannose in the urine.

label: Increased level of galactitol in plasma
definition: An increase in the level of galactitol in the plasma.

label: Increased level of galactitol in urine
definition: An increase in the level of galactitol in the urine.

label: Increased level of galactonate in red blood cells
definition: An increase in the level of galactonate in the red blood cells.

label: Increased level of galactitol in red blood cells
definition: An increase in the level of galactitol in the red blood cells.

label: Increased level of hippuric acid in blood
definition: An increase in the level of hippuric acid in the blood.

label: Increased level of hippuric acid in urine
definition: An increase in the level of hippuric acid in the urine.

label: Increased level of L-fucose in urine
definition: An increase in the level of L-fucose in the urine.

label: Increased level of propylene glycol in blood
definition: An increase in the level of propylene glycol in the blood.

label: Increased level of ribitol in urine
definition: An increase in the level of ribitol in the urine. Ribotol is a crystalline pentose alcohol (C5H12O5) and is a metabolic end product formed by the reduction of ribose.

label: Increased CSF ribitol concentration
definition: The concentration of ribitol in the cerebrospinal fluid is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased level of ribose in urine
definition: An increase in the level of ribose in the urine.

label: Increased CSF ribose concentration
definition: The concentration of ribose in the cerebrospinal fluid is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased level of xylitol in urine
definition: An increase in the level of xylitol in the urine.

label: Increased CSF xylitol concentration
definition: The concentration of xylitol in the cerebrospinal fluid is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased level of L-pyroglutamic acid in urine
definition: An increase in the level of L-pyroglutamic acid in the urine.

label: Chronic idiopathic urticaria
definition: Urticaria characterized by spontaneously recurring hives for 6 weeks or longer.

label: Cold urticaria
definition: Urticaria may be caused by cold temperatures.

label: Aquagenic urticaria
definition: A form of physical urticaria, in which contact with water, regardless of its temperature and source, evokes pruritic follicular wheals on the skin.

label: Solar urticaria
definition: Urticaria in response to exposure to ultraviolet-A (UVA), ultraviolet-B (UVB), visible and rarely infrared light.

label: Vibratory urticaria
definition: Urticaria in response to dermal vibration, with coincident degranulation of mast cells and increased histamine levels in serum.

label: Exercise induced anaphylaxis
definition: Anaphylaxis after physical activity.

label: Abnormal circulating biotinidase concentration
definition: An abnormality in the biotinidase level, an enzyme that releases biotin from biocytin, the product of biotin-dependent carboxylases degradation.

label: Decreased circulating biotinidase concentration
definition: Concentration of biotinidase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. Biotidinase is an enzyme that releases biotin from biocytin, the product of biotin-dependent carboxylases degradation.

label: Elevated circulating biotinidase concentration
definition: Concentration of biotinidase in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Biotidinase is an enzyme that releases biotin from biocytin, the product of biotin-dependent carboxylases degradation.

label: Eosinophilic infiltration in the stomach mucosa
definition: Infiltration of eosinophils in the stomach mucosa, that is diagnosed by an upper endoscopy and microscopy that shows more than 20 eosinophils per high-power field in association with peripheral eosinophilia and the absence of secondary cause of eosinophilia.

label: Idiopathic anaphylaxis
definition: A rare form of anaphylaxis for which triggers cannot be identified despite a detailed history and careful diagnostic assessment.

label: Drug-induced anaphylaxis
definition: A form of anaphylaxis that is triggered by intake of drugs or medications.

label: Eosinophilic infiltration of the esophagus
definition: Infiltration of numerous eosinophils (usually greater than 15 per high power field) into the squamous epithelium of the esophagus, and layering of eosinophils on the surface layer of the esophagus.

label: Eosinophilic microabscess formation in the esophagus
definition: The formation of small localized collection of eosinophiles (an eosinophilic microabscess) in the esophagus. Usually clusters of greater than or equal to 4 eosinophils are seen, that appear as exudates or white spots or white plaques.

label: Increased level of methylsuccinic acid in urine
definition: The concentration of methylsuccinic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased level of myristic acid in serum
definition: An increase in the level of myristic acid in the serum.

label: Increased level of N-acetylneuraminic acid in urine
definition: An increase in the level of N-acetylneuraminic acid in the urine.

label: Increased level of N-acetylneuraminic acid in fibroblasts
definition: An increase in the level of N-acetylneuraminic acid in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Defective interstrand cross-link repair
definition: A defect in the of the process of interstrand cross-link repair: removal of a DNA interstrand crosslink (a covalent attachment of DNA bases on opposite strands of the DNA) and restoration of the DNA. DNA interstrand crosslinks occur when both strands of duplex DNA are covalently tethered together (e.g. by an exogenous or endogenous agent), thus preventing the strand unwinding necessary for essential DNA functions such as transcription and replication.

label: Abnormal morphology of the chest musculature
definition: Any abnormality of the chest muscles.

label: Abnormality of the back musculature
definition: Any abnormality of the back muscles.

label: Abnormal morphology of the shoulder musculature
definition: Any abnormality of the shoulder muscles.

label: Hippocampal atrophy
definition: Partial or complete wasting (loss) of hippocampus tissue that was once present.

label: Increased cotinine level
definition: Increased concentration of cotinine in urine.

label: Increased circulating troponin I concentration
definition: An increased concentration of tropnin I in the blood, which is a cardiac regulatory protein that controls the calcium mediated interaction between actin and myosin. Raised cardiac troponin concentrations are now accepted as the standard biochemical marker for the diagnosis of myocardial infarction.

label: Abnormal cardiac biomarker test
definition: Abnormal blood test results measuring creatine kinase (CK), CK-MB, troponin (TROPI), myoglobin, and/or cardiac enzymes.

label: Increased circulating troponin T concentration
definition: An increased concentration of tropnin T in the blood, which is a cardiac regulatory protein that controls the calcium mediated interaction between actin and myosin. Raised cardiac troponin concentrations are now accepted as the standard biochemical marker for the diagnosis of myocardial infarction.

label: Abnormal circulating glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase concentration
definition: An anomaly in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase.

label: Abnormal glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in blood
definition: An anomaly in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in the blood.

label: Increased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in blood
definition: An increase in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in the blood.

label: Decreased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in blood
definition: A decrease in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in the blood.

label: Abnormal glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in dried blood spot
definition: An anomaly in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in a dried blood spot.

label: Increased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in dried blood spot
definition: An increase in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in a dried blood spot.

label: Decreased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in dried blood spot
definition: A decrease in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in a dried blood spot.

label: Abnormal glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in leukocytes
definition: An anomaly in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in leukocytes.

label: Abnormal glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in red blood cells
definition: An anomaly in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in red blood cells.

label: Abnormal glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in tissue
definition: An anomaly in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in tissue.

label: Increased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in tissue
definition: An increase in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in tissue.

label: Decreased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in tissue
definition: A decrease in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in tissue.

label: Decreased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in red blood cells
definition: A decrease in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in red blood cells.

label: Increased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in red blood cells
definition: An increase in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in red blood cells.

label: Decreased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in leukocytes
definition: A decrease in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in leukocytes.

label: Increased glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase level in leukocytes
definition: An increase in the level of glucose-6-phosphate dehydrogenase in leukocytes.

label: Abnormal circulating UDP glucose-4-epimerase concentration
definition: An abnormality in uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase level in plasma. Uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase catalyzes the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

label: Increased circulating UDP glucose-4-epimerase concentration
definition: An increase in uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase level in plasma. Uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase catalyzes the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

label: Decreased circulating UDP glucose-4-epimerase concentration
definition: A decrease in uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase level in plasma. Uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase catalyzes the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

label: Abnormal erythrocyte UDP glucose-4-epimerase concentration
definition: An abnormality in uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase level in red blood cells. Uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase catalyzes the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

label: Increased erythrocyte UDP glucose-4-epimerase concentration
definition: An increase in uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase level in red blood cells. Uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase catalyzes the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

label: Decreased erythrocyte UDP glucose-4-epimerase concentration
definition: A decrease in uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase level in red blood cells. Uridine diphosphate glucose-4-epimerase catalyzes the reaction: UDP-glucose = UDP-galactose.

label: Increased CSF urate concentration
definition: Increased concentration of urate in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Abnormal CSF urate concentration
definition: Abnormal concentration of urate in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Positive meconium barbiturate test
definition: Detection of barbiturate metabolites such as phenobarbital in meconium.

label: Meconium xenobiotic
definition: Presence of a xenobiotic in meconium.

label: Positive hair barbiturate test
definition: Detection of barbiturate metabolites such as phenobarbital in the hair.

label: Hair xenobiotic
definition: Presence of xenobiotic in hair.

label: Positive stool barbiturate test
definition: Detection of barbiturate metabolites such as phenobarbital in the stool.

label: Stool xenobiotic
definition: Presence of xenobiotic in stool.

label: Positive gastric fluid barbiturate test
definition: Detection of barbiturate metabolites such as phenobarbital in the gastric fluid.

label: Gastric fluid xenobiotic
definition: Presence of a xenobiotic in gastric fluid.

label: Increased intestinal transit time
definition: An increase in the length of time required for food to pass through the intestines.

label: Abnormal circulating nicotinurate concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of nicotinurate in the blood.

label: Increased circulating nicotinurate level
definition: An increased amount of nicotinurate in the blood.

label: Positive methadone plasma/serum test
definition: Detection of methadone or its metabolite 2-ethylidene-1,5-dimethyl-3,3- diphenylpyrrolidine (EDDP) in plasma or serum.

label: Plasma/serum xenobiotic
definition: Presence of a xenobiotic in plasma and/or serum.

label: Positive plasma/serum cotinine test
definition: Detection of cotinine, an alkaloid found in tobacco and the predominant metabolite of nicotine, in plasma or serum.

label: Folate deficiency in CSF
definition: A reduced concentration of folic acid, which is also known as vitamin B9 in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Abnormal cord blood measurement
definition: An abnormality in any umbilical cord measurement performed after birth, such as the blood gas level.

label: Abnormal blood gas level in cord blood
Hyperoxemia in cord blood
definition: An abnormally high level of blood oxygen in the cord blood.

label: Abnormal oxygen level in cord blood
definition: An abnormal level of blood oxygen in the cord blood.

label: Hypoxemia in cord blood
definition: An abnormally low level of blood oxygen in the cord blood.

label: Hypercapnia in cord blood
definition: Abnormally elevated blood carbon dioxide (CO2) level in the cord blood.

label: Abnormal carbon dioxide level in cord blood
definition: Abnormal amount of carbon dioxide in umbilical cord blood

label: Hypocapnia in cord blood
definition: Abnormally decreased blood carbon dioxide (CO2) level in the cord blood.

label: Abnormal blood 5-methyltetrahydrofolate level
definition: An abnormal concentration of 5-methyltetrahydrofolate in the blood.

label: Reduced blood 5-methyltetrahydrofolate level
definition: A decreased concentration of 5-methyltetrahydrofolate in the blood.

label: Hypoplasia of maxilla relative to mandible
definition: Abnormally small dimension of the maxilla (upper jaw) relative to the mandible (lower jaw).

label: Hypoplasia of mandible relative to maxilla
definition: Abnormally small dimension of the mandible (lower jaw) relative to the maxilla (upper jaw).

label: Increased anti-dairy protein IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against dairy proteins, including casein, alpha-lactalbumin, beta-lactoglobulin or bovine serum albumin contained in cow, sheep or goat milk and milk products.

label: Increased anti-food allergen IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against proteins found in foods, such as milk, egg, soy, wheat, peanut, treenut, fish, and shellfish.

label: Increased anti-animal protein IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against animal proteins, such as albumins that are present in animal hair, dander, shed skin, saliva and urine.

label: Increased anti-seafood IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against seafood, including fish, shrimp, lobster, crab, squid and abalone.

label: Increased anti-dust mite IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against dust mites, such as house dust mites.

label: Increased anti-bacteria IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against bacteria.

label: Increased anti-drug IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against a drug or class of drugs, such as antibiotics.

label: Increased anti-feather IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against feathers, which could be indicative of an allergy against feathers themselves, or mite allergens present in feathers.

label: Increased anti-plant based food allergen IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against a plant based food allergen, including vegetables and fruits.

label: Increased anti-gluten IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against gluten, a protein found in wheat, barley, and rye.

label: Increased anti-nut food product IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against nut food products such as peanuts or tree nuts, such as hazelnuts, walnuts, cashews, and almonds.

label: Increased anti-egg IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against eggs, including egg whites, egg yolks, and egg proteins such as ovoalbumin and ovomucoid.

label: Increased anti-fungi IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against fungus, such as molds like zygomycota, ascomycota and deuteromycota.

label: Increased anti-meat allergen IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against meat, such as mammalian meat, including beef or pork, or poultry, like duck or chicken.

label: Increased anti-parasite IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against parasites, such as helminths (parasitic worms, such as Ascaris lumbricoides, Trichuris trichiura, Ancylostoma duodenalis, Necator americanus, Strongyloides stercoralis) or parasites such as Toxoplasma gondii.

label: Increased anti-insect IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against antigens from insects such as moths, mosquitos, or cockroaches.

label: Increased anti-venom IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against venom from insects such as bees, wasps, hornets, yellowjackets.

label: Increased anti-plant product IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against antigens from plants and products derived from plants, such as wood or pollen.

label: Positive urine norcotinine test
definition: Detection of norcotinine, a metabolite of nicotine, in urine.

label: Abnormal circulating IgD concentration
definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgD immunoglobulin in blood.

label: Increased circulating IgD concentration
definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin D in blood.

label: Increased anti-animal dander IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against animal dander, tiny scales shed from animal skin or hair, such as from pet dogs or cats.

label: Increased anti-house dust mite IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against house dust mites, a common allergen.

label: Increased anti-alpha-gal IgE antibody level
definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against galactose-alpha-1, 3 galactose (alpha-gal), a carbohydrate found in mammalian meat.

label: Abnormal L-selectin shedding
definition: An abnormality in the cleavage of L-selectin during the process of guiding neutrophils to the site of infection. Proteolytic cleavage of L-selectin results in rapid shedding from the cell surface, which has a role in neutrophil rolling and accumulation at the site of infection.

label: Chronic neutropenia
definition: Neutropenia with an absolute neutrophil count (ANC) less than 1,500,000,000/L lasting for more than 3 months.

label: Myeloid maturation arrest
definition: Chornic neutropenia arising from an impaired proliferation and maturation of myeloid progenitor cells in the bone marrow.

label: Cyclic neutropenia in myeloid maturation arrest in bone marrow
definition: Cyclic neutropenia arising from an impaired proliferation and maturation of myeloid progenitor cells in the bone marrow.

label: Transient neutropenia
definition: A transient reduction in the number of neutrophils in the peripheral blood. Transient neutropenia is most commonly associated with viral infections, but other causes include drugs and autoimmunity.

label: Infection associated neutropenia
definition: Transient neutropenia caused by an infection, such as with a virus, bacteria or protozoan.

label: Neutrophilia in presence of infection
definition: An increased number of neutrophils circulating in the blood during an infection, such as with a bacteria, virus or fungus.

label: Neutrophilia in absence of infection
definition: An increased number of neutrophils circulating in the blood in the absence of an infection. Factors contributing to neutrophilia could include inflammation or congenital disorders.

label: Hepatopulmonary fusion
definition: Fusion of the liver with the lung.

label: Asymmetrical gluteal crease
definition: The presence of an asymmetrical gluteal crease, the horizontal crease formed by the inferior aspect of the buttocks and the posterior upper leg.

label: Wide space between 4th and 5th toe
definition: A widely spaced gap between the fourth toe and the fifth (pinky) toe.

label: Lower cranial nerve dysfunction
definition: A functional abnormality affecting the lower cranial nerves, which include the paired 9th (glossopharyngeal), 10th (vagal), 11th (accessory) and 12th (hypoglossal) cranial nerves.

label: Subglottic hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, located in the airway, typically below the vocal chords, that can cause severe obstruction of the airway.

label: Supraglottic hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, located in the upper part of the larynx (voice box) including the epiglottis; the area above the vocal cords.

label: Intestinal hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, located in the intestines, which includes the bowel.

label: Spleen hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the spleen.

label: Labial hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the upper lip.

label: Esophageal hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the esophagus.

label: Laryngeal hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the glottic or supraglottic regions.

label: Vulvar hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the vulva.

label: Retropharyngeal hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the retropharyngeal space, the portion of the peripharyngeal space that is located posterior to the pharynx.

label: Paraspinal hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the paraspinal muscular region, the muscles next to the spine.

label: Lumbosacral hemangioma
definition: A spinal cord hemangioma located in the lumbosacral spine region.

label: Supraumbilical raphe
definition: An abnormality of the sternum that presents at birth as a ventral sternal non-union defect, due to an abnormality of the fusion of the layers of the skin. It presents as a scar-like line that extends upward from the umbilicus (belly button).

label: Sternal pit
definition: A sternal pit is a small indentation or dimple in the skin overlying the sternum of the chest. In some cases, the skin defect can be linear, extending several inches over the sternum.

label: Pituitary gland cyst
definition: A fluid-filled sacs that develop on or near the pituitary gland.

label: Atrophic pituitary gland
definition: Partial or complete wasting (loss) of the pituitary gland.

label: Dyspepsia
definition: A heterogeneous group of symptoms that are localized in the epigastric region. Typical dyspeptic symptoms include postprandial fullness, early satiation, epigastric pain and epigastric burning, but other upper gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea, belching or abdominal bloating often occur.

label: Abnormal circulating amylase concentration
definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands.

label: Positive blood acetaminophen test
definition: Detection of acetaminophen in the blood.

label: Positive norpropoxyphene blood test
definition: Detection of norpropoxyphene in the blood, a major metabolite of the opioid analgesic drug dextropropoxyphene.

label: Positive meconium methadone test
definition: Detection of methadone or its metabolite 2-ethylidene-1,5-dimethyl-3,3- diphenylpyrrolidine (EDDP) in meconium.

label: Positive blood molindone test
definition: Detection of molindone in the blood, an antipyschotic used for treatment of schizophrenia.

label: Intrathoracic hemangioma
definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the intrathoracic or chest region.

label: Hyperamylasemia
definition: Increased level of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands.

label: Hypoamylasemia
definition: Decreased level of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands.

label: Positive urine norpropoxyphene test
definition: Detection of norpropoxyphene in urine.

label: Negativism
definition: Opposing or not responding to instructions or external stimuli.

label: Absent isohemagglutinin level
definition: Absent or undetectable level of isohemagglutinin. An isohemagglutinin refers to the naturally occurring antibodies in the ABO blood group system (i.e., anti-A in a group B person, anti-B in a group A person, and anti-A, anti-B, and anti-A,B in a group O person).

label: Decreased specific antibody response to protein vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against proteins in vaccines, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to tetanus vaccine
definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a tetanus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to hepatitis B vaccine
definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a hepatisis B antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Partial absence of specific antibody response to tetanus vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a tetanus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Partial absence of specific antibody response to hepatitis B vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a hepatitis B antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Decreased specific antibody response to polysaccharide vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against polysaccharides in vaccines, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to unconjugated pneumococcus vaccine
definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a pneumococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Partial absence of specific antibody response to unconjugated pneumococcus vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a pneumococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Decreased specific antibody response to protein-conjugated polysaccharide vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against protein-conjugated polysaccharides in vaccines, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) vaccine
definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to meningococcus vaccine
definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a meningococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Partial absence of specific antibody response to Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Partial absence of specific antibody response to meningococcus vaccine
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a meningococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

label: Positive stool methadone test
definition: Detection of methadone and its metabolites in the stool.

label: Decreased specific antibody response to infection
definition: A reduced ability to synthesize antibodies against antigens from an infectious agent or pathogen (such as bacteria, viruses, parasites, etc.), as measured by antibody titer determination following infection.

label: Alpha-aminoadipic aciduria
definition: The concentration of alpha-aminoadipic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Hyposegmentation of neutrophil nuclei in CSF
definition: Hyposegmented (hypolobulated) or bilobed neutrophil nuclei in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Hypersegmentation of neutrophil nuclei in CSF
definition: An excessive division of the lobes of the nucleus of a neutrophil in the cerebrospinal fluid.

label: Abnormal urinary 1-methylhistidine concentration
definition: Abnormal concentration of 1-methylhistidine in the urine.

label: Decreased urinary 1-methylhistidine
definition: Decreased concentration of 1-methylhistidine in the urine.

label: Increased urinary 1-methylhistidine
definition: Increased concentration of 1-methylhistidine in the urine.

label: Abnormal urinary 3-methylhistidine level
definition: Abnormal amount of 3-methylhistidine in the urine.

label: Increased urinary 3-methylhistidine
definition: Increased concentration of 3-methylhistidine in the urine.

label: Decreased urinary 3-methylhistidine
definition: Decreased concentration of 3-methylhistidine in the urine.

label: Alpha-gal allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against alpha-gal.

label: Animal protein allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against animal proteins.

label: Animal dander allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against animal dander.

label: Bacteria allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against bacteria.

label: Drug allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against drugs.

label: Dust mite allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against dust mites.

label: Feather allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against feathers.

label: Food allergy
definition: Primary food allergies primarily occur as a result (most likely) of gastrointestinal sensitization to predominantly stable food allergens (glycoproteins). A secondary food allergy develops after primary sensitization to airborne allergens (e. g., pollen allergens) with subsequent reactions (due to cross-reactivity) to structurally related often labile allergens in (plant) foods.

label: Egg allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against eggs.

label: Gluten allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against gluten.

label: Meat allergen allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against allergens contained in meat products.

label: Nut food product allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against nut food products.

label: Plant based food allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against plant based food allergens.

label: Seafood allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against seafood.

label: Fungi allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against fungus.

label: Insect allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against insects.

label: Venom allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against insect venom.

label: Parasite allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against parasites.

label: Plant product allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against plant products.

label: Insect bite allergy
definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against insect bites.

label: Focal epithelial hyperplasia of oral mucosa
definition: The occurrence of multiple or unique whitish or normal in color small papules or nodules in oral cavity, especially on labial and buccal mucosa, lower lip and tongue, and less often on the upper lip, gingiva and palate.

label: Abnormal circulating heparan sulfate level
definition: An abnormal level of heparan sulfate in the blood.

label: Increased circulating heparan sulfate level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of heparan sulfate in the blood.

label: Decreased circulating heparan sulfate level
definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of heparan sulfate in the blood.

label: Shortened O-fucosylated glycan on properdin
definition: Decreased length of O-fucosylated glycans present on properdin.

label: Increased urinary polyhexose
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of polyhexose in the urine.

label: Increased urinary galactosylated oligosaccharide
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of galactosylated oligosaccharides in urine.

label: Increased urinary high-mannose-type oligosaccharide
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of high-mannose-type oligosaccharides in the urine.

label: Increased urinary multiantennary sialylated oligosaccharide
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of multiantennary sialylated oligosaccharides in the urine.

label: Decreased glycosyltransferase O-Fucosylpeptide 3-Beta-N-Acetylglucosaminyltransferase level
definition: An abnormal decrease in glycosyltransferase O-fucosylpeptide 3-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase enzymatic level.

label: Increased urinary fucosylated oligosaccharide
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of small fucosylated oligosaccharides in the urine.

label: Abnormal complex N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal concentration of complex N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Increased complex N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of complex N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Decreased complex N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of complex N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Increased sialylated N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of sialylated N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Decreased sialylated N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of sialylated N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Abnormal high-mannose N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal concentration of high-mannose N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Increased high-mannose N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of high-mannose N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Decreased high-mannose N-glycan level
definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of high-mannose N-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Abnormal core 1 O-glycan level
definition: An abnormal in the concentration of core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Increased core 1 O-glycan level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Decreased core 1 O-glycan level
definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Decreased O-mannosyl glycans on alpha-dystroglycan
definition: Hypoglycosylation of alpha-dystroglycan with O-mannosyl glycans. Alpha-dystroglycan is a functional target of O-mannosyl glycosylation and functional glycosylation of alpha-DG is essential in its interaction with the extracellular matrix.

label: Increased monosialylated core 1 O-glycan level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of monosialylated core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Decreased monosialylated core 1 O-glycan level
definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of monosialylated core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Increased disialylated core 1 O-glycan level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of disialylated core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

label: Increased globoside Gb4 level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of globoside Gb4.

label: Increased hepatitis A virus antibody level
definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin against hepatitis A virus in the blood.

label: Increased globoside Gb3 level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of glycolipid globoside Gb3.

label: Increased hepatitis B virus antibody level
definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin against hepatitis B virus in the blood.

label: Absence of ganglioside GM3
definition: The absence of ganglioside GM3.

label: Increased hepatitis C virus antibody level
definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin against hepatitis C virus in the blood.

label: Increased Tn-antigen level
definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of Tn antigen on glycoproteins.

label: Abnormal proportion of naive CD4 T cells
definition: Any abnormality in the proportion of naive CD4 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of naive CD8 T cells
definition: Any abnormality in the proportion of naive CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of naive CD4 T cells
Increased proportion of naive CD8 T cells
definition: An abnormally increased proportion of naive CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased proportion of naive CD8 T cells
definition: An abnormally reduced proportion of naive CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased proportion of naive CD4 T cells
definition: An abnormally reduced proportion of naive CD4 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An abnormal proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Abnormal proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An abnormal proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Abnormal proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An abnormal proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Decreased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
definition: Decreased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with memory phenotype is CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Decreased proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
definition: Decresaed proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Decreased proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: A reduced proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Decreased proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: A reduced proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta central memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Decreased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: A reduced proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Increased proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
definition: An abnormally elevated proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
definition: An abnormally elevated proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Increased proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An abnormally elevated proportion of central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Increased proportion of effector memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An abnormally elevated proportion of effector memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Increased proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
definition: An increased proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Bronchiolectasis
definition: Saccular dilatation of the terminal bronchioles.

label: Positive blood lead test
definition: Detection of lead in the blood.

label: Absent sebaceous glands
definition: Absence of the sebaceous gland, the holocrine gland that secretes sebum into the hair follicles, or in hairless areas into ducts.

label: Worse in evening
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is exacerbated in the evening as compared to the day.

label: Abnormal lacrimal bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the lacrimal bone.

label: Abnormal palatine bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the palatine bone.

label: Abnormal ethmoid bone morphology
definition: An abnormality of the ethmoid bone

label: Ectopic cilia of eyelid
definition: An eyelash that emerges from the underside (conjunctiva) of the upper or lower eyelid.

label: Symblepharon
definition: A partial or complete adhesion of the palpebral conjunctiva of the eyelid to the bulbar conjunctiva of the eyeball.

label: Accessory eyelid
definition: The presence of more than the normal number of eyelids.

label: Microblepharia
definition: Abnormal shortness of the vertical dimensions of the eyelids.

label: Defect of palpebral conjunctiva
definition: An abnormality of the palpebral conjunctiva.

label: Incomplete ossification of palatine bone
definition: Failure to complete ossification (maturation and calcification) of the palatine bone.

label: Absent palatine bone ossification
definition: Lack of formation of the palatine bone.

label: Abnormality of musculature of soft palate
definition: An abnormality of one or more of the five muscles of the soft palate.

label: Abnormal morphology of musculature of pharynx
definition: An abnormality of any of the muscles of the pharynx.

label: Abnormality of tensor veli palatini muscle
definition: An abnormality of the tensor veli palatini muscle

label: Abnormality of uvular muscle
definition: An abnormality of the uvular muscle

label: Abnormality of nasal musculature
definition: An abnormality of the muscles of the structure of the nose.

label: Abnormality of muscle of facial expression
definition: An abnormality of any of the muscles of facial expression, which are innervated by the seventh (VII) cranial nerve and control facial expression.

label: Abnormality of levator labii superioris alaeque nasi muscle
definition: An abnormality of the levator labii superioris alaeque nasi muscle.

label: Abnormality of the sphenoid sinus
definition: An abnormality of the sphenoid sinus, one of the mucosa-lined, normally air-filled paranasal sinuses of the bones of the skull. The sphenoid sinus is located within the sphenoid bone.

label: Abnormality of the maxillary sinus
definition: An abnormality of the maxillary sinus, one of the mucosa-lined, normally air-filled paranasal sinuses of the bones of the skull. The maxillary sinus is located within the skeleton of the midface, lateral to the nasal cavity.

label: Abnormality of external jugular vein
definition: An abnormality of an external jugular vein of the neck.

label: Abnormal jugular vein morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a jugular vein.

label: Bilateral facial palsy
definition: Two-sided or bilateral weakness of the muscles of facial expression and eye closure.

label: Hyperplasia of the maxilla
definition: Abnormally increased dimension of the maxilla, especially relative to the mandible, resulting in a malocclusion or malalignment between the upper and lower teeth or in anterior positioning of the nasal base, increased convexity of the face, increased nasolabial angle, or increased width (transverse dimension of the maxilla.

label: Hyperplasia of the premaxilla
definition: An abnormality of the premaxilla (the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla) causing it to appear relatively large in size compared to the other parts of the maxilla or other facial structures.

label: Aqueous humor viral DNA positivity
definition: The presence of viral DNA (e.g., cytomegalovirus, herpes simplex virus, or varicella zoster virus) in the aqueous humor of the eye.

label: Electronic cigarette exposure history
definition: History of use of electronic cigarettes (vaping).

label: Tobacco use history
definition: History of use of tobacco products such as cigarettes.

label: Gottron sign
definition: Erythematous macules or patches over extensor surfaces of elbows, knuckles, knees, and ankles.

label: Hypertension resistant to conventional therapy
definition: Resistant hypertension is defined as above-goal elevated blood pressure in a patient despite the concurrent use of 3 antihypertensive drug classes, commonly including a long-acting calcium channel blocker, a blocker of the renin-angiotensin system (angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor or angiotensin receptor blocker), and a diuretic.

label: Tibiofibular interosseous membrane calcification
definition: Deposition of excess calcium in the interosseous membrane of the leg, which extends between the interosseous crests of the tibia and fibula and separates the anterior and posterior muscles of the lower leg.

label: Supracondylar elbow fracture
definition: A type of elbow fracture that involves the distal humerus just above the elbow.

label: Abnormal alcohol consumption
definition: Alcohol abuse or dependence.

label: Thoracic lordosis
definition: Thoracic lordosis refers to an abnormal curvature of the thoracic spine in which the thoracic spine displays lordosis (inward curve) instead of the normal kyphosis (outward curve).

label: Radiation into left arm
definition: Refers to pain or discomfort that is perceived to travel from the chest into the left arm.

label: Radiation into right arm
definition: Refers to pain or discomfort that is perceived to travel from the chest into the right arm.

label: Bloodstream pathogen-specific antibody positivity
definition: Positive serology for a exposure to an infectious agent (i.e., examining serum for the presence of pathogen-specific antibodies).

label: Anti-SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus type 2 (SARS-CoV-2).

label: Bloodstream virus-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a virus.

label: Anti-West Nile virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the West Nile virus.

label: Anti-microfilaria antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a microfilaria (parasite).

label: Bloodstream parasite-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a parasite.

label: Anti-trypanosoma cruzi antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of trypanosoma cruzi.

label: Anti-chikungunya virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of chikungunya virus.

label: Anti-chlamydia psittaci antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of chlamydia psittaci.

label: Bloodstream antibacterial antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a bacterium.

label: Anti-herpes simplex antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of herpes simplex.

label: Anti-Japanese encephalitis virus-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the Japanese encephalitis virus.

label: Anti-chlamydia trachomatis-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of chlamydia trachomatis.

label: Anti-Epstein-Barr virus-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the Epstein Barr virus (EBV).

label: Anti-babesia-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a parasite of the genus Babesia (parasite).

label: Anti-Zikavirus-specific antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the Zika virus.

label: Positive bloodstream nucleic acid pathogen test
definition: Positive (abnormal) result of a test such as polymerase chain reaction that is targeted against a nucleic acid sequence specific for a pathogen.

label: Positive microfilaria PCR test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of a microfilarial parasite in the blood circulation.

label: Positive JC-virus PCR test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of the JC-virus (JC-Polyomavirus, John Cunningham virus) in the blood circulation.

label: Placenta previa
definition: Implantation of the placenta over or near the internal os of the cervix.

label: Abnormal circulating beta-carotene concentration
definition: Any deviation of the concentration of beta-carotene in the blood circulation from the normal range.

label: Decreased circulating beta-carotene concentration
definition: The concentration of beta-carotene in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Increased circulating beta-carotene concentration
definition: The concentration of beta-carotene in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Mammary blocked duct
definition: Blocked mammary ducts represent an area of localized milk stasis, typically associated with breast engorgement and resulting in a localized tender breast lump or area of blushed color; the breast may feel hot; and there may be a white, painful bleb on the end of the nipple.

label: Bloodstream antifungal antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a fungus.

label: Anti-coccidioidal antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a fungus of the Coccidioides genus.

label: Anti-cryptococcal antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a fungus of the Cryptoccous genus.

label: Anti-mycoplasma antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a mycoplasmal component.

label: Anti-rickettsial antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a rickettsial bacterium. Rickettsiae are gram-negative bacteria with an obligate intracellular life cycle circulating between mammalian hosts and hematophagous arthropod vectors

label: Anti-Bartonella henselae antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Bartonella.

label: Anti-Dengue virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Dengue virus.

label: Anti-arbovirus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of an Arbovirus.

label: Anti-lymphocytic choriomeningitis antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus (LCMV).

label: Anti-varicella-zoster antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Varicella-zoster virus.

label: Anti-rubella antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of rubella virus.

label: Anti-cytomegalovirus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of cytomegalovirus (CMV).

label: Anti-measles antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of measles virus.

label: Anti-schistosoma antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a parasite of the genus Schistosomiasis is a parasitic disease historically known as bilharzia caused by the trematode of the genus Schistosoma. Schistosomiasis is a parasitic disease historically known as bilharzia caused by the trematode of the genus Schistosoma.

label: Anti-Powassan virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of a Powassan virus (POW), which is an arbovirus within the family of Flaviviruses primarily found in the Northeastern United States, Canada, and Russia. It is a zoonotic infection transmitted to humans by several tick species and is the only member of the tick-borne flaviviruses endemic to North America.

label: BCL2 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of BCL2 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-BCL2 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: BCL6 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of BCL6 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-BCL6 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD5 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD5 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD5 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD10 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD10 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD10 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD23 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD23 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD23 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD38 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD38 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD38 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD45 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD45 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD45 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: Cyclin D1 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of cyclin D1 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-cyclin D1 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: FMC7 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of FMC7 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-FMC7 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD19 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD19 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD19 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: CD20 expression
definition: Detection of the presence of CD20 on the cell(s) of interest with the use of anti-CD20 antibodies conjugated to a chromogen (for immunohistochemistry) or fluorophore (for flow cytometry).

label: Skip lesions on temporal artery biopsy
definition: Patchy inflammation of the superficial temporal artery, forming isolated foci of arteritis.

label: Sputum infectious agent
definition: The presence of an infectious agent in the sputum, as characterized by sputum culture or other investigation.

label: Positive respiratory tract infectious agent test
definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in the respiratory tract positive.

label: Positive Mycobacterium avium sputum culture
definition: Growth of mycobacterium avium in a sputum culture.

label: Positive bloodstream infectious agent antigen test
definition: A test result demonstrating the presence of an antigen (marker such as a protein against which an antibody reacts) specific to an infectious agent.

label: Positive bloodstream Cysticercosis antigen test
definition: Demonstration of an antigen specific to Cysticercosis in the bloodstream.

label: Klazomania
definition: Involuntary attacks of compulsive paroxysmal shouting. The shouting behaviors may be extremely loud and not related to the ongoing mental state of the affected individual. Shouting episodes may occur in bouts and last for several hours.

label: Coprolalia
definition: Coprolalia denotes the involuntary utterance of obscenities. Intent is an important classifier in coprolalic behaviors, and unfortunately it remains unclear how to objectively distinguish coprolalia from common swearing.

label: Continuous involuntary vocalizations
definition: Continuous groaning, moaning, grunting, and shrieking.

label: Cervical hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the uterine cervix.

label: Primary peritoneal serous papillary adenocarcinoma
definition: A serous papillary adenocarcinoma that arises from the lining of the peritoneum

label: Positive skin infectious agent test
definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in skin positive.

label: Positive skin fungus test
definition: A test for fungus, e.g., fungal hyphae, in a skin specimen (usually a skin scraping), demonstrates the presence of fungi. Most commonly, a skin scraping is obtained using a small scalpel blade, the specimen is placed on a clean glass slide, a drop of potassium hydroxide (KOH) is added, and the specimen is examined microscopically for fungal structures such as hyphae or yeast.

label: Nasal secretion eosinophilia
definition: Count of eosinophils in nasal secretions (for instance, nasal discharge) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Nasal secretion neutrophilia
definition: Count of neutrophils in nasal secretions (for instance, nasal discharge) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Seminal vesicle agenesis
definition: A developmental defect characterized by congenital absence of the seminal vesicle.

label: Abnormal seminal vesicle morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of the seminal vesicle. The seminal vesicles are a pair of glands that also include the prostate gland and the bulbourethral glands and are located in the pelvis superior to the rectum, inferior to the fundus of the bladder and posterior to the prostate. The seminal vesicles contribute around 70% of the fluid that will eventually become semen.

label: Head impulse test has corrective saccade
definition: In a patient with nystagmus, The examiner briskly rotates the head of the patient while having the patient fixate on a target. A corrective saccade indicates the patient's eye will move in one direction and quickly return back to neutral position.

label: Positive CSF infectious agent test
definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) positive.

label: Positive CSF toxoplasma gondii nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Toxoplasma gondii nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Positive CSF nucleic acid pathogen test
definition: Positive (abnormal) result of a cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) test such as polymerase chain reaction that is targeted against a nucleic acid sequence specific for a pathogen.

label: Elevated circulating plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 activity
definition: The activity or concentration of plasminogen activator inhibitor-1 in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Brain localization
definition: The pattern by which a phenotype is localized to or predominant in a part of the brain.

label: Frontal cortical localization
definition: Localization to or predominance in the frontal cortex of the brain.

label: Posterior fossa localization
definition: Localization to or predominance in the parts of the brain within the posterior fossa.

label: Subcortical localization
definition: Localization to or predominance in the subcortical region of the brain.

label: Parietal cortex localization
definition: Localization to or predominance in the parietal cortex of the brain.

label: Occipital cortex localization
definition: Localization to or predominance in the occipital cortex of the brain.

label: Bartholin cyst
definition: A fluid-filled sac near the vaginal opening. A Bartholin cyst is usually unilateral, asymptomatic blockage of the Bartholin gland, which may lead to a painless swelling.

label: Reduced circulating aspartate aminotransferase concentration
definition: The concentration of aspartate aminotransferase (AST) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine succinic acid level
definition: The concentration of succinic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive CSF varicella zoster virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Varicella zoster virus nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: CSF pathogen-specific antibody positivity
definition: Positive serology in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) for a exposure to an infectious agent (i.e., examining CSF for the presence of pathogen-specific antibodies).

label: CSF varicella zoster antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of varicella zoster virus.

label: Reduced circulating interleukin 6 concentration
definition: The concentration of interleukin-6 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Frontalis muscle overactivity
definition: Increased activity of the frontalis muscle, causing a characteristic staring and astonished facial expression.

label: Nasal dermoid cyst
definition: An ectodermal inclusion cyst containing skin and skin appendages; sebaceous glands, hair follicles, and occasionally sweat glands.

label: Elevated circulating complement C3 concentration
definition: Concentration of the complement component C3 in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating complement component concentration
definition: Concentration of a complement component in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal circulating lipoprotein(a) concentration
definition: The concentration of lipoprotein(a) in the blood circulation is outside the limits of normal.

label: Urethritis
definition: Inflammation of the urethra.

label: Iris flocculi
definition: Multiple cysts along the pupillary margin that appear as spherical or tear-drop-shaped pigmented lesions or wrinkled masses emerging from the pupillary border of the iris.

label: Cornea verticillata
definition: Golden brown or gray deposits with a clockwise, whorl-like distribution in the inferior interpalpebal portion of the cornea.

label: Dysplastic gangliocytoma of the cerebellum
definition: It is a rare, slowly growing tumor of the cerebellum, a gangliocytoma sometimes considered to be a hamartoma, characterized by diffuse hypertrophy of the granular layer of the cerebellum.

label: Moon facies
definition: A rounded, puffy face with fat deposits in the temporal fossa and cheeks, a double chin.

label: Lack of gonadotropin-releasing hormone pulsatility
definition: Secretion of gonadotropin-releasing hormone that does not occur in a pulsatile fashion.

label: Abnormal cardiac test
definition: Abnormal test result of cardiovascular physiology.

label: Abnormal cardiac MRI
definition: Abnormal results of a MRI for the heart.

label: Abnormal cardiac catheterization
definition: Abnormal results from the diagnostic tests resulting from cardiac catheterization.

label: Abnormal cardiac exercise stress test
definition: Abnormal results of exercise on heart function.

label: Abnormal resting energy expenditure from metabolic cart test
definition: Resting energy expenditure (REE) can be measured with indirect calorimetry using a metabolic cart, which is used to measure the oxygen consumption (VO2) and carbon dioxide production (VCO2).

label: Reduced brain gamma-aminobutyric acid level by MRS
definition: An decreased level of gamma-aminobutyric acid in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Shoulder muscle aplasia
definition: Absence of shoulder muscles.

label: Aplasia of the musculature of the pelvis
definition: Absence of the musculature of the pelvis.

label: Hypoplasia of the musculature of the pelvis
definition: Underdevelopment of the musculature of the pelvis.

label: Aplastic colon
definition: Congenital absence of the colon

label: Cotton wool plaques
definition: Deposition of large, diffuse cotton wool amyloid plaques (CWPs) lacking a dense core and associated neuritic changes.

label: Sclerosis of the carpal bones
definition: An elevation in bone density in one or more carpal bones of the hand.

label: Nasolacrimal sac obstruction
definition: Blockage of the nasolacrimal sac.

label: Abnormal lacrimal sac morphology
definition: An abnormality of a lacrimal sac.

label: Nasolacrimal sac granuloma
definition: A mass of granulation tissue in response to chronic dacryocystitis as polypoid formations or they follow accidental injury, from probing and as a reaction to retained foreign bodies in the sac.

label: Nasolacrimal sac papilloma
definition: Benign tumor of the nasolacrimal sac.

label: Nasolacrimal sac epithelial papillary carcinoma
definition: The malignant epithelial neoplasm with papillary growths in the nasolacrimal sac.

label: Conjunctival cicatrization
definition: An abnormality of the conjuctiva and ocular surface caused by conjunctival inflammation and associated with scarring.

label: Dermolipoma of the conjunctiva
definition: A benign tumor composed of adipose tissue and dense connective tissue usually located near the temporal fornix.

label: Myopic astigmatism
definition: A condition where one or both of the two principal meridians focus in the front of the retina when the eye is at rest.

label: Latent hypermetropia
definition: A term to describe when farsightedness is masked when the accommodative muscles are used to increase the focusing power of the eye.

label: Upper eyelid retraction
definition: An elevation of the eyelid above the normal level in the primary position.

label: Collier's sign
definition: A unilateral or bilateral eyelid retraction due to midbrain lesions.

label: Seborrhoeic blepharitis
definition: Inflammation of the eyelid due to overactivity of the sebaceous gland.

label: Nasolacrimal sac lymphoma
definition: A type of lymphoma that involves the nasolacrimal sac.

label: Delayed canalization of nasolacrimal duct
definition: A very common condition in which the extreme end of the nasolacrimal duct underneath the inferior turbinate fails to complete its canalization in the newborn period.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity
definition: An avascular or abnormally vascularized retina that occurs in premature infants and can lead to blindness.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 1
definition: The retinal vessels stop and then a linear flat white line is present that usually runs the circumference of the vascular retina.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 2
definition: The accumulating neovascularization thickens and manifests as a linear bump. The neovascularization remains along the surface of the retina and does not extend off the retina into the cortical vitreous.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 3
definition: The neovascularization accumulates at the edge of the vascularized retina and extends into the vitreous (also called extra retinal fibrosis proliferation). In cases of Zone 2 and Zone 3, this may be sausage shaped. In more posterior Zone 1 disease, the stage 3 can appear as a direct extension of the normal retinal vessels but extending tangentially over the avascular retina.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 4
definition: Scar tissue that forms a continuous sheet coming up from the edge of the vascularized retina. This scar tissue can grow toward the vitreous base/posterior lens capsule resulting in traction, distortion, and even detachment.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 4a
definition: A detachment that involves the peripheral retina that does not extend into the macula.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 4b
definition: A detachment that involves the peripheral retina that involves the macula itself. The detachment usually starts in the temporal periphery although can also involve the nasal retina as well.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 5
definition: Funnel detachment from the retina with generally traction in all four quadrants.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 5a
definition: An open funnel detachment of the retina with generally traction in all four quadrants.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity stage 5b
definition: A closed funnel detachment of the retina with generally traction in all four quadrants.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity zone I
definition: Retinopathy which extends from the center of the optic disc to twice the distance from the center of the optic disc to the center of the macula.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity zone II
definition: Retinopathy which extends centrifugally from the edge of zone I to the nasal ora serrata.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity zone III
definition: Retinopathy which is a residual crescent of retina anterior to zone II.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity plus
definition: Venous dilatation and arteriolar tortuosity of the posterior retinal vessels and may later increase in severity to include iris vascular engorgement, poor pupillary dilatation (rigid pupil), and vitreous haze. This definition has been further refined in the later clinical trials in which the diagnosis of plus disease could be made if sufficient vascular dilatation and tortuosity are present in at least 2 quadrants of the eye.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity pre-plus
definition: As vascular abnormalities of the posterior pole that are insufficient for the diagnosis of plus disease but that demonstrate more arterial tortuosity and more venous dilatation than normal.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity threshold
definition: A retinopathy with a 50% likelihood of progressing to retinal detachment. Threshold disease is considered to be present when stage 3 retinopathy of prematurity (ROP) is present in either zone I or zone II, with at least 5 continuous or 8 total clock hours of disease, and the presence of plus disease.

label: Retinopathy of prematurity prethreshold
definition: High risk patients who were in Zone 1 (no Plus or stage 3) or Zone 2 with Plus or stage 3 but not both.

label: Latent myopia
definition: The difference between total and manifest myopia.

label: Paralytic ectropion
definition: A type of ectropion associated with orbicularis muscle weakness caused by cranial nerve VII palsy.

label: Conjunctival dermolipoma
definition: A conjuctival lesion composed of adipose tissue and dense connective tissue. Such choristomas of dermal elements are normally found at the outer canthus, and have a gelatinous appearance. Classically, there is an indistinct posterior border (with the lesion frequently extending into the orbit) and a well-demarcated anterior border several millimeters posterior to the limbus.

label: Absolute eccentric fixation
definition: Eccentric fixation in which the angle of eccentricity equals the objective angle of deviation.

label: Abnormal ocular alignment
definition: Any deviation from the normal ocular alignment.

label: Dissociated vertical deviation
definition: An incomitant tendency for an occluded eye to elevate and extort which resolves on uncovering.

label: Dissociated horizontal deviation
definition: A change in horizontal ocular alignment, unrelated to accommodation, that is brought about solely by a change in the balance of visual input from the two eyes.

label: Alternating hypertropia
definition: A type of vertical tropia in which, when one eye is fixing, the other eye is deviated upwards.

label: Alternating hyperphoria
