definition: A type of vertical phoria in which, in dissociation, the occluded eye deviates upwards.

label: Alternating hypotropia
definition: A type of vertical tropia in which, when one eye is fixing, the other eye is deviated downwards.

label: Alternating hypophoria
definition: A type of vertical phoria in which, in dissociation, the occluded eye deviates downwards.

label: Pseudophakia
definition: The term pseudophakia refers to having an artificial lens implanted after the natural eye lens has been removed. During cataract surgery the natural cloudy lens is replaced by an pseudophakia intraocular lens (IOL).

label: Optic nerve gray crescent
definition: Having a characteristic appearance of a slate gray area of pigmentation within the disk margins that commonly appears along the inferotemporal or temporal neuroretinal rim areas.

label: Peripapillary atrophy
definition: Thinning in the layers of the retina and retinal pigment epithelium around the optic nerve.

label: Foveal depigmentation
definition: Loss of pigment in the fovea centralis.

label: Optic nerve sheath meningioma
definition: A benign tumor of meningothelial cells of the meninges that usually occurs in middle age. It is typically unilateral and there is an association with neurofibromatosis type 2.

label: Periocular capillary hemangioma
definition: A capillary hemangioma surrounding the eyeball but within the orbit.

label: Lymphangioma of the orbit
definition: A hamartoma of lymph vessels that usually presents in childhood. It tends to increase in size with head-down posture and with the Valsalva maneuver. Superficial lesions are visible as transilluminable cystic spaces of the lid or conjunctiva that may also contain blood. Deep lesions may cause gradual proptosis or present acutely with orbital pain and reduced vision due to hemorrhage.

label: Orbital rhabdomyosarcoma
definition: A mesenchymal tumor that is considered to be the commonest primary orbital malignancy in children. Histologically, it may be differentiated into embryonal, alveolar, and pleomorphic types. It is usually intraconal or within the superior orbit.

label: Latex allergy
definition: Latex allergy is an IgE-mediated immediate hypersensitivity response to natural rubber latex (NRL) protein with a variety of clinical signs ranging from contact urticaria, angioedema, asthma, and anaphylaxis.

label: Food-induced anaphylaxis
definition: Food-induced anaphylaxis is a severe, potentially fatal, systemic allergic reaction that occurs suddenly after contact with an allergy-causing food.

label: Venom-induced anaphylaxis
definition: A form of anaphylaxis that is triggered by exposure to venom.

label: Decreased diastolic blood pressure
definition: Abnormal decrease in diastolic blood pressure.

label: Decreased systolic blood pressure
definition: Abnormal decrease in systolic blood pressure.

label: Isolated systolic hypertension
definition: Elevated systolic blood pressure without an elevated blood pressure.

label: Isolated diastolic hypotension
definition: A decrease in diastolic blood pressure (<60 mmHg) without a decrease in systolic blood pressure (> or = to 100 mmHg).

label: Positive urine cocaine test
definition: Detection of cocaine or its major metabolite, benzoylecgonine, in urine.

label: Positive urine barbiturate test
definition: Detection of barbiturate metabolites such as Phenobarbital in urine.

label: Positive urine cannabinoid test
definition: Detection of delta-9-tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) or other cannabinoid metabolites in urine.

label: Positive urine benzodiazepines test
definition: Detection of benzodiazepine metabolites, primarily nordiazepam, oxazepam, and temazepam, in urine.

label: Positive urine amphetamine test
definition: Detection of amphetamine or its metabolites in urine.

label: Positive urine opioid test
definition: Detection of opioids or opioid metabolites in urine.

label: Abnormal stool urobilinogen concentration
definition: Abnormal concentration of urobilinogen present in the stool.

label: Increased stool urobilinogen concentration
definition: An increased amount of urobilinogen present in the stool.

label: Positive blood barbiturate test
definition: Detection of barbiturate metabolites such as Phenobarbital in blood.

label: Hypovalinemia
definition: A decreased amount of valine in the blood.

label: Hypotyrosinemia
definition: An decreased concentration of tyrosine in the blood.

label: Hypertryptophanemia
definition: An increased amount of tryptophan in the blood.

label: Hypotryptophanemia
definition: A decreased amount of tryptophan in the blood.

label: Hypothreoninemia
definition: A decreased amount of threonine in the blood.

label: Hyperserinemia
definition: An increased amount of serine in the blood.

label: Hypoprolinemia
definition: A decreased amount of proline in the blood.

label: Decreased circulating hydroxyproline concentration
definition: A decreased amount of hydroxyproline in the blood.

label: Hypophenylalaninemia
definition: A decreased amount of phenylalanine in the blood.

label: Hypolysinemia
definition: A decreased amount of lysine in the blood.

label: Hypoleucinemia
definition: Decreased amount of leucine in the blood.

label: Hypoisoleucinemia
definition: A decreased amount of isoleucine in the blood.

label: Hypohistidinemia
definition: A decreased amount of histidine in the blood.

label: Hypoglutaminemia
definition: Decreased amount of glutamine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating glutamate concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of glutamate in the blood circulation.

label: Hyperglutamatemia
definition: Concentration of glutamate in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Hypoglutamatemia
definition: A decreased amount of glutamate in the blood.

label: Hypercystinemia
definition: An increased amount of cystine in the blood.

label: Hypocystinemia
definition: A decreased amount of cystine in the blood.

label: Hyperargininemia
definition: An increased amount of arginine levels in the blood.

label: Hypoalaninemia
definition: A decreased amount of alanine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating asparagine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of asparagine in the blood circulation.

label: Hyperasparaginemia
definition: An increased amount of asparagine in the blood.

label: Hypoasparaginemia
definition: A decreased amount of asparagine in the blood.

label: Increased circulating aspartic acid concentration
definition: An increased concentration of aspartic acid in the blood circulation.

label: Abnormal circulating carnosine concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of carnosine in the blood circulation.

label: Increased circulating carnosine concentration
definition: Concentration of carnosine in the blood circulation above normal limits.

label: Decreased circulating carnosine concentration
definition: A decreased amount of carnosine in blood.

label: Hypoornithinemia
definition: An abnormal decrease in ornithine in the blood.

label: Abnormal circulating gastrin concentration
definition: An abnormal concentration of gastrin in the blood.

label: Hypergastrinemia
definition: An elevated amount of gastrin in the blood.

label: Abnormal concentration of acylcarnitine in the urine
definition: An abnormal amount of acylcarnitine in the urine.

label: Reflex asystolic syncope
definition: A loss of consciousness followed by stiffening and brief clonic movements affecting some or all limbs, often misinterpreted as an epileptic seizure.

label: Abnormal circulating amino sulfonic acid concentration
Hypertaurinemia

definition: Abnormal concentration of sebacic acid in the urine.

label: Triggered by head trauma
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a head trauma.

label: Triggered by anesthetics
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to anesthetics.

label: Atrichia
definition: The most dramatic and severe form of hair loss characterized by an absence of hair follicles.

label: Increased helper T cell proportion
definition: Increased proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
definition: An increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

label: Decreased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
definition: An decreased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

label: Abnormal proportion of gamma-delta T cells
definition: Abnormal proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
definition: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
definition: Decreased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
definition: Abnormal proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
definition: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Decreased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
definition: Decreased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Proximal scleroderma
definition: Symmetrical thickening, tightening and induration of the skin of the fingers and the skin proximal to the metacarpophalangeal or metatarsophalangeal joints. These changes can involve the entire limb, face, neck and trunk.

label: Verruca plana
definition: Slightly raised wart 2-5 mm in diameter often associated with viral infections, commonly persistent in immunodeficient individuals.

label: Bilateral basilar pulmonary fibrosis
definition: It is a bilateral reticular pattern of linear or lineonodular densities that are most pronounced in basilar portions of the lungs on standard chest x-ray. It is the third minor criterion for scleroderma diagnosis.

label: Abnormal inner ear epithelium morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of an inner ear epithelium.

label: Abnormality of medial pterygoid muscle
definition: An abnormality of a medial pterygoid muscle.

label: Abnormality of mentalis muscle
definition: An abnormality of a mentalis muscle.

label: Abnormality of mylohyoid muscle
definition: An abnormality of a mylohyoid muscle.

label: Abnormality of nasalis muscle
definition: An abnormality of a nasalis muscle.

label: Abnormality of orbicularis oris muscle
definition: An abnormality of an orbicularis oris muscle.

label: Abnormality of palatoglossus muscle
definition: An abnormality of a palatoglossus muscle.

label: Abnormality of palatopharyngeus muscle
definition: An abnormality of a palatopharyngeus muscle.

label: Abnormal platysma muscle morphology
definition: An abnormality of the platysma muscle.

label: Abnormality of procerus muscle
definition: An abnormality of a procerus.

label: Abnormality of risorius muscle
definition: An abnormality of a risorius muscle.

label: Abnormality of styloglossus muscle
definition: An abnormality of the styloglossus muscle.

label: Abnormality of temporalis muscle
definition: An abnormality of a temporalis muscle.

label: Abnormality of zygomaticus major muscle
definition: An abnormality of a zygomaticus major muscle.

label: Abnormality of zygomaticus minor muscle
definition: An abnormality of a zygomaticus minor muscle.

label: Abnormal buccal fat pad morphology
definition: An abnormality of a buccal fat pad.

label: Abnormality of angular artery
definition: An abnormality of the angular artery, the terminal branch of the facial artery.

label: Abnormal facial artery morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a facial artery, one of the branches of the external carotid artery.

label: Abnormality of ciliary ganglion
definition: An abnormality of a ciliary ganglion.

label: Abnormality of buccinator muscle
definition: An abnormality of a buccinator muscle.

label: Abnormality of depressor anguli oris muscle
definition: An abnormality of a depressor anguli oris muscle.

label: Abnormality of depressor labii inferioris
definition: An abnormality of a depressor labii inferioris.

label: Abnormality of anterior ethmoidal artery
definition: An abnormality of an anterior ethmoidal artery.

label: Abnormality of cervical plexus
definition: Abnormality of the plexus of the ventral rami of the first four cervical spinal nerves which are located from C1 to C4 cervical segment in the neck.

label: Abnormal neck blood vessel morphology
definition: An abnormality of a blood vessel of the neck, including branches of the arterial and venous systems of the neck.

label: Abnormal cricoid cartilage morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a cricoid cartilage, that is, of the ring-shaped cartilage of the larynx.

label: Abnormality of dorsal nasal artery
definition: An abnormality of a dorsal nasal artery.

label: Abnormality of external carotid artery
definition: An abnormality of an external carotid artery.

label: Abnormal facial vein morphology
definition: An abnormality of a facial vein.

label: Abnormality of frontal process of maxilla
definition: An abnormality of a frontal process of the maxilla bone.

label: Abnormality of genioglossus muscle
definition: An abnormality of a genioglossus muscle.

label: Abnormal geniohyoid muscle morphology
definition: An abnormality of a geniohyoid muscle.

label: Abnormal glossopharyngeal nerve morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the glossopharyngeal nerve, the ninth paired cranial nerve (CN IX).

label: Abnormal greater palatine artery morphology
definition: An abnormality of a greater palatine artery.

label: Abnormal hyoglossus muscle morphology
definition: An abnormality of a hyoglossus muscle.

label: Abnormal hyoid bone morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of the hyoid bone (hyoid), a small U-shaped (horseshoe-shaped) solitary bone, situated in the midline of the neck anteriorly at the base of the mandible and posteriorly at the fourth cervical vertebra.

label: Abnormal hypopharynx morphology
definition: A structural anomaly of the hypopharyx, which is the most inferior portion of the pharynx. The hypopharynx continues from the oropharynx at the pharyngoepiglottic fold superiorly and extends inferiorly to the level of the inferior aspect of the cricoid cartilage, which marks the beginning of the cervical esophagus.

label: Abnormal inferior alveolar artery morphology
definition: An abnormality of an inferior alveolar artery.

label: Abnormality of inferior alveolar nerve
definition: An abnormality of an inferior alveolar nerve.

label: Abnormality of artery of lower lip
definition: An abnormality of an artery of lower lip.

label: Abnormality of inferior oblique extraocular muscle
definition: An abnormality of an inferior oblique extraocular muscle.

label: Abnormality of inferior rectus extraocular muscle
definition: An abnormality of an inferior rectus extraocular muscle.

label: Abnormal inferior thyroid vein morphology
definition: An abnormality of an inferior thyroid vein.

label: Abnormal infraorbital artery morphology
definition: An abnormality of an infraorbital artery.

label: Abnormality of infra-orbital nerve
definition: A structural abnormality of an infra-orbital nerve. The infraorbital nerve arises from the maxillary branch of the trigeminal nerve and normally traverses the orbital floor in the infraorbital canal.

label: Abnormality of internal jugular vein
definition: An abnormality of an internal jugular vein.

label: Abnormality of intrinsic muscle of tongue
definition: An abnormality of an intrinsic muscle of tongue.

label: Abnormal lacrimal artery morphology
definition: An abnormality of a lacrimal artery.

label: Abnormal lateral cricoarytenoid muscle morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a lateral crico-arytenoid muscle, which extends from the lateral cricoid cartilage to the muscular process of the arytenoid cartilage, and can adduct the vocal cords, which closes the rima glottidis and thereby protects the airway.

label: Abnormality of lateral pterygoid muscle
definition: An abnormality of a lateral pterygoid muscle.

label: Abnormality of lateral rectus extra-ocular muscle
definition: An abnormality of a lateral rectus extra-ocular muscle.

label: Abnormality of levator anguli oris
definition: An abnormality of a levator anguli oris.

label: Abnormality of levator labii superioris
definition: An abnormality of a levator labii superioris.

label: Abnormality of levator veli palatini muscle
definition: An abnormality of a levator veli palatini.

label: Abnormal lingual artery morphology
definition: Any structural abnormality of a lingual artery.

label: Abnormality of lingual tonsil
definition: An abnormality of a lingual tonsil.

label: Abnormal mandible coronoid process morphology
definition: An abnormality of a mandible coronoid process.

label: Abnormal mandibular symphysis morphology
definition: A structural abnormality of a mandibular symphysis.

label: Abnormal cardiac magnetic resonance imaging finding
definition: Abnormal finding by magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), which uses non-ionizing radiation via a strong magnetic field and radio frequency energy to generate three dimensional images. This term comprises findings that are specific to MRI. Findings such as ventricular spetum defect that can be detected by multiple modalities should be coded separately.

label: Elevated myocardial native T2
definition: Increased duration of myocardial T2 time without gadolinium contrast. Elevated T2, which can detect myocardial edema.

label: Myocardial late gadolinium enhancement
definition: Areas of high signal intensity in magnetic resonance imaging of the heart appearing 10 to 15 minutes after injection of the intercellular contrast agent gadolinium.

label: Pericardial late gadolinium enhancement
definition: Areas of high signal intensity in magnetic resonance imaging of the pericardium appearing around 10 minutes after injection of the intercellular contrast agent gadolinium.

label: Elevated myocardial native T1
definition: Increased duration of myocardial T1 time without gadolinium contrast. T1 mapping consists of quantifying the T1 relaxation time of a tissue by using analytical expressions of image-based signal intensities. A fundamental principle of MR imaging is that the signal intensity of pixels is based on the relaxation of hydrogen nuclei protons in a static magnetic field. The T1 relaxation times between two tissues vary substantially. Edema, fat infiltration, and fibrosis also cause differences in T1 relaxivity.

label: Bronchoconstriction
definition: Tightening of smooth muscle surrounding the bronchi and bronchioles with consequent wheezing and shortness of breath.

label: Formation of multiple pronuclei during fertilization
definition: Pronuclei formation is a critical process during fertilization. Normally, there are two pronuclei (2PN), including the paternal pronucleus and the maternal pronucleus, in the zygote after fertilization. It is generally accepted that multiple pronuclei (MPN) formation is due to the abnormal extrusion of the second polar body or to abnormal fertilization with multiple sperm. The MPN therefore can cause infertility and recurrent failure of IVF/ICSI.

label: Kinesiophobia
definition: An excessive, irrational, and debilitating fear of carrying out a physical movement due to a feeling of vulnerability to painful injury or reinjury.

label: Impaired renal tubular reabsorption of bicarbonate
definition: Decreased renal tubular reabsorption of bicarbonate.

label: History of congenital HPV infection
definition: A congenital human papillomavirus (HPV) infection of the newborn. Congential HPV infection can manifest as condyloma cuminata in the newborn.

label: Anti-desmoglein-1 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoglein-1, a dermal cell adhesion molecule.

label: Anti-desmoglein-3 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoglein-3, a dermal cell adhesion molecule.

label: Anti-envoplakin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against envoplakin, a cytoskeletal linker protein that links intermediate filaments to cellular junctions.

label: Anti-periplakin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against periplakin.

label: Anti-desmoplakin I antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoplakin-1.

label: Anti-desmoplakin II antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoplakin-II.

label: Anti-BP230 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against BP230.

label: Anti-BP180 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against BP180.

label: Anti-laminin 332 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin-332.

label: Anti-laminin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a laminin. Laminins are major components of the basement membrane.

label: Anti-laminin 6 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin-6.

label: Anti-laminin gamma1 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin gamma-1.

label: Anti-integrin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against an integrin. Integrins are a family of cell adhesion molecules with 24 known integrin heterodimers. Integrins transduce mechanical and biochemical signals from fibrotic extracellular matrix into the cell, activate latent TGFbeta, and subsequently modulate fibroblast adhesion, migration, and growth.

label: Anti-transglutaminase 6 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against transglutaminase 6.

label: Anti-LAD-1 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against LAD-1, which is the soluble 120 kDa ectodomain of BP180.

label: Anti-LABD97 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against LABD97, which is structurally identical to a portion of the extracellular domain of BPAg2. BPAg2, a 180 kDa bullous pemphigoid antigen, is a transmembrane protein important for basement membrane cohesion.

label: Antigliadin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against gliadin.

label: Anti-reticulin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against reticulin.

label: Anti-type VII collagen antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against collagen type VII.

label: False perception of self-motion
definition: A perception that one's body is moving or swaying despite lack of motion of the body.

label: Non-spinning vertigo
definition: A perception of unsteadiness of dizziness that is not characterized bythe spinning sensation of classic vertigo, but rather by an oscillatory perception (rocking, bobbing, or swaying despite the fact that the subject is not moving).

label: Infection-associated lymphopenia
definition: Decreased lymphocyte count during infections.

label: Primary obstructive megaureter
definition: Megaurater associated with obstruction or an adynamic ureteral segment in the ureterovesical junction.

label: Encysted hydrocele of the cord
definition: A type of hydrocele testis in which both the proximal and distal portions of processus vaginalis get obliterated while the central portion remains patent and fluid accumulates within it.

label: Congenital hydrocele
definition: Congenital hydrocele occurs when processus vaginalis is patent and communicates with the peritoneal cavity. This communication allows the movement of peritoneal fluid but is too small to allow the intra-abdominal contents to herniate through.

label: Infantile hydrocele
definition: Infantile Hydrocele is a type pf hydrocele in which the processus vaginalis gets obliterated at the level of the deep inguinal ring. However, the portion distal to it remains patent and allows fluid accumulation.

label: Reduced proportion of mucosal-associated invariant T cells
definition: A decreased proportion of circulating mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT) cells relative to total T cell count.

label: Puerpural onset
definition: Onset of a phenotypic abnormality or a disease during childbirth or in the period immediately following.

label: AA amyloidosis
definition: Extracellular tissue deposition of fibrils that are composed of fragments of and/or intact serum amyloid A protein, a hepatic acute phase reactant.

label: Fracture type
definition: Category of fracture. Terms from this subontology can be used together with terms in the subontology that descends from Bone fracture (HP:0020110).

label: Greenstick fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the broken bone is not completely separated.

label: Transverse fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the break is in a straight line across the bone.

label: Spiral fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the break spirals around the bone.

label: Oblique fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which there is a diagonal break across the bone.

label: Compression fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the bone is crushed, causing the broken bone to be wider or flatter in appearance.

label: Comminuted fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the break is in three or more pieces and fragments are present at the fracture site.

label: Segmental fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the same bone is fractured in two places, so there is a floating segment of bone.

label: Open fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which there is an open wound or break in the skin near the site of the broken bone.

label: Closed fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the broken bone that does not penetrate the skin.

label: Displaced fracture
definition: A type of fracture in which the ends of the fractured bone are no longer aligned.

label: Intestinal inflammation
definition: A reaction characterizeds by capillary dilatation, leukocytic infiltration, redness, heat, pain, swelling localized to the in the intestinal tract.

label: Abnormal apoptosis
definition: Any abnormality of programmed cell death (apoptosis), which is defined as the orchestrated collapse of a cell characterized by membrane blebbing, cell shrinkage, condensation of chromatin, and fragmentation of DNA followed by rapid engulfment of the corpse by neighboring cells. Apoptosis is distinguished from death by necrosis by the absence of an associated inflammatory response.

label: Decreased FasL-mediated apoptosis
definition: A reduced amount of programmed cell death upon stimulation of the FAS receptor, which normally induces caspase-8 dependent apoptosis.

label: Glomerular proteinuria
definition: A type of proteinuria characterized by increased permeability of the glomerular capillary wall to macromolecules (particularly albumin), whereby protein excretion can reach 20 g/24 h and consists mainly of albumin.

label: Pancreatic alpha-cell hyperplasia
definition: A diffuse and specific increase in the number of alpha-cells.

label: 3-4 metacarpal synostosis
definition: A congenital hand malformation characterized by the coalescence of the coalescence of third and fourth metacarpals (i.e., those corresponding to the middle and ring fingers).

label: Iliac artery aneurysm
definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the iliac artery.

label: Abnormal interest
definition: Any deviation from normal intensity or subject of a person's interests, which can be defined as a state of giving selective attention to something.

label: Persistent preoccupation with parts of objects
definition: A type of abnormal interest characterized by a persistent and intense focus on parts of a toy/object. For example, affected individuals may spin the wheels on a toy car rather than drive the toy car.

label: Nonfunctional or atypical use of objects in play
definition: Use of objects in atypical, unimaginitive ways other than for which they are intended (banging, throwing, shaking, sorting, lining up, spinning).

label: Fixated interests
definition: Highly restricted, fixated interests that are abnormal in intensity or focus (e.g., strong attachment to or preoccupation with unusual objects, excessively circumscribed or perseverative interests).

label: Pronoun reversal
definition: Atypical language features characterized by first vs. second or third person pronoun errors such as using 'you' or 'he/she' in place of 'I'.

label: Reduced frequency of facial expressions
definition: The number of times facial expressions are produced in a given period is lower than expected given the social and cultural context.

label: Abnormal communicative facial expressions
definition: Abnormal expressions (movements or position of muscles of the face that convey the emotional state of an individual to observers during social interactions) comprising abnormalities of quantity, range, context-appropriateness, and quality.

label: Use of another person's body to communicate
definition: Moving another person's hand, body part, or body to communicate a desire, e.g. pushing or pulling someone toward a desired object or placing someone's hand on something.

label: Fixated interest with abnormal focus
definition: A fixated interest in a specific topic that is atypical for the social context of the individual, such as topics of a non-social nature like fossils or vacuum cleaners.

label: Fixated interest with abnormal intensity
definition: An abnormally intense interest in a topic or object that is not atypical for the social context of the affected person.

label: Sensory behavioral abnormality
definition: Abnormal sensory behavior, including avoiding or seeking sensory input or difficulty modulating sensory stimuli.

label: Reduced production of gestures
definition: Diminished use of typical non-verbal conversational gestures such as shaking the head to indicate no or nodding the head to indicate yes.

label: Reduced cooperative play
definition: Impairment in a child's ability to be able to play in a way that involves peer collaboration. Collaborative play involves things such as verbal and non-verbal communication (e.g., self-initiated interactions), turn-taking, sharing, reciprocity, and collaborative problem-solving. It is often contrasted to parallel play, which involves a form of social play in which two children do similar activities near each other and often mimic each other. Typically developing children develop collaborative play between the ages of 4 and 5.

label: Reduced social reciprocity with peers
definition: Reduced back and forth interactions with others compared to what would be expected for the developmental level.

label: Lack of interest in peers
definition: Lack of interest in peers of comparable age and social groups is evident when an individual, such as a child, shows more interest in socializing with adults rather than children their own age.

label: Reduced sharing of interests
definition: An absence or abnormally low frequency of engaging with others to share personal interests or topics. Interest sharing includes offers of information about oneself as a form of social interaction.

label: Infrequent social initiations
definition: Social initiation refers to the ability to begin interactions with other people. This term refers to a reduction in the frequency with which an individual attempts to begin interactions. The term should only be used for individuals who are assessed to have sufficient intellectual and language skills to interact with others.

label: Reduced object sharing
definition: An absence or reduction in object sharing. Object sharing is an early emerging social skill in which a child will share objects such as toys, balls, or books with parents or peers during object play.

label: Facial expressions that do not match the context
definition: Production of facial expressions that are misaligned with the social context.

label: Abnormal quality of facial expression
definition: Spontaneous production of communicative facial expressions that have poor quality or are exaggerated or muted.

label: Poor conversational reciprocity
definition: Reduced use of reciprocal (back and forth) conversation, as compared to what would be expected for language level.

label: Ectopic tooth eruption
definition: A condition in which the permanent teeth, because of deficiency of growth in the jaw or segment of jaw, assume a path of eruption that intercepts a primary tooth, causes its premature loss and produces a consequent malposition of the permanent tooth.

label: Corpus cavernosum hypoplasia
definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by undergrowth of the corpus cavernosum.

label: Elevated circulating thymine concentration
definition: Concentration of the nucleobase thymine in the blood circulation above the normal range.

label: Positive lactose hydrogen breath test
definition: Elevated hydrogen gas level in exhaled breath following oral administration of lactose. In individuals with lactose intolerance, undigested lactose in the colon will be metabolized by colonic bacteria, releasing hydrogen gas.

label: Positive hydrogen breath test
definition: Abnormally elevated quantiy of hydrogen measured by a hydrogen breath test (HBT). HBTs administer substrates such as glucose, lactulose, lactose and fructose and subsequently measure hydrogen exhaled in the breath using a gas chromatograph.

label: Triggered by allopurinol
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to allopurinol.

label: Ameliorated by oral zinc supplementation
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by oral zinc supplementation.

label: Curved dental root
definition: A root of a tooth that is more rounded than normal.

label: Abnormal four chamber view of the fetal heart
definition: The four-chamber (4Ch) view of the fetal heart is the most widely used screening examination for the detection of structural cardiac abnormalities during routine fetal ultrasonography. In the healthy normal fetus, the apical 4Ch view demonstrates four well-developed chambers, a concordant atrioventricular (AV) connection, unobstructed AV valves (mitral and tricuspid valves), the foramen ovale flap opening into left atrium (LA), and an intact interventricular septum. Additionally, the pulmonary venous opening can be visualized at the LA wall. Any structural deviations from normal anatomy may lead to congenital heart disease that can be determined by the 4Ch view of the fetal heart's ultrasound imaging.

label: Spleen hamartoma
definition: A hamartomatous lesion (benign focal lesions composed of disorganized tissue elements) localized in the spleen.

label: Positive lupus band test
definition: Deposits of immunoglobulins and complement components along the dermoepidermal junction.

label: Bone marrow erythroid vacuolization
definition: Formation of vacuoles (a space within a cell that is empty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in the cytoplasm of erythroid precursors in the bone marrow.

label: Triggered by electromagnetic field
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to an electromagnetic field.

label: Asbestos exposure
definition: History of exposure to asbestos, a fibrous mineral with physical and chemical properties that make it resistant to heat and degradation.

label: Aminoglycoside exposure
definition: History of having taken aminoglycoside antibiotics.

label: Statin exposure
definition: History of having taken statins, also known as HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors.

label: Potassium-sparing diuretic exposure
definition: History of having taken a potassium-sparing diuretic exposure such as amiloride, eplerenone, spironolactone, and triamterene.

label: Carbamazepine exposure
definition: History of having taken carbamazepine.

label: Valproate exposure
definition: History of having taken valproate (valproic acid).

label: Hydralazine exposure
definition: History of having taken hydralazine.

label: Calcium channel blocker exposure
definition: History of having taken a calcium channel blocker such as amlodipine, nicardipine, nifedipine, verapamil, or diltiazem.

label: Triggered by poison ivy, poson oak, or sumac
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure (cutaneous contact) to poison ivy, poison oak, and poison sumac. These three plants each contain urushiol. Contact with these plants is the most common causes of clinically diagnosed allergic contact dermatitis.

label: History of exclusive breast feeding
definition: A past medical history of having been fed exclusively by breast feeding.

label: Nutrition history
definition: A part of the past medical history consisting of information about the typical food intake of an individual.

label: High dietary oxalate intake
definition: A history of ingestion of a relatively high amount of foods containing high levels of oxalate, such as green-leaf vegetables, tea, nuts, chocolate and rhubarb.

label: Recent honey ingestion
definition: A history of ingestion of honey in recent weeks.

label: Raw egg-white ingestion
definition: A history of eating raw egg whites.

label: Exacerbated by sodium channel blocking agent exposure
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of sodium channel blocking agents such as phenytoin, carbamazepine, oxcarbazepine, lamotrigine, topiramate, and zonisamide.

label: Addictive nitrous oxide use
definition: Addiction to inhaled nitrous oxide gas (N2O) is a growing concern.

label: Recent blood transfusion
definition: A past medical history of a recent blood transfusion.

label: Ameliorated by colchicine
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of colchizine.

label: Ameliorated by vitamin D
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of vitamin D.

label: Exacerbated by phenytoin exposure
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of phenytoin.

label: Triggered by angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to anngiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor such as benazepril, captopril, enalapril, fosinopril, and lisinopril.

label: Prostaglandin E1 exposure
definition: History of having been treateed with prostaglandin E1.

label: 5-fluorouracil exposure
definition: History of having been treated with 5-fluorouracil.

label: 6-mercaptopurine exposure
definition: History of having been treateed with 6-mercaptopurine.

label: Isoniazid exposure
definition: History of having been treateed with isoniazid.

label: Absent cavum septum pellucidum
definition: The cavum septum pellucidum (CSP) is an important fetal midline forebrain landmark that is normally visible by prenatal sonography. This term refers to the lack of visibility of the CSP on prenatal sonography. The CSP normally can be visualized between 18 and 37 weeks of gestation. Lack of visualization of the CSP in this time period generally requires follow up and may indicate the presence of underlying malformations such as malformations of the corpus callosum. The lack of CSP before 18 weeks or after 37 weeks of gestation (or postnatally) is considered a normal finding.

label: Fetal abdominal cyst
definition: Fetal abdominal cysts are usually detected during the second trimester anomaly scan or discovered incidentally at later gestations. However, a definitive diagnosis is often not made until postnatal life. The most common etiologies of fetal abdominal cysts are: ovarian, gastrointestinal cystic duplication, liver and choledochal, meconium pseudocysts, mesenteric and adrenal. Following identification of a cyst, careful morphological assessment allows the prediction of their natural history and importantly, the likelihood of surgical intervention being required postnatally.

label: Fetal bowel dilatation
definition: Fetal bowel dilatation is characterized by fluid-filled intestinal loops which measure at least fifteen millimeters long or seven millimeters in diameter. Ultrasonographic image of dilated fetal bowel is a sign of intestinal mechanical or functional obstruction and its prevalence will depend on the underlying condition: bowel atresia or stenosis, malrotation with volvulus, meconium ileus, total colonic aganglionosis, and meconium plug syndrome. The etiology of fetal bowel dilatation is a difficult prenatal diagnosis since ultrasound has limited accuracy for bowel evaluation.

label: Left ventricular dilatation
definition: Enlargement of the chamber of the left heart ventricle.

label: Fetal trigonocephaly
definition: A fetal ultrasound finding defined by flattening of the occiput with pointing of the frontal bones and brachycephaly with an increased cephalic index. It is characterized by keel shaped deformity of forehead with midline ridge, bilateral fronto temporal constriction with compensatory biparietal expansion, supra orbital and lateral orbital retrusion and hypotelorism. This finding is said to resemble a strawberry.

label: Abnormal fetal heart outflow tract
definition: A prenatal anomaly of the outflow tract. Fetal ultrasound may not always be able to easily and accurately describe the outflow anomaly, but can detect abnormal anatomy. Often, follow up with a fetal echo is recommended, but fetal ultrasound is limited.

label: History of recent viral illness
definition: Medical history of a viral illness in recent weeks.

label: History of recent dental procedure
definition: Medical history of a dental procedure in recent weeks.

label: Abnormal hepatic artery morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the hepatic artery or its branches.

label: Hepatic artery hyperplasia
definition: Abnormal increase in size of the hepatic arteries.

label: Lymph node necrosis
definition: Areas of necrotic tissue within a lymph node.

label: Multinucleated neuron
definition: Neurons that contain more than one nucleus.

label: History of recent contralateral injury
definition: A history of an injury that occurred several hours, days, or weeks before the current presenting complaint and is located on the other side of the body relative to the current presenting complaint.

label: Alternating laterality
definition: Occurring on the left and right in succession. This term can refer to alternating sides of the body (e.g., Alternating hemiplegia) or alternative sides of the visual field (e.g., some migraine auras).

label: Cervical squamous cell papilloma
definition: A benign tumor arising from the epithelial surface of the cervix and usually caused by Human Papillomavirus infection.

label: Liver leiomyoma
definition: A benign smooth muscle neoplasm that arises in the liver.

label: Typified by high penetrance
definition: Description of conditions in which only an incomplete but relatively high proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for incomplete, but high penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least 80 percent but less than 100 percent of individuals with the given genotype would manifest the disease with a full lifespan.

label: Typified by moderate penetrance
definition: Description of conditions in which only a moderate proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for moderate penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least 20 percent but less than 80 percent of individuals with the given genotype would manifest the disease with a full lifespan.

label: Typified by low penetrance
definition: Description of conditions in which only a low proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for low penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least some but less than 20 percent of carriers would manifest the disease with a full lifespan.

label: Decreased Succinyl-CoA 3-ketoacid CoA transferase activity
definition: Decreased activity of the enzyme succinyl-CoA 3-ketoacid CoA transferase.

label: Reduced phytanic acid oxidase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of the enzyme phytanoyl-CoA hydroxylase (PhyH; EC 1.14.11.18) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts. PhyH plays a role in the catabolism of phytanic acid, a branched-chain fatty acid that is a normal constituent of the human diet.

label: Abnormal enzyme activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in cultured fibroblasts. Fibroblasts are easy to grow in culture and are the main cell type involved in producing extracellular matrix. They are used as a convenient model system for measuring enzyme activity for enzymes that are not expressed in blood cells. Usually, the test is done in fibroblasts for convenience rather than for the investigation of a pathophysiology specific to fibroblasts.

label: Reduced bifunctional protein activity
definition: Diminished activity of hydroxysteroid 17-beta dehydrogenase 4 (HSD17B4), also known as D-bifunctional protein (DBP), a peroxisomal enzyme that catalyzes multiple steps of beta-oxidation of very long chain fatty acids.

label: Decreased circulating plasmalogen concentration
definition: Reduced plasmalogen concentration in the blood circulation.

label: Post-vaccination varicella zoster virus infection
definition: Infection with live, attenuated varicella-zoster virus following vaccination. This is an extremely rare event that may indicate immunocompromise.

label: Recent steroid exposure
definition: History of having been treated with corticosteroid medications in recent weeks.

label: Shark teeth
definition: Eruption of permanent teeth behind deciduous (baby) teeth before they have fallen out, resulting in a double row of teeth. This phenomen is typically observed between the ages of 5 to 7 years.

label: Pontine T2 hypointensity
definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the pons.

label: Anti-platelet antigen antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against antigens present on the surface of thrombocytes such as the glycoproteins GPIIb/IIIa, GPIb/IX, and GPIa/IIa.

label: Anti-voltage-gated potassium channel antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a voltage-gated potassium channel.

label: Vegan diet
definition: A history of following a vegan diet characterized by avoidance of food sourced from animals including meet, fish, and dairy products.

label: History of previous pregnancy with hydrops fetalis
definition: One or more previous pregnancies in which the fetus developed hydrops fetalis.

label: Ameliorated by potassium supplements
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingesting a potassium supplement.

label: Ameliorated by niacin
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingesting niacin (vitamin B3).

label: Bleeding ameliorated by vitamin K
definition: Applies to bleeding that is significantly reduced by treatment with vitamin K.

label: Anti-retroviral therapy exposure
definition: History of having been treated with an antiretroviral agent.

label: Potassium-wasting diuretic exposure
definition: History of having been treated with a potassium-wasting diuretic such as thiazide (chlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, hydrochlorothiazide, indapamide, metolazone) and loop (bumetanide, ethacrynic acid, furosemide, torsemide) diuretics.

label: Tricyclic antidepressant exposure
definition: History of having been treated with a tricyclic antidepressant medication.

label: Excessive dental attrition
definition: A higher than expected amount of attrition of teeth, as menifested by loss of tooth characteristics including rounding or sharpening of incisal edges, loss of cusps, and fracturing of teeth, to an extent that is deemed more than would be expected at a given age.

label: Positionally dependent pain
definition: Pain improves or worsens with changes in body position.

label: Abnormal erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
definition: Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) outside of the normal range.

label: Reduced erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
definition: Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
definition: Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Spermatogonial maturation arrest
definition: A type of spermatogenesis maturation arrest in which the block of developmental occurs in the spermatogonial stage. Testicular histology shows seminiferous tubules with Sertoli cells and spermatogonial cells but no further differentiated cells like spermatocytes or round spermatids.

label: Elevated circulating neuron-specific enolase concentration
definition: Concentration of neuron-specific enolase above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Reduced leukocyte alpha-mannosidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of an alpha-mannosidase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

label: Increased circulating alpha-mannosidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha mannosidase above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Reduced leukocyte cathepsin D activity
definition: Concentration or activity of cathepsin D as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal. The reduction in cathepsin D activity can also be measured in fibroblasts.

label: Reduced leukocyte N-sulfoglucosamine sulfohydrolase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of N-sulfoglucosamine sulfohydrolase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

label: Pseudohyperkalemia
definition: Pseudohyperkalemia describes a falsely elevated potassium level upon measurement of the serum electrolyte concentration due to disruption of cells during the collection or processing of the sample.

label: Reduced heparan-alpha-glucosaminide N-acetyltransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of N-sulfoglucosamine sulfohydrolase as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

label: Reduced N-acetylgalactosamine-6-sulfate sulfatase in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of N-acetylgalactosamine-6-sulfate sulfatase as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

label: Reduced acetylglucosamine-6-sulfate sulfatase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of N-acetylglucosamine-6-sulfatase (EC 3.1.6.14) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. N-acetylglucosamine-6-sulfatase hydrolyzes heparan sulfate and keratan sulfate.

label: Reduced erythrocyte porphobilinogen deaminase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of porphobilinogen deaminase (EC 4.3.1.8) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced holocarboxylase synthetase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of holocarboxylase synthetase (EC 6.3.4.10) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

label: Reduced tissue alpha-N-acetylgalactosaminidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylgalactosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.49) is below the limits of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced erythrocyte arginase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of arginase (EC 3.5.3.1) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. Arginase catalyzes the last step of the urea cycle.

label: Reduced mitochondrial acetyl-CoA acetyltransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of mitochondrial acetyl-CoA acetyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.9) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

label: Reduced tissue beta-mannosidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of beta-mannosidase (EC 3.2.1.25) below the lower limit of normal. Beta-mannosidas enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced 3-methylcrotonyl CoA carboxylase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of 3-methylcrotonyl-CoA carboxylase (EC 6.4.1.4) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced branched-chain alpha-keto acid dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of branched-chain alpha-keto acid dehydrogenase complex (EC 1.2.4.4) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced erythrocyte galactose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of galactose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase (GALT; EC 2.7.7.12) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced isovaleryl CoA dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of isovaleryl-CoA dehydrogenase (EC 1.3.99.10) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced glycerol kinase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of glycerol kinase (EC 2.7.1.30) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Increased circulating vitamin A concentration
definition: Concentration of vitamin A above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Elevated circulating hyaluronic acid concentration
definition: Concentration of hyaluronic acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Diminished breath sounds
definition: A reduction in the intensity of the breath sound as ascertained by auscultation of the lung.

label: Anti-AK5 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-adenylate kinase 5 (AK5).

label: Anti-AMPAR antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-alpha-amino-3-hydroxy-5-methyl-4-isoxazolepropionic acid receptor (AMPAR).

label: Anti-Amphiphysin antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Amphiphysin.

label: Anti-ARHGAP26 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Rho GTPase-activating protein 26 (ARHGAP26).

label: Anti-CARP VIII antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Carbonic anhydrase-related protein VIII (CARPVIII).

label: Anti-CASPR2
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against contactin-associated protein-like 2 (CASPR2).

label: Anti-CV2/CRMP5 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against CV2/CRMP5. Anti-CV2/CRMP5 autoantibody is the most commonly detected anti-neuronal autoantibody. Patients with typical paraneoplastic chorea show fully developed chorea in the course of weeks to months with acute inflammation in the striatum.

label: Anti-DPPX antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against dipeptidyl-peptidase-like protein 6 (DPPX).

label: Anti-FGFR3 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against FGFR3.

label: Anti-GABA(A)R antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against gamma-aminobutyric acid A receptor, i.e., GABA(A)R.

label: Anti-GABA(B)R antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against gamma-aminobutyric acid B receptor, i.e., GABA(B)R.

label: Anti-GAD65 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glutamic acid decarboxylase 65 (GAD65).

label: Anti-Gephyrin antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Gephyrin.

label: Anti-GFAP antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glial fibrillary acidic protein (GFAP).

label: Anti-GlyR antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Glycine receptor (GlyR).

label: Anti-Homer-3 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Homer-3.

label: Anti-Hu antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Hu.

label: Anti-Iglon5 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against immunoglobulin-like cell adhesion molecule 5 (IgLON5).

label: Anti-ITPR1 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptor 1 (ITPR1).

label: Anti-Kelch like protein 11 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against kelch-like protein 11 (KLHL11).

label: Anti-LGI1 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against leucine-rich glioma-inactivated 1 (LGI1).

label: Anti-Ma antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma.

label: Anti-Ma2 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma2.

label: Anti-Ma1 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma1.

label: Anti-mGluR1 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against metabotropic glutamate receptor 1 (mGluR1).

label: Anti-mGluR5 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against metabotropic glutamate receptor 5 (mGluR5).

label: Anti-neurexin-3alpha antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against neurexin-3alpha.

label: Anti-P/Q-type VGCC antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against P/Q-type voltage-gated calcium channels (VGCCs).

label: Anti-MAP1B antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against microtubule-associated protein 1B (MAP1B).

label: Anti-PKCgamma antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against protein kinase Cgamma.

label: Anti-Ri antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ri, an antineuronal antibody.

label: Anti-Septin-5 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Septin-5.

label: Anti-SEZ6L2 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against seizure-related 6 homolog like 2 (SEZ6L2).

label: Anti-SOX1 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against SOX1. Anti-SOX1 antibodies, also known as antiglial nuclear antibody (AGNA), are specifically found in paraneoplastic neurological disorders. Since SOX1 is expressed in neuronal precursor cells in the developing central nervous system, it has been used as an early marker of neural stem cells.

label: Anti-Tr/DNER antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Tr/DNER. Anti-Tr antibodies are directed against cerebellar Purkinje cells (termed anti-Tr or PCA-Tr). Anti-Tr autoantibodies are frequently associated with Hodgkin lymphoma (HL). Anti-Tr antibodies are defined by a specific staining pattern in cerebellar tissue that is characterized by punctate immunoreactivity in both the dendritic tree and soma of Purkinje cells but not in their axons. This characteristic pattern is indicative of the presence of anti-Tr antibodies. The Delta/Notch-like epidermal growth factor-related receptor (DNER) was identified as the target antigen of anti-Tr.

label: Anti-TRIM46 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the axon initial segment protein tripartite motif 46 (TRIM46).

label: Anti-TRIM9/TRIM67 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against TRIM9/TRIM67.

label: Anti-Yo antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Yo.

label: Anti-titin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against titin.

label: Anti-Zic4 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Zic family member 4 (ZIC4).

label: Anti-Sj/ITPR1 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Sj/inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptor.

label: Anti-D2 R antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against dopamine-2 receptor.

label: Anti-GluK2 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glutamate kainate receptor subunit 2 (GluK2).

label: Anti-Lrp4 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against low-density lipoprotein receptor (Lrp4).

label: Anti-ryanodine receptor antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ryanodine receptor.

label: Anti-Kv1.4 antibody
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the voltage-gated potassium channel Kv1.4.

label: Selective mutism
definition: Voluntary failure to use spoken language (at whatever level attained) in selective social contexts over a period of time.

label: Limited repertoire of facial expression
definition: An abnormally limited range of facial expressions demonstrated by a lack of nuance of facial expression to match specific social situations or an inability to demonstrate a normal range of emotions with one's face.

label: Excessive interest in others
definition: A strong desire to interact and engage with others that is perceived to be inappropriate or excessive in the context of cultural norms.

label: Abnormal interest in others
definition: A social interest in others that is abnormal given the social context. This can include an increased interest with another person or an abnormal lack of interest in other people.

label: Disjointed sentences
definition: Persistent abnormalities in the sentence structure in speech, phrases may not be logically connected to each other, gives the impression of rambling. This may be a characteristic feature of the individual or may be a change from the norm of the affected individual.

label: Neologism
definition: Consistent use of an invented word that is unique to an individual.

label: Overly formal/pedantic language
definition: Use of language that is overly formal, precise, detailed, or pedantic for the social context.

label: Abnormal speech rhythm
definition: Speech with persistent abnormal rhythm or pattern for the context and cultural situation. This may occur constantly throughout conversations with the person or may occur in periodic bursts lasting several minutes to hours.

label: Ambiguous facial expression
definition: Spontaneous production of communicative facial expressions that have poor quality or are perceived as odd or mechanical. This may include inaccurate mimicry of typical facial expressions. These expressions may be difficult to interpret for someone who is not familiar with the individual making the expression.

label: Exaggerated facial expression
definition: A tendency to make facial expressions that are exaggerated and a failure to make subtle facial expressions in a social context when a subtle expression is more appropriate.

label: Muted facial expression
definition: A tendency to produce facial expressions with decreased intensity or expressivity which appear muted or flat.

label: Reduced social insight
definition: A lack of awareness of social rules in multiple social settings, which are simple or intuitive to others in the same social setting.

label: Reduced awareness of convention
definition: Reduced awareness of expected conventions, which are normal and expected for particular social settings or interactions.

label: Impaired social imitation
definition: Reduced use of imitation of tasks or movements of others in play or learning.

label: Reduced responsiveness to social cues
definition: A tendency to display responces to social cues that are interpreted (e.g., by family members, peers, or caregivers) as diminished compared to what would be expected based on the developmental stage and cultural context of an individual.

label: Diminished integration of verbal and non-verbal communicative behavior
definition: A communicative abnormality where one's nonverbal and verbal communication are poorly integrated. This may occur when verbal and nonverbal communication are intact alone but are abnormal when used together, or an abnormality in the use of typically integrated communication such as the use of beat gestures during speech.

label: Reduced cooperative imaginative play
definition: Failure of a child to engage with peers games that involve creating imaginary scenarios or narratives, for instance, in which children pretend to be characters or act out adventurous scenarios.

label: Reduced imaginative play skills
definition: Reduced or lack of pretending in play (does not assign abstract properties to objects, use invisible objects, or use objects in nonliteral ways other than their intended purpose in play).

label: Lack of expressed empathy
definition: This term refers to the observation that an affected person tends not to provide situationally appropriate responses to other people in times when these people are in emotional need. For instance, failure to provide comfort to a person who is sad or crying.

label: Abnormal social emotional interactions
definition: Social emotional interactions refer to the exchange of feelings during social interactions by means of a wide range of communicative behaviors including facial expressions, body language, and verbal communication. This term refers to an atypically low production of emotion social communication by an individual.

label: Bradylalia
definition: Speech that is abnormally slow as compared to the perceived cultural norm.

label: Excessively loud speech
definition: Speech which is persistently abnormally and noticeably loud or high volume for the social and cultural context and is not due to a structural or muscular abnormality. Those around the person often consider them to be shouting.

label: Abnormal speech volume
definition: Speech that is abnormally loud or quiet for the social and cultural context in which it is spoken. It is clinically noted by others, including family, friends, or clinical providers.

label: Excessively quiet speech
definition: Speech which is persistently abnormally quiet, or of low in volume for the social and cultural context. This includes persistent and inappropriate whispering. It is not due to a medical or surgical condition that results in hoarseness, nor structural or muscular abnormality that results in low speech volume.

label: Reduced impulse control
definition: Reduced ability to control, or a failure to resist a temptation, urge, or impulse.

label: Idiosyncratic gesture
definition: When one uses gestures that are unique to them and have no apparent meaning to others.

label: Atypical sorting
definition: Atypical focus on arranging, balancing, or positioning objects; may be atypical in focus or intensity.

label: Excessive checking
definition: Checking behavior that is excessive for the situational context.

label: Excessive hand washing
definition: Hand washing behavior that is excessive for the situational context.

label: Resistance to trivial environmental changes
definition: Distress in response to minor changes in one's environmental expectations.

label: Reduced co-speech gestures
definition: Reduced use of speech-integrated gestures such as the use of beat gestures.

label: Limited head nodding or shaking
definition: Absence or reduction in the use of head nodding to indicate agreement or head shaking to indicate disagreement.

label: Limited pointing
definition: Absence or reduction in the use of pointing to request or direct another's attention.

label: Sensory hyposensitivity unexplained by sensory deficit
definition: Increased tolerance to sensory stimuli due to diminished sensory ability.

label: Tactile hypersensitivity
definition: A decreased tolerance to physical touch.

label: Auditory sensory seeking
definition: Pursuit of specific sounds or noises that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency.

label: Gustatory sensory seeking
definition: Pursuit of a particular taste that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency.

label: Olfactory sensory seeking
definition: Pursuit of specific scents, smells, or fragrances that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency.

label: Vestibular sensory seeking
definition: Pursuit of vestibular stimulation that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency.

label: Visual sensory seeking
definition: Pursuit visual stimulation by looking at specific sights, images, and/or colors that is abnormal in intensity and/or frequency.

label: Socially inappropriate questioning
definition: A tendency to ask questions that are overly personal or otherwise inappropriate in the social situation in which they are asked.

label: Spinning
definition: An excessive frequency of spinning one's body.

label: Delayed Echolalia
definition: Repetition of borrowed words or phrases outside of the context in which they were originally heard. E.g., scripting from TV shows or movies.

label: Immediate Echolalia
definition: Immediate repetition of another person's speech.

label: Excessive cleaning
definition: Excessive cleaning of surfaces, living space, or environment that is excessive for the situational context.

label: Facial expressions not directed to others
Reduced social smiling
definition: Reduced production of smiles during engagement with an interactive parent, caregiver, or peer.

label: Infrequent social engagement with peers
definition: Social engagement refers to the interaction of an individual with others in a contextually appropriate manner. This term refers to a lower than typical number of attempts to engage peers in conversation, play, or other interactions.

label: Avoidance of emotional intimacy
definition: An atypically high tendency to avoid interpersonal exchanges characterizing by sharing of personal feelings, expressions of understanding, affirmation, and demonstrations of caring.

label: Failure to offer information to initiate social interaction
definition: An atypically low tendency to offer information as a means to initiate or sustain social interactions or direct another's attention.

label: Difficulty understanding nonliteral meaning of conversation
Difficulty recognizing another's emotions
definition: A difficulty in being able to understand the emotions of other people. This can range from recognizing emotions from facial expressions to an inability to empathize with others when they describe their feelings

label: Objectification of others
definition: A tendency to interact with others as if they are objects with functional purpose rather than engaging in social/emotional interactions.

label: Indifference to social norms
definition: Failure to follow social norms (shared standards of acceptable behavior) even though one has awareness of these norms and the ability to follow them. This is characterized by an indifference to the consequences of breaking social norms.

label: Aggression towards others
definition: Aggression that is directed towards other individuals, as opposed to oneself.

label: Aggression towards caregivers
definition: Aggression that is directed towards caregivers.

label: Aggression toward non-caregivers
definition: Aggression that is directed towards non-caregivers.

label: Abnormal rituals
definition: Insistence on rituals which are self-imposed on a person's environment including directing the behavior of those around them.

label: Jumping
definition: An excessive frequency of jumping in place.

label: Delay in the acquisition of cooperative play skills
definition: Failure to acquire the ability to play cooperatively, a type of play in whichchildren work together towards a common goal and in which a child displays interest both in the play and in the the other child or children involved in playing. This ability is observed in neurotypical children from the age of 3 to 6 years.

label: Olfactory hallucination
definition: Perception of smell without olfactory stimulus.

label: Gustatory hallucination
definition: Perception of taste without gustatory stimulus.

label: Abnormal interpretation of external stimuli
definition: Abnormal perception of reality is characterized by an abnormal or inaccurate experience of external stimuli.

label: Proprioceptive hallucination
definition: A type of hallucination that involves the perception of distorted or abnormal sensations related to one's body position or movement.

label: Illusions
definition: Perceptual experiences that involve misinterpretations or distortions of sensory stimuli.

label: Inattentiveness illusion
definition: Instances in which individuals fail to perceive or notice salient or significant stimuli in their visual field due to a lack of attention.

label: Illusions due to affect
definition: Perceptual distortions or misinterpretations of sensory information arise as a result of the individual's emotional or affective state.

label: Pareidolia
definition: Apophenia is a psychological phenomenon in which individuals perceive familiar patterns or meaningful images in random or ambiguous stimuli, such as clouds, shadows, or inanimate objects.

label: Autoscopy
definition: A phenomenon in which an individual perceives themselves from an external perspective, as if they are observing their own body or self from a location outside of their physical body.

label: Subjective eidetic images
definition: A mental phenomenon is when an individual can vividly visualize or recall visual information from memory with exceptional detail and accuracy. These images are experienced subjectively by the individual, meaning they are not physically present or visible to others.

label: Amplification of social interactions
definition: A increase in the tendency of a person to seek or maintain social connections or interactions with others compared to previous norms for an individual.

label: Abnormal change in social behavior
definition: An alternation in the habits and emotional tendencies of an individual with a change in behavior that is typically noticed by family members or peers.

label: Diminishment of emotional responsiveness
definition: A reduction in the tendency of a person to display emotional responsiveness or empathy towards others during interpersonal interactions as compared to that person's previous norm.

label: Diminishment of social interactions
definition: A reduction in the tendency of a person to seek or maintain social connections or interactions with others compared to previous norms for an individual.

label: Visceral hallucination
definition: A type of hallucination that involves the perception of internal bodily sensations or processes that do not actually exist.

label: Depersonalization
definition: A psychological experience or symptom characterized by a sense of detachment or estrangement from oneself or one's surroundings.

label: Derealization
definition: Depersonalization is a subjective experience in which an individual feels a sense of detachment or estrangement from their surroundings, leading to a distorted perception of the external world. It is characterized by a feeling of unreality or unfamiliarity with one's environment, as if things are dreamlike, artificial, or lacking in significance.

label: Decreased facial expression mirroring
definition: Diminished mirroring or reflection of facial expressions in another person during social interactions.

label: Diminishment of comfort with casual physical contact
definition: A reduction in the tendency of a person to accept casual physical contact with others as compared to that person's previous norm.

label: Thought blocking
definition: The experience of sudden cessation of the thought/thinking process, the person often describes the mind going blank and there is frequently a period of silence that is accompanied by a perplexed state, not understanding what transpired.
