Some may describe the experience as an abrupt emptying of the mind or the belief that an external force removed their thoughts from their head.

label: Hypervigilance
definition: A heightened alertness is characterized by a broad awareness and/or excessive scanning of environmental stimuli.

label: Anticipatory anxiety
definition: A state characterized by future-oriented worry, accompanied by negative affect and autonomic arousal.

label: Flight of ideas
definition: Successive thoughts and speech are easily diverted by external stimuli or internal superficial associations. Unable to maintain a constant train of thought and lose themselves in side issues, losing the thread and are unable to recover it. Superficial connections appear to drive the subject matter.

label: Pressured speech
definition: Speech pattern that is excessive and intense that often imparts a sense of urgency, the individual appears to be driven to communicate with many words that are spoken very quickly and may run into each other. The person is frequently difficult to interrupt and appears to not respond to social cues for the conversational partner(s) to take their turn in speaking.

label: Leaden paralysis
definition: The sensation of having heavy arms and legs, or feeling a heaviness in the limbs.

label: Grandiosity
definition: Persistently exaggerated feelings and thoughts of an inflated sense of self-importance, superiority, uniqueness, or invulnerability. The affected individual may project arrogance with a dismissive behavioral pattern towards others the individual deems inferior.

label: Hopelessness
definition: Persistent and excessive feelings of despair with an overwhelming lack of hope. While hopelessness is primarily a personal experience, the sense of hopelessness becomes pervasive and affects most aspects of the personal experience in relation to the world. For example the person may communicate a sense of hopelessness for family and friends (who themselves do not experience hopelessness), as well as the world in general.

label: Abnormal sadness
definition: Experience of intense or excessively negative feelings that may include profound unhappiness, feeling low, down, or sorrowful and are beyond cultural or societal norms. Commonly associated with a low self-attitude and grim outlook.

label: Decreased need for sleep
definition: There has been a noticeable decrease in the need for sleep, where individuals feel refreshed even with minimal or no sleep.

label: Bruxism during sleep
definition: Bruxism is a condition in which you grind, gnash, or clench your teeth while asleep.

label: Nightmare disorder
definition: Nightmare disorder is defined by the repeated occurrence of nightmares that cause clinically significant distress or impairment in social, occupational or other important areas of functioning, which are not attributable to the physiological effects of a substance (e.g. drug abuse or medication) and which cannot be adequately explained by coexisting mental and medical disorders.

label: Sleep-related eating disorder
definition: Eating while asleep can be problematic, as it may involve potentially harmful behaviors like overeating or consuming raw meat.

label: Microsleep
definition: Sudden onset of extreme drowsiness or falling asleep during the day for a short period of time.

label: Exploding head syndrome
definition: Sleep disorder in which one hears a loud noise or explosive crashing sound in their head. The sound is not real or heard by anyone else. The episode typically happens suddenly, either when beginning to fall asleep or when waking up during the night.

label: REM sleep behavior disorder
definition: REM Sleep Behavior Disorder (RBD) is a chronic sleep condition characterized by dream enactment and loss of REM atonia.

label: Non-restorative sleep
definition: Perception of feeling unrefreshed after sleep.

label: Sexsomnia
definition: Unintentional sexual behavior during sleep, such as masturbation, initiation of sex, or making sexual noises, is known as sexsomnia. Sexsomnia predominantly occurs during NREM sleep.

label: Periodic limb movements
definition: Repetitive limb movements during sleep can affect the quality of your sleep.

label: Abnormal sleep architecture
definition: Interruptions during the various stages of sleep.

label: Short N1 sleep
definition: Decreased duration of phase N1 of nonrapid eye movement (NREM) sleep.

label: Paradoxical insomnia
definition: Paradoxical insomnia is a condition in which individuals with a normal or near-normal sleep macrostructure tend to severely underestimate the quantity and quality of their sleep.

label: Short N2 sleep
definition: Decreased duration of phase N2 of nonrapid eye movement (NREM) sleep.

label: Short N3 sleep
definition: Decreased duration of phase N3 of nonrapid eye movement (NREM) sleep.

label: Amplification of interpersonal communication
definition: An increase in the tendency of a person to share information or emotions compared to that person's previous norms.

label: Amplification of relationship seeking
definition: Increased frequency or duration in social outings and interactions as part of relationship-seeking or maintenance compared to the previous norms of an individual. May be considered to be overfamiliar and have a tendency to engage strangers in a presumptive manner.

label: Diminishment of interpersonal communication
definition: A reduction in the tendency of a person to share information or emotions compared to that person's previous norms.

label: Diminishment of relationship seeking
definition: A reduction in the tendency of a person to seek new interpersonal relationships or maintain existing relationships.

label: Amplification of sexual behavior
definition: An abnormal increase of libido (sexual desire), typically accompanied by a higher frequency of sexual activity compared to from a person's previous norm.

label: Amplification of emotional expression
definition: An increase in the tendency of a person to express emotions compared to that person's previous norm.

label: Amplification of emotional responsiveness
definition: An increase in the tendency of a person to display emotional responsiveness or emotional empathy towards others during interpersonal interactions as compared to that person's previous norm. May be considered to be overreactive or over-engaged with interpersonal situations that may take on a persistent preoccupation and would appear to be relatively unrelated to the person, and beyond the expression of normal empathy.

label: Amplification of comfort with casual physical contact
definition: An increase in the tendency of a person to be comfortable with physical contact with others compared to that person's previous norm. Often considered to be intrusive and encroaching on personal space of others less known to the person, frequently causing discomfort and may result in argument or altercation.

label: Diminishment of sexual behavior
definition: A reduction of libido (sexual desire), typically accompanied by a reduction in the frequency of sexual activity , and/or activity compared to the affected individual's previous state.

label: Diminishment of emotional expression
definition: A reduction in the tendency of a person to express emotions that is typically noticed as a change in behavior by family members or peers.

label: Suicide behaviors
definition: Suicide attempts or preparations

label: Addictive non-substance behaviors
definition: Uncontrolled use or problematic behaviors of dependency without the use of drugs or substances can be detrimental.

label: Addictive spending behavior
definition: An uncontrollable urge to shop and spend money can lead to distress or impairment.

label: Addictive gambling behavior
definition: The act of taking chances or engaging in behaviors without restraint, typically involving the wagering of something valuable, in pursuit of acquiring something of higher value.

label: Addictive sex behavior
definition: Inability to control or manage sexual urges, fantasies, or behaviors that impair one's ability to function.

label: Addictive video game use
definition: The inability to regulate persistent gaming behavior is characterized by a heightened prioritization of gaming activities over regular daily tasks and responsibilities.

label: Compulsive stealing
definition: Irresistible impulses to take easily affordable items.

label: Excessive fire setting
definition: The inability to control urges of deliberately setting fires for pleasure and gratification, without any criminal intent.

label: Self-cutting
definition: Deliberate harm to one's body, in the form of cutting that results in tissue damage, without a conscious intent to die.

label: Addictive cannabis use
definition: A persistent and compulsive need to use cannabis, despite negative consequences.

label: Autophagia
definition: The habitual action of inflicting pain upon oneself by biting and/or devouring portions of one's body.

label: Hypnagogic sleep paralysis
definition: Sleep paralysis that occurs when falling asleep.

label: Hypnopompic sleep paralysis
definition: Sleep paralysis that occurs when waking up from sleep.

label: Sleep onset rapid eye movement period
definition: Entering REM sleep immediately upon falling asleep.

label: Prolonged N1 sleep
definition: Increased duration of phase N1 of nonrapid eye movement (NREM) sleep.

label: Prolonged N2 sleep
definition: Increased duration of phase N2 of nonrapid eye movement (NREM) sleep.

label: Prolonged N3 sleep
definition: Increased duration of phase N3 of nonrapid eye movement (NREM) sleep.

label: Overvalued idea
definition: A solitary belief that may be held by others in the society that is maintained by the person to an abnormal and morbid degree and overtly drives behaviors that are considered unhealthy, intrusive, or illegal. This includes fads and cults that the person may adhere to and practice to a morbid degree. The content may vary and ranges from religion, health, romance, or politics.

label: Time agnosia
definition: The inability to perceive the passage of time is usually due to a disorder involving the temporal area of the brain.

label: Olfactory agnosia
definition: The inability to recognize certain smells or types of odors that you previously recognized.

label: Topographical agnosia
definition: The inability to rely on visual cues to guide one's direction is due to the inability to recognize objects.

label: Delusional memory
definition: Delusional memory is a memory that is false or fantastically distorted, but held with firm and irrefutable conviction despite evidence to the contrary. It is often seen in psychiatric conditions such as delusional disorders, schizophrenia, and sometimes in severe mood disorders. These memories can be completely fabricated or have a basis in an actual event that has been grossly misinterpreted or altered by the individual's mind.

label: Auditory agnosia
definition: The condition is characterized by the inability to recognize spoken languages and/or nonverbal environmental sounds and music, despite having adequate hearing. However, spontaneous speech, reading, and writing abilities remain intact.

label: Gustatory agnosia
definition: People cannot identify tastes, even though they can experience them.

label: Allesthesia
definition: Referral of a sensory stimulus from one side of the body to the other.

label: Autotopagnosia
definition: The loss of the ability to localize, recognize, or identify specific parts of one's body.

label: Persecutory delusion
definition: False beliefs (or judgements) that are held with extraordinary conviction and subjective certainty that are impervious to other experiences or counterarguments and the content is generally considered impossible for the context and circumstance. Delusional beliefs may arise meaningfully from personal or social experiences, yet are impossible, held with conviction, and irrefutable; more commonly they may be psychologically irreducible, appearing with no logical or meaningful connection to the individual experience.

label: Morbid jealosy
definition: A disorder of delusional content wherein the affected individual believes they are a victim of their partner's infidelity. It is often based on delusional evidence of an erotic or romantic nature. There may be an affective (mood related) component or may be associated with substance use disorders. It may also occur on its own. There may be associated behaviors to monitor or gather evidence of the perceived infidelity.

label: Grandiose delusion
definition: Delusional beliefs of a fantastical, expansive, or supernatural quality related to power, ability, wealth, or station. They are often related to origin (aristocratic lineage, royal birth, being raised as a foster child), possessions (owning vast estates, castles, etc., which are withheld through intrigue), abilities (being great inventors, discoverers, artists, possessors of special wisdom, gifted with inspiration), and status (adviser to prominent diplomats, the true director of political destinies). Grandiose delusions may be related to affective states, substance use, or may occur independently.

label: Folie à deux
definition: Delusional beliefs are transmitted from one individual to another.

label: Delusion of love
definition: A delusional belief that the person is secretly loved by another individual who is often of recognized fame or authoratative significance. There is typically no overt evidence and the delusional belief may be driven by falsely perceived indicators. Often there is a blend of erotic delusions and morbid infatuation.

label: Nihilistic delusion
definition: A delusion that elements of the self, body, or world no longer exist. The person typically recognizes that the entity did in fact exist at one time, but has ceased to exist. The cause of which may be related to disease, decay, or may have been removed or taken by unknown forces.

label: Cotard delusion
definition: A false belief that you or your body parts are dead, dying, or do not exist.

label: Delusional perception
definition: A true perception, to which a patient attributes a false and usually bizarre meaning or interpretation. It is often a revelatory experience that is sudden and is a profound realization of the delusional belief. It often occurs in the context of delusional mood or atmosphere wherein vague and mysterious hunches or concerns with nebulous meaning evolve into clear, delusional observations, and expresses delusions of reference.

label: Hypochondriac delusion
definition: Delusion quality to belief that one is suffering from an illness despite reassurances based on medical examination and testing. The person may (or not) express pain or discomfort that they attribute to the disease. They are frequently treatment seeking, but do not induce illness features (which is termed Munchhausen syndrome).

label: Delusions of infestation
definition: A persistent belief that a person is infested with living or non-living pathogens, such as parasites, insects, or bugs, when no such infestation is present.

label: Delusional atmosphere
definition: A persistent sense or a hunch that something is different in an imperceptible manner. Typically the perception is one of a sinister, portentous , uncanny, mysterious, or peculiar sense of foreboding in an indefinable way. There is an innate sense of inexplicable self-relevance to the person. There is often a feeling of anticipation, sometimes even excitement, that soon the mystery may be revealed and all the separate parts of their experience will fit together to reveal something immensely significant. The duration of this experience may vary, lasting from hours to days. It may be intermittent over an extended period of time (months to years).

label: Delusional misidentification
definition: A group of complex, monothematic delusional phenomena in which subjects hold a belief that the identity of a familiar person, object, location, or self has been altered or replaced. The majority of misidentifications are spouses or first degree relatives, i.e. someone well-known to the person.

label: Religious delusion
definition: Delusions with a religious content that are considered delusional in nature based on how the belief is held and the evidence offered to support it, which is generally considered impossible or fantastical in the cultural setting of the person. It differs from unusual beliefs that are held with tenacity or conviction and are typically associated with other phenomena consistent with mental illness.

label: Incomplete unilateral cleft lip
definition: Unilateral cleft lip cleft that starts from the bottom of the upper lip but does not reach the nasal cavity.

label: Complete unilateral cleft lip
definition: Unilateral cleft lip cleft that starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity.

label: Complete cleft of the upper lip
definition: Cleft of the upper lip that starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity.

label: Microform unilateral cleft lip
definition: Notch, groove, or scar of the upper lip without noticeable rupture of the lip. Microforms are sometimes associated with disruption of the continuity of the orbicularis oris muscle.

label: Complete cleft hard palate
definition: Cleft hard palate in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the hard palate, ie. from the incisor foramen to the anterior border of the soft palate.

label: Incomplete cleft hard palate
definition: Cleft hard palate in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the hard palate, ie. the cleft does not go from the incisor foramen to the anterior border of the soft palate.

label: Complete cleft soft palate
definition: Cleft soft palate in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the soft palate, i.e. from the posterior border of the hard palate until the uvula.

label: Incomplete cleft soft palate
definition: Cleft soft palate in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the soft palate, i.e. the cleft does not go from the posterior border of the hard palate until the uvula.

label: Incomplete cleft maxillary alveolar ridge
definition: Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the maxillary alveolar ridge.

label: Complete cleft maxillary alveolar ridge
definition: Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the maxillary alveolar ridge.

label: Complete bilateral cleft lip
definition: Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides is complete, i.e. start from the bottom of the upper lip and reach the nasal cavity.

label: Incomplete bilateral cleft lip
definition: Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides are incomplete (i.e. start from the bottom of the upper lip but do not reach the nasal cavity), or the cleft lip on one is incomplete and a microform on the other side.

label: Microform bilateral cleft lip
definition: Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides are microform, i.e. a notch, groove, or scar without noticeable rupture of the lip.

label: Asymmetric bilateral cleft lip
definition: Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on one side is complete (i.e. starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity), and the one on the other side is incomplete (i.e. starts from the bottom of the upper lip but does not reach the nasal cavity) or microform (i.e. a notch, groove, or scar without noticeable rupture of the lip).

label: Left-right disorientation
definition: A tendency to mix up left and right in one's own body space, typically elicited by asking a person to perform a two-stage command involving specified lateralized anatomy.

label: Elevated circulating DNAJB9 protein concentration
definition: Concentration of DnaJ homolog subfamily B member 9 (DNAJB9) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Olecranon fracture
definition: A partial or complete break in the olecranon,which is the proximal articular portion of the ulna and makes up part of the elbow.

label: History of mastectomy
definition: Past medical history of surgical breast removal.

label: Lymphangiosarcoma
definition: A malignant neoplasm arising from the endothelial cells of the lymphatic vessels.

label: Exposure to inhaled lipids
definition: Aspiration or inhalation of lipid-containing products.

label: Holster sign
definition: Symmetric poikiloderma of hips and lateral thighs below the greater trochanter.

label: Salivary basal cell adenoma
definition: A rare neoplasm consisting of a monomorphic population of basaloid epithelial cells, and it accounts for approximately 1-2% of all salivary gland tumors.

label: Hemidiaphragm elevation
definition: Elevated Hemidiaphragm is a condition where one portion of the diaphragm is higher than the other. Elevated hemidiaphragm occurs when one side of the diaphragm becomes weak from muscular disease or loss of innervation due to phrenic nerve injury.

label: Cerebriform connective tissue nevus
definition: The cerebriform connective tissue nevus (CCTN) is one of the most characteristic skin findings. It commonly occurs on the soles of the feet, and frequently causes problems because of pain, pruritus, infection, bleeding,exudation, odor, and walking impairment.

label: Linear Hyperpigmentation along Blaschko's lines
definition: Linear streaks and swirls of macular hyperpigmentation along the lines of Blaschko.

label: Excessive guilt
definition: Excessive guilt is an internal feeling that is intense and considered clinically to be beyond normal range, out of proportion for the act or offense; excessive guilt is typically based on an incorrect judgment of responsibility for an unfavorable outcome. Excessive guilt is typically pervasive and enduring, i.e. it is not fleeting or a temporary thought associated with a specific action.

label: Mediastinal shift
definition: A deviation of the mediastinum from its normal position in the midline of the thoracic cavity. The mediastinum is a compartment of the thoracic cavity that contains the heart and its blood vessels, the esophagus, trachea, thymus, as well as nerves and lymph nodes.

label: Bendopnea
definition: Dyspnea as a result of bending forward while not holding one's breath; dyspnea or shortness of breath onset within 30 seconds of bending forward.

label: Pain worse when lying flat
definition: Refers to pain that is worse when the affected individual lies down (flat).

label: Tympanic membrane hypermobility
definition: Abnormally increased ability to move of the tympanic membrane.

label: Elevated circulating vitamin B12 concentration
definition: Concentration of vitamin B12 in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating soluble FASL concentration
definition: The concentration of soluble FASL in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. The first apoptosis signal receptor (FAS) pathway regulates apoptosis and is critical for proper development and functioning of the immune system. FAS ligand (FASL) can bind to FAS receptors.

label: Internal anal sphincter achalasia
definition: A disorder of the internal anal sphincter (IAS) in which the IAS fails to relax that manifests clinically as intractable constipation.

label: Anthracycline exposure
definition: History of treatment with an anthracycline chemotherapy agent.

label: Binge drinking
definition: A pattern of episodic heavy alcohol use characterized by the consumption of a high number of drinks per occasion.

label: Decreased circulating thrombopoietin concentration
definition: Concentration of thrombopoietin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. Thrombopoietin is a glycoprotein hormone produced by the liver and kidney that stimulates the production and differentiation of megakaryocytes.

label: Collagenoma
definition: A rare hamartomatous malformation characterized by the predominant proliferation of normal collagen fibers and normal, decreased, or increased elastic fibers. Collagenomas may be solitary or multiple, sporadic, acquired or inherited.

label: Lack of sufficient daily physical activity
definition: Physical activity levels less than those required for optimal health and prevention of premature death.

label: Synesthesia
definition: A phenomenon whereby stimulation of one sensory or cognitive pathway leads to automatic, involuntary experiences in a second sensory or cognitive pathway. For instance, people with synaesthesia may experience unusual colors, tastes, and other sensations when engaged in everyday activities like reading or listening to music.

label: Dark cerumen
definition: Abnormally dark color of cerumen (earwax), which is a waxy substance secreted in the ear canal that normally has a brown, orange, red, yellowish or gray.

label: History of spicy food intake
definition: A history of high intake of spciy foods with ingrediaents such as capsaicin, pepper, chili, ginger, garlic, onion, fenugreek, and turmeric.

label: Oil-drop brown pigmentation of the corneal limbus
definition: Brown pigment spots in the limbus (border between the cornea and the sclera).

label: Hazardous alcohol use
definition: Hazardous drinking is defined as a quantity or pattern of alcohol consumption that places individuals at risk for adverse health events. This could include alcohol use despite potentially hazardous or risky consequences, such as operating heavy machinery or drunk driving.

label: Social anxiety
definition: Excessive fear of embarrassment, humiliation, or rejection when exposed to possible negative evaluation by others when engaged in a public performance or social interaction.

label: Placidity
definition: Flat affect and reduced response to emotional stimuli. Fear and anger responses that are normally present are blunted.

label: Phaeohyphomycosis
definition: Phaeohyphomycosis refers to infections due to a large group of heterogenous organisms called dematiaceous or melanized fungi. These fungi are distinguished by the predominance of melanin in their cell walls, which likely acts as a virulence factor. Virtually, everyone is exposed to dematiaceous fungi through inhalation, as they are ubiquitous in the environment, although the development of infection is extremely uncommon.

label: Autophony
definition: Hearing one's own voice resonating loudly in the ear.

label: High altitude exposure
definition: A history of being at high altitude in situations such hiking, mountain climbing, travel to mountains, or air travel.

label: History of recent hospitalization
definition: A past medical history of recently being hospitalized.

label: Palpitations terminated by Valsava maneuver
definition: Cessation of palpitations can be induced by Valsava maneuver.

label: Long telomere length
definition: Abnormally long telomeres in somatic cells.

label: Reduced circulating aromatic L-amino acid decarboxylase activity
definition: The activity of aromatic L-amino acid decarboxylase (also known as DOPA decarboxylase, tryptophan decarboxylase, and 5-hydroxytryptophan decarboxylase) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Subclavian artery stenosis
definition: Abnormal narrowing of the subclavian artery.

label: Pulsatile liver
definition: Cardiac synchronous pulsation on palpation.

label: Neuropathic pain
definition: Neuropathic pain is triggered by lesions to the somatosensory nervous system that alter its structure and function so that pain occurs spontaneously and responses to noxious and innocuous stimuli are pathologically amplified.

label: Repeated cold water exposure
definition: A history of repeated exposure to cold water, as may result, for instance, from surfing, diving, kayaking, or swimming.

label: Tinnitus exacerbated by swallowing
definition: Tinnitus (sound heard by a subjhect when no corresponding external sound is present) that is made worse by swallowing.

label: Rhythmic movements of the tympanic membrane
definition: Regularly occurring motion of the tympanic membrane (eardrum), which is located between the inner and middle ear. This can be a manifestation of tensor tympani myoclonus, which can also be ascertained as sawtooth patterns on long-term tympanometry.

label: Elongated temporal styloid process
definition: The length of the temporal styloid process is above the upper limit of normal. The styloid process is a cylindrical, slender, needle-like projection of varying lengths averaging 2 to 3 cm. The styloid process projects from the inferior part of the petrous temporal bone and offers attachment to the stylohyoid ligament and the stylohyoid, stylopharyngeus, and styloglossus muscles.

label: Ameliorated by nitroglycerin
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with nitroglycerin.

label: Pulsus paradoxus
definition: Pulsus paradoxus refers to a systolic pressure drop greater than 10mmHg during inspiration.

label: Chest pain triggered by palpitation
definition: Chest pain can be induced by palpation of the chest, which may be an indication of costochondritis.

label: Chest pain described as pressure
definition: Discomfort in the chest described as pressure, heaviness, or tightness.

label: Chest pain described as ripping or tearing
definition: Chest pain described as a tearing or ripping sensation.

label: Ameliorated by flexion
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by bending (flexing) a joint.

label: Located on the chest
definition: Applies to a finding that is situated or occurring around the thorax (chest).

label: Localized to the penis
definition: Applies to a finding that is situated or occurring in or on the penis.

label: Snowstorm pattern of uterus on ultrasound
definition: A sonographic snowstorm pattern of the uterusresults from the presence of a complex vesicular intrauterine mass containing many grape-like cysts.

label: Multiparity
definition: History of multiple previous births.

label: Exposure to aquatic animals
definition: History of exposure to aquatic animals.

label: Superficial blush-like subcutaneous fatty lesions
definition: Multiple, oblong, fatty lesions in the superficial subcutaneous fatty tissue. They are mostly under 2 cm in long axis diameter. They demonstrate nodular (blush-like) increased fluid signal at unenhanced MRI and are markedly hyperechoic at ultrasound.

label: Dermal multinucleated giant cells
definition: Presence of giant cells in the dermis. Giant cells are formed by fusion of various cells such as macrophage, epithelioid cells, monocytes, etc., These are multi-nucleated, large in size, and generally present at the site of chronic inflammation and other granulomatous conditions.

label: Exacerbation of eyelid lesion by crying
definition: Applies to an eyelid lesion such as hemangiomas or varices that swells upon crying.

label: Localized to upper eyelid
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in the upper eyelid.

label: Aerophagia
definition: Repetitive air swallowing and belching and that may result in abdominal distention.

label: Vaginal passage of hydatidiform mole tissue
definition: Passage from the vagina of hyatidiform tissue, appearing as clusters of vesicles (similar to small grapes) developed from the transformation of chorionic villi. This is a manifestation of a molar pregnancy (hyatidiform mole).

label: Abnormal nipple discharge
definition: Abnormal fluid that seeps out of the nipple of the breast. Nipple discharge is categozied as lactational, physiologic, or pathologic.

label: Hepatolithiasis
definition: The presence of gallstones within the intrahepatic bile ducts proximal to the right and left hepatic ducts.

label: Excessive eructation
definition: Abnormally frequent belching (expelling gas noisily from the stomach through the mouth).

label: Esophageal fibrosis
definition: Fibrosis located in the subepithelial portion of the esophagus. Fibrosisis is defined by the overgrowth, hardening, and/or scarring of various tissues and is attributed to excess deposition of extracellular matrix components including collagen.

label: Triggered by extension of leg
definition: This term refers to pain that is triggered by extending (straightening) the leg.

label: Increased myocardial pyrophosphate uptake
definition: Amount of pyrophosphate uptake by the myocardium as demonstrated by by technetium pyrophosphate (99mTc-PYP) scintigraphy above the upper limit of normal.

label: Ameliorated by nerve block
definition: Refers to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by anesthetic block of a nerve.

label: Brief tear break-up time
definition: Tear film break up time (number of seconds that elapse between the last blink and the appearance of the first dry spot in the tear film) below the lower limit of normal.

label: Cutaneous granuloma
definition: A granuloma localized to the skin, that is, a chronic inflammatory manifestation with localized aggregation of histiocytes with or without other inflammatory cells (such as plasma cells, eosinophils, or neutrophils), with or without necrosis, with or without vasculitis, with or without calcification, and with or without foreign bodies. Granulomas may be due to infection or chronic inflammatory disease or reactions to foreign material.

label: Heterotopic dermal ossification
definition: Formation of abnormal, extraskeletal bony tissue in the dermis (i.e., the layer of skin that lies beneath the epidermis and above the subcutaneous layer).

label: Thinning of outer muscular layer of small bowel
definition: The depth of the outer muscular layer of the small bowel is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Renal lymphangiectasia
definition: A developmental anomaly of renal lymphatics that results from a failure of the lymphatics to make communication with the rest of the lymph trunks. The abnormal lymphatics thus dilate and form cystic spaces at the renal sinus and in the perinephric space.

label: Pharyngeal myxoma
definition: A myxoma (benign, locally infiltrative neoplasms arising from mesenchymal origin) localized to the pharynx.

label: Subcutaneous arteriolar thrombosis
definition: Fibrin thrombi inside subcutaneous arterioles.

label: Renal vasculitis
definition: Vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessels) in the kidney. Renal vasculitis can be observed with numerous disorders and presents clinically as rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis (RPGN) which is characterized by acute kidney injury (AKI), haematuria and proteinuria. Histological examination of the kidney reveals severe inflammation in the form of crescent formation, glomerular necrosis and vasculitis of small and medium sized vessels within the kidney.

label: Pancreatic islet beta cell iron deposition
definition: Accumulation of abnormally high amounts of iron in beta cells of the pancreas.

label: Nasal hamartoma
definition: A hamartoma (tissue malformation consisting of an abnormal mixture of constitutive components) originating in the nose.

label: Metachromatic intraneuronal lipid deposits
definition: A type of metachromasia localized to a peripheral nerve. Metachromasia may be defined as the staining of tissue or tissue components such that the color of the tissue-bound dye complex differs significantly from the color of the original dye complex to give a marked contrast in color. For instance in metachromatic leukodystrophy, bloated Schwann cells, containing granularmetachromatic storage material May display a characteristic yellow green dichroism under crossed polarised light.

label: Reduced phosphoserine phosphatase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of phosphoserine phosphatase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced alpha-aminoadipic semialdehyde synthase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of alpha-aminoadipic semialdehyde synthase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced hepatic beta-ureidopropionase activity
definition: Activity of beta-ureidopropionase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced hepatic dihydropyrimidinase activity
definition: Activity of dihydropyrimidinase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: Sunken fontanelle
definition: Fontanelle that is more deeply set than normal. Fontanelles are normally relatively firm and curve only slightly inward. A sunken fontanelle can be a sign of dehydration or marasmus.

label: Angulation of penis
definition: Abnormally increased curvature of the penis.

label: History of urethral procedure or catheterization
definition: A past medical history of a procedure or catheterization involving the urethra.

label: Penile swelling
definition: Abormal enlargement of the penis owing to accumulation of fluid.

label: Reduced muscle alpha-1,4-glucosidase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme alpha-1,4-glucosidase activity in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Brown tumor
definition: A brown tumor is a bone lesion that results from bony resorption by excess osteoclastic activity, and replacement by fibrous tissue and giant cells. Brown tumor is an uncommon pathognomonic sign of hyperparathyroidism.

label: Dermal flame figures
definition: Flame-figures are composed of a central part consisting of collagen fibers and eosinophilic granules, surrounded by a histiocytic and eosinophilic infiltrate. Subsequently, eosinophils tend to disappear and are replaced by phagocytic granulomas, consisting of histiocytes and sometimes giant cells, around the flame figures.

label: Postpartum exacerbation
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is present during pregnancy and becomes worse following birth.

label: Retinoid exposure
definition: History of having taken retinoids.

label: Propylthiouracil exposure
definition: History of having been treated with propylthiouracil.

label: History of outdoor activities
definition: History of spending a substantial amount of time outdoors with occupation or hobbies related to the outdoors, including hunting, gardening, farming, agriculture, horticulture, miners, working in wet fields.

label: Draining sinus tract in skin
definition: A sinus tract is an abnormal channel that originates from the skin or a mucous surface to a deep-seated focus of suppuration.

label: Corneal transplant history
definition: Past medical history of surgical replacement of the cornea with corneal tissue from a donor.

label: Spontaneous lens capsule rupture
definition: Breakage of the capsule of the lens. This is most often observed as a complication of lens surgery, but this term refers to lens capsule rupture not related to surgery or major trauma.

label: Contact lens wearer
definition: A past medical history of wearing contact lenses.

label: Airway mucosal thickening
definition: Increase in thickness of the mucosa of the airways above the upper limit of normal.

label: Hyperpolarized transepithelial nasal potential difference
definition: Increased (more negative) voltage across the nasal epithelium.

label: Corneopalpebral synechiae
definition: An adhesion between the conjunctiva of the eyelid and the cornea.

label: Breast intraductal papilloma
definition: Intraductal papilloma is a benign tumor found within breast ducts. The abnormal proliferation of ductal epithelial cells causes growth. A solitary intraductal papilloma is usually found centrally posterior to the nipple affecting the central duct. Multiple intraductal papillomas are located peripherally, found in any breast quadrant affecting the peripheral ducts.

label: Precipitous labor
definition: Precipitous labor is extremely rapid labor and delivery, usually defined as expulsion of the fetus within less than 3 hours of commencement of regular contractions.

label: Twin pregnancy
definition: Maternal history of a pregnancy with two fetuses in the uterus.

label: Vaginal mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the vagina. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Costovertebral angle tenderness
definition: Pain that is elicited by palpation of the region inside of the costovertebral angle, which is formed by the 12th rib and the spine.

label: Cervical motion tenderness
definition: Pain that is elicited by moving the uterine cervix. This finding can be ascertained by pelvic exam. Cervical motion tenderness is a gynecological exam finding that could be indicative of peritoneal infection.

label: Abnormal penile discharge
definition: Fluid that originates from the urethra that is not urine, pre-ejaculate or semen.

label: Supernumerary finger flexion crease
definition: The presence of an extra digital crease in and individual with normal joint anatomy.

label: Large joint predominance
definition: Refers to a phenotypic abnormality that mainly affect large joints.

label: Monoarticular
definition: Refers to a phenotypic abnormality that affects a single joint.

label: Hockey-stick palmar crease
definition: An abnormality of the upper palmar crease whereby the crease widens and ends between the second and third fingers and is said to resemble a hockey stick.

label: Elevated urinary succinyladenosine level
definition: The amount of succinyladenosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 5-hydroxymethyluracil level
definition: The amount of 5-hydroxymethyluracil in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Decreased urine creatinine level
definition: The amount of creatinine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary deoxyuridine level
definition: The amount of deoxyuridine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary dihydrouracil level
definition: The amount of dihydrouracil in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary dihydrothymine level
definition: The amount of dihydrothymine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary sulfatide level
definition: The amount of sulfatides in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Sulfatides are derived from GalCer via esterification of a sulfate group to 3-hydroxyl of the galactose moiety.

label: Elevated urinary xanthurenic acid level
definition: The amount of xanthurenic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased urinary N-acetylglucosamine-rich oligosaccharide level
definition: Presence of N-acetylglucosamine-rich oligosaccharides in the urine.

label: Elevated urinary 2'-deoxyadenosine level
definition: The amount of 2'-deoxyadenosine (dAdo) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive 2,4-dinitrophenylhydrazine urine test
definition: Positive (abnormal) result of the 2,4-dinitrophenylhydrazine urine test, which indicates the presence of alpha-ketoacids in the urine.

label: Elevated urinary dolichol level
definition: The amount of dolichol in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Decreased urinary bile acid level
definition: The amount of bile acids in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary creatine/creatinine ratio
definition: The ratio of creatine to creatinine concentration in the urine is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary thymidine level
definition: The amount of thymidine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary glutarylglycine level
definition: The amount of glutarylglycine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary indican level
definition: Detection of indican in the urine. Urinary indican concentration may be elevated in small bowel bacterial overgrowth. Indican is produced by bacterial deconjugation of dietary tryptophan to indole which is absorbed at all levels of the intestine, but principally from the small bowel.

label: Dacrolith
definition: Dacryolith is a concretion (accumulation of sediment) within the nasolacrimal system.

label: Reduced erythrocyte gamma-glutamyl cysteine synthetase activity
definition: Activity of gamma-glutamylcysteine synthetase (EC 6.3.2.2) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased erythrocyte nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide-cytochrome b5 reductase activity
definition: The activity of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH)-cytochrome b5 reductase in erythrocytes (red blood cells) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced alpha-methylacyl-CoA racemase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of alpha-methylacyl-CoA racemase (AMACR; EC 5.1.99.4) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Low semen volume
definition: Volume of semen in ejaculate below the lower limit of normal. This finding can be ascertained by semen analysis. Comment: Sperm are produced within the testis, in the process of spermatogenesis, then travel through the male reproductive tract (the seminiferous tubules, epididymis, vas deferens, prostate and urethra). As the sperm travel, seminal fluid is added from the seminal vesicles, prostate, testis and epididymis and periurethral glands. The function of the ejaculate is to transport sperm into the female genital tract and to provide a suitable environment for sperm survival during this transit.

label: Elbow localization
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the elbow.

label: Enlarged lunula
definition: Abnormal enlargement of the visible portion of the distal nail matrix that extends beyond the proximal nail fold, which is referred to as the lunula.

label: Heel localization
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the heel.

label: Splinter hemorrhages
definition: Thin, red to reddish-brown lines of blood (hemorrhages) under the nails. Splinter hemorrhages run vertically under the nails.

label: Lateral thrust
definition: Lateral thrust (LT) refers to an abnormal knee joint motion in the early stance phase where the knee joint center moves laterally. Also known as varus thrust, LR is defined as the dynamic worsening or abrupt onset of varus (bow-leg) alignment as the limb accepts weight (stance phase), with a return to less varus and more neutral alignment during lift-off and the non-weight-bearing (swing) phase of gait, varus thrust is a potent mechanical risk factor for medial knee osteoarthritis progression.

label: Cerebral contusion
definition: A contusion is a region of injured tissue in which blood capillaries have been ruptured without laceration (bruise). Brain contusions are bruises of the cortical surface that damage the surface from the outside inward, producing disruption of tissue and vessels. The term cerebral contusion describes the pathology of focal necrosis and hemorrhage, typically observed in older children, involving particularly cerebral cortex and subcortical white matter. Such lesions are usually found in coup and contrecoup, as well as inferior orbital, frontal, and temporal locations. Cerebral contusions cause permanent damage to tissues of the cerebrum. The etiology of cerebral contusion is trauma to the head.

label: Fecolith
definition: A mass of accumulated hardened fecal matter.

label: Appendicitis
definition: Appendicitis is inflammation of the vermiform appendix. Appendix a hollow organ located at the tip of the cecum, usually in the right lower quadrant of the abdomen.

label: Left ventricular aneurysm
definition: A severely scarred portion of infarcted ventricular myocardium that does not contract normally but instead bulges outward while the rest of the ventricle contracts during systole.

label: Boot-shaped cardiac silhouette
definition: An abnormal form of the heart seen upon chest radiography in which the heart displays an upturned apex and slight concave pulmonary artery segment. This configuration is said to resemble a boot.

label: Hydrosalpinx
definition: Hydrosalpinx is a distension or dilatation of the fallopian tube in the presence of a distal tubal occlusion.

label: Elevated methylhex-dienedioic level by MRS
definition: An increase in the level of 3-methylhex-2,4-dienedioic acid or 3-methylhex-3,4-dienedioic acid in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Perihepatic enhancement
definition: Increased signal (contrast enhancement) surrounding the liver observed on computer tomography or magnetic resonance imaging following administration of contrast agents.

label: Reduced in vitro contracture test threshold
definition: The in vitro contracture test determines the sensitivity of freshly obtained skeletal muscle specimens to caffeine or halothane applied to a bathing solution. Muscles from persons susceptible to malignant hyperthermia have lower contracture thresholds for these agents than do normal muscle.

label: Reduced F-wave amplitude
definition: Reduced strength (amplitude) of the F-wave, which is an electrophysiological artifact produced by antidromic activation of motoneurons following distal electrical stimulation of motor nerve fibers.

label: Enlarged peroxisomes
definition: Abnormal increase in size of peroxisomes.

label: Adrenocortical hyperplasia
definition: A non-malignant growth, or enlargement, of the adrenal glands, specifically the cortex, although the cortex cannot be definitively identified by conventional imaging. Adrenal cortical hyperplasia is defined radiologically as a non-malignant growth, or enlargement, of the adrenal glands.

label: Lymphocytic infiltration of the parotid gland
definition: Accumulation of lymphocytes in the parotid gland. This feature is generally defined as a count of lymphocytes per area that is above normal limits on histopathological examination.

label: Bone marrow granuloma
definition: A granuloma (a focal aggregate of immune cells that forms in response to a persistent inflammatory stimulus) localiyed to the bone marrow. A granuloma characteristically demonstrates the compact organization of mature macrophages, which may or may not be associated with other inflammatory cell types.

label: Neuronal intranuclear inclusion bodies
definition: The presence of intracellular inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in neurons.

label: Pancreatic atrophy
definition: Wasting (shrinking) of the pancreas.

label: Decreased pancreatic acinar cell density
definition: Number (count) of pancreatic acinar cells reduced below normal. This feature can be ascertained by pancreas biopsy.

label: Unesterified cholesterol accumulation in cultured fibroblasts
definition: An abnormal result of the the filipin test. In this test is based on the reaction of unesterified cholesterol with fluorescent antibiotic filipin giving a strongly fluorescent, stable cholesterol-filipin complex suitable for in situ detection. An abnormal test result is present if there is a perinuclear accumulation of staining in lysosomal storage organelles (LSOs).

label: Hepatic lipid-laden macrophage infiltration
definition: Accumulation of foamy cells (lipid-laden macrophages) in the parenchyma of the liver.

label: Splenic lipid-laden macrophage infiltration
definition: Accumulation of foamy cells (lipid-laden macrophages) in the parenchyma of the spleen.

label: Reduced hepatic N-acetylglutamate synthase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of N-acetylglutamate synthase in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal.

label: Excessive licorice consumption
definition: Ingestion of large amounts of licorice.

label: Shoulder localization
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the shoulder.

label: Pregnancy conceived despite intrauterine device
definition: Intrauterine devices (IUDs) are used for contraception. Rarely pregnancy occurs despite the presence of an IUD. Such pregnancies are associated with an increased risk of spontaneous abortion and preterm delivery due to infection, and a higher risk of maternal septic complications.

label: Maternal folate deficiency
definition: The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of folate deficiency during the corresponding pregnancy.

label: Maternal zinc deficiency
definition: The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of abnormally low zinc levels during the corresponding pregnancy.

label: Use of intrauterine device
definition: Intrauterine devices (IUD) are commonly used for contraception. IUD complications are rare, but include perforation, pelvic infection, expulsion, missing strings, and difficult IUD removal.

label: History of recent central venous catheter
definition: A past medical history of a recent central venous catheter (CVC). A CVC is an indwelling device inserted into a large, central vein (most commonly the internal jugular, subclavian, or femoral) and advanced until the terminal lumen resides within the inferior vena cava, superior vena cava, or right atrium. CVCs can be a necessary producre for critically ill patients with indications such as total parenteral nutrition administration, dialysis, plasmapheresis, medication administration, and hemodynamic monitoring, and to facilitate further complex interventions such as transvenous pacemaker placement. Complications include arrhythmia, central vein stenosis, and sepsis.

label: History of total parenteral nutrition dependence
definition: A past medical history of a recent depence on total parenteral nutrition (TPN), which refers to intravenously administered nutrition being the only source of nutrition the patient is receiving.

label: Pain alleviated by testicle elevation
definition: This refers to testicular pain that is lessened or made more bearable by elevation of the testicle.

label: Abdominal wall mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the abdominal wall (the skin, fascia, and muscle encases the abdominal cavity and viscera). The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Tympanic membrane bulging
definition: The tympanic membrane protrudes (swells outwards). This feature may be observed with otoscopy.

label: Ear pain exacerbated by manipulating tragus or pinna
definition: Applies to pain of the ear that is worsened, aggravated, or exacerbated by touching or moving the tragus or pinna.

label: Lateral neck mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the side of the neck. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Occipital location
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in the occiput (back part of the head).

label: Anterior neck swelling
definition: Abormal enlargement of the front part of the neck owing to accumulation of fluid.

label: Uvular swelling
definition: Abnormal enlargement of the uvula related to an abnormal accumulation of fluid.

label: Purulent drainage from Stensen duct
definition: Flow of pus (purulence) from the Stensen duct. The Stensen duct is also known as the parotid duct and is the route that saliva takes from the major salivary gland (parotid gland) to the mouth.

label: History of gastric bypass surgery
definition: History of having received gastric bypass surgery. This is a procedure that reduces the functional volume of the stomach and is used to treat morbid obesity.

label: Triggered by volatile organic compounds
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to volatile organic compounds (VOCs), which comprise various organic chemicals which are released as gases from different liquids or solids.

label: History of radiation therapy
definition: A medical history of having undergone radiation therapy, which is a treatment that uses ionizing radiation for purposes such as the control the growth of malignant cells in cancer treatment.

label: Absent otoacoustic emissions
definition: Failure to record otoacoustic emissions (OAE), i.e., sounds generated from the cochlea in response to an acoustic stimulus and transmitted across the middle ear to the external ear canal.

label: Thickened tympanic membrane
definition: The tympanic membrane (eardrum, myringa) is a thin, semitransparent, oval membrane, approximately 1 cm in diameter, that separates the external acoustic meatus from the tympanic cavity. Thickening refers to an increase of the dimension across the membrane.

label: Filum terminale lipoma
definition: Filum terminale lipomas (FTLs) are a type of lumbosacral lipoma in which the fat is entirely within the filum terminale and separate from the conus medullaris.

label: Low tetrahydrocortisol (THF) plus 5-alpha-THF/tetrahydrocortisone (THE) ratio
definition: The relative concentration of tetrahydrocortisol plus 5-alpha-tetrahydrocortisol relative to that of tetrahydrocortisone is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Anti-soluble liver antigen/liver pancreas antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against soluble liver antigen.

label: Anti-thrombospondin type I domain-containing 7A antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against thrombospondin type I domain-containing 7A.

label: Antisperm antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against sperm antigens.

label: Decreased circulating ficolin 3 concentration
definition: Concentration of ficolin 3 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Seminal vesicle cyst
definition: A cyst (sac-like mass that may contain serous liquid or semisolid material) caused by distention of the seminal vesicle due to atresia of the ejaculatory duct.

label: Silica dust exposure
definition: History of exposure to respirable crystalline silica (SiO2).

label: Anti-osteoprotegerin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against osteoprotegerin.

label: History of adrenalectomy
definition: A past medical history of having had a surgical procedure to remove the adrenal glands.

label: Elevated mitochondrial citrate synthase synthase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme mitochondrial citrate synthase (EC:2.3.3.1) in muscle tissue is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced muscle lactate dehydrogenase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme lactate dehdrogenase (LHD; 1.1.1.27) in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. LDH catalyzes the conversion of pyruvate to lactate and back, as it converts NAD+ to NADH and back.

label: Reduced muscle phosphoglycerate mutase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme Phosphoglycerate mutase (PGM) in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. PGM is an enzyme that catalyzes step 8 of glycolysis (EC 5.4.2.11).

label: Reduced muscle phosphorylase kinase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme muscle phosphorylase kinase (PhK) in muscle tissue below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced 3-beta-hydroxysteroid-delta-5-desaturase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of 3-beta-hydroxysteroid-delta-5-desaturase, also known as Sterol C5-desaturase (EC 1.3.3.2), or SC5D below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced hepatic glucose-6-phosphatase activity
definition: Activity of glucose-6-phosphatase (EC 3.1.3.9) in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced hepatic glucose-6-phosphate translocase activity
definition: Activity of glucose-6-phosphate translocase in liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: Cerebrospinal fluid erythrocytes
definition: The presence of red blood cells (RBCs) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). The CSF normally does not contain RBCs (erythrocytes).

label: Elevated CSF cholestanol concentration
definition: The concentration of cholestanol in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal. Cholestanol is the 5-alpha-dihydro derivative of cholesterol.

label: Elevated CSF apolipoprotein B concentration
definition: The concentration of apolipoprotein B in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF myelin basic protein concentration
definition: The concentration of myelin basic protein in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced CSF pyridoxal-5'-phosphate concentration
definition: The concentration of pyridoxal-5'-phosphate in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF thymine concentration
definition: The concentration of thymine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF 5-hydroxymethyluracil concentration
definition: The concentration of 5-hydroxymethyluracil in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF N-carbamyl-beta-aminoisobutyric acid concentration
definition: The concentration of N-carbamyl-beta-aminoisobutyric acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF N-carbamyl-beta-alanine concentration
definition: The concentration of N-carbamyl-beta-alanine in the cerebrospinal fluid is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF dihydrouracil concentration
definition: The concentration of dihydrouracil in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF dihydrothymine concentration
definition: The concentration of dihydrothymine in the cerebrospinal fluid is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating Angiotensin-converting enzyme concentration
definition: Concentration of angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Decreased 3-hydroxyisobutyrate dehydrogenase activity
definition: The activity of 3-hydroxyisobutyrate dehydrogenase in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating 3-hydroxyisobutyryl-CoA hydrolase activity
definition: The activity of 3-hydroxyisobutyryl-CoA hydrolase in the blood corculation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced HMG-CoA lyase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl coenzyme A lyase (HMG CoA lyase) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced circulating acyl-CoA oxidase activity
definition: The activity of acyl-CoA oxidase activity in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating xanthine oxidase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme xanthine oxidase (EC 1.17.3.2) below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced methylmalonate semialdehyde dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: The activity of methylmalonate semialdehyde dehydrogenase ( EC 1.2.1.27) in cultured fibroblasts is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Pharyngeal mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the pharynx (i.e., the throat, the space that connects the nose and mouth to the larynx and esophagus). The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Positive stool occult blood test
definition: The presence of hidden (occult) blood in the stool.

label: Painful defecation
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort that occurs when passing stool.

label: Recent history of caustic substance ingestion
definition: Medical history of a recent ingestion of a caustic substance, i.e., a highly acidic or alkaline chemicals that can cause severe burns to the mouth and digestive tract when swallowed.

label: Delayed passage of meconium
definition: Failure to pass meconium (the first stool following birth) in the first 48 hours of life.

label: Single second heart sound
definition: The second sound can remain single throughout the respiratory cycle due to either absence of one component or to synchronous occurrence of the two components. Since the pulmonary vascular impedance increases with age, many normal patients over age 50 have a single S2 or at most a narrow physiologic split on inspiration because P2 occurs early. A single second sound, however, is usually due to inability to auscultate a relatively soft pulmonic component. Such inability is rare in healthy infants, children, and young adults and is uncommon even in older persons under good auscultatory conditions using a rigid stethoscopic diaphragm.

label: Elevated aortic transvalvular pressure gradient
definition: The gradient (in this case, drop) in pressure across the aortic valve is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Prosthetic heart valve
definition: A past surgical history of the implanation of an artificial heart valve.

label: Failure to increase oxygen saturation on hyperoxia test
definition: Hyperoxia test is the initial method to distinguish critical congenital heart disease (CCHD) from pulmonary disease. The test consists in measuring an arterial blood gas at room air and 100% inspired oxygen after 10 minutes. Neonates with congenital heart disease are usually not able to increase PaO2 above 100 mm Hg during 100% oxygen administration. In patients with pulmonary disease, PaO2 generally increased greater than or equal to 100 mm Hg with 100% oxygen as ventilation-perfusion discrepancies are overcome. A positive result indicates the cardiac origin and further cardiac workup is indicated to rule out CCHD.

label: High-set nipples
definition: Placement of the nipples at a higher than normal location.

label: Decreased muscle caveolin-3 level
definition: The amount of calveolin-3 in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Splenic necrosis
definition: Cell dealth (necrosis) located in the spleen.

label: Carcinoid tumor of the pancreas
definition: A carcinoid tumor of the pancreas (CTP) is a rare neuroendocrine tumor arising from the serotonin-secreting cells (enterochromaffin or Kultscitsky's cells).

label: Elevated circulating dihydroxyphenylacetic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of dihydroxyphenylacetic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Inappropriately low concentration of acetoacetate
definition: Lower than appropriate concentration of acetoacetate in states such as hypoglycemia in which the normal response would be to elevate acetoacetate.

label: Inappropriately low concentration of beta-hydroxybutyrate
definition: Lower than appropriate concentration of beta-hydroxybutyrate in states such as hypoglycemia in which the normal response would be to elevate acetoacetate.

label: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxybutyryl-carnitine concentration
definition: Concentration of 3-hydroxybutyryl-carnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxyamide concentration
definition: The concentration of 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxyamide in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating tumor necrosis factor alpha concentration
definition: The concentration of tumor necrosis factor alpha in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating pyrimidine 5-prime-nucleotidase activity
definition: The activity of concentration of pyrimidine 5-prime-nucleotidase (EC 3.1.3.5) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Diminished prolactin response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation
definition: The increase in prolactin concentration (PRL) following stimulation with thyrotropin (thyrdoid releasing hormone) as compared to baseline PRL concentration is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating complement component 1s concentration
definition: The concentration of complement component 1s (C1s) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating cortisol-binding globulin concentration
definition: The concentration of cortisol-binding globulin in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating thyroglobulin concentration
definition: The concentration of thyroglobulin in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor concentration
definition: The concentration of granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF D-2-hydroxyglutaric acid concentration
definition: The concentration of D-2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Esophageal mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the esophagus. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Synovial fluid crystals
definition: The presence of crystals (microscopic solids that form distinct lattices, with definable fixed angles, faces, walls) in the joint (synovial) fluid.

label: Enlarged gastric folds
definition: Giant gastric folds are recognized at endoscopy as an increase in the size of the gastric rugae and a lack of flattening.

label: Gastric intraepithelial lymphocytosis
definition: The count of lymphocytes located in the epithelial layer of the gastric mucosa is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Small intestinal intraepithelial lymphocytosis
definition: The count of lymphocytes located in the epithelial layer of the mucosa of the small intestine is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Fetal lung hyperechogenicity
definition: Increased response (echo) of lung tissue of a fetus observed on prenatal sonography. Increased echo response is conventially displayed as a higher degree of brightness.

label: Necrotizing vasculitis
definition: A histopathological finding characterized by inflammation of the arterial and/or capillary and/or venous blood vessels, leading to a change in the vascular wall as a whole.

label: Abnormal proximal convoluted tubule morphology
definition: Any structural anomaly of the proximal convoluted tubule, which is the first tubular component of the nephron and arises as a continuation of the Bowman space from the tubular pole of the renal corpuscle. The proximal convoluted tubule is located within the renal cortex.

label: Demonstration of Leishmania in tissue
definition: Presence of Leishmania, a parasitic protozoan, in a tissue specimen. Leishmania is responsible for leishmaniasis.

label: Pneumocystis cysts in respiratory secretions
definition: Demonstration of cysts of Pneumocystis (a genus of related fungal species) in respiratory secretions such as nasopharyngeal secretions or pleural fluid.

label: Spinal cord granuloma
definition: An aggregation of macrophages (forming in response to chronic inflammation) localized in or on the spinal cord.

label: Impaired folate absorption
definition: Reduced ability to absorb folate in the diet. This finding can be measured by a folic acid loading test in which blood concentration of folate is measured after oral administration of folic acid.

label: History of recent plant thorn skin puncture
definition: A history of a plant skin puncture preceding the current presenting condition by hours, days, or weeks.

label: Absent circulating immunoglobulin kappa chain
definition: Nondetectable kappa chain in the blood circulation.

label: Pseudoglioma
definition: A circumscribed whitish-yellow mass in the posterior chamber associated with retinal folds and sometimes retinal detachment and is said to resemble a retinal glioma.

label: Papillary dermal edema
definition: Swelling due to fluid acculuation of the papillary dermis.

label: Fetal tachycardia
definition: The number of beats per minute (bpm) of the fetal heart is above the upper limit of the normal for the gestational age. Fetal tachycardia is thus defined as a heart rate greater than 160-180 bpm.

label: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxykynurenine level
definition: The amount of 3-hydroxykynurenine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: 2-oxoadipic aciduria
definition: The amount of 2-oxoadipic acid in the urine, normaliyed for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating methionine sulfoxide concentration
definition: The concentration of methionine sulfoxide in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating pipecolic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of pipecolic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary pipecolic acid level
definition: The amount of pipecolic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF saccharopine concentration
definition: Concentration of saccharopine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating glycylproline concentration
definition: Concentration in the bloodstream of glycylproline above the upper limit of normal. Glycylproline is a dipeptide composed of glycine and proline, and is an end product of collagen metabolism that is further cleaved by prolidase (EC 3.4.13.9).

label: Elevated circulating octanoylcarnitine concentration
definition: Concentration of octanoylcarnitine (C8:0) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating decanoylcarnitine concentration
definition: Concentration of decanoylcarnitine (C10:0) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: 2--hydroxyphenylacetic aciduria
definition: Increased concentration of 2-hydroxyphenylacetic acid in the urine.

label: 4-hydroxyphenyllactic aciduria
definition: Amount of 4-hydroxyphenyllactic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF beta-alanine concentration
definition: The concentration of beta-alanine present in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating 2-aminoadipic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of 2-aminoadipic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary N-carbamoyl-beta-alanine level
definition: The amount of N-carbamoyl-beta-alanine present in urine, when adjusted for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF cystathionine concentration
definition: Concentration of cystathionine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary gamma-glutamylphenylalanine level
definition: The amount of gamma-glutamylphenylalanine in the urine, when normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating aspartylglucosamine concentration
definition: Concentration of aspartylglucosamine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary saccharopine level
definition: The amount of saccharopine in the urine, when normalized to urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Tectal plate enlargement
definition: Abnormal increase in size of the tectal plate (also known as the tectum or the quadrigeminal plate). The tectum is the dorsal portion of the midbrain (brainstem).

label: Retroperitoneal mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the retroperitoneal region. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Focal T1 hyperintense brainstem lesion
definition: A lighter than expected T1 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the brainstem.

label: Subchondral fracture
definition: A type of fracture that occurs in the trabecular cancellous bone just beneath the subchondral bone plate without disruption of the articular surface.

label: Deep neck abscess
definition: An abscess (i.e., a circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris) localized in the area surrounded by the deep fascia of the neck including the pharynx, larynx, trachea, upper esophagus, thyroid, and parathyroid glands. Infections of pharyngeal, tonsillar, and laryngeal origin affect this space, which includes the parapharyngeal and retropharyngeal spaces.

label: Epiglottic enlargement
definition: Anlarged and edematous epiglottis. This sign can be observed on a lateral radiograph of the neck and it suggests a diagnosis of acute infectious epiglottitis.

label: Prevertebral space enlargement
definition: Increase in the anterior posterior dimension of the prevertebral space, which is located in the neck region between the anterior part of the cervical spine and the deep layer of the deep cervical fascia running between the transverse processes of the spine.

label: Third cranial nerve thickening
definition: Increase in diameter of the third cranial nerve (oculomotor nerve). This feature can be observed by magnetic resonance imaging and may be accompanied by contrast enhancement.

label: Elevated tissue sphingomyelin concentration
definition: Concentration of sphoingomyelin in tissues above the upper limit of normal.

label: History of recent iodated contrast medium administration
definition: Medical history of recent iodinated or radioiodine contrast use.

label: Difficulty passing nasogastric tube
definition: Difficulty inserting a nasogastric tube (NGT), a flexible plastic tube that is placed through the nose and esophagus into the stomach and used to administer drugs or for feeding. There are certain circumstances that may make NGT insertion difficult. They are esophageal narrowing, comatose or intubated patients, and patients who have sustained severe facial or skull injuries.

label: Persistent falcine venous sinus
definition: A falcine sinus that does not involute but persists beyond birth is defined as a persistent falcine sinus. In the 20-mm embryo stage, the primitive falx cerebri contains the sagittal plexus, a meshwork of anastomotic venous channels from which the superior sagittal sinus and straight sinus are thought to develop. A persistent falcine sinus represents a persistent channel of the caudal anastomotic loops of the sagittal plexus.

label: Penis uncircumcised
definition: A medical history in a male of not having been circumcized.

label: History of facial cosmetic use
definition: A medical history of use of facial makeup.

label: Snapping sensation at metacarpophalangeal joint
definition: A feeling of clicking or snapping at the knuckle (metacarpophalangeal joint) upon extension of flexion of the finger.

label: Forearm pain
