definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the forearm.

label: Rotational fracture
definition: A type of displaced fracture in which there has been a rotation of the distal fracture fragment in relation to the proximal portion.

label: Localized over bony prominences
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated on the skin in areas where bones are close to the surface (bony prominences).

label: History of compressive footwear
definition: A past medical history of wearing tight shoes, toe-box shoes, or high heel shoes.

label: Decreased skin turgor
definition: Reduced skin turgor means reduced elastic recoil of the skin to its normal contour after being pinched in a fold.

label: Recent foraged mushroom consumption
definition: Medical history of recently eating wild mushrooms.

label: Proximal to distal progression
definition: Refers to symptomatology that begins in the proximal limbs and subsequently affects the distal limbs.

label: Autonomic-voluntary dissociation of facial movements
definition: The selective paralysis of voluntary fascio-pharyngo-glosso-masticatory movements with preservation of reflexive and automatic functions is referred to as autonomic-voluntary dissociation, which is a distinctive feature of Anterior opercular syndrome (also known as Foix-Chavany-Marie syndrome).

label: Jaw mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the jaw. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Excessive nocturnal light exposure
definition: Exposure to continuous light at night, including night-shift work or a nocturnal lifestyle.

label: Menstruating female between menarche and menopause
definition: Past medical history of a woman who is menstruating, i.e., not premenstrual or post-menopause.

label: Preterm premature rupture of membranes
definition: PPROM (preterm premature rupture of membranes) occurs at less than 37 weeks of gestation. PPROM can happen spontaneously, during preterm labor, or following a procedure such as amniocentesis.

label: History of abdominal surgery
definition: A past medical history that indicates that the patient had a surgical procedure involving the abdomen.

label: Thickened Descemet membrane
definition: The thickness of the Descement membrane is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Incomplete right bundle branch block
definition: Right bundle branch block (RBBB) represents an abnormality in the intraventricular electrical conduction system of the human heart, generating enlarged QRS and modified vectors on the electrocardiogram (ECG). Incomplete RBBB (IRBBB) is defined by (i) QRS duration between 110 and 120 ms in adults; (ii) rsr, rsR, or rSR in leads V1 or V2. The R or r deflection is usually wider than the initial R wave. In a minority of patients, a wide and often notched R wave pattern may be seen in leads V1 and/or V2; (iii) S wave of greater duration than R wave or greater than 40 ms in leads I and V6 in adults; and (iv) Normal R peak time in leads V5 and V6 but greater than 50 ms in lead V1. The first 3 criteria should be present to make the diagnosis. When a pure dominant R wave with or without a notch is present in V1, criterion 4 should be satisfied.

label: Perimenopausal onset
definition: Onset of signs or symptoms of disease during the period of a woman's life shortly before the occurrence of the menopause.

label: Postmenopausal onset
definition: Onset of signs or symptoms of disease during the period of a woman's life after the occurrence of the menopause.

label: Spastic monoplegia
definition: Spastic weakness found in only one upper or lower extremity.

label: Mosaic attenuation pattern in lung
definition: Mosaic attenuation pattern in the lung is a term used to describe regions of differing pulmonary attenuation on CT imaging. It is a non-specific finding, although is associated with several conditions such as obstructive small airway disease, occlusive vascular disease (in which case is called mosaic perfusion pattern), pulmonary edema, and parenchymal diseases.

label: Elevated aldosterone:renin ratio
definition: The ratio of aldosterone concentration to renin concentration is above the upper limit of normal. If aldosterone is expressed in ng/dl and plasma renin activity is expressed as ng/ml/hr, then values above 20 with aldosterone level above 15 are considered indicative of primary aldosteronism.

label: Meteorism
definition: An increase in the gas content inside the bowel associated with distension of the abdomen and hydroaeric noises. The most common symptom of meteorism is a bloated sensation. It may be associated with abdominal discomfort. Some individuals may also complain of a distended stomach and excessive belching and/or passage of flatus.

label: Failure to elevate ammonia on ischemic exercise
definition: Normal subjects display an increase in the concentration of ammonia in the blood following an ischemic exercise test. This term refers to an increase in ammonia that is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Labile Hypertension
definition: Frequent fluctuations of blood pressure between normal and high levels, changing more dramatically than normal.

label: Absent axon flare response after intradermal histamine injection
definition: The axon reflex (also known as the flare response) is a response that is stimulated by peripheral nerves of the body that travels away from the nerve cell body and branches to stimulate target organs. In the human skin, there are three different phenomena mediated by axon reflex mechanism; flare, sweating and pilomotion. Stroking or intradermal injection of histamine or substance P into the human skin pro- duces widespread vasodilatation (flare) and plasma extravasation (wheal). This term refers to the failure of intradermal hista injection to elicit flare.

label: Reduced sympathoneural responses to the cold pressor test
definition: Response to the cold pressor test below the lower limit of normal. The cold pressor test is a simple and validated test in which the subject immerses one hand or foot into ice water for 1 to 3 minutes while blood pressure (BP) and heart rate are monitored. The cold stimulus activates afferent sensory pathways that, in turn, trigger a sympathetic response resulting in an increase in BP.

label: Positive stool Giardia antigen test
definition: Fecal analysis for Giardia antigen is abnormal. Tests include direct fluorescent-antibody (DFA), which detects intact organisms, and enzyme immunoassays (EIAs), which detect soluble stool antigens.

label: Excessive blood loss during delivery
definition: Loss of a substantial amount of blood during delivery (some definitions stipulate 1000 ml or more), typically associated with manifestations such as low blood pressure, a rapid heart rate, dizziness, light-headedness, fatigue, and weakness.

label: Cardiac valve vegetations
definition: Endocarditis infection occurs along the edges of the heart valves. Damage to the cardiac endothelium followed by platelet and fibrin deposition results in a sterile lesion known as nonbacterial thrombotic endocarditis (NBTE) or vegetation. Microbes entering the bloodstream via routine or invasive procedures adhere to the vegetation and are engulfed in an outer meshwork of fibrin and platelets. Subsequent rapid microbial multiplication in a protected area of impaired host defense leads to vegetation growth and continuous bacteremia.

label: Thoracic cage flatness
definition: The anteroposterior dimension of the chest on the lateral radiograph is often relatively narrow compared with the chest width on the frontal radiograph.

label: Absent zona pellucida
definition: Lack of the oocyte extracellular matrix region (zona pellucida). This feature can be observed following follicular aspiration (retrieval of eggs for fertility treatments).

label: Umbilical cord prolapse
definition: The presence of the umbilical cord (UC) between the fetal presenting part and the cervix, regardless of the membrane status (intact or ruptured). Descent of the UC through the cervix is essential for diagnosing cord prolapse. It can be either overt (past the presenting part) or occult (alongside the presenting part).

label: Increased ratio of deoxypyridinoline to pyridinoline cross-links in urine
definition: The relative concentration of deoxypyridinoline (Dpyr) to that of pyridinoline (Pyr) cross-links in urine is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary thymine level
definition: The amount of thymine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary indoleacetic acid level
definition: The amount of indoleacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced hepatic phosphorylase kinase activity
definition: Activity of phosphorylase kinase in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal. Phosphorylase kinase (PhK) has a major regulatory role in the breakdown of glycogen. The enzyme PhK comprises four copies each of four subunits, encoded by PHKA1, PHKA2, PHKB, and PHKG.

label: Reduced hepatic ornithine transcarbamylase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of ornithine transcarbamylase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary quinolinic acid level
definition: The amount of quinolinic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Quinolinic acids is a pyridinedicarboxylic acid that is pyridine substituted by carboxy groups at positions 2 and 3. It is a metabolite of tryptophan.

label: Rectal duplication
definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by an additional rectum that is typically lined with intestinal mucosa with one or more cell types of the gastrointestinal tract overlying submucosa and smooth muscle layer.

label: Thinned small intestinal mucosa
definition: Abrnormal reduction in the height of the mucosa of the small intestine. The mucosa is arranged in regular circular folds (the circular valves of Kerckrin), the mucosal surface is covered with small projections called villi, which are slender, about 1.5-2 mm long projections of the mucosa into the lumen. In between the villi are the crypts. This term refers to a pathological thinning of these structures.

label: Seminal vesicle hypoplasia
definition: A congenital anomaly characterized by underdevelopment of one or both seminal vesicles, which are the two small glands that store and produce the majority of the fluid that makes up semen.

label: Small fetal abdominal circumference
definition: The distance around the abdomen of a fetus, generally as measured by prenatal sonography, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Prenatal flattened diaphragm
definition: The diaphragm normally projects up into the thoracic cavity. In the presence of malformations such as enlarged lungs, the diaphragm may appear abnormally flat or even everted (with the middle of the diaphragm projecting downwards into the abdominal cavity).

label: Snowflake effect in amniotic cavity
definition: Dense floating particles in amniotic fluid, said to resemble snowflakes. This finding can result from shedding of the epidermis in conditions such as Harlequin ichthyosis.

label: Thickened mitral valve cusp
definition: An abnormally increased thickness of a leaflet of the mitral valve.

label: Antiparietal cell antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against parietal cell antigens.

label: Anti-intrinsic factor antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against intrinsic factor.

label: Anti-human immunodeficiency virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV).

label: Anti-polio virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of poliovirus.

label: Anti-NR2A antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the N-Methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptor NR2A subunit.

label: Antistreptolysin O antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against streptolysin O.

label: Reduced tissue tissue AICAR transformylase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of 5-aminoimidazole-4-carboxamide ribonucleotide formyltransferase; EC 2.1.2.3) a in a tissue is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Ameliorated by gastric acid-reducing therapy
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with an agent that reduces gastric acidity such as proton pump inhibitors, histamine receptor blockers,omeprazole, esomeprazole, dexlansoprazole, pantoprazole, lansoprazole, famotidine, or ranitidine.

label: Anti-coagulation factor antibody positivity
definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against a coagulation factor.

label: Tachyphagia
definition: Excessively rapid eating of food.

label: Reduced tissue argininosuccinate synthetase activity
definition: Concentration of argininosuccinate synthetase (EC 6.3.4.5) in body tissues is below the lower limit of normal. Clinically, argininosuccinate synthetase is measured in the liver or in cultered skin fibroblasts.

label: Reduced aspartoacylase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of aspartoacylase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts. Aspartoacylase (EC 3.5.1.15), also called aminoacylase-2, is an enzyme that hydrolyzes N-acetyl-L-aspartic acid (NAA) to aspartate and acetate.

label: Reduced malonyl-CoA decarboxylase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of malonyl-CoA decarboxylase (EC 4.1.1.9) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue medium-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of medium-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (EC 1.3.8.7;MCAD) in tissues is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced cystathionine beta-synthase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of cystathionine beta-synthase (EC 4.2.1.22) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced muscle glycogen phosphorylase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme glycogen phosphorylase in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. Glycogen phosphorylase (EC 2.4.1.1) is also known as amylophosphorylase, muscle phosphorylase a and b, polyphosphorylase, and myophosphorylase.

label: Reduced muscle 6-phosphofructokinase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme 6-phosphofructokinase in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. 6-phosphofructokinase (EC 2.7.1.11) is also known as phosphofructokinase I and phosphohexokinase. The PFKM gene encodes the muscle isoform of phosphofructokinase. PFK catalyzes the irreversible conversion of fructose-6-phosphate to fructose-1,6-bisphosphate and is a key regulatory enzyme in glycolysis.

label: Reduced tissue alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.50) below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. It is also known as alpha-acetylglucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-glucosaminidase, and alpha-D-2-acetamido-2-deoxyglucosidase.

label: Reduced succinyl-CoA:3-oxoacid-CoA transferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of succinyl-CoA:3-oxoacid-CoA transferase (SCOT, or OXCT1; EC 2.8.3.5) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Blunted aldosterone response to aldosterone suppression test
definition: A non-suppressible aldosterone excess, defined as an abnormal result of one of any four suppression tests. These tests use oral sodium loading, oral fludrocortisone, oral captopril, or saline infusion to suppress aldosterone secretion.

label: Flank mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling in the flank, which is the fleshy part of the side of the body between the ribs and the hip.

label: Synovial cyst
definition: A fluid-filled sac or pouch-like mass that is a distention of a preexisting bursa in a joint, tendon sheaths or bursae. Synovial cysts contain synovial fluid and are lined by synovial membrane.

label: Brown pigmentation of the conjunctiva
definition: Deposition of brown pigmentation in the conjunctiva.

label: Gastrocnemius contracture
definition: Limitation of simultaneous ankle dorsiflexion and knee extension during mid-stance of gait.

label: Central thinning of the outer nuclear layer of the retina
definition: Reduced thickness of the outer nuclear layer in the middle region of the retina. The outer nuclear layer (ONL) of the retina contains the nuclei of the cone and rod photoreceptors. Loss of the cellular machinery found in these nuclei causes irreparable loss of the photoreceptors and the capacity for visual function. This feature can be appreciated by directional optical coherence tomography.

label: Sonographic renal salt and pepper pattern
definition: Heterogeneous, increased parenchymal echogenicity. This imaging appearance is caused by multiple tiny cysts smaller than or just approaching the size necessary for detection, which disrupt the echo pattern without being clearly distinguishable, and appear as white grains on renal ultrasound, mainly in a subcapsular location.

label: Ductus venosus agenesis with intrahepatic drainage
definition: A form of ductus venosus agenesis in which the umbilical vein connects via the portal sinus to the portal venous system (PVS) without giving rise to the ductus venosus. In some cases an intrahepatic shunt from a portal to a hepatic vein can be detected prenatally. This variant has been reported to have a favorable prognosis.

label: Ductus venosus agenesis with extrahepatic drainage and liver bypass
definition: A form of ductus venosus agenesis in which umbilical vein does not connect to the portal venous system. The liver is bypassed and the umbilical vein drains into a systemic vein such as the inferior vena cava. This variant has been reported to have an unfavorable prognosis due to a presumed association with congestive heart failure and hydrops.

label: Elevated circulating D-glyceric concentration
definition: The concentration of D-gyceric acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF D-glyceric acid concentration
definition: The concentration of D-carboxylic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Ameliorated by riboflavin
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingestion of riboflavin (Vitamin B2).

label: Increased circulating interleukin 1beta concentration
definition: An increased concentration of interleukin-1beta in the blood circulation.

label: Reduced neutrophil myeloperoxidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of myeloperoxidase (EC 1.11.1.7) as measured in neutrophils is below the limits of normal.

label: Jugular foramen stenosis
definition: Reduction in diameter of the jugular foramen, an opening in the base of the skull that is located behind the carotid canal and is formed by the temporal bone and the occipital bone. The inferior petrosal sinus, three cranial nerves, the sigmoid sinus, and meningeal arteries pass through the jugular foramen.

label: Intramural intestinal gas
definition: The presence of extraluminal gas within the bowel wall.

label: Delayed scintigraphic gallbladder filling
definition: Hepatobiliary scintigraphy is a nuclear imaging technique that permits evaluation of the liver and biliary system for acute and chronic cholecystitis, biliary atresia, biliary obstruction, and post-surgical biliary leak. With this investigation, a radiotracer is administered intravenously, bound to albumin, transported to the liver, and excreted into the biliary system. This term refers to a longer than normal time for the radiotracer to be visualized in the gallbladder. This finding may be a sign of chronic gallbladder disease or partial obstruction of the common bile duct.

label: Pancreatic arteriovenous malformation
definition: Pancreatic arteriovenous malformation is defined as an abnormal vascular net, developed from one or more feeding arteries and enlarged early draining veins, creating an arteriovenous shunting.

label: Anti-perilipin-1 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against perilipin-1 (PLIN1).

label: Splenic calcification
definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the spleen.

label: Short esophagus
definition: Abnormal reduction in the length of the esophagus.

label: Gastric perforation
definition: A full-thickness injury of the wall of the stomach.

label: Gastric volvulus
definition: A gastric volvulus occurs when the stomach rotates on itself at least 180 degrees along its transverse or longitudinal axis.

label: Elevated circulating soluble CD163 concentration
definition: The concentration of Soluble CD163 in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive cold agglutinin test
definition: Cold agglutinin are erythrocyte antibodies which possess the property of agglutinating red blood cells at temperatures of below 37 degrees C, this phenomenon is reversible after heating.

label: Anti-D-L antibody positivity
definition: The presence of Donath-Landsteiner (D-L) autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum.

label: Non-glucose reducing substance in urine
definition: Abnormal result for this screening test for urinary reducing substances including glucose, fructose, galactose, lactose, pentose and maltose, as well as amino acids, cysteine, tyrosine, homogentisic acid, ketone bodies, ascorbic acid and many drugs. This term is applied if the urine stick test for glucose was negative (normal).

label: Elevated urinary succinylaminoimidazole carboxamide riboside level
definition: Presence of succinylaminoimidazole carboxamide riboside (SAICAr). SAICAr is a toxic intermediate metabolite of purine synthesis.

label: Elevated urine hyaluronic acid level
definition: Excessive amount of hyaluronic acid in urine.

label: Elevated urinary methylmalonylcarnitine level
definition: The amount of methylmalonylcarnitine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine trihydroxycholestanoic acid level
definition: Presence of trihydroxycholestanoic acid in the urine. Trihydroxycholestanoic acid is an intermediate in the biosynthesis of cholic acid. Elevated plasma levels of trihydroxycholestanoic acid have been found in patients with Zellweger syndrome.

label: Elevated CSF ammonia concentration
definition: The concentration of amonia in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive CSF VDRL test
definition: An abnormal (positive) result of the Venereal Disease Research Laboratory (VDRL) test performed in cerebrospinal fluid (CSF), suggesting past or present neurosyphilis.

label: Elevated CSF guanidinoacetic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: CSF oligoclonal immunoglobulin G bands
definition: Oligoclonal immunoglobulin G (IgG) bands (OCBs) are a useful diagnostic tool to detect a central humoral response. In particular, cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)-restricted OCBs represent a hallmark of multiple sclerosis (MS).

label: Decreased CSF 3-methoxy-4-hydroxyphenylglycolaldehyde concentration
definition: The concentration of 3-methoxy-4-hydroxyphenylglycolaldehyde in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF alpha-crystallin B chain concentration
definition: The concentration of alpha-crystallin B chain in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced CSF creatine concentration
definition: The concentration of creatine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating protein Z concentration
definition: The concentration of protein Z in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating 27-hydroxycholesterol concentration
definition: The concentration of 27-hydroxycholesterol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating lysophosphatidylcholine concentration
definition: The concentration of lysophosphatidylcholines in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating insulin-like growth factor 2 concentration
definition: The concentration of insulin-like growth factor 2 (IGF2) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal. IGF2 is a peptide hormone regulating various cellular processes such as proliferation and apoptosis.

label: Decreased circulating nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide concentration
definition: The concentration of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Diminished circulating reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH) concentration
definition: The concentration of reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration
definition: The concentration of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration
definition: The concentration of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is outside of the limits of normal.

label: Reduced CSF asparagine concentration
definition: The concentration of asparagine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Pancreatic mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the pancreas. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Small intestine mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the small intestine. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Facial nerve compression
definition: Impingement of another object such as a blood vessel upon the facial nerve, causing it to lose volume in the compressed region.

label: Pulmonary perfusion defect
definition: Lack of blood perfusion in a specific area of the lung. Pulmonary ventilation (V) and Perfusion (Q) scan, also known as lung V/Q scan, is a nuclear test that uses the perfusion scan to delineate the blood flow distribution and the ventilation scan to measure airflow distribution in the lungs.

label: Ectopic ureteral orifice
definition: Drainage of the ureter on one or both sides into an abnormal location. Normally the ureter drains via the internal ureteral orifice at the trigone of the urinary bladder. Ectopic ureteral orifice can be either intravesical (bladder neck) or, more often, extravesical. Ectopia in women is more frequently found in the urethra and the vaginal vestibule; much less frequently in vagina and in uterus. In men it is mostly found in the posterior urethra; in the male genital tract is very rare.

label: Duplicate uterine cervix
definition: A congenital developmental defect characterized by the presence of two cervices on the uterus.

label: Intradural spinal lipoma
definition: Intradural spinal lipoma (ISL) constitutes approximately 1% of all spinal tumors and is usually associated with lumbo-sacral spinal dysraphism. ISLs unassociated with spinal dysraphism are rare with only a few cases being reported in literature. They are seen in children and young adults and are situated on the posterior aspect of the spinal cord in the cervico-thoracic or thoracic regions. They represent intradural, subpial, juxtamedullary lesions.

label: T2 hyperintense cerebellar lesion
definition: A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the cerebellum. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the cerebellum.

label: Inferior vena cava obstruction
definition: Physical invasion or compression of the inferior vena cava by a pathological process or by thrombosis within the vein itself.

label: Rheumatoid nodule
definition: A well-demarcated, flesh colored, subcutaneous and usually freely movable lump or mass. Rheumatoid nodules can vary in size from small, pea sized lesions up to the size of a lemon and are most often round. The nodules usually are doughy or firm however and not tender. Typically rheumatoid nodules are distributed over areas of repeated trauma or pressure and occur adjacent to joints on extensor surfaces, such as the elbow, fingers and forearms.

label: Elevated circulating proinsulin concentration
definition: The concentration of proinsulin in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Burning eye sensation
definition: A feeling of stinging or irritation of the eyes.

label: Collarettes
definition: Buildup of waxy flesh-colored scales on the margin of the eyelid.

label: Tympanic membrane bulla
definition: Presence of blisters (bullae) on the tympanic membrane, often accompanied by fever, thickening, and erythematous appearance of the tympanic membrane, decreased or absent light reflex, and decreased mobility.

label: Beard and mustache distribution
definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are located at regions of the male face covered by a beard or mustache.

label: Kerion
definition: Kerion is an erythematous, boggy, tender, often sterile, weeping nodule or plaque with pustules and draining sinuses. Hair in these areas appears lusterless, brittle, and is easily plucked. Kerion can be solitary or multiple but is usually unilateral. Patients with inflammatory tinea barbae may have constitutional symptoms like fever and malaise. Kerion is a coalesced sterile pustule, but occasionally they can get superinfected with cutaneous bacteria and develop regional lymphadenopathy.

label: Truncal location
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the trunk of the body. The trunk is the main part of a person's body, not including the head, legs, or arms.

label: Reduced Acyl-CoA:dihydroxyacetone phosphate acyltransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of acyl-CoA:dihydroxyacetone phosphate acyltransferase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced alkyl-dihydroxyacetonephosphate synthase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of alkyl-dihydroxyacetonephosphate (DHAP) synthase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Glomerular fibronectin deposits
definition: Accumulation of fibronectin in the glomerulus.

label: Renal tubular karyomegaly
definition: Marked enlargement of nuclei observed predominantly in the proximal convoluted tubule cells.

label: Reduced tissue acetyl-CoA carboxylase activity
definition: Activity of acetyl-CoA carboxylase in the tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including liver.

label: Elevated urinary glycolic acid level
definition: The amount of glycolic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine propionic acid level
definition: The amount of propionic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary butyric acid level
definition: The amount of butyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary isovaleric acid level
definition: The amount of isovaleric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
definition: The concentration of alpha-ketoglutarate in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating ghrelin concentration
definition: The concentration of ghrelin in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. Ghrelin is a 28-amino-acid peptide predominantly secreted in the stomach and stimulates appetite and growth hormone (GH) release.

label: Reduced circulating stearoylcarnitine concentration
definition: The concentration of stearoylcarnitine (C18:0) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced urinary iodine level
definition: The amount of iodine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased circulating interleukin 15 concentration
definition: The concentration of interleukin 15 (IL-15) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating squalene concentration
definition: The concentration of squalene in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated blood mercury concentration
definition: The concentration of mercury in the blood is above the upper limit of a guidance value for total blood mercury concentrations that implies possible injurious effects.

label: Elevated blood cadmiun concentration
definition: The concentration of cadmium in the blood is above the upper limit of a guidance value for total blood mercury concentrations that implies possible injurious effects.

label: Elevated thallium concentration
definition: The concentration of thallium in the blood is above the upper limit of a guidance value for total blood mercury concentrations that implies possible injurious effects.

label: Abnormal circulating CC chemokine concentration
definition: The concentration in the blood circulation of a member of the CC chemokine family is outside of normal limits.

label: Decreased CSF asialotransferrin to transferrin ratio
definition: The concentration of asialotransferrin relative to that of transferrin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Anti-desmocollin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmocollin.

label: Occupational exposure to raw nonsynthetic textiles
definition: A history of exposure by inhalation of airborne particles generated during the processing of raw, nonsynthetic textiles, particularly cotton. Classically, exposure to cotton dust during the spinning and manufacturing process causes byssinosis. However, exposure to jute, flax, and hemp fibers has also been implicated in its development.

label: Rokitansky-Aschoff gallbladder sinuses
definition: Localized or diffuse epithelial proliferation with hypertrophy of the muscularis layer and invagination of the mucosa through the muscularis, forming intramural diverticula (i.e., small, bulging pouches in the wall of the gallbladder).

label: Porcelain gallbladder
definition: Porcelain gallbladder refers to the condition in which the inner gallbladder wall is encrusted with calcium. The wall becomes brittle, hard, and often takes on a bluish hue. It is usually found incidentally on plain abdominal x-rays or other imaging because most patients are asymptomatic.

label: Gallbladder adhesions
definition: Strands of scar tissue bands of scar tissue that form an abnormal connection between the gallbladder and another abdominal structure. Adhesions can form followiing gallbladder inflammation (cholecystitis).

label: Bilioduodenal fistula
definition: An abnormal connection between the gallbladder and the duodenum.

label: Cholecyst-enteric fistula
definition: Fistula between the gallbladder and the intestine.

label: Pneumobilia
definition: Accumulation of gas in the biliary tree.

label: Ectopic gallstone
definition: A gallstone located outside of the gallbladder.

label: Sleep drunkeness
definition: Sleep drunkenness refers to the prolonged and pronounced difficulty with awakening from nocturnal sleep and daytime naps. This symptom should be distinguished from the milder and physiologic state of sleep inertia seen even in healthy controls .

label: Mallory bodies
definition: Cytoplasmic hyaline inclusions of hepatocytes that are predominantly filamentous ranging from a diameter of 3 to 24 nm vs. 10 nm of classical IF. Mallory-Denk bodies can be classified as type I (parallels filaments), II (randomly orient filaments), or III (granular and amorphous). Type II occurs in the periphery while type III occurs around the center. MDB occur in ballooned hepatocytes.

label: Sulfur-containing abscess
definition: An abscess containing tiny yellow clumps (sulfur granules), formed by infection with Actinomyces and generally associated with a granulomatous and suppurative infection.

label: Retracted tympanic membrane
definition: A condition in which part of the tympanic membrane is pull backed into the middle ear cavity (also called retraction pocket).

label: Ectopic testis
definition: Localization of the testis in an anatomic location other than the scrotum.

label: Cerebral subcortical cyst
definition: A fluid-filled sac (cyst) in the region below the cortex of the cerebrum. In magnetic resonance imaging, the fluid within the cyst has the same appearance as cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Anti-ADAMTS13 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against A Disintegrin and Metalloprotease with ThromboSpondin type 1 repeats, member 13 (ADAMTS13).

label: Habitual mouth breathing
definition: A tendency to breathe through the mouth. Defined as over 25-30 percent of the air passing through the mouth instead of the nose, mouth breathing often occurs due to upper airway obstruction which reduces the nasal airflow and forces the air to enter completely or partially through oral cavity.

label: Squared off shoulders
definition: An appearance of the shoulders whereby the neck-trapezius angle (angle between the neck and the shoulder) and the angle formed by the shoulder and the arms hanging at the side of the body are both close to 90 degrees. This gives the should the appearance of the corner of a square.

label: Elevated urine mesaconic acid level
definition: The amount of mesaconic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine 3-methyladipic acid level
definition: The amount of 3-methyladipic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine D-lactate level
definition: The amount of D-lactate in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. L-lactate is a familiar molecule to the human body and is also produced in large amounts in human tissues, depending on metabolic conditions. In contrast, D-lactate is produced only in minute quantities in human tissues, and is therefore not detectable in the bloodstream under normal physiological conditions.

label: Elevated CSF alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
definition: The concentration of alpha-ketoglutarate in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine 2,3-dihydroxy-2-methylbutanoic acid level
definition: The amount of 2,3-dihydroxy-2-methylbutanoic acidin the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Fetal oral mass
definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the oral cavity of a fetus. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined. This finding is generally first observed by prenatal sonography or magnetic resonance imaging.

label: Dilated ejaculatory duct
definition: Increase in diameter of the ejeculatory duct. The ejaculatory duct delivers sperm into the urethra, adding secretions from the prostate and is formed by the union of the vas deferens with the duct of the seminal vesicle.

label: Decreased Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome protein concentration in hematopoietic cells
definition: The concentration of Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome protein in hematopoietic cells is below the lower limit of normal. This feature is measured by flow cytometry or Western blotting.

label: Decreased FOXP3-expressing T cell count
definition: The number of T cells in peripheral blood that express FOXP3-expressing is below the lower limit of normal. This finding is determined by flow cytometry.

label: Anti-beta fodrin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a component of beta-fodrin.

label: Elevated circulating tetradecenoylcarnitine concentration
definition: The concentration of tetradecenoylcarnitine (C14:1) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine 2-trans,4-cis-decadienoylcarnitine level
definition: The amount of 2-trans,4-cis-decadienoylcarnitine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating 2-trans,4-cis-decadienoylcarnitine concentration
definition: The concentration of 2-trans,4-cis-decadienoylcarnitine in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine N-acetyltyrosine level
definition: The amount of N-acetyltyrosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine manganese level
definition: The amount of manganese in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced urinary manganese level
definition: The amount of manganese in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased circulating catecholamine concentration
definition: Concentration of a catecholamine in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Empty sella turcica
definition: Empty sella or arachnoidocele has been defined as the herniation of the subarachnoid space within the sella turcica, associated with elongated pituitary stalk and flattening of the pituitary gland.

label: Elevated brain guanidinoacetate level by MRS
definition: An increase in the level of guanidinoacetate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

label: Elevated circulating beta chorionic gonadotropin concentration
definition: The concentration of beta chorionic gonadotropin in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating CXCL10 concentration
definition: The concentration of C-X-C motif chemokine 10 (CXCL10) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating interleukin 12 concentration
definition: The concentration of interleukin 12 (IL-12) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration
definition: The concentration of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Impaired heel-walking ability
definition: Difficulty or reduced ability to walk on heels. Heel-walking can be tested as a part of the neurological examination. Foot dorsal extension weakness leads to difficulties in walking on heels.

label: Anti-prothrombin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against prothrombin.

label: Anti-factor V antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against factor V.

label: Anti-factor VII antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against factor VII.

label: Anti-factor VIII antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against factor VIII.

label: Anti-factor IX antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against factor IX.

label: Anti-factor X antibody positivity
definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against factor X.

label: Anti-factor XI antibody positivity
definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against factor XI.

label: Anti-factor XIII antibody positivity
definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against factor XIII.

label: Anti-factor H antibody positivity
definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against factor H.

label: Extremities cold to touch
definition: Cool or cold arms or legs related to peripheral vasoconstriction, the narrowing of blood vessels resulting from the contraction of muscular walls in large arteries and the small arterioles of skin and most internal organs. Following exposure to low ambient temperatures, vasoconstriction decreases heat dissipation from skin surfaces, thus preventing life-threatening hypothermia.

label: Ruffled acrosome
definition: An irregular wavy appearance of sperm acrosomes.

label: Elevated circulating calprotectin concentration
definition: The concentration of calprotectin in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: 4-5 toe cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the toes 4 and 5.

label: Poly-hill sign
definition: A typical physical examination in patients with muscular dystrophies and selective weakness and atrophy of the trapezius muscle and proximal deltoid muscle. The contour of the back shows unique hills and drops.

label: 3-5 finger cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the third to the fifth fingers that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

label: Radioulnar subluxation
definition: Partial dislocation of the radioulnar joint.

label: Non-pitting edema
definition: Non-pitting edema occurs when excess fluid builds up in the body causing swelling that does not indent when pressure is applied. It usually occurs in the limbs, and often results from underlying medical conditions affecting lymphatic system function.

label: Anti-human ferritin peptide antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against the human ferritin peptide.

label: Elevated CSF L-2-hydroxyglutaric acid concentration
definition: The concentration of L-2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated erythrocyte inosine triphosphate concentration
definition: Concentration of inosine triphosphate in red blood cells is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced erythrocyte inosine triphosphatase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of inosine triphosphate pyrophosphohydrolase (EC 3.6.1.19) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating alpha-1,3-fucosyltransferase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-1,3-fucosyltransferase is below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

label: Diminished neutrophil myeloperoxidase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme myeloperoxidase (EC 1.11.1.7) in neutrophils below the lower limit of normal. This feature can be measured by peroxidase cytochemistry or biochemical assays. Myeloperoxidase is a lysosomal hemoprotein located in the azurophilic granules of polymorphonuclear leukocytes and monocytes.

label: Reduced erythrocyte uroporphyrinogen III cosynthase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of uroporphyrinogen III (EC 4.2.1.75) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated 18-hydroxycorticosterone to aldosterone ratio
definition: The relative concentration in the blood circulation of 18-hydroxycorticosterone compared to that of aldosterone is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating 21-deoxycortisol concentration
definition: The concentration of 21-deoxycortisol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated monolysocardiolipin/cardiolipin ratio
definition: The concentration of monolysocardiolipin related to that of cardiolipin is above the upper limit of normal. This is a functional assay that can be performed from a blood spot to diagnose Barth syndrome (OMIM:302060).

label: Low maternal vitamin B12 concentration
definition: The concentration of vitamin B12 in the mother's blood during pregnancy is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating inhibin A concentration
definition: The concentration of inibin A in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased circulating inhibin B concentration
definition: The concentration of inhibin B in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating lipoprotein(a) concentration
definition: The concentration of lipoprotein(a) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. Lipoprotein(a), also known as apolipoprotein(A), is encoded by LPA (HGNC:6667).

label: Reduced circulating lipoprotein(a) concentration
definition: The concentration of lipoprotein(a) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal. Lipoprotein(a), also known as apolipoprotein(A), is encoded by LPA (HGNC:6667).

label: Increased urinary bile acid level
definition: The amount of bile acids in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal urinary bile acid level
definition: The amount of bile acids in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

label: Reduced erythrocyte glutathione reductase activity
definition: Activity of glutathione reductase (EC 1.6.4.2) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label: Failure to elevate lactate upon ischemic exercise test
definition: Failure to elevate lactate in blood washed out from ischemically exercised muscles as assayed by the forearm ischemic exercise test.

label: Elevated circulating cholestanol concentration
definition: The concentration of cholestanol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. Cholestanol is the 5-alpha-dihydro derivative of cholesterol.

label: Livestock exposure
definition: A medical history of having been exposed to livestock (animals such as cattle and sheep which are kept on a farm ).

label: Synchronous skin lesions
definition: Applies to an abnormality of the skin in which multiple lesions occur at the same time.

label: Serpentine skin location
definition: Refers to a skin lseion that has a snake-like (serpentine) shape.

label: Elevated urinary histamine level
definition: The amount of histamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary N-methylhistamine level
definition: The amount of N-methylhistamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary ureidopropionic acid level
definition: The amount of ureidopropionic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary porphyrin level
definition: The amount of a porphyrin compound in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Porphrins are natural pigments containing a fundamental skeleton of four pyrrole nuclei united through the alpha-positions by four methine groups to form a macrocyclic structure. Porpyrins giove rise to heme and combalamine.

label: Elevated urinary coproporphyrin level
definition: The amount of a coproporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Ecrrine sweat gland predominance
definition: Applies to an abnormality of the skin that is located in or surrounding eccrine sweat glands.

label: Poorly demarcated skin lesion
definition: Applies to an abnormality of the skin whose boundary to the surrounding normal skin is not clearly defined.

label: History of recent cat bite
definition: Medical history of a recent bite or scratch injury due to a cat.

label: History of recent stay in area with inadequate sewage sanitation
definition: A history of having been in an area with inadequate sewage sanitation in the recent past.

label: Positive cutaneous herpes simplex virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of cutaneous herpes simplex virus nucleic acid in the skin by a method such as polymerase chain reaction. The sample is usually obtained by cutaneous swabs from skin lesions.

label: Positive CSF mycobacterium tuberculosis nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Mycobacterium tuberculosis nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Positive mycobacterium CSF culture
definition: Growth of mycobacterium in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Positive mycobacterium CSF microscopy
definition: The demonstration of mycobacterium by microscopy of the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Positive treponema pallidum PCR test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of treponema pallidum in the blood circulation by a method such a polymerase chain reaction.

label: Positive human Immunodeficiency virus nucleic acid test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of human immunodeficiency vrus (HIV) in the blood circulation by a methiod such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive CSF enterovirus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of enteroviral nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive CSF Borrelia burgdorferi nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Borrelia burgdorferi nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Positive CSF arbovirus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of arbovus nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR..

label: Positive Bartonella henselae nucleic acid test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Bartonella henselae in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive Dengue virus PCR test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of the Dengue virus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive CSF JC-virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of JC-virus nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Bloodstream Malaria parasite
definition: Presence of malaria parasites in the peripheral blood.

label: Positive bloodstream plasmodium falciparum nucleic acid pathogen test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Plasmodium falciparum (a type of Malaria parasite) in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Decreased erythrocyte fructose-1,6-bisphosphate aldolase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of fructose-1,6-bisphosphate aldolase (EC 4.1.2.13) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced circulating dopamine beta-hydroxylase activity
definition: Concentration of Dopamine beta-hydroxylase (DBH; EC 1.14.17.1) in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. DBH catalyzes the oxidative hydroxylation of dopamine to norepinephrine.

label: Reduced erythrocyte bisphosphoglycerate mutase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of bisphosphoglycerate mutase (BPGM; EC 5.4.2.4;) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. BPGM is a multifunctional enzyme specifically found in red blood cells that synthesizes 2,3-diphosphoglycerate through its synthase activity and degrades it through its phosphatase activity.

label: Reduced erythrocyte adenylate kinase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of adenylate kinase (EC 2.7.4.3) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal. Adenylate kinase is a ubiquitous monomeric enzyme that catalyzes the reversible conversion of MgATP plus AMP to MgADP plus ADP and contributes to homeostasis of the adenine nucleotide composition in the cell.

label: Reduced erythrocyte hexokinase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of hexokinase (EC 2.7.1.1) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. Arginase catalyzes the last step of the urea cycle.

label: Decreased circulating carboxypeptidase N activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme Carboxypeptidase N (arginine carboxypeptidase, EC 3.4.17.3) in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated red cell pyruvate kinase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of pyruvate kinase (EC 2.7.1.40) in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal. Pyruvate kinase (EC 2.7.1.40) is a glycolytic enzyme that catalyzes the transphosphorylation from phosphoenolpyruvate (PEP) to ADP, yielding pyruvate and ATP.

label: Reduced circulating adenosine deaminase-2 activity
definition: Concentration of adenosine deaminase 2 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced sepiapterin reductase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of sepiapterin reductase (7,8-dihydrobiopterin:NADP+ oxidoreductase; EC 1.1.1.153) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Elevated circulating vasoactive intestinal peptide concentration
definition: The concentration of vasoactive intestinal peptide (VIP) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating cholesterol sulfate concentration
definition: The concentration of cholesterol sulfate in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating lipoprotein X concentration
definition: The concentration of lipoprotein X in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating oxalate concentration
definition: The concentration of oxalate in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated blood ethylene glycol concentration
definition: The concentration of ethylene glycol in the blood is above the upper limit of a guidance value for total concentrations that implies possible injurious effects.

label: Midline notching of lower lip
definition: Exaggerated indentation at the very middle (midline) of the lower lip.

label: Reduced tissue thymidine phosphorylase activity
definition: Activity of thymidine phosphorylase (EC 2.4.2.4) in the tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes.

label: Reduced tissue tripeptidyl peptidase 1 activity
definition: Activity of tripeptidyl peptidase 1 (TPP1;EC 3.4.14.9) in the tissues below the lower limit of normal. TTP1 activity can be measured in tissues including fibroblasts and leukocytes muscle.

label: Reduced tissue arginine:glycine amidinotransferase activity
definition: Activity of L-arginine:glycine amidinotransferase (GATM; EC 2.1.4.1) in the tissues below the lower limit of normal. GATM activity can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue aspartylglucosaminidase activity
definition: Activity of aspartylglucosaminidase (AGA; EC 3.5.1.26) in the tissues below the lower limit of normal. AGA activity can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue carnitine-acylcarnitine translocase activity
definition: Activity of carnitine-acylcarnitine translocase (CACT) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. CACT activity can be measured in multiple tissues.

label: Reduced circulating 6-pyruvoyltetrahydropterin synthase activity
definition: The activity of 6-pyruvoyltetrahydropterin synthase in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced tissue mannosyl-oligosaccharide glucosidase activity
definition: Activity of mannosyl-oligosaccharide glucosidase (MOGS) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. MOGS activity can be measured in multiple tissues including liver and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue 3-methylglutaconyl-CoA hydratase activity
definition: Activity of the mitochondrial enzyme 3-methylglutaconyl-CoA hydratase (EC 4.2.1.18) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue gamma-glutamyltransferase activity
definition: Activity of gamma-glutamyltransferase in the tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Positive oropharangeal infectious agent test
definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in the oropharynx positive. The oropharynx is defined as the middle part of the throat and includes the soft palate, the side and back walls of the throat, the tonsils, and the posterior one-third of the tongue.

label: Positive oropharynx poliovirus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of poliovirus nucleic acid in the oropharynx by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive synonvial fluid infectious agent test
definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in the synovial fluid (i.e., in a joint) positive.

label: Positive synonvial fluid culture
definition: Growth of an infectious agent in a culture derived from synovial fluid.

label: Positive synovial fluid gram stain
definition: Demonstration of the presence of bacteria by gram staining of joint (synovial) fluid. The sample is generally obtained by arthrocentesis.

label: Anti Parvovirus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of parvovirus.

label: Brain parenchymal tuberculoma
definition: Tuberculoma results from hematogenous spread of Mycobacterium tuberculosis (M. tb) from an extracranial source. Diagnosis is based on computed tomography (CT) scan and magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) studies with a similar ring-enhancing lesion.

label: Muscle arteriovenous malformation
definition: An anomalous configuration of blood vessels that shunts arterial blood directly into veins without passing through the capillaries and that is located in muscle tissue.

label: Bone arteriovenous malformation
definition: An anomalous configuration of blood vessels that shunts arterial blood directly into veins without passing through the capillaries and that is located in a bone.

label: Periosteal elevation
definition: Lifting or separation of the periosteum from the outer surface of a bone. Periosteal elevation is usually seen in benign process, frequently in cranioencephalic traumas. There is an elevation of the periosteum after blood, like in cephalohematomas.

label: Esophageal dilation
definition: Widening (relatively uniform increase in diameter) of a segment of the esophagus.

label: Loose body in joint
definition: Small fragments of articular cartilage that break off in a joint as a result of a injury, degeneration, or other processes.

label: Paraspinal arteriovenous malformation
definition: An anomalous configuration of blood vessels that shunts arterial blood directly into veins without passing through the capillaries and that is located in adjacent to the spine, i.e., in a location that is normally occupied by muscles, ligaments, nerves, and other tissues that run alongside the spinal column.

label: Supernumerary tarsal bone
definition: The presence of an additional tarsal bone that is not one of the canonical tarsal bones (cuboid, medial, intermediate, and lateral cuneiform, navicular, talus, calcaneus).

label: Maxillary cyst
definition: A closed sac that has developed in the upper jaw bone (maxilla) and contains fluid or semi-solid material. Cystic lesions of the maxilla are benign entities with both odontogenic and non-odontogenic origins.

label: Mandibular cyst
definition: A closed sac that has developed in the lower jaw bone (mandibula) and contains fluid or semi-solid material.

label: Sixth cranial nerve hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the six cranial nerve (abducens nerve).

label: Third cranial nerve hypoplasia
definition: Underdevelopment of the third cranial nerve (oculomotor nerve).

label: Elevated urinary succinylacetone level
definition: Presence in the urine of succinylacetone, which is one of the toic block metabolites formed in tyrosinaemia type 1 because of a defect in the final enzyme of the pathway of the degradation of tyrosine, namely fumarylacetoacetase (FAH, EC 3.7.1.2).

label: Elevated urinary 2-oxoisocaproic level
definition: The amount of 2-oxoisocaproic in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 2-oxovaleric acid level
definition: The amount of 2-oxovaleric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 2-hydroxyisocaproic acid level
definition: The amount of 2-hydroxyisocaproic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary isovalerylglycine level
definition: The amount of isovalerylglycine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 2-methyl-3-hydroxybutyric acid level
definition: The amount of 2-methyl-3-hydroxybutyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxypentanoic acid level
definition: The amount of 3-hydroxypentanoic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 7-hydroxyoctanoic acid level
definition: The amount of 7-hydroxyoctanoic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary D-glyceric acid level
definition: The amount of D-glyceric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxyisobutyric acid level
definition: The amount of 3-hydroxyisobutyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 3,4-Dihydroxybutyric acid level
definition: The amount of 3,4-Dihydroxybutyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxyadipic acid level
definition: The amount of 3-hydroxyadipic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated erythrocyte galactose-1-phosphate concentration
definition: Concentration of galactose-1-phosphate in red blood cells (erythrocytes) above the upper level of normal.

label: Elevated circulating chitotriosidase activity
definition: Increased activity or concentration of the enzyme chitotriosidase. Serum chitotriosidase is a biomarker that has shown high specificity and sensitivity in patients with sarcoidosis.

label: Squamosal suture synostosis
definition: Premature closure of the squamosal suture, which is one of the lateral minor skull sutures, separating the parietal and squamous temporal bones.

label: Enlarged fetal lungs
definition: The size (volume) of the lungs of a fetus above the upper limit of normal for the gestational age.

label: Orbital inflammation
definition: An inflammatory condition localized to the orbit, presenting capillary dilatation, leukocytic infiltration, redness, heat, and pain. CT or MIR Imaging demonstrates enlargement of the muscle belly of one (or more) extraocular muscles typically with the involvement of tendinous insertions. Inflammation can also be observed in surrounding tissues, including the orbital fat, lacrimal gland, and optic nerve sheath.

label: Reduced Inositol polyphosphate 5-phosphatase OCRL-1 activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of inositol polyphosphate 5-phosphatase OCRL-1 as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. This enzyme has phosphoinositide 5-phosphatase (EC 3.1.3.36) activity.

label: Reduced muscle glycogen debrancher enzyme activity
definition: Activity of the gycogen debrancher enzyme (GDE) in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal. GDE is a large monomeric protein with two catalytic activities: amylo-1,6-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.33) and 4-alpha-glucanotransferase (EC 2.4.1.25).

label: Reduced tissue UDP-glucuronyl-transferase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of uridine diphosphate glucuronosyltransferase below the lower limit of normal. The activity of this enzyme can be measured in liver and rarely in other tissues.

label: Temporal artery giant cells
definition: The presence of giant cells in the temporal artery. This is a feature of giant cell arteritis. Giant cells are multinucleated cells formed by fusion of multiple macrophages and are typically located in the intima of the arterial wall. This feature is typically demonstrated by temporal artery biopsy but other arteries may also be affected.

label: Reduced phosphoenolpyruvate carboxykinase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Activity of phosphoenolpyruvate carboxykinase (EC 4.1.1.32) is below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Elevated urinary pyrroline hydroxycarboxylic acid level
definition: The amount of pyrroline hydroxycarboxylic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary N-tau-ribosylhistidine level
definition: Presence of N tau-ribosylhistidine (His-R) in the urine. His-R is a histidine derivative found in the urine of histidinemic patients.

label: Elevated urinary ureidoisobutyric acid level
definition: The amount of ureidoisobutyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Ureidoisobutyric acid is increased in the urine of patients with beta-ureidopropionase (EC 3.5.1.6) deficiency.

label: Elevated urinary N-carbamyl-beta-aminoisobutyric acid level
definition: The amount of N-carbamyl-beta-aminoisobutyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Nipple epidermal Paget cells
definition: Malignant, intraepithelial adenocarcinoma cells of variable sizes usually large in size, present singly or in the form of small groups within the epidermis of the nipple. Cells may be ovoid, round, or signet-ring forms, usually mucin positive, and the cytoplasm may contain periodic acid-Schiff (PAS)-positive, diastase-resistant granules, indicating the presence of neutral mucopolysaccharides. The cells possess microscopic features of glandular cells with pale to clear vacuolated cytoplasm, and nuclei are usually high-grade with prominent nucleoli.

label: Penile corporal blood gas ischemia
definition: Partial pressure of oxygen (pO2) in cavernous blood of the penis is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Recent temporal region trauma
definition: A history of an injury to the temporal region of the skull that occurred recently (several hours, days, or weeks before the current presenting complaint).

label: Rest limb pain
definition: Rest pain is a continuous unrelenting pain due to ischemia of the lower leg, beginning with or being aggravated by elevation and being relieved by sitting with legs in a dependent position or by standing.

label: Scalloped appearance of liver surface
definition: A lesion associated with pseudomyxoma peritonei whosetypical CT appearance is scalloping of the surface of the liver and spleen caused by loculated accumulations of mucin, which distinguishes mucin from fluid ascites. The mucinous material is similar in density to water. There are also islands of higher attenuation due to scattered solid elements and calcification within mucinous material.

label: Nipple thickening
definition: Thickening of the skin around the nipple.

label: Hypoechoic breast mass
definition: A breast mass visualized by sonography that displays a lower than normal echo signal (and this that appears dark gray in the typical ultrasound image).

label: Unilocular ovarian cyst
definition: An ovarian cyst without septa and a solid component.

label: Mesenteric torsion
definition: Mesenteric torsion is a pathological rotation of the intestinal tract around the axis of the mesenteric root, resulting in rapid occlusion of the cranial mesenteric artery.

label: High-pitched bowel sounds
definition: Abnormal bowel sounds of an unually high frequency.

label: Exacerbated by opiate medication
definition: Applied to a sign orr symptom that is worsed by administration of opiate medications.

label: Breast granuloma
definition: Formation of a non-necrotizing granuloma in breat tissue typically in combination with a localized infiltrate of multi-nucleated giant cells, epithelioid histiocytes, lymphocytes, and plasma cells.

label: Exposure to cosmetic fragrances
definition: A history of exposure to fragrances found in cosmetic products.

label: Sweating and flushing in the preauricular area in response to mastication
definition: Sweating and flushing in the preauricular area in response to mastication or a salivary stimulus. Facial warmth, flushing, and sweating in the territory of the auriculotemporal nerve overlying the parotid gland, which may include the preauricular skin, the temporal skin, the scalp, and the temporomandibular joint region. Symptoms occur during meals, especially with spicy and sour foods. This feature is inferred to be a consequence of injury to the auriculotemporal nerve, a branch if the trigeminal nerve.

label: Reduced hepatic glyoxylate reductase activity
definition: Activity of glyoxylate reductase/hydroxypyruvate reductase (GRHPR; EC 1.1.1.79) in liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: PAS-positive lymphocyte vacuolization
definition: Presence of lymphocytes with positive staining for periodic acid-Schiff (PAS) cytoplasmic vacuoles.

label: Lipid-laden bone-marrow macrophages
definition: Bone marrow with increased numbers of macrophages heavily laden with lipids.

label: Bone marrow monocytosis
definition: Increased count of monocytes in the bone marrow.

label: Sunflower cataract
definition: Sunflower cataract (SC) is a type of anterior subcapsular cataract almost only seen in Wilson disease, an autosomal-recessive condition with a defect in the metabolism of copper leading to accumulation of copper in the liver and basal ganglia. SC consists of a thin, centralized opacification that is located directly under the anterior capsule and encompasses between one-third and one-half of the anterior lens pole surface area. In all cases, the central opacification is surrounded by additional, secondary opacifications arranged in ray-like structures around it. This pattern is said to resemble a sunflower, with a large central disk surrounded by petals.

label: Anti-lamin A antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against lamin A.

label: Anti-lamin C antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against human lamin C.

label: Anti-vinculin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against vinculin.

label: Anti-annexin A5 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against annexin A5.

label: Bulging fontanelle
definition: An outward curving of a fontanelle, which occurs when fluid builds up in the brain or the brain swells, causing increased pressure inside the skull.

label: 3-4 toe cutaneous syndactyly
definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the toes 3 and 4.

label: Triangular nail
definition: Nail so wide as long with a distal part presenting an acute angle.

label: Distal tibiofibular synostosis
definition: Fusion of the distal (i.e.., located away from the trunk) part of the tibia and fibula.

label: Abnormal metacarpal ossification
definition: Any abnormal process of ossification of the metacarpal bones, which normally are each ossified from two centers: one for the body, and one for the head (metacarpal II,III,IV, and V) and one for the body and one for the base (metacarpal I). At the eighth to ninth week of fetal life, ossification commences in the middle of the body. At the third year the distal extremities of the metacarpals of the fingers and the base of the metacarpal of the thumb begin to ossify; they unite with the bodies at about the twentieth year.

label: Rib spur
definition: A bony projection (spur, osteophyte) originating from a rib.

label: Crescent-shaped iliac bone
definition: Deficient mineralization of the iliac wings, giving a paraglider/crescent shape to the iliac bone.

label: Abnormal ischium ossification
definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of ischial bones.

label: Femoral neck fracture
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the neck of femur.

label: Papillary dermis eosinophilic hyaline material
definition: Accumulation of eosinophilic hyaline material observed around the papillary dermis and the blood vessels located in it. The papillary dermis is the uppermost layer of the dermis. It intertwines with the rete ridges of the epidermis and is composed of fine and loosely arranged collagen fibers.

label: Pancreatic intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm
definition: Intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm (IPMN) is an exocrine neoplasm of the pancreas consisting of epithelial cells growing within the pancreatic ducts (main pancreatic duct or its major branches) and producing mucin. IPMN is a mucin-producing pancreatic cystic tumor. IPMN contains epithelial cells that can create papillary projections.

label: Medium vessel vasculitis
definition: A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) that affects medium-sized blood vessels. By common usage, vasculitis predominantly refers to arterial disease. Medium-sized vasculitis is observed in diseases including polyarteritis nodosa, Kawasaki disease, and cutaneous polyarteritis nodosa.

label: Elevated muscle fiber laminin alpha 5 expression
definition: A decreased amount of laminin alpha-5 in muscle tissue. This feature can be shown by immunohistochemistry or Western blotting of muscle tissue. Laminin subunit alpha-5 is a protein encoded by the LAMA5 gene.

label: Paravertebral mass
