definition: A swelling or enlargement localized next to the vertebral column. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Phlebolith
definition: A calcified structure that forms within a vein. The pathogenesis of phleboliths is thought to involve an organized thrombus produced when the peripheral blood flow slows. The thrombus calcifies, form- ing the core of the phlebolith. Then, the fibrinous com- ponent undergoes secondary calcification and becomes attached. Repetition of this process causes enlargement of the phlebolith.

label: Bladder rupture
definition: A perforation in the wall of the urinary bladder. Bladder rupture, a relatively rare condition, is most commonly due to abdominal or pelvic trauma but may be spontaneous or iatrogenic in association with surgical or endoscopic procedures. In most cases, patients with bladder rupture have gross hematuria. Other symptoms of bladder rupture include pelvic pain, lower abdominal pain, and difficulty voiding.

label: Elevated myocardial iron load
definition: Increased amount of iron in myocardial tissue.

label: Right ventricular regional wall motion abnormality
definition: The occurrence of abnormal or absent contractility of a region of the heart muscle of the right ventricule. Conventional assessment of RWMA is based on visual interpretation of endocardial excursion and myocardial thickening from the echocardiogram videos.

label: Right ventricular regional akinesia
definition: A region of the right ventricle exhibits absent contraction (akinesia) compared to the rest of the ventricle.

label: Right ventricular regional dyskinesia
definition: A region of the right ventricle exhibits abnormal contraction (dyskinesia) compared to the rest of the ventricle, leading to outward bulging or ballooning during contraction or inadequate inward movement.

label: Right ventricular aneurysm
definition: A localized, abnormal dilation or bulging of a portion of the right ventricular wall.

label: Glomerular immune-complex deposition
definition: Accumulation of immune deposits, containing immunoglobulins, complement, and other proteins, at various intraglomerular locations. This can lead to glomerulonephritis, with the type of injury that results being dependent on four factors: the mechanism of the deposit formation, the site of deposit formation, the composition of the deposits and the amount of the deposits.

label: Glomerular PLA2R immune-complex deposition
definition: Accumulation of immune deposits, containing auto-antibodies against the podocyte antigen M-type phospholipase A2 receptor (PLA2R) in intraglomerular locations.

label: Elevated urinary L-glycerate level
definition: The amount of L-glycerate in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Breast myxoma
definition: A rare, benign mesenchymal tumor of the breast characterized histologically by stellate, round, and spindle-shaped cells with vesicular nuclei and scant cytoplasm that are scattered in the myxoid stroma.

label: Ovarian cystadenoma
definition: A common, benign ovarian tumor that carries a good prognosis. The two most frequent types of cystadenomas are serous and mucinous cystadenomas whereas endometrioid and clear cell cystadenomas are rare.

label: Abnormal CSF N-acetylaspartic acid concentration
definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of N-acetylaspartic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Decreased CSF N-acetylaspartic acid concentration
definition: Concentration of N-acetylaspartic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary mevalonate lactone level
definition: The amount of mevalonate lactone in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Anti-von Willebrand factor antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react to von Willebrand factor (VWF).

label: Elevated natural killer cell count
definition: The count of natural killer cells per volume of blood is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal serum osmolality
definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the serum osmolality, defined as the sum of the osmolalities of every single dissolved particle in the blood such as sodium and associated anions, potassium, glucose, and urea.

label: Low serum osmolality
definition: Serum osmolality, which is defined as the sum of the osmolalities of every single dissolved particle in the blood such as sodium and associated anions, potassium, glucose, and urea, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: High serum osmolality
definition: Serum osmolality, which is defined as the sum of the osmolalities of every single dissolved particle in the blood such as sodium and associated anions, potassium, glucose, and urea, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: History of compressive dressings
definition: A past medical history of having been treated with tight bandages, compression sleeve, tight casts or splints, immobilizers, or similar items such as overly tight clothes, watch bands, or handcuffs.

label: Triggered by overhead motions
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is induced by repeatedly performing overhead motions, such as painting a ceiling or working on objects located above the head, or some types of athletics.

label: Radiating pain
definition: Pain that is perceived to extend or spread out from one area of the body to another.

label: Mitral opening snap
definition: Opening snap is an additional sound heard in the diastole that is related to the opening of a stenotic but mobile mitral valve. It is described as an early diastolic, high-pitched sound, which is associated with opening of the mitral and/or tricuspid valve.

label: Mucus in stool
definition: Abnormally increased amount of mucus in the feces. Mucus is a slippery aqueous secretion produced by mucous membranes including those of the intestines.

label: Elevated circulating CCL3 concentration
definition: The concentration of C-C Motif Ligand 3 (CCL3) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating CCL4 concentration
definition: The concentration of C-C Motif Ligand 4 (CCL4) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF 14-3-3 protein concentration
definition: The concentration of 14-3-3 protein in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF dihydrobiopterin concentration
definition: Concentration of dihydrobiopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Left atrial fibrosis
definition: Atrial fibrosis is an hallmark of atrial structural remodelling, characterized by the aberrant activation, proliferation and differentiation of fibroblasts, and subsequent excessive synthesis and irregular deposition of extracellular matrix proteins.

label: Reduced circulating NT-proANP concentration
definition: The concentration of NT-proANP in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced tissue delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase (P5CDH; EC 1.5.1.12) below the lower limit of normal. P5CDH can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. P5CDH is a mitochondrial matrix NAD(+)-dependent dehydrogenase which catalyzes the second step of the proline degradation pathway, converting pyrroline-5-carboxylate to glutamate.

label: Elevated circulating N-carbamyl-beta-aminoisobutyric acid concentration
definition: The concentration of N-carbamyl-beta-aminoisobutyric acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Low tissue ferrochelatase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of Ferrochelatase (FECH; EC 4.99.1.1) below the lower limit of normal. FECH enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. FECH is the terminal enzyme of the heme biosynthetic pathway, and catalyzes the insertion of iron into protoporphyrin to form heme.

label: Elevated circulating heptacarboxylporphyrin concentration
definition: The concentration of heptacarboxylporphyrin in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Aggravated by menstruation
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is more severe during mensutruation.

label: Reduced breast milk zinc concentration
definition: The concentration of zinc in breast milk is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary bile acid level
definition: The amount of bile acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary glyoxylic acid level
definition: The amount of glyoxylic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. The conjugate base of glyoxylic acid is known as glyoxylate.

label: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyanthranilic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of 3-hydroxyanthranilic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating CXCL9 concentration
definition: The concentration of chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 9 in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Thickened fibular cortex
definition: Abnormal increase in the thickness (distance between the inner and outer boundaries) of the outer layer (cortex) of the fibula.

label: New medication added in recent weeks
definition: Medical history of starting a new medication recently.

label: Noctural pain
definition: Pain at night.

label: Femoral osteosclerosis
definition: An abnormal increase of bone mineral density of the femur. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Absent Bell phenomenon
definition: The Bell phenomenon is the reflex upward movement of the front of the eyeball when the eyelids close (or blink). It protects the eye by helping to keep the cornea moist. This term refers to a lack of this phenomenon, which can be observed with certain conditions such as congenital fibrosis of the extraocular muscles.

label: Dalen Fuchs nodules
definition: Nodules (yellow-white subretinal pigment epithelium lesions) that form between Bruch's membrane and the retinal pigment epithelium.

label: Triggering by ocular trauma
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by trauma to the eye.

label: Gelatinous drop-like dystrophic cornea
definition: Deposition of amyloid material in the subepithelial space of the cornea.

label: Hepatic reticuloendothelial system cell iron deposition
definition: Abnormal accumulation of iron in reticuloendothelial cells of the liver. This feature can be appreciated on liver biopsy by Perls iron stain for granular iron deposition, based on agreement that only discernible hemosiderin granules represent significant iron deposition.

label: Reduced epidermal kindlin-1 expression
definition: Lower than normal amount of kindlin-1 in the epidermis.

label: Central giant cell lesion of the jaw
definition: A benign proliferative and asymptomatic intraosseous lesion of the jaw formed by fibrous tissue that contains multiple focus of hemorrhage and an aggregation of multinucleated giant cells.

label: Terminal hepatic lobular vascular occlusion
definition: A type of Hepatic venous outflow obstruction characterized by fibrous concentric narrowing of zone 3 terminal hepatic venules, centrilobular hepatocyte necrosis, and sinusoidal congestion, accomapnied by necrosis of pericentral hepatocytes, and narrowing and eventual fibrosis of central veins.

label: Axonal spheroids
definition: During neurodegeneration, bubble-like swellings form along the length of the axon, a primary and early effect of dynamic axonal deformation. These varicosities, spheroids, or swellings have been described as beads on a string and branches bearing fruit, and they frequently appear on degenerating axons.

label: Decreased liver bile salt export pump expression
definition: Amount of bile salt export pump (BSEP, coded by the ABCB11 gene) in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced tissue type II iodothyronine deiodinase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of type II iodothyronine deiodinase below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in tissues such as cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue fatty aldehyde dehydrogenase activity
definition: Activity of fatty aldehyde dehydrogenase (EC 1.2.1.3) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts and leukocytes.

label: Decreased circulating pancreatic isoamylase activity
definition: The activity of alpha-Amylase (1,4-alpha-D-glucan-4-glucanohydrolase E. C. 3.2.1.1, pancreatic isoamylase) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Reduced tissue guanidinoacetate methyltransferase activity
definition: Activity of the mitochondrial enzyme guanidinoacetate methyltransferase in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced erythrocyte galactokinase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of galactokinase (EC 2.7.1.6) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label: Auspitz sign
definition: The appearance of small bleeding points after successive layers of scale have been removed from the surface of psoriatic papules or plaques.

label: Salty tasting skin
definition: Skin tastes marked salty without an obvious explanation such as heat or exercise. This finding can be observed in infants with cystic fibrosis.

label: Scalp nodule
definition: A small firm lump located in the skin of the scalp that is greater than one cm in diameter.

label: History of undercooked pork ingestion
definition: A history of ingestion of undercooked pork. This is particularly relevant in areas with a high prevalence of cysticercosis.

label: History of recent rodent exposure
definition: A history of exposed to rodents (mice, rats, prarie dogs) within several weeks of the current presenting complaint.

label: Positive CSF fungus test
definition: Any kind of test for a fungal infectious agent in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) positive.

label: Positive CSF human T-lymphotropic virus type I antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of human T-lymphotropic virus type I.

label: Positive chlamydia trachomatis urine nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Chlamydia trachomatis nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Anti-streptococcus deoxyribonuclease-B antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against streptococcal deoxyribonuclease-B (ADN-B). Almost all group A streptococci have this antigen and a strong elevation of the antibody is observed in patients with acute rheumatic fever, acute glomerulonephritis and other streptococcal infections.

label: Positive streptococcus A rapid antigen detection test
definition: Positive detection of a group A streptococcal antigen in a test perforned on a throat swab.

label: Positive synovial mycobacterial culture
definition: Growth of a mycobacteria in a culture derived from synovial fluid.

label: Positive mycobacterial synovial nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of mycobacteria in the synovial fluid by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive bloodstream babesia nucleic acid pathogen test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of genus Babesia (parasite) in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive bloodstream influenza nucleic test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of an influenza virus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive bloodstream parainfluenza virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of parainfluenza virus in the blood circulation by a methiod such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive bloodstream adenovirus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of an adenovirus in the blood circulation by a methiod such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Anti-Francisella tularensis antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Francisella tularensis.

label: Positive bloodstream MERS coronavirus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Middle East Respiratory Syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive nasopharyngeal corynebacterium diphtheriae nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Corynebacterium diphtheriae in nasopharyngeal secretions by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Pediculosis capitis
definition: Visualization of at least one louse on visual inspection of the head hair. Use of a bright light, magnifying lens, or fine-toothed comb (lice comb) can aid in diagnosis.

label: Premature glabellar skin wrinkling
definition: The presence in the skin of the glabellar region of an increased degree of wrinkling (irregular folds and indentations) of the skin as compared with age-related norms.

label: Flexural reticulate hyperpigmentation
definition: Hyperpigmented macules with a reticulate (net-like) pattern involving the neck, axillae, groins, and other flexures like the inframammary folds in females. Histopathology shows orthokeratosis or hyperkeratosis, thinning of the suprapapillary epithelium, elongation of the rete ridges, hyperpigmentation of the basal layer, and follicular cysts. A perivascular lymphohistiocytic infiltrate can be observed in the papillary dermis.

label: Elevated fractional excretion of urate
definition: Abnormally increased proportion of filtered urate that is excreted in the urine as calculated using the concentrations of urate and creatinine in both blood and urine. Clinically this manifests as uric acid wasting.

label: Abnormal urinary creatine level
definition: The amount of creatine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

label: Decreased urinary creatine level
definition: The amount of creatine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating type I procollagen aminoterminal propeptide concentration
definition: The concentration of type I procollagen aminoterminal propeptide in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. The aminoterminal propeptide of type I procollagen (PINP) in serum is a sensitive indicator of the synthesis of type I collagen.

label: Decreased tissue S-adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of S-adenosylhomocysteine hydrolase (EC 3.3.1.1) below the lower limit of normal. FECH enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including erythrocytes and liver.

label: Decreased urinary dopamine level
definition: The concentration of dopamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Elevated erythrocyte AICA-ribotide concentration
definition: Concentration of 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide (AICA-riboside) in red blood cells is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating monomethyl sterol concentration
definition: Concentration of monomethylsterols (such as 4alpha-monomethylsterol) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating dimethyl sterol concentration
definition: The concentration of dimethylsterols in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating C-terminal fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration
definition: The concentration of the C-terminal portion of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is outside of the limits of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid level
definition: The amount of 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid (5-HIAA) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating thiosulfate concentration
definition: The concentration of thiosulfate in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating interleukin 1 receptor antagonist concentration
definition: The concentration of interleukin 1 receptor antagonist (IL-1RA) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive CSF West Nile virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of West Nile virus nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive CSF herpes simplex virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of herpes simplex virus (HSV) nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive CSF cryptococcal antigen test
definition: A test result demonstrating the presence of a cryptococal antigen in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Positive rubella CSF culture
definition: Growth of rubella virus in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Positive CSF treponema pallidum nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Treponema pallidum (syphillis) nucleic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Decreased CSF tetrahydrobiopterin level
definition: Concentration of tetrahydrobiopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal.

label: Decreased CSF N-acetyl-aspartyl-glutamate concentration
definition: The concentration of N-acetyl-aspartyl-glutamate (NAAG) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Positive CSF Tropheryma whipplei bacteria microscopy
definition: Demonstration of Tropheryma whipplei bacteria in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) my microscopic analysis.

label: CSF treponemal antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of treponema pallidum (syphilis).

label: Echophenomenon
definition: A stimulus triggered repetition of an action (echopraxia) or sound (echolalia) performed without the explicit awareness of an individual.

label: Paracentral hyper-autofluorecence
definition: Increased autofluorescence in areas adjacent to the central macula (but not including the very center).

label: Fixed fetal extremities
definition: A condition in which the limbs of a fetus are immobile or held in a rigid position. The limbs are consistently immobile and rigid. Fixed extremities can be observed during prenatal imaging (e.g., ultrasound).

label: Abnormal peripapillary microvascular network
definition: The density of the deep peripapillary microvascular network (i.e., the number of blood vessels) is below the lower limit of normal. This finding is observable by optical coherence tomography angiography.

label: Auriculitis
definition: Inflammation of the skin and soft tissues of the outer ear.

label: Recent history of moisture in external ear canal
definition: A recent history of being exposed to moisture in the external ear canal.

label: History of recent trauma to external ear canal
definition: Medical history of trauma to the external ear canal, including cotton-swab use, in recent weeks.

label: Elevated urinary 4-tyramine level
definition: The amount of 4-tyramine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxykynurenine concentration
definition: The concentration of 3-hydroxykynurenine in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Posterior vertebral body notching
definition: Exaggerated posterior vertebral notches.

label: Cone-shaped distal tibial epiphysis
definition: The distal epiphysis (rounded portion of bone at the far end of the tibia distal to the growth plate) has an abnormal cone-shaped appearance, that is, the epiphysis has a globular form at the bottom, tapering to a point at the top.

label: Osteoporotic femoral neck
definition: Low bone mass localized in the neck of the femur. Osteoporosis is defined based on a T-score of -2.5 or lower (bone mineral density of 2.5 or more standard deviations below that of a normal young adult).

label: Olanzapine exposure
definition: History of having taken olanzapine.

label: Reduced tissue phosphomannomutase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme phosphomannomutase (EC 5.4.2.8) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes, fibroblasts, and liver.

label: Reduced tissue phosphomannose isomerase activity
definition: Activity of the mitochondrial enzyme phosphomannose isomerase (PMI; EC 5.3.1.8) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes, fibroblasts, and liver.

label: Reduced tissue palmitoyl-protein thioesterase activity
definition: Activity of the enzyme palmitoyl-protein thioesterase (PPT; EC 3.1.2.22) in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts and leukocytes.

label: Maternal household cat exposure
definition: The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of regular exposure to one or more cats, e.g., in the household.

label: Protein craving
definition: Unusually strong preference for protein-rich foods.

label: Absent superficial temporal artery pulse
definition: The pulsation of the superficial temporal artery cannot be detected on physical examination.

label: Basilar artery fenestration
definition: A fenestration affecting the basilar artery. Basilar fenestration typically occurs at the lower end of the basilar artery just as the vertebral arteries join Fenestrations of intracranial arteries are segmental duplications of the lumen into two distinct endothelium-lined channels, which may or may not share their adventitial layer. They can range from a small focus of divided tissue to long-segment duplication. Fenestrations are the result of partial failure of fusion of paired primitive embryologic vessels or incomplete obliteration of different anastomosis in a primitive vascular network. The association of fenestrations with aneurysms has been suggested in many small case series, though the exact relationship is not well defined.

label: Displacement of the extensor tendon in metacarpophalangeal joint
definition: Dislocation of the extensor tendons from their central position on the metacarpal heads can be traumatic, congenital, spontaneous, or degenerative.

label: Heloma
definition: A corn, also known as a clavus, heloma, or focal intractable plantar hyperkeratosis, is a type of callosity. Corns are uncomfortable, thickened skin lesions that result from repeated mechanical trauma due to friction or pressure forces.

label: Exacerbated by pronation
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is aggravated by (or made more painful by) pronation. Pronation of the hand involves the rotation of the forearm and wrist so that the palm of the hand faces downwards or towards the back (posteriorly).

label: Distortion of the anterior part of the interhemispheric fissure
definition: Change in the normal shape (displacement, asymmetry) of the anterior part of the interhemispheric fissure. This finding can be identified prenatally by sonography or magnetic resonance imaging.

label: Positive lacrimal tract actinomyces culture
definition: Growth of Actinomyces israelii (anaerobic filamentous gram positive) culture of lacrimal discharge or concretions.

label: Eschar
definition: A type of wound characterized by dry, black, hard necrotic tissue.

label: History of wearing tightly fitted clothing
definition: History of wearing tight clothing such as compression shorts, sports bras, bike shorts, wet suits, spandex, veils, and tight hats.

label: Anti-folate receptor antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against the folate receptor in the blood circulation.

label: Positive bloodstream VDRL test
definition: An abnormal (positive) result of the Venereal Disease Research Laboratory (VDRL) test performed in peripheral blood, suggesting past or present syphilis.

label: Positive bloodstream rapid plasma reagin test
definition: Positive result of the the rapid plasma reagin test (RPR test. This is a rapid diagnostic test that looks for non-specific antibodies in the blood of the patient that may indicate an infection by syphilis or related non-venereal treponematoses.

label: Positive bloodstream HIV p24 antigen test
definition: Demonstration of the p24 antigen of human immunodeficiency virus in the bloodstream.

label: Positive Quantiferon tuberculosis test
definition: A positive Quantiferon test result indicating Mycobacterium tuberculosis. The Quantiferon assay is designed to stimulate IFN-gamma release from CD4+ T cells in a single tuberculosis antigen tube using long peptides from three M. tuberculosis antigens.

label: Tzanck smear with multinucleated giant cells
definition: Tzanck smear demonstrates multinucleated giant cells, a sign that is suggestive for herpetic infections. Such smears are taken from skin lesions and display multinucleated cells with ground glass nuclei, nuclear moulding, and margination of nuclear chromatin typical of herpes simplex and varicella infection.

label: Positive Mazzotti test
definition: Locally applied 1.6 percent diethylcarbamazine citrate in Nivea lotion can be used as a diagnostic test for onchocerciasis. Papular reactions are considered as positive test results.

label: Positive bloodstream Tropheryma whippelii nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Tropheryma whippelii in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Elevated urinary 2,8-dihydroxyadenine level
definition: The amount of 2,8-dihydroxyadenine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine fructose level
definition: Amount of fructose in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary uroporphyrin level
definition: The amount of uroporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary phosphohydroxylysine level
definition: The amount of phosphohydroxylysine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Cervical C6/C7 vertebrae fusion
definition: Fusion of cervical vertebrae at C6 and C7, caused by a failure in the normal segmentation or division of the cervical vertebrae during the early weeks of fetal development, leading to a short neck with a low hairline at the back of the head, and restricted mobility of the upper spine.

label: Periumbilical depression
definition: The tissue that immediately surrounds the umbilicus is located below the normal plane of the abdomen.

label: Thickened tibial cortex
definition: Abnormally increased thicknes of the cortical layer of the tibia.

label: Thickened femoral cortex
definition: Abnormally increased thicknes of the cortical layer of the femur.

label: Thickened cortex of the radius
definition: Abnormally increased thickness of the cortical layer of the radius.

label: Thickened cortex of the ulna
definition: Abnormally increased thickness of the cortical layer of the ulna.

label: Elevated circulating aspartate aminotransferase to alanine aminotransferase ratio
definition: Aspartate aminotransferase to alanine aminotransferase ratio increased greater than 1.5.

label: Temporomandibular joint dislocation
definition: The lower jawbone (mandible) pulls away from the temporomandibular joints (TMJ). It is characterized by pain, clicking and functional restriction.

label: Amyloid goiter
definition: Amyloidosis is defined as the accumulation of amorphous, proteinaceous material in different parts of the body. Amyloid can be deposited in the thyroid gland in such quantities to cause a clinically apparent enlargement of the gland known as Amyloid goiter.

label: Prominent lesser trochanter
definition: Abnormally large lesser trochanter.

label: Melorheostosis
definition: Regions of sclerosing hyperostosis in the cortex of long bones, which might have a radiologic appearance of dripping candle wax.

label: Elevated circulating beta-glucuronidase activity
definition: The activity of beta-glucuronidase (EC 3.2.1.31) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated osmolality gap
definition: Plasma osmolality is determined mainly by Sodium, its counter ions, and uncharged species such as Glucose and Urea. Knowledge of the plasma concentration of these species allows calculation of the plasma osmolality quite accurately. If the difference between the measured osmolality (MO) and calculated osmolality (CO) is known as the osmolar gap (OG) is large (greater than 15) osmolar gap can help identify the presence in plasma of substances such as ethanol, methanol, isopropanol, ethylene glycol, propylene glycol..

label: Elevated circulating bile alcohol concentration
definition: The concentration of bile alcohols in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF tetrahydrobiopterin level
definition: Concentration of tetrahydrobiopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Cerebrospinal fluid eosinophilia
definition: Presence of at least 10% eosinophils in the total cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) leukocyte count.

label: Reduced C27 3beta-HSD activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of 3beta-hydroxy-delta5-C27-steroid oxidoreductase (C27 3beta-HSD) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

label: Reduced procollagen-lysine,2-oxoglutarate 5-dioxygenase 1 activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of procollagen-lysine,2-oxoglutarate 5-dioxygenase 1 (PLOD1; also known as Lysyl hydroxylase; EC 1.14.11.4) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. PLOD1 catalyzes the formation of hydroxylysine in collagens and other proteins with collagen-like amino acid sequences, by the hydroxylation of lysine residues in X-lys-gly sequences.

label: Diminished tissue fumarylacetoacetate hydrolase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of fumarylacetoacetate hydrolase (FAH; EC 3.7.1.2) below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue peptidase D activity
definition: Concentration or activity of Peptidase D (EC 3.4.13.9; also known as prolidase, imidodipeptidase, proline dipeptidase, and aminoacyl-L-proline hydrolase) below the lower limit of normal. The activity of this enzyme can be measured in erythrocytes, leukocytes, or fibroblasts.

label: Reduced tissue glycine cleavage enzyme activity
definition: Concentration or activity of the glycine cleavage enzyme below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Diminished alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of the alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase complex as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. This enzyme is a multienzyme complex consisting of 3 protein subunits, oxoglutarate dehydrogenase, also known as alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase or E1k (EC 1.2.4.2.), dihydrolipoyl succinyltransferase (DLST, or E2k; 126063), and dihydrolipoyl dehydrogenase (DLD, or E3; 238331). The complex catalyzes a key reaction in the Krebs tricarboxylic acid cycle.

label: Increased circulating dihydroxycholestanoic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of dihydroxycholestanoic acid (DHCA) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Reduced tissue phosphorylase kinase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of phosphorylase kinase below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label: Hyperkalemia while symptomatic
definition: Increased concentration of potassium in the blood circulation specifically measured during a disease flareup, attack, or exacerbation.

label: Elevated urinary gamma-glutamylcysteine level
definition: The amount of gamma-glutamylcysteine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive CSF mycobacterial culture
definition: Growth of mycobacteria in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label: Positive respiratory tract nucleic acid pathogen test
definition: Positive (abnormal) result of a sputum or pharyngeal sample test such as polymerase chain reaction that is targeted against a nucleic acid sequence specific for a pathogen.

label: Positive respiratory tract SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus nucleic acid in the sputum or pharyngeal sample by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Positive fecal cryptosporidium antigen test
definition: Cryptosporidium antigen present in stool. Tests include direct fluorescent-antibody (DFA), which detects intact organisms, and enzyme immunoassays (EIAs), which detect soluble stool antigens.

label: Horizontal position of testicle
definition: The Bell Clapper deformity is one of the causes for the testicular torsion. In this condition, testis lacks a normal attachment to tunica vaginalis and hangs freely, causing it to sit horizontally rather than vertically in the scrotum.

label: Localized soft-tissue swelling on extremity
definition: Abnormal enlargement (swelling) that is restricted to a specific part of a limb.

label: Multiple eyelid beaded papules
definition: Multiple beaded papules along the eyelid margins and inner canthus.

label: Nonexudative conjunctivitis
definition: A type of conjunctivitis that is not characterized by appreciable exudate, i.e., fluid, cells, or other substances that have escaped from blood vessels and have been deposited around the eyelids.

label: Nematode in retina
definition: Demonstration of a nematode (roundworm) in the retina, generally by an imaging procedure such as fundoscopy.

label: Vascular compression of the eighth cranial nerve
definition: A condition in which blood vessels adjacent to the eighth cranial nerve (vestibulocochlear nerve) such as the anterior inferior cerebellar artery abnormally contact or compress the vestibulocochlear nerve as it exits the brainstem or travels within the cerebellopontine angle.

label: Beaded bile ducts
definition: Multifocal intra- and extra-hepatic bile duct strictures alternating with normal caliber or slightly dilated segments, resembling beads on a string.

label: Cardiac mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized in the heart. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Superior olive hypertrophy
definition: Abnormal increase in size of the superior olive, also known as the superior olivary complex. The superior olive is a collection of brainstem nuclei that is located in pons, functions in multiple aspects of hearing and is an important component of the ascending and descending auditory pathways of the auditory system.

label: Spinal extradural arachnoid cyst
definition: Spinal extradural arachnoid cyst is a cyst in the spinal canal that protrudes into the epidural space from a defect in the dura mater.

label: Temporal cortex localization
definition: Localization to or predominance in the temporal cortex of the brain.

label: Basilar meningeal enhancement
definition: Abnormal enhancement of CT or MIR contrast medium in the basilar meninges, that is, those located in the basal cisterns or spaces at the base of the brain, due to increased permeability of blood vessels in these areas.

label: Thyroid cyst
definition: A fluid-filled sac or cavity that develops due to fluid accumulation within the thyroid tissue.

label: Decreased circulating sulfate concentration
definition: The concentration of sulfate in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Cold intolerance
definition: The inability to maintain a comfortable body temperature in a cold environment or cold temperatures.

label: Head and neck distribution
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the head and neck region.

label: Symmetric distribution
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is highly similar on the left and right sides of the body.

label: Muscle extensor surface location
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in extensor surface of an extremity.

label: Dermal foam cells
definition: Presence of lipid-laden macrophages (foam cells) in the inner layer of the skin (dermis).

label: Diminished tissue very long-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
definition: Diminished activity of Very long-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (VLCAD), an enzyme that catalyzes the initial step of mitochondrial beta-oxidation of long-chain fatty acids with a chain length of 14 to 20 carbons. VLCAD activity can be measured with biochemical testing using cultured fibroblasts or lymphocytes.

label: Diminished tissue glycogen branching enzyme activity
definition: Activity of glycogen branching enzyme in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts.

label: Parotid adenoma
definition: A benign tumor of the parotid salivary gland.

label: Elevated serum-ascites albumin gradient (SAAG)
definition: An elevation of the serum ascites albumin gradient (SAAG), which is based on the difference between the albumin level of serum and of ascitic fluid, may be used to assess the extent of ascites. The SAAG is thought to reflect the colloid osmotic pressure gradient and the degree of portal hypertension. It has been shown that SAAG is a better discriminator of portal hypertension than ascites. A SAAG of 1.1 gm/dL or higher is considered as high, indicating the presence of portal hypertension, while SAAG less than 1.1 gm/dL is low, indicating the absence of portal hypertension.

label: Transverse smile
definition: Inability to raise the corners of the mouth during the act of smiling due to facial muscle weakness. The act of smiling is accompanied by a horizontal movement of the mouth.

label: Hyperphalangy of the 4th finger
definition: An accessory phalanx of the fourth (ring) finger that is arranged linearly with the other phalanges. Hyperphalangy results from an accessory ossification center at the metacarpophalangeal joint.

label: Delayed distal femoral epiphyseal ossification
definition: Developmental delay of ossification of the distal epiphysis of the femur.

label: Delayed tibial epiphyseal ossification
definition: Developmental delay of ossification of an epiphysis of the tibia.

label: Toe hyperphalangy
definition: Hyperphalangy is a digit morphology in which increased numbers of phalanges are arranged linearly within a toe. That is, there is an accessory phalanx that is arranged linearly with the other phalanges.

label: Sclerotic ilium
definition: An elevation in bone density in the ilium. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

label: Metaphyseal chevron deformity
definition: The chevron sign refers to an inverted V-shape metaphyses. It is most commonly seen in the distal femur and tends to disappear with age.

label: Popcorn calcification
definition: Popcorn calcifications are areas of amorphous calcifications often with rings and arcs that resemble popped corn kernels in the metaphysis and epiphysis around the growth plate.

label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the calvaria
definition: A developmental defect characterized by absence or underdevelopment of the calvaria.

label: Bowdler spurs
definition: Transverse long bone midshaft spurs or osteochondral projections typically occuring in the fibulae and less commonly in the forearms.

label: Delayed ossification of the clavicle
definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of the clavicle.

label: Wide sacroiliac joint
definition: Distance between the sacrum and the ilium bones of the pelvis at the sacroiliac joint is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Anti-Glutamate Receptor delta2 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against glutamate receptor delta2.

label: Anti-dachshund family transcription factor 1 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against dachshund-homolog 1 (DACH1) autoantigen.

label: Anti-potassium channel tetramerization domain containing 16 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against potassium channel tetramerization domain containing 16 (KCTD16).

label: Anti-regulator of G protein signaling 8 antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against regulator of G-protein signaling 8 (RGS8).

label: Anti-neurochondrin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against neurochondrin .

label: Anti-DCC netrin 1 receptor antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against Netrin-1 receptors DCC (deleted in colorectal carcinoma).

label: Anti-recoverin antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against recoverin. Recoverins are calcium-binding proteins primarily expressed in retinal rod photoreceptors and primarily involved in phototransduction.

label: Recent history of sedation by propofol infusion
definition: A history of exposure to anesthesia by propofanol infusion recently before the presenting complaint.

label: Enlarged humeral head
definition: Size (volume) of the head of the humerus above the upper limit of normal.

label: Enlarged radial head
definition: Size (volume) of the head of the radius above the upper limit of normal.

label: Enlarged distal tibial epiphysis
definition: Size (volume) of the distal epiphysis of the tiba above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated blood bismuth concentration
definition: The concentration of bismuth in the blood is above the upper limit of a guidance value for total blood bismuth concentrations that implies possible injurious effects.

label: Elevated urine bismuth level
definition: Detection of a level of bismuth in the urine high enough to raise the suspicion of bismuth toxicity, usually greater than 20microgram per deciliter.

label: Distal radioulnar joint dislocation
definition: Distal radioulnar joint dislocation is more commonly displaced dorsally (i.e. the distal ulna is dorsally dislocated with respect to the distal radius), but can be volarly displaced.

label: Proximal radioulnar joint dislocation
definition: he proximal radioulnar translocation means that both the radius and ulna are dislocated from the humerus.

label: Absent toe phalanx flexion crease
definition: Absence of one or more interphalangeal creases of a toe (i.e., of the transverse lines in the skin between the phalanges of the toes).

label: White matter globoid cells
definition: Multinucleated phagocytes in the cerebral white matter, typically are 10-15 micrometers in diameter, that contain fatty filamentous inclusions that stain positive for periodic acid-Schiff (PAS), which may be phagocytized myelin, as these cells are often found in proximity to sites where demyelination is prominent. Globoid cells have been to thought to originate from CNS resident microglia and/or infiltrating peripheral macrophages.

label: Gaucher cells
definition: Glucosylceramide forms fibrillar aggregates that accumulate in macrophages and result in the cell cytoplasm presenting a characteristic crumpled tissue paper appearance. These cells, known as Gaucher cells, infiltrate various organs (e.g., bone marrow, spleen, and liver) and are responsible for the major signs of Gaucher disease.

label: Breast adenoma
definition: A benign, well circumscribed neoplasm that arises from the breast.

label: Breast apocrine adenoma
definition: A type of breast adenoma composed of benign apocrine cells.

label: Fibrocystic breast lesion
definition: A type of benign cyst or cysts in breast tissue that are typically mobile within the glandular breast tissue, chest wall, and skin and are rubber-like in texture. The main histological features are an extracellular matrix of collagen, peri canalicular patterns of stromal cells with the presence of florid epithelial hyperplasia.

label: Pancreatic VIPoma
definition: A type of neuroendocrine tumor that originates in the pancreas and secretes excessive amounts of vasoactive intestinal peptide (VIP).

label: Gastric carcinoid tumor
definition: Originating from enterochromaffin-like cells, gastric carcinoid tumors are rare tumors that develop within the gastric mucosa. They can present as an isolated lesion or there can be multiple lesions. The tumor can invade locally into deeper structures of the gastrointestinal tract wall. Solitary gastric carcinoids have a greater chance for the development of malignancy and metastasis as compared to multiple gastric carcinoids due to hypergastrinemia.

label: Posiitve skin scabies test
definition: Identification of scabies by means of an examination of the skin such as microscopic identification of scabies mites, eggs, or feces from obtained scales by skin scraping.

label: Positive mumps virus PCR test in the blood circulation
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of the mumps virus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label: Positive bloodstream tuberculosis-induced T-cell-based interferon-gamma release assay
definition: Detection of Mycobacterium tuberculosis in the bloodstream by means of detection of interferon-gamma secreted by T cells in response to specific antigens from Mycobacterium tuberculosis, commonly 6kD early secretory antigenic target-6 and 10kD culture filtrate protein-10.

label: Positive blood Neisseria gonorrhoeae culture
definition: Growth of Neisseria gonorrhoeae in a culture derived from circulating blood.

label: Anti-mumps antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Mumps virus.

label: Positive Vibrio cholerae stool culture
definition: Growth of Vibrio cholerae in a culture derived from a feces sample.

label: Positive cutaneous varicella zoster virus nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of mucocutaneous varicella zoster virus nucleic acid in the skin by a method such as polymerase chain reaction. The sample is usually obtained by swab from skin or mucous membranes.

label: Positive bloodstream cryptococcus culture
definition: Growth of Cryptococcus in a culture derived from a blood sample.

label: Positive bloodstream Borrelia miyamotoi nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Borrelia miyamotoi in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive bloodstream Coxsackievirus nucleic acid pathogen test
definition: Detection of nucleic acid of Coxsackievirus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

label: Positive stool Cryptosporidium antigen test
definition: Fecal analysis for Cryptosporidium antigen is abnormal. Tests include direct fluorescent-antibody (DFA), which detects intact organisms, and enzyme immunoassays (EIAs), which detect soluble stool antigens.

label: Diminished tissue alpha-L-iduronidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-L-iduronidase (IDUA; EC 3.2.1.76) below the lower limit of normal. FECH enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including cultured fibroblasts and leukocytes.

label: Reduced tissue neuraminidase activity
definition: Activity of neuraminidase (EC 3.2.1.18)in tissues below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts. Neuraminidase is also known as lysosomal sialidase.

label: Nummular keratitis
definition: Nummular keratitis consists of multiple scattered small round anterior corneal superficial stromal infiltrates.

label: Swelling of inguinal region
definition: Bulging in the area of the lower abdomen, just above the thigh and near the groin.

label: Single lesion
definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are solitary and localized to a part of the skin, a tissue or an organ that differs from the surrounding healthy tissue.

label: Dysorthography
definition: A specific disorder of spelling. A score on a standardized spelling test is at least two standard errors of prediction below the level expected on the basis of the child's chronological age and general intelligence in the context of scores on reading accuracy and comprehension and on arithmetic that are within the normal range (within two standard deviations from the mean).

label: Echogenic fetal colon
definition: A type of echogenic fetal bowel in which the hyperechogenicity is strictly limited to the colon.

label: Bone marrow edema
definition: Accumulation of excess fluid in the bone marrow.

label: Trousseau sign
definition: After inflating a blood pressure cuff from 10 mm Hg to 20 mm Hg over the patient's systolic blood pressure, the Trousseau sign is considered positive if carpal spasm develops, with flexion of the thumb and adduction of the finger within 3 minutes. However, this can be painful, so the time should be noted, and the cuff should be deflated once the test is positive.

label: Craniocervical junction constriction
definition: Congenital or acquired abnormalities of the occipital bone, foramen magnum, or first two cervical vertebrae that decrease the space for the lower brain stem and cervical cord. These malformations can lead to cranial nerve compression, vertebral artery compression, and obstructive hydrocephalus.

label: Fibular torsion
definition: Excessively rotated (also called torsion) position of the fibula (calf bone). An increased external rotation of the fibula in the incisura tibiofibularis of more than 5 degrees may lead to an increased pressure and will negatively affect the cartilage.

label: Abnormal finger phalanx ossification
definition: Any abnormal process of ossification of the phalangeal bones, which normally are ossified from the body and proximal extremity. Ossification of the body commences during the eighth week of fetal development. Ossification of the proximal extremity commences in the bones between the third and fourth years.

label: Positive bloodstream EBV monospot test
definition: The monospot test is a latex agglutination test which utilizes equine erythrocytes as the primary substrate and tests for specific heterophile antibodies produced by the human immune system in response to EBV infection. When these specific antibodies are present in the patient's blood specimen, exposure to equine erythrocytes will lead to clumping of the sample, thus signaling a positive agglutination reaction.

label: Positive CSF Toxoplasma gondii antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of Toxoplasma gondii.

label: Positive tuberculin skin test
definition: A positive result of the tuberculin skin test suggesting previous expouse or infection with mycobacterium teberculosis. A standard dose of five tuberculin units (TU) (0.1ml) is injected intradermally (into the skin) and read 48 to 72 h later. A person who has been exposed to the bacteria is expected to mount an immune response in the skin containing the bacterial proteins. The volar aspect of the forearm is the preferred site of test. The basis of reading is the presence or absence of induration, which may be determined by inspection (from a side view against the light as well as by direct light) and by palpation. For standardization, the diameter of induration should be measured transversely to the long axis of the forearm and recorded in millimeters.

label: Anti-Treponema pallidum antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Treponema pallidum.

label: Positive CSF Borrelia burgdorferi antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of Borrelia burgdorferi.

label: Positive CSF JC-virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of JC-virus (also known as JC-polyomavirus and John Cunningham virus).

label: Neutralizing anti-rabies virus antibody positivity
definition: The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that act against the rabies virus function by blocking the binding of the glycoprotein to a receptor or preventing the membrane fusion process.

label: Impaired hepatobiliary scintigraphy tracer uptake
definition: An abnormal reduction in the amount of radioactive tracer uptake upon hepatobiliary scintigraphy.

label: Calcified pulmonary nodule
definition: A pulmonary nodule with calcium deposits. On radiography, these nodules appear dense.

label: Postprandial exacerbation
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is more severe following a meal.

label: Koebner Phenomenon
definition: The appearance of new skin lesions on previously unaffected skin secondary to trauma. This phenomenon is also termed the isomorphic (from Greek, equal shape) response, given the fact that the new lesions that appear are clinically and histologically identical to the patient's underlying cutaneous disease.

label: Glenoid dysplasia
definition: Glenoid dysplasia is a developmental anomaly of the scapula that is characterized by a bony deficiency of the posteroinferior glenoid and the adjacent scapular neck.

label: Prolonged retraction of penile foreskin
definition: A past medical history of recently having retracted the penile foreskin for a prolonged period of time. Paraphimosis commonly occurs iatrogenically, when the foreskin is retracted for cleaning, placement of a urinary catheter, a procedure such as a cystoscopy, or for penile examination. Failure to return the retracted foreskin over the glans promptly after the initial retraction can lead to paraphimosis.

label: Thickened cortex of the clavicle
definition: Abnormal thickening of the cortex of the clavicle.

label: Thickened cortex of the mandible
definition: Abnormal thickening of the cortex of the mandible.

label: Thumb hypoplasia grade 1
definition: Minor hypoplasia (developmental undergrowth) of the thumb, whereby all musculoskeletal and neurovascular components of the digit are present, just small in size (Blauth classification).

label: Thumb hypoplasia grade 2
definition: A type of developmental undergrowth of the thumb, whereby all of the osseous structures are present (may be small), and there is metacarpophalangeal joint ulnar collateral ligament instability and thenar hypoplasia.

label: Thumb hypoplasia grade 3A
definition: A type of developmental undergrowth of the thumb, whereby there are musculotendinous and osseous deficiencies with the carpometacarpal (CMC) joint intact. Absence of active motion at the metacarpophalangeal (MCP) or interphalangeal (IP) joint.

label: Thumb hypoplasia grade 3B
definition: A type of developmental undergrowth of the thumb, whereby there are musculotendinous and osseous deficiencies characterized by basal metacarpal aplasia with deficient carpometacarpal (CMC) joint, and absence of metacarpophalangeal (MCP) or interphalangeal (IP) joint.

label: Thumb hypoplasia grade 4
definition: A type of developmental undergrowth of the thumb characterized by attachment to the hand only by the skin and digital neurovascular structures.

label: Femoral osteopoikilosis
definition: Multiple multiple, small, well-defined radiodense foci of cortical-like bone in the medullary space parallel to the trabeculae located in the femur. The loci correspond to condensations of the lamellar trabeculae on histology.

label: Carotidynia
definition: Pain or tenderness in the region of the carotid artery.

label: Asymmetric blood pressure between arms
definition: A substantial difference in blood pressure (e.g., 20 mmHg) between the right and left arms.

label: Hemimelia of lower leg
definition: A developmental defect leading to a transverse deficiency with absence of the lower leg (eg tibia and fibula), ankle and foot.

label: Hemimelia of forearm
definition: A developmental defect leading to a transverse deficiency with absence of the forearm (eg ulna and radius), wrist and hand.

label: Sodium glucose transport inhibitor exposure
definition: History of having been treateed with a sodium glucose transport inhibitors such as dapagliflozin, empagliflozin, canagliflozin, sglt-i, SGLT2, bexagliflozin, ertugliflozin, sotagliflozin, jardiance, invokana, forxiga, brenzavvy, steglatro, inpefa.

label: Breath-holding spell
definition: A benign paroxysmal nonepileptic disorder occurring in healthy children 6 to 48 months of age. The episodes start with a provocation such as emotional upset or minor injury, and might progress to breath holding, cyanosis, and syncope.

label: Flared proximal tibial metaphysis
definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of the proximal tibia.

label: Delayed toe phalanx ossification
definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of any of the toe phalanges.

label: Sorbitol ingestion
definition: A history of ingestion of a relatively high amount of foods containing sorbitol.

label: Positive peritoneal fluid bacterial culture
definition: Growth of bacteria in a culture dervied from ascites fluid.

label: Ocular cystine crystal deposition
definition: Accumulation of cystine crsytals in the eye. Patients present with crystal accumulation affecting the cornea and conjunctiva, but crystals can also be deposited in the iris, ciliary body, choroid and retinal pigment epithelium (RPE), and lens capsule. Corneal crystal deposition starts in infancy in the anterior periphery of the cornea, and progresses centrally and posteriorly. The crystals, which have a fine, uniform needle-shaped structure, are diffusely distributed within the corneal tissues.

label: Exuberant granulation tissue
definition: A manifestation of abnormal wound healing in which there is formation of excessive granulation tissue, with the granulation tissue rising above the level of surrounding skin and creating a raised, reddish, moist, and bumpy surface.

label: Oral mucosal papule
definition: A small (less than 5 mm in diameter), elevated, circumscribed, solid, palpable mass located in thte mucosa of the oral cavity.

label: Excessive piloerection
definition: Abnormally increased degree of goose bump formation, that is, of involuntary formation of bumps on a person's skin at the base of body hairs.

label: Scalp edema
definition: A palpable swelling in the scalp caused by an increase in interstitial fluid volume (excess fluid).

label: Serpiginous burrow
definition: A slightly raised and often reddish serpentine or curvilinear path in the skin.

label: Positive brain-tissue rabies nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of rabies nucleic acid in brain tissue by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Positive respiratory tract Bordetella pertussis nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of Bordetella pertussis PCR nucleic acid in in nasopharyngeal secretions by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Demonstration of acid-fast bacilli in wound tissue
definition: Demonstration of acid-fast bacilli by microscopic examination of wound tissue. Acid fastness is a physical property that gives a bacterium the ability to resist decolorization by acids during staining procedures.

label: Positive tissue encapsulated budding yeast test
definition: Identification of encapsulated budding yeasts in smears of body fluids, secretions, exudates, or other specimens.

label: Positive tissue coccidioidomycosis culture
definition: Growth of coccidioidomycosis in a culture derived from skin or an organ.

label: Diminished tissue dihydropteridine reductase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of dihydropteridine reductase (EC 1.6.99.7) below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and erythrocytes.

label: Decreased circulating transcobalamin I concentration
definition: Concentration of transcobalamin I in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Diminished circulating cationic trypsinogen concentration
definition: Concentration of cationic trypsinogen in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label: Diminished circulating hyaluronidase activity
definition: The activity or concentration of hyaluronidase in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label: Diminished sulfotransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Rate of proteoglycan sulfation (sulfotransferase activity) is below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

label: Elevated tissue alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.50) above the upper limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. It is also known as alpha-acetylglucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-glucosaminidase, and alpha-D-2-acetamido-2-deoxyglucosidase.

label: Abnormal tissue alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase activity
definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.50) outside of the limits of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. It is also known as alpha-acetylglucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-glucosaminidase, and alpha-D-2-acetamido-2-deoxyglucosidase.

label: Elevated circulating trihydroxycholestanoic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of trihydroxycholestanoic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated circulating glyoxylic acid concentration
definition: The concentration of glyoxylic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated CSF sepiapterin concentration
definition: Concentration of sepiapterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal.

label: Intrahepatic inclusion bodies
definition: Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates of stainable substances within hepatocytes.

label: Muscle vacuoles
definition: Presence of abnormal vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles) in the sarcolemma. The vacuoles are often associated with cytoplasmic and occasionally intranuclear eosinophilic inclusions.

label: Nonrimmed muscule vacuoles
definition: Presence of abnormal vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles) in the sarcolemma. On histological staining with hematoxylin and eosin, non-rimmed vacuoles lack the prominent dark border (rim) seen in rimmed vacuoles.

label: Reduced hepatic glycogen phosphorylase activity
definition: Activity or concentration of glycogen phosphorylase L in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

label: Bone marrow hemophagocytosis
definition: Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the bone marrow.

label: Splenic granulomatosis
definition: Splenic inflammation involving a granulomatous response, i.e., a non-specific inflammatory response involving granulomas, defined as a compact organized collection of mature mononuclear phagocytes including epithelioid and giant cells.

label: Immediate detumescence of penis at time of symptom onset
definition: Loss of erection at the time point of pain or other symptom onset.

label: History of aortic valve replacement
definition: History of having received a surgical replacement of the aortic valve.

label: Coved type ST segment elevation
definition: An ST-segment elevation of at least 2 mm in at least one right precordial lead (V1 to V3), followed by an r'-wave and a concave or straight ST segment. The descending ST segment crosses the isoelectric line and is followed by a negative and symmetric T-wave.

label: Saddle-back type ST segment elevation
definition: An ST-segment elevation of at least 0.5 mm (generally at least 2 mm in V2) in at least one right precordial lead (V1 to V3), followed by a convex ST. The r'-wave may or may not overlap the J point, but it has a slow downward slope. The ST segment is followed by a positive T-wave in V2 and is of variable morphology in V1.

label: Substantially elevated circulating ethanol concentration
definition: A blood concentration of ethanol that is consistent with alcohol intoxication, generally assumed to be 0.0800 g/dL or higher.

label: Tortuous appearance of the stomach
definition: Abnormal twisting or winding of the stomach.

label: Cochlear nerve aplasia
definition: A developmental defect causing an absence of the cochlear nerve resulting in sensorineural hearing loss.

label: Slit-like lateral ventricle
definition: Abnormally small lateral ventricle with a slit-like appearance.

label: Fetal methamphetamine exposure
definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy (including during the period of conception) of the mother of a fetus or child to methamphetamine.

label: Elevated circulating 4-hydroxybutyric acid concentration
definition: Concentration of 4-hydroxybutyric acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary 2,4-dihydroxybutyric acid level
definition: The amount of 2,4-dihydroxybutyric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Pupillary hypersensitivity to parasympathomimetic agents
definition: A higher than normal tendency of parasympathomimetic agents to induce miosis.

label: Lack of pupillary response to hydroxyamphetamine
definition: 4-hydroxyamphetamine is used in eye drops to dilate the pupil, e.g.., to induce mydriasis for fundus examinations. This term refers to a lack of response of the pupil to topical application of 4-hydroxyamphetamine.

label: Subcortical U fiber lesion
definition: Abnormal morphology of subcortical U fibers, typically as assessed by abnromal intensity on magnetic resonance imaging of the brain.

label: Intraspinal extradural lipoma
definition: A lipoma (a benign encapsulated mass with lobulated mature adipose tissue enclosed by fibrous tissue) located within the spine but outside of the dura mater.

label: Intranasal mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the nasal cavity. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

label: Liver rupture
definition: Subcapsular hepatic rupture is characterized by the development of a hematoma, often quite large, beneath the liver capsule. An interval of days or hours may elapse between the time of injury and the first appearance of symptoms. A history of injury may be entirely lacking, or may be so unremarkable that it is elicited only by diligent interrogation. The hematoma tends to increase in size.

label: Elevated urinary mandelic acid
definition: The amount of mandelic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine malic acid level
definition: The amount of malic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine 3-hydroxysebacic acid level
definition: The amount of 3-hydroxysebacic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary vanillactic acid level
definition: The amount of vanillactic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine 4,5-dihydroxyhexanoic acid level
definition: The amount of 4,5-dihydroxyhexanoic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine hydroxyphenyllactic acid level
definition: The amount of hydroxyphenyllactic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Positive gastric CMV intranuclear inclusions
definition: Demonstration of the presence of cytomegalovirus in the stomach by means of a method such as in-situ hybridization.

label: Elevated urine dihydroxycholestanoic acid level
definition: The amount of dihydroxycholestanoic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary bile alcohol level
definition: The amount of bile alcohol in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urine glucose tetrasaccharide level
definition: The amount of glucose tetrasaccharide in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Increased urine 4-hydroxy-2-oxoglutarate level
definition: The amount of 4-hydroxy-2-oxoglutarate in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Inability to protrude lips
definition: Lack of ability to purse or pucker the lips.

label: Wet voice
definition: Wet voice is a perceptual vocal quality that is gurgly or liquid sounding and is due to the voice being produced through moisture. It is commonly used as an indicator of penetration and/or aspiration in clinical swallowing assessments and bedside screening tests.

label: Erythema marginatum
definition: An erythematous (pink-red, depending on the skin color of the affected individual) macule that spreads peripherally and coalesces to form polycyclic or serpentine patches or plaques. Lesions occur in crops over days to weeks and are evanescent. The rate of migration is 2 to 12 mm over a period of a few hours. Erythema marginatum tends to affect the trunk more than the extremities and to not be accompanied by pruritus.

label: Mechanic's hands
definition: Mechanic's hands are fissured, erythematous, hyperkeratotic eruptions on the hands, resembling the type of occupational dermatosis said to resemble the hands of a manual laborer. The lesions are classically on the lateral edges of the fingers and thumbs, largely sparing the palmar, and dorsal aspects of the digits.

label: Hiker's feet
definition: Hyperkeratotic scaly fissured plaques on the fingers/palms or soles, generally more evident on the lateral aspect of index fingers.

label: Anti-HLA-DQ antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen (HLA-DQ). DQ is one of several antigens involved in antibody-mediated rejection of organ transplants.

label: Inappropriate normal or low erythropoietin
definition: Erythropoietin is produced and released into the blood by the kidneys in response to hypoxemia, and would normally be expected to increase with decreasing hemoglobin levels. This term applies if the increase fails to occur, as may be seen in conditions including chronic kidney disease.

label: Rapid gastric emptying
definition: A condition in which food moves through the stomach into the small intestine at an abnormally fast rate.

label: Mediastinal lymph node calcification
definition: Abnormal deposition of calcium in mediastinal lymph nodes.

label: Eggshell calcification of lymph nodes
definition: Eggshell calcification refers to fine calcification seen at the periphery of a mass and usually relates to lamellar lymph node calcification.

label: Knee joint effusion
definition: Abnormal accumulation of fluid within the knee joint or around the knee. Symptoms maye include, pain, swelling, and stiffness.

label: Subcutaneous emphysema
definition: Skin emphysema/Subcutaneous emphysema occurs when gas or air accumulates and seeps under the skin, where normally no gas should be present. While the presence of air in subcutaneous or mediastinal tissue is not dangerous in itself, prompt recognition of the underlying cause is essential.

label: Elevated bone scintigraphy uptake
definition: Bone scintigraph is performed with technetium 99m-labeled diphosphonates. The uptake of these radiopharmaceuticals depicts osteoblastic activity and regional blood flow to bone.

label: Diminished long-chain-enoyl-CoA hydratase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of long-chain-enoyl-CoA hydratase (EC 4.2.1.74) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

label: Diminished acetyl-CoA C-acyltransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
definition: Concentration or activity of acetyl-CoA C-acyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.16) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. This enzyme catalyzes the reaction acetyl-CoA + an acyl-CoA = a 3-oxoacyl-CoA + CoA. It is also known as 3-ketoacyl-CoA thiolase and beta-ketothiolase.

label: Pathological inclusion body
definition: Pathological inclusion bodies are are composed of glycogen, proteins, nucleic acids, lipids, hemosiderin, and calcium, that accumulate as metabolic by-products, catabolic products of macromolecular complexes, or in the context of cell injury.

label: Reduced epidermal collagen IV alpha 5 chain staining
definition: Diminished or absent collagen alpha5(IV) chain staining pattern in the epidermal basement membrane.

label: Diminished glomerular basement membrane collagen IV alpha 3 chain staining
definition: Abnormal reduction in the amount of the alpha 3 chain of collagen IV in the basement membrane of the glomeruli of the kidney.

label: Diminished glomerular basement membrane collagen IV alpha 4 chain staining
definition: Abnormal reduction in the amount of the alpha 4 chain of collagen IV in the basement membrane of the glomeruli of the kidney.

label: Diminished glomerular basement membrane collagen IV alpha 5 chain staining
definition: Abnormal reduction in the amount of the alpha 5 chain of collagen IV in the basement membrane of the glomeruli of the kidney.

label: Cystine nephrolithiasis
definition: Deposition of cystine crystals in kidney tissue. Cystine crystals display a pathognomic hexagonal shape.

label: Hepatic cystine accumulation
definition: Accumulation of cystine in the liver.
