label: Bone marrow cystine accumulation
definition: The presence of cystine crystals in bone marrow cells as demonstrated in a fresh bone marrow aspiration sample.

label: Tubular jejunal duplication
definition: A segment of the jejunum that runs parallel to the normal jejunum and communicates with the jejunal lumen at one or both ends.

label: Left ventricular rupture
definition: A full thickness tear or breakage of the myocardium of the left ventricle.

label: Punctate pontine perivascular enhancement
definition: Multiple punctate (speckled, patchy spot-like) and/or curvilinear areas of gadolinium enhancement distributed around blood vessels in the pons.

label: Intestinal worm
definition: Presence of one or more adult worms in the intestine as demonstrated by sonography or passage of a worm in the stool. On sonography, worms may appear as linear, echogenic structures within the intestines.

label: Scrotal worm
definition: Demonstration of one or more worms in the scrotum. This finding can be appreciated by sonography, where echogenic, linear structures could be seen moving within the scrotum.

label: Small intestinal adenoma
definition: A small bowel tumor with adenomatous epithelium.

label: Maternal retinal mottling
definition: Mottling (spots or blotches with different shades) of the retinal pigment epithelium in the mother of the index patient. Retinal mottling may indicate a mosaic X-linked inactivation state in the mother.

label: Twisted gallbladder pedicle
definition: A stretched conical-shaped structure found at the gallbladder neck with several linear echoes converging towards its tip. This finding is demonstrated by sonography and can indicate gallbladder volvulus.

label: Dyschronometria
definition: Impaired ability to accurately measure or estimate time intervals.

label: History of recent intermittent breastfeeding
definition: History of recently intermittent breastfeeding an infant (i.e., on and off).

label: Breast cyst
definition: A benign, fluid-filled sac in the breast.

label: Circumscribed
definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are well-defined and localized to a specific area.

label: Lobulated
definition: Applies to an abnormality that displays ultiple indentations and/or elevations producing an irregular surface contour.

label: Spiculated
definition: Applies to an abnormality with irregular, radiating, or spiky edges.

label: Whorled
definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance resembles series of a concentric circles or spirals.

label: Delta brush pattern on EEG
definition: Delta brushes are transient patterns characterised by a slow delta wave with superimposed fast activity.

label: Tibiotalar synostosis
definition: Fusion of the junction between the distal tibia, fibula and the talus.

label: Vertebra plana
definition: he term given when a vertebral body has lost almost its entire height anteriorly and posteriorly, representing a very advanced compression fracture.

label: Intoeing
definition: An abnormal gait caused by a rotational variation anywhere in the lower extremity that causes the foot to point inward, instead of pointing straight ahead or outward, when walking or running.

label: Palpable thrill on extremity
definition: A vibration felt upon palpation of a blood vessel over an extremity.

label: Out-toeing
definition: The feet turn excessively outward when walking, caused by a rotational variation in the leg.

label: Ankle dislocation
definition: An abnormal separation between the talo-tibial joint.

label: Anti-neuronal intermediate filament antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against neuronal intermediate filament.

label: Anti-DREBRIN antibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against dendritic spine scaffolding protein Drebrin.

label: Anti-lipoprotein lipase autoantibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-lipoprotein lipase.

label: Anti-apolipoprotein CII autoantibody positivity
definition: The presence of autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against apoCII.

label: Eosinophilic neuronal inclusion bodies
definition: The presence of intracellular inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in neurons that stain with eosin, a red or pink dye.

label: Sweaty foot-like odor
definition: A characteristic smell said to resemble the odor of dirty socks.

label: Hair shaft lesion
definition: Applies to an abnormality that is located on hair shafts.

label: Prolonged use of tightly fitting footwear
definition: History of use of tightly fitting shoes for a long period of time.

label: Triggered by high protein intake
definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about ingestion of high quantities of protein.

label: Thickened tricuspid valve cusp
definition: An abnormally increased thickness of a leaflet of the tricuspid valve.

label: Displaced anterior fontanelle
definition: Abnormal shifting of the anterior fontanelle fropm its normal central position.

label: Subdural hygroma
definition: Accumulation of cerebral spinal fluid in the subdural space.

label: Incus ankylosis
definition: Incus ankylosis refers to congenital or acquired fixation of the incus, which is associated with conductive hearing resulting from impairment of the sound-conduction mechanism (the external auditory canal, tympanic membrane, and/or middle-ear ossicles).

label: Excessive diet restriction
definition: A tendency to reject a variety of foods and/or to eat a restricted range of foods.

label: Left ventricular apical dyskinesis
definition: Dyskinesis is used to describe ventricular muscle segments that bulge outside the left ventricular cavity during systole, as opposed to contracting inwards with the rest of the segments.

label: Longitudinal erythronychia
definition: A longitudinal red band extending from the proximal nail fold or lunula to the distal nail plate.

label: Exacerbated by exposure to sunlight
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by exposure to sunlight.

label: Exacerbated by heat
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is made worse by exposure to heat (high ambient temperatures).

label: Exacerbated by excessive sweating
definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is made worse by excessive sweating.

label: Malignant pleural effusion
definition: The accumulation of a significant amount of exudate in the pleural space, accompanied by the presence of malignant cells or tumour tissue.

label: Inappropriately low urine osmolality following challenge
definition: In diabetes insipidus, affected individuals produce large quantities of dilute urine. In nephrogenic DI, the kidneys do not respond to vasopressin. In a water deprivation test or with administration of exogenous vasopressin, the osmolaltiy of the urine does not increase as normally.

label: Reduced urine retrahydrocortisol plus 5-alpha-THF to tetrahydrocortisone ratio
definition: Abnormally low ratio of tetrahydrocortisol (THF) plus 5-alpha-THF to tetrahydrocortisone (THE).

label: Elevated urinary 2,4-dihydroxyglutarate level
definition: The amount of 2,4-dihydroxyglutarate in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Abnormal urine D-xylose test
definition: An abnormal result of the xylose absorption test that is used to assess the ability of the intestines to absorb D-xylose. D-xylose is a five-carbon monosaccharide found in some plants. The patient drinks a solution containing a specific amount of D-xylose and the concentration of xylose is measured in the blood circulation and then in the urine. A low amount of D-xylose indicates reduced small intestinal absorbtion.

label: Cerebral hemisphere mass lesion
definition: An abnormal growth or accumulation of tissue in a hemisphere of the cerebrum. Typically a mass is an initial finding that will lead to additional workup.

label: T2-hyperintense putaminal rim
definition: Increased signal on T2 magnetic resonance imaging characterized by a linear region of high signal surrounding the lateral aspect of the putamen at 1.5 Tesla.

label: Posterior fossa mass lesion
definition: An abnormal growth or accumulation of tissue in the posterior fossa, affecting the cerebellum or fourth ventricle. Typically a mass is an initial finding that will lead to additional workup.

label: Irregular RR interval
definition: Abnormal increased variability in the timing between consecutive R-waves on an electrocardiogram.

label: Irregular P-P interval
definition: Abnormally increased variability in the timing between consecutive P-waves on an electrocardiogram.

label: Fungal hair infection
definition: Demonstration of fungi growing on hair by a method such as microscopy of hairs mounted on slides with 10% potassium hydroxide.

label: Long hairstyle
definition: A past medical history of having long, full hair.

label: Conjunctival subepithelial fibrosis
definition: fine white linear scars under intact conjunctival epithelium. This scarring appears in areas of previous conjunctival ulceration or pseudomembrane formation, weeks to months after the insult is healed.

label: Conjunctival fornix foreshortening
definition: Abnormal reduction in depth of the fornix of the conjunctiva. The fornix is the area where the conjunctiva folds back upon itself, thereby creating a recessed space.

label: Strong ultraviolet light exposure
definition: History of exposure to ultraviolet light, such as may be encountered with outdoor activities, living near equator, radiation.

label: Exposure to vaginal douching
definition: A history of intravaginal cleansing with a liquid solution for personal hygiene or aesthetic reasons.

label: Exposure to oily lotions or creams
definition: A history of applying oily lotions or creams to the skin.

label: Elevated circulating pristanic acid concentration following branched-chain fatty acid ingestion
definition: Concentration of pristanic acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. This finding can be observed in Zellweger syndrome. Note that branched-chain fatty acid accumulation depends on dietary intake of phytanic acid, which is minimal in formula- and breast-fed infants. Thus, phytanic and pristanic acid levels are normal in a neonate with Zellweger spectrum disorder.

label: Decreased T-cell ZAP-70 protein expression in CD4-positive T cells
definition: Reduction in the level of ZAP-70 protein CD4-positive T cells.

label: Dorsal flexion contracture of the ankle
definition: A type of contracture in which the dorsal flexion muscles of the ankle are contracted.

label: Metaphyseal undermodelling
definition: Lack of the normal diaphyseal constriction (thinning of long bones toward the midshaft area) giving the submetaphyseal areas an abnormally wide appearance.

label: Iliac vein compression
definition: Compression of the common iliac vein against the spine by the contralateral common iliac artery.

label: Positive serum amyloid P scintigraphy
definition: Detection of abnormal amyloid deposits in the body by 123I-labeled serum amyloid P component (SAP) scintigraphy.

label: crossed brainstem sign
definition: Motor and/or sensory cranial nerve findings ipsilateral to the lesion, and at the same time motor and/or sensory findings on the contralateral side of the body.

label: Inability to puff cheeks
definition: Reduced ability to inflate the cheeks by blowing air into them while keeping the lips closed.

label: Entoptic phenomenon
definition: Visual sensations caused by changes within the eye itself, rather than by the normal light stimulation process. Entoptic phenomena are classified in the syndrome as floaters, blue field entoptic phenomenon, photopsia and self-light of the eye.

label: Abnormal vestibulo-spinal reflex
definition: An abnormality of the vestibulospinal (VS) reflexes, which contribute to the control of postural orientation. In this task, they continuously collaborate with reflexes elicited by stimulation of visual and somatosensory receptors. Labyrinthine receptors are sensitive to modifications (i) of the head position with respect to the earth vertical or (ii) of the angular/linear velocity of head motion in space. This information can be used to monitor deviations from the maintained body position.

label: Positive probe-to-bone test
definition: An abnormal result of the probe-to-bone (PTB) test. The PTB test is performed by inserting a sterile, metal surgical probe into the ulcer and is positive if a hard, gritty surface is felt inside. For large wounds, this may require gentle exploration of the wound with the probe.

label: Exposure to repetive hand impact
definition: A history of exposure to repetitive impact on palm or hand, such as working with a jackhammer.

label: Fractured scaphoid bone
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the scaphoid bone.

label: Local anesthetic ineffectiveness
definition: Resistance to the effects of local anaesthesia, with delayed onset or failure of local anesthetics to incude numbness or relieve pain.

label: Palmoplantar location
definition: Applied to lesions whose distribution is confined or restricted to the palms of the hands and soles of the feet.

label: Oral mucosa plaque
definition: A raised, flat-topped lesion with a diameter of one centimeter or more that is located in the mucosa of the mouth.

label: Positive saliva rabies nucleic acid test
definition: Detection of rabies nucleic acid in saliva by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label: Elevated tissue arylsulfatase A activity
definition: Activity of arylsulfatase A (EC 3.1.6.8) above the upper limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including culutured fibroblasts and leukocytes or in the blood circulation.

label: Elevated circulating methysterol concentration
definition: The concentration of a methysterol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

label: Elevated urinary adipic acid
definition: The amount of adipic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Adipic acid is an alpha,omega-dicarboxylic acid that is the 1,4-dicarboxy derivative of butane.

label: EEG with temporal slowing
definition: Slow-wave activity observed in the temporal area of the scalp electro-encephalogram (EEG).

label: History of high-pressure injection injury of the hand
definition: Medical history of the hand having come into contact with the nozzle of a high-pressure injecting system such as a paint gun or air compressor.

label: Hypertrophic ulnar styloid process
definition: Excessively long styloid process of the ulna.

label: History of recent peripheral venous catheter
definition: A history of placement of a peripehral venous catheter in the hours, days, or weeks before the current presenting complaint.

label: Purulent drainage from skin
definition: Exudation of a thick, opaque fluid from a wound or skin lesion, typically as a result of infection and taining pus, i.e., dead white blood cells, bacteria, and tissue debris.

label: Occupational history of putting fingers in other people's mouths
definition: A history of exposure of fingers by putting them in other peoples' mouths occupationally, e.g., as a dentist or physician.

label: Single-finger involvement
definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are limited to or predominantly affect a single finger.

label: Multiple-finger involvement
definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance affect more than one finger.

label: Pain disproportionate to abnormality on physical exam
definition: Exquisite tenderness in a specific region, beyond what one would surmise from examination.

label: Sphenoid wing dysplasia
definition: Hypoplasia or aplasia of the greater or lesser wing of the sphenoid bone, typically resulting in widening of the superior orbital fissure, elevation of the [lesser sphenoid wing, and ipsilateral orbital enlargement.

label: Skin laceration
definition: An injury in which skin and underlying tissues are cut or torn.

label: Metacarpal fracture
definition: A partial or complete breakage of a metacarpal bone.

label: Pain at the base of the thumb
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort localized to the base of the thumb, over thenar eminence or thumb metacarpal.

label: History of recent participation in athletics
definition: Medical history of participation in sports (football, basketball, soccer, skiing) in the hours, days, or weeks prior to the current presenting complaint.

label: Remote trauma history
definition: History of trauma months to years ago, including but not limited to fracture or other orthopedic injury at the symptomatic area.

label: Distal radioulnar joint arthritis
definition: An inflammatory condition of the joint that connects the far ends of the radius and the ulna, known as the distal radioulnar joint (DRUJ). DRUJ arthritis may be characterized by widening of the DRUJ interval, volar/dorsal displacement of the distal ulna, radiographic evidence of osteoarthritis at the DRUJ joint including osteophytes, subchondral cysts, subchrondal sclerosis, and joint space narrowing.

label: Radial head fracture
definition: Fracture of the proximal end of the radius involving the radial head.

label: Elbow lateral collateral ligament tear
definition: An injury to the lateral collateral ligament (LCL) of the elbow. The LCL is a complex capsuloligamentous structure critical in stabilizing the ulnohumeral and radiocapitellar articulations. LCL injury can result in elbow instability, allowing the proximal radius and ulna to externally rotate away from the humerus as a supination stress is applied to the forearm.

label: Elbow medial collateral ligament tear
definition: An injury to the medial collateral ligament (MCL) of the elbow.

label: Coronoid fracture
definition: Fracture of the coronoid process on the proximal ulna.

label: History of spinal cord injury
definition: A medical history of hving had a spinal cord injury prior to the presenting complaint.

label: Femoral nerve distribution
definition: Paresthesias in anterior/medial aspect of the thigh (anterior and medial cutaneous nerves of the thigh) and/or medial aspect of the lower leg and foot (saphenous distribution). May be accompanied by weakness in the quadriceps.

label: Triceps tendon rupture
definition: Breakage (tear) of the triceps tendon.

label: Digoxin exposure
definition: History of having been treateed with digoxin.

label: Upper arm pain
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the upper arm.

label: Capitellum fracture
definition: A partial or complete breakage of the capitulum of the humerus, which is a smooth, rounded eminence on the lateral portion of the distal articular surface of the humerus.

label: Anterior shoulder pain
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the anterior (front) part of the shoulder.

label: Pain at the anterior aspect of the elbow
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the front part of the elbow front part of the elbow, that is, on the ventral side of the arm where the arm bends.

label: Posterior fat pad sign of the elbow
definition: Lateral elbow x-ray showing lucent crescent of fat that indicates a joint effusion in the elbow .

label: Pain at the anterior aspect of the knee
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the front part of the knee, that is, the side of the knee where the patella is located.

label: Pain at the posterior aspect of the knee
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the back part of the knee, that is, opposite to the side of the knee where the patella is located.

label: Biceps tendonitis
definition: Biceps tendinitis is inflammation of the tendon around the long head of the biceps muscle.

label: Increased peripheral nerve cross sectional area
definition: Ultrasonography showing increased cross sectional area (CSA) of a peripheral nerve as it travels through a potential site of compression.

label: Pain exacerbated by passive flexion at joint
definition: Pain in extremity that worsens with joint is passively flexed.

label: Positive hook test at the elbow
definition: With forearm fully supinated and elbow flexed to 90 degrees, examiner hooks a finger a bit around the distal biceps tendon at the anterior aspect of the elbow. Test is positive when there is lack of appreciable cord like structure to hook around.

label: Positive Speed's test
definition: Manual downward pressure on the arm with the shoulders flexed forward to 90 degrees, elbows fully extended, and palm facing up recreates pain in the anterior shoulder region; named after Dr. Speed.

label: Triangular lunate bone
definition: A disruption of the greater and lesser arcs of the lunate bone, with the lunate having a triangular silhouette, know as the piece of pie sign. Often caused by falling on an outstretched hand, patients will have tenderness to palpation over the dorsum of the wrist and may have sensory deficits in the median nerve distribution.

label: Pain exacerbated by wrist deviation
definition: Pain worsens with wrist ulnar or radial deviation.

label: Pain on the lateral aspect of the foot
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the side of the foot nearest to the little (fifth) toe.

label: Pain at the medial aspect of the knee
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the inner side of knee, that is, the region of the knee that faces the other knee.

label: Pain at the lateral aspect of the knee
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the outer side of knee, that is, the region of the knee that faces away from the other knee.

label: Synovial crystals
definition: The presence of microscopic crystalline structures in the synovial fluid (the lubricating fluid within joint cavities).

label: Occupational exposure to frequent kneeling
definition: A history of exposure to frequent squatting/kneeling and/or heavy lifting.

label: Trochanteric pain
definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the structures around the greater trochanter (the bony prominence on the outer part of the femur).

label: Pulsatile mass in extremity
definition: A noticeable lump or swelling in the arm or leg that you can feel with you fingers and this lump is beating or pulsating, similar to the feeling of a heartbeat.

label: Abnormal R wave
definition: Any anomaly of the R wave of the EKG, which is the first upward deflection after the P wave. The R wave reflects early ventricular depolarisation.

label: Poor R-wave progression
definition: Absence of the normal increase in size of the R wave in the precordial leads when advancing from lead V1 to V6 of the electrocardiogram.

label: Prominent V1-V2 R wave
definition: The R wave in leads V1-V2 is normally considerably smaller in amplitude than the S wave in the same leads. Prominent R wave in these leads implies the R wave is larger than the S-wave, which may indicate cardiovascular pathology. This term includes Tall R wave in lead V1, which is defined by a R/S ratio greater than 1.

label: Finger mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to a finger.

label: Foot mass
definition: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to a foot.
